Parameter name: A2 default profile identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an A2DPR object.    The instance defines the default profile for A2 configuration for measurement based CoMP functionalities.

Parameter name: A2 time to trigger for CoMP/CS
Description: Duration for which the event A2 entry condition or leave condition must be valid at the UE, such that A2 event can be triggered for CoMP/CS purposes

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Hysteresis for A2 RSRP CoMP/CS event
Description: Hysteresis related to RSRP threshold of A2 RSRP event for CoMP/CS.  Parameter is used in the entry and leave condition of the A2 reporting condition by UE. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: A2 RSRP threshold for CoMP/CS
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell used in A2 measurement for CoMP/CS  If value is below threshold2Comp (event A2) then A3 CoMP/CS measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: A2 profile identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an A2PR object.    The instance defines the profile for A2 configuration for measurement based CoMP functionalities that allows to configure specific setting in addition to the default profile A2DPR.  If an A2PR configuration is assigned to a cell, all the values defined are used. For parameters that are not defined, the value of the default profile ADPR is being used for the cell.

Parameter name: A2 time to trigger for CoMP/CS
Description: Duration for which the event A2 entry condition or leave condition must be valid at the UE, such that A2 event can be triggered for CoMP/CS purposes

Parameter name: A3 default profile identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an A3DPR object.    The instance defines the default profile for A3 configuration for measurement based CoMP functionalities.

Parameter name: A3 offset RSRP for CoMP/CS
Description: RSRP offset by which neighbor cell must be better than the serving cell to trigger A3 event. Used in A3 measurement for CoMP/CS.

Parameter name: A3 Report Interval for CoMP/CS
Description: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are sent as long as the specific criteria for the CoMP/CS measurement event A3 are met (Intra-Frequency).  This parameter defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the CoMP/CS measurement event A3 are met. Value definitions are according to 3GPP TS36.331.

Description: Duration for which the event A3 entry condition or leave condition must be valid at the UE, such that A3 event can be triggered for CoMP/CS purposes

Parameter name: Access Class Barring for BB pool profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC ACBBBPR.  It uniquely identifies an ACBBBPR instance.

Parameter name: BB pool RRC connection AC barring start threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the upper threshold of RRC CONNECTED UEs which can trigger ACTIVE RRC_BB_ACB event on BB pool level.  RRC_BB_ACB event becomes ACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the BB pool >= ROUND(acbNumRrcConnBbStart * maxNumRrcBbPool / 100) AND acbRrcConnBbStartTimer expires.    ACTIVE RRC_BB_ACB event shall start step-wise upgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if dynamic ACB ACTIVE state not started yet.    Note:  - maxNumRrcBbPool - indicates that this is Baseband pool related maxNumRRC RAC limit.  - If LTE4741 'Access Class Barring Support for CAT-M1' is activated then CAT-M specific AC barring settings are broadcasted in SIB2-BR as well.

Parameter name: BB pool RRC connection AC barring stop threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the lower threshold of RRC CONNECTED UEs which can trigger INACTIVE RRC_BB_ACB event on BB pool level.  RRC_BB_ACB event becomes INACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the BB pool < ROUND(acbNumRrcConnBbStop * maxNumRrcBbPool / 100) AND acbRrcConnBbStopTimer expires.    INACTIVE RRC_BB_ACB event shall start step-wise downgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if there's no other ACTIVE ACB trigger.    Note:  - maxNumRrcBbPool - indicates that this is Baseband pool related maxNumRRC RAC limit.  - If LTE4741 'Access Class Barring Support for CAT-M1' is activated then CAT-M specific AC barring settings are broadcasted in SIB2-BR as well.

Parameter name: BB pool RRC triggered AC barring start timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before triggering ACTIVE RRC_BB_ACB event on BB pool level.  RRC_BB_ACB event becomes ACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the BB pool >= ROUND(acbNumRrcConnBbStart * maxNumRrcBbPool / 100) AND acbRrcConnBbStartTimer expires.    ACTIVE RRC_BB_ACB event shall start step-wise upgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if dynamic ACB ACTIVE state not started yet.    Note:  - maxNumRrcBbPool - indicates that this is Baseband pool related maxNumRRC RAC limit.  - If LTE4741 'Access Class Barring Support for CAT-M1' is activated then CAT-M specific AC barring settings are broadcasted in SIB2-BR as well.

Parameter name: BB pool RRC triggered AC barring stop timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before triggering INACTIVE RRC_BB_ACB event on BB pool level.  RRC_BB_ACB event becomes INACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the BB pool < ROUND(acbNumRrcConnBbStop * maxNumRrcBbPool / 100) AND acbRrcConnBbStopTimer expires.    INACTIVE RRC_BB_ACB event shall start step-wise downgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if there's no other ACTIVE ACB trigger.    Note:  - maxNumRrcBbPool - indicates that this is Baseband pool related maxNumRRC RAC limit.  - If LTE4741 'Access Class Barring Support for CAT-M1' is activated then CAT-M specific AC barring settings are broadcasted in SIB2-BR as well.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Profile priority
Description: This profile priority parameter is applied to identify the ACBBBPR (Access Class Barring for BB pool profile) to be used in a BB pool if a BB pool has multiple cells assigned to it with different profiles. Profile priority must be set to a different value in every profile.  The smaller the value the higher the priority.

Parameter name: Access Class Barring profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC ACBPR.  It uniquely identifies an ACBPR instance.

Parameter name: Max auto access barring class for CS fallback - Max auto access class barring list for CS fallback
Description: Access class barring list (5 bits) for originating CS fallback.  Access class barring list (5 bits) for originating CS fallback for AC 11-15.  For example, AC11 = 00001, AC12 = 00010, AC13 = 00100, AC14 = 01000, AC15 = 10000. Note: The parameter value stored in the eNB is not designed to match the IE layout in SIB messages, e.g. the stored value AC11=00001 will be sent in SIB as 10000.

Parameter name: Max auto access barring class for CS fallback - Max auto access class barring time for CS fallback
Description: Defines the access class barring time.  The access class barring time defines the time that the access barring check remains unsuccessful while the UE is not performing an emergency call. In this case, the UE starts timer T305 using Tbarring value.    Note:Tbarring = (0.7+0.6* rand) * ac-BarringTime

Parameter name: Max auto access barring class for CS fallback - Max auto access probability factor for CS fallback
Description: Defines the maximum barring threshold and probability for a UE to establish an RRC connection.  The access probability factor defines the probability for a UE to establish an RRC connection.  The UE draws a random number (0 <= rand < 1). If rand is higher than the value indicated by the access probability factor, the UE considers the access barring check to be unsuccessful.

Note: The parameter value stored in the eNB is not designed to match the IE layout in SIB messages, e.g. the stored value AC11=00001 will be sent in SIB as 10000.

Description: Defines the access class barring time.  The access class barring time defines the time that the access barring check remains unsuccessful while the UE is not performing an emergency call. In this case, the UE starts timer T305 using Tbarring value.    Note:Tbarring = (0.7+0.6* rand) * ac-BarringTime

Description: Defines the maximum barring threshold and probability for a UE to establish an RRC connection.  The access probability factor defines the probability for a UE to establish an RRC connection.  The UE draws a random number (0 <= rand < 1). If rand is higher than the value indicated by the access probability factor, the UE considers the access barring check to be unsuccessful.

Parameter name: Skip Indicator for mobile originating MMTEL video
Description: Indicates if access barring for mobile originating MMTEL video calls within RRC layer is skipped in this cell.  If this parameter is TRUE, eNB indicates UE to skip ACB in RRC layer when UE establishes the RRC connection for mobile originating MMTEL video call; otherwise (i.e. this parameter is FALSE), UE performs ACB in RRC layer.    Note: SIB2:ssac-barringForMMTEL-Video, if presented, shall always be applicable in UE, no matter if this parameter is configured to TRUE or FALSE.

Parameter name: Skip Indicator for mobile originating MMTEL voice
Description: Indicates if access barring for mobile originating MMTEL voice calls within RRC layer is skipped in this cell.  If this parameter is TRUE, eNB indicates UE to skip ACB in RRC layer when UE establishes the RRC connection for mobile originating MMTEL voice call; otherwise (i.e. this parameter is FALSE), UE performs ACB in RRC layer.    Note: SIB2:ssac-barringForMMTEL-Voice, if presented, shall always be applicable in UE, no matter if this parameter is configured to TRUE or FALSE.

Parameter name: Skip Indicator for mobile originating SMSoIP or SMS
Description: Indicates if access barring for mobile originating SMSoIP or mobile originating SMS within RRC layer is skipped in this cell.  If this parameter is TRUE, eNB indicates UE to skip ACB in RRC layer when UE establishes the RRC connection for mobile originating SMSoIP or mobile originating SMS over SG/S102. Otherwise (i.e. this parameter is FALSE), UE performs ACB in RRC layer.    Note: SIB8:ac-BarringConfig1XRTT, if presented, shall always be applicable in UE, no matter if this parameter is configured to TRUE or FALSE.

Parameter name: Step-wise Emergency Call Barring bitmask
Description: This parameter determines whether together with every executed Special Class (SC) step Emergency Calls should be 'barred' or 'not barred' (ac-BarringForEmergency IE and ac-BarringForEmergency-r12 in the SIB2). This gives possibility to the operator to NOT broadcast Emergency Call barring until last step-wise SC upgrade phase. '1' means Emergency Calls in corresponding SC step are 'barred' and '0' means 'Not barred'. Leftmost bit is for step1, the second bit in the list is for step2, and so on...  If this parameter is not configured then Emergency Call (EC) barring depends on legacy EC barring phase settings (i.e. eCallAcBarredAuto and acbEcTimer).
Range and step: bits mask: If value '1' is configured then Emergency Calls are 'barred' together with first SC step (barAC1) (0), If value '1' is configured then Emergency Calls are 'barred' together with second SC step (barAC2) (1), If value '1' is configured then Emergency Calls are 'barred' together with third SC step (barAC3) (2), If value '1' is configured then Emergency Calls are 'barred' together with fourth SC step (barAC4) (3), If value '1' is configured then Emergency Calls are 'barred' together with fifth SC step (barAC5) (4)

Parameter name: Automatic handover blocking and cell reserved for PLMN
Description: Indicates if the cell/PLMN combination is reserved for the operator to use, and incoming handovers for the combination are blocked when ACB max step is reached as a result of step-wise PLMN ACB. Note that this functionality only applies for the PLMN associated with the ACBPR.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Auto access barred for emergency calls
Description: Indicates that access is barred for emergency calls in this cell when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload or number of RRC connections.  Access Class barring for AC 10.  The access barred for emergency calls flag indicates that access is barred for emergency calls in this cell.    In case of RRC connection triggered ACB emergency calls becomes barred after acbEcTimer expiration.

Parameter name: Static access barred for emergency calls
Description: Indicates that access is barred for emergency calls in this cell.  Access Class barring for AC 10.  The access barred for emergency calls flag indicates that access is barred for emergency calls in this cell.

Parameter name: Emergency handover blocking in max PLMN barring step
Description: Indicates if incoming emergency handovers are also blocked for the cell/PLMN combination when ACB max step is reached as a result of step-wise PLMN ACB. Note that this functionality only applies for the PLMN associated with the ACBPR and only when cellResHoBlockPlmnAcbMax is set to 'reserved' or hoBlockPlmnAcbMaxOnly is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Automatic handover blocking in max PLMN barring step
Description: Indicates if the incoming handovers for the cell/PLMN combination are blocked when ACB max step is reached as a result of step-wise PLMN ACB. Note that this functionality only applies for the PLMN associated with the ACBPR.

Parameter name: Active mode load equalization profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC AMLEPR and it uniquely identifies an instance of the Active Mode Load Equalization Profile (AMLEPR).    If the feature "Inter-frequency load equalization" is activated, a default AMLEPR profile with AMLEPR-amlePrId = 0 must exist.

Parameter name: Headroom in CAC
Description: The active mode load equalization feature in direction to a certain target cell shall leave the 'active state', if the reported CAC value from this target cell is smaller than the CAC headroom for the target cells frequency layer.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Difference in CAC of source and target cells
Description: Active mode load equalization shall be applied only if the difference in composite available capacity (CAC) in source and target cells is above this target frequency-specific value.

Parameter name: Threshold for maximum CAC
Description: Active mode load equalization shall be applied only if the composite available capacity (CAC) in the source cell falls below this target frequency-specific threshold.

Parameter name: Target carrier frequency
Description: This parameter describes the FDD/TDD EUTRA absolute radio frequency channel number (EARFCN) of the (downlink) frequency layer this inter-frequency load equalization profile (AMLEPR) is valid for.

Parameter name: assigned NB-IoT parameter identifier
Description: This parameter is the instance identifier of MOC ANBIOT. It uniquely identifies a ANBIOT instance.

Parameter name: Assigned NB-IoT carrier instance ID
Description: This parameter is the instance identifier of MOC ANBIOTCARR. It uniquely identifies an ANBIOTCARR instance.

Parameter name: NB-IoT carrier type
Description: This parameter indicates the type of carrier in NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: EARFCN of downlink carrier in terms of frequency band of host cell
Description: EARFCN of downlink carrier in terms of frequency band of host cell.    The physical frequency of the downlink carrier center point is frequency of this EARFCN plus offset indicated by assignedEarfcnDLOffset.    If assignedCarrierType indicates anchor carrier, when actSepMFBI is true and eafcnDL in NBIOT_FDD is not configured, the eNB uses this parameter to look up eutraCarrierFreq in MFBIPR instances to determine the MFBI setting for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: Offset of downlink carrier to EARFCN indicated by assignedEarfcnDL
Description: The offset of downlink carrier to EARFCN indicated by assignedEarfcnDL. Refer 36.101 5.7.3F MDL.  The unit is kHz. MDL and this offset value mapping as following:  MDL: Offset (kHz)  10: -47.5  -9: -42.5  -8: -37.5  -7: -32.5  -6: -27.5  -5: -22.5  -4: -17.5  -3: -12.5  -2: -7.5  -1: -2.5  -0.5: 0  0: 2.5  1: 7.5  2: 12.5  3: 17.5  4: 22.5  5: 27.5  6: 32.5  7: 37.5  8: 42.5  9: 47.5

Parameter name: EARFCN of uplink carrier in terms of frequency band of host cell
Description: EARFCN of uplink carrier in terms of frequency band of host cell.  The physical frequency of the carrier center point is frequency of this EARFCN plus offset indicated by assignedEarfcnULOffset.

Parameter name: Offset of uplink carrier to EARFCN indicated by assignedEarfcnUL
Description: The offset of the uplink carrier to EARFCN indicated by assignedEarfcnUL. Refer 36.101 5.7.3F MUL.  The unit is kHz. MUL and this offset value mapping as following:  MUL: Offset (kHz)  10: -50  -9: -45  -8: -40  -7: -35  -6: -30  -5: -25  -4: -20  -3: -15  -2: -10  -1: -5  0: 0  1: 5  2: 10  3: 15  4: 20  5: 25  6: 30  7: 35  8: 40  9: 45

Parameter name: Assigned PRB index of guardband NB-IoT downlink carrier
Description: The Frequency offset of guardband NB-IoT downlink carrier from earfcnDL, automatically assigned by the system or manual configuration.

Parameter name: Assigned PRB index of guardband NB-IoT uplink carrier
Description: The Frequency offset of guardband NB-IoT uplink carrier from earfcnUL, automatically assigned by the system or manual configuration.

Parameter name: Assigned PRB index of inband NB-IoT downlink carriers
Description: The PRB index of the host LTE cell used for NB-IoT inband downlink carrier, automatically assigned by carrier algorithm or manual configuration.  Note:  5 MHz range is 0..24,  10 MHz range is 0..49,  15 MHz range is 0..74,  20 MHz range is 0..99

Parameter name: Assigned PRB index of inband NB-IoT uplinkcarriers
Description: The PRB index of the host LTE cell used for NB-IoT inband uplink carrier, automatically assigned by carrier algorithm or manual configuration.  Note:  5 MHz range is 0..24,  10 MHz range is 0..49,  15 MHz range is 0..74,  20 MHz range is 0..99

Parameter name: ANR basic configuration identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an ANR object.    The instance defines basic ANR configuration parameters which are not related to a dedicated carrier frequency.

Parameter name: Activate autonomous removal of LTE neighbors
Description: Activates autonomous removal of unused LTE neighbor relation and neighbor information

Parameter name: Activate autonomous removal of unused 5G-HO neighbors
Description: This parameter activates autonomous removal of unused 5G HO neighbour relation and neighbour information (LNRELN, LNADJN, LNADJNL)

Parameter name: Activate autonomous removal of unused EN-DC neighbors
Description: This parameter activates autonomous removal of unused eNB controlled EN DC X2 links and removal of unused LTE neighbour relation and neighbour information

Parameter name: Activate autonomous removal of 1xRTT neighbors
Description: Activates autonomous removal of unused CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor relation and neighbor cell configuration information        NOTE: activation of 1xRTT autonomous removal function is independent of actAnrRtt enabled for 1xANR or not.

Parameter name: Activate autonomous removal of UTRAN neighbors
Description: Activates autonomous removal of unused UTRAN neighbor relation and neighbor cell configuration information

Parameter name: Activate X2 IPv4 prioritization
Description: This parameter activates IPv4 prioritization for the eNB controlled LTE X2 link establishment.    With dual stack IPv4/IPv6 for S1/X2 enabled and ANR Fully UE based enabled:  - when this parameter is set to 'true' on X2 initiating eNB then IPv4 address is prioritized over IPv6 address for eNB controlled LTE X2 link establishment, corresponding X2 mesh IPsec tunnel will not be automatically established (even if relevant feature is enabled in eNB)  - otherwise the legacy behaviour, i.e IPv6 address is prioritized over IPv4 address for eNB controlled LTE X2 link establishment.

Parameter name: ANR interfrequency RSC timer
Description: It defines the maximum time at the eNB to wait for an LTE inter-frequency ReportStrongestCells measurement report from a UE configured to perform such measurement

Parameter name: Supervision timer for coverage verification of unknown NR-Cell for NR ANR
Description: It defines the maximum time eNB waits for an activated NR-reportStrongestCells measurement report on an NR carrier frequency for NR ANR in case unknown NR-Cell coverage is to be verified

Parameter name: Guard time for autonomous LNRELN, LNADJN, LNADJNL removal
Description: Guard time before eNB autonomous LNRELN, LNADJN, LNADJNL object removal.  The eNB removes LNRELN, if NR-PCI/NR-Carrier (represented by nrPciHoCounter) is rarely present in B2-NR 5GHO UE RRC measurement reports, so that corresponding nrPciHoCounter is below LNBTS-LNCEL-LNHON-nrPciHoNbrRelRemThresh for anrNrHoNbrRelRemGuardTime. LNADJN, LNADJNL(s) are removed when they have no associated LNCEL.LNRELN(s) for anrNrHoNbrRelRemGuardTime.

Parameter name: NR ANR parameter list for 5G HO
Description: List of parameters of NR ANR for the purpose of 5G HO.

Parameter name: Activate populating LNADJN.gNBplmnId by NR ANR
Description: Activation flag to enable populating gNBplmnId from LNADJN MOC by NR ANR, based on plmn-IdentityInfoList-r15[1].plmn-IdentityList-r15[1] of cgi-Info-r15 reported by UE as part of NR-reportCGI procedure.  LNADJN.gNBplmnId is an optional field which is autonomously set by eNB only if multiple entries of plmn-IdentityInfoList-r15[] in cgi-Info-r15 are reported by UE and NR-Carrier for which cgi-Info-r15 is reported together with PLMN from plmn-IdentityInfoList-r15[1].plmn-IdentityList-r15[1] match this configuration entry of anrNrHoParamList.  LNADJN.gNBplmnId, if defined, is used instead of LNADJNL.gNBplmnId in Target Id IE from S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED sent with "HANDOVER Type" set to "EPSto5GS" when the 5GHO is attempted towards LNADJNL.

Parameter name: Default value of LNRELN.psHoAllowed when parent object is created by eNB
Description: Default value of LNRELN.psHoAllowed when parent object is created by 5G HO ANR functionality

Parameter name: NR SSB frequency
Description: The SSB frequency of the NR carrier for which 5G HO ANR parameter set is defined.

Parameter name: NR Carrier selection
Description: Selects the NR carrier frequency range between single carrier, FR1, FR2 or all carriers. If 'Single Carrier' is selected, the dedicated NR carrier frequency needs to be configured.  When frqNrCarSelect is set to 'All', the corresponding anrNrParamList entry is applicable to all NR carriers for specified PLMN.  When frqNrCarSelect is set to 'FR1' or 'FR2', the corresponding anrNrParamList entry is applicable to all NR carriers from frequency range 1 and 2, respectively, for specified PLMN.  Any parameter defined for specific NR-carrier, i.e. with frqNrCarSelect set to 'Single Carrier', has application precedence over parameterization specified for any other value of frqNrCarSelect for specified PLMN.  Any parameter defined with frqNrCarSelect set to 'FR1' or 'FR2' has application precedence over parameterization specified with frqNrCarSelect set to 'All' for specified PLMN.

Parameter name: gNB Id length
Description: Determines length of gNB Id in NR Cell Identity.

Parameter name: RRC measurement configuration Id for 5G HO ANR parametrization
Description: paramMeasConfId links NR ANR parameter from anrNrHoParamList to a given RRC measurement configuration anrNrMeasConfList. Measurement configuration is used prior to receiving NR-reportCGI with PLMN(s) and therefore, should not be PLMN dependent, i.e. should be common for a given NR-Carrier.

Parameter name: Plmn id defined for 5G HO ANR parameter
Description: paramPlmnId links 5G HO ANR parameter from anrNrHoParamList to a given PLMN from anrNrParamPlmnList. Entries in anrNrParamPlmnList refer to PLMN(s) reported by UE for a given RRC:cellIdentity IE in NR-reportCGI. Only first PLMNs reported by UE for logical NR cells and matching anrNrHoParamList are used to create 5G HO LNRELN relations.    When paramPlmnId is set to special value of 0 then parameter entry of anrNrHoParamList is applicable to all PLMNs. Any parameter defined for specific PLMN (with non-zero value of paramPlmnId) has application precedence over parameterization defined for all PLMNs.

Parameter name: NR ANR inactivity timer
Description: It defines the minimum UE inactivity time period before triggering UE-based NR ANR measurements.  This timer applies to UE-capable of NR ANR measurements when the respective feature is enabled.

Parameter name: RRC measurement configuration list for NR ANR
Description: List of RRC measurement configurations to be used in NR ANR related parametrization. anrNrMeasConfList defines configurations used in anrNrParamList. Linkage is achieved using paramMeasConfId, which is common for anrNrParamList and anrNrMeasConfList. Measurement configuration is used prior to receiving NR-reportCGI with PLMN(s) and therefore, should not be PLMN dependent, i.e. should be common for a given NR-Carrier.

Parameter name: RRC measurement configuration Id for NR ANR parametrization
Description: paramMeasConfId links NR ANR parameter set from anrNrParamList with RRC measurement configuration defined in anrNrMeasConfList

Parameter name: RSRP threshold for NR ANR reportStrongestCells measurements
Description: RSRP threshold for eNB post-processing of reportStrongestCells measurement reports related to NR ANR. NR-Cells from RRC measurement report with RSRP lower than thresholdNrRsrp are ignored. NR ANR procedure may fail if no suitable NR-Cells is left.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP value according to TS 38.133:  * -156 dBm means a threshold lower than -156 dBm  * values between -155 dBm and -30 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -29 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -30 dBm

Parameter name: RSRQ threshold for NR ANR reportStrongestCells measurements
Description: RSRQ threshold for eNB post-processing of reportStrongestCells measurement reports related to NR ANR. NR-Cells from RRC measurement report with RSRQ lower than thresholdNrRsrq are ignored. NR ANR procedure may fail if no suitable NR-Cells is left.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP values according to TS 38.133:  - -43.5 dB means a threshold lower than -43 dB  - values between -43 dB and 19.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - 20 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 20 dB

Parameter name: 5G HO relation periodical re-verification wait timer
Description: If for a 5G HO Neighbor Relation (LNRELN) a handover procedure is started and since the last validation of LNRELN at least the time 'anrNrNbrHoRelVerifyPeriod' has elapsed, then eNB triggers a re-verification for this LNRELN via NR-CGI measurement.    If 'anrNrNbrHoRelVerifyPeriod' is set to '0', then no re-verification is triggered.

Parameter name: Guard time before eNB autonomous LNRELGNBCELL relation removal.
Description: Guard time before eNB autonomous LNRELGNBCELL relation removal. The eNB removes LNRELGNBCELL only if NR-PCI/NR-Carrier (represented by nrPciCounter) is rarely present in B1-NR ENDC UE RRC measurement reports, so that corresponding nrPciCounter is below LNBTS-NRDC[D]PR-ENDCMEASCONF-nrPciNbrRelRemThresh for anrNrNbrRelRemGuardTime or when there is no X2 ENDC connection allowing to derive NR-PCI/NR-Carrier related to LNRELGNBCELL for the same period of time.

Parameter name: NR ANR parameter list
Description: List of parameters of NR ANR.

Parameter name: Default value of LNRELGNBCELL.lteNrDualConnectAllowed when parent object is created by eNB
Description: Default value of LNRELGNBCELL.lteNrDualConnectAllowed when parent object is created by NR ANR functionality

Parameter name: NR SSB frequency
Description: The SSB frequency of the NR carrier for which the NR ANR parameter set is defined.

Parameter name: NR Carrier selection
Description: Selects the NR carrier frequency range between single carrier, FR1, FR2 or all carriers. If 'Single Carrier' is selected, the dedicated NR carrier frequency needs to be configured.  When frqNrCarSelect is set to 'All', the corresponding anrNrParamList entry is applicable to all NR carriers for specified PLMN.  When frqNrCarSelect is set to 'FR1' or 'FR2', the corresponding anrNrParamList entry is applicable to all NR carriers from frequency range 1 and 2, respectively, for specified PLMN.  Any parameter defined for specific NR-carrier, i.e. with frqNrCarSelect set to 'Single Carrier', has application precedence over parameterization specified for any other value of frqNrCarSelect for specified PLMN.  Any parameter defined with frqNrCarSelect set to 'FR1' or 'FR2' has application precedence over parameterization specified with frqNrCarSelect set to 'All' for specified PLMN.

Parameter name: gNB Id length
Description: Determines length of gNB Id in NR Cell Identity.

Parameter name: RRC measurement configuration Id for NR ANR parametrization
Description: paramMeasConfId links NR ANR parameter from anrNrParamList to a given RRC measurement configuration anrNrMeasConfList. Measurement configuration is used prior to receiving NR-reportCGI with PLMN(s) and therefore, should not be PLMN dependent, i.e. should be common for a given NR-Carrier.

Parameter name: Plmn id defined for NR ANR parameter
Description: paramPlmnId links NR ANR parameter from anrNrParamList to a given PLMN from anrNrParamPlmnList. Entries in anrNrParamPlmnList refer to PLMN(s) reported by UE for a given RRC:cellIdentity IE in NR-reportCGI. All PLMNs reported by UE and matching anrNrParamList are used to search X2 ENDC connection database. First match found is used to create LNRELGNBCELL. If no match is found, first PLMN reported by UE and matching anrNrParamList configuration is used to create LNRELGNBCELL.    When paramPlmnId is set to special value of 0 then parameter entry of anrNrParamList is applicable to all PLMNs. Any parameter defined for specific PLMN (with non-zero value of paramPlmnId) has application precedence over parameterization defined for all PLMNs.

Parameter name: PLMN list for NR ANR parameters
Description: List of PLMNs to be used in NR ANR related parametrization. anrNrParamPlmnList defines PLMNs used in anrNrParamList. Linkage is achieved using paramPlmnId, which is common for anrNrParamList and anrNrParamPlmnList.  Entries in anrNrParamPlmnList refer to PLMN(s) reported by UE for a given RRC:cellIdentity IE in NR-reportCGI. All PLMNs reported by UE and matching anrNrParamList are used to search X2 ENDC connection database. First match found is used to create LNRELGNBCELL. If no match is found, first PLMN reported by UE and matching anrNrParamList configuration is used to create LNRELGNBCELL.

Parameter name: MCC in PLMN
Description: Primary Mobile Country Code of PLMN for which NR ANR parameters are defined. Entries in anrNrParamPlmnList refer to PLMN(s) reported by UE for a given RRC:cellIdentity IE in NR-reportCGI.

Parameter name: MNC in PLMN
Description: This is the Mobile Network Code of PLMN for which NR ANR parameters are defined. Entries in anrNrParamPlmnList refer to PLMN(s) reported by UE for a given RRC:cellIdentity IE in NR-reportCGI.

Parameter name: MNC length in PLMN
Description: This parameter determines the range of MNC of the PLMN for which NR ANR parameters are defined. Entries in anrNrParamPlmnList refer to PLMN(s) reported by UE for a given RRC:cellIdentity IE in NR-reportCGI.

Parameter name: PLMN ID for NR ANR parametrization
Description: paramPlmnId links NR ANR parameter set from anrNrParamList with PLMN defined in anrNrParamPlmnList. Entries in anrNrParamPlmnList refer to PLMN(s) reported by UE for a given RRC:cellIdentity IE in NR-reportCGI. All PLMNs reported by UE and matching anrNrParamList are used to search X2 ENDC connection database. First match found is used to create LNRELGNBCELL. If no match is found, first PLMN reported by UE and matching anrNrParamList configuration is used to create LNRELGNBCELL.

Parameter name: ANR robustness level
Description: Specifies the level of robustness of UE-based ANR functions.  - For high level of robustness, eNB attempts for a longer time period to resolve a detected unknown neighbor cell via UE-based ANR before stopping these attempts.  - For high level of robustness, the minimum wait time between re-validations of the same Neighbor Relation becomes shorter.
Range and step: none (0), very low (1), low (2), middle (3), high (4), very high (5)

Parameter name: ANR Robustness Level for UTRAN
Description: Specifies the level of robustness of UTRAN UE-based ANR functions.  * For high level of robustness, eNB attempts for a longer time period to resolve a detected unknown neighbour cell via UE-based ANR before stopping these attempts.  * For high level of robustness, the minimum wait time between re-validations of the same Neighbour Relation becomes shorter
Range and step: none (0), very low (1), low (2), middle (3), high (4), very high (5)

Parameter name: ANR 1xRTT RSCFS timer
Description: It defines the maximum time eNB waits for an activated ReportStrongestCellForSon measurement report on an 1xRTT carrier frequency of the LTE cell.

Parameter name: ANR UTRA RSCFS timer
Description: It defines the maximum time eNB waits for an activated ReportStrongestCellForSon measurement report on an UTRAN carrier frequency.

Parameter name: Autonomous UTRAN neighbor removal threshold
Description: Autonomous removal of UTRAN neighbors is applied by eNB only if the number of UTRAN neighbors for the respective eNB cell and UTRAN carrier exceeds this threshold.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Consecutive 5G-HO failure re-verification threshold
Description: If for an 5G-HO Neighbor Relation (LNRELN) 'consec5gHoFailThres' consecutive 5G handover execution failures are observed, then the eNB triggers a re-verification for this LRENLN via NR-CGI measurement.  If 'consec5gHoFailThres=0', then no re-verification is triggered due to 5G HO failures.    Note: To limit the load due to re-verification, eNB triggers re-verification only if at least some minimum wait time since last validation of the same LNRELN has expired.

Parameter name: Consecutive handover execution failure re-validation TH
Description: If for an LTE Neighbor Relation (NR) 'consecHoFailThres' consecutive handover execution failures are observed, then the eNB triggers a re-validation for this NR via CGI measurement (if CGI measurements are allowed).    If 'consecHoFailThres=0', then no re-validation is triggered.  Note: To limit the load due to re-validations, eNB triggers re-validation only if at least some minimum wait time since last validation of the same NR has expired.

Parameter name: Consecutive UTRAN HO execution failure re-validation TH
Description: If for an UTRAN Neighbor Relation (UtranNR) 'consecUtranHoFailThres' consecutive UTRAN handover execution failures are observed, then the eNB triggers a re-validation for this UtranNR via CGI measurement (if CGI measurements are allowed).    If 'consecUtranHoFailThres=0', then no re-validation is triggered.    Note: To limit the load due to re-validations, eNB triggers re-validation only if at least some minimum wait time since last validation of the same UtranNR has expired.

Parameter name: Global gNB Id Blacklist
Description: This list includes the Global gNB IDs of those neighbor gNBs for which the automatic creation of relations is forbidden by the operator.  This further results in preventing automatic creation of LNADJGNB and automatic establishment of eNB controlled X2-link.  If a neighbor gNB is in this blacklist, eNB won't automatically create relation (LNRELGNBCELL) for this gNB-ID.    Blacklisting can be configured  - for a whole PLMN (gNBId configured to special value -1)  - for a single gNB within a PLMN (gnbIdRange =1)  - for a range of gNBs within a PLMN (gnbIdRange >1)

Parameter name: Blacklisted gNB ID
Description: Global gNB Id of a neighbor gNB towards which the automatic creation of neighbor relation is forbidden and no LNRELGNBCELL / eNB controlled LNADJGNB object should be created.  This is the unique ID of the neighbor gNB within PLMN, where adjGnbId and plmnId form the neighbor global gNB ID.

Parameter name: Blacklisted gNB ID range
Description: Range of global gNB IDs of neighbor gNBs towards which the automatic creation of neighbor relation is forbidden and no LNRELGNBCELL / eNB controlled LNADJGNB object should be created.  This parameter defines the number of consecutive gNB ID's starting (and including) with 'X2 blacklisted gNB ID'.    Default value '1' means, only the 'X2 blacklisted gNB ID' is blacklisted.  Otherwise, all gNB with gnbId starting from 'gnbId' up to 'gnbId + gnbIdRange -1' will be blacklisted.

Parameter name: Blacklisted global gNB id MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the Global gNB Id of a neighbor gNB towards which the automatic creation of neighbor relation is forbidden and no LNRELGNBCELL / eNB controlled LNADJGNB object should be created.

Parameter name: Blacklisted global gNB id MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the Global gNB Id of a neighbor gNB towards which the automatic creation of neighbor relation is forbidden and no LNRELGNBCELL / eNB controlled LNADJGNB object should be created.

Parameter name: Blacklisted global gNB id MNC length
Description: Length of Mobile Network Code of the Global gNB Id of a neighbor gNB towards which the automatic creation of neighbor relation is forbidden and no LNRELGNBCELL / eNB controlled LNADJGNB object should be created.

Parameter name: Global eNB id X2-link blacklist
Description: This list includes the Global eNB IDs of those neighbor eNBs for which the X2-link establishment is forbidden by the operator.

Parameter name: X2 blacklisted eNB ID
Description: Macro eNB Id of the Global eNB Id of a neighbor eNB towards which no establishment of an eNB Controlled X2-link is allowed.  If 'enbId' is not provided then the associated 'Global eNB I' is a 'partially specified Global eNB Id', i.e.:  All 'Global eNB Ids' with a PLMN ID which is identical to the associated 'X2 Blacklisted PLMN ID' are considered as members of the 'Global eNB Id X2-link Blacklist'.

Parameter name: X2 blacklisted global eNB id MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the Global eNB Id of a neighbour eNB towards which no establishment of an eNB Controlled X2-link is allowed.

Parameter name: X2 blacklisted global eNB id MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the Global eNB Id of a neighbor eNB towards which no establishment of an eNB Controlled X2-link is allowed.

Parameter name: X2 blacklisted global eNB id MNC length
Description: Length of Mobile Network Code of the Global eNB Id of a neighbor eNB towards which no establishment of an eNB Controlled X2-link is allowed.

Parameter name: ANR Idle Time Thresholds for LTE - Idle Time Threshold for LTE Neighbor Relations
Description: The eNB may autonomously remove an LTE NR, if the LTE NR is not used for handover for at least the time 'idleTimeThresLteNR'.      Notes:  * LTE NRs which are 'reserved by operator' are not autonomously removed by eNB  * The eNB checks once per hour if a LTE NR has to be removed  Note: It is recommended to choose 'idleTimeThresLteNR' to be smaller than 'idleTimeThresX2' to avoid that one eNB may autonomously close an X2 link and the peer eNB re-establishes the X2 link again, because autonomous removal of associated unused Neighbor Relations did not yet occur.  Note: It is recommended to choose 'idleTimeThresLteNR' to be greater than 24 hours if a Load-based power saving feature is activated at the eNB ('actLBPowerSaving' = 'true' or 'actLBRTXPowerSaving' = 'true') to avoid the autonomous removal of Neighbor Relations due to either the serving cell or the neighbor cell being switched off into the 'energySavingState' = 'energySaving' state or having transmit power reduced due to switched off TX paths when the 'energySavingState' = 'reducedEnergySaving.

Parameter name: ANR Idle Time Thresholds for LTE - Idle Time Threshold for Neighbor eNB Exchange
Description: If the maximum number of LTE neighbor eNBs is already stored, then a stored neighbor eNB may be exchanged against a neighbor eNB newly detected via CGI measurement only, if the idle time for the stored neighbor eNB is at least equal to 'idleTimeThresNbeNBExch'.    If 'idleTimeThresNbeNBExch' is set to '0', then no exchange of LTE neighbor eNBs is triggered.

Parameter name: ANR Idle Time Thresholds for LTE - Idle Time Threshold for Neighbor eNBs
Description: If for at least the time 'idleTimeThresNbeNB' an enbControlled NbeNB no NR and no X2 link is available, then the eNB removes the LNADJ/ LNADJL objects associated with the NbeNB    Notes:  * Neighbor eNBs and Neighbor Cells which are associated with an oamControlled LNADJ object are not autonomously removed by eNB  * The eNB checks once per hour if a LTE NR has to be removed

Parameter name: Idle time threshold for 1xRTT neighbor relations
Description: The eNB may autonomously remove a 1xRTT NR corresponding to a 1xRTT neighbor cell, only if the 1xRTT NR is not detected in 1xRTT mobility measurement reports for at least the time 'idleTimeThresRttNR' on the 1xRTT carrier of the LTE cell.      Notes:  * 1xRTT NRs corresponding to 1xRTT neighbor cells which are indicated with 'removeAllowed=false' are not autonomously removed by eNB  * The eNB checks once per hour if a 1xRTT NR has to be removed

Parameter name: Idle time threshold for UTRAN neighbor relations
Description: The eNB may autonomously remove a UTRAN NR corresponding to a WCDMA neighbor cell, if the UTRAN NR is not used by UTRAN mobility management for at least the time 'idleTimeThresUtranNR'.      Notes:  * UTRAN NRs corresponding to WCDMA neighbor cells which are indicated with 'removeAllowed=false' are not autonomously removed by eNB  * The eNB checks once per hour if a UTRAN NR has to be removed

Parameter name: ANR Idle Time Thresholds for LTE - Idle Time Threshold for X2 links
Description: If for an enbControlled X2 link no LTE Neighbor Relation exists and if for at least the time 'idleTimeThresX2' no X2 handover is received, then the eNB autonomously closes the X2 link.    Notes:  * oamControlled X2 links are not autonomously closed by eNB  * The eNB checks once per hour if a X2 link has to be closed.  Note: It is recommended to choose 'idleTimeThresX2' to be larger than 'idleTimeThresLteNR' to avoid that one eNB may autonomously close an X2 link and the peer eNB re-establishes the X2 link again, because autonomous removal of associated unused Neighbor Relations did not yet occur.

Parameter name: Maximum number of eNB-controlled incoming X2-links
Description: If the number of eNB-controlled X2-links reaches 'maxNumX2LinksIn', then the eNB shall stop accepting establishment requests for new eNB-controlled X2-links from neighbor eNBs

Parameter name: Maximum number of eNB-controlled outgoing X2-links
Description: If the number of eNB-controlled X2-links reaches 'maxNumX2LinksOut', then the eNB shall stop the automatic establishment of new eNB-controlled X2-links

Parameter name: Minimum not activated 1xRTT ReportStrongestCellsForSon
Description: This parameter defines the minimum time interval that should elapse since the last search of possible unknown PCIs on a 1xRTT carrier frequency of the LTE cell, before re-initiating a new search on that carrier.    Via this parameter, it is possible to control the minimum frequency according which a 1xRTT carrier frequency in slow search mode is scanned for potential new neighbor cell detection.    If value "0" is selected, all 1xRTT carrier frequencies for 1xRTT ANR will always be in fast Active search.

Parameter name: Minimum not activated UTRA reportStrongestCellsForSon
Description: This parameter defines the minimum time interval that should elapse since the last search of possible unknown PCIs, respectively PSCs, on an UTRAN carrier frequency, before re-initiating a new search on that carrier. Via this parameter, it is possible to control the maximum frequency according which an UTRAN carrier frequency in slow search mode is scanned for potential new neighbor cell detection. If value "0" is selected, the respective UTRAN carrier frequency will always be in fast Active search.

Parameter name: Minimum number threshold of 1xRTT neighbor relations
Description: The eNB may autonomously remove a 1xRTT NR corresponding to a 1xRTT neighbor cell, only if the number of 1xRTT neighbor relations (LNRELX instances) on the related CDMA2000 1xRTT carrier frequency of a LTE cell is larger than 'minNumThresRttNR'.

Parameter name: ANR Idle Time Thresholds for LTE - Neighbor eNB Exchange Wait Timer
Description: If the eNB performs a Neighbor eNB exchange, then the eNB will afterwards wait for at least the time given by 'nbEnbExchWaitTmr', before the next Neighbor eNB exchange may be triggered.

Parameter name: PCI-IP address mapping table
Description: Provides the mapping from cell parameters {dlEarfcn, pci} to the {ipAdr} of the eNB serving this cell, where 'ipAdr' is the IP address required for X2-link establishment.

Parameter name: PCI-IP map downlink EARFCN
Description: Downlink EARFCN of the neighbor cell included in the 'pciIpAdrMap'

Parameter name: PCI-IP map eNB ID
Description: Unique macro eNB ID of the neighbor eNB within the Primary PLMN serving the neighbor cell indicated in the PCI-IP Map entry.

Parameter name: PCI-IP map IPv4/IPv6 address
Description: X2 C-plane V4/V6 IP address of the eNB serving the cell included in the 'pciIpAdrMap'

Parameter name: PCI-IP map primary MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code included in the Primary PLMN ID of the neighbor eNB serving the cell provided in the PCI-IP Map entry

Parameter name: PCI-IP map primary MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code included in the Primary PLMN ID of the neighbor eNB serving the cell provided in the PCI-IP Map entry

Parameter name: PCI-IP map primary MNC length
Description: Length of Mobile Network Code included in the Primary PLMN ID of the neighbor eNB serving the cell provided in the PCI-IP Map entry

Parameter name: PCI-IP map PCI
Description: Physical Cell Identity of the neighbor cell included in the 'pciIpAdrMap'

Parameter name: S1 periodical revalidation wait timer
Description: If for an inter-eNB LTE Neighbor Relation (NR) without available X2 link a handover preparation is started and since the last validation of the NR at least the time 's1PrdRevalWaitTmr' has elapsed, then eNB triggers a re-validation for this NR via CGI measurement (if CGI measurements are allowed).    If 's1PrdRevalWaitTmr' is set to '0', then no re-validation is triggered.  Note 1: To limit the load due to re-validations, eNB triggers re-validation only if at least some minimum wait time since the last validation of the same NR has expired.  Note 2: To retrieve the CGI measurement for the re-validation, the eNB will start Active ANR mode and use a UE different from the one which needs the handover.

Parameter name: Sample Number threshold of 1xRTT measurement reports
Description: The eNB may autonomously remove a 1xRTT NR corresponding to a 1xRTT neighbor cell, only if the number of sent 1xRTT mobility measurement activation request on the related CDMA2000 1xRTT carrier frequency of a LTE cell is larger than or equal to 'samNumThresRttNR ' during the consecutive time period when the unknown 1xRTT NR is not detected in 1xRTT mobility measurement reports.

Parameter name: Temporary blacklist timer for 1xRTT ANR
Description: This timer is used for temporary blacklisting of a 1xRTT neighbor Cell for 1xANR on a 1xRTT carrier of the LTE cell.    The timer is started for a 1xRTT neighbor cell, when it is temporarily blacklisted due to auto removal.    When timer expires, the temporary blacklisting for that 1xRTT neighbor cell is removed.    If value "0" is selected, the temporary blacklisting mechanism is disabled.

Parameter name: UTRAN periodical revalidation wait timer
Description: If for a UTRAN Neighbor Relation (UtranNR) a UTRAN handover procedure is started and since the last validation of UtranNR at least the time 'utranPrdRevalWaitTmr' has elapsed, then eNB triggers a re-validation for this UtranNR via CGI measurement (if CGI measurements are allowed).    If 'utranPrdRevalWaitTmr' is set to '0', then no re-validation is triggered.    Note: To limit the load due to re-validations, eNB triggers re-validation only if at least some minimum wait time since the last validation of the same UtranNR has expired.

Parameter name: X2 periodical revalidation wait timer
Description: If for an intra-eNB LTE Neighbor Relation (NR), respectively for an inter-eNB NR with available X2 link a handover preparation is started and since the last validation of the NR at least the time 'x2PrdRevalWaitTmr' has elapsed, then eNB triggers a re-validation for this NR via CGI measurement (if CGI measurements are allowed).    If 'x2PrdRevalWaitTmr' is set to '0', then no re-validation is triggered.  Note 1: To limit the load due to re-validations, eNB triggers re-validation only if at least some minimum wait time since the last validation of the same NR has expired.  Note 2: To retrieve the CGI measurement for the re-validation, the eNB will start Active ANR mode and use a UE different from the one which needs the handover.

Parameter name: ANR profile for LTE identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an ANRPRL object.    An Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile (ANRPRL) defines carrier-frequency-specific settings for automatic detection of LTE intra-frequency and inter-frequency neighbor cells.

Parameter name: Activate also for UE-based ANR
Description: Activates the profile for UE-based intra- and/or inter-frequency ANR (LTE556, LTE782) too.    If set to "true" the profile applies for any kind of ANR, that is UE-based and not UE-based. If set to "false" the profile is not applied for UE-based ANR but still applied for not UE-based ANR features (for example LTE492).

Parameter name: ANR power level threshold for neighbor cells
Description: If RSRP of a neighbor cell included in ANR measurement "reportStrongestCells" is greater than anrThresRSRPNbCell, then this cell is accepted as 'candidate cell for ANR'.    The parameter is relevant only if at least one of the features; LTE782 or LTE556, is activated, that is if actUeBasedAnrIntraFreqLte and/or actUeBasedAnrInterFreqLte is set to "true".

Parameter name: ANR power level threshold for mobility events
Description: Threshold to control detection of neighbor cells via passive ANR.    If a measurement report for the mobility events A3, A4 or A5 is received, then the cell corresponding to an included PCI can be accepted as 'candidate cell for ANR' only if the PCI fulfills the condition:  RSRP(PCI) > anrThres RSRPNbCellMobEv.  The parameter is only relevant if at least one of the features LTE492, LTE782 or LTE556 is activated, i.e. if anrOmExtEnable or actUeBasedAnrIntraFreqLte or actUeBasedAnrInterFreqLte is set to 'true'.    Passive ANR can be switched off by setting the threshold to a very high value.

Parameter name: ANR quality threshold for neighbor cells
Description: The eNB will request to resolve the CGI of a 'candidate cell for ANR' only if the respective RSRQ level measured by the UE is at least equal to anrThresRSRQNbCell.    The parameter is relevant only if at least one of the features; LTE782 or LTE556, is activated, that is if actUeBasedAnrIntraFreqLte and/or actUeBasedAnrInterFreqLte is set to "true".

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Neighbor relation limit inter-frequency
Description: Once the number of LTE inter-frequency neighbor relations of the eNB cell reaches "nrLimitInterFreq", the eNB stops autonomous learning of new neighbor cells via ANR.  Note: The number of inter-frequency neighbor relations can exceed this limit since new neighbor cells/new neighbor relations still can be configured via O&M and autonomous creation of neighbor relations for already available neighbor cells might occur.

Parameter name: Neighbor relation limit intra-frequency
Description: Once the number of LTE intra-frequency neighbor relations of the eNB cell reaches "nrLimitIntraFreq", the eNB stops autonomous learning of new neighbor cells via ANR.  Note: The number of intra-frequency neighbor relations can exceed this limit since new neighbor cells/new neighbor relations still can be configured via O&M and autonomous creation of neighbor relations for already available neighbor cells might occur.

Parameter name: Target carrier frequency
Description: The parameter identifies the EUTRA target carrier frequency for which this ANR profile applies.    The profile applies for intra- and or inter-frequency ANR dependent on the carrier frequency of the cell.    If no target carrier is defined, the profile applies for any frequency which is measured by a UE. This profile is considered as default profile and must exist in any case. If an ANRPRL instance with a dedicated carrier frequency exists, this has higher priority than the default profile.  Note that ANR measurements will be only activated in a cell if an LNHOIF object is created for each relevant target carrier frequency.

Parameter name: ANR profile for WCDMA identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an ANRPRW object.    An Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile (ANRPRW) defines carrier-frequency-specific settings for automatic detection of WCDMA neighbor cells.

Parameter name: ANR UTRA EcNo threshold
Description: It defines the minimum EcNo level measured by the UE from a UTRAcell required for ordering its CGI decoding. (Mapping between the UE measured EcNo and the SFS values is according to 3GPP TS 25.133/25.123).

Parameter name: ANR UTRA RSCP threshold
Description: It defines the minimum power level that a UE should report from a measured UTRA cell for considering the corresponding PCI, respectively PSC, as a possible UTRA neighbor cell candidate. (Mapping between the UE measured RSCP and the SFS values is according to 3GPP TS 25.133/25.123)  The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm  * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

Parameter name: Cells to apply list
Description: The parameter allows to restrict the ANR profile to certain LTE cells that are identified by their lncelId.  If the parameter is omitted or the list is empty the profile is considered as default profile, which applies to all cells with no dedicated profile.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: LNRELW default values - Circuit-switched fallback with PS handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether CSFB with PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Enable ANR profile
Description: The parameter enables ANR learning for the carrier frequency of the profile.

Parameter name: Limit for ANR created UTRAN neighbor relations
Description: The parameter allows limiting the number of WCDMA neighbor relations (LNRELW instances) per UTRAN carrier frequency and LTE cell.    This limit applies only for ANR created LNRELW instances but does not apply for LNRELW instances, which are manually created via plan file.    If the limit is already reached or even exceeded by manually created LNRELW instances, no additional LNRELW instances referring to WCDMA neighbor cells with the profile carrier frequency will be added by ANR.    If the number of neighbor relations (LNRELW instances) exceeds the maximum number of WCDMA neighbor cells which might be used by eNB in measurement configurations (limit in 3GPP 36.331) but the limit which is configured with lnRelWLimitForAnr is not yet reached, then eNB will create new LNLRELW instances with handoverAllowed set to 'forbidden'. This is to ease further manual optimization of neighbor cell blacklisting.

Parameter name: LNRELW default values - PS handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: List of blacklisted PSCs
Description: The parameter specifies a list of Primary Scrambling Codes (PSC) or code ranges that are excluded from ANR learning.

Parameter name: Primary scrambling code
Description: Single PSC value or first PSC value of a range that is blacklisted.

Parameter name: Last primary scrambling code of a range
Description: Last PSC value if a range of PSC values are blacklisted.

Parameter name: LNRELW default values - Redirect with system information allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether the related neighbor cell shall be a candidate for providing system information in case of UE redirection to UTRAN.

Parameter name: Coding of RNC ID within UTRAN CI - Alignment within UTRAN CI
Description: The parameter defines whether the RNC-ID is aligned to the left or right side within Cell Identity.

Parameter name: Coding of RNC ID within UTRAN CI - RNC ID type
Description: The parameter defines whether the RNC Id is of type 'normal' (12 Bit) or 'extended' (16 Bit).

Parameter name: LNRELW default values - Single radio Voice call continuity allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether SRVCC handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: SRVCC HO indication
Description: This parameter selects if SRVCC to a WCDMA target cell is performed as a combined PS and CS SRVCC or whether SRVCC is performed for the CS bearer only.    The value is used if a new LNADJW object is created by eNB because of ANR measurements and if the profile applies for the detecting LTE cell.    The value is only relevant if the feature LTE872 'SRVCC to WCDMA' is deployed. It is highly recommended to set this value properly even if the feature is not yet deployed but shall be deployed in future. Otherwise manual setting in all LNADJW objects becomes necessary later on if the feature LTE872 is activated.  It is a capability of the target UTRAN whether 'combined PS and CS SRVCC' or 'CS SRVCC only' are supported.

Parameter name: UTRAN carrier frequency
Description: The parameter identifies the UTRA carrier frequency for which this ANR profile applies.

Parameter name: ANR profile for 1xRTT identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an ANRPRX object.    An Automatic Neighbor Relationship Profile (ANRPRX) defines carrier frequency specific settings for automatic detection of 1xRTT neighbor cells.

Parameter name: ANR 1xRTT pilot strength threshold
Description: It defines the minimum pilot strength that a UE must report from a measured 1xRTT cell for considering the corresponding unknown PCI as a possible 1xRTT neighbor cell candidate.  Value of this parameter should be tuned according to real field network deployment & 1xRTT mobility service (1xCSFB, 1xSRVCC, etc), to control the speed of 1xRTT neighbor cell detections on the 1xRTT carrier.    Per 3GPP 36.331, the value range of the pilotStrength in the measurement report is 0..63. 63 is the weakest pilot strength, while 0 is the strongest pilot strength.    The formula used by the UE to report the pilot strength is [ -2 * 10 * log (measured pilot strength)].  Therefore 63 maps to -31.5 dB. So 0..63 maps to 0..-31.5 dB.

Parameter name: Cells to apply list
Description: The parameter allows to restrict the ANR profile only applicable to certain LTE cells which are identified by their lncelId.  If the parameter is omitted or if the list is empty, the ANR profile is considered as default ANR profile which applies to all LTE cells with no dedicated ANR profile for the related 1xRTT carrier.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: LNRELX default values - E1xCSFB allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether R9 e1xCSFB to the related 1xRTT neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Enable ANR profile
Description: The parameter enables ANR learning for the carrier frequency of the ANR profile in the applicable LTE cells.

Parameter name: Limit for ANR created 1xRTT neighbor relations
Description: The parameter allows limiting the number of 1xRTT neighbor relations (LNRELX instances) per CDMA2000 1xRTT carrier frequency and LTE cell.    This limit applies only for ANR created LNRELX instances but does not apply for LNRELX instances, which are manually created via plan file.    If the limit is already reached or even exceeded by manually created LNRELX instances, no additional LNRELX instances referring to 1xRTT neighbor cells with the profile carrier frequency will be added by ANR.

Parameter name: List of blacklisted PCIs
Description: The parameter specifies a list of CDMA2000 1xRTT physical cell ids (PCI) or PCI ranges which shall be statically excluded from 1xRTT ANR learning for the 1xRTT carrier in the LTE cell.

Parameter name: Physical cell identifier
Description: Single PCI value or first PCI value of a range which shall be statically blacklisted.

Parameter name: Last physical cell identifier of a range
Description: Last PCI value if a range of PCI values shall be statically blacklisted.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT carrier frequency - CDMA2000 1xRTT ARFCN
Description: Absolute Radio Frequency Number of CDMA2000 1xRTT carrier frequency  The CDMA2000 ARFCN used to indicate the CDMA2000 carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 band, see C.S0002-A.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT carrier frequency - CDMA2000 1xRTT band class
Description: Band Class of CDMA2000 1xRTT carrier frequency  The CDMA2000 band class is used to define the CDMA2000 band in which the CDMA2000 carrier frequency can be found, as defined in C.S0057-E [table 1.5-1].  Note: Bandclasses 18, 19, 20 and 21 are not supported by this release.

Parameter name: LNRELX default values - Single Radio Voice Call Continuity allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether SRVCC handover to the related 1xRTT neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH configuration identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC APUCCH_FDD.  It uniquely identifies a APUCCH_FDD instance.

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, add number UEs RR HO
Description: Additional margin in automatic PUCCH allocation to be considered for the maximum number of RRC connected resp. active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via handover with HO-cause: 'HO desirable for radio reasons'. This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.    This additional margin is used also for UEs accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: 'Reduce load in serving cell' but only when Composite Available Capacity (CAC) in the Cell is higher than 0. If CAC in the cell is zero, the HO for 'Reduce load in serving cell' are always rejected. This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.    For supplementary DL carrier (SDLC) this parameter should be configured to 0 (as no handover traffic can be supported in this cell no resources should then be considered on AirScale BBpool level).

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, add number UEs TC HO
Description: Additional margin in automatic PUCCH allocation to be considered for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via handover with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.    For supplementary DL carrier (SDLC) this parameter should be configured to 0 (as no handover traffic can be supported in this cell no resources should then be considered on AirScale BBpool level).

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, min num. emergency sessions
Description: Minimum number reserved resources for Emergency Sessions.  This margin increases the thresholds for active UEs, active DRBs and active QCI1-DRBs in the cell. Please note that active QCI1-DRBs thresholds are not considered when actEnhAcAndGbrServices is true.    Notes:  - Any change of actEmerCallRedir or actIMSEmerSessR9 will only be applied in case of other activities leading to LNCEL lock.  - The configured value of this parameter may have impact on the minimum expansion of dynamic PUCCH (aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb + max(aPucchAddAUeRrHo, aPucchAddAUeTcHo) + aPucchMinNumEmergencySessions + aPucchMinNumRrcHps shall be less or equal to 30 in order to allow a minimum expansion level for PUCCH).  - For supplementary DL carrier (SDLC) this parameter should be configured to 0 (as no Emergency traffic can be served in SDLC cells no resources should then be reserved on AirScale BBpools).

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, min number RRC
Description: This parameter is only for AirScale with dyn. PUCCH activated and ignored otherwise.    Minimum allocated number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection.  This is needed where resources may be shifted from one cell to the other; for dynamic PUCCH this parameter can control the minimum PUCCH configuration per cell.    In case baseband pooling is activated the value of these parameters may be internally adapted by the system based on the number of cells allocated to a baseband pool.

Parameter name: APUCCH min. number RRC connections for HPS
Description: This parameter defines the minimum number of reserved RRC connections for high priority access.  This margin increases the admission control thresholds for RRC connections and active UEs in the cell in case of requested high priority traffic (public safety). Those statically reserved resources can only be used by HPS users.    Notes:  - This margin will only be used if LTE4868 Admission control to differentiate HPA and Emergency handling is activated.  - The configured value of this parameter may have impact on the minimum expansion of dynamic PUCCH (aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb + max(aPucchAddAUeRrHo, aPucchAddAUeTcHo) + aPucchMinNumEmergencySessions + aPucchMinNumRrcHps shall be less or equal to 30 in order to allow a minimum expansion level for PUCCH).  - For supplementary DL carrier (SDLC) this parameter should be configured to 0 (as no HPS traffic can be served in SDLC cells - no resources should then be reserved on AirScale BBpools).

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, min number RRC No DRB
Description: Minimum number of wideband UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection without a DRB establishment (e.g. doing tracking area updates); this parameter is relevant as additional margin for configured maxNumActUE.    On a cell which is configured as supplementary DL carrier (SDLC) this parameter should be configured to 0 (as no TAU traffic needs to be supported in this cell and consequently no resources should then be reserved on AirScale BBpools).

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, upper SR periodicity
Description: Defines the upper limit of the Scheduling Request periodicity to be used in the cell by the PUCCH algorithm.    The configured value expresses the upper SR periodicity allowed in the LNCEL.  If '20 ms' is configured, the BTS uses 10 ms or 20 ms SR periodicity, where for '40 ms' the BTS uses 10 ms, 20 ms or 40 ms SR periodicity.

Parameter name: Activate load-based PUCCH region
Description: This parameter activates feature LTE2664 "Load Based PUCCH Region". The feature is working in the cell only if LTE1130 "Dynamic PUCCH allocation" is activated.    As long as no dedicated load-based PUCCH region profile is assigned in parameter lbPucchRPrId of the APUCCH instance, the default profile values are used.    Note: Only if actAutoPucchAlloc of the parent LNCEL instance is activated, the configured value of actLbPucchReg is considered by the BTS.

Parameter name: Delta cyclic shift used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Delta cyclic shift for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm.

Parameter name: assigned delta cyclic shift in Cat-M PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter prompts delta cyclic shift using PUCCH formats 1/1a for Cat-M UEs. The value is calculated by the system and it is not configurable by operator.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE deltaPUCCH-Shift

Parameter name: ACK/NACK offset used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Indicates the calculated ACK/NACK offset resource from PDCCH CCE by the automatic PUCCH allocation.

Parameter name: assigned ACK/NACK offset in Cat-M PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter prompts Cat-M UEs ACK/NACK offset of the PUCCH resource which is calculated by LTE1130 at cell set up. The value is calculated by the system and it is not configurable by operator.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE n1PUCCH-AN-InfoList-r13

Parameter name: Assigned ACK/NACK offset in Cat-M CE ModeB PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter prompts Cat-M CE ModeB UEs ACK/NACK offset of the PUCCH resource which is calculated at cell set up. The value is calculated by the system and it is not configurable by operator.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE n1PUCCH-AN-InfoList-r13

Parameter name: PUCCH bandwidth for CQI used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b/3. The value is automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm.

Parameter name: PRBs for HARQ Format 3 used in PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter defines how many PRBs are allocated to Format 3 HARQ process when the cell is configured to support carrier aggregation with more than or equal to three component carriers.

Parameter name: PHICH duration used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Indicates the duration of PHICH automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm.

Parameter name: PHICH resource used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Indicates the PHICH resource size automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm.

Parameter name: PRACH frequency offset used in PUCCH allocation
Description: PRACH frequency offset automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm. The algorithm considered the parameter defined in LNCEL prachFreqOff as base, but the real used value in the algorithm is shown in this parameter.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: RI configuration index used in the Scell
Description: This parameter informs about the used Rank Indication (RI) when Dynamic Open Loop or any kind of Closed Loop MIMO is supported in the Scell. When none of those MIMO modes are supported in the Scell, no parameter value will be set by the BTS and is therefore not shown at the management GUI.

Parameter name: RI configuration index used in PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter informs about the used Rank Indication (RI) when Dynamic Open Loop or any kind of Closed Loop MIMO is supported. When none of those MIMO modes are supported in the cell, no parameter value will be set by the BTS and is therefore not shown at the management GUI.

Parameter name: assigned SR offset in Cat-M PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter prompts the offset where the CAT- M dedicated scheduling request region begin. The value is calculated by the system and it is not configurable by operator.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE sr-PUCCH-ResourceIndex

Parameter name: assigned SR periodicity in Cat-M PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter prompts scheduling request periodicity for Cat-M UEs. The value is calculated by the system and it is not configurable by operator.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE sr-ConfigIndex

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Load-based PUCCH region profile identifier
Description: Identifier of the Load-Based PUCCH Region Profile which shall be used for the cell. If no value is specified the configuration in the Load-Based PUCCH Region Default Profile LBPUCCHRDPR will be used for the cell if the functionality is activated.

Parameter name: Required cell capacity by Operator
Description: This parameters shows the cell capacity (in terms of RRC_Connected UE) as required by operator according to the configured parameters.  Therefore, this parameter is calculated by the system on a base of the following operator-configured aPucch parameters:  1. aPucchAddAUeRrHo  2. aPucchAddAUeTcHo  3. aPucchMinNumEmergencySessions (this parameter is optional conditioned to support emergency session activation flag according to today's implementation which is not affected by this feature)  4. aPucchMinNumRrc  5. aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb  6. maxNumActUE  7. aPucchMinNumRrcHps  If actWcdnaLteSharedSpectrum is 'true' and ulChBw is '10 MHz' then the parameter operatorsReqCellCapacity is displayed to operator  If operatorsReqCellCapacity is larger than sysPredefMaxNumActUe then the effective number of RRC_Connected UE supported by the cell is given by this calculation: maxNumActUe + sysPredefMaxNumActUE - operatorsReqCellCapacity; else the RRC_Connected UE supported by the cell is maxNumActUE.

Parameter name: Pucch Arrival Rate Evaluation  Window Length
Description: This parameter activates the option arrival rate based PUCCH region fast expansion introduced as improvement to original LTE2664.    At each second the BTS evaluates if the arrival rate in the cell is above a critical thresholds internally defined, and if yes it triggers an expansion of the PUCCH region to prevent possible cell access blocking.    When the parameter is set to a values larger than 1, the evaluation is still performed at each second but the value is averaged over a range of seconds corresponding to this parameter.    Note: Only if actLbPucchReg is activated, the configured value of pucchArRateEvalWinLength is considered by the BTS.

Parameter name: Selection of PRACH region in automatic PUCCH allocation
Description: Using this parameter, the operator defines the selected PRACH region. If LTE1130 'Dynamic PUCCH allocation' is activated, the system automatically selects the PRACH PRB offset in this region.

Parameter name: Max number of active UE predefined by the system
Description: This parameter shows the maximum number of RCC_Connected UE supported in the cell  - when actWcdmaLteSharedSpectrum is set to 'true' and ulChBw is set to '10 MHz' or  - when actSlimCoexCatM is set to 'true'    (1) When actWcdmaLteSharedSpectrum is set to 'true' and ulChBw is set to '10 MHz' the cell capacity is determined autonomously by the system taking into account the features configured in the cell by the operator.  (1.1) When dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTx' and actDLCAggr is set to 'false', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 1320  (1.2) When dlMimoMode is not set to 'SingleTx' and actDLCAggr is set to 'false', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 660  (1.3) When dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTx' and actDLCAggr is set to 'true' and maxNumScells is equal to '1', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 960  (1.4) When dlMimoMode is not set to 'SingleTx' and actDLCAggr is set to 'true' and maxNumScells is equal to '1', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 480  (1.5) When dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTx' and actDLCAggr is set to 'true' and maxNumScells is more than '1', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 760  (1.6) When dlMimoMode is not set to 'SingleTx' and actDLCAggr is set to 'true' and maxNumScells is more than '1', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 380    (2) When actSlimCoexCatM is set to 'true' the cell capacity is determined autonomously by the system taking into account the features configured in the cell by the operator.  (2.1) When dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTx' and 2 PRB are required for Msg3 and nbIoTMode is 'disabled', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 960  (2.2) When dlMimoMode is not set to 'SingleTx' and 2 PRB are required for Msg3 and nbIoTMode is 'disabled', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 480  (2.3) When dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTx' and 2 PRB are required for Msg3 and nbIoTMode is 'inband', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 480  (2.4) When dlMimoMode is not set to 'SingleTx' and 2 PRB are required for Msg3 and nbIoTMode is 'inband', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 240  (2.5) When dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTx' and 3 PRB are required for Msg3 and nbIoTMode is 'disabled', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 480  (2.6) When dlMimoMode is not set to 'SingleTx' and 3 PRB are required for Msg3 and nbIoTMode is 'disabled', then sysPredefMaxNumActUe = 240    Note: The number of PRB dedicated to Msg3 depends on configuration of raSmallMcsUl and raSmallVolUl.    (3) If operatorsReqCellCapacity is larger than sysPredefMaxNumActUe then the effective number of RRC_Connected UE supported by the cell is given by this calculation:  maxNumActUE + sysPredefMaxNumActUe - operatorsReqCellCapacity;  else the RRC_Connected UE supported by the cell is maxNumActUE
