Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH configuration identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC APUCCH_TDD.  It uniquely identifies a APUCCH_TDD instance.

Parameter name: Add Number Active Ues Radio Reason Handover
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions):  - for 10 MHz bandwidth 0..550 (recommended: 20)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..800 (recommended: 30)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..630 (recommended: 20)  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..192 (recommended: 10)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..400 (recommended: 15)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions):  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..300 (recommended: 10)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 20)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..1200 (recommended: 30)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and Massive MIMO activation and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS.    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Add Number Active Ues Time Critical Handover
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions):  - for 10MHz bandwidth 0..550 (recommended: 30)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..800 (recommended: 45)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..630 (recommended: 30)  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..192 (recommended: 10)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..400 (recommended: 20)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions):  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..300 (recommended: 15)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 30)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..1200 (recommended: 45)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and Massive MIMO activation and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS.    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, min num. emergency sessions
Description: Minimum number reserved for Emergency Sessions.  This margin increases the thresholds for active UEs, active DRBs and active QCI1-DRBs in the cell. Please note that active QCI1-DRBs thresholds are not considered when actEnhAcAndGbrServices is true.    Note:  - Any change of actEmerCallRedir or actIMSEmerSessR9 will only be applied in case of other activities leading to LNCEL lock.  - The configured value of this parameter may have impact on the minimum expansion of dynamic PUCCH (aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb + max(aPucchAddAUeRrHo, aPucchAddAUeTcHo) +aPucchMinNumEmergencySessions +aPucchMinNumRrcHps shall be less or equal to 30 in order to allow a minimum expansion level for PUCCH).

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, min number RRC
Description: Minimum allocated number of UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection.  This is needed for AirScale where resources may be shifted from one cell to the other where needed; for dynamic PUCCH this parameter can control the minimum PUCCH configuration per cell.    In case baseband pooling is activated the value of these parameters may be internally adapted by the system based on the number of cells allocated to a baseband pool.

Parameter name: APUCCH min. number RRC connections for HPS
Description: This parameter defines the minimum number of reserved RRC connections for high priority sessions.  This margin increases the thresholds for RRC connections and active UEs in the cell in case of requested high priority traffic (public safety).    Notes:  - This margin will only be used if LTE4868 Admission control to differentiate HPA and Emergency handling is activated.  - The configured value of this parameter may have impact on the minimum expansion of dynamic PUCCH (aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb + max(aPucchAddAUeRrHo, aPucchAddAUeTcHo) +aPucchMinNumEmergencySessions +aPucchMinNumRrcHps shall be less or equal to 30 in order to allow a minimum expansion level for PUCCH).

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, min number RRC No DRB
Description: Minimum number of UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection without a DRB establishment (e.g. doing tracking area updates); this parameter is relevant as additional margin for configured maxNumActUE.

Parameter name: Automatic PUCCH allocation, upper SR periodicity
Description: Defines the upper limit of the Scheduling Request periodicity to be used in the cell by the PUCCH algorithm.    The configured value expresses the upper SR periodicity allowed in the LNCEL.  If '20 ms' is configured, the BTS uses 10 ms or 20 ms SR periodicity, where for '40 ms' the BTS uses 10 ms, 20 ms or 40 ms SR periodicity.    Note:  For TDD Subframe assignment 0, i.e. tddFrameConf is set to '0'(sa0), where aPucchSrPeriodUpperLimit is configured to '20 ms' or '40 ms', the BTS uses 10 ms or 20 ms SR periodicity .

Parameter name: Activate load-based PUCCH region
Description: This parameter activates feature LTE2664 "Load Based PUCCH Region". The feature is working in the cell only if LTE1130 "Dynamic PUCCH allocation" is activated.    As long as no dedicated load-based PUCCH region profile is assigned in parameter lbPucchRPrId of the APUCCH instance, the default profile values are used.    Note: Only if actAutoPucchAlloc of the parent LNCEL instance is activated, the configured value of actLbPucchReg is considered by the BTS.

Parameter name: Delta cyclic shift used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Delta cyclic shift for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm.

Parameter name: ACK/NACK offset used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Indicates the calculated ACK/NACK offset resource from PDCCH CCE by the automatic PUCCH allocation.

Parameter name: PUCCH bandwidth for CQI used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b/3. The value is automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm.

Parameter name: PRBs for HARQ Format 3 used in PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter defines how many PRBs are allocated to Format 3 HARQ process when the cell is configured to support carrier aggregation with more than or equal to three component carriers.

Parameter name: PHICH duration used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Indicates the duration of PHICH automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm.

Parameter name: PHICH resource used in PUCCH allocation
Description: Indicates the PHICH resource size automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm.

Parameter name: PRACH frequency offset used in PUCCH allocation
Description: PRACH frequency offset automatically assigned by the PUCCH algorithm. The algorithm considers the parameter defined in LNCEL prachFreqOff as base, but the real used value in the algorithm is shown in this parameter.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Load-based PUCCH region profile identifier
Description: Identifier of the Load-Based PUCCH Region Profile which shall be used for the cell. If no value is specified the configuration in the Load-Based PUCCH Region Default Profile LBPUCCHRDPR will be used for the cell if the functionality is activated.

Parameter name: PUCCH format 3 support for 2 CC CA
Description: This parameter configures the PUCCH format 3 support for 2CC CA configurations for TDD cells.  If the value is configured to 'true' the BTS uses 4 PF3 PRBs at cell setup. If the parameter is configured to value 'false' the BTS won't configure any PF3 PRB at cell setup.  In the case of 3CC CA, the BTS always uses fixed 4 PF3 PRBs.    The parameter is applicable for FSMF as well as AirScale.

Parameter name: Selection of PRACH region in automatic PUCCH allocation
Description: Using this parameter, the operator defines the selected PRACH region. If LTE1130 'Dynamic PUCCH allocation' is activated, the system automatically selects the PRACH PRB offset in this region.

Parameter name: ARPPR identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC ARPPR, it uniquely identifies an instance of the ARPPR configuration.

Parameter name: ARP based Admission Control Offset list
Description: This parameter specifies a list of ARP based admission control offsets within a profile for wideband UEs.  This list contains a mapping table which maps ARP priority values to ARP offsets.

Parameter name: ARP admission control offset
Description: This parameter specifies an admission control offset (=percentage value) per ARP priority level how many resources may be given to this ARP based admission request in relation to the total amount of available resources (e.g. offset = 50% then the request will only get up to 50% of the total available resources, offset = 85% then the request will only get up to 85% of the total available resources ). An ARP offset with a value lower than 100% leads to a static resource reservation for ARP values requesting resources with a higher offset (e.g. for emergency or HPA requests). The ARP offset handling is done in radio - and in transport admission control. ARP based preemption is triggered in radio AC when thresholds are reached as specified in earlier ARP based AC feature;    It should be clear that low ARP offset configurations will lead to a high admission rejection for that particular ARP(s) or possibly to high number of resource preemptions!    Special case: ARP offset = 0%:  In case the operator configures an ARP value with an offset = 0 then this service represented by this ARP value is not served at all in this cell (gets 0% of the available resources).

Parameter name: ARP priority level
Description: This parameter specifies ARP priority level uniquely, with a range between 1 to 15 and every ARP priority level referring to the related ARP offset.  DRB Admission request from core network may have ARP priority level assigned in order to apply prioritization during resource admission and possibly apply preemption in case of lacking resources. Value 15 means 'no priority'. Values between 1 and 14 are ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e., 1 is the highest and 14 the lowest.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Baseband pool allocation identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC BBPOOLALLOC.  It uniquely identifies a BBPOOLALLOC instance.

Parameter name: Baseband pool allocation mode
Description: Defines the baseband pool allocation mode.  In 'automatic' mode the cell is allocated by eNB according to allocation priorities and logical groups configured with parameters 'bbPoolAllocPrioList' and 'bbPoolLogicalGroupId'. In 'manual' mode the cell is allocated to the baseband pool which is configured with parameter 'bbPoolTargetId'.  Manual mode cannot be configured with the very first commissioning because BBPOOL instances will be autonomously created by eNB after first eNB startup.

Parameter name: Baseband pool logical group ID
Description: Assigns the cell to a logical baseband pool. In 'automatic' mode eNB will assign cells with same logical group ID to the same baseband pool and cells with different logical group ID to different baseband pools. If the parameter is omitted the cell can be assigned to any pool.  The parameter is not relevant if bbPoolAllocMode is set to ' manual'.    If the logical group ID shall be considered for baseband pool allocation the criterion 'Logical group' must be configured in bbPoolAllocPrioList.

Parameter name: Target baseband pool ID
Description: Defines the physical baseband pool (bbPoolId) the cell shall be allocated to.  The parameter is not relevant if bbPoolAllocMode is set to ' automatic'.    Configuration hint:  eNB performs HW detection and as result all detected baseband modules become visible as BBMOD instances. Furthermore eNB creates BBPOOL instances related to the detected BBMOD instances. Via Element Manager or NetAct Configurator the existing BBPOOL instances and their IDs (bbPoolId) can be checked. The list of valid bbPoolTargetIds corresponds to these bbPoolIds. For a cell this list is further restricted to the bbPoolIds which are related to the BBMOD instance which serves the cell.  Please note that manual BB pool allocation is meant for special cases and not recommended for customer configurations.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Hosting baseband pool ID
Description: ID of the baseband pool the cell is allocated to.    If parameter has no value, it means that the cell is not allocated to a baseband pool (e.g. because no resources are available).

Parameter name: Hosting physical layer pool (L1) ID
Description: ID of the physical layer pool (L1) the cell is allocated to.    If parameter has no value, it means that the cell is not allocated to a L1 pool (e.g. because no resources are available).

Parameter name: A3 offset
Description: Margin for the Event A3 for SCell discovery measurement- A neighbor becomes offset better than the PCell.

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the Event A3 SCell discovery measurement must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: A3 trigger quantity
Description: Defines which quantity (RSRP or RSRQ) the UE has to use for triggering an event A3 SCell discovery measurement report at the frequency for which the default CA profile is applied.

Parameter name: A6 offset
Description: Margin for Event A6 - a neighbor cell becomes better than an SCell.

Parameter name: A6 report interval
Description: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are sent as long as the specific criteria for the measurement event A6 are met.

Parameter name: A6 time to trigger
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the measurement event A6 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Enable measurements for A3 event
Description: This parameter controls the enabling/disabling of the A3 measurements for SCell discovery and corresponding A3 event reporting.  Setting this flag conditions the way how the SCells to add are selected:  - If the A3 measurement has been enabled on a frequency that the UE can measure without measurement gaps, SCells on such frequency will be added only if detected by the UE with sufficient quality (i.e. with power and quality level above the defined scellMeasThreshRsrq and scellMeasThreshRsrp parameter values).  - If the A3 measurement for SCell discovery has been not enabled on a frequency, SCells on such frequency are added blindly.  - If the A3 measurement for SCell discovery has been enabled on a frequency that the UE cannot measure without measurement gaps, SCells on such frequency are added blindly only if there is no choice from the previous two cases.    The events A3 for SCell discovery measurement are configured with 'reportOnLeave' and 'reportAmount=1'.

Parameter name: Enable measurements for A6 event
Description: This parameter controls the enabling/disabling of the measurements and corresponding reporting for A6 event.

Parameter name: Enable PCell swap based on frequency layer priorities
Description: This is a flag to enable or disable a PCell swap based on the frequency layer (EARFCN) priorities defined in the parameters pFreqPrio and sFreqPrio.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of offset a3Offset neighbor becomes offset better than serving cell
Description: Related hysteresis of Margin for the Event A3 SCell discovery measurement - a neighbor becomes offset better than the PCell.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of offset a6Offset neighbor cell
Description: Related Hysteresis of Margin for Event A6 - a neighbor cell becomes better than an SCell.

Parameter name: Maximal number of MIMO layer in CA for FDD
Description: The parameter configures the maximal supported number of MIMO layers for PCells when carrier aggregation is activated.  The limit is for the UEs (camped on FDD PCell) and applicable for all FDD PCells the eNB serves.

Parameter name: Maximal number of MIMO layer in CA for TDD
Description: The parameter configures the maximal supported number of MIMO layers for PCells when carrier aggregation is activated.  The limit is for the UEs (camped on TDD PCell) and applicable for all TDD PCells the eNB serves.

Parameter name: Maximum number of blind SCell swaps
Description: Maximum number of blind SCell swaps on the secondary cell (SCell) frequency layer this profile applies to.

Parameter name: SCell frequency layer priority for carrier aggregation
Description: sFreqPrio enters into the comparison between candidate SCells. This comparison is based on a measure of the average load, and can be biased towards a cell by giving it (or its frequency layer) a higher priority.  It is also used in the relative comparison to pFreqPrio in the PCell swap algorithm.  Use sFreqPrio = 1 (default) for highest priority, sFreqPrio = 10000 for lowest priority.    Note: To prioritize unlicensed against licensed cells, their sFreqPrio values shall be at least one decade apart (for example, CADPRLAA-sFreqPrio configured to be within [1-10], and CADPR-sFreqPrio or CAPR-sFreqPrio within [100-10000]).

Parameter name: SCell measurement threshold for RSRP
Description: RSRP threshold for filtering candidate SCells out of the cells reported by the UE via an event A3 SCell discovery measurement.

Parameter name: SCell measurement threshold for RSRQ
Description: RSRQ threshold for filtering candidate SCells out of the cells reported by the UE via an event A3 SCell discovery measurement.

Parameter name: SCell PDCCH outer loop link adaptation
Description: The parameter selects the PDCCH outer loop link adaptation (OLLA) solution in an SCell for a UE with an activated SCell.  If the parameter is set to 'disabled' then the PDCCH OLLA will be disabled in the SCell.  If the parameter is set to 'enabledPcellBased' then the FDD/LAA SCell's PDCCH OLLA will use pdcchCqiShift from the UE's PCell and the TDD SCell's PDCCH OLLA will calculate its pdcchCqiShift as per legacy solution.  If the parameter is set to 'enabledScellBased' then the SCell's PDCCH OLLA will calculate its pdcchCqiShift based on:  1.PUSCH TX/DTX detection (if the UE's SCell is DL+UL), and  2.the UE's unambiguous ACK, NACK and DTX feedback related to the SCell's PDSCH, and  3.the UE's ambiguous NACK/DTX feedback related to SCell's PDSCH which will be interpreted either as NACK or as DTX depending on the measured SCell's PDSCH BLER.  Note: this parameter replaces disableSCellPDCCHOlLa. scellPdcchOlLa set to 'enabledPcellBased' is equivalent to disableSCellPDCCHOlLa set to 'false' and scellPdcchOlLa set to 'disabled' is equivalent to disableSCellPDCCHOlLa set to 'true'.

Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC CADPRCBRS.  It uniquely identifies an instance of the Carrier Aggregation Default Profile for Citizens Broadcast Radio Service (CADPRCBRS).

Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the measurement event A6 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Carrier Aggregation generic eNB configuration
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC CAGENB.  It uniquely identifies a CAGENB instance.  This MOC contains configuration to be used for CA features and EN-DC aware idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced CA band combination selection
Description: This parameter activates enhanced CA band combination selection only in networks that support the following 3GPP bands: 1, 3, 7, 28, and 40. This enhanced algorithm applies during CA one-step addition only.  If this parameter is:  'off': The legacy lexicographical algorithm is applied. The eNB chooses the best candidate combination from band combinations ordered in lexicographical manner of corresponding SCells.  'throughput_and_aggregate_NLCV': An enhanced CA band selection algorithm is applied in which the eNB selects the candidate combination with the highest throughput while also taking the SCells' aggregate extended biased NLCV into account.  'aggregate_NLCV': An enhanced CA band selection algorithm is applied in which the eNB selects the best candidate combination with the lowest aggregate extended biased NLCV.

Parameter name: eNB list for CA cluster
Description: This structure defines the properties of the eNBs belonging to one CA cluster.    Note:  If the eNB hosts no Pcells in the inter-eNB CA cluster via sRIO (numSrioLinks set to '1'), the lnBtsId doesn't need to be specified.  If at least one eNB in the inter-eNB CA cluster is connected via X2 (numSrioLinks set to '0'), the lnBtsId must be configured in all items of caClusterEnbList.

Parameter name: BTS ID of CA partner eNB
Description: This parameter defines the BTS ID of the CA partner eNB this instance of the structure caClusterEnbList refers to.    Note:  If the eNB hosts no Pcells in the inter-eNB CA cluster via sRIO (numSrioLinks set to '1'), the lnBtsId doesn't need to be specified.  If at least one eNB in the inter-eNB CA cluster is connected via X2 (numSrioLinks set to '0'), the lnBtsId must be configured in all items of caClusterEnbList.

Parameter name: Number of SRIO links
Description: This parameter defines the number of SRIO links that shall be configured towards the peer eNB in this CA cluster this instance of CAGENB-caClusterEnbList is referring to.    Note:  If the eNB hosts no Pcells in the inter-eNB CA cluster via sRIO (numSrioLinks set to '1'), the lnBtsId doesn't need to be specified.  If at least one eNB in the inter-eNB CA cluster is connected via X2 (numSrioLinks set to '0'), the lnBtsId must be configured in all items of caClusterEnbList.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation SCell scheduler weight factor minimum CQI
Description: This parameter is the default UE minimum CQI on an SCell that is required for the eNB to apply the configured CA SCell scheduler weight factor.  It is ignored by a PCell if actCaScellSchedWeightFactor is set to 'false' in the LNCEL instance. This parameter applies for an SCell only if the caScellSchedWtFactMinCqi parameter in the corresponding CAREL instance is not configured.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Fast load balancing configuration - MCS threshold for fast load balance
Description: eNB only selects such UE which estimated MCS in the target cell is no less than fastLoadBalanceMcsThresh to do fast load balance. If the estimated MCS of the UE in the target cell is less than fastLoadBalanceMcsThresh, this UE can't be selected for fast load balance.

Parameter name: Max. DL CA configuration for UL CA
Description: This parameter describes the maximum amount of downlink component carriers that shall be used together with uplink carrier aggregation.

Parameter name: Penalty for X2/C2-connected SCell selection
Description: Describes the penalty for X2/C2-connected SCell selection. The higher the value of nlcvDeltaX2C2, the bigger the penalty, i.e., the smaller the probability that the cells connected over X2/C2 will be selected when adding a new SCell. Note: C2 is used as interface in cloud BTS (cBTS).

Parameter name: Offset for the PCell UL pathloss threshold for advanced SCell handling
Description: This parameter defines the offset for the threshold for the uplink pathloss in a PCell for the advanced SCell handling.  If the pathloss is greater than the sum of the threshold defined in parameter pcellUlPathlossThresh and this offset, an UL+DL SCell will be downgraded to a DL-only SCell.

Parameter name: PCell UL pathloss threshold for advanced SCell handling
Description: This parameter defines the threshold for the uplink pathloss in a PCell for the advanced SCell handling.  Only if the pathloss is below this value, an SCell is allowed to be added as a DL+UL SCell.

Parameter name: Fast load balancing configuration - PRB usage ratio gap threshold
Description: When the difference value of the PRB usage ratio of two cells is equal or greater than prbUsageRatioGapThresh and the PRB usage ratio of one of those cells is equal or greater than prbUsageRatioHighThresh, eNB is able to provide fast load balance between those cells to balance the PRB usage ratio.

Parameter name: Fast load balancing configuration - PRB usage ratio high threshold
Description: When one cell's PRB usage ratio is equal or greater than prbUsageRatioHighThresh, eNB will try to lower its PRB usage ratio by fast load balance.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation aware idle mode LB configuration for PCells
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC CAILMBP.  It uniquely identifies a CAIMLBP instance.  This MOC contains configuration to be used in advanced CA aware idle mode load balancing and EN-DC aware idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: PCell configuration - Downlink EARFCN of a PCell

Note: ALL combinations of maxNumScells and less SCells with the PCell shall be present in the network. Otherwise, the structured list sCellConfig has to be split across several instances of MOC CAIMLBS sub-ordinated to the same instance of MOC CAIMLBP.

Description: This is a flag to enable or disable a PCell swap based on the frequency layer (EARFCN) priorities defined in the parameters pFreqPrio and sFreqPrio.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of offset a3Offset neighbor becomes offset better than serving cell
Description: Related hysteresis of Margin for the Event A3 SCell discovery measurement - a neighbor becomes offset better than the PCell.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of offset a6Offset neighbor cell
Description: Related Hysteresis of Margin for Event A6 - a neighbor cell becomes better than an SCell.

Parameter name: Maximum number of blind SCell swaps
Description: Maximum number of blind SCell swaps on the secondary cell (SCell) frequency layer this profile applies to.

Parameter name: SCell frequency layer priority for carrier aggregation
Description: sFreqPrio enters into the comparison between two candidate SCells. This comparison is based on a measure of the average load in uplink, and can be biased towards a cell by giving it a higher priority.  It is also used in the relative comparison to pFreqPrio in the PCell swap algorithm.  Use sFreqPrio = 1 (default) for highest priority, sFreqPrio = 10000 for lowest priority.    Note: To prioritize unlicensed against licensed cells, their sFreqPrio values shall be at least one decade apart (for example, CADPRLAA-sFreqPrio configured to be within [1-10], and CADPR-sFreqPrio or CAPR-sFreqPrio within [100-10000]).

Parameter name: SCell measurement threshold for RSRP
Description: RSRP threshold for filtering candidate SCells out of the cells reported by the UE via an event A3 SCell discovery measurement.

Parameter name: SCell measurement threshold for RSRQ
Description: RSRQ threshold for filtering candidate SCells out of the cells reported by the UE via an event A3 SCell discovery measurement.

Parameter name: SCell PDCCH outer loop link adaptation
Description: The parameter selects the PDCCH outer loop link adaptation (OLLA) solution in an SCell for a UE with an activated SCell.  If the parameter is set to 'disabled' then the PDCCH OLLA will be disabled in the SCell.  If the parameter is set to 'enabledPcellBased' then the SCell's FDD/LAA PDCCH OLLA will use pdcchCqiShift from the UE's PCell and the TDD SCell's PDCCH OLLA will calculate its pdcchCqiShift as per legacy solution.  If the parameter is set to 'enabledScellBased' then the SCell's PDCCH OLLA will calculate its pdcchCqiShift based on:  1.PUSCH TX/DTX detection (if the UE's SCell is DL+UL), and  2.the UE's unambiguous ACK, NACK and DTX feedback related to the SCell's PDSCH, and  3.the UE's ambiguous NACK/DTX feedback related to SCell's PDSCH which will be interpreted either as NACK or as DTX depending on the measured SCell's PDSCH BLER.  Note: this parameter replaces disableSCellPDCCHOlLa. scellPdcchOlLa set to 'enabledPcellBased' is equivalent to disableSCellPDCCHOlLa set to 'false' and scellPdcchOlLa set to 'disabled' is equivalent to disableSCellPDCCHOlLa set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation relation identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC CAREL.  It uniquely identifies a CAREL instance.  CAREL creation activates Carrier Aggregation in the related cells.  CAREL is created in the LNCEL that will be P-LNCEL (primary cell for Carrier Aggregation). LNCEL contains lcrId of the S-LNCEL (secondary cell for Carrier Aggregation).  Depending on enableAutoLock and enableGrflShdn settings, LNCEL is automatically locked during plan activation for CAREL creation/deletion.

Parameter name: Beamforming in SCell allowed
Description: This parameter specifies whether beamforming shall be allowed in the SCell or not.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation SCell scheduler weight factor minimum CQI
Description: This is the UE minimum CQI on an SCell that is required for the eNB to apply the configured CA SCell scheduler weight factor. If configured, and if actCaScellSchedWeightFactor is set to 'true' in the parent LNCEL instance, then for the SCell corresponding to this CAREL instance, this value overrides the CAGENB-caScellSchedWtFactMinCqi value.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Local cell resource ID of cell to be aggregated
Description: This parameter is the Local Cell Resource ID of cell to be aggregated.  Aggregate cells considering the following:  - Nokia does not guarantee correct SCell addition in case the band combination is the Nokia supported band combination but not supported by 3GPP TS 36.101  - Nokia does not guarantee correct SCell addition in case the band combination is the Nokia supported band combination and supported by 3GPP TS 36.101 but the channel bandwidths of the cells are not supported by 3GPP in this band combination (section 5.6A.1 in TS 36.101).

Parameter name: BTS ID of the parent eNB of the cell to be aggregated
Description: This parameter is the BTS ID of the parent eNB of the secondary cell (SCell) to be aggregated.    The configuration of the parameter shall be done in the PCell when the SCell is configured in another BTS of the inter-eNB carrier aggregation cluster.  Aggregate cells considering the following:  Nokia does not guarantee correct SCell addition in case the band combination is a Nokia supported band combination but not supported by 3GPP TS 36.101    Nokia does not guarantee correct SCell addition in case the band combination is a Nokia supported band combination and supported by 3GPP TS 36.101 but the channel bandwidths of the cells are not supported by 3GPP in this band combination (section 5.6A.1 in TS 36.101)

Parameter name: Maximal number of supported MIMO layers
Description: This parameter defines the maximal number of supported MIMO layer for the SCell.    For SCells handled at the connected eNB in inter-eNB CA configurations, limitations regarding the number of supported SCells with 4-layer are possible. Please refer to the official supported configurations.  In case the link capacity in inter-eNB configurations is exceeded, performance degradations will happen.

Parameter name: PCell swap allowed
Description: This is a flag to allow or forbid swapping the PCell owning this instance of CAREL with the SCell identified by this instance of CAREL.

Parameter name: SCell priority
Description: This parameter defines the priority order in which this SCell shall be used in blind SCell configuration. The smaller the value the higher the priority

Parameter name: SCell scheduler weight factor for downlink
Description: This parameter is the scheduler weight factor that is applied in the downlink to an SCell activated on the PCell. Increasing the weight factor greater than 1 increases the SCell downlink scheduling priority relative to the PCell and other activated SCells. A weight factor less than 1 decreases the SCell downlink scheduling priority relative to the PCell and other activated SCells.

Parameter name: CATMBPR identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC CATMBPR, it uniquely identifies an instance of the CATMBPR configuration.

Parameter name: AMC delta C step size up of Cat-M in CE modeB
Description: This parameter defines the stepsize up value for the DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.  Stepsize down value for delta C can be calculated by using this parameter and DL/UL target BLER.

Parameter name: AMC initial delta C of Cat-M in CE modeB
Description: This parameter defines the initial value for DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.

Parameter name: AMC maximum delta C of Cat-M in CE modeB
Description: This parameter defines the maximum limit for the DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation value delta C for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.

Parameter name: AMC minimum delta C of Cat-M in CE modeB
Description: This parameter defines the minimum limit for DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation value delta C for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Assigned number of RA preambles for Cat-M CE level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the number of RA preambles per cell that are reserved for Cat-M UEs in CE level 2 in case actOptRootSeq is set different to 'none'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Initial MCS in downlink of Cat-M in CE level 2
Description: This parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PDSCH other than BCCH, PCH or random access messages for Cat-M UEs in CE level 2.  The range of MCS value for Cat-M is defined by 3GPP 36.213 table 7.1.7.1-1: "Modulation and TBS index table for PDSCH"

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Initial MCS in uplink of Cat-M in CE level 2
Description: This parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PUSCH other than random access message 3 for Cat-M UEs in CE level 2.  The range of MCS value for Cat-M is defined by 3GPP 36.213 table 8.6.1-1: "Modulation, TBS index and redundancy version table for PUSCH"

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Initial amount of PRBs in uplink of Cat-M in CE level 2
Description: This Parameter defines the initial amount of maximum PRBs in uplink for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Maximum number of repetition for MPDCCH(UE-SS) for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum numbers of repetitions for M-PDCCH for DL and UL grants of Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NumRepetition-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(UE-SS) for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of M-PDCCH to determine the repetition number of M-PDCCH for the DL and UL grants for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-1B or DCI Format 6-0B.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(Paging) for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of paging message on M-PDCCH for Cat-M UEs mapping to paging CE Level 2.  This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-4 and Table 7.1.11-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(Random Access) for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of M-PDCCH to determine the repetition number of M-PDCCH for random access messages(Msg2, HARQ for Msg3, Msg4) for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-1B or DCI Format 6-0B.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Number of PRACH repetitions per attempt for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter defines the number of PRACH repetitions per preamble attempts for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.    Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE numRepetitionPerPreambleAttempt-r13

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of PDSCH for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PDSCH to determine the repetition number of PDSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-1B.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of Msg4 on PDSCH for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the Msg4 repetition level on PDSCH to determine the repetition number of random access Msg4 for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-1B.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of PDSCH(Paging) for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of paging message on PDSCH for Cat-M UEs mapping to paging CE Level 2.  This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212 , 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - PRACH Starting subframe for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the PRACH starting subframe for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE prach-StartingSubframe-r13.  If it is set to '0', the optional IE "prach-StartingSubframe-r13" will be dropped in SIB2-BR message for Cat-M UE in CE level2.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Maximum number of PRACH preamble transmission attempts for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of preamble transmission attempts for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE maxNumPreambleAttemptCE-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition number of PUCCH for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition number of the PUCCH Format 1 for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE pucch-NumRepetitionCE-format1-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition number of PUCCH for HARQ feedback to Msg4 in Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the number of PUCCH repetitions of the HARQ feedback in response to the Msg4 for Cat-M in CE Level 2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 RRC IE 'pucch-NumRepetitionCE-Msg4-Level2-r1'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of PUSCH for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PUSCH to determine the repetition number of PUSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-0B.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 8.2b.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of Msg3 on PUSCH for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PUSCH to determine the repetition number of Msg3 on PUSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the RAR for Msg3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 6.2d.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Maximum contention resolution timer for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum contention resolution timer for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE mac-ContentionResolutionTimer-r13    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.    Note: It is recommended to set raContResoTimrCatM to '960ms' if numCELevelCatM is set to '3' or '4'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Number of random access preambles for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the number of RA preambles per cell that are reserved for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, RACH-ConfigCommon, firstPreamble-r13, lastPreamble-r13.    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 2 Table for Cat-M - Random access response window size for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter defines the random access response window size for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, RACH-ConfigCommon, RA-ResponseWindowSize-r13.    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.    Note: It is recommended to set raRespWinSizeCatM to '400ms' if numCELevelCatM is set to '3' or '4'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Assigned number of RA preambles for Cat-M CE level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the number of RA preambles per cell that are reserved for Cat-M UEs in CE level 3 in case actOptRootSeq is set different to 'none'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Initial MCS in downlink of Cat-M in CE level 3
Description: This parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PDSCH other than BCCH, PCH or random access messages for Cat-M UEs in CE level 3.  The range of MCS value for Cat-M is defined by 3GPP 36.213 table 7.1.7.1-1: "Modulation and TBS index table for PDSCH"

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Initial MCS in uplink of Cat-M in CE level 3
Description: This parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PUSCH other than random access message 3 for Cat-M UEs in CE level 3.  The range of MCS value for Cat-M is defined by 3GPP 36.213 table 8.6.1-1: "Modulation, TBS index and redundancy version table for PUSCH"

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Initial amount of PRBs in uplink of Cat-M in CE level 3
Description: This parameter defines the initial amount of maximum PRBs in uplink for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Maximum number of repetition for MPDCCH(UE-SS) for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum numbers of repetitions for M-PDCCH for DL and UL grants of Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NumRepetition-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(UE-SS) for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of M-PDCCH to determine the repetition number of M-PDCCH for the DL and UL grants for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-1B or DCI Format 6-0B.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(Paging) for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of paging message on M-PDCCH for Cat-M UEs mapping to paging CE Level 3.  This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-4 and Table 7.1.11-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(Random Access) for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of M-PDCCH to determine the repetition number of M-PDCCH for random access messages(Msg2, HARQ for Msg3, Msg4) for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-1B or DCI Format 6-0B.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Number of PRACH repetitions per attempt for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter defines the number of PRACH repetitions per preamble attempts for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.    Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE numRepetitionPerPreambleAttempt-r13

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of PDSCH for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PDSCH to determine the repetition number of PDSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-1B.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of Msg4 on PDSCH for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the Msg4 repetition level on PDSCH to determine the repetition number of random access Msg4 for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-1B.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of PDSCH(Paging) for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of paging message on PDSCH for Cat-M UEs mapping to paging CE Level 3.  This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212 , 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - PRACH Starting subframe for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the PRACH starting subframe for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE prach-StartingSubframe-r13.  If it is set to '0', the optional IE "prach-StartingSubframe-r13" will be dropped in SIB2-BR message for Cat-M UE in CE level3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Maximum number of PRACH preamble transmission attempts for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of preamble transmission attempts for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE maxNumPreambleAttemptCE-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition number of PUCCH for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition number of the PUCCH Format 1 for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE pucch-NumRepetitionCE-format1-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition number of PUCCH for HARQ feedback to Msg4 in Cat-M CE Level3
Description: This parameter specifies the number of PUCCH repetitions of the HARQ feedback in response to the Msg4 for Cat-M in CE Level 3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 RRC IE 'pucch-NumRepetitionCE-Msg4-Level3-r13'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of PUSCH for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PUSCH to determine the repetition number of PUSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-0B.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 8.2b.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of Msg3 on PUSCH for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PUSCH to determine the repetition number of Msg3 on PUSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the RAR for Msg3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 6.2d.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Maximum contention resolution timer for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum contention resolution timer for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE mac-ContentionResolutionTimer-r13    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.    Note: It is recommended to set raContResoTimrCatM to '960ms' if numCELevelCatM is set to '4'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Number of random access preambles for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the number of RA preambles per cell that are reserved for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, RACH-ConfigCommon, firstPreamble-r13, lastPreamble-r13.    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 3 Table for Cat-M - Random access response window size for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter defines the random access response window size for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, RACH-ConfigCommon, RA-ResponseWindowSize-r13.    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.    Note: It is recommended to set raRespWinSizeCatM to '400ms' if numCELevelCatM is set to '4'.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: C-Plane inactivity timer for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter defines the time period for the indication of the UE-associated S1 logical connection inactivity DL and UL directions for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.  C-Plane inactivity timer monitors S1AP interface activity of UE-associated S1 logical connection traffic for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB. It's started with Cat-M UEs in CE modeB UE-associated S1 logical connection establishment and restarted on reception or sending S1AP message that contains NAS PDU IE.

Parameter name: Default number of paging repetition for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the default number of MPDCCH paging repetitions for Cat-M CE ModeB capable UEs if not presented in the paging message from MME.  This information is optional IE and is provided transparently by the serving eNB to the MME at transition to ECM_IDLE together with the respective cell identifier and is provided to the E-UTRAN during paging.

Parameter name: DL target BLER of Cat-M in CE modeB
Description: This parameter defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) for downlink Link Adaptation in percents used for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.

Parameter name: Maximum number of Msg3 HARQ transmissions for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in UL that is configured for message 3 of the contention-based random access procedure for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE maxHARQ-Msg3Tx.  But due to asynchronized HARQ for Cat-M UEs, the RRC IE 'maxHARQ-Msg3Tx' will be ignored by Cat-M UEs, therefore this parameter configuration is only used by eNB internally.

Parameter name: Maximum number of Msg4 HARQ transmissions for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in DL that is configured for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB at initial access (Message 4).

Parameter name: Maximum number of HARQ transmission in DL for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in DL that is configured for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.

Parameter name: Maximum number of HARQ transmission in UL for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in UL that is configured for Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE maxHARQ-Tx.  But due to asynchronized HARQ for Cat-M UEs, the RRC IE 'maxHARQ-Tx' will be ignored by Cat-M UEs, therefore this parameter configuration is only used by eNB internally.

Parameter name: Inactivity timer for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter defines the time period for the indication of the Cat-M UEs in CE modeB inactivity in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Maximum number of Cat-M CE ModeB RRC Connections
Description: This parameter specifies the threshold for the maximum number of Cat-M CE ModeB UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection.

Parameter name: Maximum number of repetition for MPDCCH(Random Access) for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of repetitions for MPDCCH for RAR, HARQ of Msg3 and Msg4 of Cat-M UEs in CE ModeB.  This parameter is applicable for both CE Level 2 and CE Level 3, i.e., CE Level 2 and CE Level 3 have same MPDCCH Rmax for Cat-M RAR, HARQ of Msg3 and Msg4 grant.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.211 and TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NumRepetition-RA-r13.

Parameter name: Maximum attempt number for paging message within current coverage level for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the unsuccessful Paging Attempt threshold for Cat-M CE ModeB capable UEs. eNB should apply the higher configured paging CE level parameters for MPDCCH and PDSCH in case of unsuccessful Paging Attempt greater than or equal to this.    It is recommended to set to value '3'.

Parameter name: Paging coverage level increase step size for Cat-M CE ModeB capable UEs
Description: This parameter specifies Paging coverage level step size to increase when unsuccessful Paging Attempt is greater than or equal to pagAttCeIncreaseModeBCatM for Cat-M CE ModeB capable UEs .  CE level step increase is not including CE levels with the same paging repetitions configured. Only CE levels with different repetitions are considered as increase step.    It is recommended to set to value '1'.

Parameter name: Paging send CE Mode priority for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies priorities for Cat-M paging records.  If this parameter is set to value 'CE ModeA', then CE ModeA UE is prioritized over CE ModeB UE for Paging .  If this parameter is set to value 'all equal', then CE ModeA UE and CE ModeB UE have the same priority for Paging.  It is recommended to set pagCEModePrioCatM to 'all equal'.

Parameter name: Maximum numbers of repetition for PDSCH of Cat-M in CE modeB
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of repetitions for PDSCH of Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and the optional IE pdsch-maxNumRepetitionCEmodeB-r13.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 3 - Poll PDU for DRB Cat-M
Description: This parameter Poll PDU defines the number of RLC PDUs that are sent on a logical channel before the RLC polling bit is set.  This parameter specifies the parameter pollPDU of [36.331]

Parameter name: Maximum numbers of repetition for PUSCH of Cat-M in CE modeB
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of repetitions for PUSCH of Cat-M UEs in CE modeB.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE pusch-maxNumRepetitionCEmodeB-r13.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: RRC guard timer radio bearer management for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This timer is started when an RRC message for setup, modification or release of a radio bearer is sent to the Cat-M UEs in CE ModeB. When the timer expires, the corresponding procedure is aborted.

Parameter name: SR prohibited timer for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter controls the minimum separation in time between consecutive Scheduling Request transmissions by the Cat-M UEs in CE ModeB.  It can be used to prevent unwanted repetitions of SRs. The parameter is expressed in number of SR periods. It is sent to the UE in the RRC IE sr-ProhibitTimer-r9.  Refer to 36.321 sec.5.4.4    srProhibitTimerCatM = 0 means no minimum interval (SRs can be sent at every SR period).

Parameter name: SRB inactivity timer for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter defines the time period for the indication of the Cat-M UEs in CE modeB inactivity on signaling radio bearer in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Timer T300 for Cat-M support CE modeB
Description: Timer T300 for Cat-M supervises the RRC connection establishment procedure of Cat-M UEs support CE modeB.  Timer T300 supervises the RRC connection establishment procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionSetup or RRCConnectionReject message, cell re-selection and upon abortion of connection establishment by upper layers    At expiry: Perform the actions as specified in 36.331, 5.3.3.6    Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: t300-v1310

Parameter name: Timer T301 for Cat-M support CE modeB
Description: Timer T301 for Cat-M supervises the RRC connection re-establishment procedure of Cat-M UEs support CE modeB.  Timer T301 supervises the RRC connection re-establishment procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionReestabilshmentRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionReestablishment or RRCConnectionReestablishmentReject message as well as when the selected cell becomes unsuitable    At expiry: Go to RRC_IDLE    Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: t301-v1310

Parameter name: Timer T310 for Cat-M support CE ModeB
Description: Timer T310 for Cat-M supervises the recovery from physical layer problems(Radio Link Failure) of Cat-M UEs support CE modeB.  Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: t310-v1330

Parameter name: PDCP PDU Timer Discard for Cat-M CE ModeB DRB
Description: This parameter indicates the delay before a PDCP PDU along with the corresponding PDCP SDU is discarded from the buffer for Cat-M UEs in CE ModeB. This timer shall be set in a way that the packet delay defined by the QCI characteristics is kept. The timer can be disabled by setting the parameter to infinity.  This parameter specifies the parameter discardTimer of [36.331]

Parameter name: Timer ExtendedWaitTime-r10
Description: tExtendedWaitModeBCatM suppresses the reselection of a cell for a while.  eNB sends this parameter to the Cat-M CE ModeB UE in the message RRC CONNECTION REJECT and RRC CONNECTION RELEASE, and only in case of Delay Tolerant access request. The Cat-M CE ModeB UE will consider access to the cell as barred for the time specified by tExtendedWaitModeBCatM.

Parameter name: Timer min lifetime of half-open RRC connection for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: The minimal time period that the eNB waits for an RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE message after sending a RRC CONNECTION SETUP message for Cat-M UEs in CE ModeB.

Parameter name: Timer missing L2 ack for Cat-M CE ModeB RRC connection release
Description: The maximum time period indicates the time after which the RRC L3 releases the RRC connection for Cat-M CE ModeB call only if no positive acknowledge is received from L2 to the RRC CONNECTION RELEASE message.  This timer has to absorb the potential preceding NAS transmission, which can be approximated via rrcGuardTimerModeBCatM. This timer is reset to 1.25 second upon reception of L1 HARQ ACK of RRC Connection Release, as per 3GPP R2-169034.

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 3 - Timer Poll Retransmit for DRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 3 - Timer Poll Retransmit for SRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 3 - Timer Status Prohibit for DRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity in order to prohibit transmission of a STATUS PDU.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-StatusProhibit of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 3 - Timer Status Prohibit for SRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity in order to prohibit transmission of a STATUS PDU.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-StatusProhibit of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 3 - Timer Reordering for DRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 3 - Timer Reordering for SRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331]

Parameter name: UL target BLER of Cat-M in CE modeB
Description: This parameter defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) for uplink Link Adaptation in percents used for Cat-M UEs in CE ModeB.

Parameter name: Minimum UL transport block size for Cat-M CE modeB
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum UL TBS (segment size) during Cat-M CE ModeB link adaptation.    Units: bits

Parameter name: CATMCEL identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC CATMCEL, it uniquely identifies an instance of the CATMCEL configuration.

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A1 measurement for Cat-M
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the measurement event A1 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A2 event to activate Cat-M intra and inter frequency handover measurement
Description: This parameter specifies the timer to trigger activation of intra and inter frequency measurement for Cat-M.  Duration for which the event A2 must be valid, such that additional Intra and inter frequency measurements are activated.

Parameter name: A3 offset for Cat-M
Description: Handover margin for better cell HO. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the neighbor cell becomes better than the serving cell by the value of the A3 offset. This parameter is used for both RSRP and RSRQ based A3 measurement for Cat-M intra-frequency HO measurements.

Parameter name: A3 offset for QCI1 Cat-M
Description: Handover margin for better cell HO. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the neighbor cell becomes better than the serving cell by the value of the A3 offset. This parameter is used for both RSRP and RSRQ based A3 measurement for Cat-M intra-frequency HO measurements when QCI1 bearer is present.

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger for Cat-M
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the measurement event A3 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report for Cat-M.

Parameter name: AC Barring number of steps for Cat-M
Description: This parameter defines absolute number of ACB thresholds for Cat-M, including: Min, Max and intermediate ACB thresholds.  Operator configures ACB Min and Max thresholds for Cat-M ACB parameters as well as number of steps (inclination of access class barring changes) in which Max ACB threshold settings are reached.    If acbNumStepsCatM=0 that is equal to disabling automatic Cat-M AC barring in that specific cell.    If acbNumStepsCatM=1 that means that Cat-M ACB Max threshold is broadcasted in a single automatic Cat-M ACB step.

Parameter name: Steps of adaptive access class barring per PLMN for Cat-M
Description: This parameter defines absolute number of access barring per PLMN thresholds for Cat-M ,including: Min, Max and intermediate ACB thresholds.  Operator configures Cat-M ACB Min and Max thresholds parameters as well as number of steps (inclination of access class barring changes) in which Max ACB threshold settings are reached.    If acbPlmnNumStepsCatM=0 that is equal to disabling access class barring per PLMN in that specific cell for Cat-M.    If acbPlmnNumStepsCatM=1 that means that Max threshold of Cat-M ACB per PLMN is broadcasted.    Note: If LTE2996 'PLMN Specific Access Class Barring' is deactivated, i.e. actAcBarringPlmn is set to 'false', acbPlmnNumStepsCatM is meaningless.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN access class barring profile identifier for Cat-M
Description: Instance ID of the Cat-M access barring profile for primary PLMN. The primary PLMN ID is unique under eNB, but operator can differentiate the Cat-M access barring profile ID for primary PLMN under each Cat-M cell.

Parameter name: ACB profile identifier for Cat-M
Description: Instance ID of the assigned Cat-M Access Class Barring profile.

Parameter name: ACB or EAB notification via RRC Paging message for CatM
Description: This parameter indicates whether ACB System Information notification or EAB parameter change notification may be sent via RRC Paging message to Cat-M UEs.  If set to 'true', ACB System Information notification or EAB parameter change notification may be sent via RRC Paging message.  If set to 'false', ACB System Information notification or EAB parameter change notification is sent via Direct Indication.

Parameter name: Activate Access Class Barring for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates Static and Automatic Access Class Barring support for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Activation flag for Cat-M AMC
Description: The parameter enables/disables Cat-M UEs link adaptation (LA) algorithm for uplink and downlink respectively. The LA algorithm responsible for selecting the MCS is called Adaptive Modulation and Coding (AMC) for Cat-M UEs.
Range and step: disabled (0), Downlink AMC enabled (1), Uplink AMC enabled (2), Both Downlink and Uplink enabled (3)

Parameter name: Activate Cat-M specific measurement
Description: This parameter activates the functionality for Cat-M specific measurements for A1, A2, A3.

Parameter name: Activate support of conversational voice bearer for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates the support of the conversational voice bearer for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Activate Downlink PCI based Narrowband allocation for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates downlink PCI-based narrowband allocation for Cat-M.  If actDlPciBasedNarBandCatM = true, Cat-M paging MPDSCH must use the same narrow band as Cat-M paging MPDCCH(which is determined by PCI) and this narrow band must not be the narrow band for Cat-M downlink data traffic. This is to avoid the impact of Cat-M paging message to Cat-M data traffic in cell with bandwidth of 5M/10M/15M/20M.  If actDlPciBasedNarBandCatM = false, no restrictions to the relationship of the narrow band of Cat-M paging MPDSCH. Cat-M paging MPDCCH and Cat-M downlink data traffic, these narrow bands can be the same or different.

Parameter name: Activate DRX for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates or deactivates the DRX feature for Cat-M UEs in a cell.

Parameter name: Activate dynamic repetition support of MPDCCH for Cat-M (non-GBR only)
Description: This parameter activates the dynamic repetition support of MPDCCH for Cat-M (non-GBR only).

Parameter name: Activate dynamic repetition support of MPDSCH for Cat-M (non-GBR only)
Description: This parameter activates the dynamic repetition support of MPDSCH for Cat-M (non-GBR only).

Parameter name: Activate dynamic repetition support of MPUSCH for Cat-M (non-GBR only)
Description: This parameter activates the dynamic repetition support of MPUSCH for Cat-M (non-GBR only).

Parameter name: Activate dynamic repetition support of VoLTE for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates the dynamic repetition support of VoLTE for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Activate eDRX in idle mode for LTE-M
Description: Parameter to activate or deactivate extended DRX for LTE-M in idle mode in a cell.  BTS synchronization mode shall be set to PhaseSync or LoosePhaseAndTimeSync in order to have the correct feature functionality.

Parameter name: Activate Extended Access Barring for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates Static and Automatic Extended Access Barring support and broadcast of SIB14-BR for Cat-M.    Note: if Automatic Extended Access Barring is configured then either or both of the following conditions must be fulfilled:  (1) actAutoAcBarring is set to 'true'  (2) eabNumRrcConnAutoCatM structure is configured  otherwise Automatic Extended Access Barring does not work.

Parameter name: Activate the support of HARQ-Ack bundling for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates the support of HARQ-Ack bundling for Rel-14 Cat-M UE in CE mode A.

Parameter name: Activate the support of high number of DL HARQ processes for Cat-M
Description: This parameter enables/disables the support of maximum 8/10 downlink HARQ processes for Rel-14 Cat-M UE in CE mode A.  UE capability to support delayed HARQ-Ack is the precondition for eNB to configure 8/10 HARQ processes in downlink for Rel-14 Cat-M UE.  If UE don't support 10 downlink HARQ processes, the maximum downlink HARQ processes that can be used for it is 8.

Parameter name: Activate high number of Cat-M DL HARQ in slim carrier
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the support of maximum 8 downlink HARQ processes for Cat-M UE of CE mode A in 5 MHz slim carrier cell.  UE capability to support delayed HARQ-Ack is the precondition for eNB to configure 8 HARQ processes in downlink for Rel-14 Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Activate support of IMS emergency sessions for Cat-M UE
Description: This parameter activates the support IMS Emergency sessions for Cat-M UEs.

Parameter name: Activation of idle mode load balancing (IdleLB) for Cat-M
Description: The parameter activates the feature Idle Mode Load Balancing for Cat-M  This flag also activates the following functionalities:  - redistribution of configured share of Cat-M1 UEs between adjacent LTE-M layers using dedicated priorities  - weights controlled LTE-M target layers prioritization, using Weighted Round Robin algorithm (WRR)

Parameter name: Activate Cat-M inter-frequency handover
Description: The parameter activates the inter-frequency handover for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Activate Cat-M intra-frequency handover
Description: The parameter activates the intra-frequency handover for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Activate load based narrowband selection for Cat-M UE
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the function of improved load balancing algorithm for multiple CE ModeA narrowbands.  If this parameter is set to 'true', Cat-M UEs are assigned to the primary NB until the primary NB load reaches the threshold which is defined by parameter loadBasedNBSelThresCatM.

Parameter name: Activate LTE-M Indication to MME
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the function of detection of CAT-M UE during UE Radio Capability retrieval procedure and sending LTE-M Indication in S1AP:UE CAPABILITY INFO INDICATION message to MME (Rel-15).    If UE is CAT-M1 UE then in the S1AP:UE CAPABILITY INFO INDICATION message LTE-M Indication IE is included, when this parameter is set to true. LTE-M Indication IE is available from 3GPP Rel-15 onwards.

Parameter name: Activate multiple HARQ support for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates the multiple HARQ support for Cat-M.  Cat-M1 UE should be able to schedule 2 HARQ processes on DL in a multi-user (multiple RRC connected users per cell) scenario if the trigger conditions are fulfilled.  Cat-M1 UE should be able to schedule 3 HARQ processes on UL in a multi-user (multiple RRC connected users per cell) scenario if the trigger conditions are fulfilled.

Parameter name: Activate the support of max PUSCH TBS for Cat-M in CE mode A
Description: This parameter activate the support of 2984 bits maximum PUSCH TBS for Rel-14 Cat-M UE in CE mode A, and if the MPDCCH corresponding to the PUSCH transmission is located in UE-specific search space, the modulation and TBS index for PUSCH is determined according to table 8.6.1-2A as indicated in 3GPP 36.213, 8.6.1.  If this parameter is set to false, the table 8.6.1-2: Modulation and TBS index table for PUSCH will be used just like Rel-13 Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Activate QCI1 Cat-M specific measurement
Description: This parameter activates the functionality for QCI1 Cat-M specific measurements for A1, A2, A3.

Parameter name: Activate RLF based RRC connection reestablishment for Cat-M
Description: Activates the feature 'Radio Link Failure (RLF) based RRC connection reestablishment (RCR)' for Cat-M

Parameter name: Activate Release Assistance Indication for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the function of RAI (Release Assistance Indication) for Cat-M.  If Cat-M UE is configured with release assistance indication and detects data inactivity then sends indication (BSR=0) to the eNB and if DL is also inactive then the eNB releases the Cat-M UE immediately.

Parameter name: Activate relaxed monitoring for Cat-M UEs
Description: This parameter activates the support of relaxed monitoring for cell re-selection for Cat-M UEs.

Parameter name: Activate Cat-M scheduler bypass function
Description: The parameter activates Cat-M scheduler bypass function and defines Cat-M scheduler bypass behavior during wideband congestion.    The meaning of the values are as follows:  'disabled' means that the Cat-M scheduler bypass function is disabled.  'bypassAllCatM' means that all Cat-M related services will not be scheduled during wideband congestion, Cat-M performance will be severely impacted.  'bypassNonGbrCatM' means that Cat-M non-GBR traffic and their HARQ retransmissions will not be scheduled but Cat-M VoLTE and signaling will be handled normally during wideband congestion.  'bypassQciBasedNonGbrCatM' means that Cat-M non-GBR traffic and their HARQ retransmissions will be scheduled/bypassed based on their QCIs but Cat-M VoLTE and signaling will be handled normally during wideband congestion.

Parameter name: Activate Cat-M selective mobility profiles
Description: The parameter activates the feature 'Selective Mobility Profiles' for Cat-M.    When this parameter is set to 'true' then Cat-M mobility profiles (CATMOPR/CATMODPR) are used to configure HO mobility for Cat-M.  When this parameter is set to 'false':  - if CATMODPR exists, then CATMODPR configuration is used for Cat-M HO mobility.  - CATMOPR configurations are never used.

Parameter name: Activate SF9 Invalid Subframe in LVRB Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates Subframe 9 with paging occasion as Cat-M invalid subframe when localized VRBs are used for SI, paging and RACH messages.  If dlsDciCch is set to 'DCI format 1A'  -if this parameter is set to 'true' , Subframe 9 is set as Cat-M invalid subframe.  -if this parameter is set to 'false' , Subframe 9 is set as Cat-M valid subframe.  The parameter is not used if dlsDciCch is set to 'DCI format 1C'.  Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released if this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: Activate support of UE data inactivity timer for Cat-M
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the support of UE data inactivity timer for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Additional MPDCCH narrowband number for Cat-M CE ModeA
