Description: This parameter specifies the index of the corresponding additional narrowband used in MPDCCH for Cat-M CE ModeA UEs.  This parameter is used by the UE during the call (refer to TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-Narrowband-r13).

Parameter name: Additional PDSCH narrowband number for Cat-M CE ModeA
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the corresponding additional narrowband used in PDSCH for Cat-M CE ModeA UEs.

Parameter name: Additional PUSCH narrowband number for Cat-M CE ModeA
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the corresponding additional narrowband used in PUSCH for Cat-M CE ModeA UEs.

Parameter name: Cell reselection priority for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the cell reselection priority for Cat-M. Absolute priority of the serving frequency for Cat-M.  0 means the lowest priority.

Parameter name: Cat-M RRC connections auto trigger for EAB - Cell Cat-M RRC connections EAB start threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the upper threshold of RRC CONNECTED Cat-M UEs which can trigger ACTIVE RRC_EAB_CATM event on the cell level.  RRC_EAB_CATM event becomes ACTIVE if number of RRC_Connected Cat-M UEs in the cell >= ROUND(cellStartThrCatM * maxNumRrcCatM / 100) AND cellStartTimerCatM expires.  ACTIVE RRC_EAB_CATM event shall start upgrade of Extended Access Barring settings and their broadcast in SIB14-BR message if dynamic EAB ACTIVE state was not started yet.  Note: maxNumRrcCatM is cell level Cat-M RAC limit. Upgrade of Extended Access Barring settings means overwriting Static settings or None EAB IEs.

Parameter name: Cat-M RRC connections auto trigger for EAB - Cell Cat-M RRC connections EAB start timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before triggering ACTIVE RRC_EAB_CATM event on the cell level.  RRC_EAB_CATM event becomes ACTIVE if number of RRC_Connected Cat-M UEs in the cell >= ROUND(cellStartThrCatM * maxNumRrcCatM / 100) AND cellStartTimerCatM expires.  ACTIVE RRC_EAB_CATM event shall start upgrade of Extended Access Barring settings and their broadcast in SIB14-BR message if dynamic EAB ACTIVE state was not started yet.  Note: maxNumRrcCatM is cell level Cat-M RAC limit. Upgrade of Extended Access Barring settings means overwriting Static settings or None EAB IEs.

Parameter name: Cat-M RRC connections auto trigger for EAB - Cell Cat-M RRC connections EAB stop threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the lower threshold of RRC CONNECTED Cat-M UEs which can trigger INACTIVE RRC_EAB_CATM event on the cell level.  RRC_EAB_CATM event becomes INACTIVE if number of RRC_Connected Cat-M UEs in the cell < ROUND(cellStopThrCatM * maxNumRrcCatM / 100) AND cellStopTimerCatM expires.  INACTIVE RRC_EAB_CATM event shall start downgrade of Extended Access Barring settings and stop their broadcast in SIB14-BR message if there's no other ACTIVE Cat-M EAB trigger.  Note: maxNumRrcCatM is cell level Cat-M RAC limit. Downgrade of Extended Access Barring settings means: broadcast of Static settings or None EAB IEs.

Parameter name: Cat-M RRC connections auto trigger for EAB - Cell Cat-M RRC connections EAB stop timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before triggering INACTIVE RRC_EAB_CATM event on the cell level.  RRC_EAB_CATM event becomes INACTIVE if number of RRC_Connected CatM UEs in the cell < ROUND(cellStopThrCatM * maxNumRrcCatM / 100) AND cellStopTimerCatM expires.  INACTIVE RRC_EAB_CATM event shall start downgrade of Extended Access Barring settings and stop their broadcast in SIB14-BR message if there's no other ACTIVE Cat-M EAB trigger.  Note: maxNumRrcCatM is cell level Cat-M RAC limit. Downgrade of Extended Access Barring settings means: broadcast of Static settings or None EAB IEs.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DeltaF PUCCH format 1 for Cat-M
Description: The parameter defines the transport format dependent offset in power control for PUCCH format 1 for Cat-M UEs.  Refer to TS 36.331 IE deltaF-PUCCH-Format1.

Parameter name: Delta preamble random access message 3 for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies power control parameter to calculate P0_NOMINAL_PUSCH(j=2) for PUSCH (re)transmission corresponding to the random access response grant for Cat-M.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 [23, 5.1.1.1] and TS 36.331 and IE deltaPreambleMsg3, Actual value = IE value * 2 [dB].    deltaPreMsg3CatM has the same value range with legacy parameter deltaPreMsg3, however for Cat-M, its value must consider the repetition gains of M-PRACH and M-PUSCH, and depends thus of the respective repetition levels and the desired Cat-M coverage.

Parameter name: The first MCS index of downlink 3HARQ for Cat-M.
Description: This parameter defines the first MCS index used in downlink 3HARQ after switching 2HARQ to 3HARQ for Cat-M.

Parameter name: DL LA down factor for HARQ-Ack Bundling for Cat-M
Description: The parameter defines the NACK number factor for DL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C calculation when HARQ feedback for the bundle is NACK or DTX for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.  When the bundled HARQ feedback is NACK or DTX, it should be treated as many NACK as MIN(the HARQ process number in this bundle, dlLADownFactorCatM).

Parameter name: Downlink MCS threshold for HARQ-Ack bundling for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the downlink MCS threshold to trigger HARQ-Ack bundling for Cat-M in CE mode A.

Parameter name: Use of partly allocated PRBs for CatM
Description: This parameter defines the sf0 and sf5 usage if Cat-M1 Support in 3 MHz Cells or 5 MHz slim carrier Cells.
Range and step: sf0 and sf5 used as invalid subframe (0), sf0 used as invalid subframe only (1), sf5 used as invalid subframe only (2), sf0 and sf5 used as valid subframe (3)

Parameter name: Support of C-Plane overload trigger for Cat-M EAB
Description: This parameter indicates whether OVL_ACB is considered by Cat-M EAB state machine as valid trigger or not.  If this parameter is set to 'false' then OVL_ACB trigger is ignored for Automatic Cat-M Extended Access Barring.  If this parameter is set to 'true' then OVL_ACB trigger may start Automatic Cat-M Extended Access Barring if it's not started yet.

Parameter name: Cat-M Extended Access Barring profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of Cat-M Extended Access Barring profile which is linked to EABPR instance.

Parameter name: Downlink HARQ process number threshold for HARQ-Ack bundling for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum used HARQ process number in downlink to trigger HARQ-Ack bundling for Cat-M in CE mode A.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of a3Offset for intra Frequency for Cat-M
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Better Cell Handover for Intra-Frequency for Cat-M  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of a3Offset for intra Frequency for QCI1 Cat-M
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Better Cell Handover for Intra-Frequency for Cat-M when a QCI1 bearer is present.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Hysteresis of A2 threshold for Cat-M intra and inter frequency handover measurement
Description: This parameter specifies hysteresis of RSRP threshold of serving cell for starting of intra and inter frequency measurements for Cat-M.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Hysteresis of A2 threshold for QCI1 Cat-M intra and inter frequency handover measurement
Description: This parameter specifies hysteresis of RSRP threshold of serving cell for starting of intra and inter frequency measurements for Cat-M when QCI1 bearer is present.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th2a for Cat-M
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for Cat-M of serving cell for stopping of InterFreq measurements  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A1 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th2a for QCI1 Cat-M
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for Cat-M of serving cell for stopping of InterFreq measurements when a QCI1 bearer is present.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A1 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Cell reselection weight factor idle mode load balancing for Cat-M
Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for Cat-M.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for Cat-M load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for Cat-M idle mode load balancing, which is matching Cat-M UE capabilities, to be used as main target for Cat-M idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Connection Release message. All other target frequency for Cat-M idle mode load balancing matching Cat-M UE capabilities and configured in CATMIRFIM subordinated to CATMCEL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB-BR with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing for Cat-M
Description: Percentage of Cat-M UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing.

Parameter name: Immediate S1 Release for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates whether S1 Release procedure is handled immediately after reception of S1AP:UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND or before sending S1AP:UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMPLETE the eNB is waiting for L2Ack from the UE after RRC Connection Release is sent or expiration of tL2AckRrcRelCatM timer.    If immediateS1ReleaseCatM is set to  - 'true': means S1 Release procedure is handled immediately after reception of S1AP:UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND.  - 'false': means eNB is waiting for L2Ack from the UE or expiration of tL2AckRrcRelCatM timer before sending S1AP:UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMPLETE.

Parameter name: Load based narrowband selection threshold for Cat-M CE ModeA
Description: This parameter specifies the threshold for weighted sum of RRC connected Cat-M UE number in primary narrowband for improved load balancing algorithm for multiple CE ModeA narrowbands.    The Cat-M UEs are assigned to the primary narrowband only until the weighted sum of RRC connected Cat-M UE number reaches the threshold. Once the threshold is reached, the following Cat-M UEs will be assigned to the narrowbands with the lowest load metric.    Note: The weighted sum of RRC connected Cat-M UE number equals to (the number of UEs in CE0 + loadWeightCL1CatM * the number of UEs in CE1).

Parameter name: Load metric offset for additional narrowbands for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates the load metric offset for Cat-M additional narrowbands.  It is an offset to balance the load between primary narrowband and additional narrowbands.

Parameter name: Load metric scale for additional narrowbands for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates the load metric scale for Cat-M additional narrowbands.

Parameter name: Load metric scale for primary narrowband for CE level 1 Cat-M UE
Description: This parameter indicates the bias of load metric of primary NB used for CE level 1 Cat-M UE in narrowband selection. The higher value of this parameter will cause the higher possibility for CE level 1 Cat-M UE being allocated to additional narrowbands.

Parameter name: Load weighting factor for CE level 1 Cat-M UE
Description: This parameter specifies the weight of a CE level1 Cat-M UE in load metric calculation.

Parameter name: Mobility profiles mapping list for Cat-M
Description: This parameter maps UE's serving PLMN ID and the UE's SPID (Subscriber Profile ID) to Cat-M mobility profiles.  Several SPIDs, ranges of SPIDs, PLMN IDs or combination of SPIDs or SPID ranges and PLMN IDs can be mapped to a common Cat-M Mobility Profile.

Parameter name: Mobile country code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Country Code of the PLMN ID that shall be mapped to a Cat-M Mobility Profile.

Parameter name: Mobile network code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Network Code of the PLMN ID that shall be mapped to a Cat-M Mobility Profile.    The actual range of the MNC depends on the MNC length in the configured entry of the Cat-M Mobility Profiles Mapping List.

Parameter name: Mobile network code length
Description: Indicates the length of the Mobile Network Code of the PLMN ID that shall be mapped to a Cat-M Mobility Profile.

Parameter name: Mobility profile ID for Cat-M
Description: Identifier of the CatM Mobility Profile, which shall be mapped to one or more SPIDs and/or PLMN IDs.

Parameter name: Subscriber profile ID
Description: Single SPID value or first SPID value of a range which shall be mapped to a Cat-M Mobility Profile.  3GPP 36.300 defines the following SPID range:  Values 1-128 are Operator specific SPIDs  Values 129-256 are Reference SPID values

Parameter name: Last subscriber profile ID of a range
Description: Last SPID value if a range of SPID values shall be mapped to a Cat-M Mobility Profile.  3GPP 36.300 defines the following SPID range:  Values 1-128 are Operator specific SPIDs  Values 129-256 are Reference SPID values

Parameter name: Mobility profile selection mode for Cat-M
Description: This parameter is used to configure selection method of Cat-M Mobility Profile for mobility procedures.  If this parameter is set to value 'spid', then SPID received from MME or incoming handover is used for CATMOPR selection.  If this parameter is set to value 'plmn' then CATMOPR selection is based on Cat-M UE's Serving PLMN ID.  If this parameter is set to 'combined' then CATMOPR selection is based on Cat-M UE's Serving PLMN ID and SPID.

Parameter name: MPDCCH narrowband number for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the primary narrowband used in MPDCCH for Cat-M UEs.  This parameter is used by the UE during the Random Access Procedure (refer to TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NarrowbandsToMonitor-r13) and during the call (refer to TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-Narrowband-r13).

Parameter name: MPDCCH narrowband number for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the narrow band used in MPDCCH for Cat-M ModeB UEs.  This parameter is used by the UE during the Random Access Procedure (refer to TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NarrowbandsToMonitor-r13) and during the call (refer to TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-Narrowband-r13).

Parameter name: MPDCCH Start SF for MPDCCH common search space for Cat-M
Description: This parameters controls the starting subframe configuration for M-PDCCH common search space for RAR, Msg3 retransmission, PDSCH with contention resolution(Msg4) and PDSCH with RRCConnectionSetup for Cat-M UEs.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.321, TS 36.213 and TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-startSF-CSS-RA-r13.

Parameter name: MPDCCH Start SF for MPDCCH UE specific search space for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameters specifies the starting subframe configuration for M-PDCCH UE-specific Search Space UESS for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.321, TS 36.213, 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-StartSF-UESS-r13.

Parameter name: MPDCCH Start SF for MPDCCH UE specific search space for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the starting subframe configuration for M-PDCCH UE-specific Search Space UESS for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.321, TS 36.213, 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-StartSF-UESS-r13.

Parameter name: MPDCCH Start SF for MPDCCH UE specific search space for Cat-M CE Level 2
Description: This parameter specifies the starting subframe configuration for M-PDCCH UE-specific Search Space UESS for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.321, TS 36.213, TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-StartSF-UESS-r13.

Parameter name: MPDCCH Start SF for MPDCCH UE specific search space for Cat-M CE Level 3
Description: This parameter specifies the starting subframe configuration for M-PDCCH UE-specific Search Space UESS for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.321, TS 36.213, TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-StartSF-UESS-r13.

Parameter name: Number of Coverage Enhancement Levels for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies supported number of coverage enhanced levels (CE-level) for Cat-M. The CE Level is decided by the PRACH RSRP threshold.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 'maxCE-Level-r13'.

Parameter name: Number of narrowbands for Cat-M CE ModeA
Description: This parameter indicates the number of narrowbands for Cat-M CE ModeA. If this parameter is set to the value larger than 1, additional Cat-M CE ModeA narrowband will be activated.

Parameter name: Nominal power for Cat-M UE PUCCH TX power calculation
Description: This parameter specifies cell specific PUCCH nominal power for controlling the mean received SNR for control data in Cat-M UE uplink power control algorithm  Refer to TS 36.213, 5.1.2.1. Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and RRC IE RadioResourceConfigCommon, UplinkPowerControlCommon and p0-NominalPUCCH for SIB2.    p0NomPucchCatM has the same value range with legacy parameter p0NomPucch, however for Cat-M, its value must be aligned with the configured repetition level for M-PUCCH and the desired Cat-M coverage.

Parameter name: Nominal power for Cat-M UE PUSCH TX power calculation
Description: This parameter specifies cell specific PUSCH nominal power for controlling the mean received SNR for user data in Cat-M UE uplink power control algorithm  See TS 36.213, 5.1.1.1. Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and RRC IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, UplinkPowerControlCommon, p0-NominalPUSCH in SIB2.    p0NomPuschCatM has the same value range with legacy parameter p0NomPusch, however for Cat-M, its value must be aligned with the configured repetition level for M-PUSCH and the desired Cat-M coverage.

Parameter name: Paging on PDSCH narrowband number for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the narrowband used for Cat-M Paging on PDSCH, sent in DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212, DCI Format 6-2.

Parameter name: Paging on PDSCH narrowband number for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the narrowband used for Cat-M CE ModeB Paging on PDSCH, sent in DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212, DCI Format 6-2.

Parameter name: PDSCH narrowband number for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the primary narrowband used in PDSCH for Cat-M UEs.

Parameter name: PDSCH narrowband number for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the narrow band used in PDSCH for Cat-M ModeB UEs.

Parameter name: Preamble transmit power ramping step for Cat-M
Description: This parameter configures the preamble transmit power step size for Cat-M UEs.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331, IE RACH-ConfigCommon and IE powerRampingStep.

Parameter name: PRACH RSRP threshold 1 for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the RSRP threshold that Cat-M UEs use to separate the Coverage Level 1 (RSRP measurement >= this threshold) and Coverage Level 2 (RSRP measurement < this threshold).  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 IE rsrp-ThresholdsPrachInfoList-r13.    Setting qRxLevMinCe1CatM less than prachRsrpThr1CatM is recommended if numCELevelCatM is set to '3'.

Parameter name: PRACH RSRP threshold 2 for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the RSRP threshold that Cat-M UEs use to separate the Coverage Level 2 (RSRP measurement >= this threshold) and Coverage Level 3 (RSRP measurement < this threshold).  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 IE rsrp-ThresholdsPrachInfoList-r13.    Setting qRxLevMinCe1CatM less than prachRsrpThr2CatM is recommended if numCELevelCatM is set to '4'.

Parameter name: PRACH RSRP threshold for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the RSRP threshold that Cat-M UEs use to separate the Coverage Level 0 (RSRP measurement >= this threshold) and Coverage Level 1 (RSRP measurement < this threshold).  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE rsrp-ThresholdsPrachInfoList-r13.    - Setting prachRsrpThrCatM to the lowest value -140dBm or less than qRxLevMinCeCatM is recommended if numCELevelCatM is set to '1'.  - Setting prachRsrpThrCatM larger than qRxLevMinCeCatM is recommended if numCELevelCatM is set to '2'.

Parameter name: PRB utilization filtering coefficient used for Cat-M scheduler bypass
Description: This parameter defines the filter coefficient used for average PRB load measurements for Cat-M scheduler bypass.

Parameter name: PUSCH narrowband number for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the primary narrowband used in PUSCH for Cat-M UEs.

Parameter name: PUSCH narrowband number for Cat-M CE ModeB
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the narrow band used in PUSCH for Cat-M ModeB UEs.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRQ in the cell for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required RSRQ level for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-QualMinRSRQ-CE1-r13 and TS36.304 Qqualmin_CE1.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRQ in the cell for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required RSRQ level in the cell used by Cat-M UEs in enhanced coverage during cell reselection.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-QualMinRSRQ-CE-r13 and TS36.304 Qqualmin_CE.    If SIB::qQualMinR9 is configured, recommendation setting is less than SIB::qQualMinR9.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRQ in intra-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required RSRQ level for intra-frequency neighbouring E-UTRA cells reselection by Cat-M UEs in enhanced coverage.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-QualMinRSRQ-CE-r13 and TS36.304 Qqualmin_CE.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRQ in intra-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required RSRQ level for intra-frequency neighbouring E-UTRA cells reselection for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-QualMinRSRQ-CE1-r13 and TS36.304 Qqualmin_CE1.

Parameter name: Minimum required RX level in the cell for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required Rx RSRP level for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-RxLevMinCE1-r13, delta-RxLevMinCE1-v1360 and TS36.304 Qrxlevmin_CE1.    - Setting qRxLevMinCe1CatM less than prachRsrpThr1CatM is recommended if numCELevelCatM is set to '3'.  - Setting qRxLevMinCe1CatM less than prachRsrpThr2CatM is recommended if numCELevelCatM is set to '4'.

Parameter name: Minimum required RX level in the cell for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required Rx RSRP level in the cell used by Cat-M UEs in enhanced coverage during cell reselection.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-RxLevMinCE-r13 and TS36.304 Qrxlevmin_CE.    - Setting qRxLevMinCeCatM larger than prachRsrpThrCatM is recommended if numCELevelCatM is set to '1'.  - Setting qRxLevMinCeCatM less than prachRsrpThrCatM is recommended if numCELevelCatM is set to '2'.

Parameter name: Minimum required RX level in intra-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required Rx RSRP level for intra-frequency neighbouring E-UTRA cells reselection by Cat-M UEs in enhanced coverage.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE SIB3-BR, q-RxLevMinCE-r13 and TS36.304 Qrxlevmin_CE.    Follow legacy implementation, this parameter is unnecessary, refer to SIB1-BR:: q-QualMinRSRQ-CE-r13

Parameter name: Minimum required RX level in intra-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required Rx RSRP level for intra-frequency neighbouring E-UTRA cells reselection for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE SIB3-BR, q-RxLevMinCE1-r13, delta-RxLevMinCE1-v1360 and TS36.304 Qrxlevmin_CE1.

Parameter name: Inter-freq and inter-RAT meas thresholds (Rel9) for Cat-M - Inter-freq and inter-RAT power meas threshold (Rel9) for Cat-M
Description: CatM inter-frequency power measurement threshold.

Parameter name: Inter-freq and inter-RAT meas thresholds (Rel9) for Cat-M - Inter-freq and inter-RAT quality meas threshold (Rel9) for Cat-M
Description: CatM inter-frequency quality measurement threshold.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency and inter-RAT measurements threshold for Cat-M
Description: The parameter defines the threshold (in dB) for Cat-M inter-frequency measurements.

Parameter name: Relaxed monitoring measurements threshold for Cat-M UEs
Description: The parameter defines the threshold (in dB) for Cat-M idle mode UE relaxed monitoring measurements.  Value dB6 corresponds to 6 dB, dB9 corresponds to 9 dB and so on.  Reference, 3GPP TS 36.304/3GPP TS 36.306.

Parameter name: SI narrowband number for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the index of the narrowband used for Cat-M System Information messages (SIM) on PDSCH.  This is not for SIB1-BR but for other SIBx-BR.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE si-Narrowband-r13.

Parameter name: SI narrowband selection for Cat-M
Description: This parameter allows operator to choose the narrowband used for Cat-M System Information messages (SIM) on PDSCH.  If this parameter is set to value 'ModeA', then siNarBandNumCatM would be same as pdschNarBandNumCatM.  If this parameter is set to value 'ModeB', then siNarBandNumCatM would be same as pdschNarBandNumModeBCatM.

Parameter name: Starting Coverage Level to support first paging attempt on ECGI only for Cat-M
Description: Starting Coverage Level supports first paging attempt on ECGI only configured for Cat-M cell. Paging optimization function will send the paging over specific cell for first paging message from MME, and paging over TAC region for re-paging messages from MME.  i.e.  Coverage Level 0 - Paging Optimization support start from coverage level 0 (all levels)  Coverage Level 1 - Paging Optimization support start from coverage level 1  Coverage Level 2 - Paging Optimization support start from coverage level 2  Coverage Level 3 - Paging Optimization support in coverage level 3  If this parameter is not configured, then this function is considered to be disabled.  It is recommended to set startingCovLevelPagingOptCatM to the highest configured Coverage level.
Range and step: Coverage Level 0 (0), Coverage Level 1 (1), Coverage Level 2 (2), Coverage Level 3 (3)

Parameter name: Timer T320 for Cat-M
Description: T320 for Cat-M defines the validity time of dedicated priorities defined in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo.  Note that this is an optional parameter. If the parameter is not configured, it means the timer 'not used' - interpreted by UE as 'infinity'. i.e, the T320 timer for Cat-M is not sent by eNB to the UE within IMMCI IE and dedicated priorities are not time limited (the UE uses dedicated priorities until another RRC connection is initiated).

Parameter name: Cell reselection timer for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the value of the cell reselection UE timer on the indicated EUTRAN frequency for Cat-M UEs in enhanced coverage.  Refer to TS 36.331 and T-ReselectionEUTRA-CE-r13.

Parameter name: Threshold of the number of all free LTE PRBs used in Cat-M QCI-Based Scheduler
Description: This parameter specifies the threshold used in Cat-M CQI-based scheduler.  If the number of all free LTE PRBs is greater than this threshold, Cat-M non-GBR is scheduled. Otherwise Cat-M CQI-based scheduler shall be triggered.    Note: if thrNumAllFreePrbCatM is set to a too low value (the number of free PRB is always greater than thrNumAllFreePrbCatM), then Cat-M non-GBR will always be scheduled.

Parameter name: Threshold of the number of LTE PRBs for scheduling Cat-M non-GBR with respect to the scheduling weight in Cat-M QCI-Based Scheduler
Description: This parameter specifies the threshold of the number of LTE PRBs to decide if a Cat-M non-GBR UE can be scheduled or not in case of high PRB utilization with respect to the scheduling weight in Cat-M QCI-Based Scheduler.    If the number of LTE PRBs (used for non-GBR with same or lower scheduling weight) is greater than this threshold, then Cat-M non-GBR UE is scheduled. Otherwise Cat-M non-GBR UE is not scheduled.    Note: if thrNumAllFreePrbCatM and thrPrbNonGbrSchedWeightCatM are both set to too high values, then Cat-M non-GBR UE will not be scheduled during congestion.

Parameter name: Lower threshold of PRB utilization for resume normal scheduler function of Cat-M
Description: The parameter defines lower threshold of PRB utilization for resuming normal scheduler function of Cat-M.

Parameter name: Upper threshold of PRB utilization for trigger scheduler bypass function of Cat-M
Description: The parameter defines upper threshold of PRB utilization for triggering scheduler bypass function of Cat-M.

Parameter name: Q-threshold for reselection towards lower prio RAT/freq for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the Squal threshold for the serving cell when reselecting towards a lower priority frequency for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Threshold serving low for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the threshold for the serving frequency used in reselection evaluation towards a lower priority EUTRAN frequency for Cat-M.

Parameter name: A2 threshold for Cat-M intra and inter frequency handover measurement
Description: This parameter specifies the RSRP threshold of serving cell for starting of intra and inter frequency measurements for Cat-M.  If value is below threshold2CatM (event A2) then intra and inter frequency measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: A2 threshold for QCI1 Cat-M intra and inter frequency handover measurement
Description: This parameter specifies the RSRP threshold of serving cell for starting of intra and inter frequency measurements for Cat-M when a QCI1 bearer is present.  If value is below threshold2CatM (event A2) then intra and inter frequency measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2a RSRP for Cat-M
Description: Threshold for Cat-M of serving cell for stopping of InterFreq measurements.  If InterFreq measurements are active and value exceeds threshold2aCatM then InterFreq measurements are stopped.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2a RSRP for QCI1 Cat-M
Description: Threshold for Cat-M of serving cell for stopping of InterFreq measurements when QCI1 bearer is present.  If InterFreq measurements are active and value exceeds threshold2aCatM then InterFreq measurements are stopped.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: UE capability information request for Cat-M
Description: This parameter controls whether new MME trigger for Cat-M UE Radio Capability transfer procedure in S1AP:DOWNLINK NAS TRANSPORT (in case UE Capability Info Request IE is set to 'requested') is further proceeded or silently ignored by the eNB.

Parameter name: Alpha for Cat-M UE PUSCH TX power calculation
Description: This parameter specifies a fractional path loss compensation factor. It controls received SNR variance (fairness) for user data in Cat-M UE uplink power control algorithm.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, UplinkPowerControlCommon, alpha in SIB2.
Range and step: alpha 0 (0), alpha 0.4 (1), alpha 0.5 (2), alpha 0.6 (3), alpha 0.7 (4), alpha 0.8 (5), alpha 0.9 (6), alpha 1 (7)

Parameter name: Preamble Initial Received Target Power for Cat-M
Description: This parameter configures the initial preamble transmit power parameter for Cat-M UEs.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331, IE RACH-ConfigCommon and IE preambleInitialReceivedTargetPower.    ulpcIniPrePwrCatM has the same value range with legacy parameter ulpcIniPrePwr, however for Cat-M, its value must be aligned with the configured repetition level for M-PRACH and the desired Cat-M coverage.

Parameter name: TPC command in random access response for Cat-M
Description: This parameter defines  TPC command which is indicated in the Random Access response for Cat-M UEs.  The TPC command is sent in the Random Access Response (RAR) as per section 6.2 of TS36.213.

Parameter name: Discontinuous reception (DRX) for Cat-M identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC CATMDRX.  It uniquely identifies a CATMDRX instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DRX profile 1 for Cat-M - DRX profile index for Cat-M
Description: Cat-M DRX profile index.  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX profile 2 for Cat-M - DRX profile index for Cat-M
Description: Cat-M DRX profile index.  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX profile 2 for Cat-M - DRX inactivity timer for Cat-M
Description: Configures the Inactivity Timer for Cat-M DRX.  The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission.    Note: It is recommended to set this parameter at least 2 * mpdcchMaxNumRepCatM. This ensure enough scheduling grant candidates during DRX active period to avoid performance impact.  If this parameter is set to a smaller value, it brings the benefit of UE DRX power saving but at the risk of larger latency.  If this parameter is set to a larger value, it brings less impact on latency but at the risk of less UE DRX power saving.

Parameter name: DRX profile 2 for Cat-M - DRX long cycle for Cat-M
Description: Configures the long DRX cycle for Cat-M .  The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.    If this parameter is set to a larger value, the DRX power saving will be higher due to longer cycle, but the downlink transmission has the risk of larger latency.  If this parameter is set to a smaller value, the transmission has lower downlink latency but at the risk of less UE DRX power saving due to shorter cycle.

Parameter name: DRX profile 2 for Cat-M - DRX on duration timer for Cat-M
Description: Configures the On Duration Timer for Cat-M DRX.  This parameter determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH.    Note: It is recommended to set this parameter at least 2 * mpdcchMaxNumRepCatM. This ensure enough scheduling grant candidates during DRX active period to avoid performance impact.  If this parameter is set to a smaller value, it brings the benefit of UE DRX power saving but at the risk of larger downlink latency.  If this parameter is set to a larger value, the transmission has lower downlink latency but at the risk of less UE DRX power saving being triggered.

Parameter name: DRX profile 2 for Cat-M - DRX DL retransmission timer for Cat-M
Description: Configures the Retransmission Timer for Cat-M DRX.  The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH until a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.    Note: It is recommended to set this parameter at least 2 * mpdcchMaxNumRepCatM. This ensure enough scheduling grant candidates during DRX active period to avoid performance impact.  If this parameter is set to a smaller value, UE has more time for DRX power saving, but the risk of missing re-transmission indication will be higher.  If this parameter is set to a larger value, UE has more time waiting for the re-transmissions, but at the risk of less UE DRX power saving being triggered.

Parameter name: DRX profile 2 for Cat-M - DRX UL retransmission timer for Cat-M
Description: Determines the maximum number of consecutive PDCCH-subframe(s) a UE monitors the PDCCH until a grant for UL retransmission is received. Setting is a tradeoff among scheduling freedom for retransmissions and UE power saving.    Note: It is recommended to set this parameter at least 2 * mpdcchMaxNumRepCatM. This ensure enough scheduling grant candidates during DRX active period to avoid performance impact.  If this parameter is set to a smaller value, UE has more time for DRX power saving, but the risk of missing re-transmission indication will be higher.  If this parameter is set to a larger value, UE has more time waiting for the re-transmissions, but at the risk of less UE DRX power saving being triggered.

Parameter name: CATMIRFIM identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC CATMIRFIM; it uniquely identifies an instance of the CATMIRFIM configuration.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: EUTRA frequency value
Description: eUTRA frequency (max. value ref to 3GPP 36.331 chapter 6.4) as EARFCN value for Cat-M

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier frequency absolute priority
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRA carrier frequency for Cat-M

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection EUTRAN - EUTRA cell reselection timer factor high mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionEUTRA is multiplied with this factor if the Cat-M UE is in High Mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection EUTRAN - EUTRA cell reselection timer factor medium mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionEUTRA is multiplied with this factor if the Cat-M UE is in Medium Mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing for Cat-M
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for Cat-M.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for Cat-M load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for Cat-M idle mode load balancing, which is matching Cat-M UE capabilities, to be used as main target for Cat-M idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Connection Release message. All other target frequency for Cat-M idle mode load balancing matching Cat-M UE capabilities and configured in CATMIRFIM subordinated to CATMCEL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB-BR with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency blacklisted cell list
Description: Defines the inter-frequency blacklisted cell list for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Number of PCI in inter-frequency range
Description: Indicates the number of PCIs in the range (including startPCI) for Cat-M. Value n4 corresponds with 4, n12 corresponds with 12 and so on. The Cat-M UE applies value 1 if the field is absent, in which case only the physical cell identity value indicated by start applies.

Parameter name: Lowest PCI in inter-frequency range
Description: Indicates the lowest PCI in the range for Cat-M

Parameter name: Inter-Frequency neighboring cell list
Description: This is a list of neighbouring cells with specific values for idle mode mobility parameters for Cat-M

Parameter name: Physical cell identifier in neighboring cell list
Description: The Physical Cell Identifier is a unique cell identification in a Neighbouring Cell List for Cat-M. It is used to indicate the physical layer identity of the cell, as defined in TS 36.211

Parameter name: Cell reselection procedure offset
Description: The parameter defines a cell-specific offset (in dB) that is used in the cell reselection procedure for Cat-M.  This specifies the offset between two cells.

Parameter name: EUTRA inter-frequency quality thresholds (Rel9) - EUTRA inter-frequency quality threshold high (Rel9)
Description: This specifies the quality threshold used by the Cat-M UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency than the currently serving frequency.

Parameter name: EUTRA inter-frequency quality thresholds (Rel9) - EUTRA inter-frequency quality threshold low (Rel9)
Description: This specifies the quality threshold used by the Cat-M UE when reselecting towards a lower priority frequency than the currently serving frequency.

Parameter name: EUTRA inter frequency threshold high
Description: This specifies the threshold used by the Cat-M UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency X than the currently serving frequency

Parameter name: EUTRA inter frequency threshold low
Description: This specifies the threshold used by the Cat-M UE in reselection towards frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency

Parameter name: EUTRA presence antenna port1
Description: The IE PresenceAntennaPort1 is used to indicate whether all the neighboring cells use Antenna Port 1. When set to TRUE, the Cat-M UE may assume that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighboring cells.

Parameter name: EUTRA cell reselection timer for Cat-M
Description: EUTRA Cell Reselection Timer in normal coverage

Parameter name: EUTRA cell reselection timer for Cat-M CE
Description: EUTRA Cell Reselection Timer in enhanced coverage

Parameter name: Neighbor cells configuration
Description: Provides information related to MBSFN configuration of neighbour cells of a non-serving frequency for Cat-M.  00: Not all neighbour cells of this frequency have the same MBSFN subframe allocation  01: No MBSFN subframes are present in all neighbour cells of this frequency  10: The MBSFN subframe allocations of all neighbour cells are identical to or subsets of this frequency

Parameter name: Allowed measurement bandwidth
Description: The IE AllowedMeasBandwidth is used to indicate the maximum allowed measurement bandwidth common for all neighbouring cells on a  carrier frequency for Cat-M. The values mbw6, mbw15, mbw25, mbw50, mbw75, mbw100 indicate 6, 15, 25, 50, 75 and 100 resource blocks respectively.

Parameter name: Pmax neighboring EUTRA cells
Description: Pmax to be used for the neighbouring E-UTRA cells on this carrier frequency for Cat-M. If Pmax is absent, the maximum power according to the Cat-M UE capability is used.

Parameter name: EUTRA frequency specific offset
Description: Frequency specific offset for equal priority E-UTRAN frequencies for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRQ in inter-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required quality level of inter-frequency neighbor cells for UEs in normal coverage.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRQ in inter-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required quality level of inter-frequency neighbor cells for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage.  This is broadcasted in SIB5-BR.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-QualMinRSRQ-CE1-r13 and TS36.304 Qqualmin_CE1.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRQ in inter-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M CE
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required quality level of inter-frequency neighbor cells for UEs in enhanced coverage.  This is broadcasted in SIB5-BR.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-QualMinRSRQ-CE-r13 and TS36.304 Qqualmin_CE.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRP level in inter-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required RSRP level of inter-frequency neighbour cells for UEs in normal coverage.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRP level in inter-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required RSRP level of inter-frequency neighbour cells for Cat-M UEs support CE ModeB in enhanced coverage.  This is broadcasted in SIB5-BR.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE q-RxLevMinCE1-r13, delta-RxLevMinCE1-v1360 and TS36.304 Qrxlevmin_CE1.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRP level in inter-freq neighbor cells for Cat-M CE
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum required RSRP level of inter-frequency neighbour cells for UEs in enhanced coverage.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 IE SIB3-BR, q-RxLevMinCE-r13 and TS36.304 Qrxlevmin_CE.

Parameter name: CATMODPR identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC CATMODPR.  It uniquely identifies a CATMODPR instance.

Parameter name: Auto adaptation to frequency layers of all neighbour cells for Cat-M
Description: This parameter offers the possibility to use existing LNCEL configuration as default Cat-M mobility profile.    autoAdaptCatM parameter is considered when CATMODPR applies.  If CATMCEL-actSelMobPrfCatM is set to 'enabled' then CATMODPR applies only when no CATMOPR instance exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the Cat-M UE.  If CATMCEL-actSelMobPrfCatM is set to 'disabled' then CATMODPR applies for all Cat-M UEs.    If autoAdaptCatM is set to 'disabled' :  - CATMODPR configuration is used for Cat-M HO mobility.  If autoAdaptCatM is set to 'enabled' :  - all frequencies configured in LNCEL-LNHOIF are to be measured.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for Cat-M inter frequency mobility
Description: CatM inter-frequency mobility is restricted to the target frequency layers configured in freqLayListCatM.    If CATMCEL-actSelMobPrfCatM is set to 'enabled' the restriction applies when a CATMOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    If CATMCEL-actSelMobPrfCatM is set to 'disabled' the restriction applies to all UEs.  - No Cat-M Inter Frequency mobility will be provided if the parameter is omitted.  - The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: CATMOPR identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC CATMOPR.  It uniquely identifies a CATMOPR instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for Cat-M inter frequency mobility for Cat-M
Description: List of downlink carrier frequencies for Cat-M inter frequency mobility.  No Cat-M Inter Frequency mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted.

Parameter name: CATMPR identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC CATMPR, it uniquely identifies an instance of the CATMPR configuration.

Parameter name: AMC delta C stepsize up of Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: The parameter defines the stepsize up value for the DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.  Stepsize down value for delta C can be calculated by using this parameter and DL/UL target BLER.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - AMC delta C stepsize up of Cat-M QCI1
Description: The parameter defines the stepsize up value for DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.  Stepsize down value for delta C can be calculated by using this parameter and DL/UL target BLER for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.    This parameter controls the speed/sensitivity of link adaptation, by setting the multiplying factor for deltaC calculation, impacting the MCS and repetition selection at the end. Thus it can have significant impact on the LA performance. The high/small value recommendation refers to target BLER setting.

Parameter name: AMC initial delta C of Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: The parameter defines the initial value for DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.

Parameter name: AMC maximum delta C of Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: The parameter defines the maximum limit for the DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation value delta C for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.  If the value delta C reaches the maximum limit, DL/UL MCS is increased by one.

Parameter name: AMC minimum delta C of Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: The parameter defines the minimum limit for DL/UL Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation value delta C for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.  If delta C value reaches the minimum limit, DL/UL MCS is decreased by one.

Parameter name: ARP based Admission Control Offset list for Cat-M UE
Description: This parameter specifies a list of ARP based admission control offsets within a profile for CAT-M UEs.  This list contains a mapping table which maps ARP priority values to ARP offsets.  Configured ARP offsets for CAT-M UE ARP priorities will have impact on cell and transport resource thresholds and on baseband pool limits in case arpOffsetUsageOnBBpool is configured to true.

Parameter name: ARP admission control offset for Cat-M UE
Description: This parameter specifies an admission control offset (=percentage value) per ARP priority level how many resources may be given to this ARP based admission request in relation to the total amount of available resources (e.g. offset = 50% then the request will only get up to 50% of the total available resources, offset = 85% then the request will only get up to 85% of the total available resources ). An ARP offset with a value lower than 100% leads to a static resource reservation for ARP values requesting resources with a higher offset (e.g. for DRBs). The ARP offset handling is done in radio - and in transport admission control. ARP based preemption is triggered in radio AC when thresholds are reached as specified in earlier ARP based AC feature;    It should be clear that low ARP offset configurations will lead to a high admission rejection for that particular ARP(s) or possibly to high number of resource preemptions!    Special case: ARP offset = 0%:  In case the operator configures an ARP value with an offset = 0 then this service represented by this ARP value is not served at all in this cell (gets 0% of the available resources).    This parameter is applicable for Cat-M UE if LTE-M feature is enabled.

Parameter name: ARP priority level for Cat-M UE
Description: This parameter specifies ARP priority level uniquely, with a range between 1 to 15 and every ARP priority level referring to the related ARP offset.  DRB Admission request from core network may have ARP priority level assigned in order to apply prioritization during resource admission and possibly apply preemption in case of lacking resources. Value 15 means 'no priority'. Values between 1 and 14 are ordered in decreasing order of priority, i.e., 1 is the highest and 14 the lowest.  This parameter is applicable for Cat-M UE if LTE-M feature is enabled.

Parameter name: Assigned number of RA preambles for Cat-M UEs
Description: This parameter specifies the number of RA preambles per cell that are reserved for Cat-M UEs in CE level 0 in case actOptRootSeq is set different to 'none'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Assigned number of RA preambles for Cat-M CE level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the number of RA preambles per cell that are reserved for Cat-M UEs in CE level 1 in case actOptRootSeq is set different to 'none'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Initial MCS in downlink of Cat-M in CE Level 1
Description: This parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PDSCH other than BCCH, PCH or random access messages for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  The range of MCS value for Cat-M is defined by 3GPP 36.213 table 7.1.7.1-1: "Modulation and TBS index table for PDSCH"

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Initial MCS in uplink of Cat-M in CE Level 1
Description: This parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PUSCH other than random access message 3 for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  The range of MCS value for Cat-M is defined by 3GPP 36.213 table 8.6.1-1: "Modulation, TBS index and redundancy version table for PUSCH".  The recommend value for 3 MHz cell where actCatM is set to 'true' is 8.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Maximum number of repetition for MPDCCH(UE-SS) for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum numbers of repetitions for M-PDCCH for DL and UL grants of Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NumRepetition-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(UE-SS) for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of M-PDCCH to determine the repetition number of M-PDCCH for the DL and UL grants for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-1A or DCI Format 6-0A.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(Paging) for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of paging message on M-PDCCH for Cat-M UEs mapping to paging CE Level 1.  This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-4 and Table 7.1.11-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of M-PDCCH(Random Access) for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of M-PDCCH to determine the repetition number of M-PDCCH for random access messages(Msg2, HARQ for Msg3, Msg4) for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-1A or DCI Format 6-0A.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Number of PRACH repetitions per attempt for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter defines the number of PRACH repetitions per preamble attempts for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.    Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE numRepetitionPerPreambleAttempt-r13

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level for PDSCH of Cat-M in CE modeA Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PDSCH to determine the repetition number of PDSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA Level 1.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-1A.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level for Msg4 on PDSCH of Cat-M in CE modeA Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the Msg4 repetition level on PDSCH to determine the repetition number of random access Msg4 for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA Level 1.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-1A.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level of PDSCH(Paging) for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of paging message on PDSCH for Cat-M UEs mapping to paging CE Level 1.  This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213  Table 7.1.11-3.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - PRACH Starting subframe for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the PRACH starting subframe for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE prach-StartingSubframe-r13.  If it is set to '0', the optional IE "prach-StartingSubframe-r13" will be dropped in SIB2-BR message for Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Maximum number of PRACH preamble transmission attempts for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of preamble transmission attempts for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE maxNumPreambleAttemptCE-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition number of PUCCH for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition number of the PUCCH Format 1 for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE pucch-NumRepetitionCE-format1-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition number of PUCCH for HARQ feedback to Msg4 in Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the number of PUCCH repetitions of the HARQ feedback in response to the Msg4 for Cat-M in CE Level 1  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 RRC IE 'pucch-NumRepetitionCE-Msg4-Level1-r13'.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Repetition level for PUSCH of Cat-M in CE modeA Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PUSCH to determine the repetition number of PUSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA Level 1.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-0A and RAR for Msg3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 8.2b.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Maximum contention resolution timer for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum contention resolution timer for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE mac-ContentionResolutionTimer-r13    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Number of random access preambles for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the number of RA preambles per cell that are reserved for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, RACH-ConfigCommon, firstPreamble-r13, lastPreamble-r13.    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.

Parameter name: CE(Coverage Enhancement) Level 1 Table for Cat-M - Random access response window size for Cat-M CE Level 1
Description: This parameter defines the random access response window size for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 1.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, RACH-ConfigCommon, RA-ResponseWindowSize-r13.    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: C-Plane inactivity timer
Description: The parameter defines the time period for the indication of the UE- associated S1 logical connection inactivity DL and UL directions.  C-Plane inactivity timer monitors activity on S1AP interface for UE-associated S1 logical connection traffic. It's started with UE-associated S1 logical connection establishment and restarted on reception or sending S1AP message that contains NAS PDU IE.

Parameter name: UE data inactivity timer for Cat-M non-VoLTE data bearer
Description: This parameter defines the time period for Cat-M non-VoLTE data bearer inactivity timer.

Parameter name: Default Paging Cycle for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies cell-specific paging DRX cycle duration for Cat-M UEs.  Refer TS 36.304 and TS 36.331, IE RadioResourceConfigCommon, IE PCCH-Config and IE defaultPagingCycle.  Value rf32 corresponds to 32 radio frames, rf64 corresponds to 64 radio frames and so on.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - DL Maximum number of HARQ transmission for Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of DL HARQ transmissions for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.

Parameter name: Downlink pathloss change for Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: This parameter specifies a trigger condition for power headroom submission due to pathloss change.

Parameter name: DL target BLER of Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: This parameter defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) for downlink Link Adaptation in percents used for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - DL target BLER for Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) for downlink Link Adaptation in percents used for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.

Parameter name: QCI default translation table for Cat-M - DRX profile index for Cat-M CE level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile for Cat-M CE level 0.

Parameter name: QCI default translation table for Cat-M - DRX profile index for Cat-M CE level 1
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile for Cat-M CE level 1.

Parameter name: Maximum number of Msg3 HARQ transmissions for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of HARQ transmissions used for message 3 of the contention-based random access procedure for Cat-M UEs.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE maxHARQ-Msg3Tx.  But due to asynchronized HARQ for Cat-M UEs, the RRC IE 'maxHARQ-Msg3Tx' will be ignored by Cat-M UEs, therefore this parameter configuration is only used by eNB internally.

Parameter name: Maximum number of HARQ transmission in DL for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in DL that is configured for Cat-M UE at initial access (Message 4) and DL data transmission.

Parameter name: Maximum number of HARQ transmission in UL for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in UL that is configured for Cat-M UE at initial access to a specific cell.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE maxHARQ-Tx.  But due to asynchronized HARQ for Cat-M UEs, the RRC IE 'maxHARQ-Tx' will be ignored by Cat-M UEs, therefore this parameter configuration is only used by eNB internally.

Parameter name: Inactivity timer for Cat-M
Description: This parameter defines the time period for the indication of the Cat-M UE inactivity in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Initial MCS in downlink of Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: The parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PDSCH for other use than BCCH, PCH or random access messages for Cat-M UEs in CE level 0.  The range of MCS value for Cat-M is defined by 3GPP 36.213 table 7.1.7.1-1: "Modulation and TBS index table for PDSCH".

Parameter name: Initial MCS in uplink of Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: The parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PUSCH for other use than random access message 3 for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.  The range of MCS value for Cat-M is defined by 3GPP 36.213 table 8.6.1-1: "Modulation, TBS index and redundancy version table for PUSCH".  The recommend value for 3 MHz cell where actCatM is set to 'true' is 8.

Parameter name: Maximum code rate for paging message on PDSCH for Cat-M
Description: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for paging. This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.    Note: The amount of paging records being transmitted per paging occasion is limited such that the configured code rate is not exceeded; a single paging record is transmitted in any case.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - Maximum GBR downlink for Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the downlink GBR for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.  eNB rejects those EPS bearers which the request downlink GBR value from MME is greater than this value for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.    Note1: eNB ignores this check for an emergency bearer setup request for Cat-M QCI1.  Note2: The coverage/quality of the VoLTE call is negatively affected when increasing the GBR value above the data rates of AMR-WB 6.6. or EVS 7.2 codecs.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - Maximum GBR uplink for Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the uplink GBR for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.  eNB rejects those EPS bearers which the request uplink GBR from MME is greater than this value for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.    Note1: eNB ignores this check for an emergency bearer setup request for Cat-M QCI1.  Note2: The coverage/quality of the VoLTE call is negatively affected when increasing the GBR value above the data rates of AMR-WB 6.6. or EVS 7.2 codecs.

Parameter name: Max number act DRB for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the threshold for the maximum number of established Cat-M DRBs in the cell. The maximum number of established Cat-M DRB includes regular Cat-M DRB and emergency Cat-M DRB.

Parameter name: Max number QCI1 DRBs (GBRs) for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the threshold for the maximum number of established Cat-M VoLTE DRBs including QCI1 and operator specific QCI per narrowband in the cell.  The parameter is always relevant independent if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices"" is set to 'false' or to 'true'.  QCI1-DRBs for CAT-M UEs are special data radio bearers in the cell and are also checked against the threshold maxNumActDrb.  In case "actEnhAcAndGbrServices"" is set to 'false', there is no interdependency to the counter/threshold for legacy VoLTE connections (maxNumQci1Drb), that means maxNumQci1Drb and maxNumQci1DrbCatM are independent from each other.

Parameter name: Max number QCI1 DRBs (GBRs) for Cat-M emergency session
Description: This parameter specifies the threshold for the maximum number of established Cat-M QCI1-GBR-DRBs per narrowband for Emergency Sessions in the cell.  QCI1-DRBs for Emergency CAT-M UEs are VoLTE data radio bearers. Each VoLTE DRB admission increases the number of CAT-M DRBs and a check against the threshold maxNumQci1DrbCatM in addition.

Parameter name: Maximum number of Cat-M RRC Connections
Description: This parameter defines the threshold for the maximum number of Cat-M UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection.  As CAT-M UEs share the RRC resources in a cell with wideband UEs, NB IoT UEs and possibly carrier aggregation guest UEs the total amount of use RRC resources cannot exceed the cell BW range capacity (defined in maxNumActUE). As usual the minimum reserved RRC resources in case of baseband pooling activation must still be considered when configuring the threshold.

Parameter name: Maximum number of Cat-M RRC Connections for Emergency Session
Description: This parameter defines the threshold for the maximum number of Cat-M UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection, used to admit RRC connections for emergency calls.  In order to give emergency sessions more chance to be established than normal traffic maxNumRrcEmergency should be greater than maxNumRrcCatM.

Parameter name: MIB Repetitions enabled for Cat-M
Description: This parameter enables the repetitions of Master Information Block (MIB) for Cat-M.

Parameter name: Minimum number of Cat-M RRC connections
Description: This parameter defines the minimum allocated number of Cat-M UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection.  This is needed for AirScale where resources may be shifted from one cell to the other where needed. This parameter is only used by AirScale regardless of dynamic PUCCH features activated or deactivated.  This parameter is never used for eNB=FSMF.

Parameter name: Maximum number of repetition for MPDCCH(UE-SS) for Cat-M Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum numbers of repetitions for M-PDCCH for DL and UL grants of Cat-M UEs.  This parameter has the range and step defined using letter the 'n', which is equivalent to 3GPP nomenclature with the letter 'r'.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NumRepetition-r13.

Parameter name: Maximum number of repetition for MPDCCH(Paging) for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of repetitions for MPDCCH for Cat-M paging messages.  This parameter has the range and step defined using letter the 'n', which is equivalent to 3GPP nomenclature with the letter 'r'.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-4.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NumRepetition-Paging-r13.

Parameter name: Maximum number of repetition for MPDCCH(Random Access) for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of repetitions for MPDCCH for RAR, HARQ of Msg3 and Msg4 of Cat-M UEs.  This parameter is applicable for both CE Level 0 and CE Level 1, i.e., CE Level 0 and CE Level 1 have the same MPDCCH Rmax for Cat-M RAR, HARQ of Msg3 and Msg4 grant.  This parameter has the range and step defined using letter the 'n', which is equivalent to 3GPP nomenclature with the letter 'r'.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.211 and TS 36.331 and IE mpdcch-NumRepetition-RA-r13.

Parameter name: Repetition level of M-PDCCH(UE-SS) for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of M-PDCCH to determine the repetition number of M-PDCCH for the DL and UL grants for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-1A or DCI Format 6-0A.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.

Parameter name: Repetition level of M-PDCCH(Paging) for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of paging message on M-PDCCH for Cat-M UEs mapping to paging CE Level 0.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-4 and Table 7.1.11-3.

Parameter name: Repetition level of M-PDCCH(Random Access) for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of M-PDCCH to determine the repetition number of M-PDCCH for random access messages(Msg2, HARQ for Msg3, Msg4) for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.    This parameter is used to set the 'DCI subframe repetition number' field of the DCI Format 6-1A or DCI Format 6-0A.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 9.1.5-3.

Parameter name: The threshold of MPDCCH repetition number for dedicated TA
Description: This parameter determines the threshold of MPDCCH repetition number for dedicated TA command. The dedicated TA command can only be triggered if the MPDCCH repetition number is no more than this threshold.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - Maximum number of MPDSCH repetition for Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum numbers of MPDSCH repetitions for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.

Parameter name: The threshold of MPDSCH repetition number for dedicated TA
Description: This parameter determines the threshold of MPDSCH repetition number for dedicated TA command. The dedicated TA command can only be triggered if the MPDSCH repetition number is no more than this threshold.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - Maximum number of PUCCH repetition for Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of PUCCH repetitions for Cat-M UE with QCI1 DRB. The number of PUCCH repetitions for Cat-M VoLTE UE is equal to MIN(mpucchMaxNumRepQci1CatM, pucchF1NumRepModeACatM) or MIN(mpucchMaxNumRepQci1CatM, catMCELevel1-pucchF1NumRepModeACatM) depends on Cat-M UE coverage level.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - Maximum number of MPUSCH repetition for Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum numbers of MPUSCH repetitions for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.

Parameter name: Maximum number of out-of-sync indications for Cat-M
Description: Constant for 'out of sync' of Cat-M UEs indications n310CatM.  This parameter defines the maximum number of consecutive "out of sync" indications received from lower layers for Cat-M.  n1 corresponds to 1 and so on.  Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: n310.

Parameter name: Maximum number of in-sync indications for Cat-M
Description: Constant for 'in-sync' of Cat-M UEs indications n311CatM.  This parameter defines the maximum number of consecutive "in-sync" indications received from lower layers for Cat-M.  n1 corresponds to 1 and so on.    Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: n311

Parameter name: Number of PRACH repetitions per attempt for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter defines the number of PRACH repetitions per preamble attempts for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.    Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE numRepetitionPerPreambleAttempt-r13

Parameter name: Number of SIB1-BR repetitions
Description: This parameter specifies the number of SIB1-BR repetitions in terms of 80ms period.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE schedulingInfoSIB1-BR-r13.

Parameter name: Paging Area Scope Check for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies whether S1AP:PAGING Next Paging Area Scope IE is checked or not for Paging algorithm optimization.    If pagAreaScopeCheckCatM is set to  - 'False': eNB does not check the S1AP:PAGING Next Paging Area Scope IE - which means that the first paging on proper ECGI is always sent regardless of the S1AP:PAGING Next Paging Area Scope IE.  - 'True': eNB checks the S1AP:PAGING Next Paging Area Scope IE - which means that the first paging on ECGI is only sent when S1AP:PAGING Next Paging Area Scope IE is the same.  - if it is not configured, eNB does not check the S1AP:PAGING Next Paging Area Scope IE - which means that the first paging per TAC (Tracking Area Code) is always sent regardless of the S1AP:PAGING Next Paging Area Scope IE.

Parameter name: Maximum attempt number for paging message within current coverage level for Cat-M CE ModeA
Description: This parameter specifies the unsuccessful Paging Attempt threshold for Cat-M CE ModeA capable UEs. eNB should apply the higher configured paging CE level parameters for MPDCCH and PDSCH in case of unsuccessful Paging Attempt greater than or equal to this.    It is recommended to set to value '3'.

Parameter name: Paging nB for Cat-M
Description: This parameter defines the number of possible paging occasions per radio frame for Cat-M UEs.  Paging nB defines the number of possible paging occasions per radio frame, i.e. the density of paging occasions. This parameter is used to calculate the number of paging occasions within one paging DRX duration, which in turn is used to calculate the paging occasion.    Refer to TS 36.331 and IE nB-v1310: in case nB-v1310 is signaled, the UE shall ignore nB (that is to say nB without suffix). eNB does not broadcast nB-v1310 in SIB2 but in SIB2-BR.
Range and step: quarterT (4), oneEighthT (5), oneSixteenthT (6), oneThirtySecondT (7), one64thT (8), one128thT (9), one256thT (10)

Parameter name: Maximum numbers of repetition for PDSCH of Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of repetitions for PDSCH of Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and the optional IE pdsch-maxNumRepetitionCEmodeA-r13.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: Repetition level for PDSCH of Cat-M in CE modeA Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PDSCH to determine the repetition number of PDSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA Level 0.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-1A.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.

Parameter name: Repetition level for Msg4 on PDSCH of Cat-M in CE modeA Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the Msg4 repetition level on PDSCH to determine the repetition number of random access Msg4 for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA Level 0.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-1A.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 7.1.11-1.

Parameter name: Repetition level for paging message on PDSCH for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of paging message on PDSCH for Cat-M UEs mapping to paging CE Level 0.  This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-2.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213  Table 7.1.11-3.

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 1 - Poll PDU for DRB Cat-M
Description: The parameter Poll PDU defines the number of RLC PDUs that are sent on a logical channel before the RLC polling bit is set.  This parameter specifies the parameter pollPDU of [36.331].

Parameter name: PRACH starting subframe for Cat-M CE Level 0
