Description: This parameter specifies the PRACH starting subframe for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE prach-StartingSubframe-r13.  If it is set to '0', the optional IE "prach-StartingSubframe-r13" will be dropped in SIB2-BR message for Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Maximum number of PRACH preamble transmission attempts for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of preamble transmission attempts for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE maxNumPreambleAttemptCE-r13.

Parameter name: Preamble transmission maximum for Cat-M
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of Random Access transmissions for Cat-M UEs, regardless of CE Levels.    Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and 3GPP TS 36.321, IE preambleTransMax-CE-r13.    For example, if the preambMaxNumAttemptCECatM for CE Level 0 and 1 are set to n3, and preambTxMaxCatM is set to n5, then a UE initiating RACH procedure at CE Level 0 would perform up to 3 preamble attempts at CE Level 0 and 2 preamble attempts at CE Level 1. If another UE starts the RACH procedure at CE Level 1, then up to 5 preamble attempts would be done at CE Level 1.

Parameter name: Repetition number of PUCCH for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition number of the PUCCH Format 1 for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE pucch-NumRepetitionCE-format1-r13.

Parameter name: Repetition number of PUCCH for HARQ feedback to Msg4 in Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the number of PUCCH repetitions of the HARQ feedback in response to the Msg4 for Cat-M in CE Level 0.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 RRC IE 'pucch-NumRepetitionCE-Msg4-Level0-r13'.

Parameter name: Maximum numbers of repetition for PUSCH of Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of repetitions for PUSCH of Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE pusch-maxNumRepetitionCEmodeA-r13.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: Repetition level for PUSCH of Cat-M in CE modeA Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the repetition level of PUSCH to determine the repetition number of PUSCH messages for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA Level 0.    This parameter is used to set the 'Repetition Number' field of the DCI Format 6-0A and RAR for Msg3  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.212  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.213 Table 8.2b.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - QCI1 protection timer for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum time between Cat-M QCI1 bearer establishment and the release of the Cat-M UE to RRC idle mode.  Cat-M QCI1 establishment starts a configurable timer which keeps the Cat-M UE in RRC connected mode even if there is no activity (e.g. during ringtone) until timer expiry.

Parameter name: UE data inactivity timer for Cat-M VoLTE bearer
Description: This parameter defines the time period for Cat-M VoLTE UE data inactivity timer.

Parameter name: Operator specific QCI for Cat-M VoLTE
Description: This parameter specifies operator-specific QCI for Cat-M VoLTE.  If this parameter is set to the value within 128~254, it means operator-specific QCI will be handled as well as QCI1 for Cat-M VoLTE.  Default value '255' means no operator specific QCI defined for Cat-M VoLTE.

Parameter name: Maximum contention resolution timer for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum contention resolution timer for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IE mac-ContentionResolutionTimer-r13    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.

Parameter name: Number of random access preambles for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter specifies the number of RA preambles per cell that are reserved for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, RACH-ConfigCommon, firstPreamble-r13,  lastPreamble-r13.    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.

Parameter name: Random access response window size for Cat-M CE Level 0
Description: This parameter defines the random access response window size for Cat-M UEs in CE Level 0.  Refer to TS 36.321 and TS 36.331 and IEs RadioResourceConfigCommon, RACH-ConfigCommon, RA-ResponseWindowSize-r13.    This parameter is defined per CE Level (1...maxCE-Level-r13) of rach-CE-LevelInfoList-r13.

Parameter name: RRC guard timer radio bearer management for Cat-M
Description: This timer is started when an RRC message for setup, modification or release of a radio bearer is sent to the Cat-M UE. When the timer expires, the corresponding procedure is aborted.

Parameter name: SI repetition patten for Cat-M
Description: The parameter SI Repetition Pattern defines the common System Information scheduling repetition pattern for all SIs of Cat-M UEs.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP 36.331 and IE si-RepetitionPattern-r13.  Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: SI validity time for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates UE whether to delete any stored system information after 24 hours or 3 hours. If set to TRUE, the timer is set to 3h, otherwise, the timer is set to 24h.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP 36.331 and IE si-ValidityTime-r13.

Parameter name: SI window length for Cat-M
Description: The parameter SI Window Length defines the common System Information scheduling window for all SIs of Cat-M UEs.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP 36.331 and IE si-WindowLength-BR-r13.  Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: SIB14 periodicity for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates the periodicity of Cat-M SI-Message which contains SIB14-BR.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP 36.331 and IE si-Periodicity.  Note: If SIB14 is configured in this cell, all Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: SIB16 periodicity for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates the periodicity of CatM SI-Message which contains SIB16-BR.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP 36.331 and IE si-Periodicity.  Note: If SIB16 is configured in this cell, all Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: SIB2-BR periodicity for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates the periodicity of CatM SI-Message which contains SIB2-BR.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP 36.331 and IE si-Periodicity.  Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: SIB3-BR and SIB4-BR periodicity for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates the periodicity of CatM SI-Message which contains SIB3-BR and SIB4-BR. SIB3-BR and SIB4-BR are sent in one SI-BR message.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP 36.331.  Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: SIB5-BR periodicity for Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates the periodicity of CatM SI-Message which contains SIB5-BR.  This is broadcasted in SIB1-BR.  Refer to 3GPP 36.331 and IE si-Periodicity.  Note: If SIB5 is configured in this cell, all Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released when this parameter is modified online.

Parameter name: SR Prohibited timer for Cat-M
Description: This parameter controls the minimum separation in time between consecutive Scheduling Request transmissions by the UE (refer to 36.321 sec.5.4.4). It can be used to prevent unwanted repetitions of SRs. The parameter is expressed in number of SR periods. It is sent to the UE in the RRC IE sr-ProhibitTimer-r9. It applies to Cat-M UEs. srProhibitTimerCatM = 0 means no minimum interval (SRs can be sent at every SR period).

Parameter name: Srb inactivity timer
Description: The parameter defines the time period for the indication of the UE inactivity on signaling radio bearer in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Timer T300 for Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: Timer T300 for Cat-M supervises the RRC connection establishment procedure of Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.  Timer T300 supervises the RRC connection establishment procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionSetup or RRCConnectionReject message, cell re-selection and upon abortion of connection establishment by upper layers    At expiry: Perform the actions as specified in 36.331, 5.3.3.6.    Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: t300.

Parameter name: Timer T301 for Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: Timer T301 for Cat-M supervises the RRC connection re-establishment procedure of Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.  Timer T301 supervises the RRC connection re-establishment procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionReestabilshmentRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionReestablishment or RRCConnectionReestablishmentReject message as well as when the selected cell becomes unsuitable    At expiry: Go to RRC_IDLE    Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: t301

Parameter name: Timer T304 intra-LTE for Cat-M
Description: Timer T304 supervises the successful completion of a handover or cell change for Cat-M.  The timer is started in the UE in connected mode upon reception of RRCConnectionReconfiguration message including the MobilityControl Information. At timer expiry, the UE initiates the RRC connection re-establishment procedure. See TS 36.331.

Parameter name: Timer T310 for Cat-M
Description: Timer T310 for Cat-M supervises the recovery from physical layer problems(Radio Link Failure).  Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: t310.

Parameter name: Timer T311 for Cat-M
Description: Timer T311 supervises the RRC connection re-establishment for Cat-M UEs.  The timer is started upon initiating the RRC connection re-establishment procedure and is stopped when a suitable cell has been selected.    Refer to TS36.331 IE UE-TimersAndConstants: t311

Parameter name: PDCP PDU Timer Discard for DRB Cat-M
Description: This parameter indicates the delay before a PDCP PDU along with the corresponding PDCP SDU is discarded from the buffer. This timer shall be set in a way that the packet delay defined by the QCI characteristics is kept. The timer can be disabled by setting the parameter to infinity.  This parameter specifies the parameter discardTimer of [36.331]

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - Timer discard for Cat-M QCI1 DRB PDCP SDU
Description: This parameter indicates the delay before a PDCP PDU along with the corresponding PDCP SDU is discarded from the buffer.  The timer can be disabled by setting the parameter to infinity.  This timer is specific defined for Cat-M QCI1-DRB, other PDCP properties should be set in a way followed as wideband LTE PDCP profile configuration.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - Timer discard for Cat-M QCI5 DRB PDCP SDU
Description: This parameter indicates the delay before a PDCP PDU along with the corresponding PDCP SDU is discarded from the buffer.  The timer can be disabled by setting the parameter to infinity.  This timer is specific defined for Cat-M QCI5-DRB, other PDCP properties should be set in a way followed as wideband LTE PDCP profile configuration.

Parameter name: Timer min lifetime of half-open RRC connection for Cat-M
Description: The minimal time period that the eNB waits for an RRC CONNECTION SETUP COMPLETE message after sending a RRC CONNECTION SETUP message for Cat-M UEs.

Parameter name: Timer missing L2 ack for Cat-M RRC connection release
Description: The maximum time period indicates the time after which the RRC L3 releases the RRC connection for Cat-M call only if no positive ack is received from L2 to the RRC CONNECTION RELEASE message. This timer has to absorb the potential preceding NAS transmission, which can be approximated via rrcGuardTimerCatM. This timer is reset to 1.25 seconds upon reception of L1 HARQ ACK of RRC Connection Release, as per 3GPP R2-169034.

Parameter name: Periodic BSR timer for Cat-M
Description: This parameter specifies the time period of the periodic Buffer Status Report for the reporting of the Cat-M UE transmission buffer utilization.  This parameter is used for non-GBR bears of Cat-M CE mode A UE.

Parameter name: Periodic PHR timer for Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: This parameter specifies sending periodic power headroom reports for Cat-M UE in CE modeA.

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 1 - Timer Poll Retransmit for DRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 1 - Timer Poll Retransmit for SRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 1 - Timer Status Prohibit for DRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity in order to prohibit transmission of a STATUS PDU.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-StatusProhibit of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 1 - Timer Status Prohibit for SRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity in order to prohibit transmission of a STATUS PDU.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-StatusProhibit of [36.331]

Parameter name: Prohibited PHR timer for Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum intermediate time between two consecutive Power Headroom Reports for Cat-M in CE modeA.

Parameter name: Retransmission BSR timer for Cat-M
Description: This parameter defines the time period when the BSR is reported when the Cat-M UE has data available for transmission and no corresponding UL grant is received so far.

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 1 - Timer Reordering for DRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 1 - Timer reordering for Cat-M VoLTE
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an UM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331]

Parameter name: RLC Profile for Cat-M in CE Level 1 - Timer Reordering for SRB Cat-M
Description: This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331]

Parameter name: The prohibit timer of scheduling dedicated TA command for CatM UE
Description: This parameter determines the interval between two times DL transmissions triggered by TA command transmission for a CatM UE. The timer is started/restarted every time DL scheduling triggered by TA command transmission, and DL scheduling can be triggered by TA command transmission only when the timer is not running.

Parameter name: Time alignment maximum offset for CatM UE
Description: This parameter determines the maximum allowed Time Alignment offset for CatM UE. If the value is exceeded, TA command is sent to the Cat-M UE to adjust UL timing.

Parameter name: Time alignment Timer for CatM UE
Description: This parameter determines the number of subframes after which a CatM UE assumes it is out-of-sync in UL if no Time Alignment command was received.

Parameter name: Time alignment Timer margin for CatM UE
Description: This parameter defines lead with respect to the taTimer expiration time for starting to send the periodic Timing Advance Command for CatM UE.  This parameter is not used when taTimerCatM is set to infinity.

Parameter name: The timer of scheduling UL grant for TA measurement
Description: This parameter determines the frequency of the UL Grant for TA measurement. The timer is started on receiving MSG3 and restarted every time there's a UL transmission occur. When the timer expires, the UL grant for TA measurement will be sent to CatM UE. With a configured value infinity, UL Grant for TA measurement is disabled.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - UL Maximum number of HARQ transmission for Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in UL for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.  Refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE maxHARQ-Tx.  Due to asynchronized HARQ for Cat-M UEs, the RRC IE 'maxHARQ-Tx' will be ignored by Cat-M UEs, therefore this parameter configuration is only used by eNB internally.

Parameter name: Uplink MCS threshold for Multiple HARQ for max PUSCH TBS of Cat-M in CE mode A
Description: This parameter specifies the Uplink MCS threshold to trigger Multiple HARQ for maximum PUSCH TBS of Cat-M in CE mode A.  Note: Table 8.6.1-2A: Modulation and TBS index for PUSCH in 3GPP 36.213, 8.6.1 is used for maximum PUSCH TBS of Cat-M UE in CE mode A.

Parameter name: UL target BLER of Cat-M in CE modeA
Description: This parameter defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) for uplink Link Adaptation in percents used for Cat-M UEs in CE modeA.

Parameter name: Cat-M VoLTE Parameters Table - UL target BLER of Cat-M QCI1
Description: This parameter defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) for uplink Link Adaptation in percents used for Cat-M QCI1 DRB.

Parameter name: Minimum UL transport block size for Cat-M CE mode A
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum UL TBS (segment size) during Cat-M CE mode A link adaptation.  The allowed value range is derived from Table 7.1.7.2.1-1 in 3GPP TS 36.213 (1&2 PRB case and MAC constraints).    Units: bits

Parameter name: CBRS Profile Id
Description: This parameter is used to specify the CBRS profile instance ID.

Parameter name: CBSD Channel Space between contiguous 10MHz spectrum
Description: This parameter defines the two contiguous CBSD Cells earfcn space distance in MHz that use the two contiguous 10MHz spectrums granted from SAS.    This parameter should be set to the value 0 or not configured when the related MRBTS/LNBTS/LNCEL/CBSDCEL.cCaPairCellId is not configured.

Parameter name: CBSD Channel Space between contiguous 10MHz and 20 MHz Spectrums
Description: This parameter defines the two contiguous CBSD Cells earfcn space distance in MHz that use the contiguous 10MHz and 20MHz spectrums granted from SAS.    This parameter should be set to the value 0 or not configured when the related MRBTS/LNBTS/LNCEL/CBSDCEL.cCaPairCellId is not configured.

Parameter name: CBSD Channel Space between contiguous 20MHz Spectrums
Description: This parameter defines the two contiguous CBSD Cells earfcn space distance in MHz that use the two contiguous 20MHz spectrums granted from SAS.    This parameter should be set to the value 0 or not configured when the related MRBTS/LNBTS/LNCEL/CBSDCEL.cCaPairCellId is not configured.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Connect to SAS Server Mode
Description: This parameter defines the connection mode of the eNB to the SAS server.
Range and step: direct connect to SAS server (0), connect through https proxy (1), connect through Domain proxy (3)

Parameter name: Primary Domain Proxy Server
Description: This parameter holds the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or Ipaddress(IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the primary domain proxy server.

Parameter name: Primary Https proxy server
Description: This parameter holds the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or IPAddress(IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the primary Https Proxy server.

Parameter name: Primary SAS Server
Description: This parameter holds the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or Ipaddress(IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the primary Spectrum Access System (SAS) server.

Parameter name: CBRS Profile Name
Description: This parameter is used to assign an unique name to the CBRS profile. This parameter has no operation impact on the system.

Parameter name: Query SAS Server Period
Description: This parameter defines the period to query the SAS server in order to check if a better spectrum grant is available.

Parameter name: Secondary Domain Proxy Server
Description: This parameter holds the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or Ipaddress(IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the secondary domain proxy server.

Parameter name: Secondary Https proxy server
Description: This parameter holds the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) or IPAddress(IPv4 or IPv6)/port or Hostname/port of the secondary Https Proxy server.

Parameter name: Secondary SAS Server
Description: This parameter holds the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) of the secondary Spectrum Access System (SAS) server.

Parameter name: WINNF Technical Specification Version
Description: This parameter indicates the version of the WINNF SAS-CBSD Interface Technical Specification used by eNB.

Parameter name: CBSD Id
Description: This parameter is used to specify the CBSD instance ID.

Parameter name: Antenna Azimuth
Description: Boresight direction of the horizontal plane of the antenna in degrees with respect to true north. The value of this parameter is an integer with a value between 0 and 359 inclusive. A value of 0 degrees means true north; a value of 90 degrees means east. This parameter is optional for Category A CBSDs and required for Category B CBSDs.

Parameter name: Antenna Beamwidth
Description: 3 dB antenna horizontal-plane beamwidth in degrees. It is optional for Category A device and required for category B CBSD.  Note: a value of 360 (degrees) means the antenna has an omnidirectional radiation pattern in the horizontal plane.

Parameter name: Antenna Downtilt
Description: Antenna downtilt in degrees. A negative value means the antenna is tilted up (above horizontal). This parameter is optional for Category A CBSDs and required for Category B CBSDs.

Parameter name: Antenna Gain
Description: Peak antenna gain in dBi. It is optional for Category A device and required for category B CBSD.

Parameter name: Antenna Model
Description: If an external antenna is used, the antenna model is optionally provided in this field.

Parameter name: List of Antenna Line distinguished names
Description: This parameter indicates the distinguished name of the ANTL instance(s) associated with this CBSD instance. These distinguished names can be either a Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or a shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  FDN example: MRBTS-1/EQM-1/APEQM-1/RMOD-1/ANTL-1  SDN example: ANTL-1    This parameter shall only be configured when multiple sector antennas are attached to the radio or when radio resiliency with cross-sectors connectivity is in use

Parameter name: SAS assigned CBSD ID
Description: This parameter indicates the CBSD ID assigned by SAS server.  When no value displayed in this parameter, it means no valid CBSD ID information from SAS server is available.

Parameter name: Call Sign
Description: A device identifier provided by FCC.

Parameter name: CBRS Frequency Type
Description: This parameter specifies whether the CBSD should operate in the Priority Access License (PAL) or General Authorized Access (GAA) mode.

Parameter name: CBRS Profile Id
Description: This parameter is used to specify the CBRS profile instance ID associated with the CBSD device.

Parameter name: CBRSA Group Identifier of Common Channel Group
Description: This parameter specifies the CBRSA Group Identifier of Common Channel Group for this CBSD.    The range represents the number of bytes to store all the characters of the string. If the string is UTF-8 encoded, each character occupies between 1 to 4 bytes, depending upon the language. If ASCII encoded, each character occupies a single byte. The numbers of characters supported in case of UTF-8 encoding is 32.

Parameter name: CBRSA Group Identifier of Interference Coordination Group
Description: This parameter specifies the CBRSA Group Identifier of Interference Coordination Group for this CBSD.    The range represents the number of bytes to store all the characters of the string. If the string is UTF-8 encoded, each character occupies between 1 to 4 bytes, depending upon the language. If ASCII encoded, each character occupies a single byte. The numbers of characters supported in case of UTF-8 encoding is 32.

Parameter name: CBSD Device Category
Description: Device Category of the CBSD cell.

Parameter name: CBSD Registration State
Description: Specifies the current registration state of the CBSD.

Parameter name: CBSD Serial Number
Description: This parameter indicates the CBSD's serial number.  It is same with the RRH serial number.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: FCC Identity
Description: The Federal Communications Commission (FCC) certification identifier of the CBSD.    FCC ID = Grantee Code(G) + Product Code(P)  Current Grantee Code Process:  - Grantee code = 3 characters  - Product code = maximum of 14 characters  - AGGPPPPPPPPPPPPPP, where A = grantee code character limited to alphabetic character only    New Grantee Code Process:  - Grantee code = 5 characters  - Product code = maximum of 14 characters  - #GGGGPPPPPPPPPPPPPP, where # = grantee code character limited to numeric value only (no zeros or ones)

Parameter name: Height
Description: CBSD antenna height in meters.

Parameter name: Height Type
Description: The value should be "AGL" or "AMSL". AGL height is measured relative to the ground level. AMSL height is measured relative to the mean sea level.

Parameter name: Horizontal Accuracy
Description: A positive number in meters to indicate accuracy of CBSD antenna horizontal location if it's smaller than the FCC requirement (50 meters).

Parameter name: Indoor Deployment
Description: This parameter indicates whether the CBSD antenna is installed indoor or not.

Parameter name: Latitude
Description: Latitude of the CBSD antenna location in degrees relative to the NAD 83 datum. Positive values represent latitudes north of the equator; negative values south of the equator.

Parameter name: Longitude
Description: Longitude of the CBSD antenna location in degrees relative to the NAD 83 datum. Positive values represent longitudes east of the prime meridian; negative values west of the prime meridian.

Parameter name: Distinguished name of paired RMOD managed object
Description: This parameter contains the distinguished name (DN) of the Radio Module (RMOD) managed object to which the CBSD instance is assigned to. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.    FDN example: MRBTS-151/EQM-1/APEQM-1/RMOD-1  SDN example: APEQM-1/RMOD-1

Parameter name: SAS User Group List
Description: This parameter reference to which sasUserGroup(s) this CBSD belongs to

Parameter name: Supported Spectrum for WINNF SAS CBSD Technical Specification post Version2
Description: This parameter describes the frequency range, in 5 MHz block increments, within the 3.5GHz spectrum (3550 - 3700 MHz) in which CBSD seeks information.  This parameter is encoded as a bitmap, where bit N is set to '0' if the corresponding frequency is not in selection list, and set to '1' if the corresponding frequency is within the selection list.    Bitmask with bits defined as follows:  0 - frequency range 3550 - 3555  1 - frequency range 3555 - 3560  2 - frequency range 3560 - 3565  3 - frequency range 3565 - 3570  4 - frequency range 3570 - 3575  5 - frequency range 3575 - 3580  6 - frequency range 3580 - 3585  7 - frequency range 3585 - 3590  8 - frequency range 3590 - 3595  9 - frequency range 3595 - 3600  10 - frequency range 3600 - 3605  11 - frequency range 3605 - 3610  12 - frequency range 3610 - 3615  13 - frequency range 3615 - 3620  14 - frequency range 3620 - 3625  15 - frequency range 3625 - 3630  16 - frequency range 3630 - 3635  17 - frequency range 3635 - 3640  18 - frequency range 3640 - 3645  19 - frequency range 3645 - 3650  20 - frequency range 3650 - 3655  21 - frequency range 3655 - 3660  22 - frequency range 3660 - 3665  23 - frequency range 3665 - 3670  24 - frequency range 3670 - 3675  25 - frequency range 3675 - 3680  26 - frequency range 3680 - 3685  27 - frequency range 3685 - 3690  28 - frequency range 3690 - 3695  29 - frequency range 3695 - 3700
Range and step: bits mask: frequency range 3550 - 3555 (0), frequency range 3555 - 3560 (1), frequency range 3560 - 3565 (2), frequency range 3565 - 3570 (3), frequency range 3570 - 3575 (4), frequency range 3575 - 3580 (5), frequency range 3580 - 3585 (6), frequency range 3585 - 3590 (7), frequency range 3590 - 3595 (8), frequency range 3595 - 3600 (9), frequency range 3600 - 3605 (10), frequency range 3605 - 3610 (11), frequency range 3610 - 3615 (12), frequency range 3615 - 3620 (13), frequency range 3620 - 3625 (14), frequency range 3625 - 3630 (15), frequency range 3630 - 3635 (16), frequency range 3635 - 3640 (17), frequency range 3640 - 3645 (18), frequency range 3645 - 3650 (19), frequency range 3650 - 3655 (20), frequency range 3655 - 3660 (21), frequency range 3660 - 3665 (22), frequency range 3665 - 3670 (23), frequency range 3670 - 3675 (24), frequency range 3675 - 3680 (25), frequency range 3680 - 3685 (26), frequency range 3685 - 3690 (27), frequency range 3690 - 3695 (28), frequency range 3695 - 3700 (29)

Parameter name: User Identity
Description: The identifier of a CBSD user.    The range represents the number of bytes to store all the characters of the string. If the string is UTF-8 encoded, each character occupies between 1 to 4 bytes, depending upon the language. If ASCII encoded, each character occupies a single byte. The numbers of characters supported in case of UTF-8 encoding is 32.

Parameter name: Vertical Accuracy
Description: A positive number in meters to indicate accuracy of CBSD antenna vertical location if it's smaller than the FCC requirement (3 meters).

Parameter name: CBSD Cell identifier
Description: This is an instance identify of a CBSDCEL MOC.

Parameter name: LNCEL id of the other CBSD cell in the carrier pair requiring contiguous carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter describes the LNCEL id of the other CBSD cell in the carrier pair requiring contiguous carrier aggregation.    If cCaPairCellId is not configured, CBRSPR.channelSpace1010, CBRSPR.channelSpace1020 and CBRSPR.channelSpace2020 of the related CBRSPR instance shall either not configured or set to value 0 if they are configured.

Parameter name: CBRS cell priority for Spectrum Assignment
Description: This parameter is used to prioritize channel allocation for CBRS cell per Cell level.
Range and step: top priority (1), 2nd priority (2), 3rd priority (3), 4th priority (4), 5th priority (5), 6th priority (6), 7th priority (7), 8th priority (8)

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Desired Channel Band Width
Description: This parameter specifies the desired CBSD Cell band width.

Parameter name: Desired Maximum Output Power
Description: This parameter defines the desired maximum output power of the CBSD cell.    Note: For Macro eNB, the parameter is used as desiredPmax for 20 MHz bandwidth (e.g. 34 dBm). In case a 10 MHz CBRS channel is used for this CBSD cell, the actual desiredPmax eNB used is (desiredPmax - 3 dB) (e.g. 31 dBm).

Parameter name: Desired TDD subframe configuration
Description: This parameter specifies the desired uplink-downlink subframe configuration in CBSD Cell.    The Subframe Assignment need to be configured according to 3GPP 36.211. The parameter corresponds to the subframeAssignment (sa#) as specified in 3GPP 36.331.  Currently only Subframe assignment 0, 1 and 2 (sa0, sa1, sa2) are supported.

Parameter name: Desired TDD special subframe configuration
Description: This parameter specifies the desired TDD Special Subframe Configuration used for the configuration of DwPTS, GP and UpPTS in the special subframe in CBSD Cell.    The configured Special Subframe Pattern corresponds to the specialSubframePatterns (ssp#) as specified in 3GPP 36.331.  Special Subframe Patterns 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 and 9 (ssp3: 11:2:1, ssp4: 12:1:1, ssp5: 3:9:2, ssp6: 9:3:2, ssp7: 10:2:2, ssp9: 6:6:2) are supported.

Parameter name: Fallback TDD subframe configuration
Description: This parameter specifies the fallback uplink-downlink subframe configuration in CBSD Cell.    The Subframe Assignment need to be configured according to 3GPP 36.211. The parameter corresponds to the subframeAssignment (sa#) as specified in 3GPP 36.331.  Currently only Subframe assignment 0, 1 and 2 (sa0, sa1, sa2) are supported.

Parameter name: Fallback TDD special subframe configuration
Description: This parameter specifies the fallback TDD Special Subframe Configuration used for the configuration of DwPTS, GP and UpPTS in the special subframe in CBSD Cell.    The configured Special Subframe Pattern corresponds to the specialSubframePatterns (ssp#) as specified in 3GPP 36.331.  Special Subframe Patterns 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 and 9 (ssp3: 11:2:1, ssp4: 12:1:1, ssp5: 3:9:2, ssp6: 9:3:2, ssp7: 10:2:2, ssp9: 6:6:2) are supported.

Parameter name: SAS grant Channel Type
Description: This parameter indicates the SAS grant channel type is Priority Access License (PAL) or General Authorized Access (GAA).  When no value displayed in this parameter, it means no valid grant channel type information from SAS server is available.

Parameter name: SAS grant ID
Description: This parameter indicates the grant ID from SAS server for the CBSD cell.  When no value displayed in this parameter, it means no valid grant ID information from SAS server is available.

Parameter name: SAS grant Max Eirp
Description: This parameter indicates the max Effective Isotropic Radiated Power (EIRP) granted by SAS server.  When no value displayed in this parameter, it means no valid max EIRP information from SAS server is available.

Parameter name: SAS grant operation state
Description: This parameter indicates the current operation state of the grant from SAS server for the CBSD cell.

Parameter name: grant Spectrum High Frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the grant spectrum high frequency assigned by SAS server.  When no value displayed in this parameter, it means no valid spectrum frequency information from SAS server is available.

Parameter name: grant Spectrum Low Frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the grant spectrum low frequency assigned by SAS server.  When no value displayed in this parameter, it means no valid spectrum frequency information from SAS server is available.

Parameter name: Maximum Grant Cell Band width Reduction
Description: This parameter defines maximum band width reduction in MHz grant for CBSD Cell.  In case there is no available spectrum that its bandwidth equal or great than the configured CBSD Cell bandwidth (LNCEL_TDD-chBw), if maxGrantChBwRed > 0, the CBSD attempts grant the reduced bandwidth (desiredChBw - maxGrantChBwRed) from SAS.

Parameter name: max allowed grant power reduction
Description: This parameter defines the max power reduction from the desiredPmax that the operator is willing to accept.

Parameter name: PUCCH bandwidth for CQI used for 10M CBRS cell
Description: This parameter defines the PUCCH bandwidth for CQI used for 10M CBRS cell.  This parameter is the number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b/3.    This parameter is part of the set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called MaxPucchResourceSize10M for 10M CPRS cell. All other parameters are related to each other according to this formula:  Note: in the formula below the term chBw shall be considered in # of PRB and not in MHz!    MaxPucchResourceSize10M = nCqiRb10M + roundup{[ (max((M-i-1)* Np +i*Np1 + rounddown (((12 * (maxNrSymPdcch-Yi) - X) * chBw - mi*roundup(phichRes * (chBw / 8)) * 12 - 16 )/ 36)) + n1PucchAn - pucchNAnCs * c / deltaPucchShift) * deltaPucchShift] / (c*12)} + roundup (pucchNAnCs / 8),  All other parameters in this formula are O&M parameters, while MaxPucchResourceSize10M is a calculated value that has a maximum allowed value, which shall not be exceeded.  Therefore the MaxPucchResourceSize10M is utilized to determine the correct offset allocation of the PRACH resources and to verify that the maximal allowed amount of PUCCH resources per BW is not exceeded.

Parameter name: PUCCH bandwidth for CQI used for 20M CBRS cell
Description: This parameter defines the PUCCH bandwidth for CQI used for 20M CBRS cell.  This parameter is the number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b/3.    This parameter is part of the set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called MaxPucchResourceSize20M for 20M CPRS cell. All other parameters are related to each other according to this formula:  Note: in the formula below the term chBw shall be considered in # of PRB and not in MHz!    MaxPucchResourceSize20M = nCqiRb20M + roundup{[ (max((M-i-1)* Np +i*Np1 + rounddown (((12 * (maxNrSymPdcch-Yi) - X) * chBw - mi*roundup(phichRes * (chBw / 8)) * 12 - 16 )/ 36)) + n1PucchAn - pucchNAnCs * c / deltaPucchShift) * deltaPucchShift] / (c*12)} + roundup (pucchNAnCs / 8),  All other parameters in this formula are O&M parameters, while MaxPucchResourceSize20M is a calculated value that has a maximum allowed value, which shall not be exceeded.  Therefore the MaxPucchResourceSize20M is utilized to determine the correct offset allocation of the PRACH resources and to verify that the maximal allowed amount of PUCCH resouces per BW is not exceeded.

Parameter name: PRACH frequency offset for 10MHz BW CBSD Cell
Description: The parameter defines the location in frequency of the PRACH transmissions for 10MHz BW CBSD Cell.  For UL scheduling its recommended that PRACH is located next to PUCCH either on the lower or upper edge of the bandwidth because UL PRB allocation for UE consist of consecutive PRBs. If there is a small gap between PUCCH and PRACH PRBs, UL scheduler cannot utilize those PRBs effectively. prachFreqOffset for each bandwidth should be set aligned with the parameters determining the number of PRBs for PUCCH, so that PRACH is located next to PUCCH.    Defines the first physical resource block allocated for PRACH  In case of preamble format 4 for special subframe, prachFreqOff10M must be set to 0.  In case of preamble format 0, 1 and 2 for normal subframe, recommendation is to set value so that PRACH does not overlap with PUCCH RBs and is located adjacent to PUCCH, and thus recommended parameter alternatives are:  1) roundup(MaxPucchResourceSize10M/2) if it is located at the lower edge, or  2) ulChBw-6-roundup(MaxPucchResourceSize10M/2 if it is located at the upper edge of the PUSCH area    The MaxPucchResourceSize10M in above defines the maximum number of allocated PUCCH RBs, and it defined in nCqiRb10M parameter.

Parameter name: PRACH frequency offset for 20MHz BW CBSD Cell
Description: This parameter defines the location in frequency of the PRACH transmissions for 20MHz BW CBSD Cell.  For UL scheduling its recommended that PRACH is located next to PUCCH either on the lower or upper edge of the bandwidth because UL PRB allocation for UE consist of consecutive PRBs. If there is a small gap between PUCCH and PRACH PRBs, UL scheduler cannot utilize those PRBs effectively. prachFreqOffset for each bandwidth should be set aligned with the parameters determining the number of PRBs for PUCCH, so that PRACH is located next to PUCCH.    Defines the first physical resource block allocated for PRACH  In case of preamble format 4 for special subframe, prachFreqOff20M must be set to 0.  In case of preamble format 0, 1 and 2 for normal subframe, recommendation is to set value so that PRACH does not overlap with PUCCH RBs and is located adjacent to PUCCH, and thus recommended parameter alternatives are:  1) roundup(MaxPucchResourceSize20M/2) if it is located at the lower edge, or  2) ulChBw-6-roundup(MaxPucchResourceSize20M/2 if it is located at the upper edge of the PUSCH area    The MaxPucchResourceSize20M in above defines the maximum number of allocated PUCCH RBs, and it defined in nCqiRb20M parameter.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 frequency idle mode configuration identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC CDFIM.  It uniquely identifies a CDFIM instance.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT - AC barring factor for overload classes 0 to 9
Description: Access Class Barring - 0 to 9  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload classes 0 through 9. This parameter is used to determine the value of the ac-Barring0to9-r9 field of the AC-BarringConfig1XRTT-r9 Information Element (IE) broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload classes 0 through 9

Parameter name: AC Barring 0To9 adaption
Description: The switch enable/disable the SIB8 acBarring0To9 adaption.  FALSE means that ac-Barring0to9-r9 field of SIB8 AC-BarringConfig1XRTT-r9 is set to the value of acBarring0To9 of CDFIM rttAcBar/rttAcBarOvl.    TRUE means that ac-Barring0to9-r9 field of SIB8 AC-BarringConfig1XRTT-r9 is set to the value based on combination of both acBarring0To9 of CDFIM rttAcBar/rttAcBarOvl and ac-BarringFactor of SIB2 ac-BarringForMo-Data    The SIB8 acBarring0To9 adaption is applicable for:static AC Barring or automatic AC Barring for overload or RRC connection triggered AC Barring.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT OVL - AC barring factor for overload classes 0 to 9 OVL
Description: Access Class Barring - 0 to 9 when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload classes 0 through 9. This parameter is used to determine the value of the ac-Barring0to9-r9 field of the AC-BarringConfig1XRTT-r9 Information Element (IE) broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload classes 0 through 9.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT - AC barring factor for overload class 10
Description: Access Class Barring - 10  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 10. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 10.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT OVL - AC barring factor for overload class 10 OVL
Description: Access Class Barring - 10 when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 10. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 10.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT - AC barring factor for overload class 11
Description: Access Class Barring - 11  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 11. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message.It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 11.

Description: Access Class Barring - 11 when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 11. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 11.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT - AC barring factor for overload class 12
Description: Access Class Barring - 12  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 12. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message.It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 12.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT OVL - AC barring factor for overload class 12 OVL
Description: Access Class Barring - 12 when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 12. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 12.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT - AC barring factor for overload class 13
Description: Access Class Barring - 13  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 13. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 13.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT OVL - AC barring factor for overload class 13 OVL
Description: Access Class Barring - 13 when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 13. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 13.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT - AC barring factor for overload class 14
Description: Access Class Barring - 14  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 14. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message.It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 14.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT OVL - AC barring factor for overload class 14 OVL
Description: Access Class Barring - 14 when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 14. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 14.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT - AC barring factor for overload class 15
Description: Access Class Barring - 15  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 15. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 15.

Description: Access Class Barring - 15 when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for access overload class 15. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST' in C.S0004 for access overload class 15.

Parameter name: AC Barring for CDMA2000 1xRTT - AC barring Factor for emergency
Description: Access Class Barring - Emergency Calls and Emergency Message Transmissions  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for emergency calls and emergency message transmissions for access overload classes 0 through 9. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST_EMG' in C.S0004.

Description: Access Class Barring - Emergency Calls and Emergency Message Transmissions when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring factor for emergency calls and emergency message transmissions for access overload classes 0 through 9. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'PSIST_EMG' in C.S0004.

Description: Access Class Barring - Message Transmissions  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring modification factor for message transmissions. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message.It is the parameter 'MSG_PSIST' in C.S0004.

Description: Access Class Barring - Message Transmissions when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload. Description: Access Class Barring - Autonomous Registrations  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring modification factor for autonomous registrations. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'REG_PSIST' in C.S0004.

Description: Access Class Barring - Autonomous Registrations when automatic AC barring broadcast condition is met due to BTS C-plane overload.  Defines the 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) access class barring modification factor for autonomous registrations. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message. It is the parameter 'REG_PSIST' in C.S0004.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT NID roamer registration indicator
Description: Defines whether the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) Network Identification (NID) roamer registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration is broadcast. Value TRUE is to enable foreign NID roamers for autonomous registration. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT SID roamer registration indicator
Description: Defines whether the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) System Identification (SID) roamer registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration is broadcast. Value TRUE is to enable foreign SID roamers for autonomous registration. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT home registration indicator
Description: Defines whether the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) home registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration is broadcast. Value TRUE is to enable home (non-roaming) autonomous registration. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the homeRegIncluded parameter is set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Speed dep scaling factors treselection HRPD - HRPD cell reselection timer factor high mobility
Description: CDMA2000 HRPD Cell Reselection Timer factor if the UE is in High Mobility state.  The field tResHrpd is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in High Mobility state as defined in 36.304

Parameter name: Speed dep scaling factors treselection HRPD - HRPD cell reselection timer factor med mobility
Description: CDMA2000 HRPD Cell Reselection Timer factor if the UE is in Medium Mobility state.  The field tResHrpd is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in Medium Mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD band class list
Description: CDMA2000 HRPD frequency bands  List of CDMA2000 HRPD frequency bands. This structure may contain up to 32 instantiated quadruples of a hrpdBdClBcl, hrpdCResPrio, hrpdFrqThrH and hrpdFrqThrL.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD band class
Description: CDMA2000 HRPD Frequency Band (used in Band Class List).  Identifies the CDMA2000 HRPD Frequency Band in which the CDMA2000 Carrier can be found.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD cell reselection priority
Description: Absolute priority of the Bandclass of CDMA2000 HRPD  Absolute priority (0 means: lowest priority).    Equal priorities between RATs are not supported according to [3GPP 36.304].

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD reselection high threshold
Description: High threshold towards this Bandclass of CDMA2000 HRPD  This specifies the high threshold used in reselection towards CDMA2000 HRPD

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD reselection low threshold
Description: Low threshold towards this Bandclass of CDMA2000 HRPD  This specifies the low threshold used in reselection towards CDMA2000 HRPD

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band priority for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the CDMA2000 HRPD band class used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of CDMA HRPD band used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD neighbor cell list
Description: CDMA2000 extended Neighbor Cell Information for HRPD  Structure contains CDMA2000 Neighbor Cell Information for HRPD.  This structure may contain up to 32 instantiated quadruples of a hrpdCellId, hrpdArfcn, hrpdBdClNcl and hrpdExSel.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD frequency
Description: HRPD carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 Band.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD band class
Description: Identifies the CDMA2000 Frequency Band in which the CDMA2000 Carrier can be found.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD physical cell identity
Description: Identifies the CDMA "Physical cell identity".

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD NCL extension selector
Description: Distributes Physical Cell Ids between 3GPP-R8 List and 3GPP-R9 Extension List.  "R8ListPartOnly" means, the related Physical Cell Id has to be placed in the 3GPP-R8 NCL.  "R9ExtensionPartPossible" means, the related Physical Cell Id can be placed in the 3GPP-R8 NCL, if all Physical Cell Ids with "R8ListPartOnly" are already placed in the 3GPP-R8 NCL and there is space left (up to 16 IDs allowed). Otherwise they shall be placed in the 3GPP-R9 Extension-NCL (acc. to ASN.1 rules)

Parameter name: HRPD pre-registration info - HRPD pre-registration allowed
Description: Defines whether the UE is allowed to perform pre-registration when the UE does not have a valid / current pre-registration. A value of false indicates UE is not allowed to perform preregistration in this cell.

Parameter name: HRPD pre-registration info - HRPD pre-registration zone ID
Description: Defines the evolved High Rate Packet Data (eHRPD) Pre-registration Information. This parameter contains the primary Color Code of the eHRPD Access Network (AN) which this Evolved Universal Terrestrial Radio Access (EUTRA) cell overlays. The UE uses this parameter to determine whether it should pre-register with the eHRPD network.

Parameter name: HRPD pre-registration info - HRPD secondary pre-registration Zone ID1
Description: Defines the evolved High Rate Packet Data (eHRPD) secondary pre-registration Information. This parameter contains the secondary Color Code of the eHRPD Access Network (AN) which this Evolved Universal Terrestrial Radio Access (EUTRA) cell overlays. The UE uses this parameter to determine whether it should pre-register with the eHRPD network. This parameter defines the first instance of secondary Color Codes which can be assigned to an eHRPD cell.

Parameter name: HRPD pre-registration info - HRPD secondary pre-registration Zone ID2
Description: Defines the evolved High Rate Packet Data (eHRPD) secondary pre-registration Information. This parameter contains the secondary Color Code of the eHRPD Access Network (AN) which this Evolved Universal Terrestrial Radio Access (EUTRA) cell overlays. The UE uses this parameter to determine whether it should pre-register with the eHRPD network. This parameter defines the second instance of secondary Color Codes which can be assigned to an eHRPD cell.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT multiple NID storage indicator
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) multiple Network Identification (NID) storage indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration. When this parameter is set to TRUE, the UE may store entries in SID_NID_LIST for each SID. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT multiple SID storage indicator
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) multiple System Identification (SID) storage indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration. When this parameter is set to TRUE, the UE may store entries in SID_NID_LIST having different SIDs. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT network identification
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) Network Identification (NID) associated with this cell for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT parameter-change registration indicator
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) parameter-change registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration. When this parameter is set to TRUE, the UE should register on parameter change events. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT power-down registration indicator
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) power down registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration. Set this parameter to TRUE for the UE to register immediately before powering down. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT power-up registration indicator
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) power up registration indicator for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration. Set this parameter to TRUE for the UE to register immediately after powering up. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT registration period
Description: Defines the time interval between timer-based registrations. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB registration parameters - CDMA2000 1xRTT registration zone
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) registration zone number associated with this cell for Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) pre-registration. This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT band class list
Description: CDMA2000 1xRTT frequency bands  List of CDMA2000 1xRTT frequency bands. This structure contains instantiated quadruples of a rttBdClBcl, rttCResPrio, rttFrqThrH and rttFrqThrL.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band priority for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the CDMA2000 1xRTT band class used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of CDMA 1xRTT band used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT band class BCL
Description: CDMA2000 1xRTT Frequency Band (used in Band Class List).  Identifies the CDMA2000 1xRTT Frequency Band in which the CDMA2000 Carrier can be found.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT cell reselection priority
Description: Absolute priority of the Bandclass of CDMA2000 1xRTT  Absolute priority (0 means: lowest priority).    Equal priorities between RATs are not supported according to [3GPP 36.304].

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT reselection high threshold
Description: This specifies the high threshold used in reselection towards CDMA2000 1xRTT

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT reselection low threshold
Description: This specifies the low threshold used in reselection towards CDMA2000 1xRTT

Description: CDMA2000 extended Neighbor Cell Information for 1xRTT  Structure contains CDMA2000 Neighbor Cell Information for 1xRTT.  This structure may contain up to 40 instantiated quadruples of a rttCellId, rttArfcn, rttBdClNcl and rttExSel

Description: 1xRTT carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 Band.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT band class (NCL)
Description: CDMA2000 1xRTT Frequency Band.

Description: CDMA2000 1xRTT Physical Cell Identity

Otherwise they shall be placed in the 3GPP-R9 Extension-NCL (acc. to ASN.1 rules)

Parameter name: Speed dep scaling factors treselection 1xRTT - 1xRTT cell reselection timer factor high mobility
Description: CDMA2000 1xRTT Cell Reselection Timer factor if the UE is in High Mobility state.  The field tResRtt is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in High Mobility state as defined in 36.304

This parameter is broadcast in the RRC: SystemInformationBlockType8 (SIB8) message and is provided in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Description: CDMA2000 HRPD Cell Reselection Timer
