Parameter name: CMAS prioritization identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC CMASPRIO.  It uniquely identifies a CMASPRIO instance.

Parameter name: CMAS default priority
Description: This parameter defines CMAS default priority which is applied to all alert message IDs that don't have specific priority assigned. A smaller value indicates higher priority.

Parameter name: CMAS default segment size factor
Description: This parameter defines CMAS default segment size factor which is applied to all alert message IDs that don't have specific priority assigned.  If cmasDefaultSsf is configured to 0% then CMAS notification will be segmented according to minReasonableTBS, if cmasDefaultSsf is configured to 100% then CMAS notification will be segmented according to maxTBS.

Parameter name: CMAS message ID priority list
Description: This structure specifies a list of associated entries from message ID range to CMAS priority and segment size factor.

Parameter name: CMAS priority
Description: This parameter defines CMAS priority associated with a range of alert message IDs. A smaller value indicates higher priority.

Parameter name: CMAS segment size factor
Description: This parameter defines CMAS segment size factor associated with a range of alert message IDs.  If cmasSsf is configured to 0% then CMAS notification will be segmented according to minReasonableTBS, if cmasSsf is configured to 100% then CMAS notification will be segmented according to maxTBS.

Parameter name: First message ID
Description: First message ID in the range of alert message IDs.

Parameter name: Last message ID
Description: Last message ID in the range of alert message IDs.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CoMP/CS configuration
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a COMPCONF object.    The instance defines the CoMP / CS configuration and allows to assign cells for the functionalities of LTE3102 and / or LTE3286.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Measurement based cell configuration
Description: This list holds the cells for which measurement based CoMP / CS feature LTE3102 and / or LTE3286 shall be activated.

Parameter name: A2 profile identifier
Description: Instance identifier of MOC A2PR used for the cell in same item. If no value is specified, the default profile definition in A2DPR is used.

Parameter name: A3 profile identifier
Description: Instance identifier of MOC A3PR used for the cell in same item. If no value is specified, the default profile definition in A3DPR is used.

Parameter name: LTE cell configuration identifier
Description: Instance identifier of MOC LNCEL in own eNB for which measurement based CoMP / CS feature is activated.

Parameter name: Supported CoMP / CS
Description: This parameter defines which CoMP / CS feature shall be activated for the cell in the defined item.

Parameter name: UL CoMP Flex Cell Occupancy In BB Pool
Description: Indicator of what portion of the BB pool hosting this cell is occupied by this measBased CoMP cell.  - This UL CoMP cell occupies a portion of the BB pool which is hosting that cell. This parameter enables changing the amount of the BB pool 'occupied' by that cell.  - The intended usage is that this allows more (or less) cells per BB pool where the amount of UL CoMP performed per cell is correspondingly more (or less) limited, e.g. with customer documentation/release notes feedback on what limits are needed.  + If the cell is allowed to perform more UL CoMP, then the portion of the BB pool occupied by a cell may need to be configured to be larger, so less cells per BB pool are possible.  + If the cell is limited to performing a smaller amount of UL CoMP, then the portion of the BB pool occupied by the cell may be configured to be smaller, so more cells per BB pool are possible.  Or from another perspective:  + If the portion of the BB pool occupied by a cell is larger, then less cells per BB pool may be possible, and that cell may be allowed to perform more UL CoMP.  + If the portion of the BB pool occupied by a cell is smaller, then more cells per BB pool may be possible, and the amount of UL CoMP in that cell may need to be more limited.  The operator may use this parameter to increase the amount of processing available, and UL CoMP performed by a cell.  The operator may use this parameter to decrease the amount of UL CoMP performed by a cell, so that the portion of the BB pool which is occupied by that cell is smaller, and more cells per BB pool are possible.    Changing this value may cause a temporary reset of this cell, and possibly other cells that are reallocated to a different BB Pool as a result of this change.    Possible values of this indicator of what portion of the BB pool hosting this cell is occupied by this cell:  - Legacy_Occupancy: This cell occupies a portion of the BB pool which corresponds to what would be the case if actCoMp = fixedULCoMp  - Flexible_Occupancy: This cell occupies a portion of the BB pool which would otherwise normally apply, i.e. would normally apply where actCoMp = measBasedCoMp  - SingleCell_Occupancy: This cell occupies a portion of the BB pool which will result in at most 1 cell per BB Pool.

Parameter name: UL CoMP Max Helper Egress
Description: For a 2 Rx cell, the allowed egress traffic as percentage of the maximum possible resource blocks that a single cell could provide if it provided all of its Rx of help, across its entire BW, to each of 4 different cells. Used to limit the amount of helper data sent by a helper cell. (Solution may impose additional restrictions. This parameter enables the operator to specify an upper limit on the parameter used.) For example, if the cell is a 2Rx 20MHhz cell, and parameter is set to 50%, then (on average across those cells) 50 PRBs on each of the 2 Rx may transmitted for each of the different requesting/serving cells, for a total of 4* 2* 50 = 400 RBs.  For a 4 Rx cells, the allowed egress traffic as percentage of the maximum possible resource blocks that a single cell could provide if it provided all of its Rx of help, across its entire BW, to each of 2 different cells. Used to limit the amount of helper data sent by a helper cell. (Solution may impose additional restrictions. This parameter enables the operator to specify an upper limit on the parameter used.) For example, if the cell is a 4 Rx 20MHhz cell, and parameter is set to 50%, then (on average across those cells) 50 PRBs for each of the 4 Rx may transmitted to each of the different requesting/serving cells, for a total of 2 * 4* 50 = 400 RBs.    Each UL CoMP "helper cell" receives requests for helper data from different serving cells. This parameter places limit on the total amount of helper data which the helper cell can provide in each TTI. If the operator wishes to reduce the amount of UL CoMP traffic provided by this cell over the gigabit ethernet network, then operator can decrease this parameter.

Parameter name: UL CoMP Max Helper Ingress
Description: Allowed ingress traffic as percentage of the maximum possible resource blocks that the cell could receive if the cell requests the entire BW of that cell, from the maximum number of cells, i.e. supporting eight Rx IRC with a total of 6Rx received if it is a 2 Rx cell, or total of 4Rx received if it is a 4 Rx cell. This is used to limit the amount of helper data requested by and received by a single serving cell. (Solution may impose additional restrictions. This parameter enables the operator to specify an upper limit on the parameter used.) For example, a) if the cell is a 2Rx 20MHhz cell, and parameter is set to 50%, then 50 PRBs on each of the 6 different Rx may be received for a total of 6 * 50 = 300 RBs, b) if the cell is a 4Rx 20MHhz cell, and parameter is set to 50%, then 50 PRBs on each of the 4 different Rx may be received for a total of 4 * 50 = 200 RBs.    Each UL CoMP transmits requests for helper data from one or more different helper cells. This parameter places a limit on the total amount of helper data which the serving cell can request during each TTI. If the operator wishes to reduce the amount of UL CoMP traffic received by this cell over the gigabit ethernet network, then operator can decrease this parameter.

Parameter name: UL CoMP Max Number of Helpers per Cell Per TTI
Description: Maximum number of different helper cells requested by this cell during any TTI.  This parameter enables the operator to specify an upper limit on the value used. (Solution may impose other/additional restrictions, e.g. the actual number of different helper cells requested by this cell in any TTI will also be no larger than the candidate set, and no larger than the ulCoMpMaxCandidateSetLimit.)  In each TTI, each serving cell may request helper data from a number of different reception set helper cells for the UEs in that cell. Different UEs may have different reception sets, i.e. use helper data from different cells.  This parameter limits the maximum total number of different helper cells (across all of the different reception sets for the different UEs in that cell using UL CoMP in that TTI) which may be requested by that cell to provide help to that cell in a single TTI.  - If the operator wishes to reduce the amount of processing and/or network traffic loading resulting from different cells sending helper data to that cell in a single TTI, then this parameter may be reduced.  - If the operator wishes to allow more cell processing and/or network traffic loading resulting from different cells sending helper data to that cell in a single TTI, then this parameter may be increased.

Parameter name: UL CoMP Max Total Rx Limit
Description: Maximum number of Rx that this serving cell will include in any single UE's UL CoMP reception set in any TTI, where a Ue's reception set includes both the serving cell's Rx and the Rx at the helper cell(s) for that UE. (Solution may impose other additional restrictions on the reception set size for each UE. This parameter enables the operator to specify an upper limit on the parameter used.)  Each serving cell may request helper data for a UE from a group of reception set cells. This parameter limits the maximum total number of Rx across the reception set cells (including the Rx number from both helper cells and the serving cell) for a UE.  Examples of use at both 2Rx cells and 4Rx cells:  - If this parameter is set to a value of 4 at a 2Rx cell, that will mean that at most one 2Rx helper cell can also be in a UE's reception set at that cell.  - If this parameter is set to a value of 8 at a 2Rx cell, that will mean that at most 6Rx of helper cells (e.g. (three 2Rx cells) or (one 4 Rx cell and one 2Rx cell)) can also be in a UE's reception set at that cell.  - If this parameter is set to a value of 4 at a 4Rx cell, that will mean that no other cells can be in a UE's reception set at that cell.  - If this parameter is set to a value of 8 at a 4Rx cell, that will mean that at most 4Rx of helper cells (e.g. (two 2Rx cells) or (one 4 Rx cell)) can also be in a UE's reception set at that cell.  If the operator wishes to reduce/limit the amount of processing and/or network traffic loading per cell by allowing only smaller Rx reception sets per UE at that cell, then this parameter may be set to a lower value.  If the operator wishes to allow more processing and/or network traffic loading per cell by allowing larger Rx reception sets per UE at that cell, then this parameter may be set to a higher value.

Parameter name: UL CoMP Max Candidate Requesters
Description: Maximum number of serving cells which can select a single (candidate) cell as an UL CoMP candidate cell. (Solution may impose additional restrictions.) This parameter enables the operator to specify an upper limit on the parameter used. Decreasing this parameter will reduce the maximum number of SINR query requests received by a single candidate cell, and will also decrease the number of different serving cells which can simultaneously retrieve helper data from the same single helper cell.    If there is the wish to reduce the amount of processing and/or network traffic loading resulting from SINR queries, then this parameter may be reduced. By reducing this parameter the amount of (SINR) messaging overhead traveling over the system can be reduced. This might be done for example, if the GbE statistics or the on-time arrival rates for helper data indicate there is a problematic amount of network congestion.  If there is the wish to allow each helper cell to receive queries from a larger number of different serving cells, then this parameter may be increased.  This parameter impacts to candidate set selector functionality, and it is calculated in some intervals, maybe every 15mins. Thus, even it is online modifiable, it is applied with some delay.

Parameter name: UL CoMP Max Candidate Set Limit
Description: Maximum number of cells that a serving cell will include in the UL CoMP candidate set in any TTI. (Solution may impose additional restrictions. This parameter enables the operator to specify an upper limit on the parameter used.)    Each serving cell can request SINR measurements from a group of candidate cells. This parameter limits the maximum number of such candidates, which can be queried by a single serving cell. The list of candidates is provided to each cell by a candidate selector function, which uses this parameter. If the operator wishes to reduce the amount of processing and/or network traffic loading resulting from SINR queries, then this parameter may be reduced. If the operator wishes to allow each serving cell to query a larger number of candidate cells for SINR measurements, then this parameter may be increased.  - This parameter impacts to candidate set selector functionality, and it is calculated in some intervals, maybe every 15mins. Thus, even it is online modifiable, it is applied with some delay.

Parameter name: UL CoMP SINR Alpha
Description: The parameter determines the filtering coefficient of the UL CoMP SINR measurements for averaging both serving cell and helper cell. As alpha increases, the existing average given greater importance, and the most recent instantaneous observation is given less importance, i.e. filtering time constant increases (more filtering).    The long term average SINR is calculated for a specific UE. At a high level, this is done based upon the instantaneous SINR observations, where the avgSINR is the current average SINR estimate for that UE, i.e. along the lines of avgSINR = alpha*avgSINR + (1-alpha)* SINR.

Parameter name: UL CoMP SINR threshold
Description: The received uplink signal from a neighbor cell is combined to the serving cell signal if its SINR is less than ulCoMPSinrThreshold below the SINR of the serving cell signal.    The recommended default value is for:  - 2RX CoMP: 10 dB  - 4RX CoMP: 15 dB

Parameter name: CRAN identifier
Description: Specifies the CRAN identifier of the cluster. The parameter is also the identifier of the class.    Flexi-BTSs allocated to same cluster shall get the same value.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CRAN gain configuration
Description: This parameter configures the CRAN gain, i.e., from which cells the RX-IQ data shall be used.    When configured to 'ON', the RX data of all internal as well as external helper cells are used. The CRAN gain is maximal.  When configured to 'OFF', only the RX data of the own cell is used. In this case there is no CRAN gain. In this case 2RX IRC combining is used an the application for all cells of the CRAN node.    IMPORTANT:  For maximal CRAN gain it is recommended to configure the value 'off' only temporary for test purposes.    Note:  CRAN-gain switching is supported only for FDD.

Parameter name: CRAN node identifier
Description: Specifies the node identifier within a CRAN cluster.    The value assigned shall be unique within the cluster.    Note: For LTE2662, the value shall be assigned to value '1'.

Parameter name: CRAN SINR threshold
Description: Signal-Interference-Noise Ratio (SINR) to be used for CRAN 8RX CoMP operation.  The received uplink signal from a neighbor cell is combined to the serving cell signal if its SINR is less than ulCoMPSinrThreshold below the SINR of the serving cell signal.    The recommended default value is 15 dB for 8RX CoMP.

Parameter name: Cell resource group profile identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a CRGPR instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Cell resource group subframe skipping threshold
Description: The parameter defines a threshold above which the resource utilization within a subframe (TTI) is considered efficient, in which case the TTI will be assigned to one of the cell resource groups (CRGs) in question. Otherwise, the assignment of the TTI to the cell resource group may be skipped.  The value '0' means disabling subframe (TTI) skipping.  This parameter is ignored if cellResourceSharingMode is set to 'selectiveTtiDonate' (FDD or TDD), 'selectiveTtiDonateEnh' (FDD only) or 'selectiveTtiDonateDlOnly' (TDD only). It is then replaced by the CRG-specific selectiveSkipThreshold parameters.

Parameter name: Default group
Description: Group that is used if there is no explicit assignment.    Online modification is performed if the profile is not assigned to any LNCEL or if the feature is deactivated in all assigned cells, i.e. if cellResourceSharingMode is equal to 'none'.  If a cell contains PLMN IDs or SPIDs that are not part of the assigned cell resource group profile (CRGPR) instance, the PLMN IDs or SPIDs are considered as part of the default group.    All UEs/traffic not being associated with a PLMN ID (no usual scenario known) or SPID is considered as belonging to the default group.

Parameter name: Group share list
Description: List of group shares. The list parameter allows reservation of cell capacity per cell resource group on a percentage basis.    If the parameter is modified then all cells referencing the profile and with cellResoureSharingMode not set to 'none' will be disabled temporarily.  Online modification is performed if the profile is not assigned to any LNCEL instance or if the feature is deactivated (i.e. if cellResourceSharingMode is equal to 'none') in all assigned cells.

Parameter name: Group identifier
Description: Specifies the group identifier as assigned in plmnGroupList or spidGroupList.

Parameter name: Cell resource group share
Description: Specifies the share of the cell resource group on a percentage basis.  For LTE1382, this parameter controls the CRG's share of various resources, including the TTIs assigned for scheduling.  If cellResourceSharingMode is set to 'selectiveTtiDonate' (FDD or TDD), 'selectiveTtiDonateEnh' (FDD only) or 'selectiveTtiDonateDlOnly' (TDD only), groupShare does not control the CRG's share of TTIs. Instead, the groupShareListSelTtiDon-minTtiShare parameter controls the minimum percentage of TTIs assigned by DL/UL schedulers.    IMPORTANT:  Because TDD has fewer DL and UL TTIs per radio frame, in order to have enough chances to be scheduled, TDD's value range shall be within 25 % and 75 %.  Lower bound 25% is decided based on uplink scheduling. If there are 4 UL TTIs per radio frame, it is expected that each CRG will be scheduled at least once per radio frame for both downlink and uplink, so CRG share is set to start from 25%.    Then upper bound is 100%-25%=75%.

Parameter name: Group Share List for Selective TTI Donation
Description: List of group shares. The list parameters allows to set for a CRG minimum and maximum TTI shares donation and TTI skipping treshold, on a percentage basis.

Parameter name: Group identifier
Description: Specifies the group identifier as assigned in groupShareListSelTtiDon.

Parameter name: maximum TTI share for a cell resource group
Description: This parameter is valid only if cellResourceSharingMode is set to 'selectiveTtiDonate' (FDD or TDD), 'selectiveTtiDonateEnh' (FDD only) or 'selectiveTtiDonateDlOnly' (TDD only).  It indicates the maximum percentage of TTIs that can be assigned to the CRG, on average.  As long as a CRG is assigned TTIs equivalent to its maxTtiShare, it is no longer qualified for receiving further TTI donations.  Setting minTtiShare equal to maxTtiShare for a CRG means that the CRG cannot accept TTI donations on top of its minTtiShare.

Parameter name: minimum TTI share for a cell resource group
Description: This parameter is valid if cellResourceSharingMode is set to 'selectiveTtiDonate' (FDD or TDD), 'selectiveTtiDonateEnh' (FDD only) or 'selectiveTtiDonateDlOnly' (TDD only).  It indicates the percentage of TTIs that is on average assigned to the cell resource group (CRG) if it has sufficient PRB usage (i.e. above its selectiveSkipThreshold). If the CRG donates TTIs to other CRGs, this percentage is not reached.  Setting minTtiShare equal to maxTtiShare for a CRG means that the CRG cannot accept TTI donations on top of its minTtiShare.

Parameter name: skipping threshold for CRG selective TTI Donation
Description: This parameter is valid only if cellResourceSharingMode is set to 'selectiveTtiDonate' (FDD or TDD), 'selectiveTtiDonateEnh' (FDD only) or 'selectiveTtiDonateDlOnly' (TDD only).  It defines a CRG-specific threshold above which the PRB usage within a TTI is considered efficient, in which case the CRG is qualified for having the TTI assigned. Otherwise, the assignment of the TTI to the cell resource group may be skipped.  The value '0' means disabling TTI skipping triggered by not reaching an estimated PRB usage higher than the selectiveSkipThreshold. Other triggers are still evaluated: even if a CRG has an estimated PRB usage below selectiveSkipThreshold, it can qualify for TTI assignment if other trigger conditions are fulfilled, like pending scheduling request, low-volume data with increasing latency. In such cases, the selectiveSkipThreshold is ignored. In particular, setting selectiveSkipThreshold to '0' does not disable such other triggers.    The PRB usage is calculated from the ratio of (estimated number of needed PRBs) over (average number of PRBs available, after all reductions), where the reductions include:  blanked PRBs, PRBs given to CatM or NB-IoT, DL: PRBs not allowed to be used under a configured EIRP reduction, PRBs not assigned from Baseband Pooling, UL PRBs used for TTI Bundling.

Parameter name: PLMN group list
Description: Assigns resource group IDs to PLMN IDs.    If the parameter is modified then all cells referencing the profile and with cellResoureSharingMode set to 'DLonly' or 'DLandUL' will be disabled temporarily.

Parameter name: Group identifier
Description: The parameter assigns the PLMN Id to a resource group.

Parameter name: Mobile country code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Country Code.  The Mobile Country Code parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.

Parameter name: Mobile network code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Network Code.  The Mobile Network Code parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.

Parameter name: SPID group list
Description: Assigns resource group IDs to single SPIDs and/or SPID ranges.  If the parameter is modified then all cells referencing the profile and with cellResoureSharingMode set to 'DLonly' or 'DLandUL' will be disabled temporarily.

Parameter name: Group identifier
Description: The parameter assigns the SPID or SPID range to a resource group.

Parameter name: Subscriber profile ID
Description: Single SPID value or first SPID value of a range which shall be assigned to a resource group.

Parameter name: Last subscriber profile ID of a range
Description: Last SPID value if a range of SPID values shall be mapped to a resource group.

Parameter name: CRM configuration information identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a CRMINFO (CRM configuration information) managed object.  This object provides information about the internal settings of the cells Common Resource Manager (CRM)

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: LTE-NR downlink sharing ratio: Maximum
Description: Assigned maximum downlink sharing ratio of MBSFN subframes and normal subframes assigned to NR for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: LTE-NR downlink sharing ratio measurement period
Description: Assigned LTE-NR downlink sharing ratio measurement period.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: LTE-NR downlink sharing ratio: Minimum
Description: Assigned minimum downlink sharing ratio of MBSFN subframes and normal subframes assigned to NR for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: DL resource sharing algorithm
Description: Assigned downlink resource sharing algorithm for LTE-NR DSS.    'DL PRB load based' -- DL PRB load reports are used to adjust LTE-NR DL share  'DL buffer level based' -- both DL PRB load reports and aggregated DL buffer level of all UEs attached to LTE/NR Cells are used to adjust LTE-NR DL share
Range and step: DL PRB load based (0), DL buffer level based (1)

Parameter name: LTE-NR downlink sharing ratio update rate
Description: Assigned LTE-NR downlink sharing ratio update rate.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: Target UL outer scheduling region
Description: Assigned Target UL outer scheduling region.  Value is valid in case LTE-NR DSS feature is activated

Parameter name: Selected PRACH region in automatic PUCCH allocation
Description: Selected PRACH region in automatic PUCCH allocation.  Value is valid in case LTE-NR DSS feature is activated

Parameter name: Random access response window size
Description: Assigned random access response window size.  Random Access Response Window Size parameter defines the window size for the random access response in TTIs.  Value is valid in case LTE-NR DSS feature is activated.

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS sharing pattern
Description: Assigned LTE-NR DSS sharing pattern.  CRM calculates this sharing pattern (80 sub-frames) based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Will be updated each time the EN DSS Cell Coordination is completed successfully.    The meaning of the symbols is:  L = fix reserved for LTE  M = MBSFN sub-frame for NR  N = Sub-frame fix for NR with LTE CRS signals  m = MBSFN sub-frame however for LTE MBSFN function  0 = sub-frame available for dynamic sharing    Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running.

Parameter name: SI window length
Description: Assigned common System Information scheduling window length.  Value is valid in case LTE-NR DSS feature is activated

Parameter name: LTE-NR uplink sharing ratio: Maximum
Description: Assigned maximum uplink sharing ratio of PRBs assigned to NR in a given TTI for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: LTE-NR uplink sharing ratio measurement period
Description: Assigned LTE-NR uplink sharing ratio measurement period.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: LTE-NR uplink sharing ratio: Minimum
Description: Assigned minimum uplink sharing ratio of PRBs assigned to NR in a given TTI for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: LTE-NR uplink sharing ratio update rate
Description: Assigned LTE-NR uplink sharing ratio update rate.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: Blanked PUCCH resources
Description: Assigned Blanked PUCCH resources.  Value is valid in case LTE-NR DSS feature is activated

Parameter name: Status of Common Resource Manager
Description: Status of Common Resource Manager (CRM)    Shows the current status of Common Resource Manager:  not connected -- cell is not connected to CRM / or link to CRM is not available  startup -- EN DSS Setup Procedure is running however not finalized successful  negotiation -- EN DSS Cell Coordination procedure is running however not finalized successful  running -- CRM is up and running and LTE NR DSS is applied to the cells  stopped -- CRM is stopped due to deactivation of LTE NR DSS feature by one RAT  failure -- CRM is reporting a failure case requesting operator intervention  emergency -- dynamic adaptation of sharing ratio is intermitted and CRM is using emergency sharing ratio.    Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated.
Range and step: not connected (0), startup (1), negotiation (2), running (3), stopped (4), failure (5), emergency (6)

Parameter name: LTE downlink relative scheduling weight
Description: Assigned LTE downlink relative scheduling weight.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: NR downlink relative scheduling weight
Description: Assigned NR downlink relative scheduling weight.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: LTE uplink relative scheduling weight
Description: Assigned LTE uplink relative scheduling weight.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: NR uplink relative scheduling weight
Description: Assigned NR uplink relative scheduling weight.  CRM calculates this common value based on the settings in LTE and NR.  Value will be updated after successful coordination of the LTE and NR DSS cell pair.  Content is valid if LTE-NR DSS feature is activated and CRM status = running

Parameter name: CSBIA identifier
Description: Instance identifier for the CSBIA

Parameter name: A3 offset for CSBIA
Description: Margin for intra-frequency better cell CSBIA.  Used in CSBIA measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the neighbor cell becomes better than the serving cell by the value of the A3 offset. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: A3 report interval for CSBIA
Description: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are sent as long as the specific criteria for the CSBIA measurement event A3 are met (Intra-Frequency).  This parameter defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the CSBIA measurement event A3 are met. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger for CSBIA
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the CSBIA measurement event A3 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report (Intra-Frequency).  Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS0 corresponds to 0 ms, MS40 to 40 ms and so on.

Parameter name: Bandwidth ratio of CSBIA
Description: Ratio of (PRB number of CSBIA region / all PRBs eligible for PDSCH transmission)  Configuration rules:  All PRBs eligible for PDSCH scheduling will be divided into two parts, one is CSBIA (Coordinate Scheduling for Beamforming Interference Avoidance) region, the other is none-CSBIA region. This parameter represents the ratio of (PRB number of CSBIA region / all PRBs eligible for PDSCH transmission)  - The realistic ratio will not always equal to the O&M parameter for percentage of CSBIA region as this should be rounded up to RBG size.  For example, with 20M bandwidth total 100 PRB, if the percentage of CSBIA region is set to be 30%, the CSBIA PRB number is 30. RGB number is not integer 30/4=7.5. Implementation will choose 7 or 8 in DL-S.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CSBIA Cell List
Description: The list contains LNCEL instance ID values as references to the cells (LNCELs)

Parameter name: Hysteresis A3 offset RSRP intra-frequency
Description: Related hysteresis margin for CSBIA better cell of intra-frequency RSRP.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Trace control identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC CTRLTS.  It uniquely identifies a Trace Control instance.

Parameter name: Trace reporting mode - Cell trace reporting mode
Description: Specifies the trace reporting mode used by OMS for sending Trace Reports for Cell Trace Sessions (Cell Traffic Trace) to NetAct.

Parameter name: Certificate type for TLS authentication
Description: This parameter defines the type (RSA/ECDSA) of certificate for Trace Expert - Subscriber/Cell trace.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: 3rd party trace reporting - 3rd party cell trace reporting
Description: Trace reporting support to 3rd Party Tool for Cell Trace.  This indicates the support for sending trace reports to 3rd Party address for Cell Traffic Tracing.

Parameter name: 3rd party trace reporting - 3rd party UE trace reporting
Description: Trace reporting support to 3rd Party Tool for Subscriber & Equipment Trace.  This indicates the support for sending trace reports to 3rd Party address for Subscriber & Equipment Trace.

Parameter name: Maximum UE trace sessions allowed
Description: The maximum number of UE trace sessions allowed.  This parameter indicates the maximum number of active subscriber UE trace sessions that can be supported by eNB.

Parameter name: NetAct IP address
Description: NetAct IP address    If feature LTE955 is activated, the operator must provide an IPv6 address, otherwise the operator must provide an IPv4 address.    For IPv4, the parameter has to be entered in dotted decimal format.    For IPv6, the parameter has to be entered according to formats specified in RFC2460.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).  Note: IP 127.0.0.1 is allowed. Parameter should be filled with IP 127.0.0.1 when TCE is NetAct.    IPv6 address ranges:  It is recommended to configure only an address within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).  Note: ::1 value can be used when TCE is NetAct.

Parameter name: OMS trace port number
Description: The Trace Port Number to be used while establishing trace connection (TCP) towards BTSMED (SOAM BTS or internally in the cOAM BTS.

Parameter name: MDT Subscriber Trace Obtain Location
Description: This parameter controls whether the eNB requests the UE to attempt to provide detailed location information. It is only used for UEs which are requested in Subscriber MDT configuration to provide GNSS location information in MDT Subscriber Trace session.  The UE is requested to attempt to have valid detailed location information available whenever sending a measurement report for which it is configured to include available detailed location information. The UE may not succeed e.g. because the user manually disabled the GPS hardware, due to no/poor satellite coverage. Further details, e.g. regarding when to activate GNSS, are up to UE implementation.    False - The eNB does not send the obtainLocationConfig-r11 field in RRC signaling to UE    True - The eNB sends the obtainLocationConfig-r11 field in RRC signaling to UEs which are GNSS capable, are 3GPP Release 11 (or higher) and are requested in Subscriber MDT configuration to provide GNSS location information in MDT Subscriber Trace session.

Parameter name: Vendor specific extension tracing - TA tracing
Description: This parameter describes whether tracing of instantaneous TA value as part of vendor specific extension tracing is enabled or not.

Parameter name: TCE ID to IP mapping
Description: Provides the mapping from TCE IP address {loggedTCEIP} and unique, corresponding TCE ID number {loggedTCEId} for MDT logged and also PLMN to with TCE is belonging {loggedTCEmcc, loggedTCEmnc, loggedTCEmncLen} and port number { loggedPortNum}. This mapping shall be the same in the whole network.

Parameter name: Trace port number for logged MDT
Description: Contains the TCP port number corresponding to TCE ( 3rd party tool ) which is needed to establish the socket connection for trace data transfer.

Parameter name: Logged TCE IP address
Description: TCE IP address to corresponding TCE ID number {loggedTCEId} for MDT logged.  If feature LTE955 is activated, the operator must provide an IPv6 address, otherwise the operator must provide an IPv4 address.    For IPv4, the parameter has to be entered in dotted decimal format.    For IPv6, the parameter has to be entered according to formats specified in RFC2460.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).  Note: IP 127.0.0.1 is allowed. Parameter should be filled with IP 127.0.0.1 when TCE is NetAct.    IPv6 address ranges:  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).  Note: ::1 value can be used when TCE is NetAct.

Parameter name: Logged TCE ID
Description: TCE ID number corresponding to TCP IP address {loggedTCEIP} v4/v6 for MDT logged.

Parameter name: TCE MDT mobile country code
Description: The Mobile Country Code parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code and is part of the PLMN identifier for TCE identification

Parameter name: TCE MDT mobile network code
Description: The Mobile Network Code parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code and is part of the PLMN identifier for TCE identification.

Parameter name: TCE MNC length in MDT PLMN identity
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC for TCE identification.

Parameter name: Enable TLS
Description: This parameter enables / disables TLS for protecting traffic for Cell Trace, Subscriber Trace and PCMD functionality.

Parameter name: Default TCE or 3rd party tool trace port number
Description: The Trace Port Number to be used while establishing trace connection (TCP) towards default TCE or 3rd Party Tool.

Parameter name: UE active trace sessions present flag
Description: This indicates if there are any active UE trace sessions running within eNB.  This parameter indicates if there are any active UE trace sessions currently running within eNB.

Parameter name: UE Trace Interface Selection
Description: This parameter allows the operator to choose the interface type for the subscriber trace session.

Parameter name: Trace reporting mode - UE trace reporting mode
Description: Specifies the trace reporting mode used at OMS for sending Trace Reports for User Trace Sessions (Subscriber & Equipment trace) to NetAct.

Parameter name: UE Trace TCE IP address
Description: This parameter indicates the IPv4 or IPv6 address of the default Trace Collector Entity Server used for LTE subscriber trace.    IPv4 address format: Dot-decimal notation(x.x.x.x).Example:10.10.10.10.  IPv6 address format: x:x:x:x:x:x:x:x.Example:ABCD:EF01:2345:6789:ABCD:EF01:2345:6789    Note: tceTracePortNum shall be used while establishing trace connection (TCP) towards ueTraceTceIpAddr

Parameter name: Differentiation for PUSCH closed loop power control identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC DPCLPC.  It uniquely identifies a DPCLPC instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Control for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - Differentiated high QAM ULPC settings applied for all QCIs
Description: This parameter selects whether closed loop power control differentiated settings for 64QAM and 256QAM are applied to all QCIs or just to the target QCI selected by the operator.  Parameter ulpcDiffSchControl-ulpcDiffTgtQci selects the target QCI and differentiated settings for 64QAM and 256QAM are respectively from structure ulpcDiffConfig64 and structure ulpcDiffDConfig256.  In case only 64QAM structure is configured, the 64QAM setting shall apply to all UE having 64QAM or higher modulation.  In case only 256QAM structure is configured, the 256QAM setting shall apply to all UE having 256QAM modulation.    This parameter is used when a UE is configured for UL modulation of 64QAM or 256QAM.    When ulpcDiffAllQciHighQam = 'true', any single QCI configured for a UE will use close loop power control settings per ulpcDiffConfig64 or per ulpcDiffConfig256, regardless of ulpcDiffSchControl-ulpcDiffTgtQci setting.  When ulpcDiffAllQciHighQam = 'false', a single configured QCI matching setting of ulpcDiffSchControl-ulpcDiffTgtQci will use settings per ulpcDiffConfig64 or per ulpcdiffConfig256. Note that in a multi-bearer per UE scenario, the settings for ulpcDiffSchControl-ulpcDiffTgtQci will have priority over all other configured QCIs.

Parameter name: Configuration of PUSCH closed loop power control for differentiation with 256QAM - Lower RSSI threshold for differentiated TPC decision with 256QAM
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation of PUSCH ULPC is enabled and UL modulation is 256QAM.

Parameter name: Configuration of PUSCH closed loop power control for differentiation with 256QAM - Lower SINR threshold for differentiated TPC decision with 256QAM
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled and UL modulation is 256QAM .

Parameter name: Configuration of PUSCH closed loop power control for differentiation with 256QAM - Upper RSSI threshold for differentiated TPC decision with 256QAM
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUSCH / SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled and UL modulation is 256QAM.

Parameter name: Configuration of PUSCH closed loop power control for differentiation with 256QAM - Upper SINR threshold for differentiated TPC decision with 256QAM
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled and UL modulation is 256QAM.

Parameter name: Configuration for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - Lower RSSI threshold for differentiated TPC decision per QCI
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled.

Parameter name: Configuration of PUSCH closed loop power control for differentiation with 64QAM - Lower RSSI threshold for differentiated TPC decision with 64QAM
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation of PUSCH ULPC is enabled and UL modulation is 64QAM (or more when no corresponding parameter for 256QAM is configured).

Parameter name: Configuration for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - Lower SINR threshold for differentiated TPC decision per QCI
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled.

Parameter name: Configuration of PUSCH closed loop power control for differentiation with 64QAM - Lower SINR threshold for differentiated TPC decision with 64QAM
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled and UL modulation is 64QAM (or more when no corresponding parameter for 256QAM is configured).

Parameter name: Control for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - MCS Delta Threshold for Up TPC with differentiated ULPC
Description: MCS threshold (delta from max MCS) for evaluating whether UE is eligible for power up TPC with differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control. This parameter configures an evaluation of whether an 'up' TPC outcome from ULPC decision matrix can be honored. If evaluation succeeds then 'up' TPC is sent to UE, else no TPC is sent.  For evaluation to succeed, averaged PHR > ulpcDiffPhrThresh and averaged MCS < (max MCS for modulation - ulpcDiffMcsThresh).    This parameter is used for:  - Any decision matrix quadrant with an 'up' TPC outcome.  -- This includes quadrants for ULPC decision matrix configured per structure ulpcDiffConfig64, ulpcDiffSchConfig, or ulpcPuschConfig.  - Independent of UL modulation. For all QCIs configured for UE.    A value of '0' for ulpcDiffMcsThresh disables the MCS part of the evaluation. A value of '6' is recommended for enabled evaluation.

Parameter name: Control for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - PHR Threshold for Up TPC with differentiated ULPC
Description: PHR threshold for evaluating whether UE is eligible for power up TPC with differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control. This parameter configures an evaluation of whether an 'up' TPC outcome from ULPC decision matrix can be honored. If evaluation succeeds then 'up' TPC is sent to UE, else no TPC is sent.  For evaluation to succeed, averaged PHR > ulpcDiffPhrThresh and averaged MCS < (max MCS for modulation - ulpcDiffMcsThresh).    This parameter is used for:  - Any decision matrix quadrant with an 'up' TPC outcome.  -- This includes quadrants for ULPC decision matrix configured per structure ulpcDiffConfig64, ulpcDiffSchConfig, or ulpcPuschConfig.  - Independent of UL modulation. For all QCIs configured for UE.    A value of '0' for ulpcDiffPhrThresh disables the PHR part of the evaluation. A value of '6' is recommended for enabled evaluation.

Parameter name: Control for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - Time interval for power command decisions with differentiated ULPC
Description: Time interval for sending averaged RSSI and SINR values to the differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control decision matrix to determine power corrections.  This parameter only applies for:  - actUlpcDiffPusch is set to 'true'  - PUSCH closed loop power control  - Decision matrix configuration in use (ulpcDiffSchConfig or ulpcDiffConfig64) per UE modulation and per QCI selected by ulpcDiffSchControl-ulpcDiffTgtQci and ulpcDiffSchControl-ulpcDiffAllQci64Qam.  Note that ulpcDiffReadPeriod does not apply for QCIs using decision matrix per ulpcPuschConfig. In this case the parameter LNCEL.ulpcReadPeriod applies.    The value range is split in two parts:  Values 10 ... 1000 indicate that discontinuous filtering is ON (i.e. during times of inactivity, RSSI/SINR target values will drift towards their window centers); filter read-out period = parameter value  values 1010 ... 2000 indicate that discontinuous filtering is OFF; filter read-out period = parameter value - 1000.

Parameter name: Control for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - QCI for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control
Description: QCI for which differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control parameters (structures ulpcDiffSchConfig, ulpcDiffConfig64 or ulpcDiffConfig256) are applied. For UE configured with multiple QCIs (and one of which is pointed to by this parameter), the power control decision matrix configuration for the QCI pointed to by this parameter has priority.    This parameter is used for any UE configured UL modulation.  If parameter ulpcDiffAllQciHighQam= 'true' and UE is configured with 64QAM or 256QAM, then parameters from structure ulpcDiffConfig64 are applied to any configured QCI regardless of setting for ulpcDiffTgtQci.  If parameter ulpcDiffAllQciHighQam= 'true' and UE is configured with 256QAM, and scheduled with 256QAM table, then parameters from structure ulpcDiffConfig256 are applied to any configured QCI regardless of setting for ulpcDiffTgtQci.
Range and step: DiffQCI1 (1), DiffQCI2 (2), DiffQCI3 (3), DiffQCI4 (4), DiffQCI5 (5), DiffQCI6 (6), DiffQCI7 (7), DiffQCI8 (8), DiffQCI9 (9), DiffQCI65 (65), DiffQCI66 (66), DiffQCI69 (69), DiffQCI70 (70)

Parameter name: Control for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - TPC Direction for Quad 1 of differentiated PUSCH ULPC Decision Matrix
Description: This parameter configures the TPC direction in quadrant 1 of the differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control decision matrix. Up= +1dB or + 3dB. Down = -1dB. Quadrant 1 means: estimated SINR > upper quality threshold and estimated RSSI < lower level threshold as defined by decision matrix configuration in use.    This parameter is used for all QCIs configured for UE. This includes quadrant 1 for UL PC decision matrix configured per structure ulpcDiffConfig64, ulpcDiffSchConfig, or ulpcPuschConfig; independent of UL modulation.    Notes:  - This parameter affects the 'up' vs. 'down' decision outcome from decision matrix quadrant 1. Output from any other decision matrix quadrant is not affected (i.e. is hardcoded for quadrants beside 1 and 9).  - If decision is 'up' then actual 'up' TPC command can be sent only if UE is allowed per PHR/MCS based evaluation. If this parameter is set to 'up' and UE fails PHR/MCS evaluation then no TPC is sent. If this parameter is set to 'down' the corresponding TPC is always sent.

Parameter name: Control for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - TPC Direction for Quad 9 of differentiated PUSCH ULPC Decision Matrix
Description: This parameter configures the TPC direction in quadrant 9 of the differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control decision matrix. Up= +1dB or + 3dB. Down = -1dB. Quadrant 9 means: estimated SINR > upper quality threshold and estimated RSSI < lower level threshold as defined by decision matrix configuration in use.    This parameter is used for all QCIs configured for UE. This includes quadrant 9 for UL PC decision matrix configured per structure ulpcDiffConfig64, ulpcDiffSchConfig, or ulpcPuschConfig; independent of UL modulation.    Notes:  - This parameter affects the 'up' vs. 'down' decision outcome from decision matrix quadrant 9. Output from any other decision matrix quadrant is not affected (i.e. is hardcoded for quadrants beside 1 and 9).  - If decision is 'up' then actual 'up' TPC command can be sent only if UE is allowed per PHR/MCS based evaluation. If this parameter is set to 'up' and UE fails PHR/MCS evaluation then no TPC is sent. If this parameter is set to 'down' the corresponding TPC is always sent.

Parameter name: Configuration for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - Upper RSSI threshold for differentiated TPC decision per QCI
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled.

Parameter name: Configuration of PUSCH closed loop power control for differentiation with 64QAM - Upper RSSI threshold for differentiated TPC decision with 64QAM
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUSCH / SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled and UL modulation is 64QAM (or more when no corresponding parameter for 256QAM is configured).

Parameter name: Configuration for differentiated PUSCH closed loop power control - Upper SINR threshold for differentiated TPC decision per QCI
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled.

Parameter name: Configuration of PUSCH closed loop power control for differentiation with 64QAM - Upper SINR threshold for differentiated TPC decision with 64QAM
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUSCH/SRS component; applied for selected QCI when differentiation for PUSCH ULPC is enabled and UL modulation is 64QAM (or more when no corresponding parameter for 256QAM is configured).

Parameter name: Discontinuous reception (DRX) identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC DRX.  It uniquely identifies a DRX instance.

Parameter name: Apply UL out-of-sync state
Description: Determines which UEs shall no longer receive TA commands and thus shall be actively sent to UL out-of-sync state if taTimer is not set to 'infinity' provided that bearer combination and applied DRX profile allows for this.  extendedDrxOnly: only UEs being configured with extended settings for the long DRX cycle, i.e. long DRX cycle durations larger than 80ms  allDrx: all UEs being configured for DRX provided that applied DRX profile allows  allUEs: all UEs independently of DRX configuration provided that bearer combination allows.  Note: if CB008220 is enabled, i.e. actCatM = true and dlChBw = '3 MHz', this parameter is recommended to configure to 'extendedDrxOnly'.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DRX apply device type
Description: This parameter determines whether the device type "noBenFromBatConsumpOpt" of the UE shall be considered for DRX configuration.  Such an UE does not foresee to particularly benefit from NW-based battery consumption optimisation.    If drxApplyDeviceType is set to "APPLY" and the device type is "noBenFromBatConsumpOpt", DRX will not be activated for this UE.

Parameter name: DRX profile 6 - DRX inactivity timer
Description: Configures the Inactivity Timer for DRX.  The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission.    Note: It is not recommended to set this timer to shorter values than the default value to allow for sufficient scheduling flexibility.

Parameter name: DRX profile 6 - DRX long cycle
Description: Configures the long DRX cycle.  The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.

Parameter name: DRX profile 6 - DRX on duration timer
Description: Configures the On Duration Timer for DRX.  The On Duration determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH.    Note: It is not recommended to set this timer to shorter values than the default value to allow for sufficient scheduling flexibility.

Parameter name: DRX profile 1 - DRX profile index
Description: DRX profile index.  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX profile 1 - DRX profile priority
Description: DRX profile priority.    Applied to identify the DRX profile to be used if a UE has multiple bearers established.  Note: Modification of DRX profile priority is not recommended; preparation for future use.

Parameter name: DRX off threshold for QCI1
Description: Threshold for the poor radio condition when DRX will be disabled for UEs using VoLTE (QCI1 bearer configured).  This threshold is defined in terms of CQI. If DRX is enabled for a VoLTE UE, and the VoLTE UE's corrected CQI value remains below this threshold for a sufficient amount of time, then DRX will be disabled for the UE.

Parameter name: DRX on threshold for QCI1
Description: Threshold for the good radio condition when DRX will be enabled for UEs using VoLTE (QCI1 bearer configured).  This threshold is defined in terms of CQI. If DRX was disabled for a VoLTE UE that is not in TTI bundling due to poor RF conditions, and if the UE's corrected CQI value remains above this threshold for a sufficient amount of time, then DRX will be re-enabled for the UE.

Parameter name: Short term inactivity factor
Description: Factor with which the DRX Inactivity Timer of the DRX profile as applied for a UE is multiplied in order to determine how long to keep a UE UL synchronized following last transmission of new data.

Parameter name: DSCP profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC DSCPPR. It uniquely identifies an instance of the DSCP profile (DSCPPR).

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DSCP marking table
Description: This structure provides a table for DSCP marking based on QCI and ARP.

Parameter name: Start value of an ARP range
Description: Start value for an ARP range.

Parameter name: Stop value of an ARP range
Description: Stop value for an ARP range.

Parameter name: DSCP value
Description: This parameter configures the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value associated with the QCI / ARP pair.  The DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target eNB.    List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal):  BE (=0),  AF11 (=10),  AF12 (=12),  AF13 (=14),  AF21 (=18),  AF22 (=20),  AF23 (=22),  AF31 (=26),  AF32 (=28),  AF33 (=30),  AF41 (=34),  AF42 (=36),  AF43 (=38),  EF (=46)

Parameter name: LTE-NR dynamic spectrum sharing configuration identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a DSSNR (LTE-NR dynamic spectrum sharing configuration) managed object.

Parameter name: Activate superfast coordination
Description: This parameter activates LTE-NR DSS superfast coordination.

Parameter name: Activate LTE-NR DSS support for VoNR
Description: This parameter activates LTE-NR DSS support for VoNR.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: NR cell for dynamic spectrum sharing
Description: Specifies the LNRELGNBCELL instance which shall be used for dynamic spectrum sharing with NR. In case NR is running in cloud, gNbDuId has to be configured additionally.

Parameter name: Next generation node B distributed unit identifier
Description: This parameter specifies the gNB-DU identifier of the partner NR cell. It uniquely identifies the gNB-DU, at least within a gNB-CU, and shall be configured only if the partner cell is on the cloud BTS.  This parameter in conjunction with dssNrCellId, define the partner NR cell.    This parameter can be modified 'online', however it is a subject to alignment with the 5G cell configuration. The value change has no effect until the next alignment is triggered, e.g. with lock/unlock operation on LTE cell or on NR cell.

Parameter name: LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio - Related hysteresis of threshold for MBSFN sharing ratio between LTE and NR
Description: Related hysteresis of threshold for MBSFN sharing ratio between LTE and NR

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS downlink sharing ratio - DL resource sharing algorithm
Description: This parameter selects the downlink resource sharing algorithm for LTE-NR DSS.    Following options are available:  0: 'DL PRB load based' -- DL PRB load reports are used to adjust LTE-NR DL share  1: 'DL buffer level based' -- both DL PRB load reports and aggregated DL buffer level of all UEs attached to LTE/NR Cells are used to adjust LTE-NR DL share (from release 23R4 onwards, this option is not allowed any more)
Range and step: DL PRB load based (0), DL buffer level based (1)

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS downlink sharing ratio - LTE relative scheduling weight
Description: Scheduling weight for LTE for calculation of the LTE-NR sharing ratio within common resource manager (CRM) for LTE-NR DSS.    This parameter can be modified 'online' however it is subject to alignment with the 5G cell configuration. This alignment is done by the Common Resource Manager within the LTE-NR cell coordination procedure, which is triggered after parameter modification. Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure. The assigned parameter values used within the system are reported within the MOC LNBTS/LNCEL/DSSNR/CRMINFO.

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS downlink sharing ratio - NR relative scheduling weight
Description: Scheduling weight for NR for calculation of the LTE-NR sharing ratio within common resource manager (CRM) for LTE-NR DSS.    This parameter can be modified 'online' however it is subject to alignment with the 5G cell configuration. This alignment is done by the Common Resource Manager within the LTE-NR cell coordination procedure, which is triggered after parameter modification. Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure. The assigned parameter values used within the system are reported within the MOC LNBTS/LNCEL/DSSNR/CRMINFO.

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS downlink sharing ratio - LTE-NR downlink sharing ratio: Maximum
Description: This parameter defines the maximum downlink sharing ratio of MBSFN subframes and normal subframes assigned to NR for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. eNB can re-configure the DL sharing ratio used for dynamic spectrum sharing between lteNrDssDlRatio-minNrDssRatio and lteNrDssDlRatio-maxNrDssRatio.    If minNrDssRatio is equal to maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.    This parameter can be modified 'online' however it is subject to alignment with the 5G cell configuration. This alignment is done by the Common Resource Manager within the LTE-NR cell coordination procedure, which is triggered after parameter modification. Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure.  The maximum achieved value depends on LTE cell configuration (e.g. SIB), so the requested maximum downlink share might be limited.    A value above 70% will enable the feature 'NR DL peak rate increase in DSS' which limits the number of PRBs used for LTE and gives the remaining PRBs to NR.  A value of 100% means, eNB will assign the maximum possible resources to NR.    The assigned parameter values used within the system are reported within the MOC LNBTS/LNCEL/DSSNR/CRMINFO.

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS downlink sharing ratio - LTE-NR downlink sharing ratio: Minimum
Description: This parameter defines the minimum downlink sharing ratio of MBSFN subframes and normal subframes assigned to NR for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. eNB can re-configure the DL sharing ratio used for dynamic spectrum sharing between lteNrDssDlRatio-minNrDssRatio and lteNrDssDlRatio-maxNrDssRatio.    If minNrDssRatio is equal to maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.    This parameter can be modified 'online' however it is subject to alignment with the 5G cell configuration. This alignment is done by the Common Resource Manager within the LTE-NR cell coordination procedure, which is triggered after parameter modification. Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure.  When minNrDssRatio is set to a high value, it may result in LTE-NR cell coordination procedure failure due to eNB or gNB system configuration (minimal needed resources required by a technology may not be enough to fulfill minNrDssRatio), thus it is not recommended to set minNrDssRatio to high values (especially above 70%).  The assigned parameter values used within the system are reported within the MOC LNBTS/LNCEL/DSSNR/CRMINFO.

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS superfast allocation performance enhancement
Description: This parameter indicates the eNB performance optimization mode of LTE-NR DSS Superfast Coordination feature. It is recommended to ensure the optimization to lower system load by reducing DSS messaging for minor changes in load and allocations.  This parameter can be modified 'online' however its value is aligned with the 5G cell configuration. The alignment is part of the DSS LTE-NR cell coordination procedure, which needs to be triggered with locking and unlocking of the LTE cell or the related DSS 5G cell. Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure.

Parameter name: LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio - Threshold to decrease MBSFN sharing ratio
Description: Threshold to decrease MBSFN sharing ratio

Parameter name: LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio - LTE relative scheduling weight
Description: Relative scheduling weight for LTE for calculation of the LTE-NR sharing ratio within common resource manager (CRM) for LTE-NR DSS

Parameter name: LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio - NR relative scheduling weight
Description: Relative scheduling weight for NR for calculation of the LTE-NR sharing ratio within common resource manager (CRM) for LTE-NR DSS

Parameter name: LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio - LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio: Maximum
Description: This parameter defines the maximum MBSFN subframe sharing ratio for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. eNB can re-configure the number of MBSFN subframes used for dynamic spectrum sharing between lteNrDssMbsfnRatio-minNrDssRatio and lteNrDssMbsfnRatio-maxNrDssRatio. Between 2 and 6 MBSFN subframes per radio frame are available for spectrum sharing (value range 20% to 60%).    If minNrDssRatio is equal to maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.

Parameter name: LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio - LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio: Minimum
Description: This parameter defines the minimum MBSFN subframe sharing ratio for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. eNB can re-configure the number of MBSFN subframes used for dynamic spectrum sharing between lteNrDssMbsfnRatio-minNrDssRatio and lteNrDssMbsfnRatio-maxNrDssRatio. Between 2 and 6 MBSFN subframes per radio frame are available for spectrum sharing (value range 20% to 60%).    If minNrDssRatio is equal to maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.

Parameter name: LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio - Threshold to increase MBSFN sharing ratio
Description: Threshold to increase MBSFN sharing ratio

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS uplink sharing ratio - LTE relative scheduling weight

This alignment is done by the Common Resource Manager within the LTE-NR cell coordination procedure, which is triggered after parameter modification. Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure. The assigned parameter values used within the system are reported within the MOC LNBTS/LNCEL/DSSNR/CRMINFO.

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS uplink sharing ratio - NR relative scheduling weight
Description: Scheduling weight for NR for calculation of the LTE-NR sharing ratio within common resource manager (CRM) for LTE-NR DSS.
