Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure. The assigned parameter values used within the system are reported within the MOC LNBTS/LNCEL/DSSNR/CRMINFO.

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS uplink sharing ratio - LTE-NR uplink sharing ratio: Maximum
Description: This parameter defines the maximum uplink sharing ratio of PRBs assigned to NR in a given TTI for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. eNB can re-configure the UL sharing ratio used for dynamic spectrum sharing between lteNrDssUlRatio-minNrDssRatio and lteNrDssUlRatio-maxNrDssRatio.    If minNrDssRatio is equal to maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.    This parameter can be modified 'online' however it is subject to alignment with the 5G cell configuration. This alignment is done by the Common Resource Manager within the LTE-NR cell coordination procedure, which is triggered after parameter modification. Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure. The assigned parameter values used within the system are reported within the MOC LNBTS/LNCEL/DSSNR/CRMINFO.

Parameter name: LTE-NR DSS uplink sharing ratio - LTE-NR uplink sharing ratio: Minimum
Description: This parameter defines the minimum uplink sharing ratio of PRBs assigned to NR in a given TTI for dynamic LTE-NR spectrum sharing. eNB can re-configure the UL sharing ratio used for dynamic spectrum sharing between lteNrDssUlRatio-minNrDssRatio and lteNrDssUlRatio-maxNrDssRatio.    If minNrDssRatio is equal to maxNrDssRatio, the sharing ratio is fixed to this value.    This parameter can be modified 'online' however it is subject to alignment with the 5G cell configuration. This alignment is done by the Common Resource Manager within the LTE-NR cell coordination procedure, which is triggered after parameter modification. Therefore, the changed value of this parameter will be used within the next LTE-NR cell coordination procedure. The assigned parameter values used within the system are reported within the MOC LNBTS/LNCEL/DSSNR/CRMINFO.

Parameter name: Maximum resource blocks allocated to LTE SIB in DSS cell
Description: This parameter defines the amount of resource blocks that can be allocated to LTE system information when DSS is active and the requested sharing ratio allows to reuse all LTE subframes in frequency division multiplexing scheme. When this parameter is set to a value different from '0' the LTE system information broadcast messages 5,15 and 24 are truncated to the size derived from the configured amount of resource blocks and coding rate.  To achieve optimal performance the value shall be set in RBG (resource block group) steps, which is 3RB for 10 MHz and 4RB in 15 MHz and 20 MHz. Additionally when this parameter is set to value other than '0' the amount of SIB repetitions is limited to 2.    Special value '0' must be set if maximum DL sharing ratio (lteNrDssDlRatio-maxNrDssRatio) is configured less than or equal to 70%.  When set to special value the SIB size and repetitions are not limited.

Parameter name: LTE-NR MBSFN subframe sharing ratio - Minimum period for changing the number of shared MBSFN subframes
Description: This is the minimum period for changing the number of MBSFN subframes shared with NR within a radio frame.

Parameter name: Extended Access Barring profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC EABPR. It uniquely identifies an EABPR instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Auto Extended Access Barring - Auto Extended Access Barring list of access classes
Description: Access class barring list (10 bits) for AC 0-9.  For example, AC0 = 0000000001, AC1 = 0000000010, AC2 = 0000000100, AC3 = 0000001000, AC4 = 0000010000, ... and AC9 = 1000000000 . Note: The parameter value stored in the eNB is not designed to match the IE layout in SIB messages, e.g. the stored value AC0=0000000001 will be sent in SIB as 1000000000.

Parameter name: Auto Extended Access Barring - Auto Extended Access Barring category
Description: Indicates the category of UEs for which EAB applies.

Parameter name: Auto Extended Access Barring - Auto Extended Access Barring Exception Data
Description: Defines whether Exception Data establishment cause should be barred or not

Parameter name: Auto Extended Access Barring - Auto Extended Access Barring list of special access classes
Description: Special Access class barring list (5 bits) for AC 11-15.  For example, AC11 = 00001, AC12 = 00010, AC13 = 00100, AC14 = 01000, AC15 = 10000. Note: The parameter value stored in the eNB is not designed to match the IE layout in SIB messages, e.g. the stored value AC11=00001 will be sent in SIB as 10000.

Parameter name: Static Extended Access Barring - Static Extended Access Barring list of access classes
Description: Access class barring list (10 bits) for AC 0-9.  For example, AC0 = 0000000001, AC1 = 0000000010, AC2 = 0000000100, AC3 = 0000001000, AC4 = 0000010000, ... and AC9 = 1000000000 . Note: The parameter value stored in the eNB is not designed to match the IE layout in SIB messages, e.g. the stored value AC0=0000000001 will be sent in SIB as 1000000000.

Parameter name: Static Extended Access Barring - Static Extended Access Barring category
Description: Indicates the category of UEs for which EAB applies.

Parameter name: Static Extended Access Barring - Static Extended Access Barring Exception Data
Description: Defines whether Exception Data establishment cause should be barred or not

Parameter name: Static Extended Access Barring - Static Extended Access Barring list of special access classes
Description: Special Access class barring list (5 bits) for AC 11-15.  For example, AC11 = 00001, AC12 = 00010, AC13 = 00100, AC14 = 01000, AC15 = 10000. Note: The parameter value stored in the eNB is not designed to match the IE layout in SIB messages, e.g. the stored value AC11=00001 will be sent in SIB as 10000.

Parameter name: EDRX identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC EDRX.  It uniquely identifies an EDRX instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: eDRX paging storm
Description: Parameter to define the distribution mode of RRC PAGING with systemInfoModification_eDRX in case of essential SIB parameter modification.    noPagStorm means that systemInfoModification_eDRX flag will be carried only in Paging Occasions within the next BCCH modification period, together with normal systemInfoModification flag.    partialPagStorm means that systemInfoModification_eDRX flag will be carried in Paging Occasions within the next 2621.44 seconds where there are RRC PAGING messages for other purpose to be sent.    fullPagStorm means that systemInfoModification_eDRX flag will be carried in every Paging Occasion within the next 2621.44 seconds no matter there are RRC PAGING messages for other purpose to be sent or not.

Parameter name: Essential SIB parameter set
Description: Parameter to define the essential SIB parameter set applicable for RRC PAGING message with systemInfoModification_eDRX in case of modification.    MTServiceOnly means that only SIB parameters related with mobile terminated service will be taken as essential SIB parameter set for eDRX.    MTService&CellCamp means that both SIB parameters related with mobile terminated service and SIB parameters related with serving cell camp will be taken as essential SIB parameter set for eDRX.

Parameter name: Energy-efficient emergency activation PS group Id
Description: Instance identifier of the object EEEAPSGRP.    This parameter uniquely identifies the Energy-efficient emergency activation power saving group(EEEAPSGRP)

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: External alarm control input Id distinguished name
Description: This parameter contains the Distinguished Name of the external alarm control input identifier.  The value has to be given as distinguished name (DN).    Distinguished name can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or shortened one as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.  Examples:  EQM-1/APEQM-1/CABINET-1/SMOD-1/EAC_IN-1  SMOD-1/EAC_IN-1    Note: Distinguished Name relation can be only made to SMOD/EAC_IN instance

Parameter name: Energy-efficient emergency activation cell list
Description: This parameter specifies list of cells entitled to be switch on from power saving state in case of external alarm.    Each item on this list must correspond to existing lnCelId.  In case of external alarm(for example fire alarm) cells, with its lnCelId on this list, will be brought On-line form power saving state.

Parameter name: B1-NR measurement configuration identifier (default)
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC ENDCDMEASCONF  It uniquely identifies a ENDCDMEASCONF instance.    ENDCDMEASCONF holds all the parameters for measurement configuration for NR Dual Connectivity in default profile NRDCDPR.

Parameter name: B1-NR beam level report quantity
Description: Specifies the B1-NR beam level report quantity according to 3GPP 38.215  Depending on the selection, the corresponding thresholds b1NrBeamThreshRsrp or b1NrBeamThreshRsrq need to be configured.

Parameter name: Threshold RSRP for B1-NR beam level measurements
Description: RSRP threshold for B1-NR beam level measurements.  Set in nr-RSRP-r15 of threshRS-Index-r15 IE of ReportConfigInterRAT for B1-NR measurement.

Parameter name: Threshold RSRQ for B1-NR beam level measurements
Description: RSRQ threshold for B1-NR beam level measurements.  Set in nr-RSRQ-r15 of threshRS-Index-r15 IE of ReportConfigInterRAT for B1-NR measurement.

Parameter name: Maximum number of NR beams included in B1-NR measurement report
Description: Maximum number of NR beams included in B1-NR measurement report

Parameter name: Purpose of B1 NR carrier measurements
Description: This parameter determines whether the associated NR carrier is measured by any UE candidate for EN-DC connection establishment (value 0), or only by the UE candidate for NR coverage based EN-DC handover, when located outside EN-DC NR coverage area (value 1), determined by parameter numB1CyclesWoEndc.
Range and step: EN-DC and EN-DC steering (0), EN-DC steering only (1)

Parameter name: B1-NR report amount
Description: Report amount for B1-NR measurements

Parameter name: B1-NR report interval
Description: Report interval for B1-NR measurements

Parameter name: B1 RSRP threshold for NR DC
Description: RSRP threshold of neighbor NR cell for triggering of B1 event.  Set in nr-RSRP-r15 of B1 event of ReportConfigInterRAT for NR frequency measurement.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 38.133:  * -156 dBm means a threshold lower than -156 dBm  * values between -155 dBm and -30 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -29 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -30 dBm

Parameter name: B1 RSRQ threshold for NR DC
Description: RSRQ threshold of neighbor NR cell for triggering of B1 event.  Set in nr-RSRQ-r15 of B1 event of ReportConfigInterRAT for NR frequency measurement.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 38.133:  - -43.5 dB means a threshold lower than -43 dB  - values between -43 dB and 19.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - 20 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 20 dB

Parameter name: B1 NR DC RSRP Time to trigger
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the NR measurement RSRP triggered event B1 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: B1 NR DC RSRQ Time to trigger
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the NR measurement RSRQ triggered event B1 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: B1 Trigger Quantity for NR DC
Description: Defines which quantity (RSRP or RSRQ) the UE has to use for triggering an event B1 measurement report for NR dual connectivity measurements.

Parameter name: NR DC carrier frequency
Description: Identifies the SSB frequency to be measured.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Threshold of 5G drops before blocking of B1-NR measurements
Description: Threshold of number of 5G drops before blocking of B1-NR measurements for this NR carrier.    If that number of 5G drops (Reception of X2AP:SgNBReleaseRequired with cause code "Radio connection with UE lost") exceeds the value of endcNrDropThresh within endcNrDropWaitTimer, then that UE will not be eligible for EN-DC service during the duration of endcNrDropThreshTimer for that specific carrier. eNB will not configure any B1-measurements for UEs which have exceeded the drop count configurable value.    Special value 0 disables the blocking of B1-NR measurements for this NR carrier.

Parameter name: Duration for blocking of B1-NR measurements
Description: Duration for blocking of B1-NR measurements for this NR carrier after exceeding the endcNrDropThres.    If the number of 5G drops (Reception of X2AP:SgNBReleaseRequired with cause code "Radio connection with UE lost") exceeds the value of endcNrDropThresh within endcNrDropWaitTimer, then that UE will not be eligible for EN-DC service during the duration of endcNrDropThreshTimer for that specific carrier. eNB will not configure any B1-measurements for UEs which have exceeded the drop count configurable value.    A value of 0s indicates that the UE is blocked from performing B1-NR for that specific carrier for the whole duration of RRC Connection immediately after exceeding the endcNrDropThres.

Parameter name: Period for counting NR drops
Description: This parameter defines the time window during which NR drops are counted for this NR carrier.    A value of 0ms indicates that the eNB does not consider the drop window, but accumulates endcNrDropCounter for the entire duration of the ENDC for that carrier.

Parameter name: Frequency Band Indicator NR list
Description: Contains the NR frequency bands with their respective priority at which the NR carrier frequency of the same ENDCMEASCONF MOC (ENDCMEASCONF-carrierFreqNrCell) operates.

Parameter name: Frequency Band Indicator NR
Description: Indicates the NR operating band as defined in TS 38.101.

Parameter name: priority of NR frequency band
Description: Defines the priority of the NR frequency band.  The lower the value, the higher the frequency band priority.    When actMfbiNr is 'true' eNB selects for the measurement object of an NR carrier frequency the respective frequency band with the highest priority which is supported by UE. If no matching frequency band is found, no NR measurement will be activated for this NR carrier frequency.    When actMfbiNr is 'false' eNB selects for the measurement object of an NR carrier frequency the respective frequency band with the highest priority. If the UE does not support it, NR measurements on that NR carrier will be not activated.

Parameter name: Hysteresis RSRP for B1 NR DC
Description: Hysteresis for RSRP triggered B1 event for NR measurements for dual connectivity.    Parameter is used in the entry and exit condition of event B1 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Hysteresis RSRQ for B1 NR DC
Description: Hysteresis for RSRQ triggered B1 event for NR measurements for dual connectivity.    Parameter is used in the entry and exit condition of event B1 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: NR carrier priority
Description: Priority of NR carrier for EN-DC target selection.    A value of 1 means lowest, 8 is highest priority.

Parameter name: NR PCI neighbor relation addition hysteresis
Description: Defines the NR carrier specific hysteresis multiplier that is used to adjust the internal counter (nrPciCount) that tracks the number of times a particular NR PCI has been reported in measurement reports.  A value of 1.0000 would disable the hysteresis multiplier functionality for this NR carrier. See nrPciNbrRelAddThresh parameter for additional information on usage.

Parameter name: NR PCI neighbor relation addition threshold
Description: Defines the NR carrier specific threshold that when exceeded allows a particular PCI to be considered for automatic neighbor relation addition. The internal counter (nrPciCount maintained for each PCI-Carrier pair, initialized to zero) is incremented by 1 every time the specific PCI is encountered in a measurement report, for the specific carrier. The internal counter (nrPciCount) is multiplied by nrPciNbrRelAddHyst every time the specific PCI is not encountered in a measurement report, for the specific carrier. When the internal counter (nrPciCount) value exceeds the nrPciNbrRelAddThresh for the specific carrier, the eNB will attempt to create a corresponding LNRELGNBCELL neighbor relation. A value of zero would disable the functionality for this NR carrier.

Parameter name: NR PCI neighbor relation removal threshold
Description: Defines the NR carrier specific threshold that, when reached, allows a particular LNRELGNBCELL corresponding to NR-PCI to be automatically removed. The internal counter (nrPciCount maintained for each NR-PCI/NR-Carrier pair) is multiplied by fractional value of nrPciNbrRelAddHyst every time the specific NR-PCI is not encountered in a measurement report, for the specific NR-Carrier and incremented by 1 every time the specific NR-PCI is present in the measurement report. When the internal counter (nrPciCount) value drops below the nrPciNbrRelRemThresh for ANR-anrNrNbrRelRemGuardTime, the eNB will remove corresponding LNRELGNBCELL. A value of zero disables the removal functionality for a particular NR-Carrier.

Parameter name: Quantity configuration index for NR
Description: Specifies the index of nrQuantityConfig.    The value of this parameter equals to quantityConfigId of one nrQuantityConfig instance in NRMEASDPR.

Parameter name: Duration for SS/PBCH blocks
Description: Duration of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks. It is defined in number of subframes.

Parameter name: Offset for SS/PBCH blocks
Description: Offset in subframes, of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: Periodicity of SS/PBCH blocks
Description: Periodicity of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.  Periodicity is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier
Description: Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier.

Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC ENDCMEASCONF  It uniquely identifies a ENDCMEASCONF instance.    ENDCMEASCONF holds all the parameters for measurement configuration for NR Dual Connectivity.

Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the NR measurement RSRP triggered event B1 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Description: Offset in subframes, of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: Periodicity of SS/PBCH blocks
Description: Periodicity of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.  Periodicity is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier
Description: Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier.

Parameter name: Forced switch off power saving group identifier
Description: Instance identifier of the object FSOPSGRP.

Parameter name: Forced cell switch off type
Description: This parameter indicates the forced cell switch off type.  - 'TimeWindow' means that selected cells are to be switched on/off according to the defined time window.  - 'LowVoltage' means that selected cells are to be switched on/off according to the defined voltage thresholds.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: LTE cell configuration identifier list
Description: List of LNCEL MOC instance Ids which are included in the forced switch off Power Saving Group.  lnCelId value must be unique in a forced switch off Power Saving Group.    Each item in this list must correspond to an existing lnCelId.

Parameter name: Low voltage cell switch off/on thresholds - Low voltage cell switch off threshold
Description: This parameter defines the Radio Unit input voltage threshold for cell switch off.    Note:  The defined threshold value is valid for all RMODs mapped to any lnCelId listed in lnCelIdList of the corresponding FSOPSGRP instance.

Parameter name: Low voltage cell switch off/on thresholds - Low voltage cell switch on threshold
Description: This parameter defines the Radio Unit input voltage threshold for cell switch on.    Note:  The defined threshold value is valid for all RMODs mapped to any lnCelId listed in lnCelIdList of the corresponding FSOPSGRP instance.

Parameter name: Time window cell switch off/on period
Description: This parameter gathers the time window cell switch off/on period parameters.

Parameter name: Forced switch off day of week
Description: This parameter indicates the day of the week for which the power saving period is defined for a specific cell.
Range and step: Sun (0), Mon (1), Tue (2), Wed (3), Thu (4), Fri (5), Sat (6), everyDay (7)

Parameter name: Forced switched off power saving duration
Description: This parameter indicates the duration of the power saving period for a specific cell.    The power saving period for a specific cell begins at the load-based power saving start time for this specific cell and continues for the defined number of minutes in this parameter.

Parameter name: Forced switched off start time hour
Description: This parameter indicates the hour information of the local time when the power saving period begins for a specific cell.

Parameter name: Forced switched off start time minute
Description: This parameter indicates the minute information of the local time when the power saving period begins for a specific cell.

Parameter name: GERAN frequency idle mode configuration identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a GFIM (GERAN frequency Idle Mode Configuration) managed object.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection GERAN - GERAN cell reselection timer factor high mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionGERAN is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in the high mobility state as defined in 36.304

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection GERAN - GERAN cell reselection timer factor medium mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionGERAN is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in the medium mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: GERAN cell reselection timer
Description: GERAN cell reselection timer

Parameter name: GERAN neighbor frequency configuration identifier
Description: Identifies GNFL (GERAN Neighbour Frequency List Configuration) managed object

Parameter name: GERAN frequency band indicator
Description: This is an indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator is not relevant.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: GERAN RAT carrier frequency absolute priority
Description: Absolute priority of the GERAN carrier frequency    Equal priorities between RATs are not supported according to [3GPP 36.304].

Parameter name: ARFCN value list
Description: Each ARFCN value explicitly listed

Parameter name: GERAN inter-frequency threshold high
Description: This specifies the threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency X than the currently serving frequency

Parameter name: GERAN inter-frequency threshold low
Description: This specifies the threshold used in reselection towards frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency

Parameter name: GERAN carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the GERAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: GERAN carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of GERAN carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: NCC permitted bitmap
Description: This parameter restricts the permitted Network Colour Code (NCC) for idle mode mobility.  Using default settings, no network is permitted.    A field encoded as a bitmap, where bit N is set to "0" if a BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is not permitted for monitoring, and set to "1" if the BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is permitted for monitoring; N = 1 to 8; bit 1 of the bitmap is the leading bit of the bit string.
Range and step: bits mask: NCC 7 (0), NCC 6 (1), NCC 5 (2), NCC 4 (3), NCC 3 (4), NCC 2 (5), NCC 1 (6), NCC 0 (7)

Parameter name: GERAN maximum allowed transmit power
Description: This is the maximum allowed transmission power for GERAN on an uplink carrier frequency.  Applicable for the neighbouring GERAN cells on this carrier frequency.  If pmaxGERAN is absent, the maximum power according to the UE capability is used.

Parameter name: GERAN minimum required receive level
Description: This specifies the minimum required RX level in the cell in dBm

Parameter name: GTPU configuration identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC GTPU

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: gNB IPv4/v6 addresses of neighbor gNB
Description: This parameter defines the list of en-gNB IP-Addresses (to be supervised).    "Transport separation for RAN sharing" not applicable on X2 interface for path supervision towards en-gNB    Both IP address formats can be used.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter acc. to RFC 4291.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).    IPv6 address ranges:  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).

Parameter name: Maximum number of unanswered N3 requests
Description: This parameter holds the number of unanswered GTP-U ECHO REQUESTs (within the time defined by parameter t3Response), after which a GTP-U path failure is declared. The parameter is only relevant in case GTPU path supervision is switched ON (parameter gtpuPathSupint has a non-zero value).

Parameter name: GTP-U path supervision interval
Description: This parameter holds the time interval between sending GTP-U ECHO REQUESTs, used for GTP-U user data path supervision on the S1 and X2 interfaces. It defines also if data path supervision is ON or OFF. Path supervision supported on X2 interface towards en-gNB only.    The 3GPP recommend GTP-U supervision interval starts with a value 60s.

Parameter name: T3 maximum waiting time for GTP-U responses
Description: This parameter holds the maximum waiting time for GTP-U ECHO RESPONSE messages, used for GTP-U data path supervision on the S1 and X2 interfaces. This parameter is only relevant in case GTP-U path supervision is switched ON (parameter gtpuPathSupint has a non-zero value). Path supervision supported on X2 interface towards en-gNB only.

Parameter name: SGW IP address list
Description: This parameter defines the S-GW IP-Address (to be supervised). In case feature "Transport separation for RAN sharing" is activated also the S-GW IP-Addresses for the additional transport network are also configured.    Also, the number of unsupervised SGW IP address(not configurable) shall be limited to 1024. Warning: Though unsupervised SGWs may be allowed to establish bearer (if included by MME/SGW) in eNB, it is recommended to configure these SGW IP address for supervision, since these unsupervised S-GWs potentially lack the monitoring of GTP-u path failures

Parameter name: Serving Gateway IPv4/v6 address
Description: Application IPv4/v6 address of the serving SAE gateway (S-GW) for which datapath supervision is switched on.  Both IP address formats can be used.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter acc. to RFC 4291.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).    IPv6 address ranges:  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).

Parameter name: Transport network identifier
Description: This parameter holds the identifier for the transport network to which the S-GW belongs.

Parameter name: Trusted firewall S-GW IP address list
Description: This parameter contains the manually configured list of remote Serving Gateway (S-GW) user plane IP addresses for which the operator wants to allow access in the firewall. If the "Transport separation for RAN sharing" is enabled, S-GW addresses for the other transport network may also be configured.      Generally the remote S-GW user plane IP addresses are communicated via control signaling and the firewall is opened at that point, but there are cases in which this does not occur. The operator can use this structure to manually open the firewall for specific IP addresses.    Note that those S-GW GTP-U paths for which the eNB is configured to supervise (as configured in sgwIpAddressList in the GTPU MOC) do not need to be configured in this parameter.

Parameter name: S-GW IP address
Description: This parameter contains the manually configured Serving Gateway (S-GW) remote user plane IP address for which the operator wants to allow access in the firewall.    For IPv4, the parameter has to be entered in dotted decimal format.    For IPv6, the parameter has to be entered according to formats specified in RFC4291.    Wildcarding is not allowed.

Parameter name: Transport network identifier
Description: This parameter holds the identifier for the transport network to which the S-GW belongs.

Parameter name: UDP maximum datagram size
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of octets of a UDP datagram excluding the UDP header in the transport layer. This value is used to determine the MSS for clamping of end user TCP traffic. The maximum segment size due to clamping is udpMaxDatagramSize - 16 (GTP-U) - 20/40 (IPv4/v6) - 20 (TCP).

Parameter name: Home eNB(s) PLMN Map identifier
Description: Uniquely identifies a HENBPLMNMAP instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Further PLMN identity list
Description: Further PLMN IDs of the home eNB(s).  These are further PLMN IDs of the home eNB(s). The parameter indicates which operators' (PLMNID) networks are available from the home eNB(s). These PLMN identities have a home eNB carrier frequency scope.  The primary PLMN ID has to be provided separately for the home eNB(s).

Parameter name: MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the further PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the further PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC length
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity - MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity - MNC length
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC.

Parameter name: Intra frequency idle mode configuration identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely Identifies an IAFIM (Intra-Frequency Idle Mode configuration) managed object.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency blacklisted cell list
Description: Defines the intra-frequency blacklisted cell list.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Number of PCI in intra-frequency range
Description: Indicates the number of PCIs in the range (including startPCI). Value n4 corresponds with 4, n12 corresponds with 12 and so on. The UE applies value 1 if the field is absent, in which case only the physical cell identity value indicated by start applies.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Lowest PCI in intra-frequency range
Description: Indicates the lowest PCI in the range.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency neighbouring cell list
Description: Intra-frequency neighbouring cell list  Defines the intra-frequency neighbouring cell list.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Physical cell identifier in neighboring cell list
Description: The Physical Cell Identifier is a unique cell identification in a neighboring cell list.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Cell reselection procedure offset
Description: The parameter defines a cell-specific offset (in dB) that is used in the cell reselection procedure.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Intra frequency idle mode configuration identifier for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an IAFIMNB (Intra-Frequency Idle Mode configuration for NB-IoT) managed object.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency blacklisted cell list for NB-IoT
Description: Defines the intra-frequency blacklisted cell list for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Number of PCI in intra-frequency range  for NB-IoT
Description: Indicates the number of PCIs in the range (including startPCI). Value n4 corresponds with 4, n12 corresponds with 12 and so on. The UE applies value 1 if the field is absent, in which case only the physical cell identity value indicated by start applies.    The setting is commonly valid for NB-IoT UE.

Parameter name: Lowest PCI in intra-frequency range for NB-IoT
Description: Indicates the lowest PCI in the range for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency neighboring cell list for NB-IoT
Description: Defines the intra-frequency neighbouring cell list for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Physical cell identifier in neighboring cell list for NB-IoT
Description: The Physical Cell Identifier is a unique cell identification in a neighboring cell list for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Cell reselection procedure offset for NB-IoT
Description: The parameter defines a cell-specific offset (in dB) that is used in the cell reselection procedure for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency default group profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC IFGDPR and it uniquely identifies an instance of the Inter-frequency Default Group Profile (IFGDPR)

Parameter name: Selection method in default group profile
Description: This parameter defines the selection method of inter-frequencies in final frequency list  The default value is "weighted probability randomization" which the weight of a frequency depends on number of neighbour cells and relations
Range and step: fixed order within the group (1), weighted probability randomization (2), equal probability randomization (3)

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Group priority in default group profile
Description: This parameter defines the group priority within the default group profile

Parameter name: Group Size in default group profile
Description: This parameter defines the group size reserved in final frequency list  The default value is 0 which means the group is no place reserved in final list, the frequency within the group will be filled in the gaps without any reservation in final frequency list.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency dedicated group profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC IFGPR and it uniquely identifies an instance of the Inter-frequency dedicated Group Profile (IFGPR).

Parameter name: Selection method in dedicated group profile
Description: This parameter defines the selection method of inter-frequencies in final frequency list  The default value is "weighted probability randomization" which the weight of a frequency depends on number of neighbour cells and relations
Range and step: fixed order within the group (1), weighted probability randomization (2), equal probability randomization (3)

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Group priority in dedicated group profile
Description: This parameter defines the group priority within the final frequency list  The smaller the value the higher the priority, i.e value "1" means highest priority and value "11" means lowest priority.  groupPrio must be unique across all IFGPR instances contained in the same LNCEL..

Parameter name: Group Size in dedicated group profile
Description: This parameter defines the group size reserved in final frequency list  The default value is 0 which means the group is no place reserved in final list, the frequency within the group will be filled in the gaps without any reservation in final frequency list.

Parameter name: IMEISV based profiling instance identifier
Description: Instance identifier of MOC object IMEISV based profiling (IMEIBASEDPRF)

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: EN-DC aware IMLB configuration for NR Cells identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC IMLBNR.  It uniquely identifies an IMLBNR instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: NR cell configuration list
Description: This structure contains an NR Cell configuration to be used in EN-DC aware idle mode load balancing.  (In current release this list can contain only one entry)

Parameter name: B1-NR measurement is required for an NR band during EN-DC IMLB
Description: If this parameter is set to 'true' for a NR band, the NR band is only valid for EN-DC IMLB candidate PSCell if a qualified B1-NR report is received.

Parameter name: Band of the NR carrier
Description: Band of the NR carrier.

Parameter name: IRFIM identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an IRFIM (Inter-frequency Idle Mode configuration) managed objects.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: EUTRA frequency value
Description: eUTRA frequency (max. value ref to 3GPP 36.331 chapter 6.4) as EARFCN value

Parameter name: Enable A4 event for idle mode load balancing
Description: This parameter enables the A4 event to be used for measurement-based idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier frequency absolute priority
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRA carrier frequency    Equal priorities between RATs are not supported according to [3GPP 36.304].

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier frequency sub priority
Description: This parameter indicates a fractional value to be added to the value of eutCelResPrio to obtain the absolute priority of the concerned carrier frequency for E-UTRA.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection EUTRAN - EUTRA cell reselection timer factor high mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionEUTRA is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in High Mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection EUTRAN - EUTRA cell reselection timer factor medium mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionEUTRA is multiplied with this factor if the UE is in Medium Mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: EUTRAN carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in algorithm for Secondary target selection for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo IE. Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 3CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for 3CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in algorithm for Secondary target selection for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo IE. Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for 5CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest. Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in algorithm for Secondary target selection for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo IE. Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in algorithm for Secondary target selection for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo IE. Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRAN carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRAN carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing.  Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities or with dedicated priority value configured by operator.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.

Parameter name: inter frequency extension selector
Description: This parameter indicates the preference between 3GPP r8 and r12 version of interFreqCarrierList when populating an interFreq carrier. An interFreq carrier can be populated: 1)only in SIB5 interFreqCarrierFreqListExt-r12 IE(3GPP r12 supported) or 2) in either interFreqCarrierList(3GPP r8 supported) or interFreqCarrierFreqListExt-r12 but shall be populated in interFreqCarrierList IE first when possible.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency blacklisted cell list
Description: Defines the inter-frequency blacklisted cell list.

Parameter name: Number of PCI in inter-frequency range
Description: Indicates the number of PCIs in the range (including startPCI). Value n4 corresponds with 4, n12 corresponds with 12 and so on. The UE applies value 1 if the field is absent, in which case only the physical cell identity value indicated by start applies.

Parameter name: Lowest PCI in inter-frequency range
Description: Indicates the lowest PCI in the range

Parameter name: Inter-Frequency neighboring cell list
Description: This is a list of neighbouring cells with specific values for idle mode mobility parameters

Parameter name: Physical cell identifier in neighboring cell list
Description: The Physical Cell Identifier is a unique cell identification in a Neighbouring Cell List. It is used to indicate the physical layer identity of the cell, as defined in TS 36.211

Parameter name: Cell reselection procedure offset
Description: The parameter defines a cell-specific offset (in dB) that is used in the cell reselection procedure.  This specifies the offset between two cells.

Parameter name: EUTRA inter-frequency quality thresholds (Rel9) - EUTRA inter-frequency quality threshold high (Rel9)
Description: This specifies the quality threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency than the currently serving frequency.  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9.

Parameter name: EUTRA inter-frequency quality thresholds (Rel9) - EUTRA inter-frequency quality threshold low (Rel9)
Description: This specifies the quality threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a lower priority frequency than the currently serving frequency.  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9.

Parameter name: EUTRA inter frequency threshold high
Description: This specifies the threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency X than the currently serving frequency

Parameter name: EUTRA inter frequency threshold low
Description: This specifies the threshold used in reselection towards frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency

Parameter name: EUTRA presence antenna port1
Description: The IE PresenceAntennaPort1 is used to indicate whether all the neighboring cells use Antenna Port 1. When set to TRUE, the UE may assume that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighboring cells.

Parameter name: EUTRA cell reselection timer
Description: EUTRA Cell Reselection Timer

Parameter name: Neighbor cells configuration
Description: Provides information related to MBSFN configuration of neighbour cells of a non-serving frequency.  00: Not all neighbour cells of this frequency have the same MBSFN subframe allocation  01: No MBSFN subframes are present in all neighbour cells of this frequency  10: The MBSFN subframe allocations of all neighbour cells are identical to or subsets of this frequency  11: Different UL/DL allocation in neighbouring cells for TDD of this frequency.    Notes:  - Value 11 is not valid for FDD cells  - For TDD cells, 00, 10 and 01 are only used for same UL/DL allocation in neighbouring cells of this frequency.

Parameter name: Allowed measurement bandwidth
Description: The IE AllowedMeasBandwidth is used to indicate the maximum allowed measurement bandwidth common for all neighbouring cells on a  carrier frequency. The values mbw6, mbw15, mbw25, mbw50, mbw75, mbw100 indicate 6, 15, 25, 50, 75 and 100 resource blocks respectively.

Parameter name: Target cell min delta RSRP for idle mode load balancing
Description: Minimum delta RSRP value of the target cell to be considered for idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Target cell min delta RSRQ for idle mode load balancing
Description: Minimum delta RSRQ value of the target cell to be considered for idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Target cell minimum RSRP for idle mode load balancing
Description: Minimum RSRP value of the target cell to be considered for idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Target cell minimum RSRQ for idle mode load balancing
Description: Minimum RSRQ value of the target cell to be considered for idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Pmax neighboring EUTRA cells
Description: Pmax to be used for the neighbouring E-UTRA cells on this carrier frequency. If Pmax is absent, the maximum power according to the UE capability is used.

Parameter name: EUTRA frequency specific offset
Description: Frequency specific offset for equal priority E-UTRAN frequencies.

Parameter name: Min required RSRQ in inter-freq neighbor cells (Rel9)
Description: Minimum required quality level in inter-frequency neighbor cells.  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9.

Parameter name: Minimum required rx RSRP level
Description: Specifies the minimum required Rx RSRP level for the neighboring EUTRA cells on this carrier frequency.

Parameter name: Reduced measurement performance
Description: This parameter indicates if the neighbouring inter-frequency is configured for reduced measurement performance or not.

Parameter name: Inter frequency idle mode configuration identifier for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an IRFIMNB (Inter-frequency Idle Mode configuration for NB-IoT) managed objects.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Downlink carrier frequency EUTRA EARFCN number for NB-IoT
Description: eUTRA frequency (max. value ref to 3GPP 36.331 chapter 6.4) as EARFCN value for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Downlink carrier frequency EARFCN Offset of NB-IoT cell
Description: Offset of the NB-IoT channel number to EARFCN as defined in TS 36.101, for customer to configure the downlink carrier offset for the neighbor NB-IoT cell.  Note:  (1) If neighbor is inband cell, this parameter is set according to lookup table (neighbor's inbandPRBIndexDL, this parameter) below:  (1.1) If neighbor's host cell is 5MHz bandwidth:  2:-2  7:-2  17:1  22:1    (1.2) If neighbor's host cell is 10MHz bandwidth:  4:0  9:0  14:0  19:0  30:-1  35:-1  40:-1  45:-1    (1.3) If neighbor's host cell is 15MHz bandwidth:  2:-2  7:-2  12:-2  17:-2  22:-2  27:-2  32:-2  42:1  47:1  52:1  57:1  62:1  67:1  72:1    (1.4) If neighbor's host cell is 20MHz bandwidth:  4:0  9:0  14:0  19:0  24:0  29:0  34:0  39:0  44:0  55:-1  60:-1  65:-1  70:-1  75:-1  80:-1  85:-1  90:-1  95:-1    (2) If neighbor is guardband cell, this parameter is set according to lookup table (neighbor's guardbandIndexDL, this parameter) below:  +2392.5kHz: -2  -2392.5kHz: 1  +4597.5kHz: -1  -4597.5kHz: 0  +4702.5kHz: 0  -4702.5kHz: -1  +4792.5kHz: -2  -4792.5kHz: 1  +6892.5kHz: -2  -6892.5kHz: 1  +6997.5kHz: -1  -6997.5kHz: 0  +7102.5kHz: 0  -7102.5kHz: -1  +7192.5kHz: -2  -7192.5kHz: 1  +7297.5kHz: -1  -7297.5kHz: 0  +9097.5kHz: -1  -9097.5kHz: 0  +9202.5kHz: 0  -9202.5kHz: -1  +9292.5kHz: -2  -9292.5kHz: 1  +9397.5kHz: -1  -9397.5kHz: 0  +9502.5kHz: 0  -9502.5kHz: -1  +9592.5kHz: -2  -9592.5kHz: 1  +9697.5kHz: -1  -9697.5kHz: 0  +9802.5kHz: 0  -9802.5kHz: -1    (3) If neighbor is standalone cell, this parameter is set v-0dot5.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing for NB-IoT
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by the round-robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for NB-IoT.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting the target for redirectedCarrierInfo for NB-IoT load balancing.  Weighted round-robin algorithm shall select the target frequency for NB-IoT idle mode load balancing, which is matching NB-IoT UE capabilities.  The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: Pmax neighboring NB-IoT cells for NB-IoT
Description: Pmax to be used for the neighbouring NB-IoT cells on this carrier frequency. If Pmax is absent, the maximum power according to the UE capability is used.

Parameter name: Physical Cell identifier of Blacklisted Cell for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter defines a unique cell identification Physical Cell Identifier of Blacklisted Cell for NB-IoT. It is used to indicate the physical layer identity of the cell, as defined in TS 36.211 interFreqBlackCellList-r13.

Parameter name: Physical cell identifier of neighboring cell for NB-IoT
Description: The Physical Cell Identifier is a unique cell identification of a Neighbouring Cell for NB-IoT. It is used to indicate the physical layer identity of the cell, as defined in TS 36.211  Note: This parameter is not used.

Parameter name: q-Offset Frequency for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter defines the q-Offset Frequency (r13) for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Minimum required RSRQ in inter-freq neighbor cells for NB-IoT
Description: Minimum required quality level in inter-frequency neighbor cells for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Minimum required Rx RSRP level for NB-IoT
Description: Specifies the Minimum required Rx RSRP level for the neighboring EUTRA cells on this carrier frequency for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Inter frequency MBMS SAI  list (IRSAILIST) identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC IRSAILIST.  It uniquely identifies a IRSAILIST instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Downlink earfcn of the MBMS service area identity list
Description: Downlink carrier frequency the inter-frequency SAI list applies to

Parameter name: SAI list of inter-frequency neighbor cells
Description: List of MBMS service area identities (SAI) for inter-frequency neighbor cells

Parameter name: Downlink interference shaping profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC ISHPR and it uniquely identifies an instance of the Downlink Interference Shaping Profile (ISHPR).    If the feature "Downlink Interference Shaping" is activated, a default ISHPR profile with ISHPR-ishPrId = 0 must exist.

Parameter name: Activation of fast pref. resource inc. mech. for GBR
Description: Activates the fast increase mechanisms of amount of preferred resources for new GBR bearer arriving into the system.

Parameter name: Act. of fast pref. resource inc. mech. for non-GBR
Description: Activates the fast increase mechanisms of amount of preferred resources for new non-GBR bearer arriving into the system.

Parameter name: Activation threshold for interference shaping
Description: Defines a fraction of the resources being available for UE scheduling on PDSCH. If average PDSCH utilization falls below this threshold, interference shaping functionality is applied.

Parameter name: Freq. edge for blanked resources in macro cell
Description: Determines at which frequency edge the blanked resources should be allocated in a macro cell. A micro cell will use always the opposite edge.    Note: Used only for preferred alignment 'macro-micro'

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: High load limit for neighbor cell
Description: Load limit for considering a neighbor cell as highly loaded

Parameter name: Max. num. of cells for neighbor cell load info exch.
Description: Determines the maximum amount of neighboring cells from which to request neighbor cell load information internally or via X2 interface for eICIC.    Note: Value '0' deactivates the neighbor cell load information exchange.

Parameter name: Number of highly loaded neighbor cells
Description: Minimum number of neighbor cells in high load in order to apply interference shaping.

Parameter name: Periodicity for neighbor cell load info exchange
Description: Determines the periodicity with which neighbor cell load information is exchanged.

Parameter name: Alignment method for DL interference shaping
Description: Determines the alignment method being applied in DL interference shaping. Available options allow giving preference to alignment of neighbor cell interference by selecting for downlink resources preferred frequency domain area:  - either based on cell PCI number via module operation (pciModBased),  - or based on macro vs. micro cell type (macroMicro).

Parameter name: Lower threshold to decrease preferred resources
Description: Lower utilization threshold of preferred resources. If exceeded downwards, the amount of preferred resource is decreased.

Parameter name: Upper threshold to increase preferred resources
Description: Upper utilization threshold of preferred resources. If exceeded upwards, the amount of preferred resource is increased.

Parameter name: Lower Limit for preferred resources
Description: Lower limit for preferred resources. Preferred resources are not decreased below this limit.

Parameter name: Step size for adjusting the amount of pref. resources
Description: Determines the step size for increasing/decreasing the amount of preferred resources.

Parameter name: Restart period for neighbor cell load info exchange
Description: Determines a period with which to restart the neighbor cell load information exchange for eICIC.    The exact cells from which to ask neighbor cell load information will be updated only with such a restart.

Parameter name: Periodicity for interference shaping for update actions
Description: Determines the basic periodicity for interference shaping to perform measurements, update preferred resources, etc.

Parameter name: The instance identifier of LAA
Description: This parameter identifies the LAA instance.

Parameter name: CCA threshold for a specific country
Description: This parameter corresponds to the maximum energy detection threshold defined by regulatory requirements, i.e., to the "Xr" factor in the 3GPP TS 36.213 formula which defines "XThresh_max" when absence of any other technology sharing the carrier can be guaranteed on a long-term basis (see lteUWiFiCoexistence parameter for details).

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Duration timer for LAA cell kickdown evaluation
Description: Defines the time duration of the conditions to trigger the kickdown.  If the CCA success rate is smaller than ccaThresholdDpc and the unlicensed channel utilization [%] is smaller than utilizationThresholdDpc and these conditions will last for evaluationDurationDpc time, LAA cell kickdown will be triggered.

Parameter name: Frequency hold-off timer
Description: Frequency hold-off timer    This timer defines the minimum period of time between LTE-U /LAA cell carrier frequency changes.    Note: In high-load conditions, it is recommended to have a value greater than 20 minutes.

Parameter name: LAA SCell release timer for LAA in-device coexistence
Description: A nonzero value for this parameter starts a supervision timer upon receiving InDeviceCoexIndication message with hardware sharing indication from the UE and stops it upon receiving InDeviceCoexIndication message that clears the hardware sharing problem. Upon timer expiry the eNB releases the LAA SCells of the UE. A value of 0 deactivates the supervision timer.

Parameter name: Delay timer for LAA cell re-activation after kickdown
Description: Defines the time, after which a cell subject to kickdown will be considered for re-activation.

Parameter name: LTE unlicensed ITU region
Description: This parameter indicates the ITU region where LTE unlicensed has to operate. eNB will adapt the LBT and the transmission mode functionalities to the selected ITU region.

Parameter name: Load based PUCCH region default profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC LBPUCCHRDPR.  It uniquely identifies a LBPUCCHRDPR instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Countdown timer SIB modification by PUCCH compression
Description: This parameter specifies the countdown timer that defines how long it takes before any new SIB modification process may be triggered again by a PUCCH region compression.  It represents the minutes until the next compression possibility.    The configured value is used for all cells where feature LTE2664 "Load-Based PUCCH Region" is configured and no dedicated configuration in an LBPUCCHRPR is assigned.

Parameter name: Countdown timer SIB modification by PUCCH expansion
Description: This parameter specifies the countdown timer that defines how long it takes before any new SIB modification process may be triggered again by a PUCCH region expansion.  It represents the minutes until the next expansion possibility.    The configured value is used for all cells where feature LTE2664 "Load-Based PUCCH Region" is configured and no dedicated configuration in an LBPUCCHRPR is assigned.

Parameter name: Minimum number of additional UEs in PUCCH expansion
Description: The parameter defines the minimum number of additional UEs that should be supported in subsequent PUCCH configurations.    Note: A small configured value of the parameter will lead in case of UE attach requests simultaneously to RAC rejections.    Please note, the modification of the parameter value impacts all cells using the default profile value.

Parameter name: Lower threshold UEs in RRC connected
Description: This parameter specifies the lower threshold load for the number of UE in RRC_Connected mode where PUCCH compression will be triggered.    The configured value is used for all cells where feature LTE2664 "Load-Based PUCCH Region" is configured and no dedicated configuration in an LBPUCCHRPR is assigned.

Parameter name: Upper threshold UEs in RRC connected
Description: This parameter specifies the upper threshold load for the number of UE in RRC_Connected mode where PUCCH expansion will be triggered.    The configured value is used for all cells where feature LTE2664 "Load-Based PUCCH Region" is configured and no dedicated configuration in an LBPUCCHRPR is assigned.

Parameter name: Load based PUCCH region profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC LBPUCCHRPR.  It uniquely identifies a LBPUCCHRPR instance.    The parameter of this class instance define specific settings in addition to the default profile LBPUCCHRDPR.    If the LBPUCCHRPR instance is not referenced by APUCCH-lbPucchRPrId, there is no need to delete it from the configuration. The configuration is not used by the application.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Countdown timer SIB modification by PUCCH compression
Description: This parameter specifies the countdown timer that defines how long it takes before any new SIB modification process may be triggered again by a PUCCH region compression.  It represents the minutes until the next compression possibility.    If no value in the LBPUCCHRPR is configured, the value from the default profile LBPUCCHRDPR is taken into use.

Parameter name: Countdown timer SIB modification by PUCCH expansion
Description: This parameter specifies the countdown timer that defines how long it takes before any new SIB modification process may be triggered again by a PUCCH region expansion.  It represents the minutes until the next expansion possibility.    If no value in the LBPUCCHRPR is configured, the value from the default profile LBPUCCHRDPR is taken into use.

Parameter name: Minimum number of additional UEs in PUCCH expansion
Description: The parameter defines the minimum number of additional UEs that should be supported in subsequent PUCCH configurations.    Note: A small configured value of the parameter will lead in case of UE attach requests simultaneously to RAC rejections.

Parameter name: Lower threshold UEs in RRC connected
Description: This parameter specifies the lower threshold load for the number of UE in RRC_Connected mode where PUCCH compression will be triggered.    If no value in the LBPUCCHRPR is configured, the value from the default profile LBPUCCHRDPR is taken into use.

Parameter name: Upper threshold UEs in RRC connected
Description: This parameter specifies the upper threshold load for the number of UE in RRC_Connected mode where PUCCH expansion will be triggered.    If no value in the LBPUCCHRPR is configured, the value from the default profile LBPUCCHRDPR is taken into use.

Parameter name: LCS ID
Description: LCS identifier

Parameter name: Antenna gain
Description: Antenna gain.

Parameter name: Antenna opening
Description: The degree, having the direction of Antenna Orientation as the center.  i.e. Antenna Opening degree.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: LCS information
Description: Location information available/unavailable.

Parameter name: Maximum antenna range
Description: The maximum distance where the radio wave of the target sector can reach.

Parameter name: Potential repeater
Description: Repeater connection identification flag.

Parameter name: SFN initialization time
Description: Time in seconds relative to 00:00:00 on 1 January 1900 where the integer part is in the first 32 bits and the fraction part in the last 32bits

Parameter name: Terrain average height
Description: Terrain average height.

Parameter name: Terrain height standard deviation
Description: Terrain height standard deviation.

Parameter name: Neighbour eNB identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of the object LNADJ. This parameter appears only in the distinguished name (DN) in the plan file and is used for O&M purposes.  It is highly recommended to use for object creation the lowest free lnAdjId value within all LNADJ instances of an eNB. This is to avoid rejection of plan file activation due to colliding lnAdjId values if an LNADJ instance is automatically created by eNB because of activated ANR features.    Please consider following hardware related information:  FSMr2 supports at maximum 128 LNADJ instances per LNCEL.  FSMr3 supports at maximum 256 LNADJ instances per LNCEL.

Parameter name: Identity of neighbor eNB within PLMN
Description: This is the unique ID of the neighbor eNB within PLMN, where adjEnbId and plmnId form the neighbor global eNB ID.

Parameter name: C-Plane IP address of neighbor eNB
Description: This parameter holds the C-Plane IPv4/v6 address of this adjacent eNB.  Both IP address formats can be used.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter acc. to RFC 4291.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).    IPv6 address ranges:  It is recommended to configure only an address within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).

Parameter name: C-Plane IP address  control
Description: The parameter determines whether the C-Plane IP address of the neighbor eNB (X2 link) is statically configured or whether eNB is allowed to update the address based on information provided by ANR procedures.    oamControlled X2 link:  It is the responsibility of the operator to configure the correct cPlaneIpAddr.    enbControlled X2 link:  The IP address will be maintained by ANR procedures. It is the default value for neighbor eNBs which have been learnt via ANR procedures.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Neighbor eNB globally unique group ID list
Description: This is a globally unique group identification of the MME(s) connected to the neighbor eNB. The ID is received during the X2 setup procedure for the respective X2 link from the neighboring eNB.

Parameter name: MCC in PLMN identity included in GU group ID
Description: Mobile Country Code in PLMN identity included in GU group ID. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MME group ID included in GU group ID
Description: MME group ID included in GU group ID.

Parameter name: MNC in PLMN identity included in GU group ID
Description: Mobile Network Code in PLMN identity included in GU group ID. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity of neighbor eNB - MCC In Primary PLMN Identity Of Neighbour ENB
Description: Mobile Country Code in the primary plmn id of neighbour eNB. MCC and MNC build the plmn Id.  Mobile Country Code in the primary PLMN ID of neighbor eNB. MCC and MNC build the PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity of neighbor eNB - MNC In Primary PLMN Identity Of Neighbour ENB
Description: Mobile Network Code in the primary plmn id of the neighbour eNB. MCC and MNC build the plmn Id.  Mobile Network Code in the primary PLMN ID of the neighbor eNB. MCC and MNC build the PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of target LNBTS. Copied automatically from target LNBTS during Plan Prepare.

Parameter name: RLF based RRC connection reestablishment supported
Description: Indicates whether RLF based connection reestablishment is supported by the neighbour NB. The setting must be aligned with the feature activation parameter actRLFbasedRCR in the neighbour eNB.

Parameter name: Target BTS DN
Description: Pointer to the adjacency target LTE BTS (LNBTS) or external LTE BTS (EXENBF). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object.

Parameter name: U-Plane IPv4/v6 addresses of neighbor eNB
Description: This parameter holds the list of X2 U-Plane IPv4/v6 addresses of this adjacent eNB. It is used only when the LTE529 Dynamic X2 and S1 Firewall feature is enabled.    Both IP address formats are supported.    Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals and IPv6 address parameter acc. to RFC 4291.  This is used to open the firewall for the specified user plane addresses and will allow incoming packets from the specified IP addresses during X2 handover direct forwarding.    oamControlled X2 link:  It is the responsibility of the operator to configure the correct uPlaneIpAddrList.    enbControlled X2 link:  The IP addresses will be maintained by ANR procedures.
