It is the default value for neighbor eNBs which have been learnt via ANR procedures.    ---------------------    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).    IPv6 address ranges:  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).

Parameter name: X2 link status
Description: The parameter provides information whether the X2 link is successfully established.

Parameter name: Neighbor GERAN BTS cell identifier
Description: GeranTarget_INDEX uniquely identifies a set of GERAN neighbour cell parameters within an eNB. Used by the operator on the cell level to associate an GERAN neighbour cell to a particular LTE cell

Parameter name: ARFCN value geran
Description: ARFCN Value of the GERAN neighbour cell  (Part of CarrierFrequency)

Parameter name: Band indicator geran
Description: Bandindicator Value of the GERAN neighbour cell  (Part of CarrierFrequency)  The IE BandIndicatorGERAN indicates how to interpret an associated GERAN carrier ARFCN, see TS 45.005 [20]. More specifically, the IE indicates the GERAN frequency band in case the ARFCN value can concern either a DCS 1800 or a PCS 1900 carrier frequency. For ARFCN values not associated with one of these bands, the indicator is not relevant.

Parameter name: Basestation colour code
Description: BaseStation Colour Code of GERAN neighbour cell    (Part of PhysicalCellId)

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DTM capability
Description: This parameter indicates whether the GERAN target cell is DTM-capable. This information is evaluated during SRVCC to GERAN when deciding whether the UE is available for PS service

Parameter name: CI GERAN
Description: Cell Identity of GERAN neighbor cell    (Part of GERAN global cell ID; CGI)

Parameter name: LAC GERAN
Description: LAC of GERAN neighbour cell    (Part of GERAN global cell ID; CGI)    used as described in TS36.413 section 9.2.1.6    "0000 and FFFE not allowed."

Parameter name: RAC GERAN
Description: Routing Areas Code (RAC) of GERAN neighbor cell.    Hint: The RAC value is needed for establishing a RIM association, that is no RIM association will be established if the value is omitted even if the feature  LTE498: RAN Information Management for GSM is activated.

Parameter name: MCC GERAN
Description: Mobile Country Code included in the PLMN ID of the GERAN neighbour cell    (Part of GERAN global cell ID; CGI)

Parameter name: MNC GERAN
Description: Mobile Network Code included in the PLMN ID of the GERAN neighbour cell    (Part of GERAN global cell ID; CGI)

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of target GSM cell (BTS/EXGCE managed object) that is copied and updated automatically from target cell during Plan Prepare.

Parameter name: Network colour code
Description: Network Colour Code of GERAN neighbour cell (Part of PhysicalCellId)  Please check that this NCC is allowed LNHOG-nccperm.

Parameter name: Network control order
Description: Network Control Order Value of the GERAN neighbor cell, where the different parameter value mean:  NC0: Normal UE control  NC1: UE control with measurement reports  NC2: Network control  RESET: The UE shall return to the broadcast parameters.

Parameter name: RIM interface status
Description: Provides the status of the RIM association to serving BSS.    Meaning of the values:    - disabled:  The GERAN neighbor cell is not RIM enabled, that is  the feature is not activated  or  PLMN of the GERAN cell is blacklisted for RIM  or  no RAC value is configured.    - unavailable:  The GERAN neighbor cell is RIM enabled but no valid system information from RIM procedure is available.    - available:  The GERAN neighbor cell is RIM enabled and valid system information from RIM procedure is available.

Parameter name: System info list GERAN
Description: This parameter contains the GERAN Systeminformation which is used when sending a UE to GSM by eNACC or UE Context Release with redirect.    At least one list entry must be configured if SystemInformationType has the value 'si' or 'psi'.    The parameter is meaningless if:  - LTE498: RIM for GSM feature is activated AND  - the PLMN of the cell is not blacklisted for RIM AND  - parameter 'gTargetRac' is configured    Constant value maxGERAN-SI is defined in 3GPP TS36.331 section 6.4    The 23 octet 3GPP parameter must be added as character string in hexadecimal notation with leading '0x', where for each octet two character must be configured, with a minimum length of one octet.

Parameter name: System information type
Description: This parameter is set by Operator to indicate which type of GERAN Systeminformation (if any) is included in the RRC MOBILITYFROMEUTRANCOMMAND message.    The parameter is meaningless  - if feature 'RIM for GSM (LTE498)' is activated and  - the PLMN of the cell is not blacklisted for RIM and  - parameter gTargetRac is configured.

Parameter name: Target cell DN
Description: Pointer to the adjacency target BTS or external GERAN cell (EXGCE). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object.

Parameter name: Neighbor gNB identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of the object LNADJGNB. This parameter appears only in the distinguished name (DN) in the plan file and is used for O&M purposes.

Parameter name: Identity of neighbor gNB within PLMN
Description: This is the unique ID of the neighbor gNB within PLMN, where adjGnbId and plmnId form the neighbor global gNB ID.

Parameter name: Length of adjGnbId
Description: This parameter defines the gNB ID length. It will be used to get the leftmost bits of the NCI to determine the gNB ID.

Parameter name: Administrative state
Description: Administrative state of the LNADJGNB X2 link.  This parameter is used to lock and unlock the LNADJGNB X2 link. Locking LNADJGNB means closing the SCTP association between eNB and gNB.  Unlocking LNADJGNB triggers SCTP association establishment and X2AP Setup procedure.

Parameter name: C-Plane IP address of neighbor gNB
Description: This parameter holds the C-Plane IPv4/v6 address of this adjacent gNB.  Both IP address formats can be used.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter acc. to RFC 4291.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).    IPv6 address ranges:  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).

Parameter name: C-Plane IP address  control
Description: This parameter determines whether the C-Plane IP address of the neighbor gNB (EN-DC X2 link) is statically configured or whether eNB is allowed to update the address based on information provided by ANR procedures.    oamControlled X2 link:  It is the responsibility of the operator to configure the correct cPlaneIpAddr.    enbControlled X2 link:  The IP address will be maintained by ANR procedures. It is the default value for neighbor eNBs which have been learned via ANR procedures.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving NR cell activation blocked
Description: If this parameter is 'true' then EN-DC Cell Activation reattempts are blocked.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity of neighbor gNB - MCC in primary PLMN identity of neighbor gNB
Description: Mobile Country Code in the primary PLMN ID of neighbor gNB. MCC and MNC build the PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity of neighbor gNB - MNC in primary PLMN identity of neighbor gNB
Description: Mobile Network Code in the primary PLMN ID of the neighbor gNB. MCC and MNC build the PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity of neighbor gNB - MNC length in primary PLMN of neighbor gNB
Description: The MNC length determines the range of MNC in the primary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Target cell DN
Description: Pointer to the adjacency target NRBTS cell or external NRBTS cell (EXNRCE). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object. Parameter used and visible only in NetAct Advanced Configurator.

Parameter name: Status of X2 link to gNB
Description: The parameter provides information whether the X2 link to the gNB is successfully established.

Parameter name: Neighbor LTE cell identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of the object LNADJL. This parameter appears only in the distinguished name (DN) in the plan file and is used for O&M purposes.    It is highly recommended to use for object creation the lowest free lnAdjlId value within all LNADJL instances subordinate to an LNADJ object. This is to avoid rejection of plan file activation due to colliding lnAdjlId values if an LNADJL instance is automatically created by eNB because of activated ANR features.

Parameter name: Broadcast PLMN identity list
Description: Broadcast PLMN ID of the cell served by the neighbor eNB. Up to 6 different PLMN IDs per served cell can be broadcast.    At least one entry with the primary PLMN ID of the neighbor eNB is mandatory required in the list.

Parameter name: MCC in broadcast PLMN identity
Description: Mobile Country Code in broadcast PLMN ID of the cell served by the neighbor eNB. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC In Broadcast PLMN Identity
Description: Mobile Network Code in broadcast PLMN ID of the cell served by the neighbor eNB. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DL cyclic prefix configuration
Description: Adjacent cyclic prefix configuration in DL. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.    Please note that the parameter is only meaningful if an X2 link is established, i.e. if x2LinkStatus of the superior LNADJ instance is 'available'.

Parameter name: UL Cyclic Prefix Configuration
Description: Adjacent cyclic prefix configuration in DL.  The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.    Please note that the parameter is only meaningful if an X2 link is established, i.e. if x2LinkStatus of the superior LNADJ instance is 'available'.

Parameter name: Downlink transmission bandwidth
Description: Downlink transmission bandwidth of the FDD neighbor cell.  The parameter is not applicable for TDD neighbor cells.    Please note that the parameter is only meaningful if an X2 link is established, i.e. if x2LinkStatus of the superior LNADJ instance is 'available'.    The enumerated values correspond to the number of resource blocks "NRB".

Parameter name: Identity of neighbor eNB in ECGI
Description: This parameter is the Macro eNB identifier which is part of the E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (ECGI) of the neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Local cell resource ID of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter is the local cell resource ID which is part of the E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (ECGI) of the neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Downlink EARFCN of LTE cell served by neighbor eNB
Description: Downlink EARFCN of the FDD or TDD cell served by neighbor eNB.

Parameter name: Uplink EARFCN of FDD cell served by neighbor eNB
Description: Uplink EARFCN of the FDD neighbor cell.  The parameter is not applicable for TDD neighbor cells.    Please note that the parameter is only meaningful if an X2 link is established, i.e. if x2LinkStatus of the superior LNADJ instance is 'available'.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity of neighbor LTE cell in ECGI - MCC of primary PLMN identity of neighbour ENB in ECGI
Description: Mobile Country Code in PLMN Identity included in ECGI of the cell served by neighbour eNB. MCC and MNC build the PLMN ID of ECGI.  Mobile Country Code in PLMN Identity included in ECGI of the cell served by neighbour eNB. MCC and MNC build the plmn Id of ECGI.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity of neighbor LTE cell in ECGI - MNC of primary PLMN identity of neighbour ENB in ECGI
Description: Mobile Network Code in PLMN Identity included in ECGI of the cell served by neighbour eNB. MCC and MNC build a plmn Id of ECGI.

Parameter name: Physical cell ID of cell served by neighbor eNB
Description: This is the physical cell ID of the cell served by the neighbor eNB.

Parameter name: Source of data
Description: The parameter provides information whether the object creation or latest update was based on plan file (OM), X2 information (X2) or UE specific ANR measurements (UE).

Parameter name: Special Subframe Configuration Of Neighbor ENB
Description: Supported special subframe configuration by neighbor eNB. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.    Please note that the parameter is only meaningful if an X2 link is established, i.e. if x2LinkStatus of the superior LNADJ instance is 'available'.

Parameter name: Tracking area code of cell served by neighbor eNB
Description: This is the tracking area code of the cell served by the neighbor eNB.

Parameter name: UL and DL transmission bandwidth
Description: Uplink and Downlink Transmission Bandwidth Of Cell Served By Neighbor ENB. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.  The enumerated values correspond to the number of resource blocks "NRB".    Please note that the parameter is only meaningful if an X2 link is established, i.e. if x2LinkStatus of the superior LNADJ instance is 'available'.

Parameter name: Uplink Downlink subframe configuration in radio frame
Description: UL and DL Configuration of a subframe in a radio frame supported by neighbor eNB. The parameter is not applicable for FDD neighbor cells.    Please note that the parameter is only meaningful if an X2 link is established, i.e. if x2LinkStatus of the superior LNADJ instance is 'available'.

Parameter name: Uplink transmission bandwidth
Description: Uplink transmission bandwidth of the FDD neighbor cell.  The parameter is not applicable for TDD neighbor cells.  The enumerated values correspond to the number of resource blocks "NRB".    Please note that the parameter is only meaningful if an X2 link is established, i.e. if x2LinkStatus of the superior LNADJ instance is 'available'.

Parameter name: Neighbor NR cell identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of the object LNADJN. This parameter appears only in the distinguished name (DN) in the plan file and is used for O&M purposes.

Parameter name: ARFCN Value NR
Description: The SSB frequency of the NR neighbour cell. It is an attribute of the physical NR cell which is commonly applicable to all logical NR cells.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: PLMN identity in Global gNB ID of neighbor NR BTS - MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the PLMN-ID in NR CGI

Parameter name: PLMN identity in Global gNB ID of neighbor NR BTS - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the PLMN-ID in NR CGI

Parameter name: PLMN identity in Global gNB ID of neighbor NR BTS - MNC length
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC.

Parameter name: MFBI list of NR Neighbour cell
Description: The MFBI list of the NR neighbour cell as broadcast in SIB of NR cell. It is an attribute of the physical NR cell which is commonly applicable to all logical NR cells.

Parameter name: NR Physical Cell ID
Description: The Physical Cell ID of the NR neighbour cell as broadcast in SIB of NR cell. It is an attribute of the physical NR cell which is commonly applicable to all logical NR cells.

Parameter name: Neighbour NR Logical Cell Identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of the object LNADJNL. This parameter appears only in the distinguished name (DN) in the plan file and is used for O&M purposes.

Parameter name: New Radio global cell identifier
Description: This parameter is the New Radio Cell Identifier, which is part of the New Radio Global Cell Identifier (NR-CGI) of the neighbor cell served by en-gNB.  A dedicated NR-CGI is defined for each logical NR cell associated with a physical NR cell

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: PLMN identity in CGI of NR neighbor cell - MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the PLMN-ID in NR CGI

Parameter name: PLMN identity in CGI of NR neighbor cell - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the PLMN-ID in NR CGI

Parameter name: PLMN identity in CGI of NR neighbor cell - MNC length
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC.

Parameter name: Length of gnbId within nrCellId
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the gNB-Identifier included in the New Radio Cell Identifier of the neighbor cell served by en-gNB.

Parameter name: PLMN identity list
Description: This list stores the PLMN-Ids which belong to a logical NR cell. The list is broadcast in SIB1 of the NR Cell  Each logical NR cell within a physical NR cell holds its own list of PLMN Ids which are associated with a NR Cell identity. A dedicated PLMN ID can only be contained in the PLMN list of a single logical NR cell within a common physical NR cell

Parameter name: MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the PLMN ID

Parameter name: MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the PLMN ID

Parameter name: MNC length
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC.

Parameter name: NR Tracking Area Code
Description: This parameter is the Tracking Area Code of the NR Cell as broadcast in SIB1 of the NR cell.  Each logical NR cell within a physical NR cell holds its own TAC

Parameter name: Neighbor TD-SCDMA cell identifier
Description: Uniquely identifies a UTRAN (TD-SCDMA) neighbour cell within an eNB.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Target primary PLMN identity - MCC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Target primary PLMN identity - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Target secondary PLMN Id list
Description: Identifies the secondary PLMNs to which a neighbouring UTRAN cell belongs. Multiple PLMNs may be specified.

Parameter name: MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the secondary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the secondary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Target cell ID
Description: Target C-ID  Uniquely identifies a neighbouring cell within the RNC. Required (together with the RNC ID) for the Source RNC To Target RNC Transparent Container IE in the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

Parameter name: Target frequency
Description: Target Frequency  UtranTarget_FREQ provides the DL Carrier Frequency of the neighbouring UTRAN cell. Received from RRM-CMC in the TCL, which together with the primary scrambling code identifies a neighbouring UTRAN cell

Parameter name: Target location area code
Description: Target Location Area Code  UtranTarget_LAC provides the Location Area Code identifying the Location Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

Parameter name: Target routing area code
Description: Target Routing Area Code  UtranTarget_RAC provides the Routing Area Code identifying the Routing Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

Parameter name: Target RNC ID
Description: Target RNC ID  Uniquely identifies a neighbouring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

Parameter name: Physical cell ID (TD-SCDMA)
Description: Physical cell Id of the TD-SCDMA neighbor cell  The cell parameter Id (TDD) of the TD-SCDMA neighbor cell which is used to indicate the physical layer identity of the cell. Received from RRMT-CMC in the TCL, which together with the cell frequency identifies a TD-SCDMA cell.

Parameter name: Neighbor WCDMA BTS cell identifier
Description: Uniquely identifies a UTRAN neighbour cell within an eNB.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Target primary PLMN identity - MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Target primary PLMN identity - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of target WCDMA cell (WCEL/EXUCE managed object) that is copied and updated automatically from target cell during Plan Prepare.

Parameter name: RIM interface status
Description: Provides the status of the RIM association to serving RNC.    Meaning of the values:    - disabled:  The WCDMA neighbor cell is not RIM enabled, i.e.  the feature is not activated  or  the WCDMA cell is blacklisted for RIM.    - unavailable:  The WCDMA neighbor cell is RIM enabled but no valid system information from RIM procedure is available.    - available:  The WCDMA neighbor cell is RIM enabled and valid system information from RIM procedure is available.

Parameter name: Target secondary PLMN ID list
Description: Identifies the secondary PLMNs to which a neighboring UTRAN cell belongs. Multiple PLMNs can be specified.

Parameter name: MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the secondary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the secondary PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Source of data
Description: The parameter provides information whether the object creation or latest update was based on plan file (OM) or UE-specific ANR measurements (UE).

Parameter name: SRVCC HO indication
Description: This parameter selects if SRVCC to a WCDMA target cell is performed as a combined PS and CS SRVCC or whether SRVCC is performed for the CS bearer only.  This parameter must be configured individually for every WCDMA cell that is used as target for SRVCC.

Parameter name: Target cell DN
Description: Pointer to the adjacency target WCEL or external UTRAN cell (EXUCE). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object.

Parameter name: Target cell id
Description: UTRAN Cell-ID which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.  It uniquely identifies a neighbouring cell within the RNC and is required (together with the RNC ID) for the Source RNC To Target RNC Transparent Container IE in the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN.    The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either  - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or  - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).

Parameter name: Target frequency
Description: Target Frequency  Target Frequency provides the DL Carrier Frequency of the neighbouring UTRAN cell. Received from RRM-CMC in the TCL, which together with the primary scrambling code identifies a neighboring UTRAN cell

Parameter name: Target location area code
Description: Target Location Area Code  UtranTarget_LAC provides the Location Area Code identifying the Location Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

Parameter name: Target routing area code
Description: Target Routing Area Code  UtranTarget_RAC provides the Routing Area Code identifying the Routing Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell. Required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN

Parameter name: Target RNC id
Description: UTRAN RNC identifier which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.    Values in the range of 4096 .. 65535 are considered as Extended RNC-ID.  It uniquely identifies a neighbouring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN and is required for the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message during handover to UTRAN.    The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either  - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or  - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).

Parameter name: Primary scrambling code (FDD)
Description: Primary Scrambling Code (FDD) Of The Neighbouring UTRAN Cell  UtranTarget_SC_FDD: The primary scrambling code (FDD) of the neighbouring UTRAN cell. Received from RRM-CMC in the TCL, which together with the cell frequency identifies a neighbouring UTRAN cell

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor cell identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute Of MOC LNADJX.  It uniquely identifies a LNADJX instance.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x carrier frequency
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) carrier frequency of this 1xRTT neighbor cell.  The CDMA2000 ARFCN used to indicate the CDMA2000 carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 band, see C.S0002-A.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x band class
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) band class of this 1xRTT neighbor cell.  The CDMA2000 band class is used to define the CDMA2000 band in which the CDMA2000 carrier frequency can be found, as defined in C.S0057-E [table 1.5-1].

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x cell ID
Description: Defines the cell number of this CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) neighbor cell

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x market ID
Description: Defines the market identifier of the CBSC for this CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x PN offset
Description: Defines the Pseudo-Random Noise (PN) offset of this CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) neighbor cell.  see C.S0002-A for the definition.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x sector ID
Description: Defines the sector number of this CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Source of data
Description: The parameter provides information whether the object creation or latest update was based on plan file (OM) or UE specific ANR measurements (UE).

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x switch number
Description: Defines the switching number of this CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Macro eNB identifier
Description: Instance identifier of object Macro eNB and used also as telecom parameter of the 3GPP 'Macro eNB ID', which is part of Global eNB ID. In addition it appears as distinguished name (DN) in the planning data at the Element Manager.

Parameter name: Activate 1xCSFB
Description: This parameter enables the feature LTE1441 enhanced CSFB to CDMA2000 1xRTT.  This parameter enables also the feature LTE1635 SIB8 AC Barring.

Parameter name: Activate support of 64 LNMME instances per eNB
Description: Parameter act64Mmes activates the support of 64 LNMME instances per eNB.

Parameter name: Activate Support of 8 EPS Bearers
Description: This parameter activates the support up to 8 EPS bearers.

Parameter name: Activate A3-based SCell selection
Description: This parameter activates the functionality for "Measurement-based SCell selection".

Parameter name: Activate AACB alarms counters and status
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the feature Automatic Access Class Barring Alarms and Counters Enhancement.

Parameter name: Activate CFR based access class barring
Description: This parameter activates LTE4175 'Connection failure rate-based Access Class Barring'. The feature aggregates the number of RRC Connection Requests and the connection failure rate defined by the ratio between RRC connection setup rejections due to RAC at cell level and total RRC attempts over sliding window and if they are exceeding start thresholds it triggers step-wise access class barring parameters broadcast in SIB2.

Parameter name: Activate automatic access class barring per PLMN
Description: This parameter activates LTE2996 'PLMN Specific Access Class Barring'.

Parameter name: Activate RRC connection triggered access class barring
Description: This parameter activates LTE2823 'RRC Connection triggered access class barring' or LTE3811 'RRC connection triggered access class barring - BB pool' in addition to LTE2823.  The feature detects that number of RRC connections is near RAC limit on cell or BB pool level and triggers access class barring parameters broadcast in SIB2.  The feature introduces ACB step-wise algorithm to broadcast access class barring parameters in SIB2.  If LTE4175 is activated, i.e. actAcBarringCFR is set to 'true' then LTE2823 does not detect that number of RRC connections is approaching RAC limit on cell level and does not trigger access class barring parameters broadcast in SIB2. LTE2823 ACB step-wise algorithm is triggered by LTE4175, LTE2235, LTE1788 or LTE3811 if activated.    Note: If LTE4741 'Access Class Barring Support for CAT-M1' is activated then CAT-M specific AC barring settings are broadcast in SIB2-BR as well.

Parameter name: Activate RACH load triggered access class barring
Description: This parameter activates 'RACH load triggered access class barring'.  The feature aggregates the number of RRC Connection Requests over sliding window and if it's exceeding start threshold it triggers step-wise access class barring parameters broadcast in SIB2.    Note: If LTE4741 'Access Class Barring Support for CAT-M1' is activated then CAT-M specific AC barring settings are broadcast in SIB2-BR as well.

Parameter name: Activate automatic access class barring for special classes
Description: This parameter activates LTE4627 'Step-wise Automatic Access Class Barring for Special Classes'.    Feature allows step-wise Special Access Class (AC11-AC15) barring. Maximum five steps are allowed and executed as the last ACB escalation phase. Optionally, emergency calls could be 'barred' or 'not barred' for each Special Class (SC) barring step (regardless of legacy Emergency Call (EC) barring phase settings), see acbScEcBitmask parameter.

Parameter name: Activate AC triggered SRVCC
Description: This parameter activates the functionality to accept an E-RAB with QCI#1 by overbooking in RAC and/or TAC and immediately trigger SRVCC to WCDMA for respective UE.

Parameter name: Activate advanced SCell measurement handling
Description: This parameter activates the feature for advanced SCell measurement handling for carrier aggregation.

Parameter name: Activate advanced step-wise SCell addition
Description: Activate advanced step-wise SCell addition.  If this parameter is set to 'oneStepAdvanced', and step-wise cell addition is enabled (numTxWithHighNonGbr is not equal to '0'), one step SCell addition occurs when the UE enters the cell.  If this parameter is set to 'buffer-based', and step-wise cell addition is enabled, the eNB starts buffer measurements when the UE enters the cell. Upon buffer overflows, one step SCell addition occurs if no SCells are configured for this UE, otherwise step-wise addition is performed.  If this parameter is 'off', and step-wise cell addition is enabled, the eNB starts buffer measurements when the UE enters the cell, and step-wise cell addition is performed upon buffer overflows.  If numTxWithHighNonGbr is equal to '0', this parameter is ignored.

Parameter name: Activate advanced UL SCell handling
Description: This parameter activates the advanced SCell handling in uplink carrier aggregation:  - the PCell UL pathloss is checked for adding a DL+UL SCell and for downgrading a DL+UL SCell to a DL-only SCell.

Parameter name: Activate CA algorithm trigger based on UE AMBR change
Description: This parameter activates the processing of UE AMBR received in E-RAB Modify Request in order to start carrier aggregation trigger algorithms. Depending on numTxWithHighNonGbr eNB may start either non-GBR buffer monitoring or one-step SCell addition procedure.  If the parameter is set to 'true', then UE AMBR for uplink and downlink are processed by the eNB.

Parameter name: Activate ANR 1xRTT
Description: Feature 'ANR interRAT 1xRTT - O&M assisted' is activated, if actAnrRtt is set to "oamAssisted".    Feature 'ANR interRAT 1xRTT - O&M assisted' is deactivated, if actAnrRtt is set to "false".    Note that ANR interRAT 1xRTT will not be supported in cells with 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz bandwidth.    The feature 'O&M assisted CDMA2000 1xRTT ANR' can not be activated if rttCellIdInfo in any of the LTE cells is set to '1'.    LNRELXs created by feature 'O&M assisted CDMA2000 1xRTT ANR' are only intended to be used in rttCellIdInfo '000' mode.

Parameter name: Activate ARP based Admission Control Offsets
Description: This parameter activates the support of ARP based admission control offsets function on eNB level.  The operator can enable/disable this function per cell level for wideband UEs by using independent ARPPR profiles with proper values.  If no specific ARPPR profile is referred to the cell, it means this function is disabled per cell.  Configuring lower ARP offsets (< 100%) in ARPPR profile(s) will lead to a static resource reservation in the cell and on transport interface (and depends on arpOffsetUsageOnBBpool on baseband pools in case of AirScale eNodeBs).  In case CAT-M feature(s) are activated the ARP offset handling applies also on CAT-M resources if configured in the CAT-M profiles similar to ARPPR profiles.

Parameter name: Active ARP based QoS scaling
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the feature ARP based QoS scaling for single ARP or multiple ARPs.

Parameter name: Activation of Automatic AC Barring
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE1788 'Automatic access class barring'.

Parameter name: Activate automatic PLMN removal
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE2460, i.e. the autonomous removal of further PLMN in SIB1 during C-plane overload.

Parameter name: Activate B1 extended measurement report for NR
Description: This parameter activates B1 extended measurement report for NR

Parameter name: Activate B1-NR based EN-DC primary target selection in IMLB
Description: This parameter activates B1-NR measurement-based EN-DC primary target selection in idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Activate B1-NR based SA NR primary target selection in IMLB
Description: This parameter activates B1-NR measurement based SA NR primary target selection in IMLB.

Parameter name: Activate baseband pooling
Description: This parameter activates baseband pooling. This activation flag is relevant for any variant of AirScale ABIA/ABIC/ABIN/ABIO/ABIP/ABIQ/ASOE/ASOF/ASOH/ASOG.  On any variant of AirScale ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ABIP, ABIQ, ASOE, ASOF, ASOH, ASOG with at least one LTE cell configured, this parameter is always set to 'true' and all precondition features need to be activated as well.

Parameter name: Activate uplink NAS and CDMA2000 message buffering in ICS procedure
Description: This parameter activates the uplink NAS and CDMA2000 message buffering during ongoing Initial Context Setup (ICS) procedure.  If activated: NAS or 1xRTT or eHRPD PDUs received from UE in RRC:UL Information Transfer messages during Initial Context Setup procedure are buffered till S1AP:INITIAL CONTEXT SETUP RESPONSE message is sent by the eNB.

Parameter name: Activation of CA in LTE-NR Dual Connectivity
Description: This parameter activates Carrier Aggregation in LTE-NR Dual Connectivity scenarios in the LTE BTS.  Meaning of parameter values is:  - blind_CA_LTE_NR: attempt to keep LTE CA when EN-DC is set up, possibly with a reconfiguration (e.g. SCell release or MIMO upgrade/downgrade). However, no further LTE SCell addition is possible as far as the UE is in EN-DC mode. Besides, both the LTE MIMO configuration as well as the LTE CA configuration assume the minimum value from the allowed band combination list for MRDC and related feature sets and, therefore, they can be adapted only during the SgNB Addition procedure.  - enhanced_CA_LTE_NR: attempt to keep LTE CA when EN-DC is set up, possibly with a reconfiguration (e.g. SCell release or MIMO upgrade/downgrade). Further LTE SCell addition is possible if needed and compatible with the currently selected MRDC band combination. Besides, both the LTE MIMO configuration as well as the LTE CA configuration are dynamically adapted to the MRDC band combination and feature set selected by the en-gNB within the constraints coming from the configured allowedBcSelectMethod parameter value.

Parameter name: Activation CMAS support
Description: Activates CMAS support  If CMAS support is set to 'true', CMAS warning messages are broadcast (SIB12) in case of Write-Replace Warning Request incl. CMAS data is received from MME    This parameter also activates the feature LTE2085 'SIB reception with parallel measurement gaps' that enables UEs in measurement gaps to receive CMAS notification at least once per SIB window.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released, when this parameter is modified online together with Cat-M are activated.

Parameter name: Activate CS fallback via redirection
Description: The parameter activates the feature 'Circuit Switched Fallback to UTRAN or GSM via Redirection'.    If the feature is activated, mobile originated and mobile terminated CS calls are redirected to targets which are to be configured via REDRT objects.    At the same time this parameter also activates the feature 'Cause value for CSFB to GERAN without DTM support'.

Parameter name: Activate the support for CBRS mobility enhancement
Description: This parameter activates the support for CBRS (Citizens Broadband Radio Service) mobility enhancement.  It is used to enable/disable the mobility enhancement for CBRS service on non-CBRS eNB (the FDD or TDD/mixed_FDD_TDD eNB with CBRS disabled)

Parameter name: Activate cell switch on for configuration management update
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates cell switch on for configuration management update.    If this parameter is not configured or is configured and equal to 'false', then cell switch on for configuration management update is deactivated.  If this parameter is equal to 'true', then cell switch on for configuration management update is activated.

Parameter name: Activate cell trace
Description: This is a feature flag to enable or disable Cell Trace feature.

Parameter name: Activate cell trace for NB-IoT
Description: This is a feature flag to enable or disable Cell Trace feature for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Activate cell trace with IMSI
Description: This parameter is used for enabling/disabling of the feature "Cell Trace with IMSI". It will be only utilized when cell trace is activated, i.e. actCellTrace is TRUE.  If the value is set to TRUE the eNB will send the CELL TRAFFIC TRACE message to MME for every call in every cell trace session.  This will allow the MME to map the Trace Reference/Trace Recording Session Reference to IMSI/IMEI.  If the parameter is set to FALSE the eNB will not send the CELL TRAFFIC TRACE message to MME for all calls in all Cell Trace Sessions.

Parameter name: Ciphering algorithm activation parameter
Description: This parameter enables/disables optional ciphering algorithms.

Parameter name: Activate CMAS configurable prioritization
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'CMAS Operator Configurable Prioritization of Message IDs'.

Parameter name: This parameter indicates whether CMAS transmission optimization is enabled or disabled
Description: CMAS transmission is optimized to broadcast SIB12 only during times when there is an alert message to transmit according to the Write-Replace Warning Request message parameter.

Parameter name: Activate CDMA2000 1xRTT coexistence with WCDMA/GSM mobility
Description: The parameter activates the feature 'CDMA2000 1xRTT coexistence with WCDMA/GSM mobility '.

Parameter name: Activate CoMP
Description: Coordinated multipoint (CoMP) feature activation for the eNB. The parameter is used to configured CoMP features supported by the eNB for UL CoMP.    For any variant of AirScale ABIA (and FSMr3) UL CoMP features such as LTE1402, LTE1691, LTE2104, LTE2128 and CB006754 please configure the value to 'fixedULCoMp'.  For any variant of AirScale ABIA (and FSMr3) measurement based CoMP features including for example Flexible UL CoMP please configure the value to 'measBasedCoMp'.    For any variant of AirScale ABIA (and FSMr3) 'fixedULCoMp', SINR measurements are used, where for 'measBasedCoMp' A3 measurements are used in addition to SINR.    For any variant of AirScale ABIO, ABIN, ASOE/ASOF, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOG/ASOH Basic UL CoMP feature such as CB006501 please configure the value to either 'fixedULCoMp' or 'measBasedCoMp,' as both are acceptable for that case.    For any variant of AirScale ABIO, ABIN, ASOE/ASOF, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOG/ASOH 'Basic CoMp' with either 'fixedULCoMp' or 'measBasedCoMp', SINR measurements are used.    The BTS will dynamically decide depending on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.    Configuration rules for FDD with 'fixedULCoMp':  Distributed sites are only supported if the distance between RRHs is less than 1 km.    Notes for TDD:  Recommendations for balancing increased TDD cell throughput and link level gain (not considered in validation) for LTE1402, LTE1691, LTE2104 or LTE2128 configurations:  If chBw is set to '20MHz' AND dlMimoMode is set to 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)', actCoMp is recommended to be configured to 'fixedULCoMp'.    Configuration rules for TDD:  Distributed sites are only supported if the distance between RRHs is less than 1 km, with a maximal Doppler shift of 250 Hz.  For 4 Rx UL-CoMP (LTE1691) only cells with 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth are supported.  For 2 Rx, 4 Rx and 8 Rx UL-CoMP (LTE1402, LTE2104 and LTE2128) cells with 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth are supported.

Parameter name: Activation of complete consistency checks
Description: The parameter activates Complete Consistency Checks in Validator tool.  This parameter can be used to disable the checks that could block eNB reconfiguration after SW upgrade.  Only particular checks in Validator tool are disabled by this parameter.  If SW upgrade, configuration validation fails in WebEM or in NetAct, it is possible to set this parameter to "false" and proceed with eNB reconfiguration. During SW upgrade the configured parameter value will not be changed.

Parameter name: Activate RRC connection and SCell context pre-emption
Description: This parameter activates the support of RRC connection and UE SCell context pre-emption.

Parameter name: Activation of coordinated enhanced DSS Power Saving
Description: This parameter activates coordinated enhanced DSS Power Saving.

Parameter name: Activate coordinated 4G-5G power saving
Description: Functional description:  1:cellDeactivation:  - Coordination of NR power saving state to eNB.  2:cellDeactAndReact  - Coordination of NR power saving state to eNB and reactivation of NR cell by eNB

Parameter name: Activation of C-plane overload handling
Description: Feature enabling flag for LTE1047 'C-plane overload handling'.  The feature detects overload and triggers countermeasures.

Parameter name: Activate CSFB EC access restriction removal
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE2410.  If the feature is activated, the CS Fallback Indicator will be verified, roaming and access restriction will not apply for CSFB emergency calls.

Parameter name: Activate CS fallback with PS-HO to UTRA
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Circuit Switched Fallback with Packet Switched Handover to UTRA'.

Parameter name: Activate CSG S1 mobility
Description: The parameter activates CSG (Closed Subscriber Group) mobility.

Parameter name: Activate Dedicated Core Networks
Description: This parameter is used for enabling/disabling of the feature "Dedicated Core Network support".  If the value is set to TRUE the eNB will Reroute the NAS messages to another Dedicated Core Network (DCN) based on the parameters received from MME or optionally configured within the eNB.  This will allow the different UE categories such as CatM, NB-IoT or Legacy Wideband UEs to be rerouted to specific dedicated networks.  If the parameter is set to FALSE the eNB will not reroute the NAS message to another MME/DCN.

Parameter name: Activation of downlink carrier aggregation
Description: The parameter activates the family of downlink carrier aggregation features.    The feature allows higher UE downlink peak data rates by aggregation of two cells.  The BTS will dynamically decide depending on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Activate DL unicast over MBSFN subframe
Description: Activates DL unicast TM9 over MBSFN subframe.

Parameter name: Activate DRX coordination for LTE-NR DC
Description: Activates DRX coordination for LTE-NR dual connectivity.    Following options are available:  basic DRX coordination -- DRX coordination during SgNB addition  basic DRX and SgNB initiated -- In addition to the basic DRX coordination during SgNB addition, it is also coordinated along with measurement gaps during SgNB initiated measurement gap coordination.
Range and step: disabled (0), basic DRX coordination (1), basic DRX and SgNB initiated (2)

Parameter name: Activate LTE-NR DSS DL share algorithm with NR UL load
Description: This parameter activates LTE-NR DSS DL share algorithm based on NR UL load measurement and NR/LTE DL load measurements.  When this parameter is set to 'false' then the LTE-NR DSS DL share algorithm is based only on NR/LTE DL load measurements.

Parameter name: Activate CSFB to CDMA 1xRTT for dual RX UEs
Description: Activates the feature CS fallback to CDMA 1xRTT for dual Rx UEs.

Parameter name: Activate support for dynamic allocation of eMBMS resources
Description: Activates the feature 'Dynamic allocation of eMBMS resources'.  If the LTE BTS is configured to support FDD and TDD concurrently (i.e. if supportedCellTechnology is configured to 'mixed_FDD_TDD') and feature 'Dynamic allocation of eMBMS resources' is activated, then it is applied only for FDD cells.  The value of actDynMBMSRes has an effect only if actMBMS is set to 'true'. If actMBMS is set to 'false', the value of actDynMBMSRes is ignored by the eNB.

Parameter name: Activation of dynamic trigger for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity
Description: This parameter activates measurement-based dynamic triggering of LTE-NR Dual Connectivity in the LTE BTS. This includes UE measurements for RSRP, RSRQ and eNB internal L2 buffer overflow verification.

Parameter name: Activate support of in-vehicle emergency call service called NG eCall (eCall over IMS).
Description: This parameter activates the support of NG-eCall (eCall over IMS), the Pan-European in-vehicle emergency call service defined under the eSafety initiative of the European Commission, supplemented with a minimum set of emergency related data (MSD).    eNB indicates NG eCall support in SIB1 and SIB1-BR, refer to 3GPP TS 36.331 and IE eCallOverIMS-Support-r14. Per 3GPP, eCallOverIMS-Support-r14 minimally indicates that the PLMN, or all of the PLMNs in the case of network sharing, and at least one emergency center or PSAP to which an eCall Over IMS session can be routed, support eCall Over IMS. This flag should not be activated unless this minimal condition is satisfied.

Parameter name: Activate  energy-efficient emergency activation
Description: This parameter enables handling of external alarm for energy-efficient emergency activation for lnCelId(s) listed in eeeaCellList.    When actEEEmergAct is set to 'true' then energy-efficient emergency activation is enabled for all the cells with lnCelId(s) listed in eeeaCellList. This means if external alarm is raised it can wake up cells from this list from power saving state.

Parameter name: Activate E-RAB modification
Description: This parameter activates the E-RAB Modification by the S1AP message E-RAB MODIFY REQUEST.  This parameter also activates the modification of the GBR related QoS parameters.

Parameter name: Activate support of non-GBR QCI8 bearer to signaling QCI5 bearer E-RAB modification.
Description: This parameter activates support for modification of non-GBR QCI8 bearer to signaling QCI5 bearer by S1AP message E-RAB MODIFY REQUEST.    Note: For example, modification of non-GBR QCI8 bearer to signaling QCI5 bearer can be triggered when a UE with QCI8 bearer for SIP signaling performs a handover from UMTS to LTE.

Parameter name: Activate modification between QCI 66 and QCI 65
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Modification between QCI 66 and QCI 65' via E-RAB Modify procedure.

Parameter name: Activation ETWS support
Description: Activates ETWS support  If ETWS support is set to 'true', ETWS primary and secondary notification are broadcast (SIB10 and SIB11) in case of Write-Replace Warning Request incl. ETWS, data is received from MME.    This parameter also activates the feature  - LTE2085 'SIB reception with parallel measurement gaps' that enables UEs in measurement gaps to receive ETWS notification at least once per SIB window.  - LTE2120 'TDD SIB reception with parallel measurement gaps' that enables UEs in measurement gaps to receive ETWS notification at least once per SIB window.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released, if this parameter is online modified and Cat-M is activated.

Parameter name: Activate emergency call via redirection
Description: The parameter activates the feature 'Emergency Call Via Redirection'.    The feature can be only activated if at least one redirection target for UTRAN or GSM has been created before.    At the same time this parameter also activates the feature 'Cause value for CSFB to GERAN without DTM support'.

Parameter name: Activate coexistence between EN-DC and DSS LTE-NR cells
Description: This parameter defines how to handle the coexistence of LTE and NR DSS cells in the same frequency band for EN-DC.    When this parameter is set to 'LTE DSS SCell band blacklist' and the MR-DC band combination selected by the en-gNB supports the frequency band of UE candidate or configured DSS SCell(s) which can be shared with NR (P)SCells then eNB performs following actions:  1) It releases and blacklists such configured LTE DSS SCell(s)  2) It blacklists such candidate LTE DSS SCell(s)    LTE DSS SCells blacklisting applies as far as the UE is in EN-DC mode.    The parameter is taken into account only by those eNB cells for which LTE4549 applies, i.e. by the cells which lcrId is included in the MRBTS/LNBTS/NRDCDPR/cAggrLteNrDcCellList (or by all eNB cells if the lcrId in this list has the special value -1).
Range and step: disabled (0), LTE DSS SCell band blacklist (1)

Parameter name: Activate LTE DL MIMO optimized EN-DC BC list selection
Description: This parameter enhances the creation of the allowedBC-ListMRDC provided to the target en-gNB during the SgNB Addition or SgNB Modification procedure by taking into account the DL MIMO mode configuration of the UE's PCell and serving/candidate SCells.    When this parameter is set to 'true' and MRBTS/LNBTS/NRDCDPR-allowedBcSelectMethod is different from 'no preference', eNB acting as MeNB enhances the creation of the allowedBC-ListMRDC provided to the target en-gNB during the SgNB Addition or SgNB Modification procedure.  eNB takes into account the DL MIMO mode configuration of the UE's PCell and serving/candidate SCells to find out the maximum potential number of DL MIMO layers that an LTE CA configuration within a UE supported MRDC band combination can provide. This is used for selecting the MRDC band combinations per each different MRDC band combination group which can maximize the number of configurable MIMO layers in the LTE leg at the UE in EN-DC mode.  When this parameter is set to 'true' and the MRBTS/LNBTS/NRDCDPR-allowedBcSelectMethod is set to 'no preference' or this parameter is set to 'false', no enhancement in the creation of the allowedBC-ListMRDC will take place.

Parameter name: Activate LTE DL throughput based EN-DC BC list selection
Description: When parameter actEnDcLteDlTputBcSel is set to 'true' and the MRBTS/LNBTS/NRDCDPR-allowedBcSelectMethod set to a value different than 'no preference', eNB acting as MeNB enhances the creation of the allowedBC-ListMRDC IE by taking into account, besides the DL MIMO mode as per legacy LTE5761 feature, also the channel bandwidth of the UE's PCell and serving/candidate LTE SCells for selecting the MRDC band combinations and providing them to the en-gNB. This allows to maximize the DL throughput in LTE leg.  If LTE5515 is also activated (i.e., enableBwComSetChkEnDc is set to 'true'), eNB shall consider only cell channel bandwidths which are also supported by the UE in the respective frequency band sub-blocks.

Parameter name: Activate EN-DC BC list selection with NR FeatureSet IDs
Description: This parameter enhances the EN-DC band combination grouping from LTE4549, based on different NR band combinations, using also the corresponding NR FeatureSetDownlinkId and NR FeatureSetUplinkId of a given EN-DC band combination.    When this parameter is set to 'true' and the MRBTS/LNBTS/NRDCDPR-allowedBcSelectMethod is different from 'no preference', eNB groups the UE's candidate MRDC band combinations per unique combination of the following three parameter values: NR band combination, NR FeatureSetDownlinkId and NR FeatureSetUplinkId.  From each such group, eNB finds out the MRDC band combinations and featureSet combinations which maximize the potential number of LTE DL MIMO layers that can be configured at the UE according to either LTE5761, if actEnDcLteDlMimoOptBcSel is 'true', otherwise LTE4549, to provide to the target en-gNB during the SgNB Addition or SgNB Modification procedure.  When this parameter is set to 'true' and the MRBTS/LNBTS/NRDCDPR-allowedBcSelectMethod is set to 'no preference' or this parameter is set to 'false', no NR featureSet related MRDC band combination grouping will take place.

Parameter name: Activate X2 partial reset in LTE-NR DC
Description: This parameter activates X2 partial reset in LTE-NR DC.

Parameter name: Activate EN-DC carrier allocation sanity check
Description: Activates carrier allocation sanity check.  If activated,  - eNB checks intra-band contiguous/non-contiguous between LTE PCell/SCell and NR PSCell/SSCell according to UE capability (intra-bandENDCSupport field)  - eNB checks overlapping between carrier allocation of LTE PCell/SCell and NR PSCell/SSCell for intra-band EN-DC    Following options are available:  disabled -- feature is disabled  eNBConfig_PCellAndSCellContiguity -- overlapping check + contiguous/non-contiguous check between LTE PCell/SCell and NR PSCell

Parameter name: Activate ANR automatic X2 setup for EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates ANR automatic X2 setup for EN-DC.

Parameter name: Activate ANR automatic X2 setup for EN-DC in SBTS
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Automatic Direct X2 Setup between eNB and gNB within an SBTS'. If this feature is activated, the LNADJGNB instance representing the neighbor gNB in a SBTS EN-DC deployment will be automatically created.

Parameter name: Activate EN-DC blocking per cause value
Description: This parameter activates EN-DC blocking due to different causes. Each cause is enabled independently by setting the corresponding bit value to '1'.    This parameter is a 4 bits bitmask with following meaning:  Bit 0 (LSB - right-most bit): RNL cause: Insufficient UE capabilities  Bit 1: RNL cause: Not supported QCI value  Bit 2: RNL cause: Target not allowed  Bit 3: RNL cause: No radio resources available
Range and step: bits mask: RNL cause: Insufficient UE capabilities (0), RNL cause: Not supported QCI value (1), RNL cause: Target not allowed (2), RNL cause: No radio resources available (3)

Parameter name: Activate blocking of B1-NR measurements for EN-DC capable UE
Description: Activates blocking of B1-NR measurements for EN-DC capable UEs.  If enabled, eNB will start monitoring the number of 5G drops (Reception of X2AP:SgNBReleaseRequired with cause code "Radio connection with UE lost") and if that number of drops per carrier meets the configurable value within certain window of time, then that frequency will not be eligible for EN-DC service for a specific amount of time.

Parameter name: Activate EN-DC capability based handover
Description: The parameter is used to activate the EN-DC capability based handover to steer EN-DC capable UEs to EN-DC dedicated frequency layers.    Please note that the change of the actEndcHo value will have no immediate impact on ongoing user connections.

Parameter name: Activate Masked IMEISV forwarding in EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates Masked IMEISV transmission on X2 in NSA procedure.

Parameter name: Activates ENDC relation removal condition option
Description: The parameter provides algorithm options for LNRELGNBCELL cell removal condition. Autonomous LNRELGNBCELL removal could be done when the removal condition for a given LNRELGNBCELL is met ANR-anrNrNbrRelRemGuardTime consecutive number of checks. The removal condition is met when internal counter (nrPciCount) maintained per PCI-Carrier pair is below ENDC[D]MEASCONF-nrPciNbrRelRemThresh constantly throughout one-hour period.    When LNBTS.actEndcRelRemCondOption=false, then throughout the first one hour interval the nrPciCount has to be always smaller than nrPciNbrRelRemThresh in order to increment removal counter, while the next increment is based on snapshot of nrPciCount value checked against nrPciNbrRelRemThresh. The snapshot is taken at the subsequent expiry of one-hour periodic timer.  When LNBTS.actEndcRelRemCondOption=true, then also at subsequent (not the first one) one-hour periodic checks nrPciCount has to be always smaller than nrPciNbrRelRemThresh throughout the whole last one-hour period which may lead to resetting of the removal counter after cell unlock (also after end of power saving period). This is because nrPciCount is initialized to ENDC[D]MEASCONF-nrPciNbrRelAddThresh after cell unlock.

Parameter name: Activate SPID forwarding in EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates SPID forwarding in EN-DC

Parameter name: Activate enforcement of HRL for all types of calls
Description: This parameter activates the enforcement of the Handover Restriction List (HRL) to all types of calls (including emergency calls).  This functionality is applied for intra-LTE handovers, both via X2 and S1 interface.    If activated, the HRL restrictions are applied to all types of calls (including emergency calls).  If deactivated, legacy behavior applies (i.e., HRL restrictions will be ignored for certain calls depending on the set of activated features).

Parameter name: Activate enhanced AC and GBR services
Description: This parameter activates support of the following features  LTE534: ARP based Admission Control  LTE497: Smart Admission Control, comprising RAC and TAC  LTE496: EPS bearers with QCI 2, 3 and 4  Feature LTE496 introduces support of QCI 2, 3, and 4 along with higher guaranteed bit rates and related congestion detection and handling mechanisms.    Admission control functionality (LTE497) is extended at the same time from a counter based solution to become load based and offer in addition congestion handling functionality to better address the needs being imposed by higher guaranteed bit rates.    Finally the ARP based admission control (LTE534) allows to consider the ARP priority in load-based admission and admission related pre-emption as well as in congestion handling as an additional more service-related dimension for differentiated treatment of bearers with guaranteed resources.    As those features are closely inter-related, they are activated via a common activation parameter.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced CBRS carrier aggregation
Description: The parameter activates the CBRS carrier aggregation operation enhancement in order to adapt CBSD cell EARFCN change during negotiation with SAS.

Parameter name: Activation of Flexible LTE CA with EN-DC enhancements
Description: This parameter activates Flexible LTE CA with EN-DC enhancements.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced LPPa cell ID location service
Description: The parameter activates retrieval of MAC assisted measurements e.g. Timing Advance Type 1, Timing Advance Type 2 and/or AoA at the expiry of ecidMeasSupervisionTimer.

Parameter name: Activate non-periodic secondary RAT usage data report for EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates the non-periodic secondary RAT usage data report for EN-DC. When activated, eNB forwards a secondary RAT usage data report received on X2 from gNB via S1 to MME. Report might be received during the following procedures: UE context release, Bearer release, S1 inter-eNB or inter-RAT Handover, X2 inter-eNB or inter-gNB Handover, EN-DC Release.    Note: Forwarding of periodic secondary RAT data usage report can be enabled with parameter actSecRatRep.

Parameter name: Activate Extended Configuration for Load Based Power Saving TX paths reduction
Description: This parameter enables activation of load based power saving MIMO muting features on Airscale SBTS even if there are massive MIMO(mMIMO) cells configured.

Parameter name: Max size allowed per Basic CoMP Set
Description: Defines the maximum size of a Basic CoMP Set.    Default value '3' means, standard Basic ulCoMP is supported, expanded Basic ulCoMP is switched off.  By default, each configured Basic CoMP set must include at least two and at most three (i.e. the default value of actExpandedBasicCoMp) cells (by lcrId of the LNCEL).    In current release this value cannot be changed.

Parameter name: Activate extended n77 band support 2
Description: This parameter activates the extended n77 band support 2 (3650 - 3980 MHz) in the eNB in countries where usage of n77 band might be restricted otherwise.    Note: eNB does not check the PLMN ID to determine whether the eNB is located in a country where n77 band usage is restricted or not. Thus, it is operator's responsibility to determine whether this functionality shall be activated in their network or not.

Parameter name: Activate Extended Cell Switch Off Method
Description: This parameter indicates whether Extended Cell Switch Off Method is enabled or disabled.    The feature CB008800 introduces additional configuration parameters to allow Operator more flexibility with configuration of custom Energy Saving specific scenarios as supported by LTE1103 and LTE1203/SR003080. As a consequence of new configuration options the Operator is able to differentiate activation periods applicable at cell level and also to customize which switch off method is applied for respective cell (Cell Switch Off method - LTE1103, TX Path Switch Off method - LTE1203/SR003080).

Parameter name: Activation for extended inter-freq measurement control
Description: This parameter enables the extended inter-freq measurement control

Parameter name: Activate extended n77 band support
Description: This parameter activates the extended n77 band support (3450-3550 MHz) in the eNB in countries where usage of n77 band might be restricted otherwise.    Note: eNB does not check the PLMN ID to determine whether the eNB is located in a country where n77 band usage is restricted or not. Thus, it is operator's responsibility to determine whether this functionality shall be activated in their network or not.

Parameter name: Activate recovery of PhyRx Symbol Index Shift detected
Description: This parameter activates automatic recovery flow in case of Fault 6056 "PhyRx Symbol Index Shift Detected".    If actFault6056Recovery is 'true', then eNB will try to automatically recover the faulty situation by triggering cell reset.  If actFault6056Recovery is 'false', then fault 6056 won't be detected and recovery mechanism won't be triggered (alarm won't be reported).    Note: Enabling this automatic recovery helps the operator to decrease number of manual resets for cells entering the sleeping state due to Symbol Index Shift problem.

Parameter name: Activate flexible carrier aggregation management
Description: This parameter activates the feature "Flexible carrier aggregation management".

Parameter name: Activate flexible carrier spacing for NB-IoT standalone
Description: This parameter activates the flexible carrier spacing between NB-IoT standalone carriers and wideband LTE or NB-IoT standalone carriers.  If actFlexCarrierSpacingNB is set to 'false', at least 100 kHz minimum edge-to-edge carrier gap is required between NB-IoT standalone carriers and wideband LTE or NB-IoT standalone carriers sharing the same antenna.  If actFlexCarrierSpacingNB is set to 'true', no gap is mandatorily required, but there is a risk of interference.

Parameter name: Activate flexible QCI and ARP PM counter profiles
Description: Parameter actFlexQCIARPPMProfiles activates or deactivates the respective counters introduced by feature LTE2766.

Parameter name: Activate flexible SCell selection
Description: This parameter activates the feature for flexible SCell selection for carrier aggregation.

Parameter name: Activate forced cell switch off
Description: Parameter actForcedCellSwitchOff activates/deactivates the forced cell switch off.

Parameter name: Activate first DMRS based shrinkage algorithm
Description: This parameter activates first DMRS only based shrinking algorithm on LTE PUSCH.    This functionality is applicable for all cells which are hosted on BB cards of AirScale ABIO/ABIN/ABIP/ABIQ/ASOE/ASOF/ASOG/ASOH, no matter if FDD or TDD and no matter if ulCoMp is enabled on the cell or not.    By default the new resource-optimized algorithm will be used in this release. In case of unexpected KPI degradation, this parameter can be used to switch back to the original algorithm.

Parameter name: Activate feature LTE4656 GTP Packet Sequence Monitoring
Description: This parameter activates feature LTE4656 GTP packet sequence monitoring.

Parameter name: Activate GSM redirect with system information
Description: This parameter activates the feature "GSM redirect with system information".

Parameter name: Activate GTP UP Sequence Numbers on the X2 interface in Uplink
Description: This parameter enables filling the GTP UP Sequence numbers on X2 interface in Uplink.    Note: Sequence Numbers are needed for monitoring the uplink packet loss on the 5G side.

Parameter name: Activate handover from LTE to eHRPD
Description: This parameter activates the feature Handover from LTE to eHRPD.

Parameter name: Activate handover to NR
Description: With this parameter the feature CB007742 'Handover from LTE to 5G Option 2' can be activated and deactivated.

Parameter name: Activate handover from LTE to WCDMA
Description: This parameter enables the Handover from LTE to WCDMA feature.

Parameter name: Activate home eNB mobility
Description: Activates open access home eNB mobility.

Parameter name: Activate home eNB S1 mobility
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE1723, i.e. S1 based handover towards home eNB

Parameter name: Activate home eNB S1 mobility with public safety
Description: This parameter activates the feature CB008607, i.e. S1 based handover to home eNB for UE with public safety bearer.

Parameter name: Activate handover from NR SA
Description: This parameter enables the feature handover from NR SA (5GS to EPS handover).

Parameter name: Activate DL data forwarding during handover from NR SA
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Data forwarding during HO from 5G SA to LTE' (DL user data forwarding during handover from 5GS to EPS).

Parameter name: Activate handover from UTRAN
Description: This parameter enables the feature Handover from UTRAN.

Parameter name: Activation HO without SgNB change
Description: This parameter activates handover without SgNB change functionality for LTE-NR DC Option 3X.    Currently, intra-eNB inter-cell handover without SgNB change functionality and inter-eNB X2 handover without SgNB change functionality are supported.

Parameter name: Activate Hybrid S1 mobility
Description: The parameter activates mobility to hybrid cells.

Parameter name: Activate IP Throughput Counting Method for NonPMQAP Counters
Description: This parameter activates IP Throughput counting method for non-PMQAP counters in the following way:  0: Currently defined method is used, depending on the counter it could be the legacy method or the LTE5077 method  1: Legacy method is imposed for all IP Throughput non-PMQAP counters  2: LTE5077 method is imposed for all IP Throughput non-PMQAP counters    Please check the LTE5077/LTE5625 feature customer documentation for more detailed information about the mentioned calculation methods.

Parameter name: Activate IP Throughput Counting Method for PMQAP Counters
Description: This parameter activates IP Throughput counting method for PMQAP counters in the following way:  0: Currently defined method is used, depending on the counter it could be the legacy method or the LTE5077 method  1: Legacy method is imposed for all IP Throughput PMQAP counters  2: LTE5077 method is imposed for all IP Throughput PMQAP counters    Please check the LTE5077/LTE5625 feature customer documentation for more detailed information about the mentioned calculation methods.

Parameter name: Activate IPv6 MBMS M1 Interface Support
Description: This parameter activates IPv6 MBMS support on the M1 interface.    Note: actIPv6MBMS is only allowed to be set to "true" for AirScale and FSMr3 eNBs.

Parameter name: Activation of idle mode load balancing (IdleLB)
Description: The parameter activates the feature Idle Mode Load Balancing  This flag also activates the following functionalities:  - inter-RAT IdleLB targets  - Load balancing for redirection (requires also the feature 'UE context release with redirect' actRedirect and 'CS Fallback via Redirection' actCSFBRedir)  - IdleLB targets in Mobility profiles (requires also the feature 'Selective Mobility Profiles' actSelMobPrf)  - Support of special SPID values (requires also the feature 'Selective Mobility Profiles' actSelMobPrf)  - Load-triggered idle mode load balancing  - Support of dedicated idle mode mobility priorities

Parameter name: Activation of idle mode load balancing for CA capable UEs
Description: The parameter activates the feature Idle Mode Load Balancing for CA capable UEs  This flag also activates the following functionalities:  - inter-RAT IdleLB targets  - IdleLB targets in Mobility profiles (requires also the feature 'Selective Mobility Profiles' actSelMobPrf)  - Load-triggered idle mode load balancing for CA capable UEs  - Support of dedicated idle mode mobility priorities for CA capable UEs

Parameter name: Activation of advanced CA aware idle mode load balancing
Description: The parameter activates the feature Carrier aggregation aware idle mode load balancing - II (advanced).    If activated, not only the PCell CA capabilities of a UE but also its SCell CA capabilities are taken into account for idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Activation of idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs
Description: The parameter activates the feature EN-DC aware idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.

Parameter name: Activation of idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs
Description: The parameter activates the feature NR SA aware idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs.

Parameter name: Activate idle mode load balancing supported band list
Description: This parameter activates use of the supportedBandListEUTRA (from UE capabilities) to populate the secondary target frequencies from the idleLBEutCelResPrio parameters. Additionally, if activated, the serving cell is always included in the secondary target list.

Parameter name: Activate idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: The parameter activates the feature Idle Mode Load Balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  This flag also activates the following functionalities:  - intra-RAT IdleLB targets  - IdleLB targets in Mobility profiles (requires also the feature 'Selective Mobility Profiles' actSelMobPrf)  - Load-triggered idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs  - Support of dedicated idle mode mobility priorities for TM9 capable UEs

Parameter name: Enable interFrequency handover
Description: This parameter enables the feature Inter Frequency Handover to FDD and TDD neighbor cells.

Parameter name: Activation idle mode mobility CDMA/eHRPD
Description: Activates "Idle mode mobility from LTE to CDMA/eHRPD".

Parameter name: Activation idle mode mobility CDMA/1xRTT
Description: Activates idle mode mobility from LTE to CDMA/1xRTT.

Parameter name: activate increased carrier monitoring
Description: feature flag for increased carrier monitoring

Parameter name: Activation of Increased Number Operator Specific QCIs
Description: CB007897 feature allows to configure up to 42 different QCI values from 3GPP defined range of operator specific QCIs (values 98-100 or 128-254) in LTE eNB database.  When activated it increases number of operator specific QCIs to 42, supporting both GBR and non-GBR QCIs.    All other handling for such QCI bearer shall be used according to legacy mechanism and this feature will not change any logic for bearer management procedures.

Parameter name: Activation of Initial MME Group Identifier
Description: CB008049 MME selection enhancement with initial MME group Id, feature activation flag.    With this feature, the configurable Initial MME Group Id is used to select an MME when a UE enters a pool area (i.e. at initial MME selection).    Load balancing is supported between MMEs having same Initial MME Group Id.    This feature is applicable if the UE has not provided the identifier of the MME at RRC connection establishment (S-TMSI, registered MME) or if the S1 connection to the MME provided by the UE is not available.    This feature applies to wideband LTE, Cat-M and NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Activate inter-eNB DL carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter activates the features 'Inter-eNB DL carrier aggregation' and 'Inter-site DL carrier aggregation' for up to 4 macro or 2 FZM eNBs.

Parameter name: Activate inter-eNB UL carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter activates the functionality for 'Inter-eNB uplink carrier aggregation'.

Parameter name: Activate MDT inter-frequency periodic measurement
Description: This parameter enables the activation of MDT inter-frequency UE periodic measurements.

Parameter name: Activate inter-frequency RSTD measurement support
Description: The parameter configures feature LTE1638 "Inter-frequency RSTD measurement support".  If the feature is activated (configured to 'true') the Flexi-BTS supports UE RSTD (reference signal time difference) inter-frequency measurements for OTDOA.  The UE may request the eNode B to start / stop measurements gaps via RRC:InterFreqRSTDMeasurementIndication message (UEs with 3GPP Release 8 or 9 are not able to request this).    The timing of the measurement gap is derived from the IE measPRS-Offset.    UE controlled inter-frequency RSTD measurements may help to improve the accuracy of OTDOA, without having the pre-requirement of activated OTDOA.

Parameter name: Activate inter-site CA HARQ enhancement
Description: This parameter activates/de-activates the feature 'Inter-site DL carrier aggregation HARQ enhancement'.

Parameter name: Feature Activation Flag Additional Layer 1 PM Group 1 and Group 3 Counters
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the following PM counters from feature Additional Layer 1 Performance Measurements:    Group 1: M8005C306-M8005C313, M8005C336-M8805C339, M8005C317-M8005C325, M8005C326-M8005C335, M8005C314, M8010C74, M8010C75  Group 3: M8031C0-M8031C259, M8031C520-M8031C539, M8031C260-M8031C519, M8031C540-M8031C559    Activation of the other counters from feature LTE1491 is controlled by parameter actServicePRButiL.

Parameter name: Activate load-based power saving
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Load-Based Power Saving for Multi-Layered Networks'. When the feature is activated, intra-eNB cells that provide service to the same coverage area may be automatically switched off/on according to the aggregate load across the set of cells (Power Saving Group).    Note:  There is no coordination between Load-Based Power Saving and the technologies that are configured for RF Sharing.

Parameter name: Activate load-based reduced TX power saving
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Load-Based Power Saving with TX-Path Switch Off'. When the feature is activated, intra-eNB cells that provide service to the same coverage area may have TX-Paths automatically switched off/on according to the aggregate load across the set of cells (Power Saving Group).    Note:  There is no coordination between Load-Based Power Saving and the technologies that are configured for RF Sharing.

Parameter name: Activate LPPa enhanced cell ID location service
Description: The parameter activates the support of the enhanced cell ID measurement initiation procedure on the LPPa layer.

Parameter name: Activate LPPa enhanced cell ID location service for NB-IoT
