Description: The parameter activates the support of the enhanced cell ID measurement initiation procedure on the LPPa layer for NB-IoT.    Note: Only Timing Advance Type 2 is supported for NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: Activate LPPa support for OTDOA
Description: Activates support of the LPPa OTDOA information request procedure via S1AP

Parameter name: Activate intra LTE S1based handover
Description: This parameter enables the feature Intra LTE Inter eNodeB Handover via S1.

Parameter name: Activate LAA prioritization over EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates LAA prioritization over EN-DC for UEs which doesn't support LAA and EN-DC on NR FR1 bands simultaneously.    Only those LNCEL which are configured to support Flexible LTE CA with EN-DC (i.e. are listed in cAggrLteNrDcCellList) are eligible to be configured for LAA prioritization over EN-DC (i.e. are allowed to be configured in laaOverEnDcCellList).  For details about supported LAA frequency bands, see description of actUnlicensedAcc.

Parameter name: Activate load based PSG control logic enhancement
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the Cell/TX switch off and PSG control logic enhancement.

Parameter name: Activate eNB system load PM counter
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the feature eNB System Load PM Counter.

Parameter name: Activate location reporting
Description: Activation/deactivation of Location Reporting (feature 'Support of cell based location service').

Parameter name: Activate location reporting for NB-IoT
Description: Activation/deactivation of Location Reporting for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Activate LTE-NR dynamic spectrum sharing
Description: This parameter activates dynamic spectrum sharing between LTE and NR.  If activated, DSS mode for each DSS cell needs to be configured.  Depending on the DSS mode (lteNrDssMode), the necessary structures lteNrDssDlRatio, lteNrDssUlRatio or lteNrDssMbsfnRatio need to be configured.

Parameter name: Activation LTE-NR dual connectivity
Description: This parameter activates LTE-New Radio Dual Connectivity (EN-DC) functionality.

Parameter name: Activate LTE-NR fast neighbor relation addition
Description: This parameter activates NR ANR fast neighbor relation addition.

Parameter name: Activate support for MBMS
Description: Activates the feature 'Multimedia Broadcast/Multicast Service (MBMS)'.  If the LTE BTS is configured to support FDD and TDD concurrently (i.e. supportedCellTechnology is set to 'mixed_FDD_TDD') and MBMS is activated then it is applied only for FDD cells.    MBMS will be only activated if actOtdoa, sib2xTransmit and liquidCellConfigInfo-csiRsSubfr (if actLiquidCell equal to 'true') have the same value in all LNCEL_FDD instances with earfcnDL equal to mbsfnEarfcn and dlChBw equal to mbsfnChBw.    MBMS will be only activated if actOtdoa, LTE2085 activation status and csiRsConfigInfo-csiRsSubfrConf (if (dlMimoMode is set to ('Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)' OR 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)' OR 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)' OR 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)' OR 'Closed Loop MIMO (16x2)') AND (activatedMimoTM is NOT set to 'TM4')) have the same value in all LNCEL_FDD instances with earfcnDL equal to mbsfnEarfcn and dlChBw equal to mbsfnChBw.    FDD only: If reportedEirpHeadroomPrb is smaller than 0 then actMBMS may need to be considered in order to achieve activation of EIRP Control (actEirpControl equal to 'nonBeamforming').    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released, if this parameter is online modified and Cat-M is activated.

Parameter name: Activates cell resource allocation to eMBMS in 3 MHz bandwidth
Description: Activates guaranteed cell resource allocation of 60% to eMBMS in 3 MHz bandwidth.

Parameter name: Activate eMBMS for public safety
Description: Activates eMBMS enhancements for Public Safety.

Parameter name: Activate MBMS service continuity
Description: This parameter activates the feature "MBMS Service Continuity".    Please note that the feature is only active in cells with SIB15 configured in sibSchedulingList.

Parameter name: Activate MDT cell trace
Description: This is a feature flag to enable or disable LTE953 MDT Trace feature. The same feature flag is also used for LTE1501 and LTE1308.

Parameter name: Activate MDT Subscriber Trace
Description: This is a feature flag to enable or disable MDT Subscriber trace feature.

Parameter name: Activate MDT logged MBA
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE1049: MDT - UE measurement logs  If new TCE connections are added or existing TCE connections are deleted, while LTRACE sessions are active, please check the description for LTE1049: MDT - UE Measurement Logs or 'Tracing in LTE and SRAN' documentation from FL19B release.

Parameter name: Activate MFBI support
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the feature "Multiple Frequency Band Indicator" (LTE1534)  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Activate mobility profile level measurement gap
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'NR Measurement Gap Need in mobility profile'.

Parameter name: Activate mapped band support in inter-frequency measurement
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates mapped band support during inter-frequency measurements.

Parameter name: Activate measurement-based idle mode load balancing
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'measurement-based idle mode load balancing'.

Parameter name: Activate measurement gaps coordination in LTE-NR DC
Description: This parameter is used to activate measurement gaps coordination in LTE-NR dual connectivity.
Range and step: disabled (0), eNB initiated (1), eNB and SgNB initiated (2)

Parameter name: Activate measurement gaps for all inter-frequency and inter-RAT measurements while in EN-DC
Description: Parameter to activate trigger of measurement gap configuration when UE is in EN-DC and LTE inter-frequency or inter-RAT measurements are configured.

Parameter name: Activate NR-MFBI support in EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates MFBI support in NR frequencies for EN-DC.

Parameter name: Activate mixed switch off method of MIMO Muting
Description: This parameter activates additional mixed power saving operation mode to support both switch off options of MIMO Muting, respectively Cell Switch Off, for a same cell during same period of time.

Parameter name: Activate MMEC PLMN ID based MME selection
Description: This parameter activates the MMEC and PLMN ID based MME selection.  If this parameter is set to 'true', then for UEs moving from 2G/3G to LTE, exclusion of MMEGI information in MME selection is possible, i.e. eNB is able to select the MME based on only the MME Code and selected PLMN-Identity.

Parameter name: Activate feature LTE5701 Mobility profile based Data Volume Counters
Description: This parameter activates feature LTE5701 Mobility profile based Data Volume Counters

Parameter name: Activate MRO inter-RAT UTRAN
Description: The parameter is used to enable feature LTE1749 "MRO InterRat UTRAN".    The activation of the feature for functional usage does require to activate LTE56 "Inter RAT handover to WCDMA" or LTE898 "TDD inter-RAT handover to TD-SCDMA".

Parameter name: Activate multiple bearers
Description: This parameter activates the support of multiple EPS Bearers.

Parameter name: Activate multiple GBR bearers
Description: This parameter activates the support of multiple GBR EPS Bearers.

Parameter name: Activation EN-DC multiple SCG split bearers
Description: This parameter activates LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC) support for multiple SCG split bearers functionality.

Parameter name: Activates multiple EN-DC bearers without eLCID
Description: This parameter activates multiple EN-DC bearers without eLCID.

Parameter name: Activate multiple carrier operation
Description: This parameter activates multiple carrier operation.  When the parameter is set to value "false", the eNB is working in a single carrier operation, when set to one of the other values, it is working in multi carrier operation. The parameter needs to be configured always to the highest number of carriers transmitted over the same antenna line in the eNB.    An FDD eNB supports up to 6 carrier configurations at the same antenna line.  A TDD eNB supports up to 4 carrier configurations at the same antenna line.    The BTS will dynamically decide depending on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Activate nonGBR service differentiation
Description: This parameter activates the Service Differentiation for non-GBR Bearers.

Parameter name: Activate NR frequency filter for EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'EN-DC control per mobility profile'.

Parameter name: Activate network requested UE radio capabilities
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Network requested UE radio capabilities'.  The feature'Network requested UE radio capabilities' implements the eNB functionality for 3GPP CR 1515/1630 to 3GPP 36.331.  It is recommended that operator enables this feature if they have configured carrier aggregation in their network.

Parameter name: Activate online TX switching
Description: This parameter activates the feature SR003080 'Power saving with online TX path switching off for Energy Efficiency'. When the feature is activated, 2Tx/4Tx cell will support load based TX-Paths automatically switched off/on without changing the MIMO configuration.    This feature extends LTE1203 feature with an option to shut down one (in 2TX configurations) or two (in 4TX configurations) TX paths without changing the MIMO configuration.

Parameter name: Activate support of operator specific QCIs
Description: This parameter activates the support of establishment of EPS bearers with QCI in the range of (98-100 or 128-254) in case of non-GBR and in the range of (128-254) for GBR.

Parameter name: Activate support of operator specific GBR QCIs
Description: This parameter activates the support of establishment of GBR EPS bearers with QCI in the range of 128...254.

Parameter name: Activate optimized MME selection
Description: Activates the optimized MME selection algorithm  If this parameter is set to 'true', the MME selection function distinguishes native and mapped GUMMEIs according to TS 23.401. If UE provides its (old) GUMMEI, the MME selection function based on GUMMEI is restricted to the corresponding RATs.    If this parameter is set to 'false', the MME selection function does not distinguish native and mapped GUMMEIs. If UE provides its (old) GUMMEI, the MME selection function based on GUMMEI will consider all RATs.

Parameter name: Activate optimized L3 pool
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE5582 'Single C-plane pool per ASIA/ASIB with ABIA/ABIAL as a BB card', optimized C-Plane pool deployment on the eNB.

Parameter name: Activate PCMD report
Description: This parameter enables the activation of PCMD Report on eNB level.  Although PCMD reporting uses the trace framework the enabling of the feature flag for cell tracing is not a precondition for PCMD reporting.  This parameter does not apply to NB-IoT technology.

Parameter name: Activate feature LTE4254 PMQAP profiles extension per counters
Description: This parameter activates feature LTE4254 PMQAP profiles extension per counters

Parameter name: Activation PS blocking for cell with PA call
Description: This parameter activates Power Saving blocking for cell with Priority access call ongoing.

Parameter name: Activate partial admission for handover
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'ARP based partial admission control for handover'.  If the feature is activated Target eNodeB will perform ARP based partial admission control for incoming handover due to radio reasons and service based handover for emergency services. If partial handover is applied, admission control may decide not to admit E-RABs with vulnerability Pre-Emptable. Nevertheless handover preparation will be accepted

Parameter name: Activate PCell swap
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'PCell Swap' for the Flexi Macro FDD and TDD eNBs.

Parameter name: Activate PDCP robust header compression
Description: This parameter activates the usage of PDCP Robust Header Compression.

Parameter name: Activate PLMN based preemption
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'PLMN based pre-emption candidate selection'.    Please note that the feature is only activated in cells where a preemption profile (PREEMPPR) is assigned with the parameter preempProfileId.

Parameter name: Activate PLMN Unavailable for cell(s) fault report
Description: Activate 'No PLMN available for cell(s)' fault report mode.  If 'disabled' is selected, the 'No PLMN available for cell(s)' fault report function is disabled.  If 'cell' is selected, the alarm will be reported at cell level. Note: There is a risk of alarm flood for cell level alarm report.

Parameter name: Activation of Predefined KPIs Observability
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE3577 'Predefined KPIs observability based on real time selected counters'.

Parameter name: Indicates if Cat-M preemption vulnerability for DRB bearers and UE Contexts is disabled or not
Description: This parameter indicates if DRB bearer and UE context pre-emption vulnerability for CAT-M devices is honored by eNB (enabled) or always treated as false (disabled) regardless of the value provided by the core network.

Parameter name: Activate prohibition of CA-specific cell deployments
Description: This parameter activates prohibition of the usage of CA-specific cell deployments for FDD cells in AirScaleABIA/ABIAL for inter-eNB FDD-TDD CA if baseband pooling is activated (actBbPooling is 'true').  - If configured to 'false', then CA-specific cell sets (CA-packed cell set/dual CA-packed cell set/triple CA-packed cell set/quad CA-packed cell set) are used.  - If configured to 'true', then legacy cell sets are used.    Note: Activating the prohibition of CA-specific cell deployments requires inter-eNB DL CA (actInterEnbDLCAggr) and baseband pooling (actBbPooling) to be activated.

Parameter name: Activate prohibition of WCDMA mobility before QCI1
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates prevention of WCDMA mobility before QCI1 bearer setup.

Parameter name: Activation of PWS Restart & Failure Indication
Description: When the parameter is set to 'true', S1AP: PWS Restart Indication and S1AP: PWS Failure Indication procedures are supported.

Parameter name: Activate QCI and PLMN ID counter profiles
Description: Parameter actQCIPLMNIDProfiles activates or deactivates the QCI and PLMNID differentiation for the PMQAP Profiles containing the PLMN ID configuration.

Parameter name: Activate marking of DSCP based on QCI and ARP
Description: This parameter activates the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) marking based on Quality of service Class Identifier (QCI) ) and Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP).    Note1: If the feature is de-activated or no (QCI + ARP) - DSCP marking is defined, legacy (QCI only) marking will be applied.  Note2: If "Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) marking based on Quality of service Class Identifier (QCI) ) and Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP)" is activated (LNBTS-actQciArpToDscpMarking = 'true') and qciTab[69|70]-includeInTacMeas is 'true', then the dscp values configured for the different ARP ranges of QCI [69|70] must be unique from the dscp values configured for the different ARP ranges of the other non-GBR QCIs 6,7,8,9,[70|69] and operator specified non-GBR.

Parameter name: Activate RRC Connection Establishment Failure reporting
Description: This parameter is used for enabling/disabling of the feature "MDT - UE RRC Connection Establishment Failure reporting".    RRC Connection Establishment Failure report can be created by UE upon failed RRC connection establishment attempt. RCEF report may contain information about signal power/quality of selected cell, RA statistics, neighbor cell measurements and UE location.

Parameter name: Activate support for RRC Connection Re-establishment with EN-DC SCG split bearers
Description: This parameter activates feature 'RRC Connection Re-establishment with EN-DC SCG split bearers' by enabling different groups of RRC Re-establishment scenarios as they are defined in legacy RRC re-establishment feature.    For feature activation following states are to be distinguished:  A. 'disabled'  B. 'RCR-servingCell' - - enables scenario 1    Following RRC Re-establishment scenarios are defined in legacy RRC re-establishment feature:  1. Serving cell  2. Source cell of HO with source cell context  3. Target cell of intra eNB HO with source cell context  4. Target cell of intra eNB HO with target cell context  5. Target cell of X2 HO with source cell context  6. Target cell of X2 HO with target cell context  7. Target cell of S1 HO with source cell context  8. Target cell of S1 HO with target cell context  9. RLF triggered intra eNodeB Handover  10. RLF triggered X2 handover    Scenarios 1 to 8 are basic re-establishment scenarios while 9 and 10 cover RLF triggered handover.    In xL current release this feature supports scenario 1 only.  Other scenarios will be supported in future SW release.

Parameter name: Activate RRC Connection reestablishment using MAC retry
Description: Activate support for the MAC retry procedures by the UE during RRC Reestablishment procedure. Activating this parameter will allow subsequent RRC Re-establishments during RRC Re-establishment procedure due to mac-ContentionResolutionTimer expiry at the UE.

Parameter name: Activate RAN Information Management for GSM
Description: The parameter activates the LTE498: RAN Information Management (RIM) for GSM feature.

Parameter name: Activate RAN information management for UTRAN
Description: The parameter activates the feature LTE1196 'RAN Information Management (RIM) for WCDMA'.

Parameter name: Activate RLF report evaluation
Description: This parameter is used for enabling/disabling of the feature "UE Radio Link Failure report evaluation".  When the feature is activated the eNB will trigger the retrieval of RLF reports from UEs if it has received the rlf-InfoAvailable IE either during  - RRCConnectionSetupComplete  - RRCConnectionReestablishmentComplete  - RRCConnectionReconfigurationComplete  message.    This retrieval is independent whether there is a trace session active to trace these messages or not.    Furthermore, RLF reports are forwarded via RLFIndication message on X2AP interface to the "RLF cell" if applicable, i.e. when the "RLF cell" is different to the current Pcell.

Parameter name: Activate RLF based RRC connection reestablishment
Description: Activates the feature 'Radio Link Failure (RLF) based RRC connection reestablishment (RCR)'

Parameter name: Activate RLF based RRC connection reestablishment during L1 reconfiguration
Description: Activates the support of RLF based RRC connection reestablishment during the reconfiguration of SR, SRS and CQI reporting.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced RLF based RRC connection reestablishment
Description: Activates the feature 'Enhanced Radio Link Failure (RLF) based RRC connection reestablishment (RCR)'

Parameter name: Activate enhanced RLF based RRC connection reestablishment for intra-eNB.
Description: Activates the feature 'Enhanced Radio Link Failure (RLF) based RRC connection reestablishment (RCR)' for intra-eNB cases. This can be activated independent of actRLFbasedRCREnhanced (LTE3105) or actRLFbasedRCR (LTE1617).

Parameter name: Activate RLF based RRC Connection Reestablishment with Target CRNTI
Description: Activates the feature 'Radio Link Failure (RLF) based RRC Connection Reestablishment (RCR) with Target CRNTI'.

Parameter name: Activate RRC reestablishment and RLF PM counters per QCI and ARP PM counter profiles
Description: Parameter actRRCConnReestablRLF files activates or deactivates the respective counters introduced by feature LTE2782.

Parameter name: Activate RSRP and RSRQ histograms
Description: Parameter actRSRPRSRQHist activates or deactivates the RSRP and RSRQ Histogram counters

Parameter name: Activate radio position flexibility
Description: This parameter indicates whether the cell should be mapped to the configured topology RMOD-connectionList-positionInChain or to the same previously connected radio when there is an OBSAI Optical Transport Network (OTN) topology change between the System/Baseband and Radio Module.  When actRadioPosFlexibility = false, the BTS will not re-establish the cell if the radio detected is not in the same position as defined in the RMOD-connectionList-positionInChain.  When actRadioPosFlexibility = true, the BTS will check if an RF module matches the one used prior to the OTN change by its serial number, and based on it re-establishes a cell.

Parameter name: Activate RAN sharing enhancements
Description: This parameter activates RAN sharing enhancements.    Allowed values are:  0:disabled (default): RAN sharing enhancements are disabled and legacy limits apply, i.e., there can be a maximum of 8 PLMNs and transport separation for maximum 6 operators.  10:max_10_PLMNs: RAN sharing enhancement are enabled and there can be a maximum of 10 PLMNs and transport separation for maximum 10 operators.

Parameter name: Activate recalculating unlocked SCells as CA candidates
Description: This parameter activates triggering CA capability re-calculation after a cell becomes unlocked.  The BTS then takes this unlocked cell as a SCell candidate by (re) starting non-GBR buffer monitoring, not only for new RRC connections as in legacy behavior, but also for UEs already in RRC_CONNECTED with any PCells, which have this unlocked cell configured as a SCell candidate.

Parameter name: Enable UE context release with redirect
Description: This parameter enables the feature UE context release with redirect.

Parameter name: Activate Reduction of Aperiodic CQI Requests with Fast UL grants
Description: This parameter enables reduction of aperiodic CQI / RI / PMI requests for Rel 14 UEs configured for "skippable" UL grants.

Parameter name: Activation reject HO in cell reserved for operator use
Description: This parameter enables the feature rejection of incoming X2/S1 handover in a target cell reserved for the operator use. When feature is enabled, handover for UEs for which selected PLMN ID in the target cell is reserved for the operator use shall be rejected.

Parameter name: Activate TDD Remote Interference Report
Description: This parameter enables the activation of Remote Interference Report on eNB level.

Parameter name: Activate RRC connected mode while no activity
Description: This parameter activates the functionality to keep the UE in RRC connected mode even if there is no activity (e.g. during ringtone) until QCI1 establishment triggered protection timer expiry.

Parameter name: Activate prohibit timer for RRC Connection Release after last QCI1 bearer release
Description: This parameter activates the functionality to keep Wide Band UE in RRC connected mode for a longer period than legacy C-Plane/ U-Plane inactivity timers after last QCI1 is released to help reduce call setup time that may happen within this period.    Activation of this functionality may lead to KPI degradation as UEs will be kept longer connected after VoLTE calls and will thus experience radio link failure (and other types of failures) with a higher probability.

Parameter name: Activate RSRQ-based A5
Description: This parameter activates the inter-frequency mobility based on A5 RSRQ measurements.

Parameter name: Activate RSRQ-based B2
Description: This parameter activates the inter-RAT mobility based on B2 RSRQ measurements.

Parameter name: Activate RT performance monitoring
Description: This is a feature flag to enable or disable the RT Performance Monitoring Feature and to select which type of RT PM is chosen.  The value All_PM_Counters is used for enabling the LTE1053 feature content, whereas PDCP_SDU_Group is used for specific PM counter subset as required in LTE2054.

Parameter name: Activation status of S1 flex feature
Description: This parameter indicates whether S1 Flex feature is enabled or disabled.

Parameter name: Activate S1 overload handling
Description: This parameter activates the S1 Overload Handling feature.

Parameter name: Activation idle mode mobility to NR SA (SIB24)
Description: This parameter activates SIB24 for cell reselection from LTE to NR SA (standalone).

Parameter name: Activate satellite backhaul support
Description: The parameter activates the support of satellite connections within S1- and X2 links.    Setting the parameter to 'true' does not indicate that the eNB itself has satellite backhaul. For indication of eNB itself having satellite backhaul its eNB ID must be included in the range of eNB IDs which is configured with the LNSENB parameter satBhEnbIdRanges.

Parameter name: SDL activation flag
Description: This is a feature flag to enable or disable the SDL Feature.

Parameter name: Activate secondary RAT usage data report for EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates the secondary RAT usage data report for EN-DC. When activated, eNB forwards a secondary RAT usage data report received on X2 from gNB via S1 to MME.      Note: Forwarding of event triggered secondary RAT data usage report can be enabled with parameter actEvtSecRatRep.

Parameter name: Activate UE capability information segmentation
Description: This parameter activates the support for uplink dedicated message (RRC:UECapabilityInformation) segmentation in the eNB.

Parameter name: Activate selective mobility profiles
Description: This parameter activates the features 'Selective Mobility Profiles' and - in case the LNBTS parameter moProfileSelect is set to 'plmn' or 'combined' - also 'PLMN ID and SPID selected mobility profiles'.    If this parameter is 'true':  - Mobility profiles are used to configure HO mobility, Redirection and Idle Mode Mobility reconfiguration (MOPR/MODPR, MORED/MODRED and MOIMP/MODIMP).    If this parameter is 'false':  - for HO mobility:  - if MODPR exists, then MODPR configuration is used for HO mobility. Otherwise LNHOIF, LNHOW, LNHOG configuration is used.  - MOPR configuration is never used.  - for Redirection and Idle Mode Mobility configuration:  - REDRT, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL configuration are always used.  - MORED, MODRED, MOIMP and MODIMP configurations are never used.

Parameter name: Activate service based mobility thresholds
Description: This parameter activates the features 'Dedicated mobility thresholds for SRVCC' and 'Service based handover thresholds' and activates a mechanism for different points of triggering handover.  Dedicated service based thresholds are used for measurements when UE has QCI1 bearer.  Note: Use of dedicated thresholds is not dependent on SRVCC features being enabled.

Parameter name: Feature Activation Flag Additional Layer 1 PM Group 2 Counters
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the following PM counters from feature Additional Layer 1 Performance Measurements:    Group 2: M8011C151-M8011C160, M8011C140-M8011C149, M8011C150, M8011C161    Activation of the other counters from LTE1491 feature is controlled by parameter actL1PM.

Parameter name: Activation SN initiated SN change for LTE-NR DC Option 3X
Description: This parameter activates SN initiated SN change for LTE-NR DC Option 3X

Parameter name: Activate special duplexing gap for NB-IoT standalone
Description: This parameter activates 3 SA NB-IoT carriers with special duplexing gap in NB-IoT cell

Parameter name: Activation of Split UE NR Capability Retrieval
Description: CB010232: 'Splitting combined NR/EUTRA-NR UE Capability Transfer procedure' feature activation flag, this parameter indicates whether "nr" and "eutra-nr" UE capabilities shall be retrieved together or separately by eNB.

Parameter name: Activation of stepwise addition of multiple bearers for EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC) support for stepwise addition of multiple SCG split bearers functionality.

Parameter name: Activate subscriber and equipment trace
Description: This is a feature flag to enable or disable Subscriber & Equipment Trace feature.

Parameter name: Activate UE IMEI SV based TM9 blocking
Description: This parameter enables the feature UE IMEI SV based TM9 blocking.

Parameter name: Activate timing advance histogram PM counters
Description: The parameter activates the feature 'Timing advance histogram PM counters'  Note: In addition, the measurement M8029 needs to be started in each LNCEL separately.

Parameter name: Activate TCP booster simplified solution
Description: This parameter activates TCP booster function.

Parameter name: Activate temporary handover blacklisting
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Temporary handover blacklisting'.  If activated, handover target cells will be temporarily blacklisted for some time in case of consecutive HO preparation failures or a rejected HO preparation with a selected set of cause values.  Blacklisting time and number of consecutive HO preparation timeouts are configurable. Cells will also be temporarily blacklisted for some time in case of a rejected HO preparation by target eNB with cause value "Radio Network Layer Cause (Cell not Available)", "Miscellaneous Cause (Control Processing Overload)" or "Miscellaneous Cause (Not enough User Plane Processing Resources)".

Parameter name: Activate trace overload protection
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the overload protection mechanism due to debug trace streaming.  More precisely, if this parameter is equal to TRUE, this activates the mechanism to automatically stop the ongoing streaming of debug logs in case of overload detection from:  - LTE L2 trace streaming  - LTE CP trace streaming

Parameter name: Block support of out of sequence ENDC DUD frames
Description: This parameter indicates the NR-U DUD loss reporting procedure.    False - the loss report is delayed after NR-U SN gap is detected, while waiting for a possible out of order DUD.  True - the loss report is sent immediately after detecting a gap in the NR-U SNs, which enables an efficient re-transmission attempt.

Parameter name: Activate transport separation for LTE RAN sharing
Description: This parameter configures the use of the feature "Transport Separation for LTE RAN Sharing".

Parameter name: Activate UL 256 QAM for EN-DC capable UEs
Description: This parameter activates UL 256 QAM for EN-DC capable UEs in the following way:  0: disabled  1: nonConcurrent - - EN-DC capable UEs may get UL 256QAM on PCell/SCell with UL carrier configured when not in EN-DC mode.  2: concurrent - - EN-DC capable UEs may get UL 256QAM on PCell with UL carrier configured independent from EN-DC mode.    If the feature is active it will be applicable on the LNCELs with actModulationSchemeUL set to '256QAM' or '256QAMand16QAMHighMCS'.

Parameter name: Activation of uplink carrier aggregation
Description: The parameter activates uplink carrier aggregation. The feature can only be activated in addition to downlink carrier aggregation.    If activated (actULCAggr is configured to 'UL_CA_with_smartSched'), only UEs with pathloss less than ulCaPathlossThr could be scheduled in multiple serving cells for uplink.    Following features in detail are activated:  - LTE1092 "FDD uplink carrier aggregation for 2 CCs"    Note:  For FDD cells UL Carrier aggregation smart scheduling is always used in mixed cell technology configurations in the BTS, i.e., if the supportedCellTechnology is set to 'mixed_FDD_TDD' and actULCAggr is set to 'UL_CA_without_SmartSched' smart scheduling applies.

Parameter name: Activate UL CA for EN-DC
Description: Activation parameter for UL CA configuration of EN-DC capable UEs. A value of 'nonConcurrentULCaAndEnDc' activates the configuration of UL CA for UEs which are EN-DC capable but not in EN-DC mode.

Parameter name: Activate GPS and UTC time broadcast
Description: This parameter enables the feature LTE3056 support GPS and UTC time Information broadcast (SIB16).    Note: If SIB16 is configured in this cell, all Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when actUTCBroadcast is modified.

Parameter name: Activate UAV support
Description: Activates support for Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (drones).    Available options:  - disabled: UAVs are handled in the same way as terrestrial UEs;  - basic support: UAV-specific handling (including uplink power control) is applied for UAV UEs during their whole lifetime on cell;

Parameter name: Activate UE-based ANR for Inter-frequency LTE
Description: This parameter indicates if the 'Intra-LTE Inter-Frequency UE-based ANR' feature is activated by the operator.

Parameter name: Activate UE-based ANR for intra-Frequency LTE
Description: This parameter indicates if the 'Intra-LTE Intra-Frequency UE-based ANR' feature is activated by the operator.

Parameter name: Activate ANR for EN-DC with resolution of unknown cells
Description: This parameter activates the feature ANR for EN-DC with resolution of unknown cells (NR-reportCGI) and enables activation of auto-removal of unused NR neighbor relations.

Parameter name: Activate ANR for 5G HO with resolution of unknown cells
Description: This parameter activates the feature ANR for 5G-HO with resolution of unknown cells (NR-reportCGI) and enables activation of auto removal of unused NR neighbor relations.

Parameter name: Activate UE-based ANR for UTRAN
Description: This parameter indicates if the feature ''UE-based ANR for Inter-RAT UTRAN" neighbor cells is activated by the operator.

Parameter name: Activate UE MR-DC capability based handover
Description: The parameter is used to activate the EN-DC capability based handover to steer EN-DC capable UEs to dedicated frequency layers which are also reported in UE MR-DC capabilities as EN-DC anchor layers for the pre-configured NR band combinations.

Parameter name: Activation UE level MRO
Description: Feature activation/deactivating flag of UE Level MRO

Parameter name: Activate support of user location information reporting
Description: This parameter activates support of user location information reporting

Parameter name: Activate UE throughput measurements
Description: This parameter is used for enabling/disabling of the feature "Addition of MAC measurements to cell trace".

Parameter name: Activate UE triggered EN-DC take-back
Description: This parameter activates UE triggered EN-DC take-back  If activated, the MeNB detects 'SCGFailureInformationNR' from the UE with the specific settings of particular information elements (measResultFreqListNR-r15, failure type).    Following options are available: disabled, ignore, release    Depending on the setting of this parameter, eNB will:  0: disabled - - send 'X2AP: SGNB MODIFICATION REQUEST' to gNB  1: ignore - - ignore this SCG failure indication and not forward it to gNB  2: release - - trigger EN-DC take-back

Parameter name: Activate improve UL grant efficiency for TCP Boost
Description: This parameter activates improvements in proactive UL grant efficiency for TCP Boost.

Parameter name: Activate in-device coexistence for UL CA with GNSS
Description: This parameter activates feature "In-Device Coexistence."  If the LTE BTS is configured to support FDD and TDD concurrently (i.e. supportedCellTechnology is configured to 'mixed_FDD_TDD'), and feature "In-Device Coexistence" is activated, then it is applied only for FDD cells.  If this feature is activated, the network supports In-Device Coexistence for uplink carrier aggregation with GNSS for emergency and non-emergency calls. When triggered, the network suspends SCell uplink scheduling. The feature can only be activated in addition to uplink carrier aggregation.

Parameter name: Activate UL traffic-driven UL CA
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'UL traffic-driven UL carrier aggregation SCell configuration'.

Parameter name: Activate low latency fast UL grants
Description: This parameter activates LTE4066 Low Latency Fast UL Grants

Parameter name: Activate Differentiation for PUSCH closed loop power control
Description: This parameter activates differentiation for PUSCH closed loop power control, per single specific QCI selected by the operator and per UL modulation.  Differentiation here refers to ability of operator to set closed loop power control settings for a specific QCI to be either more aggressive (boost) or less aggressive (de-boost) than settings for all other QCIs. Separate settings are provided for UL modulation less than 64QAM, for 64QAM and 256QAM.    The functionality enabled by setting actUlpcDiffPusch to 'true' will only take effect at cells corresponding to this LNBTS for which actUlpcMethod is set to one of the following PUSCH closed loop settings:  - PuschCLPucchOL or PuschCLPucchCL or PuschCLSrsPucchOL or PuschCLSrsPucchCL    For cells at which actUlpcMethod is not one of those mentioned above, setting actUlpcDiffPusch to 'true' has no effect.

Parameter name: Activate U-plane overload handling
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'U-plane overload handling'.    Three levels of load are defined and, if configured and enabled, countermeasures will be executed according to load level.

Parameter name: Activation of user layer TCP MSS clamping
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE 1240 'User layer TCP MSS clamping'.  If activated, the MSS in end user TCP SYN packets is reduced to a value avoiding IP fragmentation in the transport layer.

Parameter name: Activate vendor specific cell trace enhancements
Description: Parameter actVendSpecCellTraceEnh activates or deactivates additional vendor specific Cell Trace enhancements (LTE1501, LTE1931, LTE1914).

Parameter name: Activate VoLTE quality triggered inter frequency mobility
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE3723 'VoLTE quality triggered inter frequency mobility'.

Parameter name: Activate VoLTE quality triggered SRVCC to GSM
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE3443 'VoLTE quality triggered SRVCC to GSM'.

Parameter name: Activate VoLTE quality triggered SRVCC to WCDMA
Description: This parameter activates VoLTE Quality triggered SRVCC to WCDMA.

Parameter name: Activate the prevention of EN-DC setup during VoLTE
Description: This parameter activates the prevention of EN-DC setup during VoLTE.    Following options are available:  disabled -- EN-DC setup is allowed during VoLte calls  non-emergency QCI1 calls -- EN-DC setup prevented during non-emergency QCI1 calls  emergency QCI1 calls -- EN-DC setup prevented during emergency QCI1 calls  all QCI1 calls -- EN-DC setup prevented during all QCI1 calls  QCI65 and QCI66 calls -- EN-DC setup prevented during QCI65 and QCI66 calls  QCI65/66 and non-emergency QCI1 -- EN-DC setup prevented during QCI65/66 and normal non-emergency QCI1 calls  QCI65/66 and emergency QCI1 -- EN-DC setup prevented during QCI65/66 and emergency QCI1 calls  QCI65/66 and all QCI1 calls -- EN-DC setup prevented during QCI65/66 and all QCI1 calls
Range and step: disabled (0), non-emergency QCI1 calls (1), emergency QCI1 calls (2), all QCI1 calls (3), QCI65 and QCI66 calls (4), QCI65/66 and non-emergency QCI1 (5), QCI65/66 and emergency QCI1 (6), QCI65/66 and all QCI1 calls (7)

Parameter name: Activate keep En-Dc during VoLte setup
Description: This parameter activates keeping ongoing En-Dc during VoLte setup. It works on top of the feature 'VoLTE without EN-DC' (actVoLteNoEnDc) which triggers SgNB release in case of VoLte establishment.  If this parameter is set to 'true', eNB will not trigger SgNB release in case of VoLte establishment, but block En-Dc setup during ongoing VoLte (QCI1 and QCI65/66)

Parameter name: Activate X2 links to gNB to 128
Description: This feature increases the maximal number of X2 links to NR en-gNB up to 128. The maximal number of X2 links to LTE eNB is not modified.

Parameter name: Activation of ZUC algorithm
Description: Controls optional ZUC ciphering and integrity protection algorithms.  This parameter enables/disables optional ZUC ciphering algorithms.

Parameter name: Activate eNACC to GSM
Description: This parameter enables the feature LTE442 Network Assisted Cell Change from LTE to GSM

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 1 - DL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in DL direction for UE category 1.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 1 - UE category
Description: Category of UE.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 1 - UL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in UL direction for UE category 1.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 2 - DL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in DL direction for UE category 2.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 2 - UE category
Description: Category of UE.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 2 - UL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in UL direction for UE category 2.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 3 - DL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in DL direction for UE category 3.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 3 - UE category
Description: Category of UE.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 3 - UL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in UL direction for UE category 3.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 4 - DL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in DL direction for UE category 4.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 4 - UE category
Description: Category of UE.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 4 - UL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in UL direction for UE category 4.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 5 - DL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in DL direction for UE category 5.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 5 - UE category
Description: Category of UE.

Parameter name: AM RLC poll byte table 5 - UL poll byte
Description: AM RLC Poll Byte value in UL direction for UE category 5.

Parameter name: Activate ANR support for LTE with OAM extension
Description: Optional feature flag for feature LTE492 ANR support for LTE with O&M extension

Parameter name: ARP Admission Control offset usage on baseband pooling
Description: This parameter activates the ARP offset treatment on baseband pool resources (DRB admission requests) on AirScale eNodeBs.  Only in case actArpAcOffset is set to 'true' and the ARP offset for the admission request is configured to a lower value than 100% this parameter takes any effect on baseband pool resources.  This parameter is not relevant for FSMF eNodeBs.

Parameter name: Supervision timer for B1-NR for redirect to 5G SA
Description: Supervision timer for reception of B1-NR measurement report for redirection to 5G SA.  After SCG split bearer take back is executed for redirection to 5G SA carrier and timer is started, it indicates how long MeNB will wait for a B1-NR measurement report to validate configured redirection target NR carriers.  Note: Preparation of redirection to 5G SA NR carrier based on B1-NR measurement report at end of RRC phase, may require execution of SCG split bearer take back procedure.

Parameter name: Offset for calculation of B1 supervision time
Description: The parameter defines the offset value for calculation of the maximum waiting time for "CSFB with PS-HO" related B1 measurement reports.    If the supervision timer expires eNB will trigger CS Fallback with redirection to GERAN or UTRAN depending on configuration.    The value 0 ms is not recommended as the B1 supervision timer might always expire.    The B1 supervision time is calculated by adding the offset value to the frequency specific time to trigger value of the related LNHOW/LNHOT object:  B1 supervision time = b1TimeToTriggerCSFBUtraMeas + b1SupervisionOffset

Parameter name: Baseband pool allocation priority list
Description: Defines criteria and priorities for automatic cell allocation to baseband pools.

Parameter name: Allocation criterion
Description: Criterion for mapping of cells to baseband pools.    For AirScale ABIA/ABIAL:  - Parameter value 'L1 balanced' is not supported  - Parameter value 'secondary power group first' shall be selected if at least one ABIA/ABIAL is installed and highest priority (11) shall be given to this value.    For AirScale ABIN/ABINL:  - the supported parameter value is 'Logical group'  - parameter value 'secondary power group first' has no effect    For AirScale ABIO/ABIOL/ABIP/ABIQ or AirScale ASOE/ASOF or AirScale ASOG/ASOH the supported parameter values are:  'Logical group'  'L1 balanced'  AND 'L1 balanced' shall have a lower allocPriority compared to 'Logical group'  - parameter value 'secondary power group first' has no effect    L1_Balance shall balance the allocation of cells between the two L1 pools if possible. In case L1 pools are configured exclusive for different RATs and/or different duplex modes balanced allocation of cell to L1 pools on this baseband board is not possible even if 'L1_Balance' is selected. L1_Balanced mode has no impact on AirScale ABIO/ABIOL baseband boards configured for eCPRI O-RAN configurations.
Range and step: Bandwidth (0), CoMp Set (1), Frequency (2), Logical group (3), Power saving groups (4), RX antennas (5), NB-IOT mode (6), CatM (7), Cell Technology (8), Timing groups (9), L1 balanced (10), secondary power group first (11)

Parameter name: Allocation priority
Description: For AirScale ABIA/ABIAL:  - Parameter value 'L1 balanced' is not supported    For AirScale ABIN/ABINL:  - the supported parameter value is 'Logical group'    For AirScale ABIO/ABIOL/ABIP/ABIQ or AirScale ASOE/ASOF or AirScale ASOG/ASOH the supported parameter values are:  'Logical group'  'L1 balanced'  AND 'L1 balanced' shall have a lower allocPriority compared to 'Logical group'

Parameter name: Evaluation period of the pool resources
Description: Period during which the load measurements are evaluated on cell basis. Based on the load measurements the pool manager redistributes the shared resources again.

Parameter name: Minimum of baseband pool resources
Description: Minimum resource share in percent the baseband pool manager shall assign to the cells. The same share shall be assigned for PUSCH and PDSCH UEs / TTI.  This parameter defines the percentage of the dynamic baseband pool resource which is reserved as a minimum resource for all cells allocated to the baseband pool. This reserve is divided among the cells of the baseband pool. The remaining part of this baseband pool is divided among the cells based on the averaged load within the cells.

Parameter name: Blacklist S1 handover target cells special cause values
Description: If this parameter is set to 'true', eNodeB shall temporarily blacklist S1 Handover target cells in case a S1 Handover preparation is rejected with cause value 'Radio Network Layer Cause (Handover Failure In Target EPC/eNB Or Target System)'.

Parameter name: Blocking ENDC-HO retry after HO from target
Description: This parameter enables blocking periodic retry (as enabled by configUeCapEndcHoRetry) in the target cell for a UE arriving from ENDC-HO target layer.    Following options are available:  0: no blocking - - ENDC-HO periodic retries won't be blocked  1: MRDC based HO - - blocking of periodic retries for MRDC based HO  2: ENDC HO to preferred layer - - blocking of periodic retries for ENDC HO to preferred layer  3: both - - blocking of periodic retries for MRDC based HO and ENDC HO to preferred layer    The blocking can be permanent or time limited or can be disabled for a group of UEs  see timeBlockEndcAtHoFromTrg.
Range and step: no blocking (0), MR-DC based HO (1), ENDC HO to preferred layer (2), both (3)

Parameter name: Blocking NR coverage-based EN-DC steering after HO from target layer
Description: This parameter enables blocking of NR coverage-based EN-DC handover in the target cell for a UE arriving from ENDC-HO target layer.    Following options are available:  0: no blocking: NR coverage based EN-DC HO won't be blocked  1: EN-DC NR-coverage HO: blocking of NR coverage-based HO in handover target cell    The blocking can be permanent or time limited or can be disabled for a group of UEs  see timeBlockEndcAtHoFromTrg.

Parameter name: Blocking state
Description: This parameter describes blocking state of the eNodeB. The value is set by the system.

Parameter name: BTS reset requested
Description: RAT Reset request for LTE part of the BTS. Whenever a (delta-)plan modifying or setting this parameter is downloaded, LTE RAT will reset automatically. This parameter is not intended for use by the operator, but will be used by NetAct to perform automatic troubleshooting actions, which require a RAT reset of the BTS.    The value of the parameter as such is not relevant. However, at each new reset request a different value should be selected.  One way to make sure that the new parameter value is different from the last one is to use the current time stamp. Using this scheme will also document the time at which the reset decision was taken.  However, any other scheme which makes sure the parameter value changes is also possible.    Note: Full BTS reset shall be triggered by creation of MNL/CMD/SWRESETREQ MO.

Parameter name: Control plane DSCP
Description: This parameter defines the differentiated services code point (DSCP) value assigned to the control plane traffic.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation cluster ID
Description: Defines the eNBs (system modules) that are combined in carrier aggregation.  eNBs that host cells that are combined for carrier aggregation are connected via SRIO interface and must have the same caClusterId. No other eNBs in the whole network must have the same caClusterId.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation cluster member ID
Description: Identifies the eNB within a carrier aggregation cluster. Each eNB inside the a cluster must get a unique member ID.    In combination with measurement based CoMP feature fixed parameter value combinations of caClusterMemberId and btsHotelMemberId are required.  Note: Allowed combinations are independent if the BTS is deployed as a single or dual core network element, for deployment related differences please refer to SMOD-btsHotelMemberId.

Parameter name: CA config overload ratio
Description: Carrier Aggregation (CA) SCell configuration ratio in overload level 1. 0% means no SCell configuration requests are handled in overload 1. 100% (or parameter not defined) means all SCell configuration requests are handled normally i.e. no blocking of SCell configuration requests.  SCell deconfiguration requests are not subjected to this ratio and are handled normally.

Parameter name: Carrier Aggregation Control
Description: The parameter controls, whether modification of the carrier aggregation configuration at this instance of LNBTS and its child object instances is allowed only manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct SON algorithms.

Parameter name: CA  intra-cell handover mode
Description: The following intra-cell handover modes to mFBI mapped or native frequency with carrier aggregation needs are supported:    disabled:  intra-cell handover to mFBI mapped or native frequency with CA needs is disabled.    nonCAtoCA:  Intra-cell handover will be performed if there is no CA band combination supported both by UE and eNB for current operating band of the PCell, while there are CA band combinations supported both by UE and ENB for another operating band of the PCell.    moreDLCACapacity:  The mode covers the 'nonCAtoCA' mode. In addition to 'nonCAtoCA' mode Intra-cell handover will be also performed if there are CA band combinations which have more potential DL CA aggregation bandwidth supported both by UE and eNB for PCell on another operating band than current operating band.

Parameter name: Min UE-AMBR downlink for carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter excludes those UEs from carrier aggregation, in which UE-AMBR Downlink is below the caMinDlAmbr threshold.

Parameter name: Min UE-AMBR uplink for carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter excludes those UEs from uplink carrier aggregation, whose UE-AMBR Uplink is below the caMinUlAmbr threshold. Downlink carrier aggregation is still possible for the UE when the DL conditions are met.

Parameter name: Scheduling CA fairness control factor
Description: This parameter controls scheduling fairness between UEs with and without activated SCell (S-LNCEL).  This parameter controls scheduling fairness in DL time and frequency domain scheduling between UEs with and without an active SCell. Value 0 means that no fairness is provided; that is UEs with an SCell activated get maximal benefits; and value 1 means that full fairness is provided that is UEs with and without an active SCell will be treated similarly.  The group of cells that are aggregated should have the same setting for this parameter.

Parameter name: Additional MPR for UL intra-band carrier aggregation
Description: This parameter defines whether or not A-MPR values as defined in Tables 6.2.4.A-1 and 6.2.4.A-2 of 3GPP 36.101 will be sent to the UE.    If set to 'disabled',  A-MPR values will NOT be sent to the UE.    If set to 'enabled',  A-MPR values will be sent for all bands where A-MPR is defined.  For bands where A-MPR is NOT defined, the parameter does not apply.

Parameter name: Cell resource sharing type
Description: The parameter controls whether PLMN ID-based or SPID-based cell resource sharing shall apply if cell resource sharing is activated in one or more cells, i.e. if cellResourceSharingMode is set to values other than 'none'.    If the parameter is modified, all cells with cellResourceSharingMode set to 'DLonly' or 'DLandUL' will be disabled temporarily.

Parameter name: CMAS prolonged offset coefficient
Description: The parameter defines the length of the prolong offset.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Congestion weight algorithm
Description: The Parameter congWeightAlg defines a prioritization behavior in layer 2 (MAC) until either the congestion situation ends or until the congestion situation is resolved by higher layers. There are two different algorithms possible:  - qciPrio: Bearers are prioritized in order of their QCI priority.  - arpPrioPerVul: First bearers with ARP vulnerability "preemptable" are prioritized in order of the ARP priority, then the bearers with ARP vulnerability "not preemptable" also in order of ARP priority.

Parameter name: C-plane overload handling - Enable incoming HO reduction
Description: This parameter enables the C-plane overload countermeasure 'Rejection of incoming inter-eNB handover requests' to reduce the amount of active RRC connections. Dependent on the detected overload level, handovers of calls with low-priority bearers and/or GBR bearers shall be rejected. High-priority and emergency sessions will always be processed.  Explanation of the values:  none: this countermeasure is disabled  OVL1andL2: this countermeasure is enabled for C-plane overload level 1 and 2.  OVL2only: this countermeasure is enabled for C-plane overload level 2 only.

Parameter name: C-plane overload handling - Enable RRC connection reduction
Description: This parameter enables the C-plane overload countermeasure 'Rejection of RRC connection requests' to reduce the amount of active RRC connections dependent on the detected overload level.  Explanation of the values:  none: this countermeasure is disabled  OVL1andL2: this countermeasure is enabled for C-plane overload level 1 and 2.  OVL2only: this countermeasure is enabled for C-plane overload level 2 only.

Parameter name: Default DCN Group Id
Description: The default Dedicated Core Network (DCN) Group Identity per PLMN is optionally configured for rerouting UE to an MME Group when the indicated MME is not available when DECOR (actDCN) feature is activated.    The setting is valid for all category Ues, Legacy, Cat-M UE and NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Default profile index AM
Description: Default Profile Index for RLC and PDCP profiles for RLC AM mode.  The indicated RLC and PDCP profile is used for the configuration of a bearer that has been configured in RLC AM in the source cell of a handover, but for which no RLC and PDCP profile has been configured in the target cell.

Parameter name: Default profile index UM
Description: Default Profile Index for RLC and PDCP profiles for RLC UM mode.  The indicated RLC and PDCP profile is used for the configuration of a bearer that has been configured in RLC UM in the source cell of a handover, but for which no RLC and PDCP profile has been configured in the target cell.

Parameter name: FDD or TDD division
Description: FDD or TDD division

Parameter name: Preference for SCell addition
Description: The parameter defines the preference for SCell addition in case of DL+UL carrier aggregation.  dlCaPreferred is used to decide whether to add an additional downlink SCell when that additional DL SCell will result in an existing DL+UL SCell being reconfigured as a DL only SCell.  dlCaPreferred = 'DLonly'  the eNB will choose to add the additional DL SCell and reconfigure the existing DL+UL SCell to DL only.  dlCaPreferred = 'DLandUL'  the eNB will choose to keep the existing DL+UL SCell and will NOT add the additional DL Scell.

Parameter name: Duration for dynamic blacklisting
Description: This parameter defines the time for which a neighbor cell shall be dynamically blacklisted if it is considered to be barred, to be under C-Plane or U-Plane overload or to be a sleeping cell

Parameter name: Ciphering algorithm parameters - Null ciphering algorithm
Description: Null ciphering algorithm preference. A lower value represents a lower preference, and 0 does not admit the algorithm.

Parameter name: Ciphering algorithm parameters - SNOW 3G-based algorithm
Description: SNOW 3G-based algorithm preference. A lower value represents a lower preference, and 0 does not admit the algorithm.

Parameter name: Ciphering algorithm parameters - AES-based algorithm
Description: AES-based algorithm preference. A lower value represents a lower preference, and 0 does not admit the algorithm.

Parameter name: Ciphering algorithm parameters - ZUC-based algorithm
Description: ZUC-based algorithm preference.  A lower value represents a lower preference, and 0 does not admit the algorithm.

Parameter name: Integrity protection algorithm parameters - Null integrity algorithm
Description: Null integrity protection algorithm preference. A lower value represents a lower preference and 0 does not admit the algorithm.

Parameter name: Integrity protection algorithm parameters - SNOW 3G
Description: SNOW 3G-based algorithm preference. A lower value represents a lower preference, and 0 does not admit the algorithm.

Parameter name: Integrity protection algorithm parameters - AES
Description: AES-based algorithm preference. A lower value represents a lower preference, and 0 does not admit the algorithm.

Parameter name: Integrity protection algorithm parameters - ZUC
Description: ZUC-based algorithm preference.  A lower value represents a lower preference, and 0 does not admit the algorithm.

Parameter name: Enable automatic locking
Description: The parameter enables the feature "Automatic locking".    If the feature is enabled, objects are automatically locked and unlocked by eNB if a parameter which requires object locking is modified via delta plan file.    If graceful shutdown is enabled by setting enableGrflShdn to 'enabled', the less service impacting but slower graceful cell shutdown procedure is performed instead of immediate locking.

Parameter name: Enable bandwidth combination set check for EN-DC band combinations
Description: This parameter enables bandwidth combination set check for EN-DC band combinations.  This is to allow bandwidth combination set check of EN-DC band combinations to be disabled.    When this parameter is set to 'true', eNB checks the bandwidth combination set of the candidate EN-DC band combinations or of the selected EN-DC band combination, excluding from the allowed MRDC band combination list those which are not compatible with the UE's PCell and releasing (or not adding) configured (or candidate) LTE SCells which are not compatible with the selected MRDC band combination respectively.  When this parameter is set to 'false', eNB does not check the bandwidth combination set of candidate or selected EN-DC band combinations.

Parameter name: Enable Bandwidth Combination Checks
Description: This parameter enables the check of bandwidth combinations according to 36.101  If the bandwidths of the bands of a configured CA configuration are not listed in 36.101 or have not been arranged with the operator for any of the bandwidth combination sets signaled by the UE, the UE will not be configured with the CA configuration.  It is recommended to keep this functionality enabled in the field to avoid an erroneous configuration of CA that will cause an ACTIVE-to-IDLE transition of the UE.

Parameter name: Enable combined RSRP and RSRQ check
Description: This parameter enables combined RSRP and RSRQ threshold check after A5 inter-frequency measurement report is received from UE. When this flag is enabled, handover preparation is triggered only if both RSRP and RSRQ thresholds are met.

Parameter name: Activate EN-DC overload protection
Description: This parameter enables the C-plane overload countermeasure 'Restricting admission of EN DC services to reduce the C-plane load by reducing the X2(gNB) signalling'  - New EN DC users - establishing SCG split bearers. (Served as LTE user)  - Incoming Inter eNB Handover with EN DC ( Handover done with bearer take back)  - Incoming Intra eNB Handover with EN DC ( Handover done with bearer take back)    Explanation of the values:  0: none -- this countermeasure is disabled  1: HighLoadOVL1andL2 -- this countermeasure is enabled for C-plane overload level High, 1 and 2.  2: OVL1andL2 -- this countermeasure is enabled for C-plane overload level 1 and 2.  3: OVL2only -- this countermeasure is enabled for C-plane overload level 2 only.    In this release parameter can be set to value 'none' only.  Other options will be supported in future.

Parameter name: Enable graceful cell shutdown
Description: The parameter enables the feature 'Graceful Cell Shutdown'.    If the feature is activated an additional administrative state 'shuttingdown' is supported. It allows a less service impacting cell locking.  It allows a less service impacting cell locking respectively cell deactivation e.g. in case of (conditional) eNB restart.  Before entering 'locked' state of the cell the UEs will be motivated to leave the cell by stepwise reduction of the eNodeB cell TX power (DL power).

Parameter name: Enable BW combination set check for 3GPP non-compliant UEs
Description: This parameter enables Bandwidth combination set check for EN-DC band combinations for 3GPP non-compliant UEs.    Here 3GPP non-compliant UE means UEs which do not provide the supported Bandwidth Combination Set (BCS) for an intra-band EN-DC band combination or for the intra-band component of a mixed intra-band inter-band EN-DC band combination in UE capability.    If this parameter is set to 'true', eNB will assume all BCS(s) defined in 3GPP for this intra-band EN-DC band combination/intra-band component are supported in case the respective IE is not present.

Parameter name: eNB name
Description: Human-readable name of the eNB. It corresponds to the eNB name according to 3GPP 36.413.    The character set is restricted to Printable string according to 3GPP with following supported character:  lower case letters 'a' through 'z', upper case letters 'A' through 'Z', the digits '0' through '9' and the characters ' = ( ) + , - . / : ? and space.  This is a human-readable name for the eNB.  The character set is restricted to printable string according to 3GPP with following supported characters:  lower case letters 'a' through 'z', upper case letters 'A' through 'Z', the digits '0' through '9' and the characters ' = ( ) + , - . / : ? and space.

Parameter name: ENDC ANR auto removal disallowed for NR cells in ESS
Description: EN-DC ANR auto-removal for NR cells in Energy Saving state is disallowed if this parameter flag is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: EN-DC Scheduling Weight Boost for Downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the DL scheduling weight scaling factor of a non-GBR bearer if NR PDCP is configured on the bearer. If set to '1', the EN-DC DL scheduling weight boost is deactivated.

Parameter name: EN-DC Scheduling Weight Boost for Uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the UL scheduling weight scaling factor of a non-GBR bearer if NR PDCP is configured on the bearer. If set to '1', the EN-DC UL scheduling weight boost is deactivated.

Parameter name: RRC establishment cause to ARP mapping configurations
Description: RRC Establishment Cause To Arp Mapping Configurations.

Parameter name: Assigned ARP priority level
Description: ARP priority level assigned by eNB to the RRC Connection which is valid until first DRB is established.  The range of the ARP priority level is 1 to 15 with 1 as the highest level of priority.

Parameter name: RRC establishment cause
Description: Establishment Cause of RRC Connection for which ARP parameter assignment is done (valid until first DRB is established).
Range and step: emergency (0), highPriorityAccess (1), mt-Access (2), mo-Signalling (3), mo-Data (4), delayTolerantAccess-v1020 (5)

Parameter name: Assigned ARP pre-emption capability
Description: ARP Pre-emption Capability assigned by eNB to the RRC Connection which is valid until first DRB is established.  This parameter defines whether a service data flow can get resources that were already assigned to another service data flow with a lower priority level.

Parameter name: ETWS primary notification broadcast duration
Description: Duration during which an ETWS primary Notification is broadcasted.  As the broadcast parameter delivered with Write-Replace Warning Request are not to be used for ETWS primary notification (SIB10), the broadcast duration has to be administered.

Parameter name: Forced DRX ReportCGI timer for S1HO to HeNB/CSG/Hybrid
Description: It defines the maximum time in ms at the eNB for receiving the RRC Measurement Report message with an LTE (intra- or inter-frequency) ReportCGI measurement results for home eNB/CSG/Hybrid neighbor cell from a UE configured to perform such measurement.

Parameter name: Forced plan file activation
Description: Enforces the activation of a plan file independent of the configured plan file activation mode  The setting applies for the respective plan file only, i.e. it is not stored by eNB. The parameter overrules the configured plan file activation mode (LNBTS parameter planFileActivationMode) for a dedicated plan file.

Parameter name: DTM capability of the GERAN target
Description: This parameter indicates if the target GERAN system supports DTM. This parameter is evaluated during CS fallback to GERAN system via redirection.  This parameter should be set based on the network deployment.

Parameter name: Hanging reconfiguration  timer
Description: Operator configurable timer which specifies the amount of time for a reconfiguration.  If the timer is over a possible abnormal behavior of the reconfiguration is detected and an alarm is raised.    If the parameter is configured to 'infinity', the alarm is disabled.

Parameter name: HARQ delay threshold in inter-site CA
Description: This parameter defines a delay threshold for HARQ feedback before the corresponding HARQ process can be preempted by new data transmission at the X2 connected SCell.    The higher the value of the delay threshold the higher risk of HARQ stalling.    The smaller the value of the delay threshold the higher risk of RLC stalling and RLC retransmission via the PCell (LTE3022 solution).    The value "Auto" means that such threshold is determined dynamically by eNodeB (in this case, the eNodeB will automatically determine the threshold as either 0 ms or 23 ms).

Parameter name: High-priority session configurations - HPS ARP preemption capability
Description: preemCap defines the ARP preemption capability which will be used to raise ARP of non-GBR, non-high-priority-session DRBs during Radio Admission Control (RAC) for initial context setup.  In case of handover procedure the parameter is not used. Preemption capability of highest ARP of high-priority-session DRBs from handover request will be used to raise ARP of all DRBs during RAC for handover.    Note: no ramp-up is performed for handover if LTE2559 ARP based partial admission control for handover is enabled.

Parameter name: High-priority session configurations - HPS ARP preemption vulnerability
Description: preemVul defines the ARP preemption vulnerability which will be used to raise ARP of non-GBR, non-high-priority-session DRBs during Radio Admission Control (RAC) for initial context setup.  In case of handover procedure the parameter is not used. Preemption vulnerability of highest ARP of high-priority-session DRBs from handover request will be used to raise ARP of all DRBs during RAC for handover.    Note: no ramp-up is performed for handover if LTE2559 'ARP based partial admission control for handover' is enabled.

Parameter name: High-priority session configurations - HPS ARP priority level
Description: hpsRampUpArpPrioLev defines the ARP priority which will be used to raise ARP of non-GBR, non-high-priority-session DRBs during Radio Admission Control (RAC) for initial context setup.  In case of handover procedure the parameter is not used. Highest ARP of high-priority-session DRBs from handover request will be used to raise ARP of all DRBs during RAC for handover.  This configured hpsRampUpArpPrioLev value should be within the configured range of hpsSessArpMin and hpsSessArpMax.  The parameter is ignored if actAcHpsLimits is disabled in a given cell.    Note: no ramp-up is performed for handover if LTE2559 'ARP based partial admission control for handover' is enabled.

Parameter name: High-priority session configurations - HPS ARP Ramp up functionality enabled
Description: This parameter is used to enable the ramp up functionality in eNB for High Priority Session (HPS); if it is disabled then the configured ramp up ARP values in this structure are not used.

Parameter name: High-priority session configurations - High-priority session ARP priority level maximum
Description: ARP parameters with a priority level greater or equal hpsSessArpMin AND lower or equal hpsSessArpMax will be regarded as high-priority. If an ARP parameter matches both these conditions and the emergency ARP condition, it will be regarded as an emergency ARP parameter.

Parameter name: High-priority session configurations - High-priority session ARP priority level minimum
Description: ARP parameters with a priority level greater or equal hpsSessArpMin AND lower or equal hpsSessArpMax will be regarded as high-priority. If an ARP parameter matches both these conditions and the emergency ARP condition, it will be regarded as an emergency ARP parameter.

Parameter name: Improved latency initial delay for proactive UL grants triggered for TCP boosting
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum number of TTIs that pass after a HARQ ACK has been received and a 3-4 TTI UL scheduler delay passes before sending the first proactive UL grant triggered by a non-GBR DL data transmission. This parameter also applies to "skippable" proactive UL grants.

Parameter name: Improved latency gap for proactive UL grants triggered for TCP boosting
Description: This parameter specifies the number of TTIs between proactive UL grants triggered by non-GBR DL data.

Parameter name: Improved Latency Gap for proactive grants triggered for TCP boosting
Description: This parameter specifies the Number of TTIs between skippable proactive UL grants triggered for TCP boosting.

Parameter name: Improved Latency Gap for grants triggered by DL SRB transmission/UL data transmission
Description: This parameter specifies the Number of TTIs between skippable dummy UL grants triggered by DL SRB transmission/UL data transmission.

Parameter name: Improved latency minimum DL data to trigger TCP Boost proactive UL grants sending
Description: This parameter defines the minimum payload size of non-GBR DL data, sent to the UE, that will trigger a TCP boost proactive UL grant. This parameter also applies to "skippable" proactive UL grants.

Parameter name: Uplink improved latency minimum data volume TBS size for TCP Boost proactive grants
Description: This parameter is the minimum data volume (TBS size) transferred for grants triggered by TCP Boost proactive.

Parameter name: Uplink improved latency reaction timer of TCP Boost proactive grants sending
Description: This parameter is the Improved latency reaction timer in uplink for TCP boosting. It defines the time how long eNB will send to the UE proactive UL grants. If actUlGrantEffTcpBoost is 'true', the timer starts/restarts at every TTI when the UL scheduler delay has passed and ilGrantDelayTcpBoost TTIs have passed after receiving a HARQ ACK of a DL nonGBR DRB data transmission meeting or exceeding the ilMinDataTrigGrantTcpBoost threshold for the UE.  Otherwise the timer is started from every DL packet scheduled over specified QCI for the UE.

Parameter name: Improved latency reaction timer of TCP Boost proactive grants  UL Tx skippable
Description: This parameter is the Improved latency reaction timer in uplink for TCP boosting. It defines the time how long eNB will send to the UE proactive UL grants. If actUlGrantEffTcpBoost is 'true', the timer starts/restarts at every TTI when the UL scheduler delay has passed and ilGrantDelayTcpBoost TTIs have passed after receiving a HARQ ACK of a DL nonGBR DRB data transmission meeting or exceeding the ilMinDataTrigGrantTcpBoost threshold for the UE.  Otherwise the timer is started from every DL packet scheduled over any non GBR QCI for the UE. ilReacTimerUlTcpBoostTxSkip applies to "skippable" proactive UL grants only.

Parameter name: Improved latency reaction timer of dummy grants  UL Tx skippable
Description: Improved latency reaction timer in uplink defines the time in which the UE has to send useful data after either the initial skippable dummy UL grant or a previous reception of useful data. If the timer expires the, UE will not get skippable dummy UL grant anymore.

Parameter name: S1AP release causes for IMMCI support during TAU
Description: Enables the functionality of "IMMCI (Idle Mode Mobility Control Info) IE support during RRC Connection Release with TAU procedure" for selected cause values sent by MME in S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND message.  The functionality is supported if cause value received in the S1AP message corresponds to any value selected by this parameter.    The setting 'all_S1_release_causes' enables the functionality for any received cause value.

Parameter name: IMS emergency PLMN configurations
Description: PLMN related configuration parameter for support of emergency sessions

Parameter name: Emergency session ARP pre-emption Capability
Description: ARP Pre-emption Capability used by PLMN ID for emergency Sessions.  This parameter defines whether service data flow can get resources that were already assigned to another service data flow with a lower priority level.

Parameter name: Emergency session ARP pre-emption Vulnerability
Description: ARP Pre-emption Vulnerability used by PLMN ID for emergency Sessions. The pre-emption vulnerability information defines whether a service data flow can lose the resources assigned to it in order to admit service data flow with higher priority level.

Parameter name: Emergency sessions ARP
Description: ARP priority level used by PLMN ID for emergency sessions.  The range of the ARP priority level is 1 to 15 with 1 as the highest level of priority. For emergency sessions, only ARP priority levels 1-8 may be applied (cf. also to 3GPP TS23.203)

Parameter name: Emergency sessions limited service mode support
Description: Indication if PLMN ID supporting emergency sessions also supports limited service mode

Parameter name: Emergency sessions MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of PLMN ID supporting emergency sessions

Parameter name: Emergency sessions MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of PLMN ID supporting emergency sessions

Parameter name: Initial MME Group Identifier
Description: Initial MME Group Identifier(MMEGI) for initial MME selection for the primary PLMN.

Parameter name: Synchronization template distinguished name for inter-eNB carrier aggregation
Description: The parameter interEnbCaSyncTemplateDN defines the distinguished name of the SYNC template to be used for inter-eNB carrier aggregation. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.    Example:  FDN example: MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SDN example: MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.

Parameter name: Key refresh margin
Description: Defines a threshold for PDCP COUNT supervision. If the remaining COUNT space becomes less than this threshold, the eNB key hierarchy should be refreshed.

Parameter name: Synchronization template  distinguished name for LTE-NR dual connectivity
Description: The parameter lteNrDcSyncTemplateDN defines the distinguished name of the SYNC template to be used for LTE-NR dual connectivity. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.    Example:  FDN example: MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SDN example: MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.

Parameter name: Synchronization template distinguished name for LTE-NR DSS
Description: The parameter lteNrDssSyncTemplateDN defines the distinguished name of the SYNC template to be used for LTE-NR Dynamic Spectrum Sharing (DSS). The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.    Example:  FDN example: MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SDN example: MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.    The selected synchronization template is used for any LTE-NR DSS mode.

Parameter name: Synchronization template distinguished name for LTE TDD
Description: The parameter lteTddSyncTemplateDN defines the distinguished name of the SYNC template to be used for LTE TDD cell technology. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.
