Example:  FDN example: MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SDN example: MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.

Parameter name: Main transport network identifier
Description: This parameter selects the transport network which shall be used as a main transport network.

Parameter name: Maximum Size for EUTRAN capabilities within handover to UTRAN
Description: This parameter limits the size of EUTRAN capability Container which can be included into the S1AP:HANDOVER REQUIRED message which is used to trigger a PS-HO, SRVCC or CSFB by PS-HO towards UTRAN.  If EUTRAN capabilities in size of OCTETS exceeds this number, EUTRAN capabilities are excluded from the SourceToTargetTransparentContainer.  If maxEUTRANcapabilitySize is set to 0, EUTRAN capabilities are excluded irrespectively of their size.

Parameter name: Max number of allowed ANR managed object instances
Description: Configures the maximal overall number of ANR managed object instances the eNB shall support.    Note: It is highly recommended in case of reduction of the parameter value, that a gap of 10% from the specified value to the actual number of existing instances exist.  Important:  If the number of neighbor-related objects in the target configuration for the eNB (actual eNB configuration and the planned modifications to it) is equal to the value of maxNumAnrMoiAllowed or close by, there is a very high probability that the overload alarm is raised immediately after the plan file has been activated.

Parameter name: Max total number of NR cells stored in eNB
Description: Max total number of NR cells stored in eNB.  This parameter is ignored by the system if actX2gNB128 is 'false'.

Parameter name: Max number of NR cells per gNB stored in eNB
Description: Max number of NR cells per gNB stored in eNB.  This parameter is ignored by the system if actX2gNB128 is 'false'.

Parameter name: Max number of LNADJ instances
Description: Configures the overall number of LNADJ instances supported by the eNB.  Note:  For FSMr2 HW the value shall not exceed 128.  For FSMr3 HW there is no hardware specific limitation.  For Flexi Zone Micro the value shall not exceed 256    The parameter shall never be configured to a value higher than the system informs in parameter supportedNumOfLnadj.

Parameter name: Maximum number of pre-emptions
Description: This parameter limits the number of pre-emptions which the admission of a set of E-RABs (for example at initial context setup, E-RAB setup, handover request) might cause. If this number gets exceeded for an E-RAB set, the admission of this set will partly or completely fail.  Because each pre-emption takes at least 5ms (but might take more, depending on eNB load), the pre-emption number limitation should be considered carefully to avoid timeouts of procedures which depend on E-RAB admission (in particular handover preparations).This number of pre-emptions limit shall be now shared by both Radio Admission Control (RAC) and Transport Admission Control (TAC) procedures and hence the pre-emption number limitation should be considered carefully to address both RAC and TAC limit.

Parameter name: Max parallel incoming X2 Setup or ENB Config Update handling in Overload-0
Description: Maximum number of parallel handled incoming X2 Setup Request or ENB Configuration Update or EN-DC Configuration Update messages when eNB is in overload level 0 (or no overload)

Parameter name: Max parallel incoming X2 Setup or ENB Config Update handling in Overload-1
Description: Maximum number of parallel handled incoming X2 Setup Request or ENB Configuration Update or EN-DC Configuration Update messages when eNB is in overload level 1

Parameter name: Max parallel outgoing X2 Setup or ENB Config Update
Description: Maximum number of parallel handling of outgoing X2 Setup or ENB Configuration Update messages.    The parameter applies for X2 links between eNB and neighbor eNB (X2(eNB)) and for X2 links between eNB and en-gNB (X2(gNB)).

Parameter name: Max retransmission threshold for SRB Downlink
Description: The maximum number of poll retransmission for the transmitting side (eNB) of an AM RLC entity for SRB. This parameter specifies the parameter maxRetxThreshold of [36.331].  This parameter is used by the transmitting side of each AM RLC entity to count the number of transmissions of an AM PDU. It is set so that a radio link failure can be detected by the eNB before the maximum number of transmissions has been reached. The parameter is on a higher level than ARQ and HARQ.

Parameter name: Max retransmission threshold for SRB Uplink
Description: The maximum number of poll retransmission for the transmitting side (UE) of an AM RLC entity for SRB. This parameter specifies the parameter maxRetxThreshold of [36.331].  This parameter is used by the transmitting side of each AM RLC entity to count the number of transmissions of an AM PDU. It is set so that a radio link failure can be detected by the eNB before the maximum number of transmissions has been reached. The parameter is on a higher level than ARQ and HARQ.

Parameter name: Max X2 eNB ConfigUpdate retries
Description: The maximum number of times the eNB shall retry the X2 eNB Configuration Update attempts.

Parameter name: Synchronization template distinguished name for MBMS
Description: The parameter mbmsSyncTemplateDN defines the distinguished name of the SYNC template to be used for MBMS and MBMS for public safety (MBMSPS). The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.    Example:  FDN example: MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SDN example: MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.

Parameter name: MCC In PLMN
Description: Primary Mobile Country Code of eNB  Primary Mobile Country Code of eNB.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Minimum idle time of SCell
Description: This parameter defines the minimum idle time of an SCell to be a released candidate when the host cell is in high load state (refer to sCellReleaseLoadMargin).

Parameter name: Load balancing special case handling selection
Description: This parameter selects the handling of the CIO adjustment during the handling of special cases.  When set to 'returnAdjustmentToZero' the action for the special case handling will return the delta CIO adjustment to a value of zero.    When set to 'adjustmentPreserved' the action in for the special case handling will leave the delta CIO adjustment at its current value.    The special cases applies when LB Abate Threshold is reached and Cell becomes "balanced".

Parameter name: MME assignment mode
Description: This parameter enables the eNB, in case only one MME is available at MME selection for the selected PLMN ID, to select this MME even its MME capacity is set to zero.

Parameter name: MNC In PLMN
Description: Primary Mobile Network Code of eNB  This is the primary Mobile Network Code of the eNB.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Mobility profile selection mode
Description: This parameter is used to configure selection method of Mobility Profile for mobility procedures.  If this parameter is set to value 'spid', then SPID received from MME or incoming handover is used for MOPR selection.  If this parameter is set to value 'plmn' then MOPR selection is based on UE's Serving PLMN ID.  If this parameter is set to 'combined' then MOPR selection is based on UE's Serving PLMN ID and SPID.

Parameter name: Mobility prohibit timer QCI5 inactivity
Description: This parameter is the timer value to prevent mobility to WCDMA before QCI1 bearer is setup, if during this time uplink or downlink activity is detected on QCI5 bearer with schedulType=SIGNALLING.

Parameter name: Mult. factor for SCell release timer
Description: Defines the multiplication factor to calculate the value of the internal, secondary cell (SCell) release timer (ScellReleaseTimer).  The timer value is achieved by multiplying this parameter with the value of the SCell deactivation timer (LNBTS-scellDeactivationTimerEnb) as follows:  ScellReleaseTimer = multScellReleaseTimer * min(scellDeactivationTimerEnb, rf128).    If an SCell is not active for a UE for the duration of the deactivation timer (LNBTS-scellDeactivationTimerEnb) or its estimated channel quality is bad (LNCEL-scellBadChQualThr), the calculated release timer is started and when it expires, the SCell is released.    Note1: Special value '0' means that the ScellReleaseTimer is not started and the SCell is kept configured even if not active or perceived with bad channel quality or as not detected.    Note2: If the ScellReleaseTimer is used, it is recommended to set multScellReleaseTimer to value '5'.

Parameter name: ARP based QoS parameters for multiple ARP values
Description: ARP based QoS parameters for multiple ARP values

Parameter name: ARP priority level
Description: ARP priority level.  The range of the ARP priority level is 1 to 15 with 1 as the highest level of priority. The schedulingWeightSF and/or nbrUlDlSF defined in same structure will be applied for scaling factor to the ARP value set in the arpPrioLev.

Parameter name: scaling factor for nominal bitrates for UL and DL
Description: The scaling factor for nominal bitrates for uplink and downlink if actNbrForNonGbrBearers is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: scaling factor for scheduling weight
Description: The scaling factor for scheduling weight for uplink and downlink if actNonGbrServiceDiff is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Number of consecutive HO preparation timeouts
Description: The parameter is used to determine how many handover preparation attempts towards a neighbor cell must consecutively fail by supervision timer expiry until the neighbor cell is considered as sleeping cell

Parameter name: Radio problem indication based on CQI DTX
Description: Number of consecutive CQI DTX detections required for RL failure.  The parameter defines the number of consecutive CQI DTX detections causing radio link  failure indication. Special value 0 means that the feature is disabled.

Parameter name: Radio problem recovery based on CQI DTX
Description: Number of consecutive CQIs required for RL recovery.  The parameter defines number of consecutive CQI non-DTX detections causing radio link  failure recovery indication.

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of managed object.

Parameter name: Configuration mode of IE neighCellConfig in SIB3 & SIB3-BR
Description: This parameter defines configuration mode of IE 'neighCellConfig' in SIB3 and SIB3-BR:    If this parameter is 'true', then eNB will configure IE neighCellConfig in SIB3 & SIB3-BR according to SIB-mbmsNeighCellConfigIntraF value or default value 00 if optional parameter SIB-mbmsNeighCellConfigIntraF is not configured (no matter MBMS or DSS features are activated or not).    It is recommended to set neighCellConfigM to 'true' if UE power consumption shall be minimized.  For non MBMS/DSS scenario it is additionally recommended to set parameter SIB-mbmsNeighCellConfigIntraF to '01' or '10'.      If this parameter is 'false', then legacy behaviour will apply.

Parameter name: Neighbor cell check periodicity
Description: Periodicity, with which eNB repeats the check if for available X2 links there are neighbor cells with incomplete configuration information.    If 'neighbCellChkPeriodicity' is set to '0' the check for incomplete configuration information is deactivated.

Parameter name: Neighbor cell check start time
Description: The parameter configures the local time at which eNB checks if for available X2 links are neighbor cells with incomplete configuration information existing.  As long as enabled, the check for missing configuration information is repeated with a periodicity given by 'neighbCellChkPeriodicity'.    It is recommended to choose a low traffic hour as value for 'neighbCellChkStartTime'.    * If the configured day time is reached, eNb starts an internal timer of length 'neighbCellChkPeriodicity' (if not yet running).  * On expiry, the internal timer is restarted.  * The check for neighbor cells with incomplete configuration information is performed when this internal timer is started for the first time and subsequently when it expires.  * If a neighbor cell with incomplete configuration information is found, the missing information is retrieved via repetition of X2 Setup procedure.    * Neighbor cells with incomplete configuration information may occur very rarely (i.e. only if eNB is operating for some time at the maximum limit of number of supported managed objects).

Parameter name: nr cell deactivation status indication in ENDC HO
Description: The parameter determines if NR cells in energy saving mode shall be considered by ENDC-HO steering functions to decide whether serving LTE cell can provide EN-DC service for the UE.

Parameter name: Override NR restriction flag in handover restriction list
Description: When this parameter is set to 'FR1', 'FR2' or 'FR2 and FR2', then the UE is allowed to setup sgNB on FR1, FR2 or on both, FR1 and FR2 bands, respectively, even if its Handover Restriction List includes 'NR Restrict in EPS as Secondary RAT' IE and is set to 'NRrestrictedinEPSasSecondaryRAT'.  FR1 is defined as the NR frequencies in the range of 450 MHz to 6000 MHz. FR2 is defined as the NR frequencies in the range of 24250 MHz to 52600 MHz.  When actLteNrDualConnectivity is set to 'false', BTS ignores the setting of this parameter.
Range and step: disabled (0), FR1 (1), FR2 (2), FR1 and FR2 (3)

Parameter name: Null ciphering algorithm fallback
Description: This parameter determines whether a fallback to null ciphering caused by eNB limitations should be accepted (True) or not (False).

Parameter name: Number of B1 retries before NR coverage-based EN-DC steering
Description: This parameter defines the number of periodical EN-DC B1 NR measurements completions without EN-DC connection establishment, before an EN-DC capable UE, with EN-DC eligible bearer established in an EN-DC anchor cell, can become a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover to the anchor layer.    Note that UE in an EN-DC non-anchor cell is always a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover.

Parameter name: Number of bad UL packets to trigger handover for HFN reset
Description: This parameter defines the number of consecutive uncorrectable bad UL packets. It is one of the conditions to trigger handover to reset HFN of a RLC UM bearer using RoHC.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Operational state
Description: Operational state of the eNB, the value is set by system.
Range and step: initializing (0), commissioned (1), notCommisioned (2), configured (3), integrated to RAN (4), onAir (5), test (6)

Parameter name: OTDOA profile list
Description: This structure allows the definition of up to two OTDOA profiles

Parameter name: OTDOA Phase Error Threshold
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum allowable phase error with respect to absolute time at the air interface for the corresponding otdoaProfileList-otdoaSyncSourceType.  Cells with actOtdoa enabled stop transmitting Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) when the estimated phase error exceeds otdoaProfileList-otdoaPhaseErrorThreshold and the current sync source or the last sync source before holdover corresponds to otdoaProfileList-otdoaSyncSourceType.    Note: if actTimeErrorManagement is set to' true' and otdoaSyncTemplateDN is configured, then otdoaPhaseErrorThreshold will be ignored

Parameter name: OTDOA synchronization source type
Description: This parameter specifies a sync source type allowed for OTDOA service.  Cells with actOtdoa enabled stop transmitting Positioning Reference Signal (PRS) when the eNodeB switches to a synchronization source other than the ones allowed by otdoaProfileList-otdoaSyncSourceType.

Parameter name: Synchronization template distinguished name for OTDOA
Description: The parameter otdoaSyncTemplateDN defines the distinguished name of the SYNC template to be used for OTDOA. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.    Example:  FDN example: MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SDN example: MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.    Note: if actTimeErrorManagement is set to' true' and otdoaSyncTemplateDN is configured, then otdoaProfileList-otdoaPhaseErrorThreshold will be ignored

Parameter name: High-priority session configurations - Max. paging prio level for high priority sessions
Description: Paging requests with a prioLevel lower or equal to pagingPrioLevelHpsMax AND higher or equal to pagingPrioLevelHpsMin will be regarded as High Priority Session (HPS).  This parameter is used to configure the maximum priority level which shall be considered as high priority session request in the paging message. The 3GPP standard defines PrioLevel1, PrioLevel2, PrioLevel3...to indicate HPS service requests. It is expected that the HPS paging requests will use consecutive PrioLevels.  Paging requests with PrioLevels outside of the HPS range, including the case of HPS range not defined, are regarded as emergency sessions.

Parameter name: High-priority session configurations - Min. paging prio level for high priority sessions
Description: Paging requests with a prioLevel lower or equal to pagingPrioLevelHpsMax AND higher or equal to pagingPrioLevelHpsMin will be regarded as High Priority Session (HPS).  This parameter is used to configure the minimum priority level which shall be considered as high priority session request in the paging message. The 3GPP standard defines PrioLevel1, PrioLevel2, PrioLevel3...to indicate HPS service requests. It is expected that the HPS paging requests will use consecutive PrioLevels.  Paging requests with PrioLevels outside of the HPS range, including the case of HPS range not defined, are regarded as emergency sessions.

Parameter name: Prioritized bit rate nonGBR
Description: Prioritized Bit Rate for non-GBR bearers  This prioritized bit rate is used by UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].

Parameter name: PCell swap block timer
Description: This timer is started when a PCell swap target evaluation or handover preparation for a selected carrier aggregated UE failed for any reason. Before the expiry of this timer, any retry of PCell swap for this UE shall be prohibited.

Parameter name: Profile 1001 of PDCP parameters - PDCP profile id
Description: Identity of the PDCP profile

Parameter name: Profile 1001 of PDCP parameters - PI2 target delay
Description: This parameter indicates the queue delay target of the PI2 Queue Management in milliseconds. The PI2 QM can be disabled by setting the pi2Variant parameter to 'PI2 queue management disabled'.

Parameter name: Profile 1001 of PDCP parameters - PI2 target size

Parameter name: Plan file activation mode
Description: Controls whether plan file activation is allowed to implicitly trigger eNB restart or to temporarily drop all cells('totalServiceLossAllowed') or is allowed to temporarily drop some cells('partialServiceLossAllowed') or is not allowed to temporarily drop cells ('noServiceLossAllowed')  The meaning of the activation modes is as follows:    totalServiceLossAllowed: Plan file activation is allowed to implicitly trigger eNB restart or to drop all cells if needed.    partialServiceLossAllowed: Plan file activation is not allowed to implicitly trigger eNB restart or to drop all cells but is allowed to temporarily drop some cells.    noServiceLossAllowed: Plan file activation is neither allowed to trigger eNB restart nor to temporarily drop cells.    Dependent on the setting of the LNBTS parameter enableGrflShdn eNB will either perform direct locking of cell(s) or graceful shutdown according to the feature 'Graceful cell shut down'.    Notes:  The plan file activation mode can be overruled for a particular plan file with the LNBTS parameter forcedPlanFileActivation.    The plan file activation mode is ignored in case of autoconfiguration respectively commissioning of an uncommissioned eNB and in case of full commissioning via WebEM. Such plan files will be activated in any case.    The feature 'Automatic lock' shall be activated, i.e. the parameter LNBTS-enableAutoLock shall be set to 'enabled'(which is the default value). Otherwise the plan file would be rejected by eNB if cell dropping is needed.

Parameter name: Handover topology priority
Description: This parameter is used to define priorities between the 3 topology options for intra LTE handover, which are  1) Intra eNB HO  2) HO via X2  3) HO via S1  It's assumed that Intra eNB HO can not have lower priority than any other topology and S1 HO can not have higher priority than any other topology.    Four relations are possible:  1) all topologies have the same priority -> "all equal"  2) intra eNB HO is prioritized over inter eNB HO where X2-based HO and S1-based HO are not discriminated -> "intra eNB HO prior inter eNB HO"  3) intra eNB HO is prioritized over inter eNB HO where X2-based HO is prioritized over S1-based HO -> "intra prior X2 prior S1"  4) intra eNB HO and X2-based handover are not discriminated but S1-based HO takes lower priority than the others -> "low prio S1"
Range and step: all equal (0), intra eNB HO prior inter eNB HO (1), intra prior X2 prior S1 (2), low prio S1 (3)

Parameter name: Prioritize VoLTE over MBMS
Description: Determines if VoLTE target frequencies shall be prioritized in case of MBMS interested UEs with established QCI#1 bearer as far as VoLTE and MBMS target frequencies are conflicting.

Parameter name: Prohibit Load based handover timer
Description: This timer is used for temporary blacklisting of a Target Cell for load-based and service-based handover.  One Target Cell is blacklisted when a handover is rejected due to lack of resources.  The timer is started when the cell is blacklisted.  When timer expires the blacklisting is removed.  Blacklist affects all UEs in the actual source cell.  Blacklist affects Handovers for Load Balancing. (cause "Reduce Load in Serving Cell" ) and Service Based Handovers (cause "Resource Optimization Handover")  Blacklisted cells are managed internally by eNB and not added to black lists visible to operator.

Parameter name: Preemption priority of pure NB-IoT RRC connections
Description: This parameter indicates ARP priority of preempting NB-IoT RRC connection contexts without established DRBs.  The value '15' (no priority) indicates that pure NB-IoT RRC connections will not be selected for preemptions, i.e., LTE4739 for NB-IoT part is disabled.  The value '16' (LowestPrioAboveSCell) indicates that pure NB-IoT RRC connections will be selected for preemption before any wideband UE and only if no SCell context is available.  The value '17' (LowestPrioBelowSCell) indicates that pure NB-IoT RRC connections will be selected for preemption before any wideband UE and before any SCell context.

Parameter name: Power Fallback in CA mode
Description: Define power class fallback for high power UE in case of CA mode.    For HPUE, when it is NOT in CA mode, mobility thresholds for high power class is applied.    If pwrFallbackCA = "true", mobility thresholds for normal power class will be applied when HPUE gets into CA mode.  If pwrFallbackCA = "false", mobility thresholds for high power class will be applied when HPUE gets into CA mode

Parameter name: PWS with emergency area ID
Description: Indicates if the Public Warning Systems (ETWS and/or CMAS) uses Emergency Area IDs.  If ETWS or CMAS service is activated, then provision of this parameter is mandatory.    If 'pwsWithEmAreaId' is true, then for each eNB cell provision of at least one 'Emergency Area ID' in the 'emAreaIdList' must be specified.    If a warning message including 'Emergency Area IDs' is received by eNB and 'pwsWithEmAreaId' is 'false' then this warning message shall not be broadcasted by eNB.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Delay target
Description: DelayTarget is the maximum packet delay value used by the eNB MAC scheduling algorithm.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - DRX profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile  If several EPS bearers are established for UE, eNB compares the DRX profiles of the QCIs used for those EPS bearers and selects the DRX profile with highest priority

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - DSCP
Description: This parameter configures the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value associated with the QCI.  The DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target eNB.    List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal):  BE (=0),  AF11 (=10),  AF12 (=12),  AF13 (=14),  AF21 (=18),  AF22 (=20),  AF23 (=22),  AF31 (=26),  AF32 (=28),  AF33 (=30),  AF41 (=34),  AF42 (=36),  AF43 (=38),  EF (=46)

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - DSCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DSCP profile (DSCPPR). Together with the ARP-DSCP marking table in the referenced instance of the DSCP profile a marking between QCI + ARP and DSCP is provided.    If not configured, then the DSCP value from this instance of QCI table (qciTabX-dscp) is used for all ARP values.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Enforce TTI bundling
Description: This parameter enables TTI bundling if the QCI is present in the current bearer combination.  If this parameter is set to "true" for any bearer of the current bearer combination, the measurements for TTI bundling are activated and TTI bundling might be activated. Otherwise TTI bundling is not applied.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Logical channel group identifier
Description: Logical Channel Group Identifier for buffer status reporting  This parameter is used for configuration of the buffer status reports of UE according [36.321]

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Maximum GBR downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the downlink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI1 for which the GBR in downlink direction is greater than this value.    Note: it is not recommended to set this parameter larger than 1024kb/s as handling of QCI1 bearers is optimized for VoLTE calls and corresponding data rates.  Please consult customer documentation for additional information.    FDD only:  In cells with downlink channel bandwidth equal to 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz eNB will limit the downlink GBR to maximum 408 kbit/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Maximum GBR uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the uplink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI1 for which the GBR in uplink direction is greater than this value.    Note: it is not recommended to set this parameter larger than 1024kb/s as handling of QCI1 bearers is optimized for VoLTE calls and corresponding data rates.  Please consult customer documentation for additional information.    FDD only:  In cells with uplink channel bandwidth equal to 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz eNB will limit the uplink GBR to maximum 408 kbit/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - PDCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding PDCP profile.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Priority
Description: This parameter gives the priority of the EPS bearer according TS23.203.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - QCI
Description: QoS Class Identifier

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - QCI support
Description: This parameter indicates whether the given QCI is supported and enabled

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Resource type
Description: The Resource Type indicates whether a bearer is a GBR or NON-GBR bearer.  The Resource Type determines if dedicated network resources related to a service or bearer level Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) value are permanently allocated.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - RLC mode
Description: This parameter configures the RLC Mode of the data radio bearer

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - RLC profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Scheduling bucket size duration
Description: This parameter is used to configure the Bucket Size Duration (BSD) of the UL scheduler.  For GBR bearers, schedulBSD in used by eNB and UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  The bucket size of a logical channel is calculated by PBR * BSD.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 1 - Scheduling priority
Description: Logical Channel Priority for the MAC scheduler  For GBR bearers, schedulPrio in used by UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  Increasing priority values indicates a lower priority.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Delay target
Description: DelayTarget is the maximum packet delay value used by the eNB MAC scheduling algorithm.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - DRX profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile.  If several EPS bearers are established for a UE, eNB compares the DRX profiles of the QCIs used for those EPS bearers and selects the DRX profile with highest priority.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - DSCP
Description: This parameter configures the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value associated with the QCI.  The DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target eNB.    List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal):  BE (=0),  AF11 (=10),  AF12 (=12),  AF13 (=14),  AF21 (=18),  AF22 (=20),  AF23 (=22),  AF31 (=26),  AF32 (=28),  AF33 (=30),  AF41 (=34),  AF42 (=36),  AF43 (=38),  EF (=46)

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - DSCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DSCP profile (DSCPPR). Together with the ARP-DSCP marking table in the referenced instance of the DSCP profile a marking between QCI + ARP and DSCP is provided.    If not configured, then the DSCP value from this instance of QCI table (qciTabX-dscp) is used for all ARP values.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Enforce TTI bundling
Description: This parameter enables TTI bundling if the QCI is present in the current bearer combination.  If this parameter is set to "true" for any bearer of the current bearer combination, the measurements for TTI bundling are activated and TTI bundling might be activated. Otherwise TTI bundling is not applied.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Overbooking factor on radio resources (PRBs on air interface) for QCI2 GBR
Description: This parameter defines an overbooking factor on radio resources (PRBs on air interface) for QCI2 GBR traffic in radio admission control. This factor is used to allow a more optimistic GBR admission. The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise. The GBR congestion handling will not use the overbooking factor.  In case the gbrOverbookingFactor is configured to 100 (= 100%) then radio admission control will skip the usual check on requested bit rate and available air interface resources.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - L2 overhead factor GBR DL
Description: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the downlink GBR in layer 2.  eNB increases the GBR in downlink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in downlink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR DL/100.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - L2 overhead factor GBR UL
Description: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the uplink GBR in layer 2.  eNB increases the GBR in uplink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in uplink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR UL/100.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Logical channel group identifier
Description: Logical Channel Group Identifier for buffer status reporting  This parameter is used for configuration of the buffer status reports of UE according [36.321].  It is recommended that GBR and non-GBR bearers are not mapped into the same logical channel group, since in this case the data of the logical channel group are scheduled as non-GBR data and the delay budget for the GBR bearer cannot be controlled.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Maximum GBR downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the downlink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI2 for which the GBR in downlink direction is greater than this value.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 2048 kb/s.    FDD only:  In cells with downlink channel bandwidth equal to 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz eNB will limit the downlink GBR to maximum 408 kbit/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Maximum GBR uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the uplink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI2 for which the GBR in uplink direction is greater than this value.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 2048 kb/s.    FDD only:  In cells with uplink channel bandwidth equal to 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz eNB will limit the uplink GBR to maximum 408 kbit/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - PDCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding PDCP profile.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Priority
Description: This parameter gives the priority of the EPS bearer according TS23.203.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - QCI
Description: QoS Class Identifier

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - QCI support
Description: This parameter indicates whether the given QCI is supported and enabled.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Resource type
Description: The Resource Type indicates whether a bearer is a GBR or NON-GBR bearer.  The Resource Type determines if dedicated network resources related to a service or bearer level Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) value are permanently allocated.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - RLC mode
Description: This parameter configures the RLC Mode of the data radio bearer.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - RLC profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Scheduling bucket size duration
Description: This parameter is used to configure the Bucket Size Duration (BSD) of the UL scheduler.  For GBR bearers, "schedulBSD" is used by eNB and UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  The bucket size of a logical channel is calculated by PBR * BSD.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Scheduling priority
Description: Logical Channel Priority for the MAC scheduler.  For GBR bearers, "schedulPrio" is used by UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  Increasing priority values indicate lower priority.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 2 - Service-based HO allowed
Description: This parameter indicates whether service-based handover is allowed for the given QCI value.    Note: Additionally to the LNCEL-level activation (LNCEL-actServBasedHoQciX equal to 'true'), this QCIx must be enabled for the service-based HO on LNBTS level (LNBTS-qciTabX-servBasedHoAllowed = 'allowed').

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 3 - Delay target
Description: DelayTarget is the maximum packet delay value used by the eNB MAC scheduling algorithm.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 3 - DRX profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile.  If several EPS bearers are established for a UE, eNB compares the DRX profiles of the QCIs used for those EPS bearers and selects the DRX profile with the highest priority.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 3 - DSCP
Description: This parameter configures the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value associated with the QCI.  The DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target eNB.    List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal):  BE (=0),  AF11 (=10),  AF12 (=12),  AF13 (=14),  AF21 (=18),  AF22 (=20),  AF23 (=22),  AF31 (=26),  AF32 (=28),  AF33 (=30),  AF41 (=34),  AF42 (=36),  AF43 (=38),  EF (=46)

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 3 - DSCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DSCP profile (DSCPPR). Together with the ARP-DSCP marking table in the referenced instance of the DSCP profile a marking between QCI + ARP and DSCP is provided.    If not configured, then the DSCP value from this instance of QCI table (qciTabX-dscp) is used for all ARP values.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 3 - Enforce TTI bundling
Description: This parameter enables TTI bundling if the QCI is present in the current bearer combination.  If this parameter is set to "true" for any bearer of the current bearer combination, the measurements for TTI bundling are activated and TTI bundling might be activated. Otherwise TTI bundling is not applied.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 3 - Overbooking factor on radio resources (PRBs on air interface) for QCI3 GBR
Description: This parameter defines an overbooking factor on radio resources (PRBs on air interface) for QCI3 GBR traffic in radio admission control. This factor is used to allow a more optimistic GBR admission. The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise. The GBR congestion handling will not use the overbooking factor.  In case the gbrOverbookingFactor is configured to 100 (= 100%) then radio admission control will skip the usual check on requested bit rate and available resources.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 3 - L2 overhead factor GBR DL
Description: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the downlink GBR in layer 2.  eNB increases the GBR in downlink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in downlink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR DL/100.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 3 - L2 overhead factor GBR UL
Description: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the uplink GBR in layer 2.  eNB increases the GBR in uplink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in uplink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR UL/100.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - ARP range for EN-DC eligible bearer
Description: This parameter defines the range(s) of ARP values for which this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  Each bit of this parameter stands for one ARP value from 1 to 15. Bit #0 is not used.  If a bit is set to value '1', for the corresponding ARP value this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  If a bit is set to value '0', for the corresponding ARP value this QCI cannot be used for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Boosting factor for downlink
Description: This parameter defines the scaling factor for the DL scheduling weight. It is used to increase the DL scheduling weight for bearers which have TCP traffic boosting triggered according to tcpServiceDiffConfig settings.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Boosting factor for uplink
Description: This parameter defines the scaling factor for the UL scheduling weight. It is used to increase the UL scheduling weight for bearers which have TCP traffic boosting triggered according to tcpServiceDiffConfig settings.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Logical channel group identifier
Description: Logical Channel Group Identifier for buffer status reporting  This parameter is used for configuration of the buffer status reports of UE according [36.321]

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - LTE-NR Dual connectivity support
Description: This parameter defines whether or not this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  If the parameter is configured to "EN-DC" this QCI definition is eligible for eUTRA-New Radio Dual Connectivity.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Nominal bit rate downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the nominal bit rate in the downlink direction. It applies only if Scheduling Type has been set to NON-GBR.  Leaving this parameter value empty means the nominal bitrate feature does not apply to this QCI in this direction.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 5120 kb/s. In LTE FDD Technology, nbrDl values higher than 5120 kb/s are not supported and therefore internally set to 5120 kb/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Nominal bit rate uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the nominal bit rate in the uplink direction. It applies only if Scheduling Type has been set to NON-GBR.  eNB selects the value of prioritizedBitRate for UE configuration that is equal to or higher than nbrUl.  Leaving this parameter value empty means the nominal bitrate feature does not apply to this QCI in this direction.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 2048 kb/s. In LTE FDD Technology, nbrUl values higher than 2048 kb/s are not supported and therefore internally set to 2048 kb/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Scheduling bucket size duration
Description: This parameter is used to configure the Bucket Size Duration (BSD) of the UL scheduler.  The BSD is sent to UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according to [36.321].  The UE calculates the bucket size of a logical channel by PBR * BSD.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Scheduling priority
Description: Logical Channel Priority for the UE scheduler  This priority is sent to UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according for DRB [36.321].  Increasing priority values indicate lower priority.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Scheduling type
Description: This parameter specifies how the EPS bearer with QCI 5 is scheduled.  For the scheduling type 'SIGNALLING' the bearer is handled like SRBs. The MAC LCGID shall be set to 0 and schedulPrio is used for UL and DL scheduling.  For the scheduling type 'NON-GBR' the bearer is handled like other non-GBR bearers. The MAC LCGID shall not be to 0 and the schedulWeight is used for DL scheduling.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for eNB schedulers  The scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling (UL and DL), and MAC logical channel priority handling and multiplexing in DL

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - DL Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for an eNB DL scheduler.  The DL scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling and MAC logical channel priority handling and multiplexing

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 5 - UL Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for an eNB UL scheduler.  The UL scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling

Description: Logical Channel Group Identifier for buffer status reporting  This parameter is used for configuration of the buffer status reports of UE according [36.321]

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - Maximum GBR downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the downlink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI66 for which the GBR in downlink direction is greater than this value.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - Maximum GBR uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the uplink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI66 for which the GBR in uplink direction is greater than this value.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - PDCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding PDCP profile

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - Priority
Description: This parameter gives the priority of the EPS bearer according TS23.203.  This parameter is used for GBR congestion handling and is ignored for nonGBR bearers.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - QCI
Description: QoS Class Identifier  QCI for Non-Mission critical push to talk voice

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - QCI support
Description: This parameter indicates whether the given QCI is supported and enabled.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - Resource type
Description: The Resource Type indicates whether a bearer is a GBR or NON-GBR bearer  The Resource Type determines if dedicated network resources related to a service or bearer level Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) value are permanently allocated.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - RLC mode
Description: This parameter configures the RLC Mode of the data radio bearer

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - RLC profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - Scheduling bucket size duration
Description: This parameter is used to configure the Bucket Size Duration (BSD) of the UL scheduler.  For GBR bearers, schedulBSD in used by eNB and UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  The bucket size of a logical channel is calculated by PBR * BSD.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - Scheduling priority
Description: Logical Channel Priority for the MAC scheduler  For GBR bearers, schedulPrio in used by eNB for the DL scheduling algorithm and by UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  Increasing priority values indicate lower priority.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - Service-based HO allowed
Description: This parameter indicates whether service-based handover is allowed for the given QCI value.    Note: Additionally to the LNCEL-level activation (LNCEL-actServBasedHoQciX equal to 'true'), this QCIx must be enabled for the service-based HO on LNBTS level (LNBTS-qciTabX-servBasedHoAllowed = 'allowed').

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 66 - Skip power-limitation-based User-Plane preemption
Description: If skipPwrLimBasedUpPreemp is set to 'true', bearers of this type are excluded from uplink-power-limitation-based User-Plane preemption.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Block TTI bundling
Description: This parameter indicates, if TTI bundling (TTIB) configuration is blocked for the UE when QCI 67 is setup for the same UE. When set to 'true' and TTIB is configured for the UE, then Radio Admission Control does not allow QCI 67 to be setup. When set to 'true' and TTIB is not configured for the UE while QCI 67 is established, then eNB disables measurements needed for TTIB activation, and re-enables them only after last QCI 67 release. When set to 'false', the UE with QCI 67 established can operate in TTI bundling mode only when enforceTtiBundling is set to 'true' for some other DRB established in the UE context (and radio conditions are satisfied).    Note: qciTab67-enforceTtiBundling cannot be set to 'true'.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Delay target
Description: Delay target is the maximum packet delay value used by the eNB MAC scheduling algorithm.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - DRX profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile.  If several EPS bearers are established for a UE, eNB compares the DRX profiles of the QCIs used for those EPS bearers and selects the DRX profile with highest priority.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - DSCP
Description: This parameter configures the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value associated with the QCI.  The DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target eNB.    List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal):  BE (=0),  AF11 (=10),  AF12 (=12),  AF13 (=14),  AF21 (=18),  AF22 (=20),  AF23 (=22),  AF31 (=26),  AF32 (=28),  AF33 (=30),  AF41 (=34),  AF42 (=36),  AF43 (=38),  EF (=46)

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - DSCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DSCP profile (DSCPPR). Together with the ARP-DSCP marking table in the referenced instance of the DSCP profile a marking between QCI + ARP and DSCP is provided.    If not configured, then the DSCP value from this instance of QCI table (qciTabX-dscp) is used for all ARP values.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Enforce TTI bundling
Description: This parameter enables TTI bundling if the QCI is present in the current bearer combination.  If this parameter is set to 'true' for any bearer of the current bearer combination, the measurements for TTI bundling are activated and TTI bundling might be activated. Otherwise TTI bundling is not applied.    Note: enforceTtiBundling cannot be set to 'true'.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Overbooking factor on downlink radio resources (PRBs on air interface)
Description: This parameter defines an overbooking factor on downlink radio resources (PRBs on air interface) for QCI 67 GBR traffic in radio admission control. This factor is used to allow a more optimistic GBR admission. The parameter is relevant, only if actMcVideoOverbooking is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise. The GBR congestion handling will not use the overbooking factor.  In case gbrOverbookingFactorDl is configured to 100 (= 100%) radio admission control will skip the usual check on requested bit rate and available air interface resources.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Overbooking factor on uplink radio resources (PRBs on air interface)
Description: This parameter defines an overbooking factor on uplink radio resources (PRBs on air interface) for QCI 67 GBR traffic in radio admission control. This factor is used to allow a more optimistic GBR admission. The parameter is only relevant if actMcVideoOverbooking is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise. The GBR congestion handling will not use the overbooking factor.  In case gbrOverbookingFactorUl is configured to 100 (= 100%) radio admission control will skip the usual check on requested bit rate and available air interface resources.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - L2 overhead factor GBR DL
Description: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the downlink GBR in layer 2.  eNB increases the GBR in downlink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in downlink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR DL/100.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - L2 overhead factor GBR UL
Description: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the uplink GBR in layer 2.  eNB increases the GBR in uplink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in uplink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR UL/100.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Logical channel group identifier
Description: Logical Channel Group Identifier for buffer status reporting  This parameter is used for configuration of the buffer status reports of UE according [36.321].  It is recommended that GBR and non-GBR bearers are not mapped into the same logical channel group, since in this case the data of the logical channel group are scheduled as non-GBR data and the delay budget for the GBR bearer cannot be controlled.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Maximum GBR downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the downlink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI 67 for which the GBR in downlink direction is greater than this value.    It is not recommended to configure maxGbrDl to values higher than 5120 kbit/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Maximum GBR uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the uplink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with QCI 67 for which the GBR in uplink direction is greater than this value.    It is not recommended to configure maxGbrUl to values higher than 5120 kbit/s.

Description: This parameter indicates whether the given QCI is supported and enabled.

Description: The Resource Type indicates whether a bearer is a GBR or NON-GBR bearer.  The Resource Type determines if dedicated network resources related to a service or bearer level Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) value are permanently allocated.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - RLC mode
Description: This parameter configures the RLC Mode of the data radio bearer.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - RLC profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Scheduling bucket size duration
Description: This parameter is used to configure the Bucket Size Duration (BSD) of the UL scheduler.  For GBR bearers, "schedulBSD" is used by eNB and UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  The bucket size of a logical channel is calculated by PBR * BSD.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 67 - Scheduling priority
Description: Logical Channel Priority for the MAC scheduler.  For GBR bearers, "schedulPrio" is used by UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  Increasing priority values indicate lower priority.

Description: This parameter indicates whether service-based handover is allowed for the given QCI value.    Note: Additionally, service-based HO for QCI X must be activated separately at LNCEL level by setting LNCEL-actServBasedHoQciX to 'true'.

Description: If skipPwrLimBasedUpPreemp is set to 'true', bearers of this type are excluded from uplink-power-limitation-based user-plane preemption.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 69 - ARP range for EN-DC eligible bearer
Description: This parameter defines the range(s) of ARP values for which this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  Each bit of this parameter stands for one ARP value from 1 to 15. Bit #0 is not used.  If a bit is set to value '1', for the corresponding ARP value this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  If a bit is set to value '0', for the corresponding ARP value this QCI cannot be used for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).

Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile  If several EPS bearers are established for UE, eNB compares the DRX profiles of the QCIs used for those EPS bearers and selects the DRX profile with highest priority

If this parameter is set to true for any bearer of the current bearer combination, the measurements for TTI bundling are activated and TTI bundling may be activated. Otherwise TTI bundling is not applied.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 69 - Include in TAC measurement
Description: This parameter indicates whether the QCI 69 traffic shall be considered in MB-TAC (Measurement Based Transport Admission Control) measurement or not.  If the operator sets qciTab69-includeInTacMeas to False, then it is recommended to configure qciTab5-dscp and qciTab69-dscp differently, so that transport software can distinguish between QCI 5 and QCI 69 traffic (which is solely based on DSCP).    Note1: MB-TAC measures all the GBR and optionally few selected non-GBR QCI traffic using the corresponding DSCP value configured for transport admission control decision. This parameter optionally enables the QCI 69 (Mission Critical delay sensitive signaling) traffic be measured for Transport Admission control as similar to QCI 5 traffic.  Note2: If "Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) marking based on Quality of service Class Identifier (QCI) ) and Allocation and Retention Priority (ARP)" is activated (LNBTS-actQciArpToDscpMarking = 'true') and qciTab69-includeInTacMeas is 'true', then the dscp values configured for the different ARP ranges of QCI 69 must be unique from the dscp values configured for the different ARP ranges of the other non-GBR QCIs 6,7,8,9,70 and operator specified non-GBR.

Description: This parameter specifies the nominal bit rate in the downlink direction.  Leaving this parameter value empty means the nominal bitrate feature does not apply to this QCI in this direction.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 5120 kb/s. In LTE FDD Technology, nbrDl values higher than 5120 kb/s are not supported and therefore internally set to 5120 kb/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 6 - Nominal bit rate uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the nominal bit rate in the uplink direction.  eNB selects the value of prioritizedBitRate for UE configuration that is equal to or higher than nbrUl.  Leaving this parameter value empty means the nominal bitrate feature does not apply to this QCI in this direction.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 2048 kb/s. In LTE FDD Technology, nbrUl values higher than 2048 kb/s are not supported and therefore internally set to 2048 kb/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - RLC profile index for 3 CC CA
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile optimized for use with 3 CC Carrier Aggregation.  Recommendations:    If a different, optimized RLC profile for 3 CC CA shall be used, it is recommended to use the profile with the ID 6 (default). Note the different default values compared to RLC profiles 1-5.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - RLC profile index for 4 CC and 5 CC CA
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile optimized for use with 4 CC and 5 CC Carrier Aggregation.    If a different, optimized RLC profile for 4 CC and 5 CC CA is used, it is recommended to use the profile with the ID 7 (default). Note the different default values compared to RLC profiles 1-6.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - RLC profile index for 6 CC and 7 CC CA
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile optimized for use with 6 CC and 7 CC carrier aggregation.    If a different, optimized RLC profile for 6 CC and 7 CC carrier aggregation is used, it is recommended to use the profile with the ID 8 (default). Note the different default values compared to RLC profiles 1-7.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - Scheduling bucket size duration
Description: This parameter is used to configure the Bucket Size Duration (BSD) of the UL scheduler.  For GBR bearers, schedulBSD in used by eNB and UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  The bucket size of a logical channel is calculated by PBR * BSD.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - Scheduling priority
Description: Logical Channel Priority for the MAC scheduler  For GBR bearers, schedulPrio in used by eNB for the DL scheduling algorithm and by UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according [36.321].  Increasing priority values indicate lower priority.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for eNB schedulers. It applies only to NONGBR bearers  The scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling (UL and DL), and MAC logical channel priority handling and multiplexing in DL

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - DL Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for an eNB DL scheduler. It applies only to NONGBR bearers  The DL scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling and MAC logical channel priority handling and multiplexing

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - UL Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for an eNB UL scheduler. It applies only to NONGBR bearers  The UL scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 70 - Service-based HO allowed
Description: This parameter indicates whether service-based handover is allowed for the given QCI value.    Note: Additionally to the LNCEL-level activation (LNCEL-actServBasedHoQciX equal to 'true'), this QCIx must be enabled for the service-based HO on LNBTS level (LNBTS-qciTabX-servBasedHoAllowed = 'allowed').

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - ARP range for EN-DC eligible bearer
Description: This parameter defines the range(s) of ARP values for which this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  Each bit of this parameter stands for one ARP value from 1 to 15. Bit #0 is not used.  If a bit is set to value '1', for the corresponding ARP value this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  If a bit is set to value '0', for the corresponding ARP value this QCI cannot be used for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - Boosting factor for downlink
Description: This parameter defines the scaling factor for the DL scheduling weight. It is used to increase the DL scheduling weight for bearers which have TCP traffic boosting triggered according to tcpServiceDiffConfig settings.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - Boosting factor for uplink
Description: This parameter defines the scaling factor for the UL scheduling weight. It is used to increase the UL scheduling weight for bearers which have TCP traffic boosting triggered according to tcpServiceDiffConfig settings.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - DRX profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile  If several EPS bearers are established for a UE, the eNB compares the DRX profiles of the QCIs used for those EPS bearers and selects the DRX profile with the highest priority

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - DSCP
Description: This parameter configures the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value associated with the QCI.  The DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target eNB.    List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal):  BE (=0),  AF11 (=10),  AF12 (=12),  AF13 (=14),  AF21 (=18),  AF22 (=20),  AF23 (=22),  AF31 (=26),  AF32 (=28),  AF33 (=30),  AF41 (=34),  AF42 (=36),  AF43 (=38),  EF (=46)

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - DSCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DSCP profile (DSCPPR). Together with the ARP-DSCP marking table in the referenced instance of the DSCP profile a marking between QCI + ARP and DSCP is provided.    If not configured, then the DSCP value from this instance of QCI table (qciTabX-dscp) is used for all ARP values.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - Enforce TTI bundling
Description: This parameter enables TTI bundling if the QCI is present in the current bearer combination.  If this parameter is set to "true" for any bearer of the current bearer combination, the measurements for TTI bundling are activated and TTI bundling might be activated. Otherwise TTI bundling is not applied.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - Logical channel group identifier
Description: Logical Channel Group Identifier for buffer status reporting  This parameter is used for the configuration of the buffer status reports of the UE according to [36.321]

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - LTE-NR Dual connectivity support
Description: This parameter defines whether or not this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  If the parameter is configured to "EN-DC" this QCI definition is eligible for eUTRA-New Radio Dual Connectivity.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - Nominal bit rate downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the nominal bit rate in the downlink direction.  Leaving this parameter value empty means the nominal bitrate feature does not apply to this QCI in this direction.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 5120 kb/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - Nominal bit rate uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the nominal bit rate in the uplink direction.  eNB selects the value of prioritizedBitRate for UE configuration that is equal to or higher than nbrUl.  Leaving this parameter value empty means the nominal bitrate feature does not apply to this QCI in this direction.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 2048 kb/s.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - NR PDCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding PDCP profile used for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - PDCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding PDCP profile.

Parameter name: QCI translation table QCI 7 - Priority
Description: This parameter gives the priority of the EPS bearer according TS23.203.

Description: QoS Class Identifier

Description: This parameter indicates whether the given QCI is supported and enabled

Description: The Resource Type indicates whether a bearer is a GBR or NON-GBR bearer.  The Resource Type determines if dedicated network resources related to a service or bearer level Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) value are permanently allocated.
