Parameter name: QCI translation table operator specific QCIs
Description: Table to translate the S1AP parameter QCI into QCI characteristics for operator-specific QCIs

Parameter name: ARP range for EN-DC eligible bearer
Description: This parameter defines the range(s) of ARP values for which this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  Each bit of this parameter stands for one ARP value from 1 to 15. Bit #0 is not used.  If a bit is set to value '1', for the corresponding ARP value this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  If a bit is set to value '0', for the corresponding ARP value this QCI cannot be used for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).

Parameter name: Boosting factor for downlink
Description: This parameter defines the scaling factor for the DL scheduling weight. It is used to increase the DL scheduling weight for bearers which have TCP traffic boosting triggered according to tcpServiceDiffConfig settings.

Parameter name: Boosting factor for uplink
Description: This parameter defines the scaling factor for the UL scheduling weight. It is used to increase the UL scheduling weight for bearers which have TCP traffic boosting triggered according to tcpServiceDiffConfig settings.

Parameter name: Counter group
Description: This parameter indicates the counter group to which the QCI belongs

Parameter name: Delay target
Description: Delay target is the maximum packet delay value used by the eNB MAC scheduling algorithm for GBR bearers.  eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.

Parameter name: DRX profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DRX profile  If several EPS bearers are established for an UE, eNB compares the DRX profiles of the QCIs used for those EPS bearers and selects the DRX profile with highest priority

Parameter name: DSCP
Description: This parameter configures the Differentiated Services Code Point (DSCP) value associated with the QCI.  The DSCP value will be set in each IP packet sent for the related bearer to S-GW or target eNB.    List of IETF based DSCP values (numerical values in decimal):  BE (=0),  AF11 (=10),  AF12 (=12),  AF13 (=14),  AF21 (=18),  AF22 (=20),  AF23 (=22),  AF31 (=26),  AF32 (=28),  AF33 (=30),  AF41 (=34),  AF42 (=36),  AF43 (=38),  EF (=46)

Parameter name: Enforce TTI bundling
Description: This parameter enables TTI bundling if the QCI is present in the current bearer combination.  If this parameter is set to "true" for any bearer of the current bearer combination, the measurements for TTI bundling are activated and TTI bundling might be activated. Otherwise TTI bundling is not applied.

Parameter name: Overbooking factor on radio resources (PRBs on air interface) for operator defined GBR
Description: This parameter defines an overbooking factor on radio resources (PRBs on air interface) for operator defined GBR traffic in radio admission control. This factor is used to allow a more optimistic GBR admission. The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise. The GBR congestion handling will not use the overbooking factor.  The overbooking factor for a QCI value which is mapped to VoLTE service shall be set to 0.  In case the gbrOverbookingFactor is configured to 100 (= 100%) then radio admission control will skip the usual check on requested bit rate and available air interface resources.

Parameter name: L2 overhead factor GBR Dl
Description: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the downlink GBR in layer 2.  eNB increases the GBR in downlink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in downlink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR DL/100. eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.

Parameter name: L2 overhead factor GBR Ul
Description: This parameter specifies the overhead factor of the uplink GBR in layer 2.  eNB increases the GBR in uplink direction for radio layer 2 by the product GBR in uplink direction and L2 Overhead Factor GBR UL/100. eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.

Parameter name: Logical channel group identifier
Description: Logical Channel Group Identifier for buffer status reporting  This parameter is used for configuration of the buffer status reports of UE according to [36.321]

Parameter name: LTE-NR Dual connectivity support
Description: This parameter defines whether or not this QCI is eligible for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).  If the parameter is configured to "EN-DC" this QCI definition is eligible for eUTRA-New Radio Dual Connectivity.

Parameter name: Maximum GBR downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the downlink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with operator QCIs for which the GBR in downlink direction is greater than this value. eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.    Hints:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 2048 kb/s.    FDD only:  In cells with downlink channel bandwidth equal to 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz eNB will limit the downlink GBR to maximum 408 kbit/s.

Parameter name: Maximum GBR uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value of the GBR in the uplink direction.  eNB will reject those EPS bearers with operator QCIs for which the GBR in uplink direction is greater than this value. eNB ignores this parameter for nonGBR Operator QCIs.    Hints:  For LNBTSs that supporting only TDD cells (supportedCellTechnology set to 'TDD') it is not recommended to configure to values higher than 512 kb/s.  Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 2048 kb/s.    FDD only:  In cells with uplink channel bandwidth equal to 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz eNB will limit the uplink GBR to maximum 408 kbit/s.

Parameter name: Nominal bit rate downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the nominal bit rate in the downlink direction. It applies only to NONGBR bearers.  Leaving this parameter value empty means the nominal bitrate feature does not apply to this QCI in this direction.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 5120 kb/s.

Parameter name: Nominal bit rate uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the nominal bit rate in the uplink direction. It applies only to NONGBR bearers.  eNB selects the value of prioritizedBitRate for UE configuration that is equal to or higher than nbrUl.  Leaving this parameter value empty means the nominal bitrate feature does not apply to this QCI in this direction.    Hint:  It is not recommended to configure to values higher than 2048 kb/s.

Parameter name: NR PDCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding PDCP profile used for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity.

Parameter name: PDCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding PDCP profile.  If the RLC mode is set to "RLC_AM", this parameter has to set in the range {1, 2, 3, 4, 5}.  If the RLC mode is set to "RLC_UM", this parameter has to be set in range {102, 103, 104}.

Parameter name: Priority
Description: This parameter gives the priority of the EPS bearer according TS23.203.  This parameter is used for GBR congestion handling and is ignored for nonGBR bearers.

Parameter name: QCI
Description: QoS Class Identifier

Parameter name: QCI support
Description: This parameter indicates whether the given QCI is supported and enabled

Parameter name: DSCP profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding DSCP profile (DSCPPR). Together with the ARP-DSCP marking table in the referenced instance of the DSCP profile a marking between QCI + ARP and DSCP is provided.    If not configured, then the DSCP value from this instance of QCI table (qciTabX-dscp) is used for all ARP values.

Parameter name: Resource type
Description: The Resource Type indicates whether bearer is a GBR or NON-GBR bearer.  The Resource Type determines if dedicated network resources related to a service or bearer level Guaranteed Bit Rate (GBR) value are permanently allocated.

Parameter name: RLC mode
Description: This parameter configures the RLC Mode of the data radio bearer

Parameter name: RLC profile index
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile

Parameter name: RLC profile index for 3 CC CA
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile optimized for use with 3 CC Carrier Aggregation.

Parameter name: RLC profile index for 4 CC and 5 CC CA
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile optimized for use with 4 CC and 5 CC Carrier Aggregation.      If a different, optimized RLC profile for 4 CC and 5 CC CA is used, it is recommended to use the profile with the ID 7 (default). Note the different default values compared to RLC profiles 1-6.

Parameter name: RLC profile index for 6 CC and 7 CC CA
Description: This parameter specifies the ID of the corresponding RLC profile optimized for use with 6 CC and 7 CC carrier aggregation.    If a different, optimized RLC profile for 6 CC and 7 CC carrier aggregation is used, it is recommended to use the profile with the ID 8 (default). Note the different default values compared to RLC profiles 1-7.

Parameter name: Scheduling bucket size duration
Description: This parameter is used to configure the Bucket Size Duration (BSD) of the UL scheduler.  The BSD is sent to the UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according to [36.321].  The UE calculates the bucket size of a logical channel by PBR * BSD.

Parameter name: Scheduling priority
Description: Logical Channel Priority for the UE scheduler.  This priority is sent to UE for the UL scheduling algorithm according to DRB [36.321].  Increasing priority values indicate a lower priority.

Parameter name: Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for eNB schedulers  The scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling (UL and DL), and MAC logical channel priority handling and multiplexing in DL

Parameter name: DL Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for an eNB DL scheduler.  The DL scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling and MAC logical channel priority handling and multiplexing

Parameter name: UL Scheduling weight
Description: This parameter specifies the scheduling weight for an eNB UL scheduler.  The UL scheduling weight is used for MAC scheduling

Parameter name: Service-based HO allowed
Description: This parameter indicates whether service-based handover is allowed for the given QCI value.    Note: Additionally to the LNCEL-level activation (LNCEL-actServBasedHoQciX equal to 'true'), this QCIx must be enabled for the service-based HO on LNBTS level (LNBTS-qciTabX-servBasedHoAllowed = 'allowed').

Parameter name: Default QCI translation table for operator-specific QCIs
Description: This parameter identifies the default operator-specific QCI table for all operator-specific QCIs, for which no dedicated QCI table is defined.    Note: if operator-specific QCI tables are activated (LNBTS-actOperatorQCI is equal to 'true' and qciTabOperatorDefault is not configured, then legacy behavior is valid (undefined operator-specific QCIs are rejected).

Parameter name: RACH access for handover from NR SA
Description: This parameter selects whether target eNodeB shall provide and reserve a dedicated RACH preamble for HO from NR SA.  In case no dedicated RACH preamble is provided UE will perform contention based RACH access.  If a dedicated RACH preamble is provided UE will perform non-contention based RACH access as for intra LTE handover.  Note that in case eNodeB is configured to reserve a dedicated RACH preamble it may happen that eNodeB runs out of dedicated RACH preambles.  In this case contention based RACH access will be used as fallback solution.

Parameter name: RACH access for handover from UTRAN
Description: This parameter selects whether the target eNodeB shall provide and reserve a dedicated RACH preamble for HO from UTRAN.  In case no dedicated RACH preamble is provided, the UE will perform contention based RACH access.  If a dedicated RACH preamble is provided, the UE will perform non-contention based RACH access as for intra LTE handover.  Note that in case an eNodeB is configured to reserve a dedicated RACH preamble, it may happen that the eNodeB runs out of dedicated RACH preambles.  In this case, contention-based RACH access will be used as a fallback solution.

Parameter name: Random time offset for establishing X2 links to en-gNB
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum value of a random time offset, which is added to the total wait time for X2(gNB) establishment ('tTotalX2Gnb'). When configured to a value greater than 0 [s], eNB sends X2AP: EN-DC X2 SETUP REQUEST message to en-gNB only after this additional random time offset.    The purpose of this random time offset is to prevent/mitigate en-gNB overload when there are many incoming X2AP: EN-DC X2 SETUP REQUEST messages.

Parameter name: Release with redirection for WCDMA mobility prevention before QCI1
Description: This parameter specifies the treatment given to release with redirection to WCDMA when WCDMA mobility prevention before QCI1 bearer setup is enabled (actProhibitWcdmaMobPreQci1). This applies to both blind and measurement based redirection to WCDMA.

Parameter name: Release undetectable SCell
Description: This parameter determines whether to release an undetectable SCell.

Parameter name: SPID-based IF HO supervision timer A5 event
Description: Timer to supervise the A5 report in context with SPID-based IF HO. At expiry the A5 event will be de-activated.

Parameter name: Idle mode load balancing supervision timer for A4 event
Description: Timer to supervise the A4 report. At expiry, the A4 event will be deactivated.

Parameter name: QCIx service-based HO supervision timer QCIx for A5 event
Description: Timer to supervise the A5 report in context with QCIx service-based handover. At expiry the A5 event will be de-activated.

Parameter name: Requested frequency bands
Description: reqFreqBands defines the list of bands that is sent by an eNB to a UE for the retrieval of CA band combinations.  It is recommended that operator enters into reqFreqBands all band numbers that are used in his network for CA - not only those of the specific configuration of the eNB.

Parameter name: 3GPP band number
Description: bandNumber is the band that UE uses for filtering of CA band combinations except those for CA 2 DL + 1 UL.  bandNumber shall be aligned with the band numbers used in 3GPP TS 36.101 for the definition of CA band combinations.  If operator uses band numbers that require the mapping by Multiple Frequency Band Indicator (MFBI), it is recommended that actMFBI is set to true and the operator enters all band numbers into bandNumber that are contained in those CA band combinations of 3GPP TS 36.101 that they want to use.

Parameter name: Band priority
Description: BandPrio defines the order in which an eNB fills the related bandNumber into the UE Capability Retrieval message to a UE.  BandPrio 1 has the highest priority, BandPrio 16 has the lowest priority.

Parameter name: Profile 101 of RLC parameters - RLC profile id
Description: Identity of the RLC profile.

Parameter name: Profile 101 of RLC parameters - SN field length downlink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC UM procedures in the downlink direction.  If UE does not support the value '5bit', the value '10bit' is used.

Parameter name: Profile 101 of RLC parameters - SN field length uplink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC UM procedures in the uplink direction.  If UE does not support the value '5bit', the value '10bit' is used.

Parameter name: Profile 101 of RLC parameters - Timer reordering
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331].  This timer is used by the receiving side of an UM RLC entity for reordering and PDU loss detection. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

Parameter name: Profile 102 of RLC parameters - RLC profile id
Description: Identity of the RLC profile.

Parameter name: Profile 102 of RLC parameters - SN field length downlink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC UM procedures in the downlink direction.  If UE does not support the value '5bit', the value '10bit' is used.

Parameter name: Profile 102 of RLC parameters - SN field length uplink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC UM procedures in the uplink direction.  If UE does not support the value '5bit', the value '10bit' is used.

Parameter name: Profile 102 of RLC parameters - Timer reordering
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331].  This timer is used by the receiving side of an UM RLC entity for reordering and PDU loss detection. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

Parameter name: Profile 103 of RLC parameters - RLC profile id
Description: Identity of the RLC profile.

Parameter name: Profile 103 of RLC parameters - SN field length downlink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC UM procedures in the downlink direction.  If UE does not support the value '5bit', the value '10bit' is used.

Parameter name: Profile 103 of RLC parameters - SN field length uplink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC UM procedures in the uplink direction.  If UE does not support the value '5bit', the value '10bit' is used.

Parameter name: Profile 103 of RLC parameters - Timer reordering
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331].  This timer is used by the receiving side of an UM RLC entity for reordering and PDU loss detection. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

Parameter name: Profile 104 of RLC parameters - RLC profile id
Description: Identity of the RLC profile.

Parameter name: Profile 104 of RLC parameters - SN field length downlink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC UM procedures in the downlink direction.  If UE does not support the value '5bit', the value '10bit' is used.

Parameter name: Profile 104 of RLC parameters - SN field length uplink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC UM procedures in the uplink direction.  If UE does not support the value '5bit', the value '10bit' is used.

Parameter name: Profile 104 of RLC parameters - Timer reordering
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331].  This timer is used by the receiving side of an UM RLC entity for reordering and PDU loss detection. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - Max retransmission threshold for AM DRB
Description: The maximum number of poll retransmissions for the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity for DRB. This parameter specifies the parameter maxRetxThreshold of [36.331].  This parameter is used by the transmitting side of each AM RLC entity to count the number of transmissions of an AM PDU. It is set so that a radio link failure can be detected by the eNB before the maximum number of transmissions has been reached. The parameter is on a higher level than ARQ and HARQ.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - Poll PDU
Description: This parameter specifies the pollPDU parameter of [36.331].  The Poll PDU parameter defines the number of RLC PDUs that are sent on a logical channel before the RLC polling bit is set.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - RLC profile id
Description: Identity of the RLC profile.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - Timer poll retransmit common
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331]  This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll. This value is used both in the UL (by the UE) and in the DL (by the eNB).  The used minimum value of the timer shall be larger than the calculated round-trip time with considerations of HARQ retransmissions and out-of-sequence arrival. The value of the timer shall be larger than twice of the timerReorder.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - Timer poll retransmit downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331].  This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll. This value is used by the eNB for downlink data transmission.  The used minimum value of the timer shall be larger than the calculated round-trip time with considerations of HARQ retransmissions and out-of-sequence arrival. The value of the timer shall be larger than twice the timerReorder.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - Timer poll retransmit uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the t-pollRetransmit parameter of [36.331].  This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll. This value is used by the UE for uplink data transmission.  The used minimum value of the timer shall be larger than the calculated round-trip time with considerations of HARQ retransmissions and out-of-sequence arrival. The value of the timer shall be larger than twice the timerReorder.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - Timer status prohibit
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-StatusProhibit of [36.331].  This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity in order to prohibit transmission of a STATUS PDU.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - Timer reordering
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331].  This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

Parameter name: Profile 1 of RLC parameters - Timer reordering for inter-site carrier aggr.
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331].  This timer is used during inter-site carrier aggregation by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

This value is used both in the UL (by the UE) and in the DL (by the eNB).  The used minimum value of the timer shall be larger than the calculated round-trip time with considerations of HARQ retransmissions and out-of-sequence arrival. The value of the timer shall be larger than twice the timerReorder.

Parameter name: Profile 6 of RLC parameters - Timer poll retransmit downlink
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331].  This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll. This value is used by the eNB for downlink data transmission.  The used minimum value of the timer shall be larger than the calculated round-trip time with considerations of HARQ retransmissions and out-of-sequence arrival. The value of the timer shall be larger than twice the timerReorder.

Parameter name: Profile 6 of RLC parameters - Timer poll retransmit uplink
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331].  This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll. This value is used by the UE for uplink data transmission.  The used minimum value of the timer shall be larger than the calculated round-trip time with considerations of HARQ retransmissions and out-of-sequence arrival. The value of the timer shall be larger than twice the timerReorder.

Parameter name: Profile 6 of RLC parameters - Timer status prohibit
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-StatusProhibit of [36.331].  This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity in order to prohibit transmission of a STATUS PDU.

Parameter name: Profile 6 of RLC parameters - Timer reordering
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331].  This timer is used by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection, and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

Parameter name: Profile 6 of RLC parameters - Timer reordering for inter-site carrier aggr.
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-Reordering of [36.331].  This timer is used during inter-site carrier aggregation by the receiving side of an AM RLC entity for reordering, PDU loss detection and delay of STATUS PDU transmission. This timer depends on HARQ RTT and number of HARQ retransmissions.

Parameter name: Profile 7 of RLC parameters - Max retransmission threshold for AM DRB
Description: The maximum number of poll retransmission for the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity for DRB. This parameter specifies the parameter maxRetxThreshold of [36.331].  This parameter is used by the transmitting side of each AM RLC entity to count the number of transmissions of an AM PDU. It is set so that a radio link failure can be detected by the eNB before the maximum number of transmissions has been reached. The parameter is on a higher level than ARQ and HARQ.

Parameter name: Profile 7 of RLC parameters - Poll PDU
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter pollPDU of [36.331]  The parameter Poll PDU defines the number of RLC PDUs that are sent on a logical channel before the RLC polling bit is set.

Parameter name: Profile 7 of RLC parameters - RLC Profile Id
Description: Identity of the RLC profile

Parameter name: RLF based RRC connection reestablishment default
Description: Defines the default value for the LNADJ parameter rlfBasedRCRsupported, which is used if an LNADJ instance is autonomously created by an eNB due to an activated ANR feature.

Parameter name: RRC guard timer radio bearer management
Description: This timer is started when an RRC message for setup, modification or release of a radio bearer is sent to the UE. When the timer expires, the corresponding procedure is aborted.

Parameter name: Synchronization template distinguished name for CDMA/1xRTT
Description: The parameter rttSyncTemplateDN defines the distinguished name of the SYNC template to be used for CDMA/1xRTT idle mode mobility. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration.    Example:  FDN example: MRBTS-1/MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1  SDN example: MNL-1/MNLENT-1/SYNC-1/SYNCTEMPLATE-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.

Parameter name: S1 induced cell deactivation time
Description: If for an eNB cell all configured PLMN IDs are unavailable on S1 interface for the duration given by "s1InducedCellDeactDelayTime", the eNB cell is deactivated.

Parameter name: SCell activation cycle period
Description: This parameter defines the period of the SCell Activation cycle.  The parameter value is in seconds.  This parameter is not used when "sCellActivationMethod" is set to "blind".

Parameter name: SCell activation method
Description: This parameter defines the method to be used for SCell activation.  The meaning of the values is as follows:  'blind' means that SCell is blindly activated and it is never re-activated after the expiration of the timer sCellDeactivationTimerEnb.  'nonGBRBufferBased' means that SCell activation is triggered depending on the non-GBR data in the buffer. For a UE with two configured SCells, SCell activation is triggered depending on the non-GBR data in the buffer in a joint way, i.e., one MAC CE command activates all SCells.  'nonGBRBufferBasedStepWise' means that for a UE with two configured SCells, SCell activation by one or more separate MAC CE command(s) is triggered depending on the non-GBR data in buffer in a step-wise way. In the first step one SCell is activated depending on the non-GBR data in buffer and after that depending on the non-GBR data in buffer the second SCell is activated if needed.    Note: The period of the SCell activation cycle is configured in sCellActivationCyclePeriod.    With actULCAggr=UL_CA_with_smartSched, a DL&UL sCell's activation will be triggered by eNB to reach fast load balance purpose, this kind of sCell activation trigger scheme works without regard to sCellActivationMethod setting.

Parameter name: SCell deactivation timer eNB
Description: This timer controls the deactivation of Secondary Cell for Carrier Aggregation configured UEs.    The timer behaves in the same way as the SCell deactivation timer defined in TS 36.321, but result is explicit SCell deactivation by MAC CE instead of implicit SCell deactivation in order to avoid eNB - UE misalignment due to ambiguous HARQ feedback.  The value represents the number of radio frames.  Value 'infinity' means that the SCell is never deactivated by sCellDeactivationTimereNB.

Parameter name: SCell and PCell ambiguous HARQ feedback usage
Description: The parameter selects how the ambiguous HARQ feedback of UE with an active SCell related to DL transmission shall be interpreted for the purpose of controlling  1) DRX Inactivity Timer, and  2) radio link problem detection/recovery in PCell.    If set to conservative, the ambiguous HARQ feedback is interpreted as DTX for the purpose of controlling the timer and as DTX for radio link problem detection, the ambiguous HARQ feedback is ignored for radio link problem recovery.  If set to aggressive, the ambiguous HARQ feedback is interpreted as NACK for the purpose of controlling the timer and as NACK for radio link problem recovery, the ambiguous HARQ feedback is ignored for radio link problem detection. It is expected that the aggressive setting will favor the UE throughput of UEs with an active SCell.  It is expected that the conservative setting will favor cell throughput.

Parameter name: Conservativeness level of SCell activation
Description: The parameter configures aggressiveness/conservativeness level of SCell activation. The higher the value of the parameter the more conservative the SCell activation is.  If configured to value X, the meaning is as follows:  if it is estimated that the current UE data in the buffer is more than what can be drained on the PCell/PCell+ currently active SCell during the next X TTIs, then one SCell/one additional SCell will be activated (when sCellActivationMethod is configured to the value 'nonGBRBufferBased' and one SCell is configured for a UE or when sCellActivationMethod is configured to the value 'nonGBRBufferBasedStepWise' and one or two SCells are configured for a UE).  if it is estimated that the current UE data in the buffer is more than what can be drained on the PCell during the next X TTIs, then two SCells will be activated (when sCellActivationMethod is configured to the value 'nonGBRBufferBased' and two SCells are configured for a UE).    Note: This parameter has no effect if sCellActivationMethod is configured to 'blind'.

Parameter name: Measurement cycle on configured SCells
Description: The parameter is used only when an SCell is configured on the frequency indicated by the measObjectEUTRA and is in a deactivated state.

Parameter name: Select SCell mapped band in round-robin algorithm
Description: This parameter indicates whether mapped band shall be selected in smart SCell band selection round robin algorithm.

Parameter name: Time to trigger service-based HO
Description: Time to trigger of QCIx SBHO measurements

Parameter name: Shutdown step amount
Description: Number of Steps for Graceful Cell Shutdown

Parameter name: Shutdown window
Description: Time Interval for Stepwise Output Power Reduction for Graceful Cell Shutdown

Parameter name: SIB update rate threshold
Description: SIB update rate threshold which if exceeded will block non-critical SIB updates from being made.  Once the SIB update rate exceeds this threshold, non-critical SIB updates will not be made until the SIB update rate drops below this threshold. Critical SIB updates will be made regardless of the current SIB update rate. This parameter only applies to features that support non-critical SIB updates such as the PRACH Power Optimization, and Dynamic PUCCH Allocation features. The maximum update rate to guarantee that all idle UEs receive the SIB updates is equal to or less than 31 updates per 3 hours.    Note that this is an optional parameter. If the operator does not create an instance of this parameter, SIB rate monitoring will be disabled and all SIB updates will be allowed regardless of the SIB update rate.

Parameter name: Site template description
Description: The parameter specifies the description of the Site Template that is or shall be assigned for the base station. Site Template Description can be used for searching the Site Template Name, which is needed when generating complete BTS configuration. This parameter is relevant from NetAct 16.8 onwards.

Parameter name: Site template name
Description: The parameter specifies the name of the Site Template assigned for the base station. Site Template can be used for generating complete BTS configuration during the planning phase. This parameter is relevant from NetAct 16.8 onwards.

Parameter name: Skip EUTRAN UE capabilities on handover to UTRAN
Description: This parameter configures the handling of the EUTRAN capabilities in the S1AP:HANDOVER REQUIRED message.  If this parameter is set to true, eNodeB excludes the optional IE containing EUTRAN capabilities from the S1AP:HANDOVER REQUIRED message used to trigger PS-HO, SRVCC or CSFB by PS-HO towards UTRAN.  EUTRAN capabilities are only excluded if they exceed operator configurable limit.

Parameter name: SRVCC delay timer
Description: This parameter defines delay timer for SRVCC procedure trigger after establishment of first QCI#1 bearer for UE. During this timer running, eNodeB shall not start SRVCC procedures to WCDMA/GSM.    In addition this parameter acts as feature activation flag and feature LTE3290 SRVCC trigger enhancement shall be enabled when this parameter is set to any value other than 0.

Parameter name: Supported LTE cell technology
Description: This parameter specifies if the LTE cells the eNB operates shall have single technology (values 'FDD' and 'TDD') or if it shall serves cells in both technologies (value 'mixed_FDD_TDD').    Note:  Only AirScale hardware is capable to support a mixed cell technology configuration.  Cells with cellTechnology set to 'TDD' must not be allocated to BBMODs of type AirScale ABIP/ABIQ/ASOG/ASOH.

Parameter name: Supported number of ANR managed object instances
Description: Defines the number of system supported ANR managed object instances.

Parameter name: Supported number of LNADJ instances
Description: Defines the number of system supported LNADJ instances (enbControlled + oamControlled).

Parameter name: Change mobility request timer
Description: This timer controls the mobility change settings procedure at RRM load balancing function. It is started when RRM sends the Mobility Change Request message and it is stopped when RRM receives the expected Mobility Change Ack or Mobility Change Failure message.

Parameter name: Timer min lifetime of half-open RRC connection
Description: The minimal time period during which the internal state and the resources associated with a half-open RRC connection (i.e. one for which no RRC connection setup complete message has yet been received) must not be deleted in the eNB.

Parameter name: T HO overall delta
Description: Covers the estimated time taken to send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION message to the UE (no RLC Ack needed)  - send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE message from the UE  THOoverall = T304 + T311 + T301 + THOoverallDelta

Parameter name: Supervision timer for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity over X2 interface (EN-DC)
Description: The parameter specifies the maximum time that the MeNB will wait for the en-gNB message in response to a message sent by the MeNB to the en-gNB.  This timer supervises the MeNB initiated SgNB addition procedure, the MeNB initiated SgNB modification procedure, the MeNB initiated SgNB release procedure as well as the reception of the SN STATUS TRANSFER following the request from the SgNB to release the SGNB or for SN change.  During the MeNB initiated SgNB Addition procedure, this timer plays the role of TDCPrep, as defined in 3GPP.

Parameter name: AC overbooking supervision timer
Description: This parameter defines the duration for the timer which controls the temporary overbooking of RAC and TAC. The timer is started when an E-RAB with QCI#1 is admitted by overbooking in RAC and/or TAC. As long as the timer is running eNodeB tries to get rid of the UE by SRVCC to WCDMA. On expiry of the timer eNodeB triggers the release of the E-RAB admitted by temporary overbooking.

Parameter name: Timer poll retransmit for SRB Downlink
Description: This timer is used by the transmitting side (eNB) of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll for SRB.

Parameter name: Timer poll retransmit for SRB Uplink
Description: This timer is used by the transmitting side (UE) of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll for SRB.  This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit of [36.331].

Parameter name: Timer for the RLC PDU discarding
Description: Timer used to discard the PDU, which stays in the RLC' longer than this value.

Parameter name: Resource status reporting initiation wait time
Description: This time defines how long the eNB waits for the result of an earlier issued Resource Status Reporting request.  * If the Resource Status Request sent to initiate a Resource Status Reporting, then the eNB will repeat the Resource Status Request after this timer expires if the Resource Status Reporting is still needed by the eNB.  * If the Resource Status Request sent to stop an ongoing Resource Status Reporting, then on timer expiry the eNB will consider the stop request as failed and will locally release the Resource Status Reporting.

Parameter name: Resource status rep. result wait time first reporting
Description: This defines the maximum time the eNB waits for further cell load measurements before collected cell load measurements are indicated to the requesting cell for the first time.

Parameter name: Delta for supervision timer for HO execution to GSM
Description: Delta for Supervision Timer For The Execution Phase Of An S1 Handover to GSM  TS1RELOCoverallDelta_GSM is used to calculate the duration of the timer TS1RELOCoverall which is used to guard against failure of the MME to inform the source eNB of the outcome of the UEs attempt to connect to the target during S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCoverall is started in the source eNB when the RRC: MOBILITY FROM EUTRA COMMAND message is sent to the UE and is stopped when S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the handover is aborted and the UE context is released. In future releases the UE will be allowed to rejoin the source cell. The duration of TS1RELOCoverall is calculated by adding the value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_GSM to that of T304_InterRAT. The value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_GSM should be set to an estimate of an upper bound of the time taken for the RNC to communicate via the MME to the eNB during normal network conditions.

Parameter name: Delta for supervision timer for the execution HO NR
Description: Delta for Supervision Timer For The Execution Phase Of An S1 Handover to NR  TS1RELOCoverallDelta_NR is used to calculate the duration of the timer TS1RELOCoverall which is used to guard against failure of the MME to inform the source eNB of the outcome of the UEs attempt to connect to the target during S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCoverall is started in the source eNB when the RRC: MOBILITY FROM EUTRA COMMAND message is sent to the UE and is stopped when S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the handover is aborted and the UE context is released. In future releases the UE will be allowed to rejoin the source cell. The duration of TS1RELOCoverall is calculated by adding the value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_NR to that of T304_InterRATN. The value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_NR should be set to an estimate of an upper bound of the time taken for the gNB to communicate via the AMF/MME to the eNB during normal network conditions.

Parameter name: Delta for supervision timer for the execution HO WCDMA
Description: Delta for Supervision Timer For The Execution Phase Of An S1 Handover to UTRAN  TS1RELOCoverallDelta_UTRAN is used to calculate the duration of the timer TS1RELOCoverall which is used to guard against failure of the MME to inform the source eNB of the outcome of the UEs attempt to connect to the target during S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. TS1RELOCoverall is started in the source eNB when the RRC: MOBILITY FROM EUTRA COMMAND message is sent to the UE and is stopped when S1AP: UE CONTEXT RELEASE COMMAND is received from the MME to confirm the outcome. If the timer expires the handover is aborted and the UE context is released. In future releases the UE will be allowed to rejoin the source cell. The duration of TS1RELOCoverall is calculated by adding the value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_UTRAN to that of T304_InterRAT. The value of TS1RELOCoverallDelta_UTRAN should be set to an estimate of an upper bound of the time taken for the RNC to communicate via the MME to the eNB during normal network conditions.

Parameter name: Supervision timer for handover preparation to GSM
Description: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of S1 handover to GSM  Timer TS1RELOCprep_InterRAT is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

Parameter name: Supervision timer preparation intra LTE S1 HO
Description: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of intra LTE S1 handover  Timer TS1RELOCprep_LTE is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of intra LTE S1 handover. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

Parameter name: Supervision timer for the preparation HO NR
Description: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT  Timer tS1relprepN is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

Parameter name: Supervision timer for the preparation HO WCDMA
Description: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT  Timer tS1relprepIrat is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

Parameter name: Timer S1 E-RAB modification Indication
Description: Timer for supervision of S1 procedure E-RAB Modification Indication (started together with sending of S1AP: E-RAB Modification Indication and stopped upon reception of S1AP: E-RAB Modification Confirm)

Parameter name: Timer EN-DC Cell Activation wait for response
Description: max time eNB waits for response to X2AP: EN-DC CELL ACTIVATION REQUEST message

Parameter name: Supervision timer preparation intra LTE X2 HO
Description: Guard against failure of the handover target eNB to respond in preparation phase of X2 handover. This timer is started in the source eNB when the X2AP: HANDOVER REQUEST message is sent to the target eNB and is typically stopped when the X2AP: HANDOVER REQUEST ACKNOWLEDGE message is received in return.  When the timer expires, the X2AP: HANDOVER CANCEL procedure is started.

Parameter name: Timer for receiving secondary RAT data usage report on X2(gNB)
Description: Timer in MeNB to supervise X2(gNB) for secondary RAT data usage report from gNB.  eNB will keep open the UE-associated logical X2 connection and the UE-associated logical S1 connection for the duration of this timer so that eNB can still receive and forward a secondary RAT usage data report from gNB while UE context is being removed from the RAN.  Timer starts when MeNB sends 'X2AP: SGNB RELEASE REQUEST', 'X2AP: SGNB RELEASE CONFIRM', 'X2AP: SGNB CHANGE CONFIRM' or 'X2AP: SGNB MODIFICATION REQUEST for E-RAB release'  Timer stops when 'X2(gNB): SECONDARY RAT DATA USAGE REPORT' received  When timer expired or stopped 'X2AP(gNB): UE Context Release' will be send out.

Parameter name: End-Tag maximum AM
Description: The maximum bound for tag timer calculation valid for RLC-AM DRBs.

Parameter name: End-Tag maximum UM
Description: The maximum bound for tag timer calculation valid for RLC-UM DRBs.

Parameter name: Timer delayed AC continuation At pre-emption
Description: This timer delays the continuation of the admission control for pre-empted bearers.  If eNB sends the S1AP message E-RAB RELEASE INDICATION for pre-empted bearers to MME, the MME needs time to release the indicated bearers in the EPC. Until the release of a bearer S-GW might still send downlink data packets for this bearer to eNB. The expected average time is covered by this timer that delays the continuation of the admission control by the given timer value.

Parameter name: Time connection failure threshold
Description: The parameter is used to determine whether to consider an RLF Report for Inter-RAT MRO Too Late PM counting. It is compared against the timeConnFailure received in the RLF Report which represents the amount of time between the last incoming handover and the RLF.

Parameter name: Time of continuous bad UL packets to trigger handover for HFN reset
Description: This parameter defines the time of consecutive uncorrectable bad UL packets. It is one of the conditions to trigger handover to reset HFN of a RLC UM bearer using RoHC.

Parameter name: Temporary activation flags 1
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements. It is used to enable dedicated functionality in the BTS.

Parameter name: Temporary activation flags 2
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements. It is used to enable dedicated functionality in the BTS.

Parameter name: Temporary activation flags 3
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements. It is used to enable dedicated functionality in the BTS.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 1
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 10
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 2
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 3
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 4
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 5
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 6
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent features enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 7
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 8
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Temporary parameter 9
Description: This parameter is prepared for late and urgent feature enhancements.

Parameter name: Maximum transfer delay
Description: Describes the maximum allowed RLC PDU delay after the split. As the result of the applied splitting algorithm it is also defines the RLC' buffer depths.

Parameter name: TX2 RELOC overall delta
Description: Covers at a minimum the estimated time taken to:  - send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION message to the UE (no RLC Ack needed)  - send an RRC:CONNECTION RECONFIGURATION COMPLETE or RRC:CONNECTION REESTABLISHMENT REQUEST message from the UE  - send an S1AP: PATH SWITCH REQUEST message from the target eNB  Note that this value can be extended to also include the estimated time for the target eNB to complete the full handover completion phase.  TX2RELOCoverall = T304max + T311 + T301 + TX2RELOCoverallDelta

Parameter name: TX path failure mode
Description: Controls the handling of TX path failures.  If set to 'keepCellInService' a cell remains enabled as long as the minimum required number of TX path are operating as defined in dedicated features.  If set to 'disableCell' a cell is disabled if at least one TX path is not operable.  Please notice that changing the mode requires 'BTS restart'.

Parameter name: Pathloss threshold UE scheduled on single cell
Description: Pathloss threshold for UE scheduled on single cell for UL CA. When UE's pathloss is larger than the threshold, then this UE is only scheduled in single cell.

Parameter name: UL AMC timer for historical MCS
Description: The parameter defines the time in TTIs for remembering the selected Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) for the uplink when UL AMC has been enabled.

Parameter name: UL AMC inactivity timer
Description: The parameter defines the time in TTIs for starting the uplink Adaptive Modulation and Coding inactivity actions. The UE's current MCS is stored as 'historyMCS' and is then reduced by one step per each period of this inactivity timer, down to a lower boundary value. If the UE resumes UL activity before expiry of ulamcHistMcsT, the historyMCS is selected for the next transmission. If the UE resumes UL activity after expiry of ulamcHisMcsT, the current reduced MCS value is selected. To prevent MCS reset within a UE's DRX sleep phase, the parameter value must be larger than any of the configured DRX long cycle values.

Parameter name: Optimize RACH Power - RACH preamble interference power offset
Description: Offset added to the Received Interference Power (RIP) level to determine the RACH preamble target power.  The Received Interference Power (RIP) is measured over the PRACH PRBs in the PRACH TTIs and is then averaged over a period of time to generate an average PRACH RIP value. The preamble target power is then calculated by adding the value of this parameter to the average PRACH RIP value.

Parameter name: Optimize RACH Power - RACH preamble target power delta
Description: Delta to determine if RACH preamble target power should be changed.  If the newly calculated preamble target power has changed from the current SIB2 preambleInitialReceivedTargetPower by more than this parameter, then preambleInitialReceivedTargetPower will be set equal to the newly calculated preamble target power and will be communicated to the UE via SIB2.

Parameter name: Maximum RSSI for interference-aware UL-PC
Description: Sets an upper limit for RSSI received from a UE. If exceeded, the next power command indicates -1 dB UL power change even if the current UL power is insufficient for reaching Target SINR.

Parameter name: U-plane overload handling - Enable reduction of PDSCH UEs per TTI
Description: This parameter enables the U-plane overload countermeasure 'Reduction of PDSCH UEs per TTI' to reduce number of scheduled PDSCH UEs per TTI per pool dependent on the detected overload level.  Explanation of the values:  none: this countermeasure is disabled  OVL1andL2: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 1 and 2.  OVL2only: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 2 only.

Parameter name: U-plane overload handling - Enable rejection of E-RAB setup requests
Description: This parameter enables the U-plane overload countermeasure 'Rejection of E-RAB setup requests) to reduce the amount of active E-RABs dependent on the detected overload level.  Explanation of the values:  none: this countermeasure is disabled  OVL1andL2: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 1 and 2.  OVL2only: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 2 only.

Parameter name: U-plane overload handling - Enable rejection of incoming inter-eNB HO requests
Description: This parameter enables the U-plane overload countermeasure 'Rejection of incoming inter-eNB handover requests' to reduce the amount of active RRC connections. Dependent on the detected overload level, handovers of calls with low-priority bearers and/or GBR bearers shall be rejected. High-priority and emergency sessions will always be processed.  Explanation of the values:  none: this countermeasure is disabled  OVL1andL2: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 1 and 2.  OVL2only: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 2 only.

Parameter name: U-plane overload handling - Enable rejection of RRC connection requests
Description: This parameter enables the U-plane overload countermeasure 'Rejection of RRC connection requests' to reduce the amount of active RRC connections dependent on the detected overload level.  Explanation of the values:  none: this countermeasure is disabled  OVL1andL2: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 1 and 2.  OVL2only: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 2 only.

Parameter name: U-plane overload handling - Enable suspension of SRS for scheduling
Description: This parameter enables the U-plane overload countermeasure 'Suspend usage of SRS for scheduling' (SRS = sounding reference symbols) to reduce the amount of processing capacity by not considering SRS dependent on the detected overload level.  Explanation of the values:  none: this countermeasure is disabled  OVL1andL2: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 1 and 2.  OVL2only: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 2 only.

Parameter name: U-plane overload handling - Enable Tx diversity transmission
Description: This parameter enables the U-plane overload countermeasure 'Tx Diversity Transmission' to reduce the number of transport blocks sent to the UE dependent on the detected overload level.  Explanation of the values:  none: this countermeasure is disabled  OVL1andL2: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 1 and 2.  OVL2only: this countermeasure is enabled for U-plane overload level 2 only.

Parameter name: Voice support match indicator preconfiguration
Description: If voiceSuppMatchInd is set to 'supported' (respectively 'notSupported'), then eNB shall set the 'Voice Support Match Indicator' IE in a S1AP: UE RADIO CAPABILITY MATCH RESPONSE message to 'Supported' (respectively to 'Not Supported')  If voiceSuppMatchInd is set to 'errorIndication', then eNB shall answer to a S1AP: UE RADIO CAPABILITY MATCH REQUEST with an ERROR INDICATION message

Parameter name: Warning area coordinates allowed
Description: Indicates if warning area coordinates are allowed to be broadcasted in SIB12

Parameter name: X2 configuration update random delay timer
Description: eNB generates a random delay time from the interval [0, x2CfUpRdmDelayTmr] for X2 eNB Configuration Update procedure. This random delay time is added to a SW-internal timer that is defined for waiting for an X2 eNB Configuration Update Acknowledge from other eNB. It is also added to 'Time to Wait' if a failure response is received, before starting another retry of X2 eNB Configuration Update procedure.    If 'x2CfUpRdmDelayTmr' is set to '0', then no random delay is applied.    The random delay serves to avoid bursts of X2 eNB Configuration Update procedures within the network.

Parameter name: FDD wide cell configuration identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of object LNBTS_FDD. It uniquely defines the object containing FDD technology specific parameter applicable to all FDD cells. It is used only for operation and maintenance purposes.

Parameter name: Activate SRVCC to CDMA/1xRTT
Description: This parameter enables the feature SRVCC from LTE to CDMA/1xRTT.

Parameter name: Activate support of conversational voice bearer
Description: This parameter activates the support of the conversational voice bearer. The change becomes active for a cell after the next cell locking/cell unlocking sequence.

Parameter name: Activate dedicated target frequency lists for load balancing handover
Description: The parameter is used to activate feature LTE2571 "Dedicated target frequency list for load balancing". When activated dedicated configured target frequency layer lists are used for inter-frequency and WCDMA load balancing handovers.  Note that change of actDedFreqListsLB value will have no immediate impact on ongoing user connections or measurements.

Parameter name: Activate dedicated VoLTE inter-frequency handover
Description: The parameter is used to activate feature LTE1942 "Dedicated VoLTE IF frequency layers". When activated dedicated configured target frequency layer are used for inter-frequency mobility during ongoing VoLTE calls.  Please note that the change of the actDedVoLteInterFreqHo value will have no immediate impact on ongoing user connections.

Parameter name: Activate downlink interference shaping
Description: This parameter activates/de-activates the optional feature "Downlink Interference Shaping"

Parameter name: Activate support for dual band operation
Description: The eNB supports up to 6 cells dual band configurations with one system module.    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Activate flexible base band usage
Description: Activation of more flexible base band usage by allowing more enhanced recovery in case of HW failure. If set to 'true', the size of PUCCH PRB may be limited on 10 MHz system bandwidth or lower. It need to be set to 'true' to configure more than 2 cells with FSMD, more than 3 with FSME or FSMF without extension Baseband module, more than 6 with FSMF with extension Baseband module or more than 9 with FSMF+FBBx+FBBC or more than 6 with FSMF+FBBx+FBBC, if there are cells present with any of the following properties: ( (20MHz 4RX and actOptimizedBbUsage set to false) or (4x4 DL MIMO enabled) or UL CoMP 4RX enabled ) ). When set to 'true', range of parameters maxNumActUE and maxNumRrc will be limited for 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells.    AirScale:  actFlexBbUsage shall be set to false in any deployment.    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.  It is recommended to consider planned site extensions already with first commissioning if limitations for parameters maxNumActUE, maxNumRrc, addAUeTcHo, maxNumRrcEmergency, n1PucchAn, pucchNAnCs and deltaPucchShift are acceptable.    Activate Flexible Baseband Usage on BTS  Activation of more flexible baseband usage by allowing more enhanced recovery in case of HW failure. Parameter is affecting only into cells with uplink and downlink channel bandwidth is 5 MHz or 10 MHz. In case parameter is set to 'true', there may be limitations in the amount  FSMD: value 'false' => up to 2 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 3 cells can be configured.  FSME: value 'false' => up to 3 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 6 cells can be configured.  FSMF: value 'false' => up to 3 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 6 cells can be configured.  FSMF + 1 x Extension Baseband Module: value 'false' => up to 6 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 12 cells can be configured.  FSMF + FBBA + FBBC: value 'true' => up to 18 cells can be configured.    For SRAN only:  FSMF (4DSP deployment): value 'false' => up to 2 cells can be configured. Value 'true' => up to 4 cells can be configured.    Note: For AirScale the parameter value is not applicable.

Parameter name: Activate high priority services
Description: This parameter enables/disables the feature "Multimedia priority services" (LTE1074)

Parameter name: Activate high amount of RRC connected UE
Description: Activation to configure more than 840 RRC connected UE.    With this parameter it is possible to support higher amount of Active UE on cell. The amount of Active UE cannot exceed maximum number of RRC_connected.  The parameter can be configured to "true" for cell bandwidths of "5 MHz", "10 MHz", "15 MHz" or "20 MHz" using System module that supports over 840 RRC connected UE.    AirScale and newer HW: parameter is ignored.    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Activate support of IMS emergency sessions for Rel 9 UE
Description: This parameter activates the support IMS Emergency sessions for Release 9 UEs.

Parameter name: Activate in-device coexistence for LAA hardware sharing
Description: This parameter activates feature "In-Device Coexistence for LAA." If this feature is activated, the network supports In-Device Coexistence for LAA hardware sharing with WiFi. When triggered by the UE, the network suspends LAA operation so that the UE can use its hardware for WiFi.

Parameter name: Activate inter-frequency service based handover
Description: The parameter is used to activate the inter-frequency service based mobility trigger feature LTE1127 "Service based mobility trigger".  Please note that the change of the actInterFreqServiceBasedHo value will have no immediate impact on ongoing user connections.

Parameter name: Activate inter-site licensed-assisted access
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Inter-site licensed-assisted access', by which LAA cells from unlicensed WiFi bands can be used in inter-eNB/inter-site downlink carrier aggregation.

Parameter name: Activate LAA dynamic power control
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'LAA Dynamic Power Control'.

Parameter name: Activate optimized baseband resource usage
Description: This parameter enables the mapping of 2TX4RX cells to optimized baseband resources    This parameter is valid for FSMr3 HW only.    This parameter applies when there are cells with following properties configured to eNB:  - 2TX4RX with 5MHz, 10MHz, 15MHz or 20MHz and 'LNCEL instance ID' (LNCEL-lnCelId) is not member of any Uplink CoMP cell list (ULCOMP-ulCoMpCellList)    If there are no corresponding cells configured in the eNB, the parameter doesn't have any impact.    If 'actOptimizedBbUsage' is set to 'true' and above conditions are met, corresponding cells will receive optimize baseband resource mapping.  In all other cases, corresponding cells will receive standard baseband resource mapping.    With 'actOptimizedBbUsage' set to 'true' it becomes possible to create configurations for 2x2 MIMO with 4Rx diversity for up to 6 cells of 5 or 10 MHz in one basic cell set or up to 3 cells of 15 or 20 MHz in one basic cell set. No additional baseband extension module FBBA or FBBC are needed. This is referred to optimized baseband resource mapping. If parameter is set to 'false', above cells are mapped to FSMF plus FBBC or FBBA, as in all previous releases. This is referred to standard baseband resource mapping.

Parameter name: Activate periodic carrier blinking
Description: This parameter specifies the behavior of Periodic Carrier Blinking actions.

Parameter name: Activate ProSe communication
Description: This parameter activates ProSe sidelink communication for Public Safety.

Parameter name: Activate public safety bearers
Description: This parameter activates EPS unicast QCI bearers for the support of Public safety Push to talk (PTT) and data services.    If t310PubSafety or n310PubSafety are not configured, then T310 or N310 values for the UE are determined based on whether QCI 1 has been established and LNCEL-t310Qci1 or LNCEL- t310Qci1 are configured. If LNCEL-t310Qci1 or LNCEL-n310Qci1 are not configured or if QCI-1 is not established, values from LNCEL-t310 or LNCEL-n310 are used.

Parameter name: Activate support of public safety video bearer
Description: This parameter activates EPS unicast and multicast QCI 67 bearer for the support of public safety video.  Multicast QCI 67 support requires additionally an activation of LNBTS-actMBMSPS, which is not a prerequisite of actPubSafetyVideo activation.    Note: Despite general activation on LNBTS level, QCI 67 bearers are rejected in instances of LNCEL with a DL bandwidth of 1.4 or 3 MHz.

Parameter name: Activate SRVCC to GSM
Description: This parameter enables the feature 'SRVCC from LTE to GSM'.

Parameter name: Activate SRVCC to WCDMA
Description: This parameter enables the feature SRVCC from LTE to WCDMA.

Parameter name: Activate unlicensed spectrum access
Description: This parameter activates the functionality "Licensed - Assisted Access" for using cells from a unlicensed bands as SCells in carrier aggregation.    Hint:  When the parameter is set to 'off' all cells from an unlicensed band as defined in the parameter relationships are disabled.

Parameter name: Activate dynamic channel selection
Description: This parameter activates the functionality "LAA Dynamic Channel Selection" according to following mode:  - LAA mode, according to 3GPP rel.13

Parameter name: Activate DFS support for LAA
Description: This parameter activates the functionality "DFS support for LAA".

Parameter name: Activate inter-RAT UTRAN load balancing
Description: The parameter activates the feature 'Inter-RAT UTRAN load balancing'  Note: In addition, the measurement M8029 needs to be started in each LNCEL separately.

Parameter name: CIoT EPS optimization PLMN Id list
Description: This parameter specifies the PLMN ID list which are supporting CIoT EPS Optimization procedures in eNB.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 and IE CIOT-OptimisationPLMN-r13

Parameter name: Attach without PDN connectivity support
Description: This parameter specifies support of Attach without PDN Connectivity in CIoT EPS Optimization Procedure.  Refer to 3GPP TS36.331 and IE attachWithoutPDN-Connectivity-r13    'not support': Attach without PDN Connectivity is not applicable for both CAT-M and NBIoT in this PLMN.  'support': Attach without PDN Connectivity is applicable for both CAT-M and NBIoT in this PLMN  'Cat-M support': Attach without PDN Connectivity is applicable only for CAT-M in this PLMN  'NB-IoT support': Attach without PDN Connectivity is applicable only for NB-IoT in this PLMN
Range and step: not support (0), support (1), Cat-M support (2), NB-IoT support (3)

Parameter name: MCC
Description: This parameter specifies Mobile Country Code of PLMN ID supporting CIoT EPS Optimization Procedure. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC
Description: This parameter specifies Mobile Network Code of PLMN ID supporting CIoT EPS Optimization Procedure. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC length
Description: This parameter specifies the range of Mobile Network Code of PLMN ID supporting CIoT EPS Optimization Procedure.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Absolute Allowed Maximum Time Error for BTS
Description: This parameter configures the maximum allowed absolute time error of the BTS required for supporting features depending on Loose H-SFN Sync in LTE.

Parameter name: Number of sampled subframes with high non-GBR UL data traffic
Description: Number of sampled subframes that would require another UL secondary component carrier (SCC) to be configured for serving all the UE non-GBR UL data traffic.    Note: Adding another UL SCC can be done by upgrading an existing SCell with DL SCC only to have DL and UL SCC or by adding a new SCell having both, DL and UL SCC.

Parameter name: Number of sampled subframes with high non-GBR UL data traffic measured for EN-DC setup
Description: Number of consecutive sampled subframes with high non-GBR UL data volume that would require EN-DC to be configured for serving all the UE non-GBR UL data traffic.  non-GBR UL data volume is estimated in subframes after (e)BSR reception.    Note:  This parameter together with LNCEL/ulEnDcConfigLevel defines conservativeness/aggressiveness level of EN-DC setup based on UL non-GBR data buffer status.

Parameter name: Number of sampled subframes with high non-GBR DL data traffic
Description: Number of sampled subframes that would require a (another) SCell configuration for serving all the UE non-GBR DL data traffic.    Note: Special value "0" means that the UE candidate SCells are immediately configured even if not required for serving the UE non-GBR DL data traffic.

Parameter name: Prevent PS-HO to WCDMA
Description: This parameter can be used to generally prevent the execution of PS-handover towards WCDMA for all UE or to prevent the execution of PS-handover towards WCDMA for all UE without an active VoIP bearer.  If this parameter is set to "All" all UE will be sent to WCDMA by UE Context Release with redirect, even if the UE would be able to perform handover.  If this parameter is set to "NonVoiceOnly" all UE without an established VoIP bearer will be sent to WCDMA by UE Context Release with redirect, even if the UE would be able to perform handover.  This parameter must be configured if handover to WCDMA is activated. It is not needed otherwise.

Parameter name: Supplemental DL carrier frequency list
Description: This parameter list contains the frequencies (DL EARFCNs) of cells that are operated in downlink only and are used as SCells in carrier aggregation. This list can be used to forbid outgoing mobility procedures. The values are given as ranges [startEarfcnDl, endEarfcnDl].  The outgoing mobility towards cells on supplemental DL carriers can be prohibited by defining an/several appropriate EARFCN start/end couple/s into this frequency list. The corresponding measurement objects on those carrier frequencies are then forbidden to be created.

Parameter name: Ending DL EARFCN in suppl. DL carrier frequency list
Description: This parameter indicates the highest DL EARFCNs in a suppl. DL carrier range.

Parameter name: Starting DL EARFCN in suppl. DL carrier frequency list
Description: This parameter indicates the lowest DL EARFCN in a suppl. DL carrier range

Parameter name: Skip UE release check for public safety bearer setup
Description: This parameter indicates if establishment of QCI-65 or QCI-66 or QCI-69 or QCI-70 is allowed for the UE with any 3GPP release (RRC:UE-EUTRA-Capability.accessStratumRelease). If this parameter is set to false, then the UE must support at least 3GPP release 12 to be able to establish the above QCIs.  Note that 3GPP UE release check is not performed for QCI-67 establishment.

Parameter name: TDD wide cell configuration identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of object LNBTS_TDD. It uniquely defines the object containing TDD technology specific parameter applicable to all TDD cells. It is used only for operation and maintenance purposes.

Parameter name: Activate SRVCC to CDMA/1xRTT
Description: This parameter enables the feature SRVCC from LTE to CDMA/1xRTT.

Parameter name: Activate B2 suppression for HO to TD-SCDMA with VoLTE
Description: Activates B2 Measurement suppression for TD-SCDMA PS HO and Redirection with VoLTE UE

Parameter name: Activate Citizens Broadband Radio Service Support
Description: This parameter activates the support for Citizens Broadband Radio Service (CBRS).

Parameter name: Activate the support for CBRS Enhanced Measurement
Description: This parameter activates the support for CBRS (Citizens Broadband Radio Service) Enhanced Measurement.

Parameter name: Activate support of conversational voice bearer
Description: This parameter activates the support of the conversational voice bearer. The change becomes active for a cell after the next cell locking/cell unlocking sequence.

Parameter name: Activate CSBIA
Description: Coordinate Scheduling for Beamforming Interference Avoidance (CSBIA) activation for the eNB  Configuration rules:  Distributed sites is not supported

Parameter name: Activate dedicated target frequency lists for load balancing handover
Description: The parameter is used to activate feature LTE2571 "Dedicated target frequency list for load balancing". When activated dedicated configured target frequency layer lists are used for inter-frequency and WCDMA load balancing handovers.  Note that change of actDedFreqListsLB value will have no immediate impact on ongoing user connections or measurements.

Parameter name: Activate dedicated VoLTE inter-frequency handover
Description: The parameter is used to activate feature LTE1942 "Dedicated VoLTE IF frequency layers". When activated dedicated configured target frequency layer are used for inter-frequency mobility during ongoing VoLTE calls.  Please note that the change of the actDedVoLteInterFreqHo value will have no immediate impact on ongoing user connections.

Parameter name: Activate downlink interference shaping
Description: This parameter activates/de-activates the optional feature "Downlink Interference Shaping"

Parameter name: Activate Flexible TDLTE timing offset configuration for band D and F
Description: Enables Flexible TDLTE timing offset configuration to support configurable frame-offset between TDS and LTE system.  Allows the manual frame timing adjustment for band D and F to reduce interference in interworking with TD-SCDMA.    For SBTS a BTS site restart (instead of RAT restart) will happen after modifying this parameter.

Parameter name: Activate handover from LTE to TD-SCDMA
Description: This parameter enables the feature Handover from LTE to TD-SCDMA.

Parameter name: Activate high priority services
Description: This parameter enables/disables the feature "Multimedia priority services" (LTE1074)

Parameter name: Activate support of IMS emergency sessions for Rel 9 UE
Description: This parameter activates the support IMS Emergency sessions for Release 9 UEs.

Parameter name: Activate inter-frequency service based handover
Description: The parameter is used to activate the inter-frequency service based mobility trigger feature LTE1127 "Service based mobility trigger".  Please note that the change of the actInterFreqServiceBasedHo value will have no immediate impact on ongoing user connections.

Parameter name: Activate RIP per PRB counter
Description: Parameter actPMRIP activates or deactivates the RIP per PRB counter based on uplink sub-frame.

Parameter name: Activate public safety bearers
Description: This parameter activates EPS unicast QCI bearers for the support of Public safety Push to talk (PTT) and data services.    If t310PubSafety or n310PubSafety are not configured, then T310 or N310 values for the UE are determined based on whether QCI 1 has been established and LNCEL-t310Qci1 or LNCEL- t310Qci1 are configured. If LNCEL-t310Qci1 or LNCEL-n310Qci1 are not configured or if QCI-1 is not established, values from LNCEL-t310 or LNCEL-n310 are used.

Parameter name: Activate support of public safety video bearer
Description: This parameter activates EPS unicast QCI 67 bearer for the support of public safety video.

Parameter name: Activate redirect VoLTE
Description: This parameter activates feature LTE2108 "Redirect VoLTE call setup".

Parameter name: Activate SRVCC to GSM
Description: This parameter enables the feature 'SRVCC from LTE to GSM'.

Parameter name: Activate SRVCC to WCDMA
Description: This parameter enables the feature SRVCC from LTE to WCDMA.

Parameter name: Activate VoLTE call steering
Description: This parameter activates LTE2388 'VoLTE call steering enhancement'.    When the feature is activated, it is recommended to set qciTab1-qciSupp and qciTab5-qciSupp to 'ENABLE'.    Note: The parameter is only supported on FSMr3.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CSBIA Pcell A3 Reuse
Description: CSBIA Pell A3 Reuse  if csBIAPcellA3Reuse set to true, UE CSBIA property classification in SCell will reuse the A3 measurement from PCell. Suggest to set to true only in CA scenario 1.

Parameter name: Maximum CQI offset for DL OLQC
Description: The parameter defines the maximum CQI offset in Outer Loop Link Quality Control (OLQC) for Downlink.

Parameter name: Downlink sector beamforming weight customized profile
Description: Configuration of the customized downlink sector beamforming weight for "Sector Beamforming with static weights".  There are two types of the downlink sector beamforming weight profiles.  One is "predefined profile" and another is "customized profile".  "predefined profile" means the downlink sector beamforming weights shall be set as the predefined values per the specific antenna type(according to antenna spec).  "customized profile" means the operator can set the downlink sector beamforming weights via O&M interface.

Parameter name: Antenna element spacing
Description: This parameter defines the physical antenna element spacing in millimeter for the specific antenna type defined in dlSectorBFWeightProfName of the list item.  If the relative antenna element spacing is not in range of 0.470...0.525 lambda or 0.620...0.675 lambda CEBB won't be activated.  The relative antenna element spacing = LNBTS-dlSectorBFWeightCusProf-dlSectorAntennaElementSpacing(millimeter)/1000*earfcn(Hz)/(3*10^8 (m/s) ).

Parameter name: Downlink sector beamforming weight profile name
Description: This parameter identifies the name of the downlink sector beamforming weight profile.  The downlink sector beamforming weight profile shall belong to the customized profile.
