Range and step: customized profile 1 (1), customized profile 2 (2), customized profile 3 (3), customized profile 4 (4), customized profile 5 (5), customized profile 6 (6), customized profile 7 (7), customized profile 8 (8), customized profile 9 (9), customized profile 10 (10), customized profile 11 (11), customized profile 12 (12), customized profile 13 (13), customized profile 14 (14), customized profile 15 (15), customized profile 16 (16), customized profile 17 (17), customized profile 18 (18), customized profile 19 (19), customized profile 20 (20)

Parameter name: Modulus of weight for antenna group 0
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the downlink sector beamforming weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup0 which belongs to the same polarized direction.

Parameter name: Modulus of weight for antenna group 1
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the downlink sector beamforming weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup1 which belongs to the same polarized direction.

Parameter name: Modulus of weight for antenna group 2
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the downlink sector beamforming weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup2 which belongs to the same polarized direction.

Parameter name: Modulus of weight for antenna group 3
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the downlink sector beamforming weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup3 which belongs to the same polarized direction.

Parameter name: Phase of weight for antenna group 0
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the downlink sector beamforming weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup0 which belongs to the same polarized direction.

Parameter name: Phase of weight for antenna group 1
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the downlink sector beamforming weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup1 which belongs to the same polarized direction.

Parameter name: Phase of weight for antenna group 2
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the downlink sector beamforming weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup2 which belongs to the same polarized direction.

Parameter name: Phase of weight for antenna group 3
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the downlink sector beamforming weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup3 which belongs to the same polarized direction.

Parameter name: Manual frame timing adjustment offset for band D
Description: Defines the frame timing adjustment offset for band D:  (0) default alignment --- 0us  (1) aligned with 1PPS --- 0us  (2) aligned with TDS --- -697.66us
Range and step: default alignment (0), aligned with 1PPS (1), aligned with TDS (2)

Parameter name: Manual frame timing adjustment offset for band F
Description: Defines the frame timing adjustment offset for band F:  (0) default alignment --- CPRI ALU/Nokia: 0us , CPRI IR: -697.66us  (1) aligned with 1PPS --- 0us  (2) aligned with TDS --- -697.66us
Range and step: default alignment (0), aligned with 1PPS (1), aligned with TDS (2)

Parameter name: Massive MIMO vertical GoB (Grid of Beam) first vector
Description: The parameter specifies the first vertical GoB (Grid of Beam) vector for both downlink and uplink MU-MIMO in massive MIMO.  The vertical GoB vector is calculated by first vertical GoB vector and vertical relative GoB vector. For instance:  Vertical GoB OAM parameters Internal Relative value  Vertical GoB (-15, 0) First vertical GoB: -15 Vertical Relative GoB (0, 15)    The parameter 'mMimoVerticalGobFirst' has relationship with 'mMimoSectorBFProfName' setting's electrical tilt if the vendor specific sector beamforming weight profile is used, reference setting is mMimoVerticalGobFirst = mMimoSectorBFProfName's Electrical Tilt - 7 degree.  For instance, if mMimoSectorBFProfName = '3:Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(3)' then  Vertical GoB OAM parameters Internal Relative value  Vertical GoB (-4, 11) First vertical GoB: -4 Vertical Relative GoB (0, 15)

Parameter name: Number of sampled subframes with high non-GBR UL data traffic
Description: Number of sampled subframes that would require another UL secondary component carrier (SCC) to be configured for serving all the UE non-GBR UL data traffic.    Note: Adding another UL SCC can be done by upgrading an existing SCell with DL SCC only to have DL and UL SCC or by adding a new SCell having both, DL and UL SCC.

Parameter name: Number of sampled subframes with high non-GBR UL data traffic measured for EN-DC setup
Description: Number of consecutive sampled subframes with high non-GBR UL data volume that would require EN-DC to be configured for serving all the UE non-GBR UL data traffic.  non-GBR UL data volume is estimated in subframes after (e)BSR reception.    Note:  This parameter together with LNCEL/ulEnDcConfigLevel defines conservativeness/aggressiveness level of EN-DC setup based on UL non-GBR data buffer status.

Parameter name: Number of sampled subframes with high non-GBR DL data traffic
Description: Number of sampled subframes that would require a (another) SCell configuration for serving all the UE non-GBR DL data traffic.    Note: Special value "0" means that the UE candidate SCells are immediately configured even if not required for serving the UE non-GBR DL data traffic.

Parameter name: Prevent PS-HO to WCDMA
Description: This parameter can be used to generally prevent the execution of PS-handover towards WCDMA for all UE or to prevent the execution of PS-handover towards WCDMA for all UE without an active VoIP bearer.  If this parameter is set to "All" all UE will be sent to WCDMA by UE Context Release with redirect, even if the UE would be able to perform handover.  If this parameter is set to "NonVoiceOnly" all UE without an established VoIP bearer will be sent to WCDMA by UE Context Release with redirect, even if the UE would be able to perform handover.  This parameter must be configured if handover to WCDMA is activated. It is not needed otherwise.

Parameter name: Prohibit PS-HO to TD-SCDMA
Description: This parameter can be used to generally prohibit the execution of PS-handover towards TD-SCDMA.  If this parameter is set to true all UE will be send to TD-SCDMA by UE Context Release with redirect, even if the UE would be able to perform handover.  This parameter must be configured if handover to TD-SCDMA is activated. It is not needed otherwise.

Parameter name: Skip UE release check for public safety bearer setup
Description: This parameter indicates if establishment of QCI-65 or QCI-66 or QCI-69 or QCI-70 is allowed for the UE with any 3GPP release (RRC:UE-EUTRA-Capability.accessStratumRelease). If this parameter is set to false, then the UE must support at least 3GPP release 12 to be able to establish the above QCIs.  Note that 3GPP UE release check is not performed for QCI-67 establishment.

Parameter name: Support of extended CQI periodicity
Description: This parameter enables the use of PUCCH configuration to support more RRC connected UEs.  All cell in this eNB only configure old PUCCH CSI look-up table(LTE1130)  If suppExtCqiPeriod is set to 'false', all TDD cells in the eNB where LTE1130 is activated use the legacy PUCCH CSI look-up table.  If suppExtCqiPeriod is set to 'true', all TDD cells in the eNB must have LTE1130 activated. In this case a PUCCH CSI look-up table which allows to support more RRC connected UEs is taken into use.

Parameter name: Supervision Timer For Preparation HO To TD-SCDMA
Description: Guard against failure of the MME to respond in preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT  Timer TS1RELOCprep_TDSCDMA is used to guard against failure of the MME to respond preparation phase of S1 handover to another 3GPP RAT. It is started in the source eNB when the S1AP: HANDOVER REQUIRED message is sent to the MME and is stopped when the S1AP: HANDOVER COMMAND or S1AP: PREPARATION FAILURE message is received in response. If the timer expires the handover is aborted or cancelled.

Parameter name: UL AMC delta C stepsize up
Description: The parameter defines the stepsize up value for the uplink Outer Loop Link Adaption compensation delta C. Stepsize down value for delta C can be calculated by using this parameter and UL target BLER (ulTargetBler, SFS ULAMC_TARGET_BLER (ulamcTargetBler)).

Parameter name: LTE cell configuration identifier
Description: Instance identifier of the object LNCEL. This parameter is used only for O&M purposes.    Important Note:  If the lnCelId shall be modified it is recommended to use EM (Element Manager). The EM (Element Manager) will automatically perform a full commissioning instead of a delta commissioning. Otherwise 2 plan file operations are required because LNCEL as well as the related LCELL object must be deleted and recreated. Those two objects are strongly coupled and must be created and deleted in common.

Parameter name: RSRQ mobility parameters - A1 report interval for serving becomes better than RSRP
Description: For the RSRP based A1 event of serving cell for stopping of Inter-RAT (InterFreq) Measurements the UE performs periodical reporting with this indicated interval    The UE is configured to report this A1 event in an infinite way when this parameter is set, otherwise A1 event will be only reported once.

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A1 to deactivate inter measurement
Description: Time to trigger deactivation of all measurements  Duration for which the event A1 must be valid, such that Inter-Frequency/Inter-RAT measurements are deactivated

Parameter name: A2 based redirect for VoLTE calls
Description: This parameter enables and disables A2 based redirection for VoLTE calls when UE has QCI1 bearer.  A2 Redirect measurement will not be activated if UE has QCI1 bearer and this parameter is set to disabled. A2 Redirect measurements will be activated when UE has QCI1 bearer and this parameter is set to enabled, or if UE does not have QCI1 bearer. This parameter does not affect A2 redirect measurement when UE does not have any QCI1 bearer.

Parameter name: Threshold 2 config for CDMA2000 HRPD and 1xRTT - Time to trigger for A2 to activate CDMA2000 measurement
Description: Time during which specific RSRP criteria for the event A2 needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A2 to activate GERAN measurement
Description: Time to trigger activation of GERAN measurements  Duration for which the event A2 must be valid, such that GSM measurements are activated

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A2 to activate inter measurement
Description: Duration for which the event A2 must be valid, such that additional InterFrequency measurements are activated

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A2 to activate NR measurement
Description: Time to trigger activation of coverage-based 5G SA HO measurements  Duration for which the event A2 must be valid, such that coverage-based 5G SA HO measurements are activated

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A2 to activate WCDMA measurement
Description: Time to trigger activation of WCDMA measurements  Duration for which the event A2 must be valid, such that WCDMA measurements are activated

Parameter name: RSRQ mobility parameters - Time to trigger A2-RSRQ to start mobility measurement
Description: Time to trigger for A2-RSRQ.  Duration for which the event A2-RSRQ must be valid, such that mobility measurements with measurement gaps are activated.

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A2 to start redirect procedure
Description: Duration for which the event A2 must be valid, such that redirect is raised

Parameter name: RSRQ redirection parameters - Time to trigger for A2 by RSRQ to start redirect
Description: Time to trigger for A2-RSRQ.  Duration for which the event A2-RSRQ must be valid, such that redirect is raised.

Parameter name: A3 offset
Description: Handover margin for better cell HO. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the neighbor cell becomes better than the serving cell by the value of the A3 offset. This parameter is used for both RSRP and RSRQ based A3 measurement for intra-frequency HO measurements.

Parameter name: A3 report amount
Description: Defines the number of A3 measurement reports that the UE can send once the A3 threshold criteria is met for intra-frequency measurement

Parameter name: A3 report interval
Description: This parameter defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the measurement event A3 are met. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS120 corresponds to 120 ms, MS240 to 240 ms and so on, while value MIN1 corresponds to 1 min, MIN6 to 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the measurement event A3 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS0 corresponds to 0 ms, MS40 to 40 ms and so on.

Parameter name: A3 trigger quantity
Description: Defines which quantity (RSRP or RSRQ) the UE has to use for triggering an event A3 measurement report for Intra-frequency handover measurements.

Parameter name: A5 report amount
Description: Defines the number of A5 measurement reports that the UE can send once the A5 threshold criteria is met for intra-frequency measurement

Parameter name: A5 report interval
Description: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the measurement event A5 are met. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS120 corresponds to 120 ms, MS240 to 240 ms and so on, while value MIN1 corresponds to 1 min, MIN6 to 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: A5 time to trigger
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the measurement event A5 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS0 corresponds to 0 ms, MS40 to 40 ms and so on.

Parameter name: A5 trigger quantity intra freq
Description: Defines which quantity (RSRP or RSRQ) the UE has to use for triggering an event A5 measurement report for Intra-frequency handover measurements.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN access class barring profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the access barring profile for primary PLMN. The primary PLMN ID is unique under eNB, but operator can differentiate the access barring profile ID for primary PLMN under each cell.

Parameter name: Activation of 3FDD plus 3TDD restriction
Description: Restriction of maximum 3 FDD plus 3 TDD inter-frequencies in final frequency list when the UE supports only 3GPP Release 8 and 9.

Parameter name: Activate AC high priority session limits
Description: This parameter activates the support of the following feature:  LTE4868: Admission control to differentiate HPA and Emergency handling.  For resource requests with high priority session indication on RRC connections and active UEs a higher admission control threshold will be used to admit those requests. Emergency requests cannot use those resources reserved for High Priority Session (HPS) handling while HPS users may use resources for emergency and HPS.

Parameter name: Activate air-to-ground configuration
Description: Activates the air-to-ground configuration for a cell. The configuration is used to provide LTE coverage for air crafts.

Parameter name: Activate active mode load equalization
Description: This parameter activates/de-activates the optional feature "Active mode load equalization".

Parameter name: Activate AMLE serving cell threshold filtering
Description: This parameter activates/de-activates the AMLE serving cell (RSRP/RSRQ) threshold filtering.

Parameter name: Activate software antenna port re-mapping
Description: This parameter controls I/Q data stream mapping to TX antenna ports.  When set to 'false', the I/Q data streams are mapped automatically on TX antenna ports on RF modules.  When set to 'true', the I/Q data streams are mapped on CHANNEL objects in fixed pattern. Manual configuration of antenna line for each CHANNEL is then necessary (by setting CHANNEL.antlDN).

Parameter name: Activate B1-NR supported return of 5G SA
Description: This parameter activates support for validation of predefined NR carrier based on B1-NR measurement check during 5G redirection target carrier selection of 5G capable UE at the end of RRC connections.    If this parameter is set to 'true', CB007172 will use (stored) B1-NR measurements to select redirection target.  If this parameter is set to 'false', legacy CB007172 behavior will apply.    This feature adds B1-NR measurement-based redirection target carrier check to CB007172 at end of RRC connection. NR SA carrier is checked via NSA B1-NR measurements, assuming each SA gNB is also working in NSA mode. The B1-NR measurement report depends on B1-NR measurements being enabled by LTE4193 or LTE5003.    Note: redirection to 5G SA at the end of voice calls is based on blind redirection.

Parameter name: Activate improvements to CA architecture enhancements
Description: Selects the architecture enhancements of platform's internal communication.  If the parameter is set to  - 'off':  legacy CA architecture enhancements are not activated (corresponds to legacy actCaArchEnh set to 'false').  - 'on_peak_data_rate_basic':  CA architecture enhancements are activated, the peak data rate is limited by the legacy dynamic algorithm (corresponds to legacy actCaArchEnh set to 'true').  - 'on_peak_data_rate_adv':  additionally, to 'on_peak_data_rate_basic', the modulation order can be restricted for serving cells to guarantee that the UE is not exceeding its supported peak data rate related to the UE category. Serving cells with a restricted modulation order are not configured with altCQI-Table-r12 (DL 256QAM support).  Note: This parameter replaces actCaArchEnh.    If the LNCEL is linked to AirScale ABIN, AirScale ABINL, AirScale ABIO or AirScale ABIOL or AirScale ABIP/ABIQ or AirScale ASOE/ASOF or AirScale ASOG/ASOH and actCaArchEnhImp can be set different to 'off' it is recommended to set actCaArchEnhImp to 'on_peak_data_rate_adv'.

Parameter name: Activate load-based carrier aggregation PCell and SCell blocking
Description: This parameter activates the support of load-based carrier aggregation PCell and SCell blocking.

Parameter name: Activate carrier aggregation SCell scheduler weight factor
Description: Activates the carrier aggregation SCell scheduler weight factors.

Parameter name: Activate additional PM counters for CA monitoring from LTE4816
Description: The parameter activates the feature LTE4816 ("Carrier aggregation PM counter extension")  Note: In addition, the underlying CA functionality must be activated as well - else all counter values will be 0!

Parameter name: Activation of non-TM9 UEs in CSI-RS sub-frames
Description: Activate non-TM9 UEs to be scheduled in CSI-RSI sub-frames.  If actCsiRsSubFNonTM9Sch is set to 'TRUE':  - Non-TM9 UEs receive transport blocks using lower MCSs in CSI-RS sub-frames compared to normal sub-frames.    If actCsiRsSubFNonTM9Sch is set to 'FALSE':  - Non-TM9 UEs do not receive data in CSI-RS sub-frames because CSI-RS degrade the quality of the transmission.    - TM7 UEs can not be scheduled in CSI-RS sub-frames if csiRsSubfrConf is not TDD specific rsc20, rsc21 nor rsc22.

Parameter name: Activate data session profiling
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Data Session Profiling'.

Parameter name: Activate delta CQI aging in SCell channel estimation
Description: This parameter activates the eNB deltaCQI aging during SCell channel quality estimation. When this parameter is set to 'true' and the SCell channel status is 'bad' or 'undetected', as the eNB continues its SCell channel quality estimation, if the deltaCQI saved from DL link adaptation is more negative than the target deltaCQI (deltaCqiTargetScellChEst), the eNB gradually decays that saved deltaCQI.

Parameter name: Activate channel quality monitoring for 256QAM usage
Description: This parameter activates the channel quality monitoring for 256QAM usage.  Please note that actDl256QamChQualEst must be configured if actModulationSchemeDl is set to '256QAM'. It must be either set to 'true' or 'false' dependent if quality estimation shall be activated or not.

Parameter name: Downlink interference shaping configuration - DL interference shaping active
Description: Determines if the interference shaping sub-functionality shall be active

Parameter name: Activate dynamic DL power backoff
Description: This parameter is the activation flag of the feature DL dynamic power back-off.

Parameter name: Activate DL Load adaptive PF algorithm for TD and FD scheduling steps
Description: Activation flag for CRL functionality that allows operator to specify different PF alpha values for low, mid and high SE users to enable weighting of users differently compared to legacy behavior which attempts to make allocations fair across time and frequency.

Parameter name: Activate DL OLDTC
Description: Switch to activate/deactivate Outer Loop Delay Target Control (OLDTC) for voice in downlink time domain scheduling.  OLDTC algorithm measures an actual scheduling delay of voice bearer in DL and compares it to a targeted delay. Then, if the measured delay is more than the target, UE priority is increased and in case the measured delay is below the target, the priority is decreased.

Parameter name: Activate DL voice packet aggregation
Description: Switch to activate/deactivate voice packet aggregation in downlink scheduler.

Parameter name: Activate down sampling
Description: This parameter activates down sampling of a cell.

Parameter name: Activate DRX
Description: Parameter to activate or deactivate the DRX feature in a cell.    Note for the case where periodic subband CQI reporting (periodicCqiFeedbackType) is enabled together with DRX functionality:  It may not be possible to synchronize DRX start offset such that the wideband CQI report is received during the DRX OnDuration (due to periodicities) and that may cause small performance degradation in DL whenever fresh wideband channel quality information cannot be get in time. It is up to an operator whether to prevent activation of periodic subband CQI reporting and DRX in parallel because of this restriction.    It is highly recommended to stay with DRX default values if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.

Parameter name: Activate DRX during measurement gap
Description: This parameter activates the feature DRX with parallel UE measurement gaps.  During measurement gaps, only drxProfile1, drxProfile2 or drxSmartProfile2 can be setup at the UE.    If the UE can't use DRX, then drxProfile1 is used.  Else if SmartDRX can't be used, then drxProfile2 is used else drxSmartProfile2 is used.

Parameter name: Activate DRX during TTI Bundling
Description: This parameter activates the feature DRX during TTI Bundling.  During TTI Bundling, onDurationTimer is set equal to longDRXCycle to keep UE always in active state.

Parameter name: Activate dynamic data session profile
Description: This parameter activates 'Load Based Dynamic Data Session Profiling'. The Data Session Profile feature must activated on the cell, and C-Plane overload handling must be activated before 'Load Based Dynamic Data Session Profiling' can be activated (i.e. MRBTS/LNBTS/LNCEL-actDataSessionProf must be 'true, and MRBTS/LNBTS-actCplaneOvlHandling must be 'true'').

Parameter name: Activate eDRX in idle mode
Description: Parameter to activate or deactivate extended DRX in idle mode in a cell.  BTS synchronization mode shall be set to PhaseSync or LoosePhaseAndTimeSync in order to have the correct feature functionality.    This activation parameter is applicable for both WB-LTE and NBIOT cell. For LTE-M there is a separate activation parameter.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced inter-cell interference coordination
Description: Activates the features eICIC for macro and small cells  It is recommended (but not required) to also enable feature LTE1617 RLF triggered Handover, when activating LTE1113 in the macro cell in order to allow RRC connection reestablishment without prepared context of small cell CRE UEs. This is useful for UEs located in high CRE values (higher than 6 dB) in the small cell eICIC partners.    Note: Features 'LTE1113: eICIC - macro' and 'LTE1496: eICIC - micro' are no longer supported and cannot be activated any more. Due to that, also all dependent features, i.e., 'LTE2208: eICIC enhancements - micro', 'LTE2209: eICIC enhancements - macro', 'LTE2133: eICIC for HetNet eNodeB configurations', 'LTE2125: eICIC Micro Enhancement for Carrier Aggregation Interworking', 'LTE3378: eICIC and eMBMS interworking support', and 'LTE3571: NB-IoT: Coexistence with eICIC', can no longer be activated/will not be active any longer.

Parameter name: Activate EIRP Control
Description: This parameter activates EIRP control on the LTE cell scope (For TDD massive MIMO, it is on cell segment level) and defines the EIRP (Effective Isotropic Radiated Power) control mode. With an EIRP reduction greater than 0 dB in place, the cell applies a reduction on the radiation that the cell generates in its coverage area. It is inevitable that this also causes a reduction of the cell's capacity, as the cell is allowed to use only a part of its DL resources on either time, power, or bandwidth dimension.    Only UE-specific LTE traffic is throttled down to meet the configured EIRP reduction level. HARQ repetitions and common channels (SIB, RACH) are not limited by this function. Also NB-IoT and CatM traffic are not limited by this function, i.e. they enjoy highest priority and therefore can cause severe service degradation in the remaining LTE downlink especially if they are configured with high numbers of PRBs / TTIs and/or power boosting. (Note: NB-IoT and CatM functions are for FDD only.)    The meaning of the values are as follows:  'disabled' means that the EIRP control function is disabled.  'nonBeamforming' means to enable the EIRP control in a non-beamforming cell. Currently this value is not used for TDD.  'Beamforming' means to enable the EIRP control in a cell which has beamforming capable. Currently this value is not used for FDD.    FDD only:  If an error is reported when trying to activate this feature then any or all of these parameters may need to be considered in order to achieve activation of EIRP Control (actEirpControl equal to 'nonBeamforming'):  eirpReduction,  for Slim Carrier and DSS features: actDlSlimCarrier, numBlankDlPrbsDown, numBlankDlPrbsUp,  for DSS features: actDynamicSharedSpectrum, lteNrDssMode, minNrDssRatio, actWcdmaLteSharedSpectrum  for MBMS: actMBMS, cellPwrRedForMBMS, maxSubfrPShare,  for NB-IoT: nbIoTMode, dlPwrBoost, numDlNonAnchCarrierNB,  for CatM: actCatM, numNarBandModeACatM

Parameter name: Activate load-based En-Dc blocking
Description: This parameter activates the support of load-based EN-DC blocking

Parameter name: Activate EN-DC-capability-based HO to preferred layer
Description: This parameter activates EN-DC capable handover to preferred frequency layer.    Preferred frequency layers can be specified in mobility profiles MO(D)PR in target frequency list freqLayEndcHoList.

Parameter name: Activate EN-DC MDT intra-frequency periodic measurement
Description: This parameter is used to activate and deactivate MDT (Minimization of Drive Tests) intra-frequency periodic measurements during EN-DC.  If activated, subscribers eligible for MDT will get intra-frequency LTE periodic measurements activated also during EN-DC.

Parameter name: Activate extended scheduling information for SIB24 in SIB1
Description: This parameter activates extended scheduling information for SIB24 in SIB1.  If extended scheduling information for SIB24 in SIB1 is activated, cell broadcasts SIB24 by using extended scheduling information schedulingInfoListExt-r12 in SIB1.  If extended scheduling information for SIB24 in SIB1 is deactivated, cell broadcasts SIB24 by using traditional scheduling information schedulingInfoList[without suffix] in SIB1.    Note:  'actExtSib1' is effective only when actSIB24 is 'true' and SIB24 is configured in sibSchedulingList in the cell.

Parameter name: Activate Fast PDCCH adaptation
Description: Specifies if Fast PDCCH Adaptation feature is enabled. The purpose of the feature is to quickly minimize the number of PDCCH symbols that are used per TTI so that the number of symbols available for data transmissions is maximized.

Parameter name: Activate flexible duplexing gap
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Flexible duplexing gap'. The feature is only applicable for FDD cells.    If activated non 3GPP compliant duplexing gaps can be configured. Downlink and uplink frequency must nevertheless belong to the same E-UTRA operating band as specified in 3GPP TS36.104.

Parameter name: Activate enhanced flow control
Description: This parameter activates Nokia proprietary mechanism for flow control between PCell and SCell(s). This flow control mechanism monitors the delay of the PCell and SCell(s) paths and dynamically adjusts the data flow over PCell and SCell(s).

Parameter name: Activate forced DRX S1 mobility to HeNB/CSG/HybridCell
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE3745, i.e. S1 based mobility to open access Home eNB, CSG and Hybrid cell

Parameter name: Activation flag of SRVCC to GSM measurement optimization
Description: This parameter activates SRVCC to GSM measurement optimization  This parameter is used for activating SRVCC to GSM measurement optimization.    If actGsmSrvccMeasOpt is set to  - 'true': LTE inter-freq measurements (e.g. A3/A4/A5/ReportStrongestCell/ReportCGI/etc.) are exclusive with IRAT SRVCC to GSM measurement (B2)  - 'false': LTE inter-freq measurements are allowed to run in parallel with IRAT SRVCC to GSM measurement.

Parameter name: Activate high altitude platform PRACH configuration
Description: This parameter indicates whether the high altitude platform PRACH configuration feature is activated.

Parameter name: Activate high altitude platform PRACH timing advance filter
Description: This parameter indicates whether the high altitude platform PRACH timing advance filter feature is activated.

Parameter name: Activate IMMCI support at TAU
Description: Support of IMMCI (Idle Mode Mobility Control Info) information element in RRC release messages as part of NAS TAU procedure.

Parameter name: Activate inactive time forwarding
Description: Enables the remaining inactive time functionality.

Parameter name: Activate increase of NR carriers for 3GPP non-compliant UEs
Description: This parameter activates the increase of NR measurement objects (carriers) for 3GPP non-compliant UEs (UE supports EN-DC but does not support extendedMaxMeasId-r12 capability) from currently maximum two up to maximum eight NR measurement objects for B1 for EN-DC purpose.

Parameter name: Activation of inter-frequency load balancing (iFLB)
Description: The parameter activates Inter- frequency load balancing (iF-LB) feature.  If the feature iF-LB is activated ("true"), inter-frequency load measurements are performed per cell. Dependent on the actual load situation UEs might be handovered to low loaded neighbor cells (different frequency layer).

Parameter name: Activate SPID-based IF HO
Description: This parameter activates the inter-frequency mobility based on a mobility profile a UE is assigned to.  UE is assigned to a mobility profile based on its subscriber profile ID (SPID) or any combination of SPID, PLMN-ID, UE's EN-DC capability.

Parameter name: Activation of intra-frequency load balancing
Description: If activated, the intra-frequency load balancing algorithm continuously estimates the cell load, triggering a handover threshold negotiation with the neighbors when the cell load is above a predefined value. The handover threshold negotiation procedure is done over the X2 interface to align the handover thresholds between neighbor cells.  If the feature is deactivated, the "cellIndOffNeighDelta" parameter is implicitly set to 0 in all LNREL objects.

Parameter name: Activate SPID based offload UE candidate selection
Description: The parameter activates SPID based offload UE candidate selection feature.    The parameter activates SPID based offload UE candidate selection in Connected Mode Load Balancing offload UE selection algorithm.  In the high load situation UEs might be handovered to low loaded neighbor cells (different frequency layer). UE selection for offload is prioritized according to operator defined SPID groups.

Parameter name: Activate load adaptive PDCCH
Description: Activate or deactivate the load adaptive number of PDCCH symbols in a cell  The actual OFDM symbol amount used for PDCCH in a TTI is selected from values between the minimum reasonable amount of symbols for the selected DL bandwidth and maximum allowed number of PDCCH symbols (maxNrSymPdcch).    Note for FDD cell:  If the bandwidth is set to '3 MHz'. it is recommended to set the parameter to 'false'.    Note for TDD cell:  Not every sub-frame need adaptive PDCCH symbol adjustment because not every sub-frame has PDSCH.

Parameter name: Activate maximum number of non-GBR UEs per TTI
Description: Activates functionality to restrict the number of non-GBR UEs scheduled per subframe. If enabled (parameter not equal 0) this parameter specifies the maximum number of first transmission non-GBR UEs that can be scheduled per subframe. Restricting the number of non-GBR UEs scheduled per TTI forces UEs to wait in the queue until their PF metric improves. When the UE is scheduled their RF conditions are typically better, and because the number of UEs scheduled is low the UE will get a larger, more spectrally efficient allocation. However limiting the number of non-GBR UEs scheduled per TTI can increase latency. If latency is a concern additional non-GBR UEs can be scheduled if the number of UEs in the scheduling queue exceeds lowLatencyAddlUeThreshold.    Note 1: When this parameter is enabled the scheduler uses exhaustive scheduling to schedule the non-GBR UEs.  Note 2: For FDD, the scheduler will stop scheduling more UEs in the current subframe when maxNumUeDl has been met, regardless of the values of actMaxNumUeDlNonGbr and maxNumUeDlNonGbrAddl.  Note3: For TDD, the scheduler will stop scheduling more UEs in normal subframes when maxNumUeDl has been met, and in special subframes when maxNumUeDlDwPts has been met, regardless of the values of actMaxNumUeDlNonGbr and maxNumUeDlNonGbrAddl.

Parameter name: Activate MCS upgrade
Description: Activates downlink MCS Upgrade functionality for non-GBR transmissions and specifies if the upgrades can increase the MCS index by one or two. The purpose of this function is to improve over the air spectral efficiency. Full RBG allocations (RAT0) are used for DL scheduling. This leads to spectrally inefficient allocations when a partial RBG is needed to drain a UE's buffer. For example in a 20 MHz system if 5 PRBs are required to drain a UE's buffer, an allocation of two RBGs is required, i.e. 8 PRBs. If MCS Upgrade is enabled, an MCS upgrade will be used so that an allocation of one full RBG (4 PRBs) can be used to drain the UE's buffer. MCS upgrades are only used to reduce a 3 RBG allocation to 2 RBGs or to reduce a 2 RBG allocation to 1 RBG. MCS upgrade is not applied to UEs that are being considered for MU MIMO pairing.    If this parameter is set to 0, downlink MCS upgrades are disabled.

Parameter name: Activate MFBI duplicate frequency delivery
Description: When this parameter is set to "TRUE", the eNB will send both the native and the overlapping band in the Idle Mode Mobility Control IE of RRCConnectionRelease with the same priority. If LTE2754 is not configured (frequency bands priority is not defined), then this parameter is not applicable and will have no effect

Parameter name: Activate eNode B power saving - Micro DTX
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'eNode B power saving - Micro DTX'. The feature is activated by default.  It is possible to reduce power consumption by having the power amplifiers associated with a cell shut down during OFDM symbol times that are not used for any DL transmission.

Parameter name: Micro DTX optimized muting patterns for DRX
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Optimized traffic concentration with 4ms DRX 'on' timer'. Some micro-DTX energy saving in the eNB is traded for more energy saving in the UEs. For micro-DTX using Flexi radios, the feature changes the muting patterns for low PRB usage against patterns with fewer muting occasions. This helps to have UEs running DRX with drxOnDuratT reduced to 4 ms, with reduced call drop rate.

Parameter name: Activate modulation scheme DL
Description: Selects the highest modulation scheme for link adaptation use in PDSCH.  If 64QAM is selected this includes also 16QAM and QPSK  If 256QAM is selected this includes also 64QAM, 16QAM and QPSK.  Please note that the LNCEL parameter actDl256QamChQualEst must be configured if 256QAM is selected. It must be either set to 'true' or 'false' dependent if quality estimation shall be activated or not.

Parameter name: Activate modulation scheme UL
Description: The parameter selects the highest order modulation scheme which is supported in the cell for UL transmissions .    Depending on the setting of actModulationSchemeUl the supported MCS range is determined for the UEs in the cell.    - QPSK: supported MCS range is from MCS0 to MCS10 for all UEs  - 16QAM: supported MCS range is from MCS0 to MCS20 for all UEs  - 16QAMHighMCS: supported MCS range is from MCS0 to MCS24 for all UEs  - 64QAM: supported MCS range is from MCS0 to MCS28 for UEs with 64QAM capability and from MCS0 to MCS20 for UEs without 64QAM capability  - 64QAMand16QAMHighMCS: supported MCS range is from MCS0 to MCS28 for UEs with 64QAM capability and from MCS0 to MCS24 for UEs without 64QAM capability.  - 256QAM: supported MCS range is from MCS0 to MCS28 for UEs with 64QAM and 256QAM capability and from MCS0 to MCS20 for UEs without 64QAM and 256QAM capability. supporting new modulation table for 256QAM capable UE.  - 256QAMand16QAMHighMCS: supported MCS range is from MCS0 to MCS28 for UEs with 64QAM and 256QAM capability and from MCS0 to MCS24 for UEs without 64QAM and 256QAM capability. supporting new modulation table for 256QAM capable UE.

Parameter name: Activate nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers
Description: Activates the feature 'Nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers

Parameter name: Activate support for excluded intra-band IF measurement
Description: For interfrequency load balancing neighbour frequencies within the same frequency band as the frequency of the own cell shall be excluded

Parameter name: Activate NR coverage based EN-DC anchor handover
Description: This parameter activates NR coverage based EN-DC anchor handover.

Parameter name: Activate outer loop link adaptation
Description: Activate / Deactivate Outer loop Link Adaptation for PDCCH  O&M switch for activating / deactivating an additional Outer Loop Link Adaptation for PDCCH. This additional PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation controls the PDCCH link adaptation CQI shift such that the PDCCH and HARQ Response Target BLER is achieved when the OLQC Target BLER is achieved.  If PDCCH OLLA is additionally based on PUSCH TX/DTX detection, PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation controls the PDCCH link adaptation CQI shift such that the PDCCH target BLER and PUSCH missed detection is achieved.  From SRAN20C onwards actOlLaPdcch must be set to 'true'.

Parameter name: PRS activation
Description: Activates the transmission of PRS signals according to the PRS configuration.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: Activate PDCCH QCI1 and SRB based control
Description: Parameter activates PDCCH controls for maximum Aggregation Level, default Aggregation Level and dynamic CQI shift for QCI1 and SRB.

Parameter name: Activation of periodical B1-NR measurements
Description: This parameter enables periodic activation/deactivation of B1-NR measurements used for dynamic triggering of LTE-NR Dual Connectivity or redirection to 5G SA. Timing of this functionality is controlled via configurable supervision and retry timers.  Parameter can be set to following values:  'disabled' - periodic B1-NR measurements functionality is turned off.  'basic' - supervision/retry cycle is started after measurements activation and remains active until reception of first measurement report for B1-NR measurements.  'enhanced' - supervision/retry cycle is started after measurements activation and remains active as long as conditions for measurements activation are still satisfied (e.g. until EN-DC establishment).

Parameter name: Activate periodical 5GSA redirection
Description: Activate periodical 5GSA redirection

Parameter name: Activate proactive scheduling by SRB
Description: The parameter activates proactive UL scheduling triggered by SRB traffic in DL. This means that the UL Candidate Set 3 is extended by UEs with active SRB.

Parameter name: Activate providing NRCGI for EN-DC
Description: This parameter activates the function of providing NRCGI for each NR PSCell candidate in cgi-info in X2AP: SgNB Addition Request message during the blind or/and measurement-based dynamic triggering of EN-DC setup.

Parameter name: PRS Tx diversity activation
Description: If Tx Diversity is enabled for PRS transmission, then precoding vector switching will be used and therefore all configured Tx antennas will be used for the transmission of the PRS signal. If Tx diversity is disabled then the PRS signal will just be transmitted on a single antenna (the physical antenna corresponding to antenna port {0}).

Parameter name: Activate (non)-mission-critical PushToTalk overbooking
Description: This parameter activates the (Non)-Mission-critical PushToTalk Overbooking feature.

Parameter name: Activate PUSCH PRB Distribution
Description: Enables PUSCH PRB allocations to be distributed more uniformly across the bandwidth when Channel Aware Scheduling (CAS) or Interference Aware Scheduling (IAS) is used. This feature smooths out UL noise peaks.

Parameter name: Activate PUSCH PRB distribution enhancement
Description: This parameter is the activation flag for the PUSCH PRB selection enhancement algorithm.

Parameter name: Activate BLER Targets and Max HARQ  for QCI1
Description: Activates the use of target BLER and maximum HARQ attempts for QCI1. When activated, QCI1 specific parameters for UL and DL BLER/HARQ attempts within the qci1UlBlerTgtConfig structure are used.    Notes regarding interaction between parameters associated with actQci1BlerTgt and similar parameters associated with eVTT:  - If actQci1eVTT='true' AND actQci1BlerTgt='false', then parameters within structure qci1eVTTConfig are applied.  - If actQci1eVTT='true' AND actQci1BlerTgt='true', then parameters within structure qci1BlerTgtConfig are applied.  - If actQci1eVTT='false' AND actQci1BlerTgt='true', then parameters within structure qci1BlerTgtConfig are applied.  - If actQci1eVTT=false' AND actQci1BlerTgt='false', then parameters common to all QCIs are applied.

Parameter name: Activate RF-based disabling of DRX for VoLTE Ues
Description: This parameter activates the RF-based disabling of DRX for VoLTE UEs (QCI1 bearer configured) in poor radio conditions.

Parameter name: Activate extended VoLTE talk time
Description: Activates the feature 'Extended VoLTE talk time'

Parameter name: Activate recommended bit rate
Description: Activates the feature LTE4244 "VoLTE coverage extension by codec rate adaptation" using recommended bit rate mechanism.

Parameter name: Activate reduced format
Description: This parameter activates the usage of the reduced format to receive E-UTRA UE capabilities.

Parameter name: Active requesting fallback CA band comb. with different radio capabilities in UE CA capability signaling.
Description: Activates the feature 'UE CA capability signalling - different fallbacks', which allows the eNode B to retrieve from a UE the fallback CA band combinations with different radio capabilities than the parent combination. A UE is requested by the eNB to indicate the fallback CA band combinations only for the explicit list of CA combinations.

Parameter name: Activation of Resource Allocation Type 1
Description: This parameter activates allocation of DL resources with PRB granularity using Resource Allocation Type 1 (RAT1).

Parameter name: Activate return of 5G SA
Description: This parameter activates redirection of 5G capable UE to a predefined 5G carrier at the end of voice calls or non-emergency voice calls or RRC connections based on the setting of the parameter:    0: disabled  -- no redirection to 5G  1: at end of voice calls  -- fast redirection at the end of voice and emergency voice calls only  2: at end of non-emerg voice calls  -- fast redirection at the end of non-emergency voice calls only  3: at end of RRC or voice calls  -- fast redirection at the end of voice and emergency voice calls and at the end of RRC connections  4: at end of non-emerg RRC or non-emerg voice  -- fast redirection at the end of non-emergency voice calls and at the end of non-emergency RRC connections  5: at end of non-emerg RRC connection  -- redirection of all non-emergency connections at the end of RRC connection    Note: redirection at the end of voice call in this context means, at the last QCI1 bearer release.
Range and step: disabled (0), at end of voice calls (1), at end of non-emerg voice calls (2), at end of RRC or voice calls (3), at end of non-emerg RRC or non-emerg voice (4), at end of non-emerg RRC connection (5)

Parameter name: Activate forwarding of elapsed time of prohibit timer for RRC Connection Release
Description: This parameter enables prohibit timer for RRC connection release with mobility feature.    This feature enhances Prohibit timer for RRC connection release after last QCI1 bearer release to work in all intra-LTE handover scenarios. Prohibit timer for RRC connection release after last QCI1 bearer release and inactivity timer forwarding can be activated at the same time in the same cell.    All coverage, service and load-based handover, including Pcell Swap, are in the scope:  - intra-eNode B, intra-frequency handover  - intra-eNode B, inter-frequency handover  - inter-eNode B, intra-frequency handover via X2  - inter-eNode B, inter-frequency handover via X2  - inter-eNode B, intra-frequency handover via S1  - inter-eNode B, inter-frequency handover via S1    RRC re-establishment, RLF triggered handover, forced service-based handover are not in the scope. When any intra-LTE handover is performed and qci1RrcRelDelayTimer is running, the source cell transfers to the target cell the elapsed time since qci1RrcRelDelayTimer has started. The UE RRC connection will be maintained for at least qci1RrcRelDelayTimer minus the transferred time duration. In this way, qci1RrcRelDelayTimer can start in the source cell and expire in the target cell.    The elapsed time is provided by the source to the target cell via private IEs in X2AP and S1AP interfaces.    This feature is FDD and TDD WB only functionality. Not supported by Cat-M.

Parameter name: Activate Extended Monitoring for SCell Bad Channel Quality
Description: This parameter determines whether a SCell with poor RF is released or moved to an extended channel quality monitoring state, per CRL-26379.    A value of 'false' releases the SCell with 'bad channel quality', per existing behavior. A value of 'true' activates the CRL. When active, first 'bad channel quality' estimation sends SCell into an extended channel quality 'monitoring' state. DL scheduling on SCell is stopped, but SCell is kept active to obtain CQI for use in continuing evaluation of SCell channel quality. SCell is returned to normal active state if a 'good channel quality' estimation is obtained.

Parameter name: Activate SCell configuration for high demand UEs
Description: This parameter activates the SCell configuration for high demand UEs if numTxWithHighNonGbr is greater than 0 in this eNB. When activated, if a DL non-GBR data buffer overflow trigger for SCell addition occurs, the eNB checks that the DL non-GBR data buffer depth for the UE is sufficiently large before triggering the SCell configuration procedure. This parameter is applicable only in cells configured as PCells.

Parameter name: Activate QCIx service-based HO
Description: This parameter activates QCIx service-based handover on cell level.    Note: Additionally to this LNCEL-level activation (LNCEL-actServBasedHoQciX equal to 'true'), the respective QCIx must be enabled for the service-based HO on LNBTS level (LNBTS-qciTabX-servBasedHoAllowed = 'allowed').

Parameter name: Activate serving radio link qualification with load balancing
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Serving radio link qualification with load balancing - I'.

Parameter name: Activate support for up to six Inter-freq measurement
Description: The parameter allow to extend the number of interfrequency measurements from 3 to 6

Parameter name: Activate smart DRX
Description: Parameter to activate/deactivate the Smart DRX feature in a cell.

Parameter name: Activate spatial PUCCH bundling
Description: This parameter activates the spatial PUCCH bundling according to 3GPP Release 13.  It applies only to UEs configured with more than 5 serving cells.    - If set to 'true', and if UE's transmission mode indicates it will transmit two code words in the cell, then binary AND operation is applied for the two HARQ-ACK bits corresponding to the first and second code words. The spatial-bundled 1 HARQ-ACK bit is concatenated with HARQ-ACK bits of other serving cells and reported to the eNB on PUCCH. For a UE configured with more than 5 serving cells and PUCCH format 3 (not configured with PUCCH format 4/5) when the UE simultaneously reports periodic CSI and HARQ-ACK and/or SR on PUCCH at the same TTI, setting the parameter to 'true' can protect total volume of UCI from exceeding 22 bits without need for downlink 'scheduling avoidance' on all SCells. Note, that if the UE's downlink air condition is not good, e.g., RSRP is low, the 'true' setting can cause the downlink throughput degradation.  - If set to 'false', and if UE's transmission mode indicates it will transmit two code words in the cell, then binary AND operation is not applied for the two HARQ-ACK bits corresponding to the first and second code words. The original 2 HARQ-ACK bits are concatenated with HARQ-ACK bits of other serving cells and reported to the eNB on PUCCH. For a UE configured with more than 5 serving cells and PUCCH format 3 (not configured with PUCCH format 4/5), the 'false' setting allows the downlink 'scheduling avoidance' on all SCells for the UE, when the UE is expected to simultaneously report periodic CSI and HARQ-ACK and/or SR on PUCCH at the same TTI and the total number of UCI bits exceeds 22.    Please refer to Section 5.2.3 of TS 36.212 for the details of the channel coding for uplink control information on PUCCH.

Parameter name: Activate SRB1 robustness
Description: Activate RRC Signaling Robustness in downlink and uplink

Parameter name: Activate TA-based disconnect
Description: This parameter activates the feature "RRC disconnect based on timing advance limits".

Parameter name: Activate TCP Service Differentiation
Description: This parameter activates TCP Service Differentiation functionality.

Parameter name: Activate TCP UL Power Boost
Description: This parameter activates a power boost to UL TCP for non-power limited UEs and applies only if UL TCP Boosting is enabled.

Parameter name: Activate TTI bundling
Description: Parameter to activate or deactivate the TTI Bundling feature in a cell.    Please note that UEs in TTI bundling mode will typically use higher PDCCH aggregation levels. Cell capacity can most likely be limited by PDCCH capacity. This is especially relevant in case of cells with 3 MHz bandwidth.

Parameter name: Activate ACQI reporting for TTI bundled UEs
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates Aperiodic CQI reporting for UEs in TTI bundling mode

Parameter name: Activate adaptive UL min TBS for TTI Bundling
Description: When this parameter is set to 'true', the adaptive UL minTBS(t) is used for link adaptation when UE has QCI1 bearer and is in TTI bundling. UL minTBS(t) is calculated based on the measured UL PDCP PDU size of voice packets and the value of the parameter ttibUlsMaxPacketSeg.

Parameter name: Activate RSC Measurements during TTI bundling
Description: Parameter to activate RSC (Report Strongest Cell) measurements when TTI Bundling is active. RSC measurements are disabled if parameter is set to false.  This parameter is applicable only if TTI Bundling feature is enabled (actTtiBundling).

Parameter name: Activate UCA antenna with 8T8R
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates UCA antenna with 8T8R.    The parameter value shall be the same in all cells connected to the same radio unit, that means in all LNCEL and NRCELL instances.

Parameter name: Activate UE uplink power based mobility thresholds
Description: This parameter activates the features 'High power UE specific mobility thresholds' and activates a mechanism for different points of triggering handover for high power UE.  Dedicated power based thresholds are used for measurements when UE is identified with high power capability in uplink.  Note: Configuration of dedicated thresholds is not dependent on this feature being enabled.

Parameter name: Activate channel quality monitoring for 256QAM UL usage
Description: This parameter activates the channel quality monitoring for 256QAM UL usage.  Please note that actUl256QamChQualEst must be configured if actModulationSchemeUl is set to '256QAM' or '256QAMand16QAMHighMCS'. It must be either set to 'true' or 'false' dependent if quality estimation shall be activated or not.

Parameter name: Activate uplink dynamic target BLER
Description: This parameter activates uplink dynamic target BLER for nonGBR traffic.  If set to 'true', target BLER for uplink nonGBR traffic is adapted based on UE channel conditions instead of using a static target BLER as defined by ulTargetBler.

Parameter name: Activation of uplink group hopping
Description: Activates uplink group hopping in PUSCH and PUCCH.

Parameter name: Activate uplink link adaptation
Description: Activates Uplink Link Adaptation and defines Link Adaptation mode  When set to "off" no Uplink link Adaptation function is active at all.  When set to "eUlLa" the extended Uplink Link Adaptation function is activated.  When set to "fUlLa" the new Fast Uplink Link Adaptation function is activated.  The other choice "slowAmcOllaATB" allows to set to active all the 3 old components of the UL LA function as it was up to RL20.

Parameter name: Activate variance driven UL adaptation
Description: Activation flag for variance driven MCS/BLER UL adaptation. This can be activated only when Fast Uplink Link Adaptation function is activated. This functionality does not apply for Cat-M UEs.

Parameter name: Method for UL power control
Description: Selects a working mode for UL power control. Offers various combinations between open-loop and closed-loop control for PUCCH and PUSCH/SRS power.  values:  PuschOLPucchOL: PUSCH open loop, PUCCH open loop;  PuschOLPucchCL: PUSCH open loop, PUCCH closed loop;  PuschCLPucchOL: PUSCH closed loop, PUCCH open loop;  PuschCLPucchCL: PUSCH closed loop, PUCCH closed loop;  PuschCLSrsPucchOL: PUSCH closed loop with SRS input, PUCCH open loop; PuschCLSrsPucchCL: PUSCH closed loop with SRS input, PUCCH closed loop; PuschIAwPucchOL: PUSCH interference-aware, PUCCH open loop;  PuschIAwPucchCL: PUSCH interference-aware, PUCCH closed loop.
Range and step: PuschOLPucchOL (0), PuschOLPucchCL (1), PuschCLPucchOL (2), PuschCLPucchCL (3), PuschCLSrsPucchOL (4), PuschCLSrsPucchCL (5), PuschIAwPucchOL (6), PuschIAwPucchCL (7)

Parameter name: Activate RACH preamble power control
Description: Activates the dynamic RACH preamble power control feature.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Activate UL Load adaptive PF algorithm for TD and FD scheduling steps
Description: Activation flag for CRL functionality that allows operator to specify different PF alpha values for low, mid and high SE users to enable weighting of users differently compared to legacy behavior which attempts to make allocations fair across time and frequency.

Parameter name: Activate Uplink Scheduling for Optimized PRB / MCS Allocations
Description: Activates functionality which optimizes the uplink MCS / PRB allocation that will be assigned to UEs in poor R.F. When enabled, ulsOptimizePrbMinMcs specifies the minimum target MCS that once reached the scheduler will stop decreasing the MCS and instead will decrease the maximum number of PRBs allowed for the UE. Once the maximum number of PRBs allowed for the UE reaches the minimum as specified by ulsMinRbPerUE for data UEs and ulsMinRbNonTtibVolte for non-TTI bundling VoLTE UEs the scheduler will ensure a minimum MCS derived from the minimum TBS parameter ulMinTbs for data UEs and ulsMinTbsNonTtibVolte for non-TTI bundling VoLTE UEs.    Note that when actUlsOptimizePrbMcs = False, the existing functionality associated with ulsMinRbPerUE and ulMinTbs is used for both data and non-TTI bundling VoLTE UEs. When actUlsOptimizePrbMcs = True, ulsMinRbPerUE and ulMinTbs are only used for data UEs, while ulsMinRbNonTtibVolte and ulsMinTbsNonTtibVolte are used for non-TTI bundling VoLTE UEs.

Parameter name: Activate VoLTE source rate based UL assignment
Description: This parameter activates LTE2774 'Source rate based UL grant assignment for VoLTE'.

Parameter name: Activation of VoIP coverage boosting in UL scheduling
Description: Activates VoIP coverage boosting in UL scheduling, feature LTE2098 "VoLTE uplink coverage boosting".

Parameter name: Activates VoLTE coverage boosting improvements
Description: Activates "VoLTE coverage boosting improvements":  - Revert the CR13343  - make PHR based entry to TTIB configurable,  - remove QPSK condition from TTIB entry,  - configure TTIB retention times,  - restrict the initial #PRBs after boosting is left,  - re-use min delay after QCI1 bearer setup,  - Introduce a new VLDR codec of up to 8 kbps.

Parameter name: Adapt maxNumUEConn
Description: This parameter indicates whether the PUCCH algorithm is allowed to increase the value of parameter maxNumUEConn

Parameter name: Adaptive PDCCH symbol decrease dwell time
Description: This parameter determines the minimum time the criteria to decrease the number of PDCCH OFDM symbols must be met in order to decrease the number of PDCCH OFDM symbols.

Parameter name: Add GBR-DRB traffic for radio reason handover
Description: Additional margin on the threshold "maxGbrTrafficLimit" in case of handover for radio reasons.  The amount of radio resources (PRBs) is calculated in % of the available PRBs depending on the system.  1.4 MHz = 6 DL PRBS*,  3.0 MHz = 15 DL PRBS*,  For 5 MHz system 25 PRBs*,  for 10 MHz system 50 PRBs*,  for 15 MHz system 75 PRBs*,  for 20 MHz system 100 PRBs* are available.  * reduced by common resources like PUCCH, RACCH, PDCCH, SIBs and so on, which can consume some PRBs (for example three PRBs) in average.    The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to True and ignored otherwise.    The "addGbrTrafficRrHo" parameter should be configured significantly lower than the "maxGbrTrafficLimit" parameter to reduce admitting handover traffic and preempting other low prior traffic immediately with next cell local admission requests.

Parameter name: Add GBR-DRB traffic for time critical reason handover
Description: Additional margin on the threshold "maxGbrTrafficLimit " in case of handover for time critical reasons.  The amount of radio resources (PRBs) is calculated in % of the available PRBs depending on the system.  1.4 MHz = 6 DL PRBS*,  3.0 MHz = 15 DL PRBS*,  For 5 MHz system 25 PRBs*,  for 10 MHz system 50 PRBs*,  for 15 MHz system 75 PRBs*,  for 20 MHz system 100 PRBs* are available.  * reduced by common resources like PUCCH, RACCH, PDCCH, SIBs and so on, which can consume some PRBs (for example three PRBs) in average.    The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to True and ignored otherwise.    The "addGbrTrafficTcHo" parameter should be configured significantly lower than the parameter maxGbrTrafficLimit to reduce admitting handover traffic and preempting other low prior traffic immediately with next cell local admission requests.

Parameter name: Additional spectrum emission mask
Description: The additional spectrum emission mask parameter is broadcast into a cell to indicate that the UE should meet an additional requirement.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UEs and Cat-M UEs.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Administrative state
Description: Administrative state of the cell, the value is set by the operator.  Note: This parameter used for NB-IoT standalone cell, but not directly used for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: 5GSA redirection enabler at the end of RRC connection
Description: 5GSA redirection enabler at the end of RRC connection    Currently, this parameter indicates if 5GSA redirection for 5G capable UE can be triggered when RRC connection is released due to "user inactivity". eNB does not support 5GSA redirection at the end of RRC connection yet, so eNB ignores the setting of this parameter.

Parameter name: 5GSA redirection enabler for emergency call
Description: 5GSA redirection enabler for emergency call    In case UE ever made emergency call, after it is completed, there may be a call back. This parameter allows operator to forbid 5GSA redirection for UE made an emergency call and keep the UE in LTE waiting for call back after emergency call (i.e. setting this parameter to 'false').    Currently, eNB always disallows 5GSA redirection for emergency call, so eNB ignores the setting of this parameter.

Parameter name: Allow cell specific PB ratio zero
Description: The cell specific PDSCH EPRE ratio to the cell RS EPRE (PB) can be set to zero.  If allowPbIndexZero is set to 'false' and dlRsBoost is equal to 0dB, then index 1 is chosen for pbIndexPdsch (instead of index 0)  (see 36.312 / Table 5.2-1).  It's for backward compatibility with legacy releases

Parameter name: Allow traffic concentration
Description: This parameter defines if Traffic Concentration is allowed for the cell while micro-DTX is activated. Traffic Concentration means that PDSCH traffic is held back in certain selected subframes (defined in internal muting patterns) in order to allow the RF unit to power down its main amplifier, for energy saving.  In FDD cells, allowTrafficConcentration is ignored if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Altitude
Description: Altitude in meters (coded value)  Relation between coded Altitude N and range of absolute altitudes a (a >= 0 meters) it encodes is the following:    for 0 <= N <= 2^15-2:  N <= a < N+1    for N = 2^15-1:  a >= 2^15-1    According to above relation an encoded value N corresponds to a range of absolute altitudes a in meters

Parameter name: AM RLC SN field length for downlink
Description: This parameter configures the length of the SN field for RLC AM procedures in downlink direction.  In case of carrier aggregation, the SN field for RLC AM procedures in downlink direction is derived from the amRlcSnFieldLengthDl parameter setting in the PCell.  In case of inter-site carrier aggregation, if amRlcSnFieldLengthDl in the PCell is set to '16bit' and peer eNB hosting SCells doesn't support 16 bits then those SCells will not be considered as SCell candidates

Parameter name: Max number of AMLE-based HOs between two CAC updates
Description: This parameter describes how many active mode load equalization handovers per partner neighbor cell are allowed between two CAC reports received from this cell.

Parameter name: X2 resource status update periodicity for AMLE
Description: This timer defines the periodicity according which neighbor cells are requested to report their available resource status.

Parameter name: AMLE serving cell RSRP threshold filter
Description: Serving cell RSRP threshold for filtering for AMLE consideration.

Parameter name: AMLE serving cell RSRQ threshold filter
Description: Serving cell RSRQ threshold for filtering for AMLE consideration.

Parameter name: Downlink interference shaping configuration - Amount of blanked resources
Description: Determines the amount of resources to be blanked for PDSCH scheduling of UE specific transmissions.  Given percentage will be rounded to the next larger integer multiple of the system bandwidth dependent allocation granularity on PDSCH (resource block group size for resource allocation type 0). Position of resources to be blanked is derived dynamically.  Value "0" disables the PDSCH blanking sub-functionality.

Parameter name: Tilt angle
Description: Antenna element electrical tilt angle.

Parameter name: Antenna bearing for AoA calculation
Description: This parameter describes the antenna normal direction with respect to geographical north in 0.1 degrees clockwise, i.e. from North to East. It is used for Angle-of-Arrival (AoA) calculation for LTE1501 and LTE951 and also used for Left & Right Boundary Angle for LTE2462.

Parameter name: Antenna Element Spacing for AoA Calculation
Description: This parameter defines the spacing between the antenna elements and is necessary for AoA calculation.

Parameter name: Antenna Gain for Non Beamforming
Description: The antenna gain in the main lobe for a cell that does not use beamforming antennas. The configured value has to include antenna feeder losses and depends on antenna tilt angle.  For combined supercells (LTE2445), antGainNonBF must be set such that the highest resulting EIRP value in the coverage area is calculated in LTE4972, even if the configured value is not found in any of the existing antennas.    Example (combined supercell):  Tx1: transmit power = 20 dBm, antenna gain = 3 dB (EIRP = 23 dBm)  Tx2: transmit power = 18 dBm, antenna gain = 7 dB (EIRP = 25 dBm)    LTE4972 calculates the point of zero EIRP restrictions from highest pMax and the single antGainNonBF value. antGainNonBF must be set to 5 dB so that LTE4972 calculates EIRP reductions downward from 25 dBm as a result from 20 dBm + 5 dB.    The configured value of antGainNonBF may need to be updated whenever the antenna tilt angle (LTE160 Flexi BTS 3GPP Antenna Tilt Support) is changed.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Antenna gain
Description: Antenna gain

Parameter name: Antenna orientation
Description: This parameter defines antenna orientation.

Parameter name: Apply FeICIC functionality
Description: This parameter determines whether an eICIC R11 related CIO shall be applied or not. It is required to set this parameter to the same value in all cells (macro & small cells) between which an eICIC partnership is or shall be established, i.e., within an eICIC area.  applyFeicicFunctionality = 'true': Setting of parameter eIcicMaxCre defines the maximum CIO value for R11 UEs in all small cell eICIC partners. This setting is recommended for operators intending to deploy NOKIA Networks equipped HetNets.    applyFeicicFunctionality = 'false': Setting of parameter eIcicMaxCre defines the maximum CIO value for all UEs in all small cell eICIC partners. This setting is recommended for operators intending to deploy HetNets with macro eNB and small cell eNBs from different vendors.

Parameter name: ARP based parameters - ARP priority level
Description: ARP priority level.  The range of the ARP priority level is 1 to 15 with 1 as the highest level of priority.

Parameter name: Instance ID of the assigned ARPPR profile
Description: This parameter specifies the instance ID of the assigned ARPPR profile.

Parameter name: Total number of RA preambles
Description: Total number of RA preambles a UE can select assigned by system in case actOptRootSeq is set different to 'none'.

Parameter name: Assigned number of RA preambles for Cat-M CE level 0
Description: Defines the size of the Random Access preambles Group A assigned by system in case actOptRootSeq is set different to 'none'.

Parameter name: Assigned VoLTE quality profile
Description: Instance ID of the assigned VoLTE quality profile (VOLTEQUALPR)

Parameter name: Blacklisted cell for intra and inter freq HO list
Description: This is a list of blacklisted intra-frequency and inter-frequency neighbouring cells for active mode mobility. Cells are identified by their PCI.

Parameter name: Blacklisted topologies
Description: This parameter is introduced to allow blacklisting for X2-Handover only other HO variants are still allowed  If set to "all" the respective entry in blacklistHoL is valid for all kinds of Handover Topology. If set to "onlyX2", handover to the respective entry in blacklistHoL shall only be excluded as targets for X2-based handover but may still be used as target for S1 based handover.    This parameter is only evaluated for inter eNodeB target cells which can be used as target for X2-Handover as well as for S1-Handover

Parameter name: eUTRA carrier frequency
Description: It is used to specify the eUTRA Frequency (max value refer to 36.331)  This parameter must be configured for a inter frequency cell. It will be taken as a intra frequency cell if this parameter is set to ownCarrierFreq.

Parameter name: Range of physical cell id range
Description: Indicates the number of PCIs in the range (including startPCI). If Parameter rangePCI is only one, PCI (startPCI) is specified.

Parameter name: Start of physical cell id range
Description: Indicates the lowest PCI in the range

Parameter name: Blocking state
Description: This parameter describes the blocking state of the cell. The value is set by the system.

Parameter name: TCP Service Differentiation Configuration - Boost guard time
Description: This parameter defines the maximum amount of time traffic boosting can be applied to a bearer carrying TCP traffic.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation pool ID
Description: This parameter defines which PCells and SCells in carrier aggregation shall belong to the same C-RNTI group, if the feature "Flexible carrier aggregation management" is de-activated.    In case of LNCEL creation the BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.  In any case all cells with the same caPoolId will be temporarily dropped.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - Cell capacity class value
Description: This parameter provides the value that classifies the cell capacity relative to other types of cells in the network, in particular neighbor cells for load balancing and cells which are members of the same power-saving group. The Cell Capacity Class Value only indicates the relative weight of those resources that are available for LTE PDSCH.  Set this parameter to 100 for the most capable cell type in the network, for example the cells with 20 MHz, 40 W, 4x4 DL MIMO. Set this parameter to lower values for cells with lower capabilities, e.g. 50 for cells with 10 MHz and otherwise same capability. From there, reduce the values further for cells which have DL PRB usage outside LTE PDSCH, such as MBMS, CatM, NB-IoT, DSS. Also reduce cellCapClass for TDD cells, to reflect the configured UL/DL ratio.  Reduce the value also if the cell has EIRP control activated and its eirpReduction value is set to a value bigger than 0.  For power-saving groups (LTE1103 / LTE1203 / SR003080) the sum of cellCapClass values of the active member cells serves to evaluate the capacity of the PSGRP before and after shutdown or switch-on of a cell. In the calculations, cells in reducedEnergySaving state (from LTE1203 / SR003080) have their cellCapClass reduced by a factor of lbpsRTXCellCapOffset.

Parameter name: Cell individual offset of own serving cells PCI
Description: Cell Individual Offset (CIO) of own served cell for insertion into the CIO Cell List of EUTRA Serving Carrier Measurement Object  Only if CIO is different from zero, will the eNB consider it for Measurement Configuration.

Parameter name: Cell name
Description: This parameter allows the operator to give a cell a name.    The range represents the number of bytes to store all the characters of the string. If the string is UTF-8 encoded, each character occupies between 1 to 4 bytes, depending upon the language. If ASCII encoded, each character occupies a single byte. The numbers of characters supported in case of UTF-8 encoding is at least 20.  Cell name is just a text string and may have any value.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Cell power reduction for MBMS transmission
Description: This parameter is used to set the power for MBSFN transmission together with antenna maximum TX power and cell power reduction (pMax, dlCellPwrRed).  The total power of MBSFN sub-frames would be cell maximum power - cell power reduction - cell power reduction for MBMS, or pMax - dlCellPwrRed - cellPwrRedForMBMS.    Note that when defining the values for the pmax-dlCellPwrRed - cellPwrRedForMBMS relationship assume that average transmitted energy (averaged radio module output power) should not go under 25 dBm.

Parameter name: Cell reset requested
Description: Reset request for Cell  Will be downloaded with current timestamp to indicated reset request, new request will receive new timestamp and therefore cause parameter change.  Cell reset will be executed automatically, since parameter change requires cell lock/unlock.  String is in human readable format, e.g.  Cell reset requested : YYYYMMDD hhnnss  where YYYYMMDD hhnnss is timestamp.

Parameter name: Assigned cell resource group profile
Description: Identifier of the cell resource group profile (CRGPR) instance which shall apply for the cell.

Parameter name: Cell resource group SCell mode
Description: This parameter enables/disables the function to use in SCell the default cell resource group (CRG) in case the CA requesting UE (CA guest UE) has no SPID assigned or a SPID, which does not match with any CRG in SCell. It is only relevant for SPID-based CRG inter-working with carrier aggregation.  The default behavior is that, if the CA requesting UE has no SPID or a non-matching SPID, but in the SCell SPID-based CRG is configured, the SCell addition request is rejected as the default CRG may not be used.  For PLMN ID-based CRG function this parameter is not relevant.

Parameter name: Cell resource sharing mode
Description: The parameter activates the features LTE1382 'Cell resource groups', CB007303 'CRG Selective TTI Donation', CB011120 'CRG selective TTI donation enhancement', CB011141 'CRG selective TTI donation - TDD' and selects the resource sharing mode.  The features allow pre-reservation of cell resources in admission control per PLMN group or SPID. PLMN-based or SPID-based cell-resource sharing is selected with the cellResourceSharingType parameter.    The parameter value 'selectiveTtiDonate' activates CB007303 (FDD) / CB011141(TDD).  The parameter value 'selectiveTtiDonateEnh' activates CB011120 (FDD only).  The parameter value 'selectiveTtiDonateDlOnly' activates CB011141(TDD only).    If cellResourceSharingMode is set to 'selectiveTtiDonate' or 'selectiveTtiDonateEnh'  - the feature operates in DL and UL  - groupShare controls only resources assigned by Radio Admission Control, not TTI assignments by DL/UL schedulers  - TTI assignments by UL/DL schedulers are controlled by CRG-specific parameters minTtiShare, maxTtiShare, and selectiveSkipThreshold.    If cellResourceSharingMode is set to 'selectiveTtiDonateDlOnly',  - the feature operates in DL only  - groupShare controls only resources assigned by Radio Admission Control, not TTI assignments by DL schedulers  - TTI assignments by DL schedulers are controlled by CRG-specific parameters minTtiShare, maxTtiShare, and selectiveSkipThreshold.
Range and step: none (0), DLonly (1), DLandUL (2), selectiveTtiDonate (3), selectiveTtiDonateEnh (4), selectiveTtiDonateDlOnly (5)

Parameter name: Cell technology
Description: This parameter identifies of the LNCEL instance shall be used as FDD or TDD or NB-IoT cell. Dependent on the configuration of the technology, subordinated classes to the LNCEL have to be configured.    Note.  For cells allocated on any variant of AirScale ABIP/ABIQ or Airscale ASOG/ASOH capacity board this parameter must not be set to value 'TDD'.

Parameter name: Cell type
Description: This parameter allows the operator to specify the size of an LTE cell.    This parameter is used for preparing the UE History IE during an outgoing handover, according to LTE1768.    It will be also considered  if the feature LTE1140 'Intra-frequency load balancing' is activated for deriving the corresponding cellBeta co-efficient.  if the features LTE1113/1496 'eICIC macro'/'eICIC micro' are activated (when eICIC is enabled, macro cell should use 'large', micro cell should use 'very small', 'small' and 'medium').  if the feature LTE1768 'Mobility robustness optimization ping-pong' is activated (CellType is included in the UE History IE when preparing a X2 handover).  if the feature LTE1800 'Downlink interference shaping' is activated (when DL Interference shaping is enabled, macro cell should use 'large', micro cell should use 'very small', 'small' and 'medium').

Parameter name: Commercial Mobile Alert System paging period
Description: The parameter defines the paging period which is used by eNB to send CMAS indication.    If CB007456 feature is enabled and SIB24 is configured to be broadcasted, eNB shall keep the implementation of CB007456 feature to use one Modification Period as CMAS paging period.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Confidence
Description: Confidence by which the position is known to be within the shape description expressed as a percentage  Confidence = 0 means no information available

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Enable aperiodic CQI reporting on PUSCH
Description: O&M switch for enabling / disabling aperiodic CQI / RI / PMI reporting on PUSCH.

Parameter name: Aperiodic CQI feedback reporting mode
Description: Corresponds to cqi-ReportingModeAperiodic of 3GPP-36.213. CQI format indicator for aperiodic reporting on PUSCH. The operator can choose one of the 2 family modes available, the MIMO algorithm embedded in RRM chooses the effective mode based on the UE capabilities and the family mode chosen by the operator and forwards this to UE; FTB1 selects the reporting mode 2.x, FTB2 selects the reporting mode 3.x; x is determined by the MIMO algorithm internal in eNB.

Parameter name: Periodic CQI subbands cycles
