Description: Periodic subband CQI cycles K.  Between consecutive periodic wideband CQI reporting occurrences each subband CQI report might be transmitted as many times as the parameter shows.

Parameter name: Enable simultaneous CQI and ACK/NACK
Description: O&M switch for enabling / disabling simultaneous transmission of periodic CQI / RI / PMI feedback and HARQ ACK/NACK on PUCCH.

Parameter name: Averaging filter constant for CRE tagging
Description: Averaging filter constant for averaging CQI reports sent by UE used for cell range expansion (CRE) tagging for ABS and non-ABS subframes.

Parameter name: Closed Subscriber Group type
Description: This parameter enables the CSG (Closed Subscriber Group) functionality for the cell.  A value of 'openAccess' means that the cell is not a CSG cell.  A value of 'CSG' means that the cell is a CSG cell.

Parameter name: DeltaF PUCCH list - DeltaF PUCCH format 1
Description: The parameter defines the transport format dependent offset in power control for PUCCH format 1.

Parameter name: DeltaF PUCCH list - DeltaF PUCCH format 1b
Description: The parameter defines the transport format dependent offset in power control for PUCCH format 1b.

Parameter name: DeltaF PUCCH list - DeltaF PUCCH format 2
Description: The parameter defines the transport format dependent offset in power control for PUCCH format 2.

Parameter name: DeltaF PUCCH list - DeltaF PUCCH format 2a
Description: The parameter defines the transport format dependent offset in power control for PUCCH format 2a.

Parameter name: DeltaF PUCCH list - DeltaF PUCCH format 2b
Description: The parameter defines the transport format dependent offset in power control for PUCCH format 2b.

Parameter name: Dedicated SR transmission maximum
Description: This is the maximum number of the allowed dedicated Scheduling Requests. Once this limit is exceeded, UE releases all PUCCH resources. The value 4n corresponds to 4 transmissions, 8n corresponds to 8 transmissions and so on.    Indirectly provides the UE-specific maximum time within which the UE must receive a valid uplink grant for a new transmission on UL-SCH. If this time expires, the UE releases PUCCH resources and no longer performs a dedicated Scheduling Request, but instead performs a random access Scheduling Request. This time is calculated by cell Scheduling Request periodicity * dedicated SR transmission maximum.

Parameter name: Default paging cycle
Description: The default paging cycle defines the cell-specific paging DRX cycle duration. It also determines the maximum paging DRX duration applicable in the cell.  Referred to as ' T ' in TS 36.304. Value rf32 corresponds to 32 radio frames, rf64 corresponds to 64 radio frames and so on.

Parameter name: Default NR cell for dual connectivity
Description: Specifies the default LNRELGNBCELL instance which shall be used for dual connectivity when coverage based NR cell selection is not in use.    If coverage based NR cell selection is not in use and if parameter is not defined, then LTE-NR Dual Connectivity is disabled for this cell.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Degrees of latitude
Description: Latitude in degrees (coded value)  Relation between coded Degrees of latitude N and range of absolute latitudes X (0' <= X <= 90') it encodes is the following:    for 0 <= N <= 2^23-2:  N <= 2^23/90*X < N+1    for N = 2^23-1:  N <= 2^23/90*X <= N+1    According to above relation an encoded value N corresponds to a range of absolute latitudes X in degrees

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Degrees of longitude
Description: Longitude in degrees  (coded value)  Relation between coded Degrees of longitude N and range of absolute longitudes X (-180' <= X < +180') it encodes is the following:    N <= 2^24/360*X < N+1    N is coded in 2's complement binary on 24 bits.    According to above relation an encoded value N corresponds to a range of absolute longitudes X in degrees

Parameter name: Delta CQI aging window in SCell channel estimation
Description: This parameter controls the window size used in the eNB deltaCQI aging formula for SCell channel quality estimation when the SCell channel status is 'bad' or 'undetected'. A larger value slows the rate of deltaCQI decay.

Parameter name: Delta CQI target value in SCell channel estimation
Description: This parameter is the target deltaCQI that the eNB deltaCQI aging algorithm decays to in the eNB SCell channel quality estimation when the SCell channel status is 'bad' or 'undetected'.

Parameter name: Minimum margin for load balancing CIO adjustment
Description: This parameter defines the minimum signal difference between the target and the source cell required for triggering an intra-frequency CIO adjustment due to load unbalance.

Parameter name: Delta preamble random access message 3
Description: Used for the calculation of P0_NOMINAL_PUSCH(j=2) for PUSCH (re)transmission corresponding to the random access response grant.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Enabled TB size impact to UE PUSCH power calculation
Description: Enabling/disabling of the transport format dependent offset on a per UE basis. If this parameter is "true", PUSCH power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P1) takes the Transport Block size in account during the power calculation.

Parameter name: Deployment Type
Description: Deployment type of the cell.

Parameter name: Deprioritisation Type
Description: deprioType indicates whether the current frequency or RAT is to be de-prioritised.  Deprioritise current frequency/RAT during RRC Connection rejection procedure, UE would select other frequency layer/RAT instead of repeating connection requests to current frequency/RAT.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Direction of altitude
Description: Represents height above resp. depth below WGS84 ellipsoid surface

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - Disable video GBR service for PCell swap
Description: This parameter defines whether or not UEs with ongoing video GBR service (QCI 2, QCI 4 or QCI 67) can be considered as candidates by the PCell swap selection algorithm.  The parameter settings are irrelevant, if LNBTS-actPcellSwap is set to false.  When set to 'QCI_67', then PCell swap for a UE is not allowed, if QCI 67 bearer is established.  When set to 'all_GBR_QCIs' ,then PCell swap for a UE is not allowed, if QCI 67 or QCI 4 or QCI 2 bearer is established.  When set to 'none', then PCell swap for a UE is not restricted due to established video GBR service.

Parameter name: MCS threshold for deactivating 256QAM for the UE
Description: MCS threshold for deactivating 256QAM for the UE. Value refers to legacy MCSs so it needs to be converted eNB internally.

Parameter name: MCS threshold for reactivating 256QAM for the UE
Description: MCS threshold for reactivating 256QAM for the UE. Value refers to legacy MCSs.

Parameter name: Load threshold for  turning on DL Adaptive PF Scheduler
Description: Load value of cell (max (PDSCH load, PDCCH load)) is monitored in the cell. If the load exceed the threshold specified by this parameter, then load adaptive PF algorithm is applied.

Parameter name: SCell add DL CQI window
Description: This parameter determines the minimum time a UE must meet the CQI threshold defined by dlCaMinPcellCqi Addition CRL20777 or dlCaMinPcellCqiQci1 on PCell End CRL20777 before it can be considered a candidate for adding an Scell.

Parameter name: SCell add DL CQI threshold
Description: This parameter determines the minimum Pcell CQI for a UE with no established QCI1 bearer to be considered a candidate for adding an SCell.  If parameter is set to 0, a UE with no established QCI1 bearer can be considered a candidate for adding an Scell without checking its PCell CQI.

Parameter name: SCell add DL CQI threshold for QCI1
Description: This parameter determines the minimum PCell CQI for a UE with an established QCI1 bearer to be considered a candidate for adding an SCell.  If parameter is set to 0, a UE with an established QCI1 bearer can be considered a candidate for adding an SCell without checking its PCell CQI.  If parameter is set to 15, a UE with an established QCI1 bearer is blocked from being considered a candidate for adding an SCell.

Parameter name: Cell power reduce
Description: Sets the power reduction from the antenna maximum TX power.    Cell locking is not required if dlCellPwrRed is changed by 0.2 dB or less. If the feature 'Automatic Locking (LTE830)' is activated, eNB will not perform cell locking in this case.  The user can define a lower cell output power with the cell power reduction parameter. Reduction is deducted from the antenna maximum TX power.  Note: This parameter used for NB-IoT standalone cell, but not directly used for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell.    Hint for TDD cell:  If dlCellPwrRed is modified by 0.2 dB or less, more often than 32 times within 3 hours, a valueTag overflow occurs. As consequence the changed System Information (SIB2 ff.) might sporadically not be read by UEs which come back to the cell and have stored valid system information from 3h validity rule viewpoint.    Note: the dlCellPwrRed shall be set to 0 whenever possible, or to values as small as possible. If a cell power needs to be reduced, then it shall be done by reducing the parameter Pmax as far as possible. If pMax reduction is not sufficient, then dlCellPwrRed shall be set different from 0.

Parameter name: Enable downlink interference generation
Description: The parameter dlInterferenceEnable is used for enabling and disabling interference generation in downlink.

Parameter name: Interference level for generated downlink interference
Description: The dlInterferenceLevel parameter defines percentage of physical resource blocks (PRB) that are used for downlink data and interference transmission.  If transmission bandwidth is reduced by Slim Carrier functionality, than this parameter configures interference level relative to maximum available Slim Carrier bandwidth.

Parameter name: Modulation scheme for downlink interference
Description: The dlInterferenceModulation parameter defines modulation scheme to be used for generated downlink interference. That is, for a non-existing UE the downlink interference is transmitted.

Parameter name: TCP Service Differentiation Configuration - Downlink maximum boosting bytes
Description: This parameter defines the amount of downlink data to be sent (for a bearer which is being TCP boosted in the downlink) after which downlink TCP boosting for the bearer is stopped.

Parameter name: TCP Service Differentiation Configuration - Downlink minimum boosting bytes
Description: This parameter defines the minimum amount of downlink data which must be sent (after downlink TCP traffic has been detected on a certain bearer) in order to start downlink TCP boosting for the bearer.

Parameter name: Enable OLQC
Description: O&M switch for enabling / disabling downlink Outer loop Link Quality Control which is acting based on the 1st transmission HARQ result, that is, 1st transmission BLER.    From SRAN20C onwards dlOlqcEnable must be set to 'true'

Parameter name: Downlink pathloss change
Description: This is a trigger condition for power headroom submission due to pathloss change; named ULATB_DLPL_CHANGE in RRM SFS.

Parameter name: Downlink PCFICH transmission power boost
Description: Transmission power of the Physical Control Format Indicator Channel is boosted by set value

Parameter name: Downlink PHICH transmission power boost
Description: Transmission power of the Physical Hybrid ARQ Indicator Channel is boosted by set value.    Hint for downlink-only cell operating in an unlicensed band as defined in parameter actUnlicensedAcc it is recommended to set this parameter to '0 dB'.

Parameter name: Structure for DL dynamic power back-off - Applicability of DL power back-off
Description: This parameter value determines to which PRBs with modulation (QPSK and QAM) that back-off is applied. If dynamic DL power back-off is applied in case of paired UEs in MU-MIMO scenarios it shall be applied for the paired UEs disregard to the used modulation. Same principle is uses for the single UE multi layers case with different modulation schemes for the two layers.

Parameter name: Structure for DL dynamic power back-off - Threshold for applying DL power backoff
Description: If sum of all PRBs per TTI with EVM limited higher order modulation schemes is above this defined threshold parameter (calculated in % of the DL system bandwidth), then a dynamic power back-off shall be applied . A PRB is considered as a PRB with EMV limited higher order modulation scheme as soon as one layer for multi-layer cases or as soon as one UE for MU-MIMO cases is using an EVM limited higher order modulation scheme.

Parameter name: Minimum TTI to empty buffer in DL to trigger SCell configuration
Description: This parameter controls the minimum number of TTIs required to empty the UE's DL non-GBR data buffer in order to trigger SCell addition.

Parameter name: Downlink SRB1 CQI offset
Description: Provides the CQI link adaptation offset applied to downlink transmissions containing SRB1 messages.    The more negative the value, the more conservative the MCS and PDCCH aggregation level will be for the downlink SRB1 message transmissions

Parameter name: DL target BLER
Description: Defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) for downlink Link Adaptation in percents. Used with downlink Outer loop Link Quality Control (OLQC) functionality.

Parameter name: Default CQI
Description: Defines the default Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) value for downlink Link Adaptation use. Default CQI is used when there is no valid CQI available, that is, a CQI report is not received or it is too old.

Parameter name: Enable DL AMC
Description: O&M switch for enabling / disabling downlink Adaptive Modulation and Coding.    From SRAN20C onwards dlamcEnable must be set to 'true'

Parameter name: DCI format for common channel transmission
Description: Parameter to configure whether common channel signaling (SI, paging RACH ) use DCI format 1A or 1C on PDCCH.    If the value of the parameter is set to 'DCI format 1C' distributed VRBs are used for SI, paging and RACH.    If the value of the parameter is set to 'DCI format 1A' localized (not distributed) VRBs are used for SI, paging and RACH.

Parameter name: DL OLDTC target
Description: Target value for Outer Loop Delay Target Control.  This parameter defines a probability of packets exceeding a set delay target.

Parameter name: PDSCH congestion control for NBR traffic
Description: This parameter activates PDSCH congestion control for NBR traffic.    It is highly recommended to configure the value to 'true' if 'Nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers' is activated, i.e. if actNbrForNonGbrBearers is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: PF alpha to be used when DL instantaneous spectral efficiency is higher than rInstDlHigh
Description: Load adaptive PF algorithm allows operator to set independent PF alpha settings for high, mid and low spectral efficiency (SE) users. This parameter sets the PF alpha setting for DL high SE users. Set greater than 1 to weigh cell center users more, and less than 1 to de-prioritize cell center users.

Parameter name: PF alpha to be used when DL instantaneous spectral efficiency is lower than rInstDlLow
Description: Load adaptive PF algorithm allows operator to set independent PF alpha settings for high, mid and low spectral efficiency (SE) users. This parameter sets the PF alpha setting for DL low SE users. Set greater than 1 to weigh cell edge users more, and less than 1 to de-prioritize cell edge users.

Parameter name: PF alpha to be used when DL instantaneous spectral efficiency is between rInstDlLow and rInstDlHigh
Description: Load adaptive PF algorithm allows operator to set independent PF alpha settings for high, mid and low spectral efficiency (SE) users. This parameter sets the PF alpha setting for DL mid SE users. Set greater than 1 to weigh mid-cell users more, and less than 1 to de-prioritize mid-cell users.

Parameter name: Use of partly allocated PRBs
Description: Determines whether PRBs partly allocated for transmission of Primary (PSS) and Secondary synchronization Signals (SSS) and Physical Broadcasting Channel (BPCH) should be used in dynamic scheduling.    It is recommended to stay with the default value 'PRBs with PSS or SSS and PBCH used' if dlChBw is set to '3 MHz'.    Value "not used" mean that partial PRBs are not used.
Range and step: not used (0), PRBs with PSS or SSS used (1), PRBs with PSS or SSS and PBCH used (2)

Parameter name: DRX profile 104 - DRX inactivity timer
Description: Configures the Inactivity Timer for DRX.  The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission

Parameter name: DRX profile 104 - DRX long cycle
Description: Configures the long DRX cycle in ms.  The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.

Parameter name: DRX profile 104 - DRX on duration timer
Description: Configures the On Duration Timer for DRX.  The On Duration determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH

Parameter name: DRX profile 101 - DRX inactivity timer
Description: Configures the Inactivity Timer for DRX.  The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission.

Parameter name: DRX profile 101 - DRX long cycle
Description: Configures the long DRX cycle. It is recommended to use carefully the 40 ms value, as so far tested UEs are not able to do ReportCGI measurement with this cycle size.  The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.

Parameter name: DRX profile 101 - DRX on duration timer
Description: Configures the On Duration Timer for DRX.  The On Duration determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH.

Parameter name: DRX profile 101 - DRX profile index
Description: DRX profile index.  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX profile 101 - DRX profile priority
Description: DRX profile priority.    Applied to identify the DRX profile to be used if a UE has multiple bearers established.  Note: Modification of DRX profile priority is not recommended; preparation for future use.

Parameter name: DRX profile 101 - DRX retransmission timer
Description: Configures the Retransmission Timer for DRX.  The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH as soon as a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.

Parameter name: DRX profile 102 - DRX inactivity timer
Description: Configures the Inactivity Timer for DRX.  The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission.

Parameter name: DRX profile 102 - DRX long cycle
Description: Configures the long DRX Cycle.  The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.

Parameter name: DRX profile 102 - DRX on duration timer
Description: Configures the On Duration Timer for DRX.  The On Duration determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH.

Parameter name: DRX profile 102 - DRX profile index
Description: DRX profile index  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX profile 102 - DRX profile priority
Description: DRX profile priority.    Applied to identify the DRX profile to be used if a UE has multiple bearers established.  Note: Modification of DRX profile priority is not recommended; preparation for future use.

Parameter name: DRX profile 102 - DRX retransmission timer
Description: Configures the Retransmission Timer for DRX.  The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH as soon as a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.

Parameter name: DRX profile 103 - DRX inactivity timer
Description: Configures the Inactivity Timer for DRX.  The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission

Parameter name: DRX profile 103 - DRX long cycle
Description: Configures the long DRX cycle. It is recommended to carefully use the 40 ms value, as so far tested UEs are not able to do ReportCGI measurement with this cycle size.  The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.

Parameter name: DRX profile 103 - DRX on duration timer
Description: Configures the On Duration Timer for DRX.  The On Duration determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH

Parameter name: DRX profile 103 - DRX profile index
Description: DRX profile index  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX profile 103 - DRX profile priority
Description: DRX profile priority.    Applied to identify the DRX profile to be used if a UE has multiple bearers established.  Note: Modification of DRX profile priority is not recommended; preparation for future use.

Parameter name: DRX profile 103 - DRX retransmission timer
Description: Configures the Retransmission Timer for DRX.  The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH as soon as a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.

Parameter name: DRX profile 105 - DRX inactivity timer
Description: Configures the Inactivity Timer for DRX.  The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission.

Parameter name: DRX profile 105 - DRX long cycle
Description: Configures the long DRX Cycle.  The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.

Parameter name: DRX profile 105 - DRX on duration timer
Description: Configures the On Duration Timer for DRX.  The On Duration determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH.

Parameter name: DRX profile 105 - DRX profile index
Description: DRX profile index  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX profile 105 - DRX profile priority
Description: DRX profile priority.    Applied to identify the DRX profile to be used if a UE has multiple bearers established.  Note: Modification of DRX profile priority is not recommended; preparation for future use.

Parameter name: DRX profile 105 - DRX retransmission timer
Description: Configures the Retransmission Timer for DRX.  The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH as soon as a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.

Parameter name: DRX profile 104 - DRX profile index
Description: DRX profile index  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX profile 104 - DRX profile priority
Description: DRX profile priority.    Applied to identify the DRX profile to be used if a UE has multiple bearers established.  Note: Modification of DRX profile priority is not recommended; preparation for future use.

Parameter name: DRX profile 104 - DRX retransmission timer
Description: Configures the Retransmission Timer for DRX.  The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH as soon as a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.

Parameter name: eHRPD sector-ID list for pre-registration
Description: This Structure contains a list of eHRPD Sector-IDs which shall be used to address eHRPD-AN when tunneling cdma2000 HRPD PDU for Pre-Registration with eHRPD.  Each Sector-ID is associated with a loadbalancing factor to allow loadbalancing between multiple eHRPD-AN

Parameter name: Loadbalancing factor for pre-registration with eHRPD
Description: Each eHRPD sector-ID which is configured for preregistration is associated with this loadbalancing factor to allow for loadbalancing according to a weighted round robin mechanism when selecting the sector-ID of the eHRPD-AN for Pre-Registration

Parameter name: SectorID of eHRPD access network
Description: This Parameter contains the HRPD Sector ID used for HRPD handover pre-registration and defined as specified in 3GPP2 C.S0024-A.    The parameter must be added as character string in hexadecimal notation with leading '0x'.  It is used to populate the CDMA2000 sector ID (128 bits) using hexadecimal characters.    In addition to the leading '0x' it shall only contain hexadecimal characters '0' to '9', 'A' to 'F', 'a' to 'f'.    The format of Sector ID equals the format of an IPv6 address but without colons.

Parameter name: ABS adaptation beta
Description: This parameter is used in the ABS adaptation algorithm as a weighting factor to bias towards more or less ABS.  Though possible, it is not recommended to set this parameter to values higher than 2. The higher the value of this parameter, the more seldom the switch to a higher ABS pattern will occur.  The impact of this parameter on the ABS adaptation result is closely related to the number of established eICIC partnerships. Example: eIcicAbsAdaptationBeta = 1 and four established partnerships results to the same algorithm outcome as eIcicAbsAdaptationBeta = 2 and eight established partnerships.

Parameter name: Threshold to switch from MP0 to MP1
Description: Threshold to switch from MP0 to MP1  A higher value of this parameter leads to fewer cases where the ABS pattern MP1 is switched on.

Parameter name: ABS delta adjustment
Description: This parameter defines a threshold used in the ABS adaptation algorithm for switching from higher to lower muting pattern ratios and vice versa.  A higher value of parameter eIcicAbsDeltaAdjustment means that the MP will be switched at a later point.

Parameter name: Delay timer for applying a new ABS pattern
Description: Schedulers in the macro cell apply the new ABS pattern after said timer has expired. This is valid only when new pattern has a smaller ABS ratio than the previous one.

Parameter name: CIO adaptation type
Description: Defines whether the CIO adjustment for eICIC is statically configured or adapted to the current load conditions.

Parameter name: Threshold for re-tagging UEs from CRE to non-CRE
Description: This parameter is used in the scheduler for tagging UE's location w.r.t cell's range expansion (CRE) area based on the non-ABS related CQI value. The sum of this parameter and the non-ABS related CQI value determined by the DL link adaptation sets the CQI threshold for UEs tagged as 'CRE' to be re-tagged as 'non-CRE'.  Said tagging is used in the prioritized scheduling of UEs during ABSs.

Parameter name: Max F-eICIC-related CRE value
Description: This parameter determines the maximum allowed CIO adjustment, i.e., the maximum cell range expansion for the eICIC partner cells, equal for all eICIC partners. Once this value is reached, only reducing the CIO adjustment is allowed.    For applyFecicFunctionality = 'false', the maximum allowed value is 6dB. For applyFecicFunctionality = 'true', a value larger than 8 dB is recommended in order to exploit the FeICIC capabilities of R11 UEs.

Parameter name: Highest allowed muting pattern
Description: Highest allowed muting pattern  For dynamic ABS adaptation this parameter defines the maximum pattern the algorithm can go to.  When LTE907 TTI bundling is enabled in the macro cell together with LTE1113 it is recommended not to exceed value 'mp4'.

Parameter name: Maximum number of allowed eICIC partnerships
Description: Maximum number of allowed eICIC partnerships, i.e. number of entries in the list for eICIC partnerships

Parameter name: Timer for transition to MP0
Description: Transition to MP0 is monitored by this timer. On its expiry ABS is switched off.  5 s provides time to process 50 UEs, 10 s provides time to process 100 UEs, etc.

Parameter name: Preference on eICIC partner target ABS load
Description: Defines operator's preference on eICIC partner target ABS load during eICIC operation.

Parameter name: Preference on eICIC partner target load
Description: Defines operator's preference on eICIC partner target load during eICIC operation.

Parameter name: ECGI of the eICIC macro partner - ID of the eNB in the ECGI of the eICIC macro partner
Description: Identity of the eNB in the ECGI of the eICIC macro partner

Parameter name: ECGI of the eICIC macro partner - ID of the cell in the ECGI of the eCICI macro partner
Description: Identity of the cell in the ECGI of the eCICI macro partner

Parameter name: ECGI of the eICIC macro partner - MCC in the ECGI of the eCICI macro partner
Description: MCC in the ECGI of the eCICI macro partner

Parameter name: ECGI of the eICIC macro partner - MNC in the ECGI of the eCICI macro partner
Description: MNC in the ECGI of the eCICI macro partner

Parameter name: Averaging filter configuration for expected throughput
Description: This parameter configures two values V and F of an exponential moving average filter for expected throughput calculation.    eTputFilterConfig = (V+F):  F: determines how fast the averaging window of the expected throughput calculation is increasing after the initialization (higher F means slower averaging window increase), F = LNCEL-eTputFilterConfig % 10; F = 0 means that the averaging window is constant and its length does not change in time.  V: determines the final averaging window length of the expected throughput calculation (rounded down to an integer multiple of 10), V = LNCEL-eTputFilterConfig - F;

Parameter name: Initial MCS for expected throughput
Description: This parameter configures the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) Index (I_MCS) used to initialize the expected throughput calculation, if the serving cell is activated.    Note: Special value '99' of this parameter means that the expected throughput calculation is initialized based on the average UE throughput of this cell.

Parameter name: Extended uplink link adaptation ATB periodicity
Description: When not externally triggered by Outer Loop Link Adaptation (OLLA), the Adaptive Transmission Bandwidth (ATB) algorithm will be activated when the amount of TTI events here defined has been reached.

Parameter name: Extended uplink link adaptation BLER averaging window
Description: Averaging window for BLER in E-ULA.  It is expressed in number of TTI when UE has been actively scheduled

Parameter name: Extended uplink link adaptation delta MCS
Description: Defines how many MCS indexes above the minimal MCS index are required before ATB may increase the amount of allocable PRBs

Parameter name: Extended uplink link adaptation low MCS threshold
Description: Defines the lowest possible MCS index before Adaptive Transmission Bandwidth (ATB) algorithm may act and decrease the amount of allocable PRBs.

Parameter name: Extended uplink link adaptation low PRB threshold
Description: Defines the lowest possible amount of allocable PRBs  This shall be always bigger than or equal to redBwMinRbUl

Parameter name: Extended uplink link adaptation PRB factor
Description: Incremental and decremental factor for the Adaptive Transmission Bandwidth's calculation of allocable PRBs  Multiplying the amount of PRBs by this factor the total amount of allocable PRBs is decreasing.  Dividing the amount of PRBs by this factor, then the number of allocable PRB is increasing

Parameter name: Overall supervision timer for ECID measurements
Description: Timer to guard against gathering of all measurements requested by eSMLC for Location Services.    Supported measurements are  - Angle of Arrival (AoA)  - Timing Advance Type 2  - Timing Advance Type 1  - RSRP measurement (periodic/reportStrongestCells)  - RSRQ measurement (periodic/reportStrongestCells)    The timer is stopped when all collected measurements are ready to be sent to the eSMLC.

Parameter name: Window Length for Average EIRP Reporting
Description: This parameter defines the length (in minutes) of the time window over which to calculate the average EIRP that is generated from the cell and reported in PM Counters.  if eirpLongCtrlWin is set to 'true' then this parameter also defines the length of the moving window used in EIRP control.    PM counters may report incorrect data if eirpAvgWinLen is greater than the granularity period of EIRP related PM counters, or if the granularity period is not an integer multiple of the control window length. It is therefore recommended to set eirpAvgWinLen to a value that is a equal to, or an integer fraction of, the PM counter granularity period.

Parameter name: List of EIRP control power reduction factor per cell segment
Description: This parameter is a list with one element per cell segment in the grid, i.e. (LNCEL-eirpControl-numOfSegElevationEdges + 1) x (LNCEL-eirpControl-numOfSegmentAzimuthEdges + 1). Each element indicates the power reduction factor to be applied to the max EIRP to obtain the absolute EIRP threshold(dBm) in the considered cell segment.    max EIRP calculation: EIRP (dBm) = P_total (dBm) + LNCEL-eirpControl-nomMaxAntennaGain (dBi)  P_total (dBm) = pMax (dBm)+ 10*Log(N)  where:  -pMax is the max power per antenna (corresponding to LNCEL.pMax).  -N is the number of TX ports.    The order of elements in LNCEL-eirpCtrlPwrRedFactorList shall be configured corresponding to cellSegIndex of the grid as the below formula:    cellSegIndex = 1+ j * (LNCEL-eirpControl-numOfSegmentAzimuthEdges+1) + i  Where:  -cellSegment (j,i) corresponds to the jth elevation and the ith azimuth.      Note:  This parameter is only used for Beamforming EIRP control, i.e. LNCEL.actEirpControl = 'Beamforming'.  If LNCEL-eirpControl-nomMaxAntennaGain is not configured during EIRP control activation, it will be calculated by internal.

Parameter name: Extended averaging window length for actual EIRP control
Description: If eirpLongCtrlWin is set to 'false',  - the control of actual EIRP in LTE works with internal control periods of 120 ms to realize the configured eirpReduction value. Depending on traffic scenarios, traffic bursts are served up to cell capacity and the configured eirpReduction is maintained within a maximum of 4..7 such periods.  - eirpAvgWinLen controls PM counters only.  - Established GBR bearers have their average PRB usage reserved over this time.  - The configured EIRP budget is maintained already within 1 s.    If eirpLongCtrlWin is set to 'true',  - the duration of the control periods is increased, depending on the configured value of eirpAvgWinLen, i.e. PM counter reporting and controlling the averaged (actual) EIRP are done on the same timing basis.  - PRB reservation for GBR is no longer based on measured short-term averages. Reserving PRBs for GBR must be done by setting eirpMinPrbsForLte to a desired value.    PM counters may report incorrect data if eirpAvgWinLen is greater than the granularity period of EIRP related PM counters, or if the granularity period is not an integer multiple of the control window length. It is therefore recommended to set eirpAvgWinLen to a value that is a equal to, or an integer fraction of, the PM counter granularity period.

Parameter name: EIRP reduction
Description: This parameter specifies the reduction value on the EIRP (Effective Isotropic Radiated Power) which reduces actual EIRP generation to a level below the 'zero' point.  The starting value ('zero' point) for the EIRP reduction for a cell is calculated from configuration data (pMax, antGainNonBF, power reduction factors) and is assumed to have contributions from all configured antennas and RF amplifiers (supercell, MIMO, TxDiv). PRB blanking (LTE3145 Slim carrier, LTE1800 DL interference shaping) affects the selection of particular PRBs by the DL scheduler but has no effect on EIRP control.    Note that using high values for EIRP reduction translates into severe capacity reductions (down to 1/4 = 25% if set at 6 dB).    Cells with EIRP reduction are likely to run their RF amplifiers at some reduced average output power where they have smaller efficiency than if they run at full power. It is therefore recommended to concentrate EIRP reductions on a small number of cells among those with the same or overlapping coverage area.    Distributing a given EIRP reduction over several cells with same or overlapping coverage has the disadvantage of running more RF hardware units, including power consumption for bias currents and processing equipment, to achieve the same (reduced) capacity in a given coverage area. The same applies to cells with EIRP reduction as members of power-saving groups (LTE1103 Load-based power saving and follow-up features).    Shutdown of transmit paths from LTE1203 does not change the EIRP reduction, the cell is then allowed to generate the same EIRP using the remaining transmit paths.  Since EIRP reduction is done by limiting the PRB usage, LTE1800 DL interference shaping can be used with benefit to reduce interference levels between cells on the same frequency.    EIRP reduction is handled by the LTE DL scheduler only. (e)MBMS, LTE-M, NB-IoT traffic are not limited.    FDD only:  If reportedEirpHeadroomPrb or reportedEirpHeadroomdB is smaller than 0 then any or all of these parameters may need to be reconsidered in order to achieve activation of EIRP Control (actEirpControl equal to 'nonBeamforming'):  eirpReduction, eirpMinPrbsForLte,  for Slim Carrier and DSS features: actDlSlimCarrier, numBlankDlPrbsDown, numBlankDlPrbsUp,  for DSS features: actDynamicSharedSpectrum, lteNrDssMode, minNrDssRatio, actWcdmaLteSharedSpectrum  for MBMS: actMBMS, cellPwrRedForMBMS, maxSubfrPShare,  for NB-IoT: nbIoTMode, dlPwrBoost, numDlNonAnchCarrierNB,  for CatM: actCatm, numNarBandModeACatM    Note:  This parameter is only used for nonBeamforming EIRP control, i.e. LNCEL.actEirpControl = 'nonBeamforming'

Parameter name: Set GBR traffic to priority over a reduction of actual EIRP
Description: Control of actual EIRP divides traffic into two types:  - prioritized traffic is allowed to generate any level of actual EIRP. Prioritized traffic always includes MBMS, CatM, NB-IoT, HARQ retransmissions, Control Channels, and reference symbols.  - If eirpReduction is configured to a value greater than 0, non-prioritized traffic receives fewer resources, in order to maintain the EIRP reduction over the whole traffic. Non-prioritized traffic always includes non-GBR.    If eirpSetGbrOverEirp is set to 'false',  - GBR and 'duty' parts of Nominal Bit Rate (NBR) traffic are treated as non-prioritized.  - GBR still has scheduling priority over non-GBR traffic.  - the cell can compensate bursts of excessive prioritized traffic by restricting GBR and non-GBR allocations.    If eirpSetGbrOverEirp is set to 'true',  - GBR is also treated as prioritized traffic.  - only DL non-GBR traffic can be restricted in order to control actual EIRP.  - GBR traffic can generate any level of EIRP, without consideration of the configured eirpReduction. This can violate local regulation.    Note: Above MBMS, CatM, NB-IoT functions are for FDD only.

Parameter name: Emergency area ID list
Description: An element of the emAreaIdList identifies an Emergency Area ID (emAreaId) of the eNB cell.  Multiple emAreaId's may be configured for the eNB cell.    An 'emAreaId' ID may be used in signalling messages received via S1-i/f to indicate the set of cells with emergency impact (e.g. which have to broadcast the warning message).  If e.g. a WRITE-REPLACE WARNING REQUEST message with 'emAreaId' is received, the warning message shall be broadcasted by an eNB cell if 'pwsWithEmAreaId' is true and the 'emAreaId' received in the request message matches with the 'emAreaId' assigned to the eNB cell.

Parameter name: Enable AMC for PDCCH link adaptation
Description: The parameter defines the switch for enable/disable Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) based Adaptive Modulation and Coding (AMC) for PDCCH link adaptation. If the parameter is disabled, default aggregation is used implicitly.    From SRAN20C onwards enableAmcPdcch must be set to 'true'

Parameter name: Enable better cell HO
Description: Flag if better cell HO is enabled.

Parameter name: Enable coverage HO
Description: Flag if coverage HO is enabled.

Parameter name: Enable default BW combination set check for EN-DC band combinations
Description: This feature enables the eNB to assume BCS0 if no BCS is provided by the UE for certain intra-band EN-DC band combination.

Parameter name: Enable lower aggregation selection for PDCCH LA
Description: The parameter determines the enabling/disabling switch for automatic selection of lower aggregation during PDCCH scheduling. This means that a required aggregation level which is defined from UE's Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) reports may be downgraded by one step without any other particular reason (e.g. blocking due to UE hash function or overall space). Assigning of lower aggregation decreases number of blocked UEs in case of PDCCH resource deficiency, and gives possibility for greater number of PDCCH messages per TTI. A corresponding increase in PDCCH power compensates caused degradation in PDCCH code robustness.    There are some restrictions for utilizing the automatic lower aggregation for an UE:  - the required aggregation shall be at least 4,  - enableAmcPdcch and enablePcPdcch shall be enabled, and  - used PDCCH capacity for all uplink and downlink allocations shall exceed a limit defined by the threshold pdcchLowAggTh of total PDCCH capacity for allocated number of PDCCH symbols in TTI    The parameter will be ignored in FDD cells if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.

Parameter name: Enable PDCCH power control
Description: The parameter defines the switch for enabling / disabling power control on PDCCH. If the parameter is disabled, a flat downlink Power Spectral Density (PSD) is used.    From SRAN20C onwards enablePcPdcch must be set to 'true'

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - Enable carr. aggr. UEs with VoLTE calls for PCell swap
Description: Defines whether or not UEs with ongoing VoLTE calls can be considered as candidates by the PCell swap selection algorithm.

Parameter name: Energy saving state
Description: Energy Saving state of the cell.  The Energy Saving state value is set by the eNB.
Range and step: notEnergySaving (0), energySaving (1), reducedEnergySaving (2), switchingOffRTX (4), switchingOff (3), switchingOnTX (5)

Parameter name: E-UTRAN cell identifier
Description: The E-UTRAN cell identifier is unique within one PLMN and has a length of 28 bits. The leftmost 20 bits of the value correspond to the value of the eNB ID (parameter lnBtsId) and the 8 rightmost bits correspond to the value of the local cell resource ID (lcrId). This parameter cannot be set by operator, it is calculated system internally and is only readable.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Expected cell range
Description: Expected cell range indicates the size of coverage area of a cell. This is used as an input for the PRACH preamble selection during configuration of physical random access channel.

Parameter name: Expected Cell Size
Description: This parameter determines the appropriate counter histogram range (set), which should be aligned with the expected size of the cell from preceding network planning.

Parameter name: Fast uplink link ATB trigger threshold
Description: The parameter defines the threshold under which the OLLA DCM triggers an earlier ATB calculation.  It has always values <=0.

Parameter name: Fast PDCCH adaptation blocked UE threshold
Description: Specifies a threshold for the number of UEs that could not be scheduled in current TTI due to lack of PDCCH resources below which the PDCCH fast adapt counter can be decremented.

Parameter name: Fast PDCCH adaptation step down size
Description: Specifies the amount that will be decremented from the PDCCH fast adapt counter when there are more PDCCH resources than is required for the load in the current TTI. Once the PDCCH fast adapt counter is less than a threshold the PDCCH will be reduced by one symbol. Setting this parameter to a high value will tend to minimize the number of PDCCH symbols per TTI.

Parameter name: Fast PDCCH adaptation step up size
Description: Specifies the amount that will be added to the PDCCH fast adapt counter when there are insufficient PDCCH resources for the load in the current TTI. Once the PDCCH fast adapt counter exceeds a threshold the PDCCH will be increased by one symbol. The maximum number of PDCCH symbols that can be expanded to is defined by maxNrSymPdcch. Setting this parameter to a high value will tend to maximize the number of PDCCH symbols per TTI.

Parameter name: Filter center TX
Description: This parameter defines absolute TX frequency in kHz for overriding normal filter center frequency tuning.    This parameter can be used to override normal filter tuning to minimize noise to neighboring frequency band. If the parameter value is not defined, TX filter frequency is evaluated as an average of the configured center frequencies.    eNB restart will be only performed if the optional parameter is configured in case of cell creation or is modified for an existing cell.

Parameter name: Filter coefficient
Description: Filter coefficient for RSRP measurements used to calculate path loss as specified in [3GPP-36.213. 5.1.1.1]. Value fc0 corresponds to k = 0, fc1 corresponds to k = 1, and so on.

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for CSFB Cpich-Ecn0
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for UTRA-WCDMA CSFB Cpich-Ecn0  Specifies the filtering coefficient used for Cpich-Ecn0 within the measurement quantity configuration of UTRA-WCDMA

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for CSFB Cpich-RSCP
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for UTRA-WCDMA CSFB Cpich-RSCP  Specifies the filtering coefficient used for Cpich-RSCP within the measurement quantity configuration of UTRA-WCDMA

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for cpich ecN0
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for UTRA Cpich-EcNo  Specifies the filtering coefficient used for Cpich-EcNo within the measurement quantity configuration of UTRA.    filterCoefficientCpichEcNo within quantity configuration of UTRA is an optional IE

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for cpich RSCP
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for UTRA Cpich-RSCP  Specifies the filtering coefficient used for Cpich-RSCP within the measurement quantity configuration of UTRA    filterCoefficientCpichRscp within quantity configuration of UTRA is an optional IE

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for RSRP
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for RSRP (to be set in QuantityConfigEUTRA)

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for RSRQ
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for RSRQ (to be set in QuantityConfigEUTRA)

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for RSSI
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for RSSI  Specifies the filtering coefficient used for RSSI within the measurement quantity configuration of GERAN

Parameter name: First PLMN in MORAN SIB1
Description: This parameter is valid for special non-3GPP compliant MORAN deployment only.  It indicates MNC of the configured further PLMN which should be broadcasted in first instance of plmn-IdentityList IE in SIB1 of this cell instead of the primary PLMN.  The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE, Cat-M and NB-IoT UE.    In legacy network configurations this parameter must not be configured.  Before setting this parameter, please consult NOKIA service team for details.

Parameter name: Frame start offset
Description: The parameter defines the frame start offset for the cell. The defined offset is observed as a shift of the frame start at the air interface with the reference to the BTS clock (as best represented by its 1PPS output). If both manualFrameTimingAdjustment and frameStartOffset are configured, frameStartOffset takes precedence in shifting the Air Interface timing. If frameStartOffset is not configured, then manualFrameTimingAdjustment applies.    Restrictions:  - If sfnOffset is configured for the cell, then frameStartOffset must be also configured.  - The cell with the configured offset must be connected to eCPRI or CPRI-N capable radio modules. frameStartOffset is not allowed to be configured for the cell, if the connected radio module is not eCPRI or CPRI-N capable.  - Configuration of the frameStartOffset must be the same for all cells allocated to the same baseband cell set of a baseband card.  - All LTE cells on the same radio module must have the same frameStartOffset configuration.  - A PCell and all its SCells must have the same frameStartOffset configuration.  - All cells in the same UL CoMP cluster must have the same frameStartOffset configuration.    The configuration of the frameStartOffset is not applied by the system, if the parameter actCellTimingOffset is set to 'false' in an eCPRI cell and actCellTimingOffsetCpriN is set to 'false' in a CPRI-N cell.    Note: Addition, removal or updating this parameter may provoke a reset.

Parameter name: Further PLMN identity list
Description: Further PLMN IDs of the cell.  These are further PLMN IDs of the cell. The parameter indicates which operators' (PLMN ID) networks are available from the cell. These PLMN identities have a cell scope.  The primary PLMN ID has to be provided separately for the eNB.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Further PLMN access class barring profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the access barring profile for each further PLMN

Parameter name: Further PLMN access class barring profile identifier for Cat-M
Description: Instance ID of the Cat-M access barring profile for each further PLMN.

Parameter name: Autonomous PLMN removal allowed
Description: This parameter specifies whether the further PLMN is allowed to be autonomously removed from SIB1 in case of the PLMN not supported by eNB cell temporarily (e.g. when C-plane overload)  Feature of autonomous further PLMN removal in SIB1 due to C-plane overload can be deactivated in a specific cell indeed if the flag of all further PLMNs of the cell are set to FALSE.

Parameter name: Cell reserved for operator use
Description: Indicates if the cell/PLMN combination is reserved for operator use.  Cells reserved for operator use are treated as barred by 'normal' UEs without a USIM with AC 11 or 15 inserted. UEs with AC 11 or 15 USIM inserted are specific operator UEs and thus allowed to camp on and access such cells. The default value is not reserved.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Default DCN Group Id
Description: The default Dedicated Core Network (DCN) Group Identity per PLMN is optionally configured for rerouting UE to an MME Group when the indicated MME is not available when DECOR (actDCN) feature is activated.

Parameter name: Initial MME Group Identifier
Description: Initial MME Group Identifier(MMEGI) for initial MME selection for further PLMNs configured for the cell.

Parameter name: Mobile country code
Description: The Mobile Country Code parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Mobile network code
Description: The Mobile Network Code parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Cell PLMN indicator for supporting EN-DC.
Description: Indication of the cell/PLMN supports EN-DC in SIB2.

Parameter name: Geographical area identity uncertainty
Description: This parameter indicates the radius error of GAI [m].

Parameter name: GBR congestion handling
Description: Determines if and on which layer congestion handling is applied if congestion is detected by layer 2.  It is highly recommended to configure the value '"l2andl3" if 'Enhanced AC and GBR services' are activated, that is if "actEnhAcandGbrServices" equals True.

Parameter name: Group assignment for PUSCH or NPUSCH
Description: The parameter defines the assigned PUSCH or NPUSCH group.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Maximum number of message 3 HARQ transmissions
Description: Indicates the maximum number of HARQ transmissions used for message 3 of the contention-based random access procedure.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Maximum number of HARQ transmission in DL
Description: Indicates the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in DL that is configured for each UE at initial access to a specific cell.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Maximum number of HARQ transmission in DL for Signaling
Description: Indicates the maximum number of HARQ transmissions for DL transmissions containing Signaling traffic. Signaling traffic is defined as belonging to an SRB, a signaling bearer or containing a TAC MAC control element.

Parameter name: Max number of UL HARQ transmissions during TTI bundling
Description: Indicates the maximum number of transmissions that is configured for a UE in TTI bundling operation.

Parameter name: Maximum number of HARQ transmission in DL for VoLTE
Description: Indicates the maximum number of HARQ transmissions for DL transmissions containing VoLTE traffic.

Parameter name: Maximum number of HARQ transmission in UL
Description: Indicates the maximum number of HARQ transmissions in UL that is configured for each UE at initial access to a specific cell.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency load balancing load thresholds - DL GBR resource high load
Description: This parameter defines the high load for the DL GBR resources. The value represents a percentage of PRBs available to GBR in the cell.    A cell is considered 'non-balanced' if any load component has reached its highLoad threshold.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency load balancing load thresholds - DL non-GBR resource high load
Description: This parameter defines the high load for the DL non-GBR resources. The value represents a percentage of the non-GBR load scale 0 and 100.    A cell is considered 'non-balanced' if any load component has reached its highLoad threshold.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency load balancing load thresholds - PDCCH high load
Description: This parameter defines the high load for the PDCCH. The value represents a percentage of the available PDCCH resources in the cell.    A cell is considered 'non-balanced' if any load component has reached its highLoad threshold.

Parameter name: Hopping mode of PUSCH
Description: This parameter defines if hopping is only inter-subframe or both inter- and intra-subframe.

Parameter name: Highspeed scenario
Description: Defines highspeed train scenario for a cell.  Scenario 1 (open space scenario) and scenario 3 (tunnel scenario).    Scenarios are described in 36.104 Annex B.3 and 36.141 Annex B.3:  Scenario 1: Open space  Scenario 3: Tunnel for multi-antennas

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of offset a3Offset for RSRP intra F
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Better Cell Handover of Intra-Frequency  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Threshold 2 config for CDMA2000 HRPD and 1xRTT - Related hysteresis of RSRP threshold 2 for CDMA2000
Description: Related hysteresis of threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of CDMA2000-eHRPD or CDMA2000-1XRTT measurements    Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th2 GERAN for RSRP
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of GERAN measurements  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th2 interFreq for RSRP
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of inter frequency measurements  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: RSRQ mobility parameters - Related hysteresis of threshold Th2 for RSRQ mobility
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell for mobility measurements activation.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2-RSRQ triggered reporting condition.  The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.331: IE value = value [dB] * 2

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th2 NR for RSRP
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of coverage-based 5G SA HO measurements  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th2 WCDMA for RSRP
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of WCDMA measurements  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th2a for RSRP
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for stopping of Inter-RAT (InterFreq) Measurements  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A1 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of thresholds th3 and th3a
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Coverage Handover of Intra-Frequency  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A5 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.  This parameter applies to both RSRP based and RSRQ based A5 Intra frequency measurement.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th4 for RSRP
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for redirection trigger  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: RSRQ redirection parameters - Related hysteresis of threshold Th4 for RSRQ
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell for redirection trigger.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2-RSRQ triggered reporting condition.  The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Hysteresis for DL GBR resource load measurement
Description: This parameter defines the hysteresis when determining whether DL GBR resource load is balanced or unbalanced. The value represents a percentage of the available DL PRBs in the cell.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Hysteresis for DL Non-GBR resource load measurement
Description: This parameter defines the hysteresis when determining whether DL Non-GBR resource load is balanced or unbalanced. The value represents a percentage of the available DL PRBs in the cell.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Hysteresis for PDCCH load measurement
Description: This parameter defines the hysteresis when determining whether PDCCH load is balanced or unbalanced. The value represents a percentage of the available PDCCH resources in the cell.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency ENDC handover retry timer
Description: The parameter defines the inter-frequency UE MR-DC capability handover retry timer. The value is assigned to all active UEs to trigger a cyclical re-check if they can be inter-frequency UE MR-DC ENDC HO candidates. The timer is only applicable when UE MR-DC capability based HO feature is switched on and applicable to UE.  The basic value given by the operator is used directly as timer expiry rate.

Parameter name: Inter Freq Load Balance A4 active limit
Description: Maximum number of UEs per cell that have iF-LB A4 measurements activated at a time.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Inter-frequency load balancing QCI1 bearer check timer
Description: Timer is started when S1AP sends back Initial Context Setup Response. After timer expiration it is checked whether or not the UE has a QCI1 bearer.    The value '0' indicates that UEs with QCI1 (VoIP) bearers are not excluded from the inter-frequency load balancing. Note that when QCI1 check is not performed, there is 1 s wait time before load balancing starts.  In LTE1387 UEs with QCI1 (VoIP) bearer are excluded from the inter-frequency load balancing. As the bearer establishment takes some time, SW has to wait before making a check.

Parameter name: SPID based offload UE candidate selection update timer
Description: This cell level timer is started when the already existing trigger for the Connected Mode Load Balancing offload is reached. The evaluation of SPID groups priority is done at the expiry of the iFLBCandSelUpdateTimer.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Inter-frequency load balancing GBR high load DL
Description: High Load for usage of GBR Uu I/F resources in DL direction.  High Load is the treshold that controls the Inter Frequency Load Balancing.    If iFLBHighLoadGBRDL and iFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL and iFLBHighLoadPdcch are set to 100%, the cell will never enter active Inter Frequency Load Balancing state.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Inter-frequency load balancing non-GBR high load DL
Description: High Load for usage of nonGBR Uu I/F resources in DL direction.  High Load is the treshold that controls the Inter Frequency Load Balancing.    If iFLBHighLoadGBRDL and iFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL and iFLBHighLoadPdcch are set to 100%, the cell will never enter active Inter Frequency Load Balancing state.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Inter-frequency load balancing PDCCH high load
Description: High Load for usage of PDCCH Uu I/F resources  High Load is the treshold that controls the Inter Frequency Load Balancing.    If iFLBHighLoadGBRDL and iFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL and iFLBHighLoadPdcch are set to 100%, the cell will never enter active Inter Frequency Load Balancing state.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load threshold step - Inter-frequency load balancing GBR high load DL threshold step
Description: Represents the additional load amount above iFLBHighLoadGBRDL. With the SPID based offload UE candidate selection feature UE selection for offload is prioritized according to operator defined SPID groups. If the Load for usage of GBR Uu I/F resources in DL direction exceeds iFLBHighLoadGBRDL plus iFLBLoadStepGBRDL then next SPID Groups are added for offload (gradually according to SPID Group priority for offload).  High Load is the threshold that controls the Inter Frequency Load Balancing.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load threshold step - Inter-frequency load balancing non - GBR high load DL threshold step
Description: Represents the additional load amount above iFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL. With the SPID based offload UE candidate selection feature UE selection for offload is prioritized according to operator defined SPID groups. If the Load for usage of nonGBR Uu I/F resources in DL direction exceeds iFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL plus iFLBLoadStepNonGBRDL then next SPID Groups are added for offload (gradually according to SPID Group priority for offload).  High Load is the threshold that controls the Inter Frequency Load Balancing.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load threshold step - Inter-frequency load balancing Pdcch high load threshold step
Description: Represents the additional load amount above iFLBHighLoadPdcch. With the SPID based offload UE candidate selection feature UE selection for offload is prioritized according to operator defined SPID groups. If the Load for usage of PDCCH Uu I/F resources in DL direction exceeds iFLBHighLoadPdcch plus iFLBLoadStepPdcch then next SPID Groups are added for offload (gradually according to SPID Group priority for offload).  High Load is the threshold that controls the Inter Frequency Load Balancing.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Inter Freq Load Bal Retry Timer
Description: This timer is assigned to all active UEs to trigger a cyclical re-check if they can be inter-frequency or UTRAN load balancing candidates.  The basic value given by the operator is dynamically adapted depending on number of active UEs in the cell to restrict the timer expiry rate

Parameter name: Inter-freq. service based HO retry timer
Description: The parameter defines the inter-frequency service based handover retry timer. The value is assigned to all active UEs to trigger a cyclical re-check if they can be inter-frequency service based HO candidates. The timer is only applicable when Service Based HO feature is switched on and QCI1 bearer is established for UE.  The basic value given by the operator is used directly as timer expiry rate.

Parameter name: Idle mode load balancing capacity threshold
Description: Only if the Composite Available Capacity (CAC) is below or equal to this threshold, idle mode load balancing actions shall be triggered.

Parameter name: Idle mode load balancing capacity threshold for CA capable UEs
Description: Only if the Composite Available Capacity (CAC) is below or equal to this threshold, idle mode load balancing for CA capable UEs actions shall be triggered.

Parameter name: Threshold for advanced Idle mode load balancing capacity for CA capable UEs
Description: Composite Available Capacity (CAC) threshold used to start/stop advanced CA-aware idle mode load balancing actions.    Only if the CAC value is greater than this threshold (but still smaller than or equal to idleLBCapThreshCAUe), advanced idle mode load balancing for CA capable UEs actions shall be triggered. If the CAC value is smaller than or equal to this threshold, non-CA-aware idle mode load balancing shall be used.    Note: For idleLBCapThreshCaUeAdv equal to '0' or '100', CAC value calculation is not triggered if not otherwise requested. For idleLBCapThreshCaUeAdv equal to '0', LTE4154 is then active under all load conditions, while for idleLBCapThreshCaUeAdv equal to '100', LTE4154 is then not active under all load conditions.

Parameter name: Idle mode load balancing capacity threshold for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Only if the Composite Available Capacity (CAC) is below or equal to this threshold, idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs actions shall be triggered.    "Note: For idleLBCapThreshUeTM9 equal to '0' or '100', CAC value calculation is not started if not otherwise requested. For idleLBCapThreshUeTM9 equal to '0', TM9-aware idle mode balancing is disabled in the cell, while for idleLBCapThreshUeTM9 equal to '100', it is triggered under all load conditions."

Parameter name: Cell reselection weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: Cell reselection weight factor for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs
Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing.  Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities or with dedicated priority value configured by operator.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: Cell reselection weight factor for idle mode load balancing for 3CC CA UEs
Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 3CC CA UEs.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing.  Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities or with dedicated priority value configured by operator.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 4CC CA UEs.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing.  Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 5CC CA UEs. Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters. Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 6CC CA UEs.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing.  Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 7CC CA UEs. Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters. Parameter name: Cell reselection weight factor idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.

Parameter name: Cell reselection weight factor idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: Serving cell carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: Serving cell carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in algorithm for Secondary target selection for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo IE. Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Serving cell frequency is not added in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo when Idle Mobility Configuration is taken from MOIMP or MODIMP.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: Serving cell carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 3CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for 3CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in algorithm for Secondary target selection for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo IE. Decision which CC type used in IE sent to UE depends on UE Capabilities and other CC type configuration parameters.    Serving cell frequency is not added in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo when Idle Mobility Configuration is taken from MOIMP or MODIMP.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for 4CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in algorithm for Secondary target selection for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo IE. Parameter name: Serving cell carrier frequency priority for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: Serv cell carr freq prio for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing for CA capable UEs
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing for CA capable UEs.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing for TM9 capable UEs.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing.

Parameter name: Uplink improved latency reaction timer
Description: Improved latency reaction timer in uplink defines the time in which the UE has to send useful data after either the initial dummy grant or a previous reception of useful data. If the timer expires the, UE will not get dummy grant anymore.

Parameter name: Inactivity timer
Description: Defines the time period for the indication of the UE inactivity in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Inactivity timer multiplier
Description: Used for internal calculation of a new UE inactivity timer.  With LTE1819, the eNB decides on the value of the RRC inactivity timer based on recent UE activity. Either the existing inactivityTimer value or the new internally calculated value inactivityTimerMult * inactivityTimer is applied. The new calculated value is greater than the inactivityTimer by definition.

Parameter name: Inactivity timer for public safety bearer
Description: Defines the time period for the indication of the UE inactivity in both DL and UL directions for UE with public safety bearer QCI 65 or QCI 66 or QCI 67 or QCI 69.  For the UEs with QCI 65 or QCI 66 or QCI 67 or QCI 69 established, inactivityTimerPubSafety value is used instead of existing inactivityTimer value.  When LNBTS_FDD-actPubSafetyBearers or LNBTS_FDD.actPubSafetyBearers is activated, for the UEs which has expressed interest in sidelink communication, inactivityTimerPubSafety value is used instead of existing inactivityTimer value.

Parameter name: Inactivity timer for QCI5 bearer with signaling traffic
Description: Inactivity timer for QCI5 data radio bearers carrying signalling traffic (as determined by scheduling type setting of the bearer).
