This inactivity timer is triggered by any traffic being carried on QCI5 bearer in DL or UL (if scheduling type of qciTab5 is "signalling").  It allows, e.g., to prevent UE inactivity detection during the ringing phase of a voice call establishment.

Parameter name: headroom of Inter-RAT measurements
Description: Number of Measurement Ids and Report-Configuration Ids statically reserved for Inter-RAT (incl. 5G SA) measurements

Parameter name: Initial decision period for channel quality estimation
Description: Initial decision period for channel quality estimation.

Parameter name: Initial MCS in downlink
Description: The parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PDSCH for other use than BCCH, PCH or random access messages.    iniMcsDl is applicable for PDSCH LA only if both dlOlqcEnable and dlamcEnable are set to 'false' where it determines the static target code rate for PDSCH user data transmissions. Otherwise, UE reported CQI or default CQI (dlamcCqiDef) with or without OLQC correction determines the target code rate.

Parameter name: Initial MCS in uplink
Description: The parameter defines an initial Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used on PUSCH for other use than random access message 3.    Depending on the chosen modulation scheme in UL the range of iniMcsUl differs.    The following ranges are possible:  QPSK: iniMcsUl = 0-10  16QAM: iniMcsUl = 0-20  16QAMHighMCS: iniMcsUl = 0-24  64QAM: iniMcsUl = 0-28  64QAMand16QAMHighMCS: iniMcsUl = 0-28    Note for TDD cells:  The allowed range for iniMcsUl is restricted to 0-20.

Parameter name: Initial amount of PRBs in uplink
Description: Defines the initial amount of maximum PRBs in uplink.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Initial decision period for channel quality estimation for UL
Description: Initial decision period for channel quality estimation for UL.

Parameter name: Downlink interference shaping configuration - Downlink interference shaping profile identifier
Description: The instance ID of the DL interference shaping profile that shall be used for subscribers served by this LNCEL.    As a default, a profile with ishPrId = 0 will be used if not configured otherwise.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Latitude sign
Description: Distinguishes between north and south latitude

Parameter name: Load filtering coefficient
Description: This parameter defines the filter coefficient used for each of the load measurements (exponential filter).

Parameter name: Local cell resource ID
Description: ID of the Local Cell Resource. The value for each cell shall be unique in the eNB.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Load balancing profile
Description: This parameter selects the cell load balancing profile. From the profile parameters controlling the cell load condition will be derived.

Parameter name: Cell load CA/EN-DC blocking start threshold - Cell RRC connection blocking start threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the upper threshold of RRC CONNECTED UEs which can trigger load-based carrier aggregation SCell and PCell blocking or EN-DC blocking in the cell level.  Carrier aggregation / EN-DC blocking becomes ACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the cell >= ROUND(blockNumRrcConn * maxNumRRC.Cell / 100).    Note: maxNumRRC.Cell - indicates that this is the cell related maxNumRRC RAC limit.

Parameter name: Cell load CA/EN-DC blocking start threshold - Cell downlink GBR load blocking start threshold
Description: Represents the downlink GBR load threshold for load-based carrier aggregation SCell and PCell blocking feature and EN-DC blocking feature.  The eNB may block SCell and PCell additions in this cell when its load exceeds defined thresholds (PDCCH, GBR, non-GBR).  The eNB may block EN-DC setup in this cell when its load exceeds defined thresholds (PDCCH, GBR, non-GBR).

Parameter name: Cell load CA/EN-DC blocking start threshold - Cell downlink non-GBR load blocking start threshold
Description: Represents the downlink non-GBR load threshold for load-based carrier aggregation SCell and PCell blocking feature and EN-DC blocking feature.  The eNB may block SCell and PCell additions in this cell when its load exceeds defined thresholds (PDCCH, GBR, non-GBR).  The eNB may block EN-DC setup in this cell when its load exceeds defined thresholds (PDCCH, GBR, non-GBR).

Parameter name: Cell load CA/EN-DC blocking start threshold - Cell PDCCH load blocking start threshold
Description: Represents the PDCCH load threshold for load-based carrier aggregation SCell and PCell blocking feature and EN-DC blocking feature.  The eNB may block SCell and PCell additions in this cell when its load exceeds defined thresholds (PDCCH, GBR, non-GBR).  The eNB may block EN-DC setup in this cell when its load exceeds defined thresholds (PDCCH, GBR, non-GBR).

Parameter name: Long decision period for  channel quality est.
Description: Defines the long decision period for collecting the MCS samples from the SCell, before deciding about its channel quality. The long decision period applies after the first SCell good channel quality estimation.    Within the specified decision period, one MCS sample is taken every 25 ms.

Parameter name: Low latency additional non-GBR UE threshold
Description: Specifies the number of non-GBR UEs in the scheduling queue, above which additional non-GBR UEs will be scheduled in the current subframe. This parameter is only used if actMaxNumUeDlNonGbr is not equal to 0.

Parameter name: Cell individual offset change lower margin
Description: This parameter defines the minimum value that a CIO can assume, when changed autonomously by the eNB during e.g. the intra-frequency load balancing function.

Parameter name: LTE-NR dynamic spectrum sharing mode
Description: This parameter specifies the LTE-NR dynamic spectrum sharing mode.  If lteNrDssMode is set to 'none', LTE-NR spectrum sharing is disabled for this cell    Following options are supported:  0 none (default) -- no spectrum sharing  1 DSS_Phase_I -- pre-defined sharing pattern will be used  2 DL_CRS_TDM_UL_FDM -- DSS in DL TDM based with CRS rate matching and DSS in UL FDM based DSS  3 DSS_Phase_III -- improved allocation range and superfast coordination    For details about sharing ratio etc. please refer to settings in DSSNR.    FDD only: If reportedEirpHeadroomPrb is smaller than 0 then lteNrDssMode may need to be considered in order to achieve activation of EIRP Control (actEirpControl equal to 'nonBeamforming').

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Maximum Antenna Range
Description: MAR(Maximum Antenna Range) is the maximum distance where the radio wave of the target sector can reach.

Parameter name: Maximum bitrate downlink
Description: Maximum Bit Rate that shall not be exceeded in DL (configured value is limitation on TTI base, i.e., a calculation on maximum bitrate per TTI is done).  This parameter is only effective if parameter mbrSelector of the same cell object is set to value 'OaM'.  This parameter has no effect for UEs having DL carrier aggregation activated. For CA UEs the limitations are taken from the 3GPP standard TS 36.306 considering the UE's category. Due to that the range of this parameter is not adapted to higher possible transmission rates defined in 3GPP Rel.10 and beyond.

Parameter name: Maximum bitrate uplink
Description: Maximum bit rate that shall not be exceeded in UL (configured value is converted to and applied as a per TTI limit).  This parameter is only effective if parameter mbrSelector of the same cell object is set to value 'OaM'.  The parameter has no effect (over multiple carriers) for UEs having UL carrier aggregation activated.

Parameter name: Maximum code rate for paging
Description: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for paging. This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.    Note:  The amount of paging records being transmitted per paging occasion is limited such that the configured code rate is not exceeded; a single paging record is transmitted in any case.

Parameter name: Maximum code rate for random access message 4
Description: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for random access procedure messages 4 (SRB0 message). This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.    Recommended defaults  - for FDD cell: 0.12  - for TDD cell: 0.39    Note:  For small bandwidth system a sufficient number of HARQ retransmissions or according segmentation is applied in order to reach to the configured code rate.

Parameter name: Maximum code rate for random access message 2
Description: The parameter defines:  - the maximum code rate for contention based random access procedure messages 2 (RA response) for FDD.  - the maximum code rate for contention based and for contention free random access procedure messages 2 (RA response) for TDD.    This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.    Note:  For small bandwidth system the number of RAR records per RAR message is limited such that the configured code rate is not exceeded; a single RAR record is transmitted in any case.

Parameter name: Maximum code rate for contention free random access message 2
Description: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for contention free random access procedure messages 2 (RA response). This maximum code rate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.    Note:  For small bandwidth system the number of RAR records per RAR message is limited such that the configured code rate is not exceeded; a single RAR record is transmitted in any case.

Parameter name: Maximum code rate for SIB
Description: The parameter defines the maximum code rate for System Information Broadcast. This maximum coderate is taken into account during PDSCH scheduling.    Recommendation for FDD-cells:  For the cells with a bandwidth of 1.4 MHz and the cells with a bandwidth of 3 MHz where the actCatM 'true', the code rate should be >= 0.12 as lower code rates may not be reached.  For the cells with CATMCEL.actHighHarqInSlimCarrierCatM equal to 'true', the code rate should be >= 0.12 as lower code rates may not be reached.

Parameter name: Structure for DL dynamic power back-off - Maximum DL power backoff value 1
Description: This parameter defines the maximum DL power back-off for 64QAM and/or 256 transmissions depending on configuration.

Parameter name: Structure for DL dynamic power back-off - Maximum DL power backoff value 2
Description: This parameter defines the maximum DL power back-off for QAM256 transmissions depending on configuration.

Parameter name: Maximum GBR-DRB Traffic Limit
Description: Maximum radio resource consumption (PRBs) for GBR traffic in UL and DL  The amount of radio resources (PRBs) is calculated in % of the available PRBs depending on the system.  1.4 MHz = 6 DL PRBS*,  3.0 MHz = 15 DL PRBS*,  For 5 MHz system 25 PRBs*  for 10 MHz system 50 PRBs*  for 15 MHz system 75 PRBs*  for 20 MHz system 100 PRBs* are available  * reduced by common resources like PUCCH, RACCH, PDCCH, SIBs etc. which can consume some PRBs (e.g. 3 PRBs) in average. Features like Slim Carrier where less PRBs are used may also reduce the available PRBs per cell;  LNCEL linked to AirScale ABIC the available PRBs are not only cell BW depending, but also baseband pool load dependent.  LNCEL linked to AirScale ABIO/ABIOL/ABIN/ABINL/ABIP/ABIQ or AirScale ASOE/ASOF or AirScale ASOG/ASOH the available PRBs are not only cell BW depending, but also baseband pool load dependent.    The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise.    maxGbrTrafficLimit is also used for 1.4 and 3 MHz cells (for 1.4. only for congestion handling).  The parameter should be set to a high % value otherwise rather no GBR traffic will be possible in a 1.4 MHz or 3 MHz cell.

Parameter name: High altitude platform PRACH timing advance maximum filter value
Description: This parameter defines the high altitude platform PRACH timing advance maximum filter value.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Maximum number of load balancing partner candidates
Description: Defines the maximum number of LB partner candidates that a cell will establish LB partnerships with.

Parameter name: Maximum NBR-DRB traffic limit
Description: Maximum combined radio resource consumption (PRBs) for GBR and NBR traffic in UL and DL.  The amount of radio resources (PRBs) is calculated in % of the available PRBs depending on the system.  For 5 MHz system 25 PRBs*,  for 10 MHz system 50 PRBs*,  for 15 MHz system 75 PRBs*,  for 20 MHz system 100 PRBs* are available.  * reduced by common resources like PUCCH, RACCH, PDCCH, SIBs etc. which can consume some PRBs (e.g. 3 PRBs) in average.

Parameter name: Max number of NR inter-freq carriers for en-gNB measurements
Description: Optional limit for the maximum number of NR carriers which can be activated by en-gNB at the UE operating in EN-DC mode for NR inter-frequency measurements.  If not provided, the limit is assigned internally by eNB and passed to the en-gNB, otherwise configured value is provided to the en-gNB.  Note, that minimal requirements for the UE operating in EN-DC in terms of supported number of monitored frequency layers are provided in 3GPP TS 36.133, chapter 8.1.2.1.1b Monitoring of multiple layers using gaps (E-UTRA-NR dual connectivity) / 8.1.2.1.1b.1 Maximum allowed layers for multiple monitoring for UE in NSA operation. Those shall not be crossed in planned deployments, unless UEs operating in the given market support higher limits.  In intra- or inter-eNB HO scenario with keeping EN-DC connectivity, when different values of maxNrIfFreqs are set on source and target LTE cells, en-gNB shall support functionality of dynamic update of max allowed number of inter-freq NR carriers during handover.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency load balancing load thresholds - Maximum number of AMLE neighbors
Description: This parameter limits the number of active mode load equalization (AMLE) neighbors per target frequency layer. The same value is valid for each target frequency layer.    In case more inter-frequency neighbors are enabled for AMLE for a certain target frequency layer, layer (LNREL-amleAllowed = 'allowed'), a ranking mechanism based on successful inter-frequency handovers will select the maxNumAmleNeigh highest ranked ones as AMLE candidates. candidates.    Note: A value '0' effectively would disable AMLE for the corresponding target frequency layer.

Parameter name: Maximum number of CA guest UEs in SCell
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs, which use that cell as SCell.

Parameter name: maximum number of inter frequency carriers to be measured
Description: Maximum increased number of inter frequency carriers to be measured simultaneously

Parameter name: Max. number of secondary cells for DL carrier aggr
Description: Maximum number of secondary cells (SCells, S-LNCELs) a UE can get configured in DL carrier aggregation in addition to the primary cell (PCell, P-LNCEL).

Parameter name: Admission Control limit for PUCCH optimization
Description: This parameter sets the maximum limit for increasing maxNumActUE. PUCCH capacity Optimization algorithm will not increase maxNumActUE beyond this limit.

Parameter name: Maximum number of additional non-GBR UEs to schedule
Description: Specifies the maximum additional non-GBR UEs that can be scheduled per TTI if increased latency is a concern. See lowLatencyAddlUeThreshold for additional information.

Parameter name: Maximum amount of UE proactive Ul grants per TTI
Description: This parameter is the maximum amount of UE proactive Ul grants per TTI (all kinds of skippable and incapable of skipping Ul grants). Value of zero means proactive scheduling is turned off.

Parameter name: Maximum number of UE proactive grants to UE incapable of skipping UL grant
Description: This parameter is the maximum amount of all kinds of incapable of skipping proactive UL grants per TTI. Value of zero means incapable of skipping proactive UL grants are not allowed.

Parameter name: Maximum number of VoLTE proactive UL grants per TTI
Description: This is the maximum number of simultaneous (non TTIB) users which can have a VoLTE proactive UL grant per TTI. A value of zero means VoLTE proactive UL grants are turned off.    The following values are allowed for FDD cells:  1.4 MHz: 0...3  3 MHz: 0...3  5 MHz: 0...3  10 MHz: 0 .. 7  15 MHz: 0 .. 8  20 MHz: 0 .. 10    The following values are allowed for TDD cells:  5 MHz: 0 .. 6  10 MHz: 0 .. 7  15 MHz: 0 .. 8  20 MHz: 0 .. 10

Parameter name: Max PDCCH Aggregation
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed aggregation per UE to be required by PDCCH Link Adaptation.

Parameter name: Max PDCCH Aggregation During High PDCCH Load
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed aggregation per UE to be required by PDCCH Link Adaptation when there is high PDCCH loading.

Parameter name: Max PDCCH Aggregation During High PDCCH Load for QCI1
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed aggregation per UE to be required by PDCCH Link Adaptation when there is high PDCCH loading and UE has a QCI1 bearer.  In DL, parameter is applied for DL transmissions with QCI1 data.  In UL, parameter is applied for UL transmissions for a UE with a QCI1 bearer.

Parameter name: Max PDCCH Aggregation During High PDCCH Load for SRB
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed aggregation per UE to be required by PDCCH Link Adaptation when there is high PDCCH loading and grant is for DL SRB.

Parameter name: Max PDCCH Aggregation for QCI1
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed aggregation per UE to be required by PDCCH Link Adaptation for a UE with QCI1 bearer.  In DL, parameter is applied for DL transmissions with QCI1 data.  In UL, parameter is applied for UL transmissions for a UE with a QCI1 bearer.

Parameter name: Max PDCCH Aggregation for SRB
Description: This parameter defines the maximum allowed aggregation per UE to be required by PDCCH Link Adaptation for DL SRB.

Parameter name: Max PDCCH LA CQI shift
Description: This parameter defines the upper limit of the dynamically adjusted CQI shift used in PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation (OLLA).

Parameter name: Max PDCCH LA CQI shift for QCI1
Description: This parameter defines the upper limit of the dynamically adjusted CQI shift used in PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation (OLLA) for a UE with a QCI1 bearer.

Parameter name: Maximum Periodic CQI Increase
Description: This parameter clips the CQI increase as a result of a periodic CQI report.

Parameter name: Max PDCCH Physical CCEs
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of physical CCEs per UE to be allocated on PDCCH

Parameter name: Maximum NBR-DRB PRBs per UE
Description: Maximum number of PRBs allocated for NBR traffic per UE in UL and DL.  The amount of radio resources (PRBs) is calculated in % of the available PRBs depending on the system.  For 5 MHz system 25 PRBs*,  for 10 MHz system 50 PRBs*,  for 15 MHz system 75 PRBs*,  for 20 MHz system 100 PRBs* are available.  * reduced by common resources like PUCCH, RACCH, PDCCH, SIBs etc. which can consume some PRBs (e.g. 3 PRBs) in average.

Parameter name: Max Number of UEs in TCP UL Power Boost
Description: This parameter limits number of UEs in TCP UL Power Boost.

Parameter name: Maximum bitrate selector
Description: Selects whether the UE Capability or O&M parameters limits the Maximum Bitrate UL and Maximum Bitrate DL  if UE capabilities respectively the UE categories are used the limit is per UE; if the O&M parameters are used the limit is for all UEs in the cell.  In case of using DL carrier aggregation for an UE this selector is ignored and in any case the standardized limits (3GPP 36.306) are used for max. number of transport block bits per TTI in DL.

Parameter name: MCC In PLMN
Description: Primary Mobile Country Code of eNB.

Parameter name: Micro-DTX aggressiveness
Description: In FDD cells, if allowTrafficConcentration is set to 'false', mdtxAggressiveness is ignored.    For LTE1891 and LTE1891 fallback from follow-up features, this parameter controls the decision between using a standard muting pattern and applying no muting. If the estimated PRB usage in the upcoming pattern period exceeds the value mdtxAggressiveness, no muting is applied in this upcoming period.  For LTE3036 and follow-up features, it controls the safety margin of PRBs in non-muted subframes in the upcoming period of 40 ms (FDD) or 20 ms (TDD).    It is recommended to set the parameter value to 0.4 in FDD cells and to 0.2 in TDD cells.    If micro-DTX operates with rel4 RF units (LTE1891 fallback-mode), the parameter value is internally limited to 0.6.

Parameter name: Number of non-muted PDCCH symbols if cell is empty
Description: In FDD cells, if allowTrafficConcentration is set to 'false', mdtxPdcchSymb is ignored.    Number of PDCCH symbols left non-muted by micro-DTX, if the cell is empty.  Temporarily overrides the maxNrSymPdcch value for muted subframes, when eNB is in mdtxMinimumState and cell has at least 10 MHz bandwidth. Small values can lead to reduced PRACH performance.

Parameter name: Measurement quantity for UTRA-CSFB FDD measurements
Description: Defines which quantity to use for Event B1 measurements towards this frequency set in QuantityConfigUTRA-FDD.  The quantities used to evaluate the triggering condition for the event.  cpich-RSCP corresponds to CPICH_RSCP in TS 25.133 for FDD, and P-CCPCH_RSCP in TS 25.123 for TDD.  cpich-EcN0 corresponds to CPICH_Ec/No in TS 25.133 for FDD only, and is not applicable for TDD.  This parameter refers to event B1 for CSFB to WCDMA.

Parameter name: Measurement quantity used for 5G SA measurement
Description: Defines which measurement quantity (RSRP or RSRQ) of the 5G SA neighbor cell the UE has to use for triggering B2-NR measurement reporting

Parameter name: Measurement quantity used for UTRA FDD measurements
Description: Defines which quantity to use for Event B1/B2 measurements towards this frequency set in QuantityConfigUTRA    The quantities used to evaluate the triggering condition for the event.  cpich-RSCP corresponds to CPICH_RSCP in TS 25.133 for FDD.  cpich-EcN0 corresponds to CPICH_Ec/No in TS 25.133 for FDD.  This parameter refers to event B1/B2 for HO to WCDMA.

Parameter name: Minimum bitrate downlink
Description: Minimum bit rate that shall be granted in DL TTI.

Parameter name: Minimum bitrate uplink
Description: Minimum bit rate that shall be granted in UL TTI.

Parameter name: High altitude platform PRACH timing advance minimum filter value
Description: This parameter defines the high altitude platform PRACH timing advance minimum filter value.

Parameter name: Minimum remaining inactivity time threshold
Description: Defines the minimum remaining inactivity time below which the UE will be released if a handover is attempted during that time.  Setting the value to 0 effectively disables this functionality.

Parameter name: Min PDCCH LA CQI shift
Description: This parameter defines the lower limit of the dynamically adjusted CQI shift used in PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation (OLLA).

Parameter name: Min PDCCH LA CQI shift for QCI1
Description: This parameter defines the lower limit of the dynamically adjusted CQI shift used in PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation (OLLA) for a UE with QCI1 bearer.

Parameter name: TCP Service Differentiation Configuration - Minimum TCP packet size
Description: This parameter defines the minimum size threshold for a TCP packet. TCP packet size must exceed this threshold in order for the packet to considered in TCP restart/stop boosting logic.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - Mode for calculating the CAC in load bal. and eICIC
Description: This parameter selects the cell load evaluation profile. The selected profile controls the cell resources that are included in the determination of the load condition. In addition, the parameter is used to define the set of UEs that will receive the adjusted CIO value.

Parameter name: MNC In PLMN
Description: Primary Mobile Network Code of eNB.

Parameter name: Mobility profiles mapping list
Description: This parameter maps UE's serving PLMN ID and the UE's SPID (Subscriber Profile ID) to mobility profiles.  Several SPIDs, ranges of SPIDs, PLMN IDs or combination of SPIDs or SPID ranges and PLMN IDs can be mapped to a common Mobility Profile.

Parameter name: LTE-NR Dual Connectivity support
Description: This parameter defines the LTE-NR DC capability for UEs using this mobility profile.    The value 'all' shall be used if this mobility profile shall not differentiate between the UE capability with respect to LTE-NR DC.  The value 'EN-DC_capable' will limit the use of this mobility profile to UEs which are EN-DC-capable.  The value 'EN-DC_not_capable' will limit the use of this mobility profile to UEs which are not EN-DC-capable.

Parameter name: Mobile country code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Country Code of the PLMN ID that shall be mapped to a Mobility Profile.

Parameter name: Mobile network code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Network Code of the PLMN ID that shall be mapped to a Mobility Profile.    The actual range of the MNC depends on the MNC length in the configured entry of the Mobility Profiles Mapping List.

Parameter name: Mobile network code length
Description: Indicates the length of the Mobile Network Code of the PLMN ID that shall be mapped to a Mobility Profile.

Parameter name: Mobility profile ID
Description: Identifier of the Mobility Profile, which shall be mapped to one or more SPIDs and/or PLMN IDs.

Parameter name: Subscriber profile ID
Description: Single SPID value or first SPID value of a range which shall be mapped to a Mobility Profile.  3GPP 36.300 defines the following SPID range:  Values 1-128 are Operator specific SPIDs    Values 129-256 are Reference SPID values  Reference SPIDs have the following meaning:  SPID 256 High prio to eUTRA, Medium prio to UTRAN, Low prio to GERAN  SPID 255 High prio to UTRAN, Medium prio to GERAN, Low prio to eUTRA  SPID 254 High prio to GERAN, Medium prio to UTRAN, Low prio to eUTRA

Parameter name: Last subscriber profile ID of a range
Description: Last SPID value if a range of SPID values shall be mapped to a Mobility Profile.  3GPP 36.300 defines the following SPID range:  Values 1-128 are Operator specific SPIDs    Values 129-256 are Reference SPID values  Reference SPIDs have the following meaning:  SPID 256 High prio to eUTRA, Medium prio to UTRAN, Low prio to GERAN  SPID 255 High prio to UTRAN, Medium prio to GERAN, Low prio to eUTRA  SPID 254 High prio to GERAN, Medium prio to UTRAN, Low prio to eUTRA

Parameter name: Mobility state parameters NCellChangeHigh
Description: The number of cell changes to enter the high mobility state. Corresponds to NCR_H in TS 36.304.

Parameter name: Mobility state parameters NCellChangeMedium
Description: The number of cell changes to enter the medium mobility state. Corresponds to NCR_M in TS 36.304.

Parameter name: Mobility state parameters evaluation
Description: The duration for evaluating criteria to enter mobility states. Corresponds to TCRmax in TS 36.304. Value in seconds, s30 corresponds to 30 s and so on.

Parameter name: Mobility state parameters THystNormal
Description: The additional duration for evaluating criteria to enter the normal mobility state. Corresponds to TCRmaxHyst in TS 36.304. Value in seconds, s30 corresponds to 30 s and so on.

Parameter name: Maximum number of message 3 DTX detections
Description: Message 3 HARQ re-transmissions are enabled with parameter 'msg3ConsecutiveDtx' non-zero values.    HARQ re-transmissions are enabled with the non-zero value of the parameter.  Setting the parameter 'msg3ConsecutiveDtx' to '0' disables layer 2 dtx functionality, and message 3 HARQ re-transmissions.

Parameter name: DTX Offset for message 3 detection
Description: Message 3 DTX offset.  PUSCH SINR offset for DTX detection on layer 2.

Parameter name: CIO adaptation algorithm periodicity multiplier
Description: This value is multiplied by (multLoadMeasRrmEicic * tLoadMeasX2Eicic) to define the execution periodicity of the CIO adaptation algorithm for eICIC in relation to the ABS algorithm for eICIC.    It is recommended to execute the CIO adaptation algorithm less frequent than the ABS adaptation algorithm due to following aspects:  i.) CIO changes take longer time to show in the HetNet area (UEs must be reconfigured and HOs must be executed) as compared to an ABS pattern change,  ii.) eNB processing load is increased due to UE reconfiguration.

Parameter name: Load measurement RRM timer multiplier
Description: This value is multiplied by tLoadMeasX2 to define the periodicity with which the collected available resource reports from the enquired neighbor cells are evaluated

Parameter name: Load measurement RRM timer multiplier for eICIC
Description: This value is multiplied by tLoadMeasX2Eicic to define the periodicity with which the collected available resource reports from the enquired neighbor cells are evaluated by the eNB cell and the periodicity of the ABS algorithm.

Constant n310PubSafety is the maximum number of consecutive "out of sync" indications received from lower layers for UE with established public safety bearers QCI 65/66/67.  For UEs with QCI 65/66/67 DRB established, settings of n310PubSafety will be configured in RRC Connected mode (overwriting SIB2 N310 value) via RRC Connection Reconfiguration message.    Note:  If n310PubSafety is not configured, then the N310 value for the UE are determined based on whether QCI 1 has been established and LNCEL-n310Qci1 is configured. If LNCEL-n310Qci1 is not configured or if QCI 1 is not established, the value from LNCEL-n310 is used.

Parameter name: N310 for QCI1
Description: Constant n310Qci1 is the maximum number of consecutive "out of sync" indications received from lower layers for UE with established QCI1 bearer.  With feature LTE1569 for UEs with established QCI1, settings of n310Qci1 will be configured in RRC Connected mode (overwriting SIB2 T310 value) via RRC Connection Reconfiguration message.

Parameter name: RAC overbooking limit
Description: This parameter sets a limit for the number of QCI#1 bearers which may be admitted by RAC in a LTE cell by temporary overbooking in parallel

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of managed object.

Parameter name: NB-IoT operation mode
Description: The parameter determines FDD NB-IoT (NarrowBand Internet of Things) operation mode.  The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Local cell resource ID of the paired host cell or NB-IoT cell
Description: Local cell resource ID of the paired host cell or NB-IoT cell (inband or guardband)

Parameter name: NBR Congestion Handling
Description: Determine if congestion handling shall be applied if congestion is detected by layer 2.  It is highly recommended to configure the value to 'true' if 'Nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers' is activated, i.e. if actNbrForNonGbrBearers is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: ARP based parameters - scaling factor for nominal bitrates for UL and DL
Description: The scaling factor for nominal bitrates for uplink and downlink, if actNbrForNonGbrBearers is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Nominal maximum antenna gain
Description: This parameter indicates the nominal maximum antenna gain of main lobe on beamforming for EIRP control. The point of zero EIRP restrictions (corresponding to max EIRP) is calculated from highest pMax, antenna TX ports and this parameter.  Note: If this parameter is not configured during EIRP control activation, it will be calculated by internal.    max EIRP calculation: EIRP (dBm) = P_total (dBm) + nomMaxAntennaGain (dBi)  P_total (dBm) = pMax (dBm)+ 10*Log(N)  where:  -pMax is the max power per antenna (corresponding to LNCEL.pMax).  -N is the number of TX ports.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - Nominal number of PRBs for load balancing
Description: This parameter is a scaling factor that serves to map the nonGBR load into the range of 0..100.  nonGBR load samples are obtained in each TTI by addding the scheduling weights of nonGBR bearers which can be served (are ready for scheduling: have data, and UE is available for scheduling), regardless of whether they actually get served. The load samples increase with more data in buffers, with higher scheduling weight, and with more frequent appearance of a bearer as 'ready for scheduling'. The moving average of the load samples, divided by the number of PRBs available for nonGBR, is the raw value of nonGBR load. It can vary over several orders of magnitude. The final nonGBR load is obtained by multiplying the raw value with nomNumPrbNonGbr.  Example: set nomNumPrbNonGbr = 0.05 if an average weight sum of 20000 with 10 PRBs available for non-GBR traffic shall be mapped to 100% load.

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - Threshold for number of carr. aggr. UEs for PCell swap
Description: Defines the threshold for the maximum allowed number of carrier aggregated UEs in the source PCell, which triggers the PCell swap process. The PCell swap process is triggered when the number of carrier aggregated UEs is greater than or equal to this threshold. It is also used in the PCell swap criteria to select SCells as candidates for the PCell swap.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Number of cell segment edges in elevation
Description: The parameter indicates the number of cell segment minus 1 in the elevation direction over which EIRP is monitored.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Number of cell segment edges in azimuth
Description: The parameter indicates the number of cell segment minus 1 in the azimuth direction over which EIRP is monitored.

Parameter name: Intra EUTRA offset frequency
Description: Offset value applicable to the EUTRA serving carrier frequency.  The IE Q-OffsetRange is used to indicate a cell or frequency specific offset to be applied when evaluating candidates for cell re-selection or when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Operational state
Description: This is the operational state of the cell, the value is set by the system.  Note: This parameter used for NB-IoT standalone cell, but not directly used for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Orientation of major axis
Description: Orientation of major axis of uncertainty ellipsoid measured clockwise from north

Parameter name: Nominal power for UE PUCCH TX power calculation
Description: This parameter defines the cell specific nominal power to be used for PUCCH power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P2), for controlling mean received SNR for control data.

Parameter name: Nominal power for UE PUSCH or NPUSCH TX power calculation
Description: This parameter defines the cell-specific nominal power for the PUSCH. Used for P0_PUSCH calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P1) for controlling the mean received SNR for user data during (re)transmission corresponding to a received PDCCH with DCI format 0 associated with a new packet transmission. This parameter is used to control mean received SNR for user data.

Parameter name: Interference aware UL-PC configuration - Nominal PUSCH P0 for interference-aware UL-PC
Description: P0 setting that is broadcast in SIB2 if interference-aware UL-PC is activated.  ulpcAlpha must be set to "alpha 1" for interference-aware UL-PC.

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - PCell frequency layer priority for carrier aggregation
Description: pFreqPrio enters into the optional trigger condition between a PCell and candidate SCells for PCell swapping. The swapping can be triggered additionally to other conditions if the frequency layer priority of candidate SCells (CA/D/PR-sFreqPrio) is higher than the frequency layer priority of the PCell. Use pFreqPrio = 1 (default) for highest priority, pFreqPrio = 10 for lowest priority.

Parameter name: Maximum output power
Description: This parameter defines the maximum output power of the cell per antenna carrier in dBm. The maximum output power is the maximum value for the linear sum of the power of all downlink physical channels and physical signals that is allowed to be used in a cell. The reference point is the antenna connector.  The most common configurable dBm values correspond to following Watt:  10.0 dBm = 10 mW  37.0 dBm = 5 W  39.0 dBm = 8 W  40.0 dBm = 10 W  41.8 dBm = 15 W  43.0 dBm = 20 W  44.3 dBm = 27 W  44.8 dBm = 30 W  46.0 dBm = 40 W  46.5 dBm = 45 W  47.8 dBm = 60 W  49.0 dBm = 80 W  50.0 dBm = 100 W  50.8 dBm = 120 W    For low power RRH the carrier power value is used for repeater(s) connected to low power RRH, where the carrier power value in RRH is fixed. For example FHCB output power is fixed to 10 mW (10 dBm) and FHEC output power is fixed to 1 mW (0 dBm).    Note for LTE-GSM sharing configurations:  45W and 80W power level is only supported in LTE dedicated configuration.    Note: The allowed cell power value which are allowed to be configured depend on the used hardware variant. During online commissioning the WebEM will based on the hardware variant support only the allowed values. Please refer to the documentation where per variant the supported power values are specified.    Note: for RF sharing configurations:  When same antenna line is shared with other technology it needs to be ensured that maximum supported power per antenna line is not exceeded.  Note: This parameter used for NB-IoT standalone cell, but not directly used for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell.      Note: This parameter is disregarded for LAA cells. For details, please, see parameter LNCEL_FDD-pMaxLaa.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Paging nB
Description: Paging nB defines the number of possible paging occasions per radio frame, i.e. the density of paging occasions. This parameter is used to calculate the number of paging occasions within one paging DRX duration, which in turn is used to calculate the paging occasion.
Range and step: oneT (2), halfT (3), quarterT (4), oneEighthT (5), oneSixteenthT (6), oneThirtySecondT (7)

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - Threshold for rate of HOs allowed for PCell swap
Description: Defines the maximum number of outgoing PCell swap handovers per measurement period (HO rate per 500ms) allowed to be executed from a source PCell.

Parameter name: PCI control
Description: The parameter controls, whether the modification of the parameter phyCellId at this instance of LNCEL is allowed only manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct SON algorithms.

Parameter name: PDCCH LA UE default aggregation
Description: The parameter defines default aggregation for UE to be used in PDCCH Link Adaptation when enableAmcPdcch has been disabled or when enableAmcPdcch has been enabled and there is no valid Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) available due to an expiry of the timer determining CQI remembering.

Parameter name: PDCCH LA UE default aggregation for QCI1
Description: The parameter defines default aggregation for a UE with QCI1 bearer to be used in PDCCH Link Adaptation when enableAmcPdcch has been disabled or when enableAmcPdcch has been enabled and there is no valid Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) available due to an expiry of the timer determining CQI remembering.  In DL, parameter is applied for DL transmissions with QCI1 data.  In UL, parameter is applied for UL transmissions for a UE with a QCI1 bearer.

Parameter name: PDCCH LA UE default aggregation for SRB
Description: The parameter defines default aggregation for grant associated with DL SRB to be used in PDCCH Link Adaptation when enableAmcPdcch has been disabled or when enableAmcPdcch has been enabled and there is no valid Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) available due to an expiry of the timer determining CQI remembering.

Parameter name: PDCCH aggregation for RA msg4
Description: The parameter defines the reserved number of Control Channel Elements (CCEs) for dedicated Random Access Message 4 assignment on PDCCH.

Parameter name: PDCCH aggregation for paging
Description: PDCCH aggregation for paging defines how many CCEs shall be used for one PDCCH.

Parameter name: PDCCH aggregation level for preamble assignments
Description: The parameter defines the aggregation level by means of control channel elements (CCEs) for preamble assignments on PDCCH. The preamble assignment is message 0 sent during the non-contention based Random Access procedure if DL data arrives during UL out-of-sync.

Parameter name: PDCCH aggregation for random access response message
Description: The parameter defines:  - the PDCCH aggregation (number of CCEs used for one PDCCH) for contention based random access procedure messages 2 (RA response) for FDD.  - the PDCCH aggregation (number of CCEs used for one PDCCH) for contention based and for contention free random access procedure messages 2 (RA response) for TDD.

Parameter name: PDCCH aggregation for contention free random access response message
Description: PDCCH aggregation for contention free Random Access response message and minimum PDCCH aggregation for HARQ retransmissions of a non-contention based Random Access Procedure initial transmission defines how many effective CCEs (actual CCEs + CCE power boost) are used for one PDCCH:  Value of 4 = 4 CCEs + 0 dB power boost  Value of 8 = 8 CCEs + 0 dB power boost  Value of 12 = 8 CCEs + 1.8 dB power boost  Value of 16 = 8 CCEs + 3 dB power boost    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: PDCCH aggregation for secondary system information
Description: PDCCH aggregation for secondary system information defines how many CCEs should be used for one PDCCH.

Parameter name: PDCCH allocation limit
Description: The parameter defines the limit for PDCCH allocations. PDCCH UE-specific search space capacity is multiplied by this factor.    Note for FDD cells:  The parameter will be ignored if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.  If dlChBw equals '3 MHz' it is recommended to set the parameter to '1.0'.

Parameter name: PDCCH congestion control for DL NBR traffic
Description: This parameter activates PDCCH congestion control for Downlink NBR traffic.    It is highly recommended to configure the value to 'true' if 'Nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers' is activated, i.e. if actNbrForNonGbrBearers is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: PDCCH congestion control for UL NBR traffic
Description: This parameter activates PDCCH congestion control for Uplink NBR traffic.    It is highly recommended to configure the value to 'true' if 'Nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers' is activated, i.e. if actNbrForNonGbrBearers is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: PDCCH CQI offset for QCI1
Description: Provides the CQI link adaptation offset applied to DL transmissions with QCI1 data.  The more negative the value, the more conservative PDCCH aggregation level will be for UE transmissions.  If a DL transmission has both QCI1 and SRB content then offset from dlSrbCqiOffset is applied

Parameter name: PDCCH LA CQI shift
Description: The fine-tuning parameter for adjustment of measured and averaged CQI towards lower or higher aggregation in PDCCH Link Adaptation.    The parameter gives the initial starting point for PDCCH shift dynamic control in case actOlLaPdcch is true.    The configured PDCCH CQI shift value is automatically adjusted for control channels boosting in need basis.

Parameter name: PDCCH CQI shift for 4Tx
Description: Adjustment of measured and averaged CQI to allow a slightly more conservative choice of PDCCH aggregation level with 4Tx. Adjustment will only be applied by cell if it is configured for 4Tx.

Parameter name: PDCCH and HARQ response target BLER
Description: BLER target for PDCCH outer loop link adaptation in percent.  Defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) of PDCCH and UL HARQ response for initial downlink transmissions for PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation in percents.  If PDCCH OLLA is additionally based on PUSCH TX/DTX detection, the parameter defines target Block Error Ratio (BLER) of PDCCH and PUSCH missed detection for initial uplink transmissions for PDCCH Outer Loop Link Adaptation in percents.

Parameter name: PDCCH Order Configuration
Description: This parameter enables/disables PDCCH order usage for UEs in out of sync state. If set to 'enabled' or if not configured, PDCCH order can be triggered for any traffic type. If set to 'disabled', PDCCH order is not triggered for DL user data but is still triggered for RRC signaling.

Parameter name: PDCCH LA UL DL allocation balance initial value
Description: PDCCH allocation balance initial between UL and DL for load adaptive PDCCH    The parameter determines initial value the PDCCH allocation balance constant between uplink and downlink. The Load Adaptive PDCCH algorithm optimizes the value depending on the actual load distribution between DL and UL  In fact, the PDCCH UE-specific search space capacity is divided into uplink and downlink based on the parameter before dynamic schedulings.  The parameter pdcchUlDlBal (PDCCH LA UL DL allocation balance constant) has been originally introduced as fixed factor of split of UL and DL PDCCH resources. When Usage Based PDCCH is activated by means of parameter actLdPdcch, the pdcchUlDlBal parameter is used as an initial value of the split and as a sort of target value of the algorithm adapting the split.    Note for FDD cells:  Please note that the parameter is ignored if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.

Parameter name: Decision period for channel quality estimation
Description: Decision period for channel quality estimation.

Parameter name: Decision period for channel quality estimation for UL
Description: Decision period for channel quality estimation for UL.

Parameter name: Periodic CQI feedback type
Description: Parameter determines if Wideband CQI or UE_selected subband CQI report mode for periodic CQI reporting on PUCCH or PUSCH should be used.  If periodicCqiFeedbackType is set to UE_selected subband CQI this means that UEs supporting subband CQI (proved via check of FGI) use it and UEs which do not support subband CQI will use wideband CQI.    Note for the case where periodic subband CQI reporting is enabled together with DRX functionality (actDrx):  It may not be possible to synchronize DRX start offset such that the wideband CQI report is received during the DRX OnDuration (due to periodicities) and that may cause small performance degradation in DL whenever fresh wideband channel quality information cannot be get in time. It is up to an operator whether to prevent activation of periodic subband CQI reporting and DRX in parallel because of this restriction.

Parameter name: Physical layer cell identity
Description: Physical layer cell identity defines a cell uniquely.  It consists of two parts; physical layer cell identity group and physical layer identity, and is calculated with the following formula:  physical layer cell identity = 3 x physical layer cell identity group + physical layer identity.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.  Guidance for configuration:  Neighbor cells should have different values, and in a three cell eNB all cells should have phyCellId which belongs to same physical layer cell identity group. For example, in a three cell eNB, good PhyCellIds values are 0, 1, 2

Parameter name: PRACH control
Description: The parameter controls, whether the modification of the PRACH parameters at this instance of LNCEL is allowed only manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct SON algorithms.

Parameter name: PRACH detection threshold scaling
Description: Scaling factor for PRACH preamble detection threshold. Increasing the PRACH preamble detection threshold will decrease detection sensitivity. In this case less ghost preambles are detected.Decreasing the PRACH preamble detection will increase detection sensitivity, leading to increased ghost preamble detection.    3GPP specification (3GPP 36.104) defined performance is ensured, only when the prachDetThresScaling has been configured to '1'.

Parameter name: Assigned preemption profile
Description: Identifier of the preemption profile (PREEMPPR) instance which shall apply for the cell

Parameter name: Prevent cell activation
Description: This parameter prevents cell activation.  If this parameter is set to true, then the cell can't be set to unlocked.  Note: This parameter used for NB-IoT standalone cell, but not directly used for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: PRS bandwidth
Description: PRS Bandwidth in terms of PRBs.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: PRS muting - PRS muting info
Description: The prsMutingInfo is a bit string consisting of 16 bit. Only the first prsMutingInfoPatternLen bits will be taken into account starting from prsMutingInfoBit1.  This means the first prsMutingInfoPatternLen bits of the prsMutingInfo bit string will determine the PRS Muting Info pattern with a given periodicity. Details of the description can be found in TS36.355.  Muting configuration allows to increase the reuse of the PRS signal. PRS of individual cells can be muted in order to increase hearability of cells with the same frequency reuse.    WebUI:  When prsMutingInfoBit is not ticked (meaning bit has value '0'), respective PRS occurrence is muted, and when prsMutingInfoBit is ticked (meaning bit has value '1'), respective PRS occurrence is transmitted (not muted).
Range and step: bits mask: prsMutingInfoBit16 (0), prsMutingInfoBit15 (1), prsMutingInfoBit14 (2), prsMutingInfoBit13 (3), prsMutingInfoBit12 (4), prsMutingInfoBit11 (5), prsMutingInfoBit10 (6), prsMutingInfoBit9 (7), prsMutingInfoBit8 (8), prsMutingInfoBit7 (9), prsMutingInfoBit6 (10), prsMutingInfoBit5 (11), prsMutingInfoBit4 (12), prsMutingInfoBit3 (13), prsMutingInfoBit2 (14), prsMutingInfoBit1 (15)

Parameter name: PRS muting - PRS muting info pattern length
Description: The prsMutingInfoPatternLen determines how many PRS Muting Info Bits are used to describe PRS muting sequence. The sequence starts from the prsMutingInfoBit1 and it corresponds to the first positioning occasion, prsMutingInfoBit2 corresponds to second positioning occasion and so on.

Parameter name: PRS power boost
Description: Power Boosting for PRS increases hearability and allows for a more flexible use of the DL Tx power.    With de-boosting it is possible to lower PRS power in interference sensitive areas.  PRS power is related to DL RS power, and when prsPowerBoost is set to value 0dB, and dlRsBoost is set to same 0dB value, PRS and DL RS has same power in each TX Antenna.    Note also the case when actPrsTxDiv is TRUE. Power is same in each TX Antenna, but as PRS is transmitted at the same time from each used TX Antenna, sum of PRS power over all TX Antennas are higher. To compensate power in TxDiv case, prsPowerBoost can be set to proper value. See examples below:    Example 1:  dlMimoMode is set to TxDiv, value -3 dB sets the sum of PRS power to equal to DL RS power.    Example 2:  dlMimoMode is set to 4-way TxDiv, value -6 dB sets the sum of PRS power to equal to DL RS power.    Example 3:  dlMimoMode is set to Closed Loop MIMO (4x2), value -3 dB sets the sum of PRS power to equal to DL RS power.

Parameter name: PUCCH Control
Description: The parameter controls, whether the modification of PUCCH parameters at this instance of LNCEL is allowed only manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct SON algorithms.

Parameter name: PUSCH decoding offset index for ACK
Description: The parameter defines the delta offset index for the decoding of the HARQ ACK / NACK information on PUSCH channel.

Parameter name: PUSCH decoding offset index for CQI
Description: The parameter defines the delta offset index for the decoding of the Channel Quality Indicator (CQI) / precoding matrix indicator information on PUSCH channel.

Parameter name: PUSCH HARQ Retransmission Mode
Description: This parameter determines the default PUSCH HARQ retransmission mode.

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - PUSCH load index hysteresis for PCell swap
Description: Prevents ping-pong behavior if the PUSCH load varies only slightly between a number of candidate cells for PCell Swap. The hysteresis is configured as a percentage of the PUSCH load index. Once triggered, the PCell Swap feature will attempt to reduce PUSCH load until the PUSCH load index falls below the configured threshold, minus the configured hysteresis percentage. So, with puschLoadIndexThr = 0.5 and puschLoadHyst = 0.2 (20%), PCell Swap attempts will stop if puschLoadIndex falls below (1-0.2)*0.5 = 0.4    It is also used in the PCell swap criteria to select SCells as candidates for the PCell swap.

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - PUSCH load index threshold for PCell swap
Description: This parameter defines the threshold value against which puschLoadIndex is compared. The PCell swap process is triggered when the puschLoadIndex is greater than or equal to this threshold. This threshold is used as one criterion for switching into "PCell Swap Active" state, and also for candidate cell selection. PUSCH load index is a measure of the cell's load situation, for PUSCH only. puschLoadIndex is the ratio a/b of the values:  a: average number of UEs found in each TTI that are available for scheduling and have data in UL buffers of bearers in non-GBR logical channel groups (i.e., waiting for non-GBR service), set to 0.001 if the measured value is smaller;  b: average number of UL PRBs which are available (after resources have been allocated for GBR bearers and for the duty parts of nonGBR bearers with nominal bit rate, NBR) for non-GBR traffic.  Higher values indicate higher PUSCH load in the cell.  PUSCH load index increases with the number of UEs waiting for nonGBR service. It also increases with each GBR / NBR bearer that is admitted in the cell and is given resources in the scheduling rounds for GBR and duty parts of NBR bearers. Conversely, the UL load index decreases with decreasing numbers of UEs with nonGBR traffic, and with decreasing number and bandwidth of GBR / NBR bearers.  UL load index can vary across a wide value range because the average number of UEs can range from fractions of 1 up to several hundreds, and because GBR/NBR bearers can consume any number between zero and almost all of the cell's UL resources.

Parameter name: PUSCH decoding offset index for rank indicator
Description: The parameter defines the delta offset index for the decoding of the Rank Indicator information on the PUSCH channel.

Parameter name: Configuration for QCI1 BLER and HARQ Targets - DL target BLER for QCI1
Description: Dedicated BLER target for DL LA in % for QCI1.

Parameter name: Configuration for QCI1 BLER and HARQ Targets - UL AMC target BLER for QCI1
Description: Dedicated Target BLER for AMC UL for QCI1

Parameter name: Extended VoLTE Talk Time Configuration for QCI1 - DL target BLER for QCI1
Description: Dedicated BLER target for DL LA in % for QCI1

Parameter name: Extended VoLTE Talk Time Configuration for QCI1 - eVTT Maximum number of HARQ transmission in DL for QCI1
Description: Indicates the dedicated Maximum number of HARQ transmission for QCI1 in DL, when in RRC_Connect mode in the cell.  This setting is used not only at a QCI1 bearer setup and when the UE's throughput falls below a calculated throughput threshold

Parameter name: Extended VoLTE Talk Time Configuration for QCI1 - Maximum number of HARQ transmission in UL for QCI1
Description: Indicates the dedicated Maximum number of HARQ transmission for QCI1 in UL, which is configured for each UE when in RRC_Connect mode in the cell.

Parameter name: Configuration for QCI1 BLER and HARQ Targets - Maximum number of HARQ transmission in DL for QCI1
Description: Indicates the dedicated Maximum number of HARQ transmission for QCI1 in DL, when in RRC_Connect mode in the cell.  This setting is used not only at a QCI1 bearer setup and when the UE's throughput falls below a calculated throughput threshold

Parameter name: Configuration for QCI1 BLER and HARQ Targets - Maximum number of HARQ transmission in UL for QCI1
Description: Indicates the dedicated Maximum number of HARQ transmission for QCI1 in UL, which is configured for each UE when in RRC_Connect mode in the cell.

Parameter name: QCI1 protection timer
Description: The timer determines the maximum time between QCI1 bearer establishment and the release of the UE to RRC idle mode.  QCI1 establishment starts a configurable timer which keeps the UE in RRC connected mode even if there is no activity (e.g. during ringtone) until timer expiry.

Parameter name: Extended VoLTE Talk Time Configuration for QCI1 - HARQ and BLER reconfiguration timer for QCI1
Description: Dedicated HARQ and BLER reconfiguration timer for QCI1. When this timer expires UL-S and/or DL-S are entitled to perform a reconfiguration of HARQ and BLER parameters if throughput measures of the UE are such that require they reconfiguration.

Parameter name: QCI1 RRC Connection Release prohibit timer
Description: The timer determines the time that WB (Wide band) UE, for which last QCI1 was released, is kept in RRC Connected mode and user inactivity and UE Context Release procedure is delayed.  Last QCI1 release re-starts fixed C-Plane inactivity timer with configurable value which keeps the UE in RRC connected mode longer even if there is no activity until timer expiry.

Parameter name: Extended VoLTE Talk Time Configuration for QCI1 - Multiplication factor for the QCI1 traffic in downlink
Description: Multiplication factor for the QCI1 traffic (based on GBR) to achieve the qci1MaxThroughputDl.

Parameter name: Extended VoLTE Talk Time Configuration for QCI1 - Multiplication factor for the QCI1 traffic in uplink
Description: Multiplication factor for the QCI1 traffic (based on GBR) to achieve the qci1MaxThroughputUl.

Parameter name: Extended VoLTE Talk Time Configuration for QCI1 - UL AMC target BLER for QCI1
Description: Dedicated Target BLER for AMC UL for QCI1

Parameter name: High water mark to trigger use of different PF Alpha metric in DL TD and FD scheduling steps
Description: Defines the lower threshold (in bits per PRB) for a UE to be considered high spectral efficiency user. If UE is in this category 'dlsPfAlphaHigh' is used for calculating PF metric in TD and FD scheduling steps

Parameter name: Low water mark to trigger use of different PF Alpha metric in DL TD and FD scheduling steps
Description: Defines the upper threshold (in bits per PRB) for a UE to be considered low spectral efficiency user. If UE is in this category 'dlsPfAlphaLow' is used for calculating PF metric in TD and FD scheduling steps

Parameter name: High water mark to trigger use of different PF Alpha metric in UL TD and FD scheduling steps
Description: Defines the lower threshold (in TBS bits) for a UE to be considered high spectral efficiency user. If UE is in this category 'ulsPfAlphaHigh' is used for calculating PF metric in TD and FD scheduling steps

Parameter name: Low water mark to trigger use of different PF Alpha metric in UL TD and FD scheduling steps
Description: Defines the upper threshold (in TBS bits) for a UE to be considered low spectral efficiency user. If UE is in this category 'ulsPfAlphaLow' is used for calculating PF metric in TD and FD scheduling steps

Parameter name: Maximum contention resolution timer
Description: The maximum contention resolution timer parameter defines the maximum amount of time allowed for contention resolution.

Parameter name: Large size random access MCS in uplink
Description: Defines the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used for large size random access message 3 in case of initial access or handover.    The size of the large size Random Access Msg3 may be restricted depending on the setting of raLargeMcsUl. For FDD cells with smaller bandwidth following applies:  - for '1.4 MHz': if raLargeMcsUl is equal to the default, the TBS of Msg3 is 328 bit  - for '3 MHz': if raLargeMcsUl is equal to the default, the TBS of Msg3 is 504 bit

Parameter name: RA message power offset for group B selection
Description: Path loss threshold in dB required for selecting one of the two groups of Random Access preambles.  The UE will only use preambles from group B if it needs to send a large Msg3 AND its measured path loss is less than Pmax - PREAMBLE_INITIAL_RECEIVED_TARGET_POWER - DELTA_PREAMBLE_MSG3 - messagePowerOffsetGroupB (see 36.321 ch 5.1.2)

Parameter name: Number of random access preambles
Description: This parameter determines the total number of non-dedicated RA preambles that a UE can select from (i.e. for contention based RA). The minimum cannot be zero.

Parameter name: Random access preambles group A size
Description: Defines the size of the Random Access preambles Group A.

Parameter name: Random access response window size
Description: Random Access Response Window Size parameter defines the window size for the random access response in TTIs.    Notes:  For FDD cells if eICIC feature is activated a value higher than default 7 is recommended to be used.    For TDD cells with ...  - Preamble format 0:  If the UL/DL configuration is 0 or 1 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 5.  If the UL/DL configuration is 2 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 4.  - Preamble format 1:  If the UL/DL configuration is 0 or 1 and the special subframe configuration is 5 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 4.  - Preamble format 2:  If the UL/DL configuration is 1 and the special subframe configuration is 5, 6 or 9 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 4.  - Preamble format 4:  If the UL/DL configuration is 0 and the special subframe configuration is 6, 7 or 9 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 3.  If the UL/DL configuration is 0 and the special subframe configuration is 5 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 7.  If the UL/DL configuration is 1 and the special subframe configuration is 6, 7 or 9 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 3.  If the UL/DL configuration is 1 and the special subframe configuration is 5 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 6.  If the UL/DL configuration is 2 and the special subframe configuration is 6, 7 or 9 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 3.  If the UL/DL configuration is 2 and the special subframe configuration is 5 then the raRespWindowSize must be set to a value greater than or equal to 5.

Parameter name: Small size random access MCS in uplink
Description: Defines the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) to be used for the small size random access message 3 in case of UL or DL data arrival.

Parameter name: Small size random access data volume in uplink
Description: Defines the data volume to be used for small size Random Access message 3 in case of UL or DL data arrival.

Parameter name: Random challenge value
Description: Defines the random challenge value.  This parameter is sent in the RRC CSFBParametersResponseCDMA2000 messages during CDMA2000 1xRTT pre-registration procedure; and it is also sent in the RRC HandoverFromEUTRAPreparationRequest and S1AP UPLINK S1 CDMA2000 TUNNELING during the 1x Circuit Switched Fallback (1xCSFB) and 1x Single Radio Voice Call Continuity (1xSRVCC) procedure.

Parameter name: RBR configuration - Consider cell PRB usage in RBR
Description: Indicates, whether the status of unused PRBs of the cell shall be taken into consideration for the bit rate recommendation as upper limit;

Parameter name: RBR configuration - RBR DL queries response mode
Description: This parameter determines, if UE RBR queries for DL are answered with the available bit rate (ABR) value in UL or with RBR index = 0 (indicating that no bit rate recommendation is given).  Value 'None': No bit rate recommendation is given, but rbrIndex = 0 is sent  Value 'UL_RBR': eNB uses UL RBR

Parameter name: RBR configuration - Maximal RBR index
Description: Maximal RBR index to be used. See Table 6.1.3.13-1 in 3GPP TS 36.321, Ch. 6.1.3.13.

Parameter name: RBR configuration - Ave. meas. time for avail. bit rate measurement
Description: Averaging time of available bit rate measurements (done per PHR report) for use in unsolicited RBR recommendations and in responses to UE RBR queries.    It is recommended to set this parameter to a value at least 10 times greater than the value of LNCEL-tPeriodicPhr.

Parameter name: RBR configuration - RBR operational mode
Description: RBR operational mode to support UE RBR queries AND/OR unsolicited eNB recommendations:  0:UeQueryAllowed  1:eNbUnsolicitedAllowed  2:bothAllowed

Parameter name: RBR configuration - RBR additional power headroom UL
Description: The correction factor applied to reported PHR while calculating UL RBR. The bigger the value, the more conservative the UL RBR value.

Parameter name: RBR configuration - RBR query wait timer
Description: Prohibit timer to be used by the UE for initiating RBR queries.  The parameter corresponds to the bitRateQueryProhibitTimer specified in 3GPP TS 36.321 and TS 36.331.  A value of zero means no prohibit timer, i.e., no restriction.

Parameter name: RBR configuration - Step size for RBR index down-switching
Description: Step size for RBR index used in unsolicited RBR messages for down-switching.

Parameter name: RBR configuration - Step size for RBR index up-switching
Description: Step size for RBR index used in unsolicited RBR messages for up-switching.

Parameter name: RBR configuration - RBR wait timer for next RBR message for up-switching
Description: Wait time before the next unsolicited RBR message for up-switching can be sent.

Parameter name: DL rate capping AMBR margin
Description: The parameter determines the multiplier for non-GBR (non-Guaranteed Bit Rate) radio bearers AMBR (Aggregated Maximum Bit Rate) in order to consider overhead caused by PDCP and RLC layers.

Parameter name: Rate capping AMBR margin in uplink
Description: Margin factor for the comparison of the measured AMBR and the UE AMBR in uplink.

Parameter name: Enable rate capping in downlink
Description: The parameter switches the rate capping functionality on/off in downlink direction. Rate capping functionality in downlink restricts non-GBR (non-Guaranteed Bit Rate) radio bearers bitrate to AMBR (Aggregated Maximum Bit Rate).

Parameter name: Enable rate capping in uplink
Description: Enabling/disabling of rate capping in uplink.

Parameter name: Enable reduced bandwidth DL
Description: The parameter switches Restricted RB Assignment functionality on/off in the downlink direction. When the functionality is enabled, the UE-specific PRB assignment is restricted to a limit defined in the redBwMaxRbDl parameter.

Parameter name: Maximum number of PRBs assigned in downlink
Description: This parameter defines the maximum UE-specific PRB assignment per TTI in downlink. Note that this value will be rounded up in the RRM algorithm to fit the system bandwidth dependent RGB granularity.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Restricted PRB assignment in uplink configuration - Maximum number of PRBs assigned in uplink
Description: Defines the maximum number of PRBs which may be assigned to a UE scheduled in UL when restricted PRB assignment in uplink is enabled.  Note that the actual number of PRBs in UL allocation must be of the form 2^i*3^j*5^k where i, j and k are non-negative integers, so effectively the value will be rounded down to the next value complying with the rule.    Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are:  - if ulChBw is set to '1.4 MHz':6  - if ulChBw is set to '3 MHz': 15  - if ulChBw is set to '5 MHz': 25  - if ulChBw is set to '10 MHz': 50  - if ulChBw is set to '15 MHz': 75  - if ulChBw is set to '20 MHz':100    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Restricted PRB assignment in uplink configuration - Minimum number of PRBs assigned in uplink
Description: Defines the minimum number of PRBs which may be assigned to a UE scheduled in UL when restricted PRB assignment in uplink is enabled. However, a lower number of PRBs is allowed if the transport block size with this number of PRBs and the MCS selected by AMC would exceed the UE capabilities.  Note that the actual amount of PRBs in UL allocation must be of the form 2^i*3^j*5^k where i, j and k are non-negative integers, so effectively the value will be rounded up to the next value complying with the rule.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Enable restricted PRB assignment in uplink
Description: Enabling/disabling the restricted PRB assignment functionality in uplink.

Parameter name: Periodical measurements for location services - Report amount periodical meas for location
Description: Number of periodic ReportStrongestCells measurement reports configured at the UE for Location Services

Parameter name: Periodical measurements for location services - Report interval periodical meas for location
Description: Time interval between two consecutive periodic ReportStrongestCells measurement reports configured at the UE for Location Services

Parameter name: Requested maximum number of DL CCs offset
Description: This parameter and the parameter LNCEL-maxNumScells are used to determine the requestedMaxCCsDL-13 IE value that is sent in the RRC UE Capability Enquiry message. The requestedMaxCCsDL-13 is equal to: reqMaxCCsDlOffset + maxNumScells + 1.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell id - CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell cell ID
Description: Defines the cell ID  Defines the cell ID used by this cell to build the CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell ID when tunnelling the CDMA2000-PDU message from UE to the proper destination node in the CDMA2000 RAT via MME.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT cell ID info
Description: This parameter indicates whether 1x cell Identifier shall be used by this cell to build IE "CDMA2000 1xRTT Pilot List" when sending UPLINK S1 CDMA2000 TUNNELING message to the MME during e1xCSFB and 1xSRVCC Handover preparation procedure.  Value 0 means "000": A Cell Identifier field is not included for this pilot. The pilot is an actual 1x pilot.    Value 1 means "001": A 1x Cell Identifier field is included for this pilot. The pilot is an actual 1x pilot.    LNRELXs created by feature LTE2562(O&M assisted CDMA2000 1xRTT ANR ) are only intended to be used in rttCellIdInfo '000' mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT CSFB type
Description: Defines the 1xCSFB type which shall be used in the cell. If set to forbidden, 1xCSFB is not allowed; if set to R81xCsfbEnforced, R8 1xCSFB with redirection shall be enforced; if set to R9e1xCsfb, R9 enhanced 1x Circuit Switched Fallback (e1xCSFB) will be attempted.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell id - CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell market ID
Description: Defines the Market ID  Defines the Market ID used by this cell to build the CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell ID when tunnelling the CDMA2000-PDU message from UE to the proper destination node in the CDMA2000 RAT via MME.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell id - CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell sector ID
Description: Defines the sector ID  Defines the sector ID used by this cell to build the CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell ID when tunnelling the CDMA2000-PDU message from UE to the proper destination node in the CDMA2000 RAT via MME.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell id - CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell switch number
Description: Defines the switch number  Defines the switch number used by this cell to build the CDMA2000 1xRTT reference cell ID when tunnelling the CDMA2000-PDU message from UE to the proper destination node in the CDMA2000 RAT via MME.

Parameter name: SCell release load margin
Description: This parameter is used to determine whether a cell is in high load state so that the longest no scheduled SCells will be released. A cell reaches high load state if the number of hosted SCells or the number of RRC connections in the cell reach the configurable percentage (sCellReleaseLoadMargin) of the total allowed values.

Parameter name: Service based handover mode
Description: This parameter is used to configure in which mode Service Based HO will select UEs to be candidates for Service Based HO.  If this parameter is set to 'all', then all UEs with QCI1 will be candidates for SB HO.  If this parameter is set to 'ec', then all UEs with QCI1 and emergency ARP will be candidates for SB HO.  If this parameter is set to 'ec_no_rstd', then all UEs with QCI1 and emergency ARP, which do not support RSTD in UE Capabilities, will be candidates for SB HO.

Parameter name: Maximum number of bad channel quality estimations for SCell
Description: Defines the maximum number of channel quality estimations performed by an SCell in bad channel quality monitoring state triggered by CRL-26379. The Scell is kept in the monitoring states while the number of estimations is below this number. If the result of the last channel quality estimation is 'bad', the SCell will be released with 'bad channel quality'. Note that if any channel quality estimation while in this monitoring state is 'good' the SCell will be returned to normal active state where scheduling in the SCell is allowed.

Parameter name: Threshold for a SCell detected -  bad channel quality
Description: Defines the maximum modulation and coding scheme (MCS) index estimated for transmission from the secondary cell (SCell) to infer that the SCell is detected with bad channel quality by the served UE. If the estimated MCS index is smaller than this threshold for the pre-defined decision period (shortPeriodScellChEst or longPeriodScellChEst ), data transmission from the SCell is suspended and, depending on the configured multScellReleaseTimer parameter value, multScellReleaseTimer is started.  The "MCS" mentioned here is the "wideband MCS", i.e. it is assumed that all the PRBs are used for transmission.

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - Threshold for SCell channel quality for PCell swap
Description: Defines the minimum modulation and coding scheme (MCS) index applied for transmission from the SCell to infer that the SCell has sufficient good channel quality to accept the UE for PCell swap.  The quality thresholds are intended for pre-rel.12 UEs. For rel.12 UEs configured for 256QAM usage in the DL, an internal conversion is operated by the eNB.

Parameter name: Scell fast downlink scheduling selection
Description: This parameter selects the fast downlink SCell scheduling method after SCell activation in the PCell.

Parameter name: Threshold for a SCell detected -  good channel quality
Description: Defines the minimum modulation and coding scheme (MCS) index estimated for transmission from the secondary cell (SCell) to infer that the SCell is detected with good channel quality by the served UE. If the estimated MCS index is greater than this threshold for the pre-defined decision period (shortPeriodScellChEst or longPeriodScellChEst), data transmission from the SCell is resumed and multScellReleaseTimer is stopped if running.  The "MCS" mentioned here is the "wideband MCS", i.e. it is assumed that all the PRBs are used for transmission.

Parameter name: Threshold for a not detectable Scell
Description: Defines the maximum modulation and coding scheme (MCS) index estimated for transmission from the secondary cell (SCell) to infer that the SCell is not detectable by the served UE. If the estimated MCS index is smaller than this threshold for the pre-defined decision period (shortPeriodScellChEst or longPeriodScellChEst ), data transmission from the SCell is suspended and, depending on the configured multScellReleaseTimer parameter value, the SCell is released.  The "MCS" mentioned here is the "wideband MCS", i.e. it is assumed that all the PRBs are used for transmission.

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - State of the SCell for which PCell swap is allowed
Description: Defines the state of the SCell in which a PCell swap is allowed. Possible configurations are to allow it for any configured SCells or for activated SCells only.

Parameter name: ARP based parameters - scaling factor for scheduling weight
Description: The scaling factor for scheduling weight for uplink and downlink if actNonGbrServiceDiff is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 0
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge0 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from -90 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge0 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge0 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge0 to segmentAzimuthEdge1 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise. If not configured, there is a single cell segment from -90 degree to 90 degree.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 1
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge1 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge0 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge1 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge1 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge1 to segmentAzimuthEdge2 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 2
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge2 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge1 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge2 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge2 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge2 to segmentAzimuthEdge3 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 3
