Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge3 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge2 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge3 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge3 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge3 to segmentAzimuthEdge4 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 4
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge4 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge3 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge4 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge4 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge4 to segmentAzimuthEdge5 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 5
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge5 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge4 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge5 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge5 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge5 to segmentAzimuthEdge6 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 6
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge6 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge5 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge6 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge6 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge6 to segmentAzimuthEdge7 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 7
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge7 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge6 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge7 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge7 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge7 to segmentAzimuthEdge8 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge azimuth 8
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in azimuth (segmentAzimuthEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentElevationEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge8 as an upper azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge7 degree to segmentAzimuthEdge8 while the cell segments sharing segmentAzimuthEdge8 as a lower azimuth edge cover azimuth range from segmentAzimuthEdge8 to 90 degree.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge elevation 0
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in elevation (segmentElevationEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentAzimuthEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge0 as an upper elevation edge cover elevation range from -90 degree to segmentElevationEdge0 while the cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge0 as a lower elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge0 to segmenElevationEdge1 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise. If not configured, there is a single cell segment from -90 degree to 90 degree.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge elevation 1
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in Elevation (segmentElevationEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentAzimuthEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge1 as an upper elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge0 degree to segmentElevationEdge1 while the cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge1 as a lower elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge1 to segmentElevationEdge2 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge elevation 2
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in Elevation (segmentElevationEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentAzimuthEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge2 as an upper elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge1 degree to segmentElevationEdge2 while the cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge2 as a lower elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge2 to segmentElevationEdge3 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge elevation 3
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in Elevation (segmentElevationEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentAzimuthEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge3 as an upper elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge2 degree to segmentElevationEdge3 while the cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge3 as a lower elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge3 to segmentElevationEdge4 if configured, to 90 degree otherwise.

Parameter name: EIRP control - Cell segment edge elevation 4
Description: This parameter indicates a boundary in Elevation (segmentElevationEdge) between two consecutive cell segments sharing the same segmentAzimuthEdge index. The cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge4 as an upper elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge3 degree to segmentElevationEdge4 while the cell segments sharing segmentElevationEdge4 as a lower elevation edge cover elevation range from segmentElevationEdge4 to 90 degree.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - SFN initialisation time
Description: SFN Initialisation Time in seconds relative to 00:00:00 on 1 January 1900 where the integer part is in the first 32 bits and the fraction part in the last 32bits    [0]:second part  [1]:fraction part

Parameter name: SFN offset
Description: The parameter defines the SFN offset for the cell. The defined offset is observed as a shift of the frame number at the air interface with the reference to the BTS clock (as best represented by its 1PPS output).    Restrictions:  - If frameStartOffset is configured for the cell, then sfnOffset must be also configured.  - The cell with the configured offset must be connected to eCPRI or CPRI-N capable radio modules. sfnOffset is not allowed to be configured for the cell, if the connected radio module is not eCPRI or CPRI-N capable.  - Configuration of the sfnOffset must be the same for all cells allocated to the same baseband cell set of a baseband card.  - All LTE cells on the same radio module must have the same sfnOffset configuration.  - A PCell and all its SCells must have the same sfnOffset configuration.  - All cells in the same UL CoMP cluster must have the same sfnOffset configuration.    The configuration of the sfnOffset is not applied by the system, if the parameter actCellTimingOffset is set to 'false' in an eCPRI cell and actCellTimingOffsetCpriN is set to 'false' in a CPRI-N cell.    Note: Addition, removal or updating this parameter may provoke a reset.

Parameter name: Short decision period for channel quality est.
Description: Defines the short decision period for collecting the MCS samples from the SCell, before deciding about its channel quality. The short decision period applies when the SCell channel quality has not yet been estimated as good.    Within the specified decision period, one MCS sample is taken every 25 ms.

Parameter name: Site template description
Description: The parameter specifies the description of the Site Template that is or shall be assigned for the base station. Site Template Description can be used for searching the Site Template Name, which is needed when generating complete BTS configuration. This parameter is relevant from NetAct 16.8 onwards.

Parameter name: Site template name
Description: The parameter specifies the name of the Site Template assigned for the base station. Site Template can be used for generating complete BTS configuration during the planning phase. This parameter is relevant from NetAct 16.8 onwards.

Parameter name: Site template object match
Description: When applying a site template to a plan, this parameter can be used to match the LNCEL object in the site template with the LNCEL object in the plan.

Parameter name: Cell data for supercell deactivation
Description: The parameter stores data of the "normal" cell before configuring that as part of supercell configuration. The stored data is used to create the "normal" cell back when supercell configuration is deactivated. This parameter is relevant only when configuring supercell with NetAct Configurator Intelligent Feature Activation tool.

Parameter name: Cell name
Description: Unique cell name provided by operator for the former "normal" cell (network parameter).

Parameter name: Local cell resource ID
Description: Local Cell Resource ID parameter of the former "normal" cell.

Parameter name: LTE cell configuration identifier
Description: LNCEL instance identifier of the former "normal" cell.

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of LNCEL object of the former "normal" cell (non-network name parameter).

Parameter name: Physical layer cell identity
Description: Physical layer cell identity parameter of the former "normal" cell.

Parameter name: RACH root sequence
Description: RACH Root Sequence parameter of the former "normal" cell.

Parameter name: Sub cell identifier
Description: Identifier parameter to link supercell's CHANNELGROUP (subcell) with the former "normal" cell.

Parameter name: Tracking area code
Description: Tracking area code parameter of the former "normal" cell.

Parameter name: Sync Channel Power Deboost for 4Tx
Description: This parameter controls the total power reduction (deboost) for sync channel (PSS/SSS) transmissions at 4Tx sites. The reduction is applied only if syncSigTxMode = 'TxDiv'.

Parameter name: Timer T301 Guard
Description: Timer t301Guard supervises the UE Context Fetch procedure at the eNB.  Start: Receipt of RRCConnectionReestabilshmentRequest from UE  Stop: Reception of X2 Handover Request from failure eNB (for UE context fetch)    At expiry: send RRCConnectionReestablishmentReject to the UE

Parameter name: Timer T301 for QCI1
Description: Timer T301 supervises the RRC connection re-establishment procedure for UEs with QCI1 bearer.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionReestabilshmentRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionReestablishment or RRCConnectionReestablishmentReject message as well as when the selected cell becomes unsuitable    At expiry: Go to RRC_IDLE    This parameter is applicable only if actConvVoice is set to 'true' in the same cell.  If this parameter is not configured (while actConvVoice is set to 'true'), then SIB-t301 parameter is used for UEs with QCI1 bearer as well.

Parameter name: Timer T302
Description: eNB sends this parameter to the UE in the message RRC CONNECTION REJECT.  The UE will consider access to the cell as barred for the time specified by t302.

Parameter name: Timer T304 for interRAT
Description: This timer value is used eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target WCDMA system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. It is used eNodeB internally to calculate the supervision timer for the Handover Execution Phase (TS1RELOCoverall)

Parameter name: Timer T304 for interRAT GSM
Description: This timer value is used eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target GSM system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. It is used eNodeB internally to calculate the supervision timer for the Handover Execution Phase (TS1RELOCoverall)  Despite this timer is transparently provided by GERAN Target system its value is needed in LTE to calculate TS1RELOCOverall

Parameter name: Timer T304 for interRAT NR
Description: This timer value is used eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target NR system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. It is used by eNodeB internally to calculate the supervision timer for the Handover Execution Phase (TS1RELOCoverall)

Parameter name: Timer T304 intra-LTE
Description: Timer T304 supervises the successful completion of a handover or cell change.

Parameter name: Timer T304 for eNACC to GSM
Description: 3GPP defined Timer T304 (used for RRC Re-Establishment) for the case of eNACC to GSM  This timer value is passed to the UE in an RRC: MobilityFromEUTRANCommand message and is used by the UE to identify CCO Failure

Timer t310PubSafety supervises the recovery from physical layer problems for UE with established public safety bearers QCI 65/66/67  For UEs with QCI 65/66/67 DRB established, settings of t310PubSafety will be configured in RRC Connected mode (overwriting SIB2 T310 value) via RRC Connection Reconfiguration message.    Note:  If t310PubSafety is not configured, then the T310 value for the UE are determined based on whether QCI 1 has been established and LNCEL-t310Qci1 is configured. If LNCEL-t310Qci1 is not configured or if QCI 1 is not established, the value from LNCEL-t310 is used.

Parameter name: T310 for QCI1
Description: Timer t310Qci1 supervises the recovery from physical layer problems for UE with established QCI1 bearer.  With feature LTE1569 for UEs with established QCI1, settings of t310Qci1 will be configured in RRC Connected mode (overwriting SIB2 T310 value) via RRC Connection Reconfiguration message.

Parameter name: Timer T312
Description: Timer T312 supervises the recovery from physical layer problems when a measurement report has been triggered for a measurement identity for which T312 has been configured, while T310 is running. This parameter is used in intra-frequency measurement object.    It is recommended that the value of this parameter be smaller than SIB-t310.

Parameter name: Timer T320
Description: T320 defines the validity time of dedicated priorities defined in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo.

Parameter name: Deprioritisation Timer
Description: t325 indicates the period for which either the current carrier frequency or E-UTRA is deprioritised.  The UE shall be able to store a deprioritisation request for up to 8 frequencies (applicable when receiving another frequency specific deprioritisation request before T325 expiry).

Parameter name: CDMA2000 timers - CDMA2000 1xRTT measurement report timer
Description: Defines the amount of time the eNodeB waits for a measurement report for 1x Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB) to be received from the UE.

Parameter name: HRPD Timers - CDMA2000 HRPD Handover Relocation Execution Timer
Description: This timer value is used for eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target HRPD system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. eNodeB internally use this value to calculate the supervision timer for the eHRPD optimized Handover Execution Phase (TC2KRelocOverall).

Parameter name: CDMA2000 timers - CDMA2000 relocation preparation timer
Description: Defines the amount of time the eNodeB waits for the Downlink CDMA2000 Tunneling message after sending the Uplink Handover Preparation Transfer message (received from the UE) to the MME.

Parameter name: HRPD Timers - CDMA2000 HRPD Handover Relocation Preparation Timer
Description: This timer value defines the amount of time the eNodeB waits for the Downlink CDMA2000 Tunneling message from MME after forwarding the dedicatedInfoCDMA2000-HRPD PDU in UplinkHandoverPreparationTransfer message (received from UE) to MME.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 timers - CDMA2000 relocation execution timer
Description: Defines the amount of time the eNodeB waits to release the UE context after sending the Mobility From Evolved Universal Terrestrial Radio Access (EUTRA) Command message to the UE.

Parameter name: Timer ExtendedWaitTime-r10
Description: tExtendedWait suppresses the reselection of a cell for a while.  eNB sends this parameter to the UE in the message RRC CONNECTION REJECT and RRC CONNECTION RELEASE, and only in case of Delay Tolerant access request. The UE will consider access to the cell as barred for the time specified by tExtendedWait.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UEs in CE ModeA.

Parameter name: Load measurement X2 timer for MLB
Description: This timer defines the periodicity according which neighbor cells are requested to report their available resource status

Parameter name: Load measurement X2 timer for eICIC
Description: This timer defines the periodicity with which neighbor cells are requested by the eNB cell to send updated values of the load measurements for eICIC via X2    Note:  Valid values are 1000, 2000, 5000, 10000;

Parameter name: Timer paging correlation interval
Description: A RRC connection setup request which is correlated to (i.e. matches by s-TMSI) a S1 paging with priority will be prioritized ("emergency callback"). The timer determines the maximum time between the S1 paging and its correlated RRC connection setup request.  When the parameter is set to value "0" any correlation is disabled.

Parameter name: Periodic BSR time
Description: Time period of the periodic Buffer Status Report for the reporting of the UE transmission buffer utilization.

Parameter name: Periodic PHR timer
Description: UE configuration for sending periodic power headroom reports.

Parameter name: Ping pong time
Description: This parameter defines the maximum time interval which may elapse from when a UE has left a cell by handover till when it returns to that cell by another handover in order to consider such event as a PingPong

Parameter name: Prohibited PHR timer
Description: Minimum intermediate time between two consecutive Power Headroom Reports.

Parameter name: Retransmission BSR timer
Description: Time when the regular BSRs are repeated when the UE has data available for transmission and no corresponding UL grant is received so far.

Parameter name: Timer to store UE context
Description: This timer is started when an UE enters a cell by handover or RRC Re-Establishment.    The timer controls how long the context needed to send an X2AP: HANDOVER REPORT is stored in the new cell after handover.  No special action is triggered on timer expiry

Parameter name: CDMA2000 timers - UL Handover preparation transfer timer
Description: Defines the amount of time the eNodeB waits to receive an Uplink (UL) Handover Preparation Transfer message from the UE after sending a Handover From EUTRA Preparation Request message to the UE.

Parameter name: HRPD Timers - CDMA2000 HRPD UL Handover Preparation Transfer Timer
Description: The timer value defines the amount of time the eNodeB waits to receive an UlHandoverPreparationTransfer message from UE after sending a HandoverFromEUTRAPreparationRequest message to the UE.

Parameter name: Number of TA units for TA-based disconnect threshold
Description: This parameter is the threshold for disconnecting the RRC connection in timing advance (TA) units.    Note 1 TA unit = 16 time slots (TS), which corresponds roughly to a distance of 78 m.

Parameter name: Timer for TA-based disconnect
Description: This parameter is the timer how long the disconnection threshold (LNCEL-taDiscThr) needs to be exceeded before the RRC connection is released.

Parameter name: Time alignment maximum offset
Description: Determines the maximum allowed Time Alignment offset. If the value is exceeded, TA command is sent to the UE to adjust UL timing.

Parameter name: Time alignment timer
Description: Determines the number of subframes after which a UE assumes it is out-of-sync in UL if no Time Alignment command was received.

Parameter name: Time alignment timer margin
Description: The parameter defines lead with respect to the taTimer expiration time for starting to send the periodic Timing Advance Command.    Recommended default values:  for FDD cell: 2000  for TDD cell: 87    If taTimer is set to 'infinity', this parameter defines the lead time with respect to the expiration of a 10.24 seconds timer for starting to send the periodic Timing Advance Command

Parameter name: Tracking area code
Description: Identifies the tracking area for this cell.  A code that commonly identifies the tracking area for all PLMNs listed for this cell.    It is recommended to modify the tracking area code (tac) of a cell only during the daily maintenance window.  UEs newly entering a cell may not be able to connect for about 10-20 sec, respectively UEs camping in the cell might not be reachable for about 10-20 sec if the tracking area code is changed to a value which has been previously not used in any other cell of the eNB . This is because the old TAC may be still broadcasted via SIB while the TAC has been already deleted in the MME.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - DL GBR resource target load
Description: Target load for usage of GBR Uu I/F resources in DL direction.    If all load components (GBR, non-GBR, PDCCH) indicated by the load evaluation profile selected in 'mlbEicicOperMode' are below their individual target load values, a cell is considered having its load balanced.  Target Load represents the operating point = load at which the cell should work according to its dimensioning and the traffic model.  Because of using the minimum of the values, if either targetLoadGbrDl or targetLoadNonGbrDl or targetLoadPdcch are set to 0%, the cell will never offer any available capacity for Load Balancing to its neighbor cells.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - DL non-GBR resource target load
Description: Target load for usage of nonGBR Uu I/F resources in DL direction.    If all load components (GBR, non-GBR, PDCCH) indicated by the load evaluation profile selected in 'mlbEicicOperMode' are below their individual target load values, a cell is considered having its load balanced.  Target Load represents the operating point = load at which the cell should work according to its dimensioning and the traffic model.  Because of using the minimum of the values, if either targetLoadGbrDl or targetLoadNonGbrDl or targetLoadPdcch are set to 0%, the cell will never offer any available capacity for Load Balancing to its neighbor cells.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - PDCCH target load
Description: Target load for usage of PDCCH Uu I/F resources.    If all load components (GBR, non-GBR, PDCCH) indicated by the load evaluation profile selected in 'mlbEicicOperMode' are below their individual target load values, a cell is considered having its load balanced.  Target Load represents the operating point = load at which the cell should work according to its dimensioning and the traffic model.  Because of using the minimum of the values, if either targetLoadGbrDl or targetLoadNonGbrDl or targetLoadPdcch are set to 0%, the cell will never offer any available capacity for Load Balancing to its neighbor cells.

Parameter name: Cell reselection method for idle mode load balancing
Description: Selection method for the target frequency/layer for idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Terrain average height
Description: Terrain Average Height

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Terrain standard deviation
Description: Terrain standard deviation

Parameter name: Target threshold profile identifier
Description: Identifier of the Target Threshold Profile which shall be used for the cell.    Note: The referred Target Threshold Profile Managed Object Instance must exist.

Parameter name: Threshold th1 for RSRP
Description: Threshold Th1 for RSRP  If RSRP of serving cell is greater than Th1, only the serving cell is measured.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold 2 config for CDMA2000 HRPD and 1xRTT - RSRP threshold 2 for CDMA2000
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of CDMA2000-eHRPD or CDMA2000-1XRTT measurements    Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If value below threshold2Cdma2k (event A2) then CDMA2000-eHRPD or CDMA2000-1XRTT measurements are started.  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold 2 config for CDMA2000 HRPD and 1xRTT - RSRP threshold 2 For CDMA2000 during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of CDMA2000-1XRTT measurements when UE has QCI1 bearer.  Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. For a UE with QCI1 bearer and if RSRP value is below threshold2CkQci1 (event A2) then CDMA2000-1XRTT measurements are started.  If actServBasedMobThr (LTE2112/LTE64) is disabled or this parameter is not configured, then threshold2C2k(LTE738) is used    Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2 GERAN for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of GERAN Measurements  Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If the value is below threshold2GERAN (event A2) , GERAN measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2 GERAN for RSRP during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of GERAN Measurements when UE has QCI1 bearer    Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. For a UE with QCI1 bearer, if value is below threshold2GERANQci1 (event A2) then GERAN measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2 interFreq for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of inter frequency measurements  If value is below threshold2InterFreq (event A2) then inter frequency measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2 interFreq for RSRP of the high power UE
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of inter frequency measurements when HPUE has no QCI1 bearer.  Defines the threshold for serving cell RSRP of A2 event, as a trigger to start Inter-Frequency handovers. If value is below threshold2InterFreqHpue (event A2) then inter frequency measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold Th2 InterFreq for RSRP during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of inter frequency measurements when UE has QCI1 bearer  Defines the threshold for serving cell RSRP of A2 event, as a trigger to start Inter-Frequency handovers. If value is below threshold2InterFreqQci1 (event A2) and if UE has QCI1 bearer then inter frequency measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: RSRQ mobility parameters - Threshold th2 for RSRQ mobility
Description: Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ of serving value < threshold2MobRsrq then mobility measurements with measurement gaps are activated.  The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: Threshold th2 NR for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of coverage-based HO NR Measurements  Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If the value is equal to or below threshold2NR (event A2), coverage-based HO NR measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2 WCDMA for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of WCDMA Measurements  Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If the value is below threshold2Wcdma (event A2) , WCDMA measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2 WCDMA for RSRP during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of WCDMA Measurements when UE has QCI1 bearer    Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. For a UE with QCI1 bearer, if value is below threshold2WcdmaQci1 (event A2) then WCDMA measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2a for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for stopping of Inter-RAT (InterFreq) Measurements  Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If Inter-RAT (InterFreq) measurements are active and value exceeds Th2a (event A1) then Inter-RAT measurements are stopped. Th2_XXX <= Th2a for XXX= InterFreq, WCDMA, GSM, CDMA2000-HRPD    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2a for RSRP of the high power UE
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for stopping of Inter-Frequency (Inter-RAT) Measurements when HPUE has no QCI1 bearer  Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If Inter-Frequency (Inter-RAT) measurements are active and RSRP value exceeds threshold2aHpue (event A1) then Inter-Frequency (Inter-RAT) measurements are stopped.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th2a for RSRP During QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for stopping of Inter-RAT and Inter-Frequency Measurements when UE has QCI1 bearer  Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. For a UE with QCI1 bearer, if Inter-RAT and Inter-Frequency measurements are active and RSRP value exceeds threshold2aQci1 (event A1) then Inter-RAT measurements are stopped.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: RSRQ mobility parameters - Threshold th2a for RSRQ mobility
Description: Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell for stopping of Inter-RAT (Inter-Freq) measurements.  The RSRP based A1 event reports also the RSRQ value which is compared with this threshold in eNB.  When RSRP of serving cell becomes better than threshold2a the UE sends the A1 event. If the reported RSRQ of that A1 event of serving cell is also better than this configured threshold2aRsrq in eNB then InterFreq and InterRAT measurements are de-activated.  This check is done at each time the A1 report is received in eNB until either the RSRQ value fits or the leaving condition for this A1 event is fulfilled.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: Threshold th3 for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving cell is lower than threshold3 and RSRP of neighbor cell is greater than threshold3a, a handover is triggered.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th3 for RSRQ Intra frequency
Description: Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ of serving cell is lower than threshold3RsrqIntraFreq and RSRQ of neighbor cell is greater than threshold3aRsrqIntraFreq, a handover is triggered.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  * -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  * values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  * -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB"

Parameter name: Threshold th3a for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of intra-frequency neighbor cell. If RSRP of serving cell is lower than threshold3 and RSRP of neighbor cell is greater than threshold3a, a handover is triggered.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th3a for RSRQ Intra Frequency
Description: Threshold for RSRQ of intra-frequency neighbor cell. If RSRQ of serving cell is lower than threshold3RsrqIntraFreq and RSRQ of neighbor cell is greater than threshold3aRsrqIntraFreq, a handover is triggered.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  * -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  * values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  * -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB"

Parameter name: Threshold th4 for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of intra-frequency neighbor cell. If RSRP of serving value < Th4 then re-direct is triggered.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: RSRQ redirection parameters - Threshold th4 for RSRQ
Description: Threshold for RSRQ of intra-frequency serving cell. If RSRQ of serving value < Th4Rsrq then re-direct is triggered.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: TCP Service Differentiation Configuration - Time between TCP packets
Description: This parameter defines the minimum time which must elapse between two large TCP packets (defined as having size > minTcpPacketSize) in order to stop TCP boosting for a certain bearer.

Parameter name: TCP Service Differentiation Configuration - Time until next boosting round
Description: This parameter defines the minimum time without a large TCP packet (defined as having size > minTcpPacketSize) which must elapse after TCP boosting of a certain bearer has stopped. TCP boosting for the same bearer can be restarted only after this minimum time has elapsed.

Parameter name: Time to trigger SF high
Description: The timeToTrigger in ReportConfigEUTRA and in ReportConfigInterRAT are multiplied with the scaling factor applicable for the UE's speed state, that is, if the UE is in the high mobility state as defined in TS 36.304 .

Parameter name: Time to trigger SF medium
Description: The timeToTrigger in ReportConfigEUTRA and in ReportConfigInterRAT are multiplied with the scaling factor applicable for the UE's speed state, that is, if the UE is in the medium mobility state as defined in TS 36.304.

Parameter name: TTI bundling BLER target
Description: BLER target value for link adaption while in TTI Bundling mode

Parameter name: TTI bundling BLER threshold
Description: Controls the BLER threshold for switching UEs from non-bundling mode into TTI-Bundling mode

Parameter name: TTI bundling SINR threshold
Description: SINR threshold for switching UEs from TTI-Bundling mode into non-TTI-bundling mode    This threshold value is used if ttibOperMode is set to any of (blerBasedNoMeasGap, blerBasedTtibOnAllowed, blerBasedTtibOnOffAllowed), together with threshold conditions for current MCS and the estimated number of PRBs that the UE can handle.  If ttibOperMode is set to any of (sinrBasedNoMeasGap, sinrBasedTtibOnAllowed, sinrBasedTtibOnOffAllowed), this parameter has no function and TTI Bundling mode switches are controlled by the ttiBSinrThresholdIn and ttiBSinrThresholdOut parameters.

Parameter name: Alternating UL PRB threshold for TTI bundling mode
Description: This parameter determines the minimum gain which must be achieved by using interference-aware scheduling (IAS)or channel-aware scheduling (CAS) for UEs in TTI bundling mode, which looks for spectrum positions with minimized interference. If the achieved gain is smaller than this threshold, UEs in TTI bundling mode are given UL grants in alternating positions on the spectrum, for added diversity gain.  If parameter is set to 0, a UE in TTI bundling mode is always given UL grants using interference-aware scheduling (IAS) or channel-aware scheduling (CAS).

Parameter name: Minimum time to enter TTI bundling after Bearer Setup
Description: This parameter determines the minimum time a UE in non TTI bundling mode must spend after VoLTE bearer setup before it can enter TTI bundling mode.    If ttiOperMode is set to any of (sinrBasedNotWithMeasGap, sinrBasedTtibOnAllowed, sinrBasedTtibOnOffAllowed) or if VoLTE coverage boosting is activated (actVoipCovBoost is 'true'), UE enters TTI bundling mode only after ttibMinDelayAfterBearerSetup subframes have elapsed since VoLTE Bearer Setup.    Setting this parameter to zero disables this functionality, i.e. a UE can enter TTI bundling mode as soon as the VoLTE bearer is established.

Parameter name: Minimum number of UL PRBs in TTI bundling
Description: This parameter defines the minimum number of uplink PRBs which can be allocated to a UE in TTI bundling mode.  Setting this parameter to 3 means that the number of UL PRBs for a UE in TTI bundling is fixed at 3. This is because 3GPP limits the number of PRBs for a UE in TTI bundling to a maximum of 3.

Parameter name: TTI bundling operation mode
Description: This parameter determines  - which set of threshold conditions is used for entering / leaving TTI Bundling mode  - whether TTI bundling can be started or stopped while the UE is configured with measurement gaps.  BLER-based thresholds include TTIB mode entry conditions on the MCS assigned to a UE, the maximum number of PRBs that link adaptation has determined, and the current BLER.  SINR-based thresholds do not depend on link adaptation. They include the UE's power headroom, so essentially they are based on how much energy the UE can deliver at the eNB's receiver input.    values:  blerBasedNotWithMeasGap: BLER-based threshold used for TTIB mode switching;  TTI Bundling not allowed if measurement gaps are configured  blerBasedTtibOnAllowed; BLER-based threshold used for TTIB mode switching;  entering TTIB mode is allowed with configured measurement gaps  blerBasedTtibOnOffAllowed: BLER-based threshold used for TTIB mode switching;  entering and leaving TTIB mode is allowed with configured measurement gaps  sinrBasedNotWithMeasGap: SINR-based threshold used for TTIB mode switching;  TTI Bundling not allowed if measurement gaps are configured  sinrBasedTtibOnAllowed: SINR-based threshold used for TTIB mode switching;  entering TTIB mode is allowed with configured measurement gaps  sinrBasedTtibOnOffAllowed: SINR-based threshold used for TTIB mode switching;  entering and leaving TTIB mode is allowed with configured measurement gaps
Range and step: blerBasedNotWithMeasGap (0), blerBasedTtibOnAllowed (1), blerBasedTtibOnOffAllowed (2), sinrBasedNotWithMeasGap (3), sinrBasedTtibOnAllowed (4), sinrBasedTtibOnOffAllowed (5)

Parameter name: VoIP coverage boosting configuration - Minimum time to enter PHR based TTI bundling
Description: This parameter determines the minimum time the PHR value for a UE must be below the PHR Low threshold before it can enter PHR-based TTI bundling mode.

Parameter name: VoIP coverage boosting configuration - Minimum time to exit PHR based TTI bundling
Description: This parameter determines the minimum time the PHR value for a UE must be above the PHR Low+Hyst threshold before it can leave PHR-based TTI bundling mode.

Parameter name: Minimum time to enter SINR based TTI bundling
Description: This parameter determines the minimum time the SINR measurement for a UE must be below the threshold before it can enter SINR-based TTI bundling mode.    If ttiOperMode is set to any of (sinrBasedNotWithMeasGap, sinrBasedTtibOnAllowed, sinrBasedTtibOnOffAllowed), UE enters TTI bundling mode only after SINR measurement is below ttibSinrThresholdIn for ttibSinrDwellTimeIn consecutive subframes.

Parameter name: Minimum time to exit SINR based TTI bundling
Description: This parameter determines the minimum time the SINR measurement for a UE must be above the threshold before it can leave SINR-based TTI bundling mode.    If ttiOperMode is set to any of (sinrBasedNotWithMeasGap, sinrBasedTtibOnAllowed, sinrBasedTtibOnOffAllowed), UE leaves TTI bundling mode only after SINR measurement is above ttibSinrThresholdOut for ttibSinrDwellTimeOut consecutive subframes.

Parameter name: SINR threshold for entering TTI bundling mode
Description: If ttibOperMode is configured to use SINR-based conditions, this is the threshold for switching UEs from normal (non-TTI-Bundling) mode into TTI-bundling mode. The calculation also includes the UE's power headroom, so essentially this threshold condition looks at how much energy the UE can deliver at the eNB's receiver input.  If ttibOperMode is configured to use BLER-based conditions, this parameter is not used.

Parameter name: SINR threshold for leaving TTI bundling mode
Description: If ttibOperMode is configured to use SINR-based conditions, ttibSinrThresholdOut is used the threshold value for leaving TTIB mode.  if ttibOperMode is configured to use BLER-based conditions, this parameter is not used.

Parameter name: Maximum number of packet segmentation in TTIB
Description: Maximum number of UL VoIP packet segmentation. This parameter is used to calculate UL minTBS(t) together with the measured UL PDCP PDU size of voice packets. UL minTBS(t) is used for link adaptation when UE has QCI1 bearer and is in TTI bundling.

Parameter name: Minimum UL TBS for UEs for TTI bundled UEs
Description: This parameter defines the minimum UL TBS (segment size) for TTI bundled UEs.

Parameter name: UAV profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the assigned UAV profile.

Parameter name: UE context pre-emption guard timer
Description: ueCntxtPreempGuardT timer guards completion of UE context pre-emption procedure. The eNB internal resources are released at its expiry even if there are pending UE or MME transactions. The recommended value is at least 300ms and should be smaller than SIB-t300, CATMPR-t300ModeACatM, LNBTS-tS1RelPrepL and LNBTS-tX2RelocPrep.

Parameter name: UE level MRO offset
Description: UE Level MRO Offset parameter as a configurable offset being added to a CIO value of neighbor cell to avoid further unnecessary handovers when a ping-pong handover is detected between a serving cell and neighbor cell.  Value range: -3...0 step 1, where '0' makes no change in reality in the configured cell by adding 0 value, and Unit in dB.

Parameter name: SINR threshold for deactivating 256QAM UL for the UE
Description: SINR threshold for deactivating 256QAM UL for the UE.

Parameter name: SINR threshold for activating/reactivating 256QAM UL for the UE
Description: SINR threshold for activating/reactivating 256QAM UL for the UE.

Parameter name: Load threshold for turning on UL Adaptive Proportional Fair (PF) Scheduler
Description: Load value of cell (max (PUSCH load, PDCCH load)) is monitored in the cell. If the load exceed the threshold specified by this parameter, then load adaptive PF algorithm is applied.

Parameter name: SCell add UL SINR threshold
Description: This parameter determines the minimum PCell UL SINR for a UE with no established QCI1 bearer to be considered a candidate for adding an Scell.  If parameter is set to 0, a UE with no established QCI1 bearer can be considered a candidate for adding an Scell without checking its PCell UL SINR.

Parameter name: SCell add UL SINR threshold for QCI1
Description: This parameter determines the minimum PCell UL SINR for a UE with an established QCI1 bearer to be considered a candidate for adding an SCell.  If parameter is set to 0, a UE with an established QCI1 bearer can be considered a candidate for adding an SCell without checking its PCell UL SINR.

Parameter name: SCell add UL SINR window
Description: This parameter determines the minimum time a UE must meet the UL SINR threshold defined by ulCaMinPcellSinr or ulCaMinPcellSinrQci1 before it can be considered a candidate for adding an Scell.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - Uplink CAC Ignore Option
Description: This parameter indicates whether the Uplink CAC will be ignored or used in load balancing related calculations.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - Uplink CAC source selection
Description: This parameter selects the value to report in the Resource Status Update message for the uplink CAC.  When set to 'ulFixedCac' the uplink CAC reported in the X2 Resource Status Update will be the value set in ulStaticCac.    When set to 'ulReflectDlCac' the uplink CAC reported in the X2 Resource Status Update will be set to the same value as the downlink CAC.

Parameter name: Minimum number of TTI to empty buffer in UL to trigger EN-DC configuration
Description: This parameter controls the minimum number of TTIs required to empty the UE's UL non-GBR data buffer. If draining of the UE's UL non-GBR data buffer needs more TTIs and such condition occurs number of times configured by LNBTS_xDD-numRxWithHighNonGbrEnDc, EN-DC setup is triggered.    Note:  This parameter together with LNBTS_FDD-numRxWithHighNonGbrEnDc or LNBTS_TDD-numRxWithHighNonGbrEnDc defines conservativeness/aggressiveness level of EN-DC setup based on UL non-GBR data buffer status.

Parameter name: TCP Service Differentiation Configuration - Uplink maximum boosting bytes
Description: This parameter defines the amount of uplink data to be received (for a bearer which is being TCP boosted in the uplink) after which uplink TCP boosting for the bearer is stopped.

Parameter name: TCP Service Differentiation Configuration - Uplink minimum boosting bytes
Description: This parameter defines the minimum amount of uplink data which must be received (after uplink TCP traffic has been detected on a certain bearer) in order to start uplink TCP boosting for the bearer.

Parameter name: Uplink reference signals cyclic shift
Description: Defines cyclic shift of uplink reference signals.

Parameter name: Minimum TTI to empty buffer in UL to trigger SCell configuration
Description: This parameter controls the minimum number of TTIs required to empty the UE's UL non-GBR data buffer in order to trigger SCell upgrade from DL only SCC to DL + UL SCC, or SCell addition having DL + UL SCC.

Parameter name: PCell swap configuration - UL SINR threshold for PCell swap
Description: Defines the threshold for UL Signal-to-Interference-and-Noise-Ratio (SINR) below which a carrier aggregated UE is not considered for PCell swap by the source PCell.

Parameter name: Intra- and inter-freq. load bal. common load settings - Static CAC for uplink
Description: This parameter defines the uplink CAC value that will be sent in the X2 Resource Status Update message when ulCacSelection is set to 'ulFixedCac'.

Parameter name: UL AMC target BLER
Description: Defines target Block Error Ratio for uplink Adaptive Modulation and Coding.

Parameter name: UL variation adaptation initialization
Description: This initializes the value of the variance tracking filter. A value of 1 starts with a conservative assumption of 10% BLER while a value of 18 starts with an aggressive variance assumption that could likely start with a high BLER.

Parameter name: Enable all TBs in UL AMC
Description: O&M switch for enabling/disabling the counting of all Transport Blocks instead of the 1st transmission Transport Blocks for defining Uplink Adaptive Modulation and Coding inner loop factor (UEs in non-TTI bundling mode), BLER measurements (UEs in TTI bundling mode).  If set to false, only HARQ feedback for initial transmissions is considered in UL AMC.  If set to true, HARQ feedback for initial transmissions and for retransmissions is considered in UL AMC.

Parameter name: UL AMC delta C stepsize down
Description: The parameter defines the Fast Uplink Link Adaptation compensation delta C stepsize down.

Parameter name: UL AMC MCS switch period
Description: The parameter defines the period in sent Transport Blocks (TBs) when uplink Adaptive Modulation and Coding inner loop functionalities should be executed. Depending on the parameter ulAmcEnableAllTbs, all TBs or 1st transmission TBs have been calculated for the period. MCS increase/decrease based on the UL AMC inner loop factor can be only done after the period ends.

Parameter name: UL ATB period
Description: The parameter defines the period in MCS increase/decrease events when uplink Adaptive Transmission Bandwidth (ATB) functionality should be performed. MCS change events are calculated and UL ATB functionality is executed every time the event counter reaches the value defined in the parameter.

Parameter name: Alpha
Description: Used as a fractional path loss compensation factor: alpha. It controls received SNR variance (fairness) for user data and sounding reference symbol.  Alpha can't control the fractional pathloss compensation for the sounding in the case PUSCH masking is activated (actPuschMask equal to 'true') as SRS is disabled in this case.    Recommended default values are  - for FDD cell: 'alpha 1'  - for TDD cell: 'alpha 0.8'.    Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.
Range and step: alpha 0 (0), alpha 0.4 (1), alpha 0.5 (2), alpha 0.6 (3), alpha 0.7 (4), alpha 0.8 (5), alpha 0.9 (6), alpha 1 (7)

Parameter name: Interference aware UL-PC configuration - Cell-center/edge balancing for interference-aware UL-PC
Description: Controls Target SINR in interference-aware UL-PC: provides a tilt in the balancing between Target SINR in cell-center and Target SINR at cell-edge. Target SINR determines the max. throughput, therefore higher values increase cell-center throughput at the cost of cell-edge throughput, and vice versa.

Parameter name: Interference aware UL-PC configuration - Target SINR margin for interference-aware UL power control
Description: This parameter defines a margin added to the pre-defined UL SINR corresponding to the maximum UL MCS.

Parameter name: Uplink power control PUCCH configuration - Lower RSSI threshold for PUCCH power command decision
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUCCH component

Parameter name: Uplink power control PUSCH configuration - Lower RSSI threshold for PUSCH power command decision
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUSCH / SRS component

Parameter name: Uplink power control PUCCH configuration - Lower SINR threshold for PUCCH power command decision
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUCCH component

Parameter name: Uplink power control PUSCH configuration - Lower SINR threshold for PUSCH power command decision
Description: Lower threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUSCH / SRS component

Parameter name: Interference aware UL-PC configuration - Minimum UL quality for interference-aware UL-PC
Description: Minimum quality measure for interference-aware UL-PC. Target SINR for UEs in poor conditions cannot go below a limit defined by this parameter even if they generate higher UL interference.  Defines a minimum quality level in linear scale that is a multiplier to a reference SINR calculated from ulpcRefPwrIAw and the UE's UL signal plus noise.

Parameter name: Interference aware UL-PC configuration - Minimum waiting time for next UL-PC decision
Description: Minimum number of TTIs (ms) that must pass before another UL power decision is made for a UE.

Parameter name: Time interval for power command decisions
Description: Time interval for sending averaged RSSI and SINR values to the decision matrix to determine power corrections in closed-loop uplink power control.  The value range is split in two parts:  Values 10 ... 1000 indicate that discontinuous filtering is ON (i.e. during times of inactivity, RSSI/SINR target values will drift towards their window centers); filter read-out period = parameter value  values 1010 ... 2000 indicate that discontinuous filtering is OFF; filter read-out period = parameter value - 1000.

Parameter name: Interference aware UL-PC configuration - Reference UL power value for interference-aware UL-PC
Description: Controls Target SINR in interference-aware UL-PC: provides an equal shift of Target SINR for all UEs in the cell, regardless of their pathloss ratios.

Parameter name: Uplink power control PUCCH configuration - Upper RSSI threshold for PUCCH power command decision
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUCCH component.

Parameter name: Uplink power control PUSCH configuration - Upper RSSI threshold for PUSCH power command decision
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the RSSI (signal level) for PUSCH / SRS component.

Parameter name: Uplink power control PUCCH configuration - Upper SINR threshold for PUCCH power command decision
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUCCH component.

Parameter name: Uplink power control PUSCH configuration - Upper SINR threshold for PUSCH power command decision
Description: Upper threshold of the power control window for the SINR (signal quality) for PUSCH/SRS component.

Parameter name: UL scheduler FD type
Description: Scheduler Type for FD scheduler  Defines the scheduling method which shall be applied in frequency domain for the scheduler in UL  - the "RoundRobinFD" scheduler assigns the physical resources equally fair to the UEs selected by the TD scheduler until the PRBs are sufficient for the service or the physical resources of the cell are exhaust  - the "ExhaustiveFD" scheduler assigns in the priority sequence defined by the TD scheduler as many physical resources as possible to the UEs until the number of PRBs are sufficient for the service or the resources of the cell are exhaust  - the "MixedFD" scheduler is a joint FD scheduler which assigns the PRBs for SRB and GBR bearers by the exhaustive FD scheduler and the PRBs for the nonGBR bearers by the Round Robin FD scheduler to the UEs.

Parameter name: VoIP coverage boosting configuration - Maximum number of PRBs after coverage boosting
Description: Restrict the initial number of PRBs that are allocated to the UE in UL  after sensitivity-based scheduling mode is left to ulsMaxNumPrbAfterCovBoost.  The restriction shall be considered for one PHR measurement period.

Parameter name: Max packet aggregation UL
Description: Maximum number of aggregated VoIP packets in UL (with Inter Arrival Time of 20 ms)  Defines the maximum number of VoIP packets which may be aggregated for UL transmission based on a IAT of 20 ms. If the IAT of the VoIP packets is 10 ms the maximum packet aggregation is {1,3,5,7}.  Note that values of the parameter are {1,2,3,4} regardless of Inter Arrival Time, therefore following mapping is used to configure UL Packet Aggregation for IAT of 10ms - ulsMaxPacketAgg value (aggregation level with IAT of 10ms) -> 1 (1), 2 (3), 3 (5), 4 (7).

Parameter name: VoIP coverage boosting configuration - Number of carried VoIP samples before limitation
Description: Number of carried VoIP samples before the state change between the regular TX modes (Regular TX - SINR based scheduling / Regular TX - Sensitivity based scheduling) or between the TTI bundling modes (TTI mode LTE907 - SINR based scheduling / TTIB mode LTE2098 - Sensitivity based scheduling) based on stable conditions can occur.

Parameter name: Minimum Resource Blocks for Non-TTI Bundling VoLTE UEs
Description: Specifies the minimum number of PUSCH PRBs that can be allocated to a non-TTI bundled VoLTE UE.    Note that this parameter does not apply to UL VoLTE Sensitivity Resource Allocation mode or TDD UL SPS allocations.

Parameter name: Minimum PRB allocation for UEs which are power limited
Description: Defines the minimum PRB allocation for UEs which are power limited.    Note: When LTE2098 "VoLTE uplink coverage boosting" is activated, the configured value is not relevant for VoLTE power limited UEs.  This is used for the UEs for which the maximum number of PRBs due to power limitation is limited to low values (e.g. <= 5).    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Minimum UL transport block size
Description: Defines the minimum UL TBS (segment size).  The lower limit of the range is defined equal to the minimum transport block size (TBS) in the Table 7.1.7.2.1-1 in 3GPP TS 36.213.    The upper limit of the range is defined equal to the TBS belonging to modulation order 2 and 10 PRBs.

Parameter name: Minimum TBS for Non-TTI Bundling VoLTE UEs
Description: Specifies the minimum uplink transport block size (TBS) that can be allocated to a non-TTI bundled VoLTE UE.    Note that this parameter does not apply to UL VoLTE Sensitivity Resource Allocation mode or TDD UL SPS allocations.

Parameter name: Number of scheduling areas for UL scheduler
Description: Defines the number of scheduling areas supported by the PUSCH.

Parameter name: Uplink Scheduling Minimum MCS for Optimized PRB Allocations
Description: Specifies the target minimum MCS that will be used to derive the maximum number of PRBs allowed for a UE until the number of PRBs allowed has reached the minimum as specified by ulsMinRbPerUE for data UEs and ulsMinRbNonTtibVolte for non-TTI bundling VoLTE UEs.

Parameter name: PF alpha to be used when UL instantaneous spectral efficiency is higher than rInstUlHigh
Description: Load adaptive PF algorithm allows operator to set independent PF alpha settings for high, mid and low spectral efficiency (SE) users. This parameter sets the PF alpha setting for UL high SE users. Set greater than 1 to weigh cell center users more, and less than 1 to de-prioritize cell center users.

Parameter name: PF alpha to be used when UL instantaneous spectral efficiency is lower than rInstUlLow
Description: Load adaptive PF algorithm allows operator to set independent PF alpha settings for high, mid and low spectral efficiency (SE) users. This parameter sets the PF alpha setting for UL low SE users. Set greater than 1 to de-prioritize cell edge users and less than 1 to weigh cell edge users more.    Note: Unlike dlsPfAlphaLow, a value greater than 1 for ulsPfAlphaLow de-emphasizes edge cell users.

Parameter name: PF alpha to be used when UL instantaneous spectral efficiency is between rInstUlLow and rInstUlHigh
Description: Load adaptive PF algorithm allows operator to set independent PF alpha settings for high, mid and low spectral efficiency (SE) users. This parameter sets the PF alpha setting for UL mid SE users. Set greater than 1 to increase the priority at the better RF side of the 'mid cell' compared to the weaker RF side. Set less than 1 to have higher priority on the weaker RF side of the mid cell compared to the better RF side of the mid cell.

Parameter name: VoIP coverage boosting configuration - Threshold hysteresis related to VoLTE bearer
Description: PHR hysteresis factor of the corresponding VoLTE bearer (additive to the entry point to "Sensitivity based scheduling") for leaving the "Sensitivity based scheduling" states.

Parameter name: VoIP coverage boosting configuration - Threshold of the power headroom related to VoLTE bearer
Description: PHR threshold of the corresponding VoLTE bearer for entering the "Sensitivity based scheduling" states.

Parameter name: PUSCH congestion control for NBR traffic
Description: This parameter activates PUSCH congestion control for NBR traffic.    It is highly recommended to configure the value to 'true' if 'Nominal bitrate for non-GBR bearers' is activated, i.e. if actNbrForNonGbrBearers is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Scheduling method of the UL scheduler
Description: Defines the scheduling method which shall be applied in the cell for the UL branch.  Selects the method for the scheduling of the UEs in UL.  For FDD cells, three methods can be chosen - the channel unaware UL scheduler, the interference aware UL scheduler and the channel aware UL scheduler.  For TDD cells, two methods can be chosen - the channel unaware UL scheduler and the channel aware UL scheduler.
Range and step: channel unaware (0), channel aware (1), interference aware (2)

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Uncertainty altitude
Description: Uncertainty of altitude  Relation between coded Uncertainty altitude K and absolute uncertainty of altitude h (0 <= h <= 990.5 meters) it encodes is the following:    h = 45*(1.025^K-1)

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Uncertainty semi-major
Description: Semi-major of uncertainty ellipsoid  Relation between coded Uncertainty semi-major K and absolute semi-major uncertainty r (0 <= r <= 1800 meters) it encodes is the following:    r = 10*(1.1^K-1)

Parameter name: E-UTRAN access point position - Uncertainty semi-minor
Description: Semi-minor of uncertainty ellipsoid  Relation between coded Uncertainty semi-minor K and absolute semi-minor uncertainty r (0 <= r <= 1800 meters) it encodes is the following:    r = 10*(1.1^K-1)

Parameter name: Cell individual offset change upper margin
Description: This parameter defines the maximum value that a CIO can assume, when changed autonomously by the eNB during e.g. the intra-frequency load balancing function.

Parameter name: Structure for DL dynamic power back-off - Usage Of maxdlPwBackoffValue2
Description: This parameter defines the preference of the usage of maxdlPwBackoffValue2.

Parameter name: Unique sector electronics ID
Description: Unique sector electronics ID provided by operator.  This parameter allows the operator to assign a unique sector electronics ID to a cell period.

Parameter name: VoLTE UL Proactive grants  non TTIB UE Tx skippable
Description: This is the skippable VoLTE proactive UL grant period (in mseconds) for non TTIB UEs. Value of zero means skippable VoLTE proactive UL grant functionality is turned off for non TTIB UEs.

Parameter name: RegTx VoLTE proactive UL grant period
Description: This is the VoLTE proactive UL grant period (in mseconds) for non TTIB UEs. Value of zero means VoLTE proactive UL grant functionality is turned off for non TTIB UEs.

Parameter name: TTIB VoLTE proactive UL grant period
Description: This is the VoLTE proactive UL grant period (in mseconds) for TTIB UEs. Value of zero means VoLTE proactive UL grant functionality is turned off for TTIB UEs.

Parameter name: TTIB VoLTE proactive UL grant period Skippable
Description: This is the Skippable VoLTE proactive UL grant period (in mseconds) for TTIB UEs. Value of zero means skippable VoLTE proactive UL grant functionality is turned off for TTIB UEs.

Parameter name: VoLTE bearer setup protect timer
Description: In ICS/Incoming HO case, to avoid 5GSA Capability-based mobility (Redirection) triggered before VoLTE bearer setup, eNB applies the timer to delay 5GSA Capability-based mobility (Redirection) B1-NR activation.    When timer expires, eNB checks whether VoLTE bearer is established or not on UE. If VoLTE bearer is established, eNB does not activate 5GSA Capability-based mobility (Redirection) B1-NR on UE.    The parameter and the same treatment as for VoLTE bearer (with QCI 1) is also applicable to E-RABs established with QCI 65 (mission critical voice), QCI 66 (non-mission critical voice) and QCI 67 (mission critical video with possible multiplexed audio).

Parameter name: LNCELDESC  identifier
Description: Instance identifier of the object LNCELDESC.

Parameter name: Cell configuration type
Description: The user can freely define any site specific information with this parameter.  Note: The parameter is persistently stored but not used/modified by the BTS.

Parameter name: Cell info
Description: The user can freely define any site specific information with this parameter.  Note: The parameter is persistently stored but not used/modified by the BTS.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Descriptive name
Description: The user can freely define any site specific information with this parameter.  Note: The parameter is persistently stored but not used/modified by the BTS.

Parameter name: Target parameters info
Description: The user can freely define any site specific information with this parameter.  Note: The parameter is persistently stored but not used/modified by the BTS.

Parameter name: FDD specific cell identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of object LNCEL_FDD. It uniquely defines the object containing FDD technology specific cell parameter. It is used only for operation and maintenance purposes.

Parameter name: Activate 1TX in 2TX configuration
Description: This is to activate Dual transmission mode 1 operation when 2 Tx RF unit can be used for two times 1Tx transmission in Distributed Antenna Systems (DAS)  Note: If Dual transmission mode 1 is enabled in host LTE cell, the inband or guardband NB-IoT cell paired with this cell will also worked in Dual transmission mode 1 operation.

Parameter name: activate aperiodic PMI polling function
Description: This parameter activates aperiodic PMI polling function for LTE FDD mMIMO cell in TM9 mode, then periodic PMI information will be skipped.

Parameter name: Activation of automatic PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter activates the automatic PUCCH configuration of the LNCEL. When activated a limited set of PUCCH parameter need to be configured in class MPUCCH belonging to the cell, all other parameter are assigned by the system itself automatically.    For disabled functionality the standard PUCCH remain available.    Note: Only if actAutoPucchAlloc of the LNCEL_FDD instance is activated, the configured value of actLbPucchReg is considered by the BTS.

Parameter name: Activate LTE-M feature
Description: This parameter activates the LTE-M (CatM) feature.

Parameter name: Activate combined supercell configuration
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Combined Supercell'.  Combined supercells can consist of two to three subcells (FSMr3 deployment) respectively two to six subcells (AirScale deployment), i.e. CHANNELGROUP instances. In DL, the same data is transmitted from all subcells. In UL, data is received from selected subcells.

Parameter name: Activate Downlink MU-MIMO
Description: Parameter to activate or deactivate DL MU-MIMO in a cell. It is used to support TM9 MU-MIMO which supports 8 CSI-RS ports.

Parameter name: Activate downlink slim carrier
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates feature 'Slim Carrier' in the downlink.

Parameter name: Activate donut type of cell
Description: This parameter indicates whether the donut cell is activated.    Note1: Creation/deletion of parent LNCEL_FDD object instance while this parameter is set to 'true' and any modification of the parameter value will cause a BTS restart.  Note2: If this parameter is set to 'true', then any modification of parameter startOfDonutCell will cause a BTS restart.

Parameter name: Activate max. 240 active users per 3 MHz public safety FDD cell
Description: This parameter activates the possibility to extend the maximum number of active UEs from 120 to 240 active UEs for public safety applications within a 3 MHz LTE FDD cell served by an ABIA/ABIAL baseband board.

Parameter name: Activate fast adaptive MIMO switch
Description: Enables 'Fast Adaptive MIMO Switching' for Closed Loop MIMO modes based on PMI/RI reports sent by UEs if actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'true'.  Enables 'Dynamic MIMO Switching' if actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'.  actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'true': Activation of 'Fast Adaptive MIMO Switching'  'Fast adaptive MIMO Switching' supports fast rank selection and fast codebook based precoding of data transmission using closed loop feedback of precoding matrix indicator (PMI) in combination with rank indicator (RI). PMI and RI reporting delays shall be minimized by periodic and aperiodic reports sent by UEs in order to optimize PMI closed loop gains in combination with optimized rank selection.    actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false': Activation of 'Dynamic MIMO Switching'  'Dynamic MIMO Switching' supports RI and CQI based rank selection after filtering of CQI and RI reports sent by the UE. 'Dynamic MIMO Switching' is using RI and CQI thresholds for rank selection by comparison with filtered values. The threshold parameters 'mimoClCqiThD', 'mimoClCqiThU', 'mimoClRiThD', 'mimoClRiThU' are activated and used for rank switching.

Parameter name: Activate liquid cell configuration
Description: This parameter used to activate the feature LTE1709 'Liquid cell'. It cannot be set to 'true' any more.  The feature 'Liquid cell' allows to reuse the same PRBs in downlink for different UEs.    actLiquidCell can be configured to 'true' only on FSMr3 and later HW releases .    Downlink MIMO mode must be set to 'Closed Loop Mimo'. No other modes are supported.    For better performance it is recommended to activate also the feature LTE980 '4Rx IRC for 4RX Path'.

Parameter name: Massive MIMO activation
Description: This parameter activates Massive MIMO with AAS 16TRX antenna system in FDD system.

Parameter name: Activate overbooking for mission-critical video
Description: This parameter activates overbooking for mission-critical video.

Parameter name: Activate DL CA with mixed TMs
Description: This parameter activates mixed MIMO transmission modes for DL CA in the eNB.    Activated feature allows to configure DL CA with different MIMO modes on serving cells (i.e., PCell and SCell/s).

Parameter name: Activates PRACH Root Sequence capacity enhancement
Description: Parameter actOptRootSeq activates the feature PRACH Root Sequence capacity enhancement for ABIO/ABIN/ABIP/ABIQ/ASOE/ASOF/ASOG/ASOH boards on cell level. Depending on the parameter value the number of cells with high cell range which can be allocated to a resource pool is increased.

Parameter name: Activate O-RAN cell
Description: This parameter activates O-RAN cell with O-RU in FDD system.

Parameter name: Activate PDCCH load generation
Description: This parameter controls the activation or deactivation of "Inter cell load generation for PDCCH".

Parameter name: Activate PUSCH 100 PRB allocations
Description: Parameter activates 100 PRBs allocation to PUSCH in absence of PRACH and msg3, with only 1 UE connected (in absence of PUCCH allocation for this TTI) and if A-MPR functionality actUlPwrRestrScn is set to "band1_NS05"

Parameter name: Activate PUSCH masking
Description: Activates PUSCH masking

Parameter name: RIP alarming configuration - Activate RIP alarming
Description: Parameter actRIPAlarming activates/deactivates RIP alarming in the LNCEL instance. RIP alarms for the LNCEL instance are only send if the parameter is set to value 'true'.

Parameter name: Activation reduced frequency offset
Description: This parameter activates the reduced frequency offset feature.

Parameter name: Repeater mode activation
Description: Defines mode of the radio module or RIU unit.    The "actRepeaterMode" parameter value Coupled needs to be used for coupled mode cells (R type configuration), value Dedicated for dedicated mode cells (cell have resources only from RIU unit) and value None for all other cells (cells do not have resources from RIU unit).    Possible modes are None, Dedicated and Coupled.    The Coupled is supported only with Configuration Type R.    The RIU is able to work either in Dedicated or Coupled mode also in case a RF unit is chained via it.    Super cell configurations are not released in conjunction with Repeater Interface Units.      If a new LNCEL instance is created with repeater mode 'Dedicated' then eNB will not trigger eNB restart but only 'cell locking'.

Parameter name: Activate supplemental downlink carrier
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Supplemental downlink carrier'.  Note: A cell that is using a "supplemental downlink carrier" is using a carrier located in any FDD band. SDLC cells are operated on downlink only and can be used only as secondary cells (SCells) in downlink carrier aggregation. Otherwise, the cells appears as barred to UEs.  When local restrictions for uplink apply, also carriers on other frequencies might be configured for downlink operation only.    Carriers that are for use on downlink only are specified/indicated by LNBTS-sdlcFreqList.    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Activate Shutting Down Tx Path
Description: This parameter activates shutting down one Tx-Path by OAM when the cell deploys as two Tx RF units

Parameter name: Activate Cat-M coexistence with slim carrier
Description: This parameter activates the Cat-M coexistence with slim carrier.

Parameter name: Activation of SRS-based positioning for 1.4 MHz cells
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'SRS (Sounding reference signal)-based positioning with 1.4 MHz cells'.

Parameter name: Activate supercell configuration
Description: Activates the transmission of duplicated data streams via different RRHs in downlink, and the combination of uplink signals received from different RRHs.  The super cell configurations can just be applied in 5 MHz, 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth configurations, that is LNCEL "dlChBw" and "ulChBw" parameters are configured to 5 MHz, 10 MHz, 15 MHz or 20 MHz.  Super cell configurations are not released in conjunction with Repeater Interface Units.

Parameter name: Activate transmission mode switch for FDD massive MIMO
Description: Activate or deactivate the dynamic transmission mode switch function for FDD massive MIMO

Parameter name: Activate UCI only grant transmission
Description: The parameter activates UCI only grant transmission.  When this parameter is set to 'true', aperiodic CSI reports can be scheduled in the cell without the precondition of PUSCH data.  It is highly recommended to activate this feature if eICIC is used in the cell.

Parameter name: Activate UL multi-cluster Scheduling
Description: Activates the multi-cluster scheduling in UL scheduler

Parameter name: Activate UL Power Restriction Scenario
