Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE3230 UL interference offsets (if the parameter is set to "band18_26" or "band30_NS21") or LTE3242/LTE4851 A-MPR (if the parameter is set to "band13_NS07" or "band1_NS05") or CB007828 (if the parameter is set to 'band19_NS08') by selecting a pre-configured UL power restriction scenario. LTE3230/LTE3242/LTE4851 also reconfigure the UL spectrum to have two outer PUSCH scheduling regions.  Use this parameter to select an UL power restriction defined in 3GPP TS36.101. Except for CB007828, PUSCH and PUCCH PRB ranges are reconfigured such that the power restrictions either match the size of outer scheduling areas or are covered by an interference offset. PUSCH allocations with further restrictions are avoided.  An interference offset value must be present if actUlPwrRestrScn is not set to 'none' or 'band19_NS08'.    When deactivating any of the A-MPR related features, i.e. setting actUlPwrRestrScn to 'none', make sure to have these related parameters set to suitable values or defaults:  - redBwMaxRbUl (for the 'band19_NS08' scenario)  - addSpectrEmi (for all scenarios)
Range and step: none (0), band18_26 (1), band30_NS21 (2), band13_NS07 (3), band1_NS05 (4), band19_NS08 (6)

Parameter name: Activated MIMO transmission mode
Description: This parameter configures the selection of the Closed Loop MIMO transmission mode TM4 or TM9 depending on the capability of the UE for 4Tx LTE basestation configurations. Up to 4 spatial multiplexing layers can be supported based on TM4 (MIMO4x4-TM4) or TM9 (MIMO4x4-4pTM9, MIMO8x2-8pTM9, MIMO8x4-8pTM9 or MIMO16x2-16pTM9_ClassA, where 'p' is 'CSI-RS ports' ).    The following settings for the parameter activatedMimoTM are supported to configure the selection of the transmission mode for closed loop single user downlink MIMO modes for 4Tx LTE basestation configurations:  - activatedMimoTM == "TM4": all UEs select TM4  - activatedMimoTM == "TM9": all TM9 capable UEs select TM9; all other legacy Rel.8,9 UEs select TM4  - activatedMimoTM == "TM9_maxLayer": only UEs with 4 RX antennas supporting 4 layers use TM9, all other UEs use TM4. This selection is only allowed to set when dlMimoMode = 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)'    Notes:  (1) The parameter 'activatedMimoTM' is only configurable for the following Closed Loop MIMO modes to control the selection of the transmission mode.  - 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)'  - 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)'  - 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)'  - 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)'  - 'Closed Loop MIMO (16x2)'  (2) The setting activatedMimoTM == "TM9_maxLayer" is only configurable if dlMimoMode=='Closed Loop MIMO (4x4) '

Parameter name: Add number DRB radioReasHo
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active DRBs in the cell accessing the cell via HO with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons".  This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActDrb.  This additional margin is used also for UEs accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Reduce load in serving cell" but only when Composite Available Capacity (CAC) in the Cell is higher than 0. If CAC in the Cell is zero, the HOs due to "Reduce load in serving cell" are always rejected.  Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell.    The following max. DRB values are allowed to be configured as sum of maxNumActDrb + max(addNumDrbRadioReasHo, addNumDrbTimeCriticalHo):    1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 2520  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3000  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3750  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 4500    Dependencies:  AirScale deployment:  For AirScale the maximum DRB values for the cells do not only depend on the cell BW but also on the baseband pool limits.  For variant of AirScale ABIA, ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOE/ASOF, ASOG/ASOH the max. number of DBRs admissions may be limited by the baseband pool limits which can be looked up in the release documentation.    A special configuration has to be considered by operator for AirScale ABIA/ABIAL without BBpooling:  - if AirScale deployment on 1 ABIA (any variant) has mixed BW cells i.e. at least 1 cell > 10MHz and cells <= 10 MHz then the 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells are restricted for parameter addNumDrbRadioReasHo to 0...1260.

Parameter name: Add number DRB timeCriticalHo
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active DRBs in the cell accessing the cell via HO with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActDrb.  Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell.    The following max. DRB values are allowed to be configured as sum of maxNumActDrb + max(addNumDrbRadioReasHo, addNumDrbTimeCriticalHo):    1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 2520  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3000  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3750  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 4500    Dependencies:  AirScale deployment:  For AirScale the maximum DRB values for the cells do not only depend on the cell BW but also on the baseband pool limits.  For any variant of AirScale ABIA, ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOE/ASOF, ASOG/ASOH the max. number of DBRs admissions may be limited by the baseband pool limits which can be looked up in the release documentation.    A special configuration has to be considered by operator for any variant of AirScale ABIA without BBpooling:  - if AirScale deployment on 1 ABIA (any variant) has mixed BW cells i.e. at least 1 cell > 10MHz and cells <= 10 MHz then the 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells are restricted for parameter addNumDrbTimeCriticalHo to 0...1260.

Parameter name: Add number QCI1 DRB for radioReasHo
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active GBRs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: 'HO desirable for radio reasons'.  This additional margin is used also for UEs accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: 'Reduce load in serving cell' but only when Composite Available Capacity (CAC) in the Cell is higher than 0. If CAC in the cell is zero, the HOs due to 'Reduce load in serving cell' are always rejected.  This margin is added to the threshold maxNumQci1Drb.    Hand over traffic has some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell.    The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:    Value ranges for the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA and actEnhAcAndGbrServices = false (FSMr3 in brackets)  1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 10 (10)  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 60 (60)  5 MHz bandwidth 0 ... 200 (200)  10 MHz bandwidth 0 ... 200 (400)  15 MHz bandwidth 0 ... 300 (500)  20 MHz bandwidth 0 ... 300 (600)    For any variant of AirScale ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOE/ASOF, ASOG/ASOH with at least one LTE cell configured, this parameter is not relevant as those AirScale deployments operate always with BBpooling activated and feature bundle LTE534, LTE496, LTE497 activated (actEnhAcAndGbrServices =true).    Dependencies:  maxNumQci1Drb + max( addNumQci1DrbRadioReasHo, addNumQci1DrbTimeCriticalHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above e.g. for FSMr3 (10, 60, 200, 400, 500, 600)).  The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'false' and ignored otherwise.

Parameter name: Add number QCI1 DRB for timeCriticalHo
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active VoLTE GBR-DRbs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumQci1Drb.  The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'false' and ignored otherwise.    Hand over traffic has some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell.    The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:    Value ranges for the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA and actEnhAcAndGbrServices = false (for no AirScale upper limits in brackets)  1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 10 (10)  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 60 (60)  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200 (200)  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200 (400)  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 300 (500)  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 300 (600)    For any variant of AirScale ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOE/ASOF, ASOG/ASOH with at least one LTE cell configured, this parameter is not relevant as those AirScale deployments operate always with BBpooling and feature bundle LTE534, LTE496, LTE497 activated (actEnhAcAndGbrServices = true).    Dependencies:  maxNumQci1Drb + max( addNumQci1DrbRadioReasHo, addNumQci1DrbTimeCriticalHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above e.g. for FSMr3. (10, 60, 200, 400, 500, 600))

Parameter name: RIP alarming configuration - Alarm threshold crossing time
Description: Parameter alarmThresholdCrossingTime defines when a RIP alarm will be raised or cleared. When the RIP value is above/below the alarm threshold for the alarm threshold crossing time (e.g. 5 minutes) then the RIP alarm will be raised/cleared.  This parameter is used for RIP alarms for Uplink Subframe and Special Subframe (applicable for TDD cell only).

Parameter name: RIP alarming configuration - Alarm threshold for UL subframe
Description: Parameter alarmThresholdULSF defines the threshold for the RIP alarming for UL subframe. If the measured RIP value is above/below the threshold for at least Alarm Threshold Crossing Time (e.g. 5 minutes) an alarm with severity major is raised/cleared.

Parameter name: Assigned number of PRACH root sequences
Description: Number of PRACH root sequences which are skipped from processing in case actOptRootSeq is set different to 'none' .

Parameter name: Blanked PUCCH resources
Description: Defines the pointer to PRB from where the CQI-allocation shall start in order to leave some PRBs free and therefore to avoid interference with neighbor bands.  When set to 0 the feature 'Flexible UL Bandwidth' is deactivated.    The 'blankedPucch' is the number of blanked PUCCH PRBs, counted inward from the band edges, and indicating the sum of PRBs from upper and from lower edge. They are counted into (i.e. part of) the nCqiRb value.  When set to values different from 0 all the PRBs from 0 up to 'blankedPucch' value are not utilized by the PUCCH allocation algorithm for allocating the periodic CQI.  In other words all those PRBs up to blankedPucch are skipped by the periodic CQI allocation algorithm.    Example: blankedPucch = 6 would mean that CQI-allocation will start from the seventh PRB, the PRB #6.  All the PRB up to the PRB#6 excluded (3 at each BW edge accordingly to PUCCH physical allocation policy) are left free, to avoid interferences with neighbor bands supported by other radio technologies.    The configuration of the blanked PRBs region in one operators network shall be the same for all the cells having same E-UTRA Operating Band, same channel bandwidth and same center carrier frequency (i.e. same Transmission bandwidth configuration according to 3GPP-36.104).    In case of simultaneous activation of feature LTE46 'Channel-aware Scheduler (UL)', SRS configuration must avoid that SRS signal is sent within the blanked RF area.    This parameter is ignored by the system if LTE3230 UL interference offsets is activated. LTE3230 uses its own pre-defined configuration data.    This parameter is ignored by the system if feature LTE4738-RP001783 is active (that is if actDynamicSharedSpectrum == TRUE). Instead, in LTE4738-RP001783, blankedPucch is internally set by eNodeB to: blankedPucch= 2 * max(numBlankDlPrbsDown, numBlankDlPrbsUp).    For FDD massive MIMO cells in dual-cell configuration, blankedPucch must be set to the same value in both cells. Check actMMimo parameter for details.    When dynamic spectrum sharing with GSM or with WCDMA is active, the system set autonomously the correct value of blankedPucch, therefore operator shall leave the value of this parameter to 0.

Parameter name: Data split CA SCell scheduler weight factor activation timer
Description: Timer for the application of data split CA SCell scheduler weight factors after SCell configuration.

Parameter name: Supercell parameter set - UL SINR offset to serving subcell for candidate subcell
Description: Defines the maximum UL SINR offset to serving for candidate subcell selection.  If the SINR gap between serving subcell and a measurement-only subcell is less than this offset the measurement-only subcell can be selected as candidate subcell.

Parameter name: Instance ID of the assigned CATMBPR profile
Description: Instance ID of the assigned CATMBPR profile.  CATMBPR contains some LTE-M ModeB functional parameters which is subordinate under LNBTS.

Parameter name: Instance ID of the assigned CATMPR profile
Description: Instance ID of the assigned CATMPR profile.    CATMPR contains some LTE-M functional parameters which is subordinate under LNBTS.

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information for 16 ports TM9 class A - Codebook Config Rel-13
Description: This parameter defines codebook Config

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information for 16 ports TM9 class A - Codebook Config N1
Description: This parameter defines codebook Config N1 for r13.

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information for 16 ports TM9 class A - Codebook Config N2
Description: This parameter defines codebook Config N2 for r13.

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information for 16 ports TM9 class A - Codebook OverSampling Rate Config O1
Description: This parameter defines codebook oversampling rate config O1 for r13.

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information for 16 ports TM9 class A - Code Division Multiplexing Type
Description: cdmType

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Timer for aperiodic CQI / PMI feedback requesting
Description: This parameter defines a timer in TTIs for polling aperiodic CQI / RI / PMI feedback. The scheduler handles the aperiodic feedback requesting based on this timer.

Parameter name: Timer for aperiodic CQI / PMI feedback requesting for UE supporting skippable UL grant
Description: This parameter defines a timer in TTIs for polling aperiodic CQI / RI / PMI feedback. The scheduler handles the aperiodic feedback requesting based on this timer for Rel. 14 UEs configured for "skippable" UL grants.  This parameter is only used if LNBTS.actReduceAcqiReqTxSkip = 'true' of corresponding LNBTS.

Parameter name: R13 periodic CQI wideband periodicity factor
Description: If the periodicity of CQI/PMI reporting is N (in subframes),the wideband first precoding matrix indicator report has period  cqiPerWbPeriodFactor * N.

Parameter name: CSI reporting submode
Description: This parameter indicates the submode of wideband periodic CSI reporting mode 'mode 1-1', this mode 1-1 will be taken if PUCCH CQI Feedback Type is 'wideband' and PMI Feedback Type is 'Single PMI' for a 8 CSI-RS ports TM9 capable UE, there are two options: "submode1" and "submode2".

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information for 16 ports TM9 class A - CSI-RS power offset
Description: Defines the ratio of PDSCH EPRE to CSI-RS EPRE  For FDD cell configured with 16-ports CSI-RS:  - The allowed range is from -6dB to 15dB, step 1dB  - The recommended value is -6dB

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information - CSI-RS power offset
Description: Defines the ratio of PDSCH EPRE to CSI-RS EPRE  For FDD cell configured with 8-ports CSI-RS:  - The allowed range is from -6dB to 15dB, step 1dB  - The recommended value is -6dB    For FDD cell configured with 4-ports CSI-RS:  - The allowed range is from -3dB to 15dB, step 1dB  - The recommended value is -3dB

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - CSI-RS power offset near access point
Description: Defines the ratio of PDSCH EPRE to CSI-RS EPRE near the access point.  Simulations have shown that reasonable values vary from -2 dB to +2 dB.

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - CSI-RS power offset overlapping region
Description: Defines the ratio of PDSCH EPRE to CSI-RS EPRE in the overlapping region of the subcells.  Simulations have shown that reasonable values vary from -2 dB to +2 dB.

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - CSI-RS resource configuration
Description: Defines which resource elements in the PRBs are used for the CSI-RS information.  See 36.211 Table 6.10.5.2-1  If this parameter is not configured, the resource elements will be defined and set automatically. The configured value will be displayed in liquidCellCsiRsResInUse.

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information - CSI-RS configuration
Description: Defines the cell specific CSI-RS configuration for normal cyclic prefix.    In case cell is object of a FDD massive MIMO dual-sector configuration then corresponding paired cell is locked/unlocked to configure zero Tx power CSI-RS for the same resource elements.

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information for 16 ports TM9 class A - CSI-RS configuration for 16 ports TM9 class A
Description: Defines the second cell specific CSI-RS configuration for normal cyclic prefix

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - CSI-RS subframe configuration
Description: Defines which subframes are used for the CSI-RS information (offset + periodicity).  See 36.211 Table 6.10.5.3-1

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information - CSI-RS subframe configuration
Description: Defines the cell specific CSI-RS subframe configuration  0-4: 5ms period  5-14: 10ms period  15-34: 20ms period  35-74: 40ms period  75-154: 80ms period    Note:  when CSI-RS periodicity is 5ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf(subframes)  when CSI-RS periodicity is 10ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 5(subframes)  when CSI-RS periodicity is 20ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 15(subframes)  when CSI-RS periodicity is 40ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 35(subframes)  when CSI-RS periodicity is 80ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 75(subframes).

Parameter name: Downlink channel bandwidth
Description: Downlink channel bandwidth defines the DL bandwidth for the eNB transmission in a cell, and also defines the number of available Physical Resource Blocks (PRBs).  The downlink channel bandwidth mapping to number of Physical Resource Blocks is:  1.4 MHz = 6 DL PRBs  3.0 MHz = 15 DL PRBs  5.0 MHz = 25 DL PRBs  10.0 MHz = 50 DL PRBs  15.0 MHz = 75 DL PRBs  20.0 MHz = 100 DL PRBs    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.    Following configuration rules need to be considered:    FSMD:  maximum downlink channel bandwidth is 10 MHz if more than 2 cells are configured.    FSME:  maximum downlink channel bandwidth is 10 MHz if more than 3 cells are configured.    Cell bandwidth 1.4 MHz:  - is not supported with FSMD/FSME    If a 'SuperCell' is activated (actSuperCell set to 'true') the bandwidth usage is limited to 5 MHz, 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz.    1.4 MHz and 3.0 MHz downlink channel bandwidth is only supported on FSMF or the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA.

Parameter name: Downlink MIMO mode
Description: Cell-specific downlink transmission/MIMO mode  The used DL MIMO mode for each physical channel is the following:    SingleTX: Single Stream Downlink: All downlink physical channels are transmitted using this mode;    TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for two antennas using Transmission Mode 2.    4-way TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for four Tx antennas using Transmission Mode 2.  Please note that '4-way TXDiv' must not be configured in dual band configurations.    Dynamic Open Loop MIMO: Dynamic Open Loop MIMO: SRB1 (DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Dual Stream MIMO with spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions; SRB0 (CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity;  If dlMimoMode is set to 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO', mimoOlCqiThD, mimoOlCqiThU, mimoOlRiThD, mimoOlRiThU are relevant. Default values will be used if no dedicated values are configured.    Closed Loop Mimo: Dynamic Closed Loop MIMO: SRB1 (DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0 (CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity.    Closed Loop MIMO (4x2): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO4x2: SRB1 (DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0 (CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity.    Closed Loop MIMO (4x4): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO4x4: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity    Closed Loop MIMO (8x2): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO8x2: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity    Closed Loop MIMO (8x4): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO8x4: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity    Closed Loop MIMO (16x2): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO16x2: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity      In case dlMimoMode is set to 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' or 'Closed Loop Mimo' it is recommended to set riEnable to value 'true' to enable dynamic switching between dual stream MIMO spatial multiplexing and single stream transmission.    If dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTX', dlpcMimoComp is not applicable. The default value is used implicitly.
Range and step: SingleTX (0), TXDiv (10), 4-way TXDiv (11), Dynamic Open Loop MIMO (30), Closed Loop Mimo (40), Closed Loop MIMO (4x2) (41), Closed Loop MIMO (8x2) (42), Closed Loop MIMO (4x4) (43), Closed Loop MIMO (8x4) (44), Closed Loop MIMO (16x2) (45)

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Downlink MU-MIMO correlation threshold
Description: The correlation threshold below which two TM9 MU-MIMO candidate which supports 8 CSI-RS ports can be paired.

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Downlink MU-MIMO CQI threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the CQI threshold above which the TM9 UEs which supports 8 CSI-RS ports can be selected as DL MU-MIMO candidate. This DL MU-MIMO candidate must be rank 1 UE.

Parameter name: Downlink reference signals transmission power boost
Description: Transmission power of the downlink reference signals in a cell is boosted (positive value) respectively deboosted (negative value) compared to PDSCH

Parameter name: Downlink SRB MIMO mode
Description: This parameter determines the MIMO mode to be used for Downlink SRB traffic

Parameter name: MIMO power compensation
Description: Sets the compensation in 'TXDiv', '4-way TXDiv', 2x2 MIMO SM, 4x2 MIMO SM , 4x4 MIMO SM, 8x2 MIMO SM, 8x4 MIMO SM, 16x2 MIMO SM case into the DL power control.  Compensation of MIMO Coverage effects for MIMO Spatial Multiplexing and MIMO Diversity  The parameter determines the power compensation factor for antenna-specific maximum power in case of a downlink transmission using at least two TX antennas. This means that every single subcarrier power determined for multiple TX antenna transmission is reduced by this factor. The parameter does not apply in case of a single TX (TM1) transmission, and thus neither affects the power of cell-specific reference signal transmission. Note that only the limited set of dlpcMimoComp values (-3dB, 0dB, 1.77dB, 3dB, 4.77dB, 6dB) can be communicated to the UE due to p-a signaling restrictions and the extended range has been determined only for fine tuning purposes. Please be informed that Nokia does not guarantee a successful DL transmission using amplitude dependent modulations, especially 64QAM, if other values than the values presented in the limited set (-3dB, 0dB, 1.77dB, 3dB, 4.77dB, 6dB) are used.  Please note, that if the Cell-Specific Reference Symbol Power Boost is activated by setting the dlRsBoost parameter, only the values 0dB and 3dB are allowed for dlpcMimoComp.    For FDD cells: The parameter will be ignored if dlChBw is set to '1.4 MHz'.

Parameter name: RAT1 Algorithm Mode
Description: This parameter activates RAT1 functionality in Downlink scheduler:  - 'basic' :  - At most one RAT1 UE per TTI  - 'extended' :  - Multiple RAT1 UEs per TTI

Parameter name: EARFCN downlink
Description: E-UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number in downlink.  Band 1 (2110-2170 MHz): 0-599  Band 2 (1930-1990 MHz): 600-1199  Band 3 (1805-1880 MHz): 1200-1949  Band 4 (2110-2155 MHz): 1950-2399  Band 5 (869-894 MHz): 2400-2649  Band 6 (875-885 MHz): 2650-2749  Band 7 (2620-2690 MHz): 2750-3449  Band 8 (925-960 MHz): 3450-3799  Band 9 (1844.9-1879.9 MHz): 3800-4149  Band 10 (2110-2170 MHz): 4150-4749  Band 11 (1475.9-1495.9 MHz): 4750-4949  Band 12 (729-746 MHz): 5010-5179  Band 13 (746-756 MHz): 5180-5279  Band 14 (758-768 MHz): 5280-5379  Band 17 (734-746 MHz): 5730-5849  Band 18 (860-875 MHz): 5850-5999  Band 19 (875-890 MHz): 6000-6149  Band 20 (791-821 MHz): 6150-6449  Band 24 (1525-1559 MHz): 7700-8039  Band 25 (1930-1995 MHz): 8040-8689  Band 26 (859-894 MHz): 8690-9039  Band 27 (852-869 MHz): 9040-9209  Band 28 (758-803 MHz): 9210-9659  Band 29 (717-728 MHz): 9660-9769  Band 30 (2350-2360 MHz): 9770-9869  Band 31 (462.5-467.5 MHz): 9870-9919  Band 32 (1452-1496MHz): 9920-10359  Band 46:  Sub-band 46a: (5150-5250 MHz): 46790-47789  Sub-band 46b (5250-5350 MHz): 47790-48789  Sub-band 46c (5470-5725 MHz): 49990-52539  Sub-band 46d: (5735-5835 MHz): 52640-53639  Band 65 (2110-2200 MHz): 65536-66435  Band 66 (2110-2200 MHz): 66436-67335  Band 68 (753-783MHz): 67536-67835  Band 70 (1995-2020 MHz): 68336-68585  Band 71 (617-652 MHz): 68586-68935  Band 72 (461-466 MHz): 68936-68985  Band 75 (1432-1517 MHz): 69466-70315  Band 85 (728-746 MHz): 70366-70545  Band 87 (420-425 MHz): 70546-70595  Band 111 (722-728 MHz): 11131-11191  Band 125 (2347-2350 MHz): 130000-130029  Band 126 (420-425 MHz): 130200-130249  Band 222 (1995-2020 MHz): 13111-13361    Note 1: only frequency range 1930 MHz-1990 MHz is supported on band 25.  Note 2: band 29, band 32 and band 75 are downlink only.  Note 3: Downlink frequency range 2180-2200 MHz is restricted to E-UTRA operation when carrier aggregation is configured.  Note 4: If actFlexDupGap is set to 'true' non 3GPP compliant duplexing gaps are supported for band 1-28 and band 30-31.  Note 5: If "LAA Dynamic Channel Selection" is activated, then the configured value for earfcnDL might not match the actual value.  Note 6: The frequencies from sub-bands 46b/c cannot be configured, but are assigned by the dynamic frequency selection feature.

Parameter name: EARFCN uplink
Four layer MIMO average spectral efficiency
Description: The four layer MIMO average spectral efficiency is used by the throughput check during SCell addition as follows.  If the throughput metric after the SCell addition is greater than the throughput metric before the SCell addition then this SCell addition is admitted. Otherwise this SCell addition is rejected. The throughput metric is the sum of xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff*bandwidth of the UE's serving cells. Where xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to twoLayerMimoAvSpectralEff if the UE is configured with two layer MIMO on a given serving cell respectively xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to fourLayerMimoAvSpectralEff if the UE is configured with four layer MIMO on a given serving cell.    A reasonable value of the parameter can be derived from the existing KPI LTE_5747a 'DL Spectral efficiency' as follows. The KPI shall be collected in conditions where all UEs are four layer MIMO capable in this cell in order not to underestimate the average value (with dlMimoMode set to 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)' OR 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)' OR 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)').    The throughput check is not used by setting the parameter value to '0.5' i.e. any SCell addition will be always admitted by the check if twoLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to fourLayerMimoAvSpectralEff in all involved cells.

Parameter name: Kickdown state of an LAA cell
Description: Indicates, whether an LAA cell operates normally, or is subject to kickdown. If kicked down, pMaxLaa of the remaining LAA cell(s) linked to the same RRH than the kicked-down cell might have been increased.

Parameter name: Liquid cell CSI-RS resource configuration in use
Description: Defines which resource elements in the PRBs are used for the CSI-RS information, value is calculated automatically.  It is possible to define which resource elements in the PRBs are used for the CSI-RS information with parameter csiRsRes.

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - Liquid cell Single User Multi User mode
Description: Defines whether single and multi user, only single user or only multi user transmission is supported in the respective region.  If set to MultiUserOnly also in SU region Multi user transmission is applied.  The UL RSSI measurement is not very precise. In order to make it possible to control the utilization of single and multi user transmissions this switch provides a hard decision.

Parameter name: Unlicensed Cell Profile Identifier
Description: This parameter is used to indicate which profile is applied to the unlicensed cell.

Parameter name: Number of lower PUSCH Region Harq Nacks
Description: The parameter provides the threshold for the number of consecutive NACKs/DTX for a UE, from the lower PUSCH region PRBs 0-23, which must be reached so that eNB declares that this UE is located under a repeater with limited capabilities, and will no longer receive PUSCH allocations in that PRB range in the ongoing session.  Recommended value: 20.  If the parameter is set to '0', eNB does not check for consecutive NACKs/DTX from the lower PUSCH PRB range.

Parameter name: massive MIMO horizontal sector beamforming profile
Description: This parameter specifies massive MIMO horizontal sector beamforming profile
Range and step: SingleSectorBFProf(0 degree) (10), DualSectorBFProf(-30 degree) (11), DualSectorBFProf(+30 degree) (12)

Parameter name: Control of maximum number of spatial MIMO layers for TM4 with downlink MIMO mode 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)'
Description: This parameter controls the configuration of maximum number of spatial MIMO layers for TM4 when transmissions using TM9 based on 8 CSI-RS ports is limited to 2 layers (dlMimoMode=='Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)').  If set to value '2' then up to 2 layers for TM4 are supported.  If set to value '4' then up to 4 layers for TM4 are supported.

Parameter name: Maximum number of OFDM symbols for PDCCH
Description: The parameter defines how many OFDM symbols can be used for PDCCH channel transmission. eNB selects based on usage the actual value for each TTI, which and value is signaled to the UEs in PCFICH.    If dlChBw equals '3 MHz' it is recommended to set the parameter to '3'.

Parameter name: Max number act DRB
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of established DRBs in the cell.  The maximum number of established DRBs depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:    1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 600  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 2520  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3000  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 3750  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 4500    Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are:    1.4 MHz bandwidth 60  3 MHz bandwidth 200  5 MHz bandwidth 480  10 MHz bandwidth 600  15 MHz bandwidth 1200  20 MHz bandwidth 1200    Dependencies:  maxNumActDrb + max( addNumDrbRadioReasHo, addNumDrbTimeCriticalHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above)    For AirScale deployment:  For AirScale deployed eNBs the maximum values for the cells do not only depend on cell BW but also on pool limits. A special configuration has to be considered by operator on any variant of AirScale ABIA without BBpooling:  - if AirScale deployment on 1 ABIA (any variant) has mixed BW cells i.e. at least 1 cell > 10MHz and cells <= 10 MHz then the 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells are restricted for parameter maxNumActDrb to 0...1260.    For Interworking with LTE-M/CAT-M:  DRBs admitted for CAT-M UEs are checked against the maxNumActDrb threshold and counted as for legacy UEs in the hosting cell and on any variant of AirScale ABIA/ABIC baseband pool.

Parameter name: Maximum number of active UEs
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell. Active UEs are UEs with at least one DRB.  With introduction of dynamic PUCCH or AirScale HW this parameter is also used to calculate the allowed number of RRC connections per cell.  In case CAT-M UEs are served in the same cell (hosting cell) and have at least 1 DRB the admitted CAT-M UEs will reduce number of legacy active UEs because they share the same resources.    Note that default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. User shall configure this parameter based on different bandwidth and BTS type.    The maximum cell RRC capacity per BW are as given below:  1.4 MHz bandwidth: 0-40  3 MHz bandwidth without inband NB-IoT: 0-120  3 MHz bandwidth with inband NB-IoT on AirScale: 0-120 (the sum of wideband and NB-IoT UEs may not exceed 120 admitted UEs)  5 MHz bandwidth: 0-840  10 MHz bandwidth: 0-1000  15 MHz bandwidth: 0-1250  20 MHz bandwidth: 0-1500    Any variant of AirScale ABIA/ABIC/ABIN/ABIO/ABIP/ABIQ/ASOE/ASOF/ASOG/ASOH:  On AirScale deployments the configured maxNumActUE is the basic amount of admittable UEs per cell and maxNumRrc is no longer used.  The maximum amount of admittable UEs is additionally limited due to BB pool limitations.    The sum of maxNumActUE + minNumRrcNoDrb replaces the former maxNumRrc used for FSMr3 in case dyn. PUCCH is deactivated.  The sum of maxNumActUE + aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb replaces the former maxNumRrc in case dyn. PUCCH is activated (also on FSMr3).  The sum of handover margins and possibly configured emergency/HPS margins and maxNumActUE may not exceed the upper value ranges per BW (see below the description of dependency of dyn. PUCCH feature);    For AirScale deployment:  The admission of RRC requests with threshold maxNumActUE values for the cells do not only depend on cell BW but also on baseband pool limits.  The baseband pool limits for different baseband modules (like ABIA, ABIC, ABIN, ABIP/ABIQ etc.) may be different and need to be looked up in the release documentation for each BB HW.    The following special configurations have to be considered by operator for any variant of AirScale ABIA without BB pooling:  - if any variant of AirScale ABIA deployment on 1 ABIA has mixed BW cells i.e. at least 1 cell > 10 MHz and cells <= 10 MHz then the 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells are restricted for maxNumActUE to 0-420.  - if any variant of AirScale ABIA deployment on 1 ABIA has 7 or 8 cells of 5/10 MHz bandwidth then the 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells are restricted for maxNumActUE to 0-630 even if cellTechnology = FDD and nbIoTMode = inband  Dependencies of dynamic PUCCH feature:  if dynamic PUCCH is deactivated  maxNumActUE + minNumRrcNoDrb + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) + minNumEmergencySessions must be less than the cell RRC capacity per BW (e.g. 840 for 20 MHz)  if dynamic PUCCH is activated  maxNumActUE + aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb + max(aPucchAddAUeRrHo, aPucchAddAUeTcHo) + aPucchMinNumEmergencySessions + aPucchMinNumRrcHps must be less than the cell RRC capacity per BW (e.g., 840 for a 20 MHz cell)    In case ABIA (any variant) baseband pooling is activated the value of these parameters may be internally adapted by the system based on the number of cells allocated to that pool.    For more information related AirScale on allocation of cells to baseband pools and maximum cell capacity, please see related CuDo for feature LTE2733.  Please note that cells are allocated dynamically to pools by eNB. This means that offline checks on thresholds can only consider the max. value for a single cell.  The maximum value of 1500 active UEs can only be reached if aPucchSrPeriodUpperLimit is configured to 40 ms.    In case of interworking with CAT-M the allowed CAT-M UEs may reduce the admissions of legacy active UEs as they share the same resource pool and they are counted on same admission counter. The upper threshold for both types of active UEs is BW specific as specified above {40, 120, 840,1000,1250,1500}).

Parameter name: Max number carrier aggr configured UEs
Description: Threshold to limit the maximum number of carrier aggregation configured UEs in a PCell (P-LNCEL);  UEs may have 1 PCell (P-LNCEL) and 1 or several SCell(s) (S-LNCEL).  Carrier aggregated UEs with 1 or more SCell need more resources than nonCA Ues (PUCCH and MAC PS);  Therefore limiting the amount of CA-UEs is necessary.    In case the threshold is modified online and the value is decreased, existing CA-UEs may stay in the cell, but the new value applies to new admission checks only.

Parameter name: Max number carrier aggr configured UEs 3 Carriers
Description: Threshold to limit the maximum number of carrier aggregation configured UEs in a PCell (P-LNCEL); 3c (3 carriers) indicates that these UEs have 1 PCell (P-LNCEL) and 2 or more (up to 5) SCells (S-LNCEL).  Carrier aggregated UEs with 2 or more SCell need a higher amount of resources (PUCCH) compared with single carrier UEs as long as UL signalling is done only via PCell. That's why the information 3c is relevant.    In case the threshold is modified online and the value is decreased, existing CA-UEs may stay in the cell, but the new value applies to new admission checks only.

Parameter name: Max number Carrier Aggr configured UEs double carrier
Description: Threshold to limit the maximum number of carrier aggregation configured UEs in a cell PCell (P-LNCEL); Dc (Double carrier) indicates that these UEs have 1 PCell (P-LNCEL) and only 1 SCell (S-LNCEL).  Carrier aggregated UEs with 1 SCell need double amount of UL resources compared with single carrier UEs as long as UL signaling is done only via PCell. That's why the information Dc is relevant.  In case the threshold is modified online and the value is decreased, existing CA-UEs may stay in the cell, but the new value applies to new admission checks only.

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Maximum number of layers per MU RBG
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of layers per MU RBG which are paired into DL MU-MIMO in massive MIMO.

Parameter name: Max number QCI1 DRBs (GBRs)
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of established QCI1-GBR-DRBs in the cell.  The parameter is only relevant if ""actEnhAcAndGbrServices"" is set to 'false' and ignored otherwise.  QCI1-DRBs are additional counted data radio bearers in the cell and are also checked against the threshold maxNumActDrb.    The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:    Value ranges for the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA and actEnhAcAndGbrServices is equal to 'false' (for no AirScale upper limits in brackets)  1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 10 (10)  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 60 (60)  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200 (200)  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 200 (400)  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 300 (500)  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 300 (600)    Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are:    1.4 MHz bandwidth 5  3 MHz bandwidth 25  5 MHz bandwidth 75  10 MHz bandwidth 100  15 MHz bandwidth 100  20 MHz bandwidth 100    For any variant of AirScale ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOE/ASOF, ASOG/ASOH with at least one LTE cell configured, this parameter is not relevant as those AirScale modules operates always with BBpooling and Smart AC activated (actEnhAcAndGbrServices = true).    Dependencies:  maxNumQci1Drb + max( addNumQci1DrbRadioReasHo, addNumQci1DrbTimeCriticalHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above for e.g. FSMr3 (10, 60, 200, 400, 500, 600)).

Parameter name: Maximum amount of users per TTI in DL
Description: This is the maximum number of simultaneous users scheduled in a TTI in downlink.    The following values are allowed:    1.4 MHz bandwidth: 1...7  3 MHz bandwidth: 1...7  5 MHz bandwidth: 1...7  10 MHz bandwidth: 1...14  15 MHz bandwidth: 1...17  20 MHz bandwidth: 1...20    Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths.

Parameter name: Maximum amount of users per TTI in UL
Description: This is the maximum number of simultaneous users scheduled in a TTI in uplink.    The following values are allowed:      1.4 MHz bandwidth: 1...7  3 MHz bandwidth: 1...7  5 MHz bandwidth: 1...7  10 MHz bandwidth: 1...14  15 MHz bandwidth: 1...17  20 MHz bandwidth: 1...20    Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths.

Parameter name: PRB limit for high prio UCI-only grants per TTI
Description: The parameter limits the total number of PRBs to be assigned for high priority UCI-only grants per TTI.

Parameter name: MIMO Closed Loop configuration - CQI threshold for fallback to CL MIMO 1 CW mode
Description: CQI Threshold for fallback to closed loop MIMO single codeword transmission (in CQI) in case of activated 'Dynamic MIMO Switch' (i.e. actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'). Not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true'.

Parameter name: MIMO Closed Loop configuration - CQI threshold for activation of CL MIMO 2 CW mode
Description: CQI Threshold for activation of closed loop MIMO dual codeword transmission (in CQI) in case of activated 'Dynamic MIMO Switch' (i.e. actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'). Not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true'.

Parameter name: MIMO Closed Loop configuration - Rank threshold for fallback to CL MIMO 1 CW mode
Description: Rank Threshold for fallback to closed loop MIMO single codeword transmission in case of activated 'Dynamic MIMO Switch' (i.e. actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'). Not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true'.

Parameter name: MIMO Closed Loop configuration - Rank threshold for activation of CL MIMO 2 CW mode
Description: Rank Threshold for activation of closed loop MIMO dual codeword transmission in case of activated 'Dynamic MIMO Switch' (i.e. actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'). Not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true'.

Parameter name: MIMO Open Loop configuration - CQI threshold for fallback to MIMO diversity
Description: CQI threshold for fallback to Open Loop MIMO diversity (in CQI).

Parameter name: MIMO Open Loop configuration - CQI threshold for activation of OL MIMO SM
Description: CQI threshold for activation of Open Loop MIMO Spatial Multiplexing (in CQI).

Parameter name: MIMO Open Loop configuration - Rank threshold for fallback to MIMO diversity
Description: Rank threshold for fallback to Open Loop MIMO diversity.

Parameter name: MIMO Open Loop configuration - Rank threshold for activation of OL MIMO SM
Description: Rank threshold for activation of Open Loop MIMO Spatial Multiplexing.

Parameter name: Adjust max number of high prio UCI-only grants per TTI
Description: The parameter limits the number of UCI-only grants scheduled per TTI.  The product multNumUeHighPrioUciGrant* maxNumUeUl defines the max. number of UEs eligible for high priority UCI-only grants allowed per TTI.  The result of the product multNumUeHighPrioUciGrant* maxNumUeUl shall be rounded down to the next integer number.

Parameter name: Adjust timer for low and high priority UCI-only grants
Description: The parameter is used in the UL scheduler to determine candidate UEs for a) low priority UCI-only grants and b) high priority UCI-only grants.  Higher values of this parameter lead to longer timer periods until UE becomes a candidate for low/high priority UCI-only grant.

Parameter name: Number of downlink PRBs blanked at the lower end of the spectrum
Description: Number of downlink Physical Resource Blocks (PRBs) blanked at the lower end of the spectrum

Parameter name: Number of downlink PRBs blanked at the upper end of the spectrum
Description: Number of downlink Physical Resource Blocks (PRBs) blanked at the upper end of the spectrum

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information - CSI-RS ports number
Description: Number of CSI-RS ports  In 3GPP 2,4,8 CSI-RS ports are supported.  Currently 4 ports for LTE1987 are supported.  Currently 8 ports for LTE4300 are supported.  Currently 8 ports for one aggregation of CSI-RS configuration for LTE4304 are supported.

Parameter name: Maximum output power, LAA mode
Description: This parameter defines the maximum output power of the LAA cell per antenna carrier in dBm, as limited by country-specific regulatory constraints. The maximum output power is the maximum value for the linear sum of the power of all downlink physical channels that is allowed to be used in a cell. The reference point is the antenna connector.    For the LAA Micro RRH, the range of maximum output power is 14 dBm to 27 dBm;    Note: The allowed cell power value is set by the system and depends on the used hardware variant, the country of operation, the number of LAA cells configured, and the specific Wi-Fi channels / sub-bands enabled. Please refer to the documentation where per variant the supported power values are specified.    Note: This parameter is valid for LAA cells and will be used instead of LNCEL-pMax.

Parameter name: PDCCH load level
Description: The PDCCH load level configures the percentage of used PDCCH CCEs on all available PDCCH CCEs.  Used PDCCH CCEs include all CCEs of CSS/USS space and dummy PDCCHs.  This parameter will not restrict normal PDCCH allocation. Only when normal PDCCH load has not reach the level defined by this parameter, dummy PDCCHs will be added.  This parameter is mandatory when actPdcchLoadGen is set to "true".    If transmission bandwidth is reduced by Slim Carrier functionality, than this parameter configures interference level relative to maximum available Slim Carrier bandwidth.

Parameter name: PSD offset for dummy PDCCH
Description: This parameter defines the dummy PDCCH PSD offset to flat PSD.  Maximum dummy PDCCH PSD is calculated based on flat PSD and this offset.  If there is not enough power remaining for dummy PDCCHs, smaller dummy PDCCH PSD will be used.  This parameter is mandatory when actPdcchLoadGen is set to "true".

Parameter name: PRACH cyclic shift
Description: Preamble cyclic shift defines the configuration which is used for preamble generation. The configuration determines how many cyclic shifts are needed to generate preamble. Unrestricted set is supported.  Configuration also defines the zero correlation zone and respective maximum cell range.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: PRACH configuration index
Description: Defines allowed system frame and subframe numbers for random access attempts, and the preamble format.  Supported values of the prachConfIndex are: 0...8, 15...24, 31, 48...56, 63.    For a cell with bandwidth 1.4 MHz the following prachConfIndex values are recommended dependent on the physical cell id (PCI):  For a cell with bandwidth 1.4 MHz or 3 Mhz the following prachConfIndex values are recommended dependent on the physical cell id (PCI):  In case of PRACH format 0:  - PCI modulo 3 = 0 => prachConfIndex = 3 => PRACH occasion is within TTI 1  - PCI modulo 3 = 1 => prachConfIndex = 4 => PRACH occasion is within TTI 4  - PCI modulo 3 = 2 => prachConfIndex = 5 => PRACH occasion is within TTI 7  In case of PRACH format 1:  - PCI modulo 3 = 0 => prachConfIndex = 19 => PRACH occasion is within TTI 1 and 2  - PCI modulo 3 = 1 => prachConfIndex = 20 => PRACH occasion is within TTI 4 and 5  - PCI modulo 3 = 2 => prachConfIndex = 21 => PRACH occasion is within TTI 7 and 8

Parameter name: PRACH frequency offset
Description: Defines the location in frequency for the PRACH transmissions.  For UL scheduling it is recommended that PRACH is located next to PUCCH either on the lower or upper edge of the bandwidth because UL PRB allocations for UEs consist of consecutive PRBs. If there is a small gap between PUCCH and PRACH PRBs, UL scheduler cannot utilize those PRBs efficiently. prachFreqOffset for each bandwidth should be set aligned with the parameters determining the number of PRBs for PUCCH, so that PRACH is located next to PUCCH.  It is recommended to set the value such that PRACH does not overlap with PUCCH PRBs and is located adjacent to PUCCH; thus recommended parameter alternatives are:  1) roundup((MaxPucchResourceSize+blankedPucch)/2) if it is located at the lower edge, or  2) ulChBw(in PRBs)-6-roundup((MaxPucchResourceSize+blankedPucch)/2 ) if it is located at the upper edge of the PUSCH area    The MaxPucchResourceSize in above defines the maximum number of allocated PUCCH PRBs, and it defined in nCqiRb parameter.

Parameter name: PRACH high speed flag
Description: High speed flag for PRACH preamble generation determines whether an unrestricted or a restricted set has to be used by the UE.  false = Unrestricted; true = Restricted

Parameter name: PRS configuration index
Description: Determines the periodicity and offset of the PRS occasions for FDD    PRS period based on the configured value of prsConfigurationIndex:  7, 14, 27, 47, 67, 87, 107, 127, 147, 151: 160 ms period  471: 320 ms period  1111: 640 ms period  2391: 1280 ms period  The periodicity and offset can be computed according to 3GPP TS 36.211 Rel9    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: PRS Number of DL frames
Description: Number of DL Frames that are used for PRS per PRS occasion for FDD. With this PRS transmission can be repeated within a PRS occasion in order to increase the hearability of PRS    All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: PUCCH cyclic shift for mixed formats
Description: Number of cyclic shifts for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b in a resource block used for a mix of formats 1/1a/b and 2/2a/2b.  This parameter is one of the parameters in a set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called as MaxPucchResourceSize.

Parameter name: RACH density
Description: Used as an input parameter for selecting possible PRACH Configuration Index parameter.

Parameter name: Reduced frequency offset
Description: This parameter defines the reduced frequency offset from carrier center frequency to sub-block edge at both downlink and uplink direction. However, uplink direction is not applicable for supplemental downlink carrier.

Parameter name: Supercell parameter set - UL SINR Hys for removing candidate subcell
Description: Defines the UL SINR hysteresis on top of candSubCellUlSinrOffset for candidate subcell to be removed.  If the SINR gap between serving subcell and current candidate subcell is larger than candSubCellUlSinrOffset plus this parameter this candidate subcell will be changed to measurement-only subcell.

Parameter name: Supercell parameter set - UL SINR Hys for replacing candidate subcell
Description: Defines the UL SINR hysteresis to replace candidate subcell by a measurement subcell.  If one measurement-only subcell's SINR is larger than current candidate subcell's SINR plus repCandSubCellUlSinrHys, this measurement-only subcell will replace current candidate subcell as new candidate subcell.

Parameter name: RACH root sequence
Description: The preamble generation is started from the Root Sequence which is pointed by the logical root sequence number. 64 preambles can be transmitted in the PRACH frame. If one root is not enough to generate all the 64 preambles, then the consecutive number is selected until the full set is generated. RACH root sequence is cell specific information and neighbouring cells should have a different value. RACH root sequence is transmitted in system information.

Parameter name: Target UL outer scheduling region
Description: This parameter activates the feature LTE825 'Uplink outer region scheduling' by selecting the target UL outer scheduling region for PUSCH and PRACH. When the feature is activated, additional PRBs in the outer region of the UL spectrum are allocated for PUSCH and PRACH scheduling.  The feature LTE825 'Uplink outer region scheduling' is deactivated if parameter is set to 'None'.  The outer region is conform to the blanked PUCCH PRBs.

Parameter name: Slim Carrier RF Filter in Downlink
Description: The parameter slimRfFilterDL allows configuring a dedicated RF filter in downlink. Only enumerated set of dedicated filter bandwidths are supported. With the default value (slimRfFilterDL = nominal) RF filter bandwidth is set based on value of the parameter dlChBw.    In case RF unit does not support configured dedicated downlink filter bandwidth, nominal filter bandwidth is used (configured based on dlChBw).

Parameter name: Slim Carrier RF Filter in Uplink
Description: The parameter slimRfFilterUL allows configuring a dedicated RF filter in uplink. Only enumerated set of dedicated filter bandwidths are supported. With the default value (slimRfFilterUL = nominal) RF filter bandwidth is set based on value of the parameter ulChBw.    In case RF unit does not support configured dedicated uplink filter bandwidth, nominal filter bandwidth is used (configured based on ulChBw).

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Downlink MU-MIMO spectrum efficiency threshold
Description: This parameter specifies the spectrum efficiency threshold which works as a criteria for adding a UE to a UE pairing and ensure the gain of spectrum efficiency.  The spectrumEffThd shall be set to 1.0 by default and further optimized by simulation.

Parameter name: SRS feature activation/deactivation
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates SRS (sounding reference symbol) feature in the cell.

Parameter name: Power offset for SRS transmission power calculation
Description: UE specific power offset to be used for Sounding Reference Signal transmission power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P3).    Note: The actual power offset depends on value of deltaTfEnabled.  For deltaTfEnabled = 'true' (KS = 1.25) the actual parameter value is "srsPwrOffset-3" corresponding to the dB-range of -3 dB to 12 dB in steps of 1 dB. For deltaTfEnabled = 'false' (KS = 0) the actual parameter value is "-10.5 + 1.5 * srsPwrOffset" value corresponding to the dB-range -10.5 dB to 12 dB in steps of 1.5 dB.

Parameter name: Starting cell range for donut cell
Description: This parameter defines the starting cell range for a donut cell. It will be internally converted into a corresponding Rx window shift.    Note: If the feature activation parameter actDonutCell is set to 'true', then any creation/modification of this parameter (startOfDonutCell) will cause a BTS restart.

Parameter name: Subcell Configuration
Description: This parameter gives the possibility to define the maximum output power of the subcells per antenna carrier.

Parameter name: Subcell Maximum Transmission Power
Description: This parameter defines the maximum output power of the subcell per antenna carrier in dBm.

Parameter name: Subcell ID
Description: This parameter defines the subcell for which the maximum transmission power shall be defined.

Parameter name: Supercell parameter set - UL SINR hysteresis for subcell switch 1
Description: Defines the UL SINR hysteresis for subcell switch.  The parameter defines the UL SINR hysteresis for subcell switch from candidate to serving subcell. It will be used in conjunction with subcellSinrFiltConst1.  It is recommended to keep the parameter set to default values.

Parameter name: Supercell parameter set - UL SINR hysteresis for subcell switch 2
Description: Additional UL SINR hysteresis for subcell switch.  The parameter defines an additional UL SINR hysteresis for subcell switch from candidate to serving subcell. It is applicable when prachHsFlag is set to true and will be used in conjunction with subcellSinrFiltConst 2.  It is recommended to keep the parameter set to the default value.

Parameter name: Supercell parameter set - Subcell SINR filter constant 1
Description: Coefficient of the exponential filter applied to SINR measurements from the subcells.  The value of subcellSinrFiltConst1 determines the settling time of the filter applied to SINR measurements. It is used in conjunction with parameter subCellSwitchUlSinrHys1.  If prachHsFlag is set to false, a default value of 0.9 shall be used.  If prachHsFlag is set to true, a default value 0.3 shall be used.  It is recommended to keep the parameter set to the default values.

Parameter name: Supercell parameter set - Subcell SINR filter constant 2
Description: Additional coefficient of the exponential filter applied to SINR measurements from the subcells.  The value of subcellSinrFiltConst2 allows additional tuning of the settling time of the filter applied to SINR measurements. It is used in conjunction with parameter subCellSwitchUlSinrHys2 and applicable when prachHsFlag is set to true.  It is recommended to keep the parameter set to the default value.

Parameter name: Synchronization signals transmission mode
Description: The parameter determines whether Primary and Secondary Synchronization Signals (PSS, SSS) are transmitted into a cell via one antenna port (SingleTx) or via all antenna ports using TX diversity with Precoding Vector Switching (PVS). In case of 2 or 4 antenna port configuration is done in a flexible way based on the antenna configuration.

Parameter name: Transmission mode switch profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the assigned transmission mode switch profile.    The profile contains CQI thresholds and time interval for switching between transmission modes.

Parameter name: Two layer MIMO average spectral efficiency
Description: The two layer MIMO average spectral efficiency is used by the throughput check during SCell addition as follows.  If the throughput metric after the SCell addition is greater than the throughput metric before the SCell addition then this SCell addition is admitted. Otherwise this SCell addition is rejected. The throughput metric is the sum of xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff*bandwidth of the UE's serving cells. Where xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to twoLayerMimoAvSpectralEff if the UE is configured with two layer MIMO on a given serving cell respectively xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to fourLayerMimoAvSpectralEff if the UE is configured with four layer MIMO on a given serving cell.    A reasonable value of the parameter can be derived from the existing KPI LTE_5747a 'DL Spectral efficiency' with dlMimoMode set to 'Closed Loop Mimo' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)'.    The throughput check is not used by setting the parameter value to '0.5' i.e. any SCell addition will be always admitted by the check if twoLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to fourLayerMimoAvSpectralEff in all involved cells.

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - UL measurement alpha base
Description: Basic value for alpha. This value is recalculated according cqiPerNp and used in the exponential filters for UL measurements.  The value of uLMeasAlphaBase determines the settling time of the UL measurement filter and should be chosen according uLMeasN.

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - UL measurement joint transmission region hysteresis
Description: Defines the hysteresis used on the threshold uLMeasJtCsiRs.  The hysteresis value is a function of uLMeasN and uLMeasAlphaBase.    A larger hysteresis value leads to a more stable UE location estimation at the cost of lower resolution.    It should be chosen such that the difference of 90th-percentile and 10th-percentile of the RSSI ratio estimate coresponds to twice the value of uLMeasHystJT.    Example setup for >80% location estimates inside hysteresis range:  uLMeasN=75; uLMeasAlphaBase=0.013  @2GHz: uLMeasHystJT=2dB  @1GHz: uLMeasHystJT=2.6dB  @700MHz: uLMeasHystJT=3.3dB    uLMeasN=100; uLMeasAlphaBase=0.01  @2GHz: uLMeasHystJT=1.7dB  @1GHz: uLMeasHystJT=2.5dB  @700MHz: uLMeasHystJT=2.9dB

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - UL measurement SU MU transmission region hysteresis
Description: Defines the hysteresis used on the threshold uLMeasThrSuMuCsiRs.  The hysteresis value is a function of uLMeasN and uLMeasAlphaBase.    A larger hysteresis value leads to a more stable UE location estimation at the cost of lower resolution.    It should be chosen such that the difference of 90th-percentile and 10th-percentile of the RSSI ratio estimate coresponds to twice the value of uLMeasHystJT.    Example setup for >80% location estimates inside hysteresis range:  uLMeasN=75; uLMeasAlphaBase=0.013  @2GHz: uLMeasHystJT=2dB  @1GHz: uLMeasHystJT=2.6dB  @700MHz: uLMeasHystJT=3.3dB    uLMeasN=100; uLMeasAlphaBase=0.01  @2GHz: uLMeasHystJT=1.7dB  @1GHz: uLMeasHystJT=2.5dB  @700MHz: uLMeasHystJT=2.9dB

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - UL measurement counter N samples
Description: Defines the number of samples to be received before measurement evaluation and switching the filter to state reliable.    After N samples a new evaluation of region/group assignment is triggered.  A larger value of uLMeasN leads to less variance of location estimation.

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - UL measurement joint transmission region threshold
Description: Defines the threshold of the UE UL pathloss ratio to both tx point of a Liquid Cell. It separates the Joint transmission region and the single transmission region.

Parameter name: Liquid cell configuration information - UL measurement SU MU transmission region threshold
Description: Defines the threshold of the UE UL pathloss ratio to both tx point of a Liquid Cell. It separates the single user transmission region and the multi user transmission region.  The smallest value must be set equal greater than uLMeasThrJTCsiRs.

Parameter name: Uplink channel bandwidth
Description: Uplink channel bandwidth defines the UL bandwidth for the eNB transmission in a cell, and also defines the number of available Physical Resource Blocks.    If a 'SuperCell' is activated (actSuperCell set to 'true') the bandwidth usage is limited to 5 MHz, 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz.  Uplink channel bandwidth defines the UL bandwidth for the eNB transmission in a cell, and also defines the number of available Physical Resource Blocks.    The uplink channel bandwidth mapping to number of PRBs is:  1.4 MHz = 6 UL PRBS  3.0 MHz = 15 UL PRBS  5.0 MHz = 25 UL PRBS  10.0 MHz = 50 UL PRBS  15.0 MHz = 75 UL PRBS  20.0 MHz = 100 UL PRBS    Maximum 10 MHz uplink channel bandwidth may be used with single FSMD to configure more than 2 cells or with single FSME to configure more than 3 cells.    1.4 MHz and 3.0 MHz uplink channel bandwidth is only supported on FSMF or the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA.    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Uplink combination mode
Description: Identifies the uplink combination mode, possibilities are MRC and IRC.    2-way or 4-way RX diversity will be automatically selected by eNB dependent on the number of RX antenna lines which are configured in the CHANNEL instances of the related LCELL.  In case of 4 RX antennas, the IRC algorithm will automatically switch to MRC dependent on the interference situation.    For optimal performance of the IRC mode it is recommended to deploy phase synchronization via GPS.    IRC reception is not supported with FSMD / FSME.  Four RX antenna reception is not supported with FSMD / FSME.

Parameter name: UL interference offset
Description: This parameter adds an offset to the measured UL interference, in order to bias the selection of the UE's preferred scheduling area away from a PRB region with power restrictions.  The value is configured in percent of the A-MPR or equivalent power reduction that the UL scheduler adds to the measured UE's UL interference in a PRB range where UL Tx power restrictions apply (A-MPR etc., from TS36.101), on top of the value needed to compensate the UL power reduction given by the scenario identified by actUlPwrRestrScn (band18_26: 1.5 dB; band30_NS21: 3 dB; band13_NS07: {8dB or 12dB for lower PUSCH region depending on UL grant size, 0dB or 12dB for center PUSCH region depending on UL grant size, 0dB for upper PUSCH region}; band1_NS05: {11dB for lower PUSCH region, 0dB or 3dB or 5dB for center PUSCH region depending on UL grant size, 1dB or 5dBdB for upper PUSCH region depending on UL grant size}). Example: an offset of +50% adds 0.75 dB on top of the 1.5 dB that is required for compensation in the band18_26 scenario.  No offset is added to PM counter values.  If actUlPwrRestrScn is set to 'band19_NS08' then ulInterferenceOffset is not required to be configured. If it is configured, its value is ignored.

Parameter name: TPC command in random access response
Description: TPC command indicated in the Random Access response related to Random Access message 3 or 1st scheduled uplink transmission.

Parameter name: Maximum PUSCH coding rate for small allocations
Description: This parameter defines the maximum code rate for PUSCH in case of small allocations (1...3 PRBs)  Smaller values increase the robustness of the transmission. High values may increase UL BLER and PING RTT.  The robustness of small PUSCH allocations is more susceptible to the addition of data like aperiodic CQI.

Parameter name: PUSCH mask
Description: Table which defines the location of the PUSCH mask in the UL spectrum.

Parameter name: Length of the PUSCH mask
Description: Length of the PUSCH mask in the UL spectrum. The length is defined by number of PRBs.

Parameter name: Start PRB of the PUSCH mask
Description: Start PRB of the PUSCH mask in the UL spectrum.

Parameter name: UTRAN balancing load thresholds - DL GBR resource high load
Description: This parameter defines the high load for the DL GBR resources. The value represents a percentage of PRBs available to GBR in the cell.    A cell is considered 'non-balanced' if any load component has reached its highLoad threshold.

Parameter name: UTRAN balancing load thresholds - DL non-GBR resource high load
Description: This parameter defines the high load for the DL non-GBR resources. The value represents a percentage of the non-GBR load scale 0 and 100.    A cell is considered 'non-balanced' if any load component has reached its highLoad threshold.

Parameter name: UTRAN balancing load thresholds - PDCCH high load
Description: This parameter defines the high load for the PDCCH. The value represents a percentage of the available PDCCH resources in the cell.    A cell is considered 'non-balanced' if any load component has reached its highLoad threshold.

Parameter name: TDD specific cell parameter identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of object LNCEL_TDD. It uniquely defines the object containing TDD technology specific cell parameter. It is used only for operation and maintenance purposes.

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A2 to activate TD-SCDMA measurement
Description: Time to trigger activation of TD-SCDMA measurements  Duration for which the event A2 must be valid, such that TD-SCDMA measurements are activated

Parameter name: Activate 1TX in 2TX configuration
Description: This is to activate Dual transmission mode 1 operation when 2 Tx RF unit can be used for two times 1Tx transmission in Distributed Antenna Systems (DAS)

Parameter name: Activate 2-CRS in 4 TX configuration
Description: This parameter activates the 2 cell-specific reference signal deployment in 4 TX antenna lines.    Note: LNCEL_TDD - dlMimoMode is recommended to equal to 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)', if act2CrsIn4Tx is equal to 'true'.

Parameter name: Activate support of 4RX for high speed UEs
Description: Activates 4Rx receiver is supported for PUSCH/PUCCH with high speed

Parameter name: Activate adaptive PRB number for DL Retransmission
Description: Parameter to activate or deactivate the Adaptive PRB number for DL retransmission in a cell, it is only for TDD massive MIMO. it is used to improve PRB resource utilization when the number of Ues scheduled is limited due to PDCCH limitation, shortage of the number of active Ues with data, etc.

Parameter name: Activate Adaptive Sector BF Weight
Description: The parameter can activate or deactivate the functionality of adaptive sector beamforming(BF) weight.  When actAdptSectorBfWeight is set to 0: OFF, no impact from dynamic sector BF weight adaption. When it is not set to 0:OFF, the sector BF weight of mMIMO will be dynamic adaptive based on Time or Traffic trigger. The 'Traffic based trigger' mode which combines with 'Time based trigger' further increase the traffic related conditions for this functionality.    Note: When the functionality of adaptive sector beamforming(BF) weight is activated, the secondary sector beamforming profile will be applied for high load if the parameter LNCEL_TDD-mMIMOSecSectorBFProfName is configured.
Range and step: OFF (0), Time based trigger (1), Traffic based trigger (2)

Parameter name: Activation of automatic PUCCH allocation
Description: This parameter activates the automatic PUCCH configuration of the LNCEL. When activated a limited set of PUCCH parameters need to be configured in class MPUCCH belonging to the cell, all other parameters are assigned by the system itself automatically.    For disabled functionality the standard PUCCH remains available.    Note: Only if actAutoPucchAlloc of the LNCEL_TDD instance is activated, the configured value of actLbPucchReg is considered by the BTS.

Parameter name: Beamforming fallbacking activation
Description: Active/deactive the functionality of beamforming fallbacking  If actBfFallback is set to true, fallback functionality from beamforming to TxDiv is activated based on the thresholds defined in mimoBfslCqiThD and mimoBfslCqiThU.

Parameter name: Activate CEBB
Description: This parameter activates feature LTE1783 "Constrained Beamforming" per individual cell.    Constrained Beamforming in the cell will be functional only if the relative antenna element spacing of the antenna used for the cell is in range 0.470...0.525 lambda or 0.620...0.675 lambda.  Calculation:  relative antenna element spacing [lambda] = antennaElementSpacing [mm]/1000*earfcn[Hz]/(3*10^8 [m/s])

Parameter name: Adaptive number of layers for downlink MU-MIMO activation
Description: This parameter activates adaptive number of layers of downlink MU-MIMO in TDD Massive MIMO

Parameter name: The activation of mitigating higher DL BLER
Description: This parameter activates mitigating higher DL BLER for certain types of UE chipsets which don't support port8 DMRS in single streaming while using TM8.

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - MU gain maximization
Description: MU gain can be maximized by pairing as many RBGs as possible at the cost of violating legacy weighted round robin criterion.  GBR performance will not be affected by MU maximization.  This parameter is used for 8T8R DL MU MIMO.

Parameter name: Activate Downlink MU-MIMO
Description: Parameter to activate or deactivate DL MU-MIMO in a cell. It is used to support TM7, TM8 or TM9 MU-MIMO.

Parameter name: Activate downlink MU-MIMO zero forcing
Description: This parameter activates advanced algorithm to mitigate MU-MIMO downlink interference and improve performance.

Parameter name: Activate downlink new transmission schedule based on buffer
Description: The parameter activates/deactivates the function of HARQ Selective Scheduling for Dl New transmission in SF/3/8 with TDD UL-DL config 2, it is only for TDD massive MIMO. It is used to increase priority of Dl new transmission based on data in buffer for improve DL PRB resource utilization in Subframe /3/8 , when PDCCH load is high.

Parameter name: The enhancement of DL OLLA for mode control of beamforming activation
Description: This parameter activates OLLA enhancement by adding delta CQI to corrected CQI for beamforming relevant mode control, including TM3/TM7/TM8 mode switch and rank switch in TM8 mode

Parameter name: The enhancement of OLLA initialization for downlink rank switching activation in TM8
Description: This parameter activates the enhancement of delta CQI initialization during TM8 rank switching

Parameter name: Activate Downlink Pre-grouping for mMIMO MU
Description: The parameter can activate or deactivate the functionality of ue beam pre-grouping in TD for downlink MU-MIMO, it is only for TDD massive MIMO. It is used for multi-user pairing enhancement to improve spatial efficiency.

Parameter name: Activate Downlink QoE Based Enhancement
Description: Parameter to activate or deactivate the downlink Quality of Experience based scheduling in a cell, it is only for TDD massive MIMO. It is used to improve downlink throughput with support PTP(prioritized tail packet scheduling), PAS(packet aggregation scheduling), WBS(workload based scheduling), SPA(small packet aggregation) and dynamic optimizing number of UE per TTI.

Parameter name: Activate downlink retransmission schedule based on PDCCH capacity
Description: The parameter activates/deactivates the function of HARQ Selective Scheduling for Dl retransmission in Subframe /3/8 with TDD UL-DL config 2, it is only for TDD massive MIMO. It is used to optimize DL PRB resource utilization for Dl retransmission in Subframe /3/8 via improve the PDCCH resource allocation for UEs, when PDCCH load is high.

Parameter name: Activate DL dynamic target BLER
Description: This parameter activates the function of downlink dynamic target BLER  When this parameter is set to 'true', downlink dynamic target BLER shall be activated for the UEs configured with TM2/3/4/7, the relationship of CQIstepup and CQIstepdown shall update according to different target BLER in corresponding to the current modulation order. When DL dynamic target BLER and 256QAM feature (LTE2479) are activated together, the 256QAM capable UEs shall use the legacy algorithm instead of dynamic target BLER algorithm.

Parameter name: Activate Dual OLLA for TM8
Description: This parameter configures the codeword methodology to be applied for dual layer beamforming transmission mode 8.
Range and step: Single OLLA for TM8 (0), Dual OLLA for TM8 (1), Auto configure OLLA for TM8 (2)

Parameter name: Activate support of extended cell range in high speed
Description: This parameter enables the support of extended cell range in high speed. When activated, eNB supports extended cell range up to 77km even in high speed scenarios up to 350 km/h in open space (A2G scenario with LoS channel).

Parameter name: Activate extended Ncs
Description: actExtNcs activates and deactivates extended Ncs.  PRACH is extended for FWA (Fixed Wireless Access).

Parameter name: Extended timer to delay to use beamforming weight activation
Description: This parameter activates extended timer to delay to use beamforming weight in TDD Massive MIMO

Parameter name: Activate fast adaptive MIMO switch
Description: Enables 'Fast Adaptive MIMO Switching' for Closed Loop MIMO modes based on PMI/RI reports sent by UEs if actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'true'.  Enables 'Dynamic MIMO Switching' if actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'.  actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'true': Activation of 'Fast Adaptive MIMO Switching'  'Fast adaptive MIMO Switching' supports fast rank selection and fast codebook based precoding of data transmission using closed loop feedback of precoding matrix indicator (PMI) in combination with rank indicator (RI). PMI and RI reporting delays shall be minimized by periodic and aperiodic reports sent by UEs in order to optimize PMI closed loop gains in combination with optimized rank selection.    actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false': Activation of 'Dynamic MIMO Switching'  'Dynamic MIMO Switching' supports RI and CQI based rank selection after filtering of CQI and RI reports sent by the UE. 'Dynamic MIMO Switching' is using RI and CQI thresholds for rank selection by comparison with filtered values. The threshold parameters 'mimoClCqiThD', 'mimoClCqiThU', 'mimoClRiThD', 'mimoClRiThU' are activated and used for rank switching.

Parameter name: Massive MIMO activation
Description: This parameter activates Massive MIMO with AAS mMIMO capable antenna system.

Parameter name: Virtual resource load balance activation
Description: This parameter activates virtual resource load balance function.

Parameter name: Activate overbooking for mission-critical video
Description: This parameter activates overbooking for mission-critical video.

Parameter name: Activate PDCCH load generation
Description: This parameter controls the activation or deactivation of "Inter cell load generation for PDCCH".

Parameter name: Activate PDCCH multiplexing
Description: This parameter activates or deactivates PDCCH multiplexing for TDD mMIMO. The feature requires AirScale ABIC, AirScale ABIO/ABIOL, AirScale ABIN/ABINL, AirScale ASOE.  SRS based TM9 could be PDCCH beam candidate

Parameter name: Activate TDD Remote Interference Avoidance feature
Description: This parameter activates 'TDD Remote Interference Avoidance' feature

Parameter name: Activate TDD Remote Interference Mitigation feature
Description: This is a feature flag to activate TDD Remote Interference Mitigation feature

Parameter name: RIP alarming configuration - Activate RIP alarming
Description: Parameter actRIPAlarming activates/deactivates RIP alarming in the LNCEL instance. RIP alarms for the LNCEL instance are only send if the parameter is set to value 'true'.

Parameter name: Activate reduced WiMax interference
