Description: Activates reduced WiMax interference.    Under scenario which have WiMAX co-existence, the parameter shall be set to true to indicate the co-existence of WiMAX.    Under scenario which has no WiMAX co-existence but has other vendor's TD-LTE in co-existence there are two options:  - (1) to activate feature LTE1913, which requires configuring 'actReduceWimaxInterference' to 'true'  - (2) to activate feature LTE1388 to support SSP=4. This solution is preferred in this scenario, since it does not sacrifice the last symbol of normal uplink subframe #3 and #8.

Parameter name: Activate SFN cell configuration
Description: This parameter activates the combination of normal cells to one Single Frequency Network cell, in which same PCI is used for all subcells of the SFN cell.

Parameter name: Activate user Tput-based serving radio link qualification in load balancing
Description: This parameter activates the feature 'Serving radio link qualification with load balancing - II'.

Parameter name: Activate supercell configuration
Description: Activates the transmission of duplicated data streams via different RRHs in downlink, and the combination of uplink signals received from different RRHs.

Parameter name: Active transmission mode switch
Description: Activate or deactivate the dynamic transmission mode switch function.  dlMimoMode is needed to be set to {'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)'} or act2CrsIn4Tx is needed to be set to 'true' to enable TM3/TM9 mode switch, because csiRsConfigInfo can be configured when dlMimoMode is set to {'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)'} or act2CrsIn4Tx is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: UL MU-MIMO activation
Description: This parameter activates or deactivates UL MU-MIMO in a cell.

Parameter name: Activate UL Power Restriction Scenario mask
Description: This parameter activates the feature A-MPR for "band48_NS27" by selecting a preconfigured UL power restriction scenario.  Use this parameter to select an UL power restriction defined in 3GPP TS36.101. An interference offset value must be present if actUlPwrRestrScn is not set to 'none'.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Activate UL SPS
Description: Activation of UL Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS) for UEs with Quality of Service Class Identifier 1 (QCI-1) bearers.

Parameter name: Activate UpPTS blanking
Description: Activates UpPTS blanking.

Parameter name: Activated MIMO transmission mode
Description: This parameter configures the selection of the Closed Loop MIMO transmission mode TM4 or TM9 depending on the capability of the UE. Up to 4 spatial multiplexing layers can be supported based on TM4 (MIMO4x4-TM4) or TM9 (MIMO4x4-TM9, MIMO8x2-8pTM9 or MIMO8x4-8pTM9).    The following settings for the parameter activatedMimoTM are supported to configure the selection of the transmission mode for closed loop single user downlink MIMO modes configurations:  - activatedMimoTM == "TM4": all UEs select TM4  - activatedMimoTM == "TM9": all TM9 capable UEs select TM9; all other legacy Rel.8,9 UEs select TM4  - activatedMimoTM == "TM9_maxLayer": UEs supporting up to 4 spatial multiplexing layers based on TM9 and maximum two layers based on TM4 select transmission mode 9. All other UEs select TM4.    Notes:  (1) The parameter 'activatedMimoTM' is configurable for several Closed Loop Mimo modes (dlMimoMode: "Closed Loop MIMO (4x4) OR 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)'" and "Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)" Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)") to control the selection of the transmission mode.  (2) The setting activatedMimoTM == "TM9_maxLayer" is only configurable if dlMimoMode=="Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)".  (3) This parameter is ignored if act2CrsIn4Tx of the LNCEL_TDD instance is equal to 'true'.

Parameter name: Add number DRB radioReasHo
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active DRBs in the cell accessing the cell via HO with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActDrb.  Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell.    The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions)::  - for 10 MHz bandwidth 0..1650 (recommended: 60)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..2400 (recommended: 90)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..1890 (recommended: 60)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions)::  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..900 (recommended: 30)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..1800 (recommended: 60)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..3600 (recommended: 90)  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..576 (recommended: 30)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..1200 (recommended: 45)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and Massive MIMO activation and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS.    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS    The range of this parameter may be adapted considering baseband pooling configuration, including the value of actBbPooling and the number of cells allocated to a baseband pool.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Add number DRB timeCriticalHo
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active DRBs in the cell accessing the cell via HO with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActDrb.  Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell.    The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions):  - for 10 MHz bandwidth 0..1650 (recommended: 90)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..2400 (recommended: 135)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..1890 (recommended: 90)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions):  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..900 (recommended: 45)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..1800 (recommended: 90)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..3600 (recommended: 135)  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..576 (recommended: 30)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..1200 (recommended: 60)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and Massive MIMO activation and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS.    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS.    The range of this parameter may be adapted considering baseband pooling configuration, including the value of actBbPooling and the number of cells allocated to a baseband pool.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Add number QCI1 DRB for radioReasHo
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active GBRs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumQci1Drb.  Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell.    The maximum additional margin depends on the Uplink-downlink configuration of the cell. The following values are allowed:  (1) tddFrameConf is set to '1'(sa1)  Max value: 300 for 10 MHz and 400 for 15 MHz and 20 MHz  Default value: 10 for 10 MHz, 16 for (15 MHz or 20 MHz)    (2) tddFrameConf is set to '2'(sa2)  Max value: 150 for 10 MHz and 250 for 15 MHz and 20 MHz  Default value: 10 for 10 MHz, 12 for (15 MHz or 20 MHz)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum additional margin depends on the Uplink-downlink configuration of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 or conf.1 or conf.2, 0..80 (recommended: 16)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..150 (recommended: 16)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..250 (recommended: 16)  - for 10 MHz and 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..140 (recommended: 16)  the range of this parameter may be adapted considering baseband pooling configuration, including the value of actBbPooling    For any variant of AirScale ABIC/ABIN/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF with at least one LTE cell configured, this parameter is not relevant as those AirScale deployments operate always with BB pooling activated and feature bundle LTE534, LTE496, LTE497 activated (actEnhAcAndGbrServices =true).

Parameter name: Add number QCI1 DRB for timeCriticalHo
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active GBRs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumQci1Drb.  Hand over traffic shall have some preference against new upcoming traffic in the cell.    The maximum additional margin depends on the Uplink-downlink configuration of the cell. The following values are allowed:  (1) tddFrameConf is set to '1'(sa1)  Max value: 300 for 10 MHz and 400 for 15 MHz and 20 MHz  Default value: 10 for 10 MHz, 16 for (15 MHz or 20 MHz)    (2) tddFrameConf is set to '2'(sa2)  Max value: 150 for 10 MHz and 250 for 15 MHz and 20 MHz  Default value: 10 for 10 MHz, 12 for (15 MHz or 20 MHz)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum additional margin depends on the Uplink-downlink configuration of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 or conf.1 or conf.2, 0..80 (recommended: 16)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..150 (recommended: 16)  - for 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..200 (recommended: 16)  - for 10 MHz and 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..140 (recommended: 16)  - for 15 MHz or 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..250 (recommended: 16)    For any variant of AirScale ABIC/ABIN/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF with at least one LTE cell configured, this parameter is not relevant as those AirScale deployments operate always with BB pooling and feature bundle LTE534, LTE496, LTE497 activated (actEnhAcAndGbrServices = true).    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC: Massive MIMO activation is always enabled.

Parameter name: RIP alarming configuration - Alarm threshold crossing time
Description: Parameter alarmThresholdCrossingTime defines when a RIP alarm will be raised or cleared. When the RIP value is above/below the alarm threshold for the alarm threshold crossing time (e.g. 5 minutes) then the RIP alarm will be raised/cleared.  This parameter is used for RIP alarms for Uplink Subframe and Special Subframe (applicable for TDD cell only).

Parameter name: RIP alarming configuration - Alarm threshold for special subframe
Description: Parameter alarmThresholdSpecialSF defines the threshold for the RIP alarming for special subframe. If the measured RIP value is above/below the threshold for at least Alarm Threshold Crossing Time (e.g. 5 minutes) an alarm with severity major is raised/cleared.

Parameter name: RIP alarming configuration - Alarm threshold for UL subframe
Description: Parameter alarmThresholdULSF defines the threshold for the RIP alarming for UL subframe. If the measured RIP value is above/below the threshold for at least Alarm Threshold Crossing Time (e.g. 5 minutes) an alarm with severity major is raised/cleared.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - AMR WB/NB voice bitrate threshold
Description: Voice call determination threshold for AMR WB as well as AMR NB.  For a QCI-1 bearer, if GBR requirement from S1AP is higher than amrVoiceBRThreshold, it is assumed this QCI-1 bearer carries a AMR WB voice call, else it is assumed this QCI-1 bearer carries a AMR NB voice call.    A correct GBR requirement from S1AP is the precondition for correct SPS TBS selection.  This parameter setting should refer to core network setting according to 3GPP TS26.114.

Parameter name: CQI Threshold Downgrade for TM8
Description: CQI threshold for switching from dual codeword to single codeword in case of TM8  If the current CQI is less than or equal to bfCqiThDown, OR current rank is less than or equal to bfRankThDown, then switching from dual codeword to single codeword for TM8.

Parameter name: CQI Threshold Upgrade for TM8
Description: CQI threshold for switching from single codeword to dual codeword in case of TM8  If the current CQI is bigger than bfCqiThUp, AND current rank is bigger than bfRankThUp, then switching from single codeword to dual codeword for TM8.

Parameter name: mMIMO parameter set - The threshold of beamforming gain for TDD mMIMO
Description: This parameter defines the threshold of beamforming gain (linear scale) for TDD mMIMO. The beamforming weight should not be applied when the beamforming gain is low than the threshold.

Parameter name: Rank Threshold Downgrade for TM8
Description: Rank threshold for switching from dual codeword to single codeword in case of TM8.  If the current CQI is less than or equal to bfCqiThDown, or current rank is less than or equal to bfRankThDown, then switching from dual codeword to single codeword for TM8.

Parameter name: Rank Threshold Upgrade for TM8
Description: Rank threshold for switching from single codeword to dual codeword in case of TM8  If the current CQI is bigger than bfCqiThUp, AND current rank is bigger than bfRankThUp, then switching from single codeword to dual codeword for TM8.

Parameter name: The aging coefficient to calculate beamforming weight
Description: This parameter defines the aging coefficient to calculate beamforming weight.

Parameter name: Super cell parameter set - UL SINR offset for candidate sub-cell
Description: Defines the maximum UL SINR offset to serving for candidate sub-cell selection.  If the SINR gap between serving sub-cell and a second sub-cell is less than this offset the second sub-cell can be selected as candidate sub-cell.

Parameter name: Channel bandwidth TDD
Description: Channel Bandwidth defines the Downlink and Uplink bandwidth for the eNode-B transmission in a cell, and also defines the number of available Physical Resource Blocks which is transmitted in the MIB. The Channel Bandwidth mapping to Number of Physical Resource Blocks is: 1.4 MHz = 6 PRB; 3.0 MHz = 15 PRB; 5.0 MHz = 25 PRB; 10.0 MHz = 50 PRB; 15.0 MHz = 75 PRB; 20.0 MHz = 100 PRB.    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.    For AirScale: 5 MHz bandwidth is supported for the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF/ABIN.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Timer for aperiodic CQI / PMI feedback requesting
Description: This parameter defines a timer in TTIs for polling aperiodic CQI / RI / PMI feedback. The scheduler handles the aperiodic feedback requesting based on this timer.

Parameter name: Timer for aperiodic CQI / PMI feedback requesting for UE supporting skippable UL grant
Description: This parameter defines a timer in TTIs for polling aperiodic CQI / RI / PMI feedback. The scheduler handles the aperiodic feedback requesting based on this timer for Rel. 14 UEs configured for "skippable" UL grants.  This parameter is only used if LNBTS.actReduceAcqiReqTxSkip = 'true' of corresponding LNBTS.

Parameter name: R10 periodicity factor
Description: If the periodicity of CQI/PMI reporting is N (in subframes),the wideband first precoding matrix indicator report has period  cqiPerSbPeriodFactor * N.

Parameter name: CSBIA Left Neighbor Cell
Description: Left Neighbor's LNCEL instance ID values as references to the Left Neighbor cell (LNCEL) of one cell

Parameter name: CSBIA Right Neighbor Cell
Description: Right Neighbor's LNCEL instance ID values as references to the Right Neighbor cell (LNCEL) of one cell

Parameter name: CSI reporting submode
Description: If a UE configured with TM9 and with 8 CSI-RS ports and configured periodic CSI reporting mode 1-1, mode 1-1 is configured to be either "submode1" or "submode2".

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information - CSI-RS power offset
Description: Defines the ratio of PDSCH EPRE to CSI-RS EPRE

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information - CSI-RS resource configuration
Description: Defines the cell specific CSI-RS configuration for normal cyclic prefix

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information - CSI-RS subframe configuration
Description: Defines the cell specific CSI-RS subframe configuration  0-4: 5ms period  5-14: 10ms period  15-34: 20ms period  35-74: 40ms period  75-154: 80ms period    Note:  when CSI-RS periodicity is 5ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf(subframes)  when CSI-RS periodicity is 10ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 5(subframes)  when CSI-RS periodicity is 20ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 15(subframes)  when CSI-RS periodicity is 40ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 35(subframes)  when CSI-RS periodicity is 80ms, CSI-RS subframe offset is csiRsSubfrConf minus 75(subframes).

Parameter name: mMIMO parameter set - The timer to delay using service beamforming weight
Description: This parameter defines the timer to delay using service beamforming weight (millisecond) calculated from SRS in order to avoid performance loss.

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Scaling factor of adaptive number of layers for DL MU-MIMO
Description: This parameter specifies the scaling factor of the maximum number of layers for downlink MU-MIMO in TDD Massive MIMO

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Co-efficient of Resource utilization ratio
Description: This parameter specifies the co-efficient of resource utilization ratio to tune the maximum number of layers for downlink MU-MIMO in TDD Massive MIMO

Parameter name: mMIMO parameter set - The coefficient for restriction of downlink beamforming gain for TDD mMIMO
Description: This parameter defines the coefficient for restriction of downlink beamforming gain for TDD mMIMO is in order to balance between performance and robustness. It is configured together with dlMaxBfGain. The beamforming gain of UE beam shall be restricted via the maximum allowed value and coefficient because it is evaluated too optimistic in some scenario.

Parameter name: Power dynamic adjust range for DL power allocation
Description: Transmission power can be adjusted dynamically in DL power allocation.  When dlDynPcRange is set to 0:OFF, no impact to original flow. When dlDynPcRange is not set to 0:OFF, transmission power for DL power allocation can be adjusted dynamically by respective set value.

Parameter name: Spatial Mode for Downlink Interference
Description: This parameter specifies the spatial mode for the downlink interference.    If dlMimoMode is set to 'SingleTX' then one element of the structure must be present with dlInterferenceSpatialMode 'SingleTx'.  If dlMimoMode is set to 'TXDiv', '4-way TXDiv', 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' , 'Closed Loop Mimo', 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)' then one element of the structure must be present with dlInterferenceSpatialMode 'TXDiv'.  If dlMimoMode is set to 'Single Stream Beamforming' or 'Dual Stream Beamforming' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)' then both elements of the structure must be present, one with dlInterferenceSpatialMode 'TXDiv' and the other with dlInterferenceSpatialMode 'Single Stream Beamforming'.

Parameter name: Transmission Power Offset for Downlink Interference
Description: This parameter defines the interference data power spectrum density offset to flat PSD in beamforming.

Parameter name: Update Period for Downlink Interference
Description: This parameter specifies the update period for the downlink interference weights.

Parameter name: mMIMO parameter set - The maximum allowed value of downlink beamforming gain for TDD mMIMO
Description: The maximum allowed value of downlink beamforming gain for TDD mMIMO is in order to balance between performance and robustness. It is configured together with dlBfGainCoeff. The beamforming gain of UE beam shall be restricted via the maximum allowed value and coefficient because it is evaluated too optimistic in some scenarios.

Parameter name: The maximum delta CQI for mode control of downlink beamforming
The maximum multiplexing layers per MU RBG for downlink MU-MIMO of TDD mMIMO
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of layers per MU RBG which are paired into downlink MU-MIMO of TDD mMIMO.  The maximum number of layers depends on HW and the antenna array mode.

Parameter name: Downlink MIMO mode
Description: Cell specific downlink transmission/mimo mode  The used DL mimo mode for each physical channel is the following:    SingleTx: Single Stream Downlink: All downlink physical channels are transmitted using this mode;    2-way TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for two antennas using Transmission Mode 2.    4-way TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for four antennas using Transmission Mode 2.    Dynamic Open Loop MIMO (2x): Dynamic Open Loop MIMO: SRB1 (DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Dual Stream MIMO with spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity;    Closed Loop MIMO (4x2): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO4x2: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity    Closed Loop MIMO (4x4): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO4x4: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity    Closed Loop MIMO (8x2): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO8x2: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity    Closed Loop MIMO (8x4): Fast Adaptive Closed Loop MIMO8x4: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using either Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity or Single or Dual Stream MIMO with Closed Loop spatial multiplexing depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity    Single Stream Beamforming: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using Single Stream Beamforming depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity    Dual Stream Beamforming: SRB1(DCCH) and RBs(DTCH) on PDSCH are transmitted using Dual Stream Beamforming depending on radio conditions and UE category; SRB0(CCCH), BCCH and PCCH on PDSCH and all other physical channels are transmitted using Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity.
Range and step: SingleTX (0), TXDiv (10), 4-way TXDiv (11), Dynamic Open Loop MIMO (30), Closed Loop Mimo (40), Closed Loop MIMO (4x2) (41), Closed Loop MIMO (8x2) (42), Closed Loop MIMO (4x4) (43), Closed Loop MIMO (8x4) (44), Single Stream Beamforming (50), Dual Stream Beamforming (60)

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - MU-MIMO beam interference cancellation method selection in horizontal direction for downlink TDD mMIMO
Description: This parameter defines MU-MIMO beam interference cancellation method selection in horizontal direction for downlink TDD mMIMO.

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - MU-MIMO beam interference cancellation method selection in vertical direction for downlink TDD mMIMO
Description: MU-MIMO beam interference cancellation method selection in vertical direction for downlink TDD mMIMO.

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Downlink MU-MIMO correlation threshold
Description: The correlation threshold below which two TM8 and/or TM9 MU-MIMO candidate can be paired.  This parameter is used for both 8T8R and 64T64R DL MU MIMO.

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Downlink MU-MIMO CQI threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the CQI threshold above which the TM7, TM8 or TM9 UE can be selected as DL MU-MIMO candidate. This parameter is commonly used for both 8T8R and massive MIMO DL MU MIMO.  In 8T8R DL MU MIMO, this parameter indicates the CQI threshold above which the TM8 or TM9 UE can be selected as DL MU-MIMO candidate, This DL MU-MIMO candidate must be rank 1 UE.  In Massive MIMO DL MU MIMO, this parameter indicates the CQI threshold above which the TM7 or TM8 UE can be selected as DL MU-MIMO candidate.

Parameter name: CQI offset decrease for HARQ NACK/DTX response for DL OLQC with 16QAM or 64QAM
Description: The parameter defines the decrease in CQI offset for a HARQ NACK/DTX response for downlink transmission with 16QAM/64QAM in DL OLQC  When DL dynamic target BLER algorithm is applied, this parameter is used for the decrease in CQI offset for a HARQ NACK/DTX response in OLQC for downlink transmission with 16QAM/64QAM, CQIstepup can be calculated based on this parameter and the selected target BLER with 16QAM/64QAM.

Parameter name: CQI offset decrease for HARQ NACK/DTX response for DL OLQC with QPSK
Description: The parameter defines the decrease in CQI offset for a HARQ NACK/DTX response for downlink transmission with QPSK in DL OLQC  When DL dynamic target BLER algorithm is applied, this parameter is used for the decrease in CQI offset for a HARQ NACK/DTX response in OLQC for downlink transmission with QPSK, CQIstepup can be calculated based on this parameter and the selected target BLER with QPSK.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Maximum delay timer for DL PAS
Description: The parameter specifies the maximum delay timer for PAS, it is used to improve TCP performance while the cell load is high.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Aggregation TTI threshold for DL SPA
Description: The parameter specifies the number of TTI threshold as a criterion for DL SPA(small packet aggregation). When the remaining TTIs for the downlink data in buffer of the scheduling UE not exceed this threshold, the SPA will be applied to the UE for improving the IP scheduling throughput and spectrum efficiency.    Note: If dlAggrTtiThd is set to '0', the function of SPA is deactivated.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Average number of UEs window for DL WBS
Description: The parameter specifies the measurement window size to calculate the average number of active UEs for DL WBS.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Low load number of UE threshold for DL WBS
Description: The parameter specifies the number of UE threshold as a criterion of low load for WBS (workload based scheduling) in downlink. When the average number of active UEs not exceed this threshold, the WBS will be applied to improve the QoE for the scheduled UEs. The average number of active UEs is calculated according to number of active UEs with downlink data in buffer per TTI and the measurement window size which defined by dlAvgNumUeWin.    Note: If dlLowLoadNumUeThd is set to '0', the function of WBS is deactivated.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Maximum delay TTIs for DL SPA
Description: The parameter specifies the maximum delay TTIs for DL SPA(small packet aggregation). When the SPA function is applied to a UE, the UE will be de-prioritized scheduling for at most TTIs which defined by this parameter.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Minimum DL UEs per TTI
Description: The parameter specifies the minimum number of scheduling UE per TTI in downlink for dynamic optimizing the number of UE per TTI which can increase the PRB resource per UE.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Margin factor of concurrent scheduled UEs for DL PA
Description: The parameter specifies the margin factor of the number of concurrent scheduled UE which shall be calculated by dlPasBurstNumMargin* (the num of UE per TTI) in TD metric processing for PAS.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Scaling factor of scheduling priority for DL PA  in high load
Description: The parameter specifies the scaling factor of scheduling priority to tune the degree of PAS(packet aggregation scheduling) when the cell load is high.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - QoE and cell throughput balance for downlink
Description: The parameter specifies selecting a balance between QoE and cell throughput in a cell after LNCEL_TDD-actDlQoeEnhance is set to 'true'. When it is set to '0', the improvement of QoE for scheduled UEs has priority over cell throughput. When it is set to '1', the improvement of cell throughput has priority over QoE for scheduled UEs.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - TTIs threshold for DL PTP
Description: The parameter specifies the TTIs threshold which as a criterion. When the number of remaining TTI not exceed it, the PTP (prioritized tail packet) scheduling in downlink to improve the user throughput via decreasing the transmission time.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Scaling factor of DL UEs per TTI
Description: The parameter specifies the scaling factor of number of scheduling TD UE in downlink for dynamic optimizing the number of UE per TTI which can increase the PRB resource per UE.

Parameter name: Downlink QoE Based Enhancement parameter set - Work load factor for DL WBS
Description: The parameter specifies the scaling factor of work load in downlink, it is used to calculate WBS(workload based scheduling) weight for UEs to adjust scheduling priority when the cell load is low. Higher value means more dominant work load impact.

Parameter name: Downlink reference signals transmission power boost
Description: Transmission power of the downlink reference signals in a cell is boosted (positive value) respectively deboosted (negative value) compared to PDSCH

Parameter name: Downlink sector beamforming weight profile name
Description: This parameter identifies the name of the downlink sector beamforming weight profile.  There are two types of the downlink sector beamforming weight profiles.  One is "predefined profile" and another is "customized profile".  "predefined profile" means the downlink sector beamforming weights shall be set as the predefined values per the specific antenna type(according to antenna spec).  "customized profile" means the operator can set the downlink sector beamforming weights via O&M interface.  Each profile name maps to the downlink sector beamforming weight of the specific antenna type(predefined profile) or the customized sector beamforming weight profile.

Parameter name: Downlink sector beamforming mode
Description: Identifies the downlink sector beamforming mode.

Parameter name: Downlink SRB MIMO mode
Description: This parameter determines the MIMO mode to be used for Downlink SRB traffic

Parameter name: Downlink user Tput threshold with load bal.
Description: Average user throughput threshold for selecting serving radio link qualification threshold with inter-frequency load balancing based trigger

Parameter name: MIMO power compensation
Description: Sets the compensation in 'TXDiv', '4-way TXDiv', 2x2 MIMO SM, 4x2 MIMO SM , 4x4 MIMO SM, 8x4 MIMO SM case into the DL power control.  Compensation of MIMO Coverage effects for MIMO Spatial Multiplexing and MIMO Diversity  The parameter determines the power compensation factor for antenna-specific maximum power in case of a downlink transmission using at least two TX antennas. This means that every single subcarrier power determined for multiple TX antenna transmission is reduced by this factor. The parameter does not apply in case of a single TX (TM1) transmission, and thus neither affects the power of cell-specific reference signal transmission. Note that only the limited set of dlpcMimoComp values (-3dB, 0dB, 1.77dB, 3dB, 4.77dB, 6dB) can be communicated to the UE due to p-a signaling restrictions and the extended range has been determined only for finetuning purposes. Please be informed that Nokia does not guarantee a successful DL transmission using amplitude dependent modulations, especially 64QAM, if other values than the values presented in the limited set (-3dB, 0dB, 1.77dB, 3dB, 4.77dB, 6dB) are used.  Please note, that if the Cell-Specific Reference Symbol Power Boost is activated by setting the dlRsBoost parameter, only the values 0dB and 3dB are allowed for dlpcMimoComp.

Parameter name: Distributed virtual resource block gap value
Description: Parameter defines the gap value used in the interleaving function which maps VRBs to PRBs when using Distributed VRB mapping.

Parameter name: Downlink scheduler type
Description: Parameter to choose between different available scheduler types

Parameter name: The reference SINR for eULLA ATB's calculation
Description: This parameter specifies the reference SINR for eULLA ATB's calculation, it is only for TDD massive MIMO.

Parameter name: EARFCN for both downlink and uplink (TDD)
Description: E-UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number.  Supported bands and related EARFCNs are the following:  Band 34 (2010-2024.9 MHz): 36200-36349  Band 38 (2570-2619.9 MHz): 37750-38249  Band 39 (1880-1919.9 MHz): 38250-38649  Band 40 (2300-2399.9 MHz): 38650-39649  Band 41 (2496-2689.9 MHz): 39650-41589  Band 42 (3400-3599.9 MHz): 41590-43589  Band 43 (3600-3799.9 MHz): 43590-45589  Band 48 (3550-3699.9 MHz): 55240-56739  Band 50 (1432-1517 MHz): 58240-59089  Band 52 (3300-3399.9 MHz): 59140-60139    The allowed EARFCN value depends on the radio module capability.    Note that for intra-band contiguous CA, the spacing between the central frequencies of the two carriers must be equal or greater than 183 EARFCN (18.3 MHz) for 20 MHz +20 MHz bandwidth combination, and 159 EARFCN (15.9 MHz) for 20 MHz + 15 MHz bandwidth combination, and 138 EARFCN (13.8 MHz) for 20 MHz + 10 MHz bandwidth combination.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: The RI specific eNB identification derived from ECI.
Description: This parameter indicates the RI specific eNB identification which is derived from the E-UTRAN Cell Identifier (ECI) of own cell according to operator's specific mapping rule.

Parameter name: mMIMO parameter set - Scaling factor of extended delay timer
Description: The parameter specifies the scaling factor of extended timer to delay to use beamforming weight in TDD Massive MIMO

Parameter name: Filter coefficient for CSFB PCCPCH-RSCP
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for UTRA-WCDMA CSFB Cpich-RSCP  Specifies the filtering coefficient used for PCCPCH-RSCP within the measurement quantity configuration of UTRA TD-SCDMA.

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for PCCPCH-RSCP
Description: Specifies the filtering coefficient used for UTRA TD-SCDMA PCCPCH-RSCP  Specifies the filtering coefficient used for PCCPCH-RSCP within the measurement quantity configuration of UTRA TD-SCDMA

Parameter name: Four layer MIMO average spectral efficiency
Description: The four layer MIMO average spectral efficiency is used by the throughput check during SCell addition as follows.  If the throughput metric after the SCell addition is greater than the throughput metric before the SCell addition then this SCell addition is admitted. Otherwise, this SCell addition is rejected. The throughput metric is the sum of xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff*bandwidth of the UE's serving cells. Where xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to twoLayerMimoAvSpectralEff if the UE is configured with two layer MIMO on a given serving cell respectively xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to fourLayerMimoAvSpectralEff if the UE is configured with four layer MIMO on a given serving cell.    A reasonable value of the parameter can be derived from the existing KPI LTE_5747a 'DL Spectral efficiency' as follows. The KPI shall be collected in conditions where all UEs are four layer MIMO capable in this cell in order not to underestimate the average value (with dlMimoMode set to 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)').    The throughput check is not used by setting the parameter value to '0.5' i.e. any SCell addition will be always admitted by the check if twoLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to fourLayerMimoAvSpectralEff in all involved cells.

Parameter name: Hopping bandwidth of PUSCH
Description: This is the number of PRBs used for PUSCH hopping.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold th2 TD-SCDMA for RSRP
Description: Related Hysteresis of Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of TD-SCDMA measurements  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Massive MIMO secondary profile name
Description: This parameter specifies mMIMO secondary profile name of the assigned MMIMOCPR profile or Vendor Specific profile.    Note: When the functionality of adaptive sector beamforming(BF) weight is activated, the secondary sector beamforming profile will be applied for high load if this parameter is configured.

Parameter name: Massive MIMO Antenna Array Mode
Description: (1)This parameter indicates the mMIMO antenna array mode on 64 pipes or 32 pipes mMIMO MAA.    (2)For CPRI radio, if the parameter mMimoAntArrayMode is set to "0:Full 64TRX Array (4x8x2)", the 64 TRX antennas are connected and configured as:  - 64 LCELL/CHANNELGROUP/CHANNEL instances with direction value set to 'RX'  - 64 LCELL/CHANNELGROUP/CHANNEL instances with direction value set to 'TX'    (3)For CPRI radio, if the parameter mMimoAntArrayMode is set to "1:Left 32TRX Array (4x4x2)", or "2:Right 32TRX Array (4x4x2)", or "3:Top 32TRX Array (2x8x2)", or "4:Bottom 32TRX Array (2x8x2)" or "5:Full 32TRX Array (2x8x2)", the 32 TRX antennas are connected and configured as:  - 32 LCELL/CHANNELGROUP/CHANNEL instances with direction value set to 'RX'  - 32 LCELL/CHANNELGROUP/CHANNEL instances with direction value set to 'TX'    (4)For eCPRI radio, if the parameter mMimoAntArrayMode is set to "0:Full 64TRX Array (4x8x2)", the 64 TRX antennas are connected and configured as:  - 1 LCELL/CHANNELGROUP/CHANNEL instances with direction value set to 'RX'  - 1 LCELL/CHANNELGROUP/CHANNEL instances with direction value set to 'TX'    (5)For eCPRI radio, if the parameter mMimoAntArrayMode is set to "5:Full 32TRX Array (2x8x2)", the 32 TRX antennas are connected and configured as:  - 1 LCELL/CHANNELGROUP/CHANNEL instances with direction value set to 'RX'  - 1 LCELL/CHANNELGROUP/CHANNEL instances with direction value set to 'TX'
Range and step: Full 64TRX Array (4x8x2) (0), Left 32TRX Array (4x4x2) (1), Right 32TRX Array (4x4x2) (2), Top 32TRX Array (2x8x2) (3), Bottom 32TRX Array (2x8x2) (4), Full 32TRX Array (2x8x2) (5)

Parameter name: mMIMO parameter set - Massive MIMO beamforming update rate
Description: This parameter specifies the UE beamforming weight update rate which is depended on the number of the RRC connected UE per cell, it is only for TDD massive MIMO. Based on the number of the RRC connected UE per cell, the UE beamforming weight update period could be adjusted via this parameter.

Parameter name: Massive MIMO GoB(Grid of beam) TD metric factor for downlink
Description: As a parameter for the functionality of GoB based TD scheduling optimization that only for downlink MU-MIMO of TDD mMIMO, it specifies the scaling factor for the TD scheduling metric of the best selected UEs. It is used to adjust the multi-user pairing efficiency.    Note:  -If mMimoGoBTdMetricFactorDl is set to '1', the functionality of GoB based TD scheduling optimization is deactivated

Parameter name: massive MIMO virtual resource load setting - The maximum virtual PDCCH load capacity in mMIMO cell
Description: This parameter defines the maximum virtual PDCCH load capacity in mMIMO cell. The long term averaging will be used to allow the short term burst.

Parameter name: massive MIMO virtual resource load setting - The maximum virtual PRB load capacity in mMIMO cell
Description: This parameter defines the maximum virtual PRB load capacity in mMIMO cell. The long term averaging will be used to allow the short term burst.

Parameter name: massive MIMO virtual resource load setting - The minimum virtual PDCCH load capacity in mMIMO cell
Description: This parameter defines the minimum virtual PDCCH load capacity in mMIMO cell. The long term averaging will be used to allow the short term burst.

Parameter name: massive MIMO virtual resource load setting - The minimum virtual PRB load capacity in mMIMO cell
Description: This parameter defines the minimum virtual PRB load capacity in mMIMO cell. The long term averaging will be used to allow the short term burst.

Parameter name: Massive MIMO profile name
Description: This parameter specifies profile name of the assigned MMIMOCPR profile or Vendor Specific profile.    The parameter 'mMimoSectorBFProfName' setting's electrical tilt and 'mMimoVerticalGobFirst' has relationship if the vendor specific sector beamforming weight profile is used, reference setting is mMimoVerticalGobFirst = mMimoSectorBFProfName's Electrical Tilt - 7 degree.  For instance, if mMimoSectorBFProfName = '3:Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(3)' then  Vertical GoB OAM parameters Internal Relative value  Vertical GoB (-4, 11) First vertical GoB: -4 Vertical Relative GoB (0, 15)
Range and step: Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(0) (0), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(1) (1), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(2) (2), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(3) (3), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(4) (4), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(5) (5), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(6) (6), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(7) (7), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(8) (8), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(-1) (9), Macro-0 Electrical Tilt-(-2) (10), High Building-0 (20), customized profile 1 (101), customized profile 2 (102), customized profile 3 (103), customized profile 4 (104), customized profile 5 (105), customized profile 6 (106), customized profile 7 (107), customized profile 8 (108), customized profile 9 (109), customized profile 10 (110), customized profile 11 (111), customized profile 12 (112), customized profile 13 (113), customized profile 14 (114), customized profile 15 (115), customized profile 16 (116), customized profile 17 (117), customized profile 18 (118), customized profile 19 (119), customized profile 20 (120)

Parameter name: massive MIMO virtual resource load setting - virtual PRB adjust factor for a mMIMO cell
Description: This parameter defines virtual PRB adjust factor for a mMIMO cell. The number of available virtual PRB equals to mMimoMaxVirtualPrbCapacity *(The number of available PRBs for GBR and nonGBR)* mMimoVirtualResAdjustFactor or mMimoMaxVirtualPrbCapacity * (The number of available PRBs for GBR and nonGBR)/mMimoVirtualResAdjustFactor.

Parameter name: Maximum number of OFDM symbols for PDCCH
Description: The parameter defines how many OFDM symbols can be used for PDCCH channel transmission. eNB selects based on usage the actual value for each TTI, which and value is signaled to the UEs in PCFICH.

Parameter name: Max. number of 2CC CA UEs with PUCCH format 3
Description: Threshold to limit the maximum number of UEs configured with 2CC DL CA in a TDD PCell (P-LNCEL), which are allowed to be allocated with PUCCH format 3.    UEs configured with 2CC DL CA include the TDD-TDD 2CC CA UEs and TDD-FDD 2CC CA UEs, and the TDD UL/DL configuration of the PCell can be either TDD UL/DL frame configuration 1 or TDD UL/DL frame configuration 2.

Parameter name: Max number act DRB
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of established DRBs in the cell.    The maximum number of established DRBs depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions)::  - for 10 MHz bandwidth 0..1650 (recommended: 600)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..2400 (recommended: 900)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..1890 (recommended: 900)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum number of established DRBs depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions)::  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..900 (recommended: 300)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..1800 (recommended: 600)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..3600 (recommended: 900)  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..576 (recommended: 192)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..1200 (recommended: 450)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC:  The maximum number of established DRBs depends on the bandwidth of the cell and Massive MIMO activation and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF:  The maximum number of established DRBs depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS.    The range of this parameter may be adapted considering baseband pooling configuration, including the value of actBbPooling and the number of cells allocated to a baseband pool.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Maximum number of active UEs
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell with established DRB.  The maximum number of UEs in the cell with established DRB.    The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions)::  - for 10 MHz bandwidth 0..550 (recommended: 200)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..800 (recommended: 300)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..630 (recommended: 200)    The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell and the configuration of suppExtCqiPeriod in the BTS. The following lists the maximal allowed values (not all conditions)::  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..300 in AirScale (recommended: 100)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..600 in the LNCEL which is linked to AirScale ABIA/ABIAL (recommended: 200)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..1200 in the LNCEL which is linked to AirScale ABIA/ABIAL (recommended: 300)  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..192 in the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA(recommended: 64)  - for 10 MHz,15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..400 in the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA(recommended: 150)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC maxNumActUE value for the cells depends on cell BW, Massive MIMO activation and also on pool limits.    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN/ABIO/ASOE/ASOF maxNumActUE value for the cells depends on cell BW and pool limits.    In case baseband pooling is activated the value of these parameters may be internally adapted by the system based on the number of cells allocated to a baseband pool.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Max number carrier aggr configured UEs
Description: Threshold to limit the maximum number of carrier aggregation configured UEs in a PCell (P-LNCEL);  UEs may have 1 PCell (P-LNCEL) and 1 or several SCell(s) (S-LNCEL).  Carrier aggregated UEs with 1 or more SCell need more resources than nonCA Ues (PUCCH and MAC PS);  Therefore limiting the amount of CA-UEs is necessary.    In case the threshold is modified online and the value is decreased, existing CA-UEs may stay in the cell, but the new value applies to new admission checks only.

Parameter name: Max number carrier aggr configured UEs 3 carriers
Description: Threshold to limit the maximum number of carrier aggregation configured UEs in a PCell (P-LNCEL); 3c (3 carriers) indicates that these UEs have 3 or more serving cells, i.e., 1 PCell (P-LNCEL) and up to 4 SCells (S-LNCEL).  Carrier aggregated UEs with 2 or more SCells need a higher amount of resources (PUCCH) compared with single carrier UEs as long as UL signaling is done only via PCell. That's why the information 3c is relevant.    In case the threshold is modified online and the value is decreased, existing CA-UEs may stay in the cell, but the new value applies to new admission checks only.

Parameter name: Max number carrier aggr configured UEs with PUCCH format 1bCS and CPA
Description: The parameter specifies the maximum number of 2CC CA UEs that are allowed to be configured with PUCCH format 1b with channel selection and are managed by CPA for PUCCH format 1b with channel selection. In TDD, only TDD-FDD 2CC CA UEs and inter-site 2CC CA UEs are managed by CPA for PUCCH format 1b with channel selection, TDD cell acts as PCell in both cases. Intra-eNB or intra-site TDD-TDD 2CC CA UEs are managed by semi-static PUCCH allocation algorithm.

Parameter name: Max number Carrier Aggr configured UEs double carrier
Description: Threshold to limit the maximum number of carrier aggregation configured UEs in a PCell (P-LNCEL); Dc (Double carrier) indicates that these UEs have 1 PCell (P-LNCEL) and only 1 SCell (S-LNCEL).  Carrier aggregated UEs with 1 SCell need double amount of UL resources compared with single carrier UEs as long as UL signalling is done only via PCell. That's why the information Dc is relevant.    In case the threshold is modified online and the value is decreased, existing CA-UEs may stay in the cell, but the new value applies to new admission checks only.

Parameter name: Max number QCI1 DRBs (GBRs)
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of established QCI1-GBR-DRBs in the cell    The parameter is only relevant if "actEnhAcAndGbrServices" is set to 'false' and ignored otherwise.  QCI1-DRBs are additional data radio bearers in the cell and are also checked against the threshold maxNumActDrb.    The maximum additional margin depends on the Uplink-downlink configuration of the cell. The following values are allowed:  (1) tddFrameConf is set to '1'(sa1)  Max value: 300 for 10 MHz and 400 for 15 MHz or 20 MHz  Default value: 24 for 10 MHz, 36 for (15 MHz or 20 MHz), TDD conf.1.    (2) tddFrameConf is set to '2'(sa2)  Max value: 150 for 10 MHz and 250 for 15 MHz or 20 MHz  Default value: 24 for (10 MHz or 15 MHz or 20 MHz), TDD conf.2    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 or conf.1 or conf.2, 0..80 (recommended: 36)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..150 (recommended: 36)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..250 (recommended: 36)  - for 10 MHz and 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 , 0..140 (recommended: 36)  the range of this parameter may be adapted considering baseband pooling configuration, including the value of actBbPooling

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Maximum number of SPS scheduled UEs for UL scheduler
Description: Maximum number of UEs for UL Scheduler in each TTI, including only SPS scheduling UE.  The maximum number of UL SPS UE is the part of maxNumUeUl. The margin between maxNumSPSUeUl and maxNumUeUl is left for dynamic scheduling. Dynamic scheduling is mandatory for UE which cannot be SPS scheduled.    Both maxNumSPSUeUl and ulSpsMaxNumPrb will limit the SPS usage in the cell.    Range depends on chBw and actUlSps value as follows:  chBw = '10 MHz' or '15 MHz' or '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...19    Recommended value for the different bandwidth are:  10 MHz = 6  15 MHz = 8  20 MHz = 8

Parameter name: Maximum amount of users per TTI in DL
Description: Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in each TTI  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...10 (recommended: 10)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...12 (recommended: 12)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...12 (recommended: 12)    if the following features are excluded:  - LTE1558/LTE1830/LTE1562 carrier aggregation  - LTE42/473/585 DRX  - LTE1042 nominal bitrate for non-GBR  - LTE493/541 Beamforming  - LTE568 DL 4x2 SU MIMO  - LTE1543 DL SU MIMO 8x2 with TM9    - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 20)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 20)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in each TTI  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '5 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...8 (recommended: 8)  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 10)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC:  Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in each TTI  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 10)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN/ABIO or ASOE/ASOF:  Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in each TTI  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '5 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...8 (recommended: 8)  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 10)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Maximum amount of users per TTI in DL DwPTS
Description: Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in special sub-frames  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...10 (recommended: 7)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...12 (recommended: 8)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...12 (recommended: 8)    if the following features are excluded:  - LTE1558/LTE1830/LTE1562 carrier aggregation  - LTE42/473/585 DRX  - LTE1042 nominal bitrate for non-GBR  - LTE493/541 Beamforming  - LTE568 DL 4x2 SU MIMO  - LTE1543 DL SU MIMO 8x2 with TM9    - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...12 (recommended: 12)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...12 (recommended: 12)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in special sub-frames  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '5 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...6 (recommended: 6)  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 7)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 8)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 8)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC:  Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in special sub-frames  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 7)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 8)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 8)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN or ABIO or ASOE/ASOF:  Maximum Number of UEs for DL Scheduler in special sub-frames  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '5 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...6 (recommended: 6)  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 7)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 8)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 0...16 (recommended: 8)    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Maximum amount of users per TTI in UL
Description: Maximum Number of UEs for UL Scheduler in each TTI, including dynamic scheduling UE and Semi-Persistent-Scheduling UE.  Range and default value depend on chBw and actUlSps.    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  Maximum Number of UEs for UL Scheduler in each TTI  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '5 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...8 (recommended: 8)  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 10)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)    For all LNCELs which are linked to AirScale ABIC:  Maximum Number of UEs for UL Scheduler in each TTI  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 10)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)    For all LNCELs which are linked to any variant of AirScale ABIN or ABIO or ASOE/ASOF:  Maximum Number of UEs for UL Scheduler in each TTI  Range depends on chBw value as follows:  - chBw = '5 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...8 (recommended: 8)  - chBw = '10 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 10)  - chBw = '15 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)  - chBw = '20 MHz', value range is restricted to 1...20 (recommended: 12)    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Measurement Gap Pattern
Description: This parameter defines the measurement gap pattern scheme for Inter-Frequency Measurements.

Parameter name: CQI averaging constant in beamforming
Description: Averaging filter constant for CQI measurements in beamforming  If dlMimoMode is not 'Single Stream Beamforming' or 'Dual Stream Beamforming' and actTmSwitch is set to 'FALSE', mimoBfCqiAvg is not defined and the default value is used implicitly.

Parameter name: CQI compensation in dual layer beamforming
Description: CQI Compensation applied to Measurements when reported RI=2 in dual layer beamforming  If dlMimoMode is not configured to 'Dual Stream Beamforming', mimoBfCqidlComp does not need to be specified.

Parameter name: RI averaging constant in dual layer beamforming
Description: Averaging filter constant for RI measurements in dual layer beamforming  If dlMimoMode is not 'Dual Stream Beamforming' mimoBfdlRiAvg is not defined and the default value is used implicitly.

Parameter name: MIMO Closed Loop configuration - CQI threshold for fallback to CL MIMO 1 CW mode
Description: CQI Threshold for fallback to closed loop MIMO single codeword transmission (in CQI) in case of activated 'Dynamic MIMO Switch' (i.e. actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'). Not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true'.

Parameter name: MIMO Closed Loop configuration - CQI threshold for activation of CL MIMO 2 CW mode
Description: CQI Threshold for activation of closed loop MIMO dual codeword transmission (in CQI) in case of activated 'Dynamic MIMO Switch' (i.e. actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'). Not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true'.

Parameter name: MIMO Closed Loop configuration - Rank threshold for fallback to CL MIMO 1 CW mode
Description: Rank Threshold for fallback to closed loop MIMO single codeword transmission in case of activated 'Dynamic MIMO Switch' (i.e. actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'). Not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true'.

Parameter name: MIMO Closed Loop configuration - Rank threshold for activation of CL MIMO 2 CW mode
Description: Rank Threshold for activation of closed loop MIMO dual codeword transmission in case of activated 'Dynamic MIMO Switch' (i.e. actFastMimoSwitch is set to 'false'). Not applicable if actFastMimoSwitch set to 'true'.

Parameter name: MIMO Open Loop configuration - CQI threshold for fallback to MIMO diversity
Description: CQI threshold for fallback to Open Loop MIMO diversity (in CQI).

Parameter name: MIMO Open Loop configuration - CQI threshold for activation of OL MIMO SM
Description: CQI threshold for activation of Open Loop MIMO Spatial Multiplexing (in CQI).

Parameter name: MIMO Open Loop configuration - Rank threshold for fallback to MIMO diversity
Description: Rank threshold for fallback to Open Loop MIMO diversity.

Parameter name: MIMO Open Loop configuration - Rank threshold for activation of OL MIMO SM
Description: Rank threshold for activation of Open Loop MIMO Spatial Multiplexing.

Parameter name: mMIMO parameter set - Minimum sector beamforming gain
Description: This parameter specifies the lower limit of sector beamforming gain in liner scaling for TDD mMIMO. It is used to adjust downlink throughput of the cell edge UEs and the interference to neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Consecutive SRS DTX detections number
Description: Number of consecutive SRS DTX detections required for RL Failure  The parameter defines number of consecutive SRS DTX detections causing radio link failure indication. Special value 0 means that the feature is disabled.

Parameter name: Consecutive SRS DTX recovery number
Description: Number of consecutive SRS required for RL recovery  The parameter defines number of consecutive SRS non-DTX detections causing radio link failure recovery indication

Parameter name: CSI-RS configuration information - CSI-RS ports number
Description: Number of CSI-RS ports  In 3GPP 2,4,8 CSI-RS ports are supported. Currently supported values are 8 ports for LTE1543 and LTE2068 and 4 ports for LTE1515 and LTE1987.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Nominal power for SPS UE PUSCH TX power calculation
Description: Cell specific PUSCH nominal power for controlling the mean received SNR for user data in SPS UE uplink power control algorithm.  The parameter defines the cell specific nominal power for the PUSCH. Used for P0_PUSCH calculation in SPS UE uplink power control equation for controlling the mean received SNR for user data during (re)transmission. For all the PUSCH transmissions that are CRC scrambled by the SPS C-RNTI shall use this value.    Note:  If Interference-aware UL power control is disabled, the parameter value shall equal to p0NomPusch.  If Interference-aware UL power control is enabled, the parameter value shall equal to p0NomPuschIAw.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Modulus of weight for horizontal antenna group 0
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup0 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Modulus of weight for horizontal antenna group 1
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup1 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Modulus of weight for horizontal antenna group 2
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup2 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Modulus of weight for horizontal antenna group 3
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup3 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Modulus of weight for horizontal antenna group 4
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup4 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Modulus of weight for horizontal antenna group 5
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup5 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Modulus of weight for horizontal antenna group 6
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup6 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Modulus of weight for horizontal antenna group 7
Description: This parameter specifies the modulus of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup7 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Phase of weight for horizontal antenna group 0
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup0 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Phase of weight for horizontal antenna group 1
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup1 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Phase of weight for horizontal antenna group 2
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup2 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Phase of weight for horizontal antenna group 3
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup3 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Phase of weight for horizontal antenna group 4
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup4 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Phase of weight for horizontal antenna group 5
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup5 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Phase of weight for horizontal antenna group 6
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup6 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam customized profile - Phase of weight for horizontal antenna group 7
Description: This parameter specifies the phase of the PDCCH beam weight which is one complex number for AntennaGroup7 which belongs to the horizontal direction.

Parameter name: PDCCH beam weight profile name
Description: This parameter specifies profile name of the PDCCH beam weight profile. if 'Customized Profile' is chosen, the phase and magnitude is configured by phaseOfAntGrp?0-7?H and modulusOfAntGrp?0-7?H in pdcchBeamWeightProf.  Explanation of the values:  20dB IC: 20dB Interference Cancellation  25dB IC: 25dB Interference Cancellation  30dB IC: 30dB Interference Cancellation  Customized Profile:

Parameter name: PDCCH multiplexing parameter set - The threshold of beamforming gain for PDCCH beam
Description: This parameter defines the threshold of beamforming gain (linear scale) for PDCCH beam. The PDCCH beam should not be chosen when the beamforming gain is low than the threshold.

Parameter name: PDCCH factor for downlink retransmission and PDCCH block
Description: The parameter specifies the factor of PDCCH used for DL retransmission and PDCCH Block transmission per TTI.

Parameter name: PDCCH load level
Description: The PDCCH load level configures the percentage of used PDCCH CCEs on all available PDCCH CCEs.  Used PDCCH CCEs include all CCEs of CSS/USS space and dummy PDCCHs.  This parameter will not restrict normal PDCCH allocation. Only when normal PDCCH load has not reach the level defined by this parameter, dummy PDCCHs will be added.  This parameter is mandatory when actPdcchLoadGen is set to "true".

Parameter name: PSD offset for dummy PDCCH
Description: This parameter defines the dummy PDCCH PSD offset to flat PSD.  Maximum dummy PDCCH PSD is calculated based on flat PSD and this offset.  If there is not enough power remaining for dummy PDCCHs, smaller dummy PDCCH PSD will be used.  This parameter is mandatory when actPdcchLoadGen is set to "true".

Parameter name: PDCCH multiplexing parameter set - Multiplexing prior to PDCCH resource
Description: The parameter activates PDCCH multiplexing prior to fully use PDCCH resource (CCE).

Parameter name: PDCCH multiplexing parameter set - PDCCH beamforming CQI threshold
Description: This parameter indicates the CQI threshold above which the TM7, TM8 or TM9 UE can be selected as PDCCH multiplexing candidate.

Parameter name: PDCCH utility threshold for downlink retransmission
Description: The parameter specifies the PDCCH utility threshold to trigger PDCCH limitation for DL retransmission and PDCCH Block transmission in SF3/8.

Parameter name: SFN cell parameter set - Averaging filter constant for equivalent DL RSRP
Description: Averaging filter constant for equivalent DL RSRP for DL serving subcell determination

Parameter name: SFN cell parameter set - DL RSRP offset threshold
Description: DL RSRP offset threshold for DL serving subcell determination

Parameter name: SFN cell parameter set - DL serving subcell update timer
Description: DL serving subcell update timer to avoid too frequent switch of DL serving subcells

Parameter name: PRACH cyclic shift
Description: Preamble cyclic shift defines the configuration which is used for preamble generation. The configuration determines how many cyclic shifts are needed to generate preamble.  Configuration also defines the zero correlation zone and respective maximum cell range.

Parameter name: PRACH configuration index
Description: Defines allowed system frame and subframe numbers for random access attempts, and the preamble format.

Parameter name: PRACH frequency offset
Description: Defines the location in frequency for the PRACH transmissions.For UL scheduling its recommended that PRACH is located next to PUCCH either on the lower or upper edge of the bandwidth because UL PRB allocation for UE consist of consecutive PRBs. If there is a small gap between PUCCH and PRACH PRBs, UL scheduler cannot utilize those PRBs effectively. prachFreqOffset for each bandwidth should be set aligned with the parameters determining the number of PRBs for PUCCH, so that PRACH is located next to PUCCH.    Defines the first physical resource block allocated for PRACH  In case of preamble format 4 for special subframe, prachFreqOff must be set to 0.  In case of preamble format 0, 1 and 2 for normal subframe, recommendation is to set value so that PRACH does not overlap with PUCCH RBs and is located adjacent to PUCCH, and thus recommended parameter alternatives are:  1) roundup(MaxPucchResourceSize/2) if it is located at the lower edge, or  2) ulChBw-6-roundup(MaxPucchResourceSize/2 if it is located at the upper edge of the PUSCH area    The MaxPucchResourceSize in above defines the maximum number of allocated PUCCH RBs, and it defined in nCqiRb parameter.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: PRACH high speed flag
Description: High speed flag for PRACH preamble generation determines whether an unrestricted or a restricted set has to be used by the UE.  false = Unrestricted; true = Restricted

Parameter name: Preferred PUCCH format for 2CC CA UE
Description: This parameter specifies the preferred PUCCH format for an UE configured with 2CC DL CA with a TDD PCell.  If the parameter is set to 'PF1bcs', eNB will try to allocate PUCCH format 1b with channel selection to the UE. If the parameter is set to 'PF3', eNB will try to allocate PUCCH format 3 to the UE. If the preferred PUCCH format is not available, eNB will try to allocate PUCCH in the other format to the UE configured with 2CC DL CA with a TDD PCell.    Note:  (1) The above mentioned UE configured with 2CC DL CA with a TDD PCell includes both UEs configured with TDD-TDD DL 2CC CA and UEs configured with TDD-FDD DL 2CC CA.  (2) TDD UL/DL configuration of PCell can be TDD UL/DL frame configuration 0 or TDD UL/DL frame configuration 1 or TDD UL/DL frame configuration 2. In case TDD UL/DL configuration of PCell is TDD UL/DL frame configuration 2, according to 3GPP TS 36.213, eNB will always allocate PUCCH format 3 to such UE, regardless of the setting of this parameter.

Parameter name: PRS configuration index
Description: Determines the periodicity and offset of the PRS occasions for TDD.  14, 153-159: 160ms period  473-479: 320ms period  1113-1119: 640ms period  2393-2399: 1280ms period  The periodicity and offset can be computed according to 3GPP TS 36.211 Rel9.    Note:  - when PRS periodicity is 160ms, PRS subframe offset is prsConfigurationIndex(subframes)  - when PRS periodicity is 320ms, PRS subframe offset is prsConfigurationIndex minus 160(subframes)  - when PRS periodicity is 640ms, PRS subframe offset is prsConfigurationIndex minus 480(subframes)  - when PRS periodicity is 1280ms, PRS subframe offset is prsConfigurationIndex minus 1120(subframes)

Parameter name: PRS Number of DL frames
Description: Number of DL Frames that are used for PRS per PRS occasion for FDD. With this PRS transmission can be repeated within a PRS occasion in order to increase the hearability of PRS

Parameter name: PUCCH cyclic shift for mixed formats
Description: Number of cyclic shifts for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b in a resource block used for a mix of formats 1/1a/b and 2/2a/2b.  This parameter is one of the parameters in a set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called as MaxPucchResourceSize.

Parameter name: PUSCH hopping offset
Description: The PUSCH hopping offset parameter defines the offset used for PUSCH frequency hopping, expressed in a number of resource blocks.

Parameter name: RACH density
Description: Used as an input parameter for selecting possible PRACH Configuration Index parameter.

Parameter name: Super cell parameter set - UL SINR hysteresis for removing candidate sub-cell
Description: Defines the UL SINR hysteresis on top of UL SINR offset for removing candidate sub-cell.  If the SINR gap between serving sub-cell and current candidate sub-cell is larger than candSubCellUlSINROffset plus this parameter this candidate sub-cell will be changed to measurement sub-cell.

Parameter name: Super cell parameter set - UL SINR hysteresis for replacing candidate sub-cell
Description: Defines the UL SINR hysteresis to replace candidate sub-cell by a measurement sub-cell.  If one measurement sub-cell's SINR is larger than current candidate sub-cell' this measurement sub-cell will replace current candidate sub-cell as new candidate sub-cell.

Parameter name: Instance ID of the assigned RIAPR profile
Description: Instance ID of the assigned RIAPR profile.  RIAPR contains Remote Interference Avoidance functional parameters which is subordinate under LNBTS.

Parameter name: RACH root sequence
Description: The preamble generation is started from the Root Sequence which is pointed by the logical root sequence number. 64 preambles can be transmitted in the PRACH frame. If one root is not enough to generate all the 64 preambles, then the consecutive number is selected until the full set is generated. RACH root sequence is cell specific information and neighbouring cells should have a different value. RACH root sequence is transmitted in system information.

Parameter name: RRM PDCCH utilization coefficient
Description: The parameter specifies the PDCCH utilization filter coefficient to calculate averaged PDCCH utilization ratio in SF3/8.

Parameter name: Antenna cabling mapping configuration - RRU physical antenna port1 antenna index
Description: To indicate which of the physical antenna index shall be connected to RRU port 1 via the RF cable.

Parameter name: Antenna cabling mapping configuration - RRU physical antenna port2 antenna index
Description: To indicate which of the physical antenna index shall be connected to RRU port 2 via the RF cable.

Parameter name: Antenna cabling mapping configuration - RRU physical antenna port3 antenna index
Description: To indicate which of the physical antenna index shall be connected to RRU port 3 via the RF cable.

Parameter name: Antenna cabling mapping configuration - RRU physical antenna port4 antenna index
Description: To indicate which of the physical antenna index shall be connected to RRU port 4 via the RF cable.

Parameter name: Antenna cabling mapping configuration - RRU physical antenna port5 antenna index
Description: To indicate which of the physical antenna index shall be connected to RRU port 5 via the RF cable.
