Parameter name: Antenna cabling mapping configuration - RRU physical antenna port6 antenna index
Description: To indicate which of the physical antenna index shall be connected to RRU port 6 via the RF cable.

Parameter name: Antenna cabling mapping configuration - RRU physical antenna port7 antenna index
Description: To indicate which of the physical antenna index shall be connected to RRU port 7 via the RF cable.

Parameter name: Antenna cabling mapping configuration - RRU physical antenna port8 antenna index
Description: To indicate which of the physical antenna index shall be connected to RRU port 8 via the RF cable.

Parameter name: RX calibration in UL subframe
Description: The parameter defines where the RX calibration for optimized coexistence with WiMAX Networks shall be executed by the eNodeB.

Parameter name: Scaling factor for number of subgroup
Description: As a parameter for the functionality of ue beam pre-grouping in TD for downlink MU-MIMO of TDD mMIMO, it specifies the scaling factor for the number of subgroup in which there is at least one UE. It is used to adjust priority of beam-group based on the pairing capability.

Parameter name: Sector beam fallback timer
Description: This parameter specifies the time threshold of UE beam falling back to sector beam due to unavailability of SRS in TDD Massive MIMO.    Note:  -If the value of this parameter is set as 0 or actExtendedDelayToUseBfWeightTimer is set to 'false', the function of falling back to sector beam is deactivated.

Parameter name: Sector beam group weight
Description: As a parameter for the functionality of ue beam pre-grouping in TD for downlink MU-MIMO of TDD mMIMO, it specifies the sector beam group weight for all the NonGBR UE without MU-MIMO capability, it is used to leverage scheduling priority of non-pairable UEs and pairable UEs, the higher value higher priority of non-pairable UEs.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile based on Traffic - Downlink cell throughput increase rate threshold
Description: The parameter specifies the threshold of increasing rate for average downlink cell throughput as a traffic condition in case of traffic based trigger.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile based on Traffic - Downlink PRB usage threshold
Description: The parameter specifies the threshold of downlink PRB utilization ratio as a traffic condition in case of traffic based trigger.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile based on Traffic - Downlink user throughput decrease rate threshold
Description: The parameter specifies the threshold of decreasing rate for average downlink scheduled user throughput as a traffic condition in case of traffic based trigger

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile based on Traffic - Downlink user throughput threshold
Description: The parameter specifies the threshold of average downlink scheduled user throughput as a traffic condition in case of traffic based trigger.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile based on Traffic - RRC connected UEs increasing rate threshold
Description: The parameter specifies the threshold of increasing rate for the RRC connected UEs as a traffic condition in case of traffic based trigger.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile based on Traffic - Offset1 for threshold calculation in adaptive sector BF weight
Description: The parameter defines the offset value for calculation of the thresholds (numRrcConnUeIncRateThr, dlCellTputIncRateThr and dlPrbUsageThr) in dynamic sector BF weight adaption when actAdptSectorBfWeight is set to 'Traffic based trigger'.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile based on Traffic - Offset2 for threshold calculation in adaptive sector BF weight
Description: The parameter defines the offset value for calculation of the thresholds dlUserTputDcrRateThr in dynamic sector BF weight adaption when actAdptSectorBfWeight is set to 'Traffic based trigger'.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile based on Traffic - Start Monitor time hour
Description: Parameter start Monitor time hour identifies the local time to start monitor the traffic in low load, after that if the traffic conditions are met it will switch into the sector BF weight dynamic adaptive for high load in case of traffic based trigger.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile - Delta of electronic down tilt angle for high load
Description: The parameter specifies the degrees of the electronic down tilt angle which shall be increased to the configured vertical sector BF weight for high load.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile - Delta of electronic down tilt angle for low load
Description: The parameter specifies the degrees of the electronic down tilt angle which shall be increased to the configured vertical sector BF weight for low load.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile - Start switch time hour for high load
Description: The parameter specifies start switch time hour for high load, along with the start switch time minute for high load parameter, identifies the local time when switch into sector BF weight dynamic adaptive for high load, it is used for both time and traffic based trigger. When in case of traffic based trigger, they act as the deadline time to switch into the sector BF weight dynamic adaptive for high load if traffic conditions not met. When setting this parameter value to 255, the switch function impacted by this parameter will be disable.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile - Start switch time hour for low load
Description: The parameter specifies start switch time hour for low load, along with the start switch time minute for low load parameter, identifies the local time when switch into sector BF weight dynamic adaptive for low load, it is used for both time and traffic based trigger. When setting this parameter value to 255, the switch function impacted by this parameter will be disable.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile - Start switch time minute for high load
Description: The parameter specifies start switch time minute for high load, along with the start switch time hour for high load parameter, identifies the local time when switch into sector BF weight dynamic adaptive for high load, it is used for both time and traffic based trigger. When in case of traffic based trigger, they act as the deadline time to switch into the sector BF weight dynamic adaptive for high load if traffic conditions not met.    Note: When the value of startSwitchHourHighLoad is set to 255, this parameter is invalid.

Parameter name: Sector BF Weight Change Profile - Start switch time minute for low load
Description: The parameter specifies start switch time minute for low load, along with the start switch time hour for low load parameter, identifies the local time when switch into sector BF weight dynamic adaptive for low load, it is used for both time and traffic based trigger.    Note: When the value of startSwitchHourLowLoad is set to 255, this parameter is invalid.

Parameter name: SFN cell parameter set - SFN DL algorithm
Description: SFN DL algorithm
Range and step: static broadcasting (0), PDSCH adaptive selective transmission (1)

Parameter name: Enable sim. UL SPS and PUCCH format 3 for a UE
Description: Enable a UE simultaneously having PUCCH format 3 resource assigned and UL SPS activated.  This parameter provides a tradeoff between VoLTE performance in case of CA, and UL PRB efficient usage.    If set to 'true', a UE assigned PUCCH format 3 can simultaneously have UL SPS activated.    If set to 'false', when a UE assigned PUCCH format 3, its UL SPS shall be de-activated.

Parameter name: Downlink MU-MIMO parameter set - Downlink MU-MIMO spectrum efficiency threshold
Description: This parameter specifies the spectrum efficiency threshold which works as a criteria for adding a UE to a UE pairing and ensure the gain of spectrum efficiency.  The spectrumEffThd shall be set to 1.0 by default and further optimized by simulation.  This parameter is used for 64T64R DL MU MIMO.

Parameter name: SRS feature activation/deactivation
Description: Activates/Deactivates srs (sounding reference symbol) feature in Cell.

Parameter name: SRS bandwidth configuration
Description: Defines together with the channel bandwidth (chBw) and the srsBandwidthNonBf (srs bandwidth for non beamforming users) or srsBandwidthBf (srs bandwidth for beamforming users) the bandwidth of one srs symbol.  Please refer to table 5.5.3.2-1 to 5.5.3.2-4 in 3GPP TS36.211 for different system bandwidth.  If dlMimoMode is set to a beamforming mode ("Single Stream Beamforming" or "Dual Stream Beamforming") , than srsBandwidthForNonBf is chosen to define the bandwidth of one srs symbol for UEs which rrc transmission mode is set to tm0 to tm4. srsBandwidthForBf is chosen to define the bandwidth of one srs symbol for UEs which rrc transmission mode is set to tm7 or tm8.  If dlMimoMode is set to a non beamforming mode ("SingleTX", "TXDiv", "4-way TXDiv", "Dynamic Open Loop MIMO", "Closed Loop Mimo" or "Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)"), than srsBandwidthForNonBf is chosen to define the bandwidth of one srs symbol for all UEs.

Parameter name: SRS downlink MIMO mode dependent configuration
Description: SRS configuration parameter specific for non beamforming and optional beamforming users.    In case of carrier aggregation, dlMimoMode/actTmSwitch setting under both PCell and SCell shall be considered.  If dlMimoMode is set to a non beamforming mode ('SingleTX', 'TXDiv', '4-way TXDiv', 'Closed Loop Mimo', 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)'), then one structure element is mandatory for the configuration for non beamforming users (srsBeamformingType 'nonBeamforming').  If dlMimoMode is set to 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' and actTmSwitch is set to false, then one structure element is mandatory for the configuration for non beamforming users (srsBeamformingType 'nonBeamforming').  If dlMimoMode is set to 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' and actTmSwitch is set to true, then the structure must contain 2 elements, one for non beamforming user (srsBeamformingType 'nonBeamforming') and one for beamforming user (srsBeamformingType 'beamforming') configuration.  If dlMimoMode is set to a beamforming mode ('Single Stream Beamforming' or 'Dual Stream Beamforming' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x4)'), then the structure must contain 2 elements, one for non beamforming user (srsBeamformingType 'nonBeamforming') and one for beamforming user (srsBeamformingType 'beamforming') configuration.

Parameter name: SRS beamforming type
Description: Defines the beamforming type for which srsBandwidth and srsUePeriodicity are valid.  Two elements of srsDlMimoModeDepConf with same beamformingType are not allowed.

Parameter name: SRS bandwidth
Description: Defines together with srsBwConf (srs bandwidth configuration) the bandwidth for srs for non beamforming or beamforming configured UEs . Please refer to table 5.5.3.2-1 to 5.5.3.2-4 in 3GPP TS36.211. This depends on the value of LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType.    If LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType is set to 'nonBeamforming', then srsBandwidth defines the bandwidth of one SRS symbol for UEs which are configured to the RRC transmission mode tm1 to tm4.  If LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType is set to 'beamforming', then srsBandwidth defines the bandwidth of one SRS symbol for UEs which are configured to the RRC transmission mode tm7 or tm8.

Parameter name: SRS periodicity of UE transmission
Description: Defines the UE periodicity for srs in which the UE will provide srs to the eNB.  If LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType is set to 'nonBeamforming' then this parameter defines the periodicity for UEs which are configured to the RRC transmission mode tm1 to tm4.  If LNCEL-srsDlMimoModeDepConf-srsBeamformingType is set to 'beamforming' then this parameter defines the periodicity for UEs which are configured to the RRC transmission mode tm7 or tm8.

Parameter name: SRS duration
Description: Defines the Ue transmission duration for srs. Only indefinite duration is supported.

Parameter name: SRS hopping bandwidth
Description: Defines the srs hopping bandwidth. If srsHoppingBw >= srsBandwidthforNonBf than for non beamforming users frequency hopping is disabled.  If srsHoppingBw < srsBandwidthforNonBf than for non beamforming users frequency hopping is enabled.  If srsHoppingBw >= srsBandwidthforBf than for beamforming users frequency hopping is disabled.  If srsHoppingBw < srsBandwidthforBf than for non beamforming users frequency hopping is enabled.

Parameter name: SRS transmission on 2 symbols of UpPTS act/deact
Description: Active/deactivate srs transmission on 2 symbols of UpPts. If srsOnTwoSymUpPts is set to true, then srs transmission on 2 symbols of UpPTS is allowed.  If srsOnTwoSymUpPts is set to false, then the transmission of srs in two symbols of upPTS is not allowed. This parameter is only used in case srs periodicity of Ue is set to 2ms.

Parameter name: Power offset for SRS transmission power calculation
Description: UE specific power offset to be used for Sounding Reference Signal transmission power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P3).    SRS will be implicitly disabled if PUSCH masking is configured. The parameter is therefore not relevant and ignored if PUSCH masking is activated, i.e. if actPuschMask is equal to "true".    Note: The actual power offset depends on value of deltaTfEnabled.  For deltaTfEnabled = 'true' (KS = 1.25) the actual parameter value is "srsPwrOffset-3" corresponding to the dB-range of -3 dB to 12 dB in steps of 1 dB. For deltaTfEnabled = 'false' (KS = 0) the actual parameter value is "-10.5 + 1.5 * srsPwrOffset" value corresponding to the dB-range -10.5 dB to 12 dB in steps of 1.5 dB.

Parameter name: SRS simultaneous ack/nack activation/deactivation
Description: Activates/Deactivates SRS and Ack/Nack simultaneous transmission. If this parameter is set to true, in uplink the transmission of srs and ack/nack is allowed in the same TTI.

Parameter name: SRS subframe configuration
Description: Defines the cell specific srs subframe configuration as specified in 3GPP TS36.211 table 5.5.3.3-2.

Parameter name: Super cell parameter set - Uplink SINR hysteresis for a sub-cell switch
Description: The parameter defines the UL SINR hysteresis for a sub-cell switch.

Parameter name: Super cell parameter set - Filter coefficient for averaging UL UE SINR
Description: The parameter defines the time length as the filter coefficient for averaging UL UE SINR per RRH on SRS, PUSCH and PUCCH for sub-cell switch.

Parameter name: Synchronization signals transmission mode
Description: The parameter determines whether Primary and Secondary Synchronization Signals (PSS, SSS) are transmitted into a cell via one antenna port (SingleTx) or via all antenna ports using TX diversity with Precoding Vector Switching (PVS). In case of 2 or 4 antenna port configuration is done in a flexible way based on the antenna configuration.

Parameter name: Timer t304 for handover to TD-SCDMA
Description: This timer value is used eNodeB internally to estimate the time the UE may spend to access the target TD-SCDMA system after receiving RRC:MOBILITY FROM EUTRAN COMMAND before starting RRC Re-Establishment. It is used eNodeB internally to calculate the supervision timer for the Handover Execution Phase (TS1RELOCoverall)

Parameter name: mMIMO parameter set - Target Sounding reference signal power
Description: The parameter specifies the target power per PRB per pipe of SRS to calculate extended timer to delay to use beamforming weight in TDD Massive MIMO

Parameter name: TDD subframe configuration
Description: The TDD Uplink-downlink Configuration parameter indicates the uplink-downlink subframe configuration in TDD.  The Subframe Assignment need to be configured according to 3GPP 36.211. The parameter is transmitted in the System Information Broadcast and corresponds to the subframeAssignment (sa#) as specified in 3GPP 36.331.  Currently only Subframe assignment 0, 1 and 2 (sa0, sa1, sa2) are supported.

Parameter name: TDD special subframe configuration
Description: The TDD Special Subframe Configuration parameter is used for the configuration of DwPTS, GP and UpPTS in the special subframe. The configured Special Subframe Pattern is transmitted in the System Information Broadcast and corresponds to the specialSubframePatterns (ssp#) as specified in 3GPP 36.331.  Special Subframe Patterns 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 and 9 (ssp3: 11:2:1, ssp4: 12:1:1, ssp5: 3:9:2, ssp6: 9:3:2, ssp7: 10:2:2, ssp9: 6:6:2) are supported.    For DCM, Special Subframe Patterns 0, 1, 2, 5, 6, 7 are supported.

Parameter name: Threshold th2 TD-SCDMA for RSRP
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell for start of TD-SCDMA Measurements  Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If value is below threshold2Tdscdma (event A2) then TD-SCDMA measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Time Period for Channel Information Valid
Description: Time period during which channel information is valid  timeChInfoValid indicates that the maximum time during which the measurement channel information is valid.  If timeChInfoValid is set to 0, the measurement channel information is always invalid.  If timeChInforValid is set to infinite, the measurement channel information is always valid.

Parameter name: Transmission mode switch profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the assigned transmission mode switch profile.    The profile contains CQI thresholds for switching between transmission modes.

Parameter name: Two layer MIMO average spectral efficiency
Description: The two layer MIMO average spectral efficiency is used by the throughput check during SCell addition as follows.  If the throughput metric after the SCell addition is greater than the throughput metric before the SCell addition then this SCell addition is admitted. Otherwise, this SCell addition is rejected. The throughput metric is the sum of xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff*bandwidth of the UE's serving cells. Where xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to twoLayerMimoAvSpectralEff if the UE is configured with two layer MIMO on a given serving cell respectively xLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to fourLayerMimoAvSpectralEff if the UE is configured with four layer MIMO on a given serving cell.    A reasonable value of the parameter can be derived from the existing KPI LTE_5747a 'DL Spectral efficiency' with dlMimoMode set to 'Closed Loop Mimo' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (8x2)'.    The throughput check is not used by setting the parameter value to '0.5' i.e. any SCell addition will be always admitted by the check if twoLayerMimoAvSpectralEff is equal to fourLayerMimoAvSpectralEff in all involved cells.

Parameter name: Maximum code rate for UCI-only TX in UL
Description: Maximum code rate for UCI only transmissions in UL.

Parameter name: massive MIMO virtual resource load setting - UE delay measurement threshold
Description: This parameter defines UE delay threshold. If non-GBR UE delay bigger than the threshold, max virtual resource will downgrade with mMimoVirtualResAdjustFactor as downgrade factor.

Parameter name: Uplink combination mode
Description: Identifies the uplink combination mode.    Recommendations for balancing increased cell throughput and link level gain:  If dlMimoMode is set to 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x4)', ulCombinationMode is recommended to be configured to 'IRC'.

Parameter name: The maximum multiplexing layers per MU PRB for uplink MU-MIMO of TDD mMIMO
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum number of layers per MU PRB which are paired into uplink MU-MIMO of TDD massive MIMO.  The maximum number of layers depends on HW and the antenna array mode.

Parameter name: UL MU-MIMO parameter set - MU-MIMO beam interference cancellation method selection in horizontal direction for uplink TDD mMIMO
Description: MU-MIMO beam interference cancellation method selection in horizontal direction for uplink TDD mMIMO.

Parameter name: UL MU-MIMO parameter set - MU-MIMO beam interference cancellation method selection in vertical direction for uplink TDD mMIMO
Description: MU-MIMO beam interference cancellation method selection in vertical direction for uplink TDD mMIMO.

Parameter name: UL MU-MIMO MCS compensate offset
Description: This parameter specifies UL MU-MIMO MCS compensate offset.

Parameter name: UL MU-MIMO parameter set - UL MU-MIMO orthogonality factor threshold
Description: The orthogonality factor between two UEs shall be bigger than ulMuMimoOrthThrehold.

Parameter name: UL MU-MIMO parameter set - UL MU-MIMO PRB differential threshold
Description: This parameter specifies UL MU-MIMO PRB differential threshold.

Parameter name: UL MU-MIMO parameter set - UL MU-MIMO SINR threshold
Description: SINR threshold above which UEs can be selected as the candidate users of UL MU-MIMO.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - UL SPS interval
Description: Specifies the radio resource allocation period for Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS).  Although 3GPP supports several values, only 20 msec is supported.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Uplink SPS maximum number PRB
Description: Cell level maximum number of PRB for UL SPS.  Specifies the maximum number of uplink Physical Resource Blocks (PRB) per Transmission Time Interval (TTI) which can be allocated to Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS).  The maximum number of ulSpsMaxNumPrb depends on the bandwidth and PUCCH/PRACH PRB number of the cell. The parameter setting shall consider the dynamic scheduling UE and adaptive retransmission PRB requirement.    The recommended value is 20.    Both maxNumSpsUeUl and ulSpsMaxNumPrb will limit the SPS usage in the cell.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Uplink SPS max PRB per UE for AMR NB
Description: Specifies the maximum allowed number of PRB for the AMR NB Voice over IP (VoIP) of a single UE per TTI when Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS) is activated.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Uplink SPS max PRB per UE for AMR WB
Description: Specifies the maximum allowed number of PRB for the AMR WB Voice over IP (VoIP) of a single UE per TTI when Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS) is activated.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Uplink SPS minimum voice packet size
Description: Threshold of the size of a Voice Over IP (VoIP) talkspurt packet in the uplink direction.  Specifies the minimum size of a Voice Over IP (VoIP) talkspurt packet in the uplink direction. If the estimated uplink buffer size of the Logical Channel Group (LCG) including Quality of Service (QoS) Class Identifier 1 (QCI-1) traffic is larger than defined by the ulSpsMinVoicePktSize parameter, uplink Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS) allocation for the UE is attempted. The parameter should be set to the value between the size of SID packet and AMR payload packet.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - UL SPS number of empty transmissions
Description: Uplink SPS number of empty transmissions before implicit release.  Specifies number of consecutive empty transmissions before the eNodeB assumes the uplink Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS) allocation is released. UE automatically releases the UL SPS allocation once it reaches this number of consecutive empty transmissions.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Uplink SPS QCI1 throughput factor
Description: ulSpsQci1ThroughputFactor is used to set the threshold of the ratio (total UL TP)/(QCI1 bearers provided UL TP): Only if the ratio <= ulSpsQci1ThroughputFactor, UE can be activated with UL SPS. Total UL TP here is counted in the eNB at the moment when the check is done.  With a small ulSpsQci1ThroughputFactor, it means UL SPS can be applied on a UE which has little data transmission besides QCI1 bearer in UL.  With a big ulSpsQci1ThroughputFactor, it means UL SPS can be applied on a UE even who has lots of data transmission besides QCI1 bearer in UL.    When no value is defined for the parameter, whenever the eNB tries to activate UL SPS for a UE, it doesn't check UE's total UL TP at all for the cell.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - UL SPS two-intervals SPS configuration
Description: Trigger of two-intervals-Semi-Persistent Scheduling in uplink.  Although 3GPP supports both "true" and "false", only value "true" is supported to get better performance.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Uplink SPS allocation transport block size for AMR NB
Description: Specifies the way to determine Transport Block Size (TBS) used to calculate the number of PRB and MCS for uplink Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS) allocation in the case of AMR NB payload.  - small means select TBS with assumption short RLC header in use and no MCA CE included, eNB estimates the TBS with no other overheads consideration such as Power Headroom Report, Buffer Status Report or extra RLC/MAC overhead and with rlcProf101-snFieldLengthUL is set to "5bit" and pdcpProf101-snSize is set to "7bit".    - big means select TBS with assumption long RLC header in use and MacCEs included, eNB estimates the TBS with Power Headroom Report and Buffer Status Report. If rlcProf101-snFieldLengthUL is set to "10bit" and pdcpProf101-snSize is set to "12bit", longRLC_and_MacCE is recommended.    This parameter setting is a tradeoff between SPS PRB cost and dynamic scheduling (PDCCH cost), ulSpsVoicePktTbsNB=small result in small TBS, and small TBS will save PRB and may cost more PDCCH.  Note: dynamic scheduling may trigger between two SPS_Reserved_TTIs.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Uplink SPS allocation transport block size for AMR WB
Description: Specifies the the way to determine Transport Block Size (TBS) used to calculate the number of PRB and MCS for uplink Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS) allocation in the case of AMR WB payload.  - small means select TBS with assumption short RLC header in use and no MCA CE included, eNB estimates the TBS with no other overheads consideration such as Power Headroom Report, Buffer Status Report or extra RLC/MAC overhead and with rlcProf101-snFieldLengthUL is set to "5bit" and pdcpProf101-snSize is set to "7bit".    - big means select TBS with assumption long RLC header in use and MacCEs included, eNB estimates the TBS with Power Headroom Report and Buffer Status Report. If rlcProf101-snFieldLengthUL is set to "10bit" and pdcpProf101-snSize is set to "12bit", longRLC_and_MacCE is recommended.    This parameter setting is a tradeoff between SPS PRB cost and dynamic scheduling (PDCCH cost), ulSpsVoicePktTbsNB=small result in small TBS, and small TBS will save PRB and may cost more PDCCH.  Note: dynamic scheduling may trigger between two SPS_Reserved_TTIs.

Parameter name: SPS configuration - Uplink SPS PUSCH BLER target
Description: Specifies the uplink Block Error Rate (BLER) target for UL PUSCH transmissions when a UE is using Semi-Persistent Scheduling (SPS).

Parameter name: massive MIMO virtual resource load setting - Period for checking UE delay situation
Description: This parameter defines the period for checking UE delay situation. During this period, cell virtual resource capacity will not change.

Parameter name: Redirected VoLTE call setup supervision timer
Description: The parameter defines the redirected VoLTE call setup guard timer. This timer is started when A4 measurement for inter-frequency VoLTE call setup triggered Handover is activated and used to supervise the whole Handover procedure.  The timer is only applicable when Redirected VoLTE call setup feature is switched on and QCI1 bearer is requested to be established for UE.

Parameter name: Closed subscriber group identifier
Description: Instance identifier of the object LNCSG. This parameter is used only for O&M purposes.  The LNCSG MOC is used to identify CSG neighbors.

Parameter name: CSG cell individual offset
Description: Cell Individual Offset (CIO) of CSG cells for insertion into the CIO Cell List of EUTRA Serving or Neighbor Carrier Measurement Object.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier frequency
Description: Indicates the LTE earfcnDL / earfcn for which this instance of LNCSG applies.

Parameter name: CSG neighbor first PCI
Description: Indicates the lowest PCI in the CSG Neighbor range for a frequency.

Parameter name: Number of PCI in CSG neighbor range
Description: Indicates the number of PCIs in the CSG Neighbor range for a frequency.

Parameter name: eNB ID Size
Description: This parameter defines the size of the eNB ID.  The setting is commonly valid for all CSG cells of a dedicated frequency.  20 refers to usage of Macro eNB ID whereas 28 refers to the usage of Home eNB ID.

Parameter name: Hybrid identifier
Description: Instance identifier of the object LNHBD. This parameter is used only for O&M purposes.  The LNHBD MOC is used to identify Hybrid neighbors.

Parameter name: Hybrid cell individual offset
Description: Cell Individual Offset (CIO) of hybrid cells for insertion into the CIO Cell List of EUTRA Serving or Neighbor Carrier Measurement  CIO values for macro eNodeB(s) always have higher priority than those for hybrid cells as far as the PCI of the macro eNB is not in a hybrid cell PCI range.    CIO is only included in the measurement object if there is sufficient space.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: eNB ID Size
Description: This parameter defines the size of the eNB ID.  The setting is commonly valid for all hybrid cells of a dedicated frequency.  In most cases a hybrid cell should have an eNB ID Size of 28 bits but in some home eNB gateway implementations it is possible that a hybrid cell may have an eNB ID Size of 20 bits.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier frequency
Description: Indicates the LTE earfcn for which this instance of LNHBD applies.

Parameter name: Hybrid neighbor first PCI
Description: First pci in the range of physical cell ids which are reserved for hybrid neighbor cells for a frequency.

Parameter name: Hybrid neighbor last PCI
Description: Last pci in the range of physical cell ids which are reserved for hybrid neighbor cells for a frequency.  In case of a single PCI the same value as pciFirst needs to be configured.

Parameter name: Home eNB set identifier
Description: Uniquely identifies a LNHENB instance.

Parameter name: Home eNB cell individual offset
Description: Cell Individual Offset (CIO) of home eNB cells for insertion into the CIO Cell List of EUTRA Serving or Neighbor Carrier Measurement Object  CIO values for macro eNodeB(s) always have higher priority than those for home eNBs as far as the PCI of the macro eNB is not in a home eNB PCI range.    CIO is only included in the measurement object if there is sufficient space.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: eNB ID size
Description: This parameter defines the size of the eNB ID.  The setting is commonly valid for all home eNB cells of a dedicated frequency.    In most cases a home eNB should have an eNB ID Size of 28 bits but in some home eNB gateway implementations it is possible that a home eNB may have an eNB ID Size of 20 bits.

Parameter name: Home eNB EUTRA carrier frequency
Description: EARFCN value of the home eNB carrier frequency

Parameter name: Home eNB first PCI
Description: First pci in the range of physical cell ids which are reserved for home eNBs.

Parameter name: Home eNB last PCI
Description: Last pci in the range of physical cell ids which are reserved for home eNBs.    In case of a single PCI the same value as pciFirst needs to be configured.

Parameter name: Neighbor GERAN BTS cell handover identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming Attribute of the MOC LNHOG.  Instance Identifier of a GERAN eNACC HO Target

Parameter name: ARFCN value list
Description: Explicit List of ARFCNs  The ARFCN values in the set (including the startingARFCN) are explicitly listed one by one.

Parameter name: Threshold1 GERAN for RSRP of serving cell
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1GERAN and RSRP of GERAN neighbour cell ? b2Threshold2RssiGERAN  then handover is triggered (B2 event)    Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event  type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  b2Threshold1GERAN AND the GERAN neighbour cell becomes better than b2Threshold2GERAN.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for GERAN    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold1 GERAN for RSRP of  serving cell during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell when UE has QCI1 bearer. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1GERANQci1 and RSRP of GERAN neighbour cell ? b2Threshold2RssiGERANQci1  then handover is triggered (B2 event).    Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event when UE has QCI1 bearer. Used in measurement event type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than b2Threshold1GERANQci1 AND the GERAN neighbour cell becomes better than b2Threshold2RssiGERANQci1.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for GERAN.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 GERAN mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 GERAN threshold1
Description: Threshold1 for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ of serving cell is less than b2Threshold1RsrqGERAN, then the first entering condition of the B2 event is fulfilled.  If also for the second entering condition the measurement results of RSSI of GERAN neighbour cell is greater than b2Threshold2RssiGERAN, then handover is triggered.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 GERAN mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 GERAN threshold1 during QCI1
Description: Threshold1 for RSRQ of serving cell for B2-UTRA event when UE has QCI1 bearer. If RSRQ of serving cell is less than b2Threshold1RsrqGERANQci1, then the first entering condition of the B2 event is fulfilled.  If also for the second entering condition the measurement results of RSSI of GERAN neighbor cell is greater than b2Threshold2RssiGERAN, then handover is triggered.  The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: Threshold2 GERAN for RSSI neighbor cell
Description: Threshold for RSSI of GERAN neighbour cell. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1 and RSSI of GERAN neighbour cell ? b2Threshold2RssiGERAN  then handover is triggered (B2 event).      Receive level threshold for GERAN neighbour cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than b2Threshold1 AND the GERAN neighbour cell becomes better than b2Threshold2RssiGERAN.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for GERAN.  Note: The mapping for RSRP based GERAN thresholds is different from the one defined in 3GPP TS 36.133 and are defined in TS 45.008    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 45.008:  * -110 dBm means a threshold lower than -110 dBm  * values between -109 dBm and -48 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -47 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -48 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold2 GERAN For RSSI neighbor cell during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSSI of GERAN neighbor cell when UE has QCI1 bearer. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1GERANQci1 and RSSI of GERAN neighbor cell ? b2Threshold2RssiGERANQci1  then handover is triggered (B2 event).    Receive level threshold for GERAN neighbor cell in B2 event when UE has QCI1 bearer. Used in measurement event type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than b2Threshold1GERANQci1 AND the GERAN neighbor cell becomes better than b2Threshold2RssiGERANQci1.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for GERAN.  Note: The mapping for RSRP based GERAN thresholds is different from the one defined in 3GPP TS 36.133 and are defined in TS 45.008    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 45.008:  * -110 dBm means a threshold lower than -110 dBm  * values between -109 dBm and -48 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -47 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -48 dBm

Parameter name: Time to trigger GERAN measurement report
Description: Duration for which the RSRP based event B2 must be valid  Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRP based measurement event B2 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 GERAN mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 GERAN time to trigger
Description: Duration for which the RSRQ based event B2 must be valid.  Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRQ based measurement event B2 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: ARFCN frequency band indicator
Description: Indicates how to interpret the ARFCN of the BCCH carrier  The IE BandIndicatorGERAN indicates how to interpret an associated GERAN carrier ARFCN, see TS 45.005 [20]. More specifically, the IE indicates the GERAN frequency band in case the ARFCN value can concern either a DCS 1800 or a PCS 1900 carrier frequency. For ARFCN values not associated with one of these bands, the indicator is not relevant.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of thresholds B2Th1 and B2Th2 for H
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for HO to GERAN  Parameter is used within the entry and leaves condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 GERAN mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 GERAN hysteresis
Description: Related hysteresis of handover margin for HO to GERAN applied to the first (threshold1) and second (threshold2) entering and leaving condition.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the RSRQ based B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: NCC permitted bit map
Description: Network (PLMN) Color Code  This parameter restricts the permitted Network Color Code (NCC) for connected mode mobility.  Using default settings, no network is permitted.    Field encoded as a bit map, where bit N is set to "0" if a BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is not permitted for monitoring and set to "1" if the BCCH carrier with NCC = N-1 is permitted for monitoring; N = 1 to 8; bit 1 of the bitmap is the leading bit of the bit string.
Range and step: bits mask: NCC 7 (0), NCC 6 (1), NCC 5 (2), NCC 4 (3), NCC 3 (4), NCC 2 (5), NCC 1 (6), NCC 0 (7)

Parameter name: Interval for periodical GERAN measurement reporting
Description: The RSRP based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval  The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRP

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 GERAN mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 GERAN report interval
Description: The RSRQ based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval.    The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRQ based event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: Neighbor HRPD cell handover identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a LNHOH instance.

Parameter name: Threshold1 CDMA2000-HRPD for RSRP of serving Cell
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1Hrpd and pilotStrength of eHRPD neighbor cell ? b2Threshold2PstrHrpd  then handover is triggered (B2 event)    Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event  type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  b2Threshold1Hrpd AND the eHRPD neighbor cell becomes better than b2Threshold2PstrHrpd.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for CDMA2000-eHRPD.  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 HRPD mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 HRPD threshold1
Description: Threshold1 for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ of serving cell is less than b2Threshold1RsrqRtt, then the first entering condition of the B2 event is fulfilled.  If also for the second entering condition the measurement results of pilot strength of CDMA2000-HRPD neighbor cell is greater than b2Threshold2PstrHrpd, then handover is triggered.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: Threshold2 CDMA2000 for HRPD Neighbor Cell
Description: CDMA2000 pilot strength, the ratio of pilot power to total power in the signal bandwidth of a CDMA2000 forward channel. See 3GPP2 C.S0087-A (chp. 5.4.6.2.1) for CDMA2000-HRPD  The pilotStrength of eHRPD maps onto the 3GPP parameter b2-Threshold2CDMA2000 with 0 as the strongest and with 63 (-31.5 dB) as the weakest pilot strength.

Parameter name: Time to Trigger CDMA2000-HRPD Measurement Report
Description: Time during which specific criteria for the RSRP&Pstr based measurement event B2 needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 HRPD mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 HRPD time to trigger
Description: Duration for which the RSRQ based event B2 must be valid.  Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRQ based measurement event B2 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD Carrier Frequency - CDMA2000 HRPD ARFCN
Description: Absolute Radio Frequency Number of CDMA2000 eHRPD carrier frequency  The CDMA2000 ARFCN used to indicate the CDMA2000 carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 band, see C.S0002-A.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD Carrier Frequency - CDMA2000 HRPD Band Class
Description: Band Class of CDMA2000 eHRPD carrier frequency  The CDMA2000 band class is used to define the CDMA2000 band in which the CDMA2000 carrier frequency can be found, as defined in C.S0057-E [table 1.5-1].  Note: Bandclasses 18, 19, 20 and 21 are not supported by this release.

Parameter name: Relative weight of the eHRPD carrier
Description: Defines the relative weight of this eHRPD neighbor frequency in the search algorithm used for selecting the carrier used for measurement configuration during eHRPD handover procedures. A higher value indicates higher priority.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD Preregistration Allowed
Description: Defines whether the eNodeB and MME support preregistration and handover procedures to an evolved High Rate Packet Data (eHRPD) RAN. This parameter is used in Measurement Configuration of eHRPD neighbors in RRC CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD Search Window Size
Description: Provides the search window size to be used by the UE for the neighboring pilot.  The parameter is mandatory.  Provides the search window size to be used by the UE for the neighboring pilot, see C.S0005-A.

Parameter name: Related Hysteresis of B2Th1 and B2Th2 for C2K-HRPD
Description: Related hysteresis of handover margin for HO to CDMA2000-eHRPD  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 HRPD mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 HRPD hysteresis
Description: Related hysteresis of handover margin for HO to CDMA2000-HRPD applied to the first (threshold1) and second (threshold2) entering and leaving condition.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the RSRQ based B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 HRPD Frequency Specific Offset
Description: Offset value applicable to the eHRPD carrier frequency.  The IE Q-OffsetRangeInterRAT is used to indicate a frequency specific offset to be applied when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

Parameter name: Interval for Periodical C2K-HRPD Measurement Reporting
Description: The RSRP&Pstr based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval    The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRP&Pstr based event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 HRPD mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 HRPD report interval
Description: The RSRQ based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval.  The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRQ based event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: Neighbor interfrequency LTE cell handover identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC LNHOIF

Parameter name: A3 offset RSRP inter frequency
Description: Margin for RSRP for better cell HO. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the inter frequency neighbor cell becomes A3 offset better than the serving cell.

Parameter name: A3 offset RSRP inter frequency for Cat-M
Description: Margin for RSRP for better cell HO for Cat-M. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the inter frequency neighbor cell becomes A3 offset better than the serving cell.

Parameter name: A3 offset RSRP inter frequency for high power UE
Description: Margin for RSRP of the high power UE when HPUE has no QCI1 bearer. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the inter frequency neighbor cell becomes A3 offset better than the serving cell.

Parameter name: A3 Offset RSRP Inter Frequency during QCI1
Description: Handover Margin for Better Cell Handover when UE has QCI1 bearer    RSRP Offset value to be used in EUTRA measurement report triggering condition for event A3 when UE has a QCI1 bearer.  The event is triggered when the neighbor cell becomes better in RSRP than the serving cell by at least the A3 offset. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: A3 offset RSRP inter frequency for QCI1 Cat-M
Description: Margin for RSRP for better cell HO for Cat-M. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the inter frequency neighbor cell becomes A3 offset better than the serving cell.  This parameter is used when a QCI1 bearer is present.

Parameter name: A3 offset RSRQ inter frequency
Description: Margin for RSRQ for better cell HO. Used in measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the inter frequency neighbor cell becomes A3 offset better than the serving cell.

Parameter name: A3 report amount RSRP Inter-frequency
Description: Defines the number of A3 measurement reports that the UE can send once the RSRP based A3 threshold criteria is met for inter-frequency measurement

Parameter name: A3 report amount RSRQ Inter-frequency
Description: Defines the number of A3 measurement reports that the UE can send once the RSRQ based A3 threshold criteria is met for inter-frequency measurement

Parameter name: A3 report interval RSRP inter frequency
Description: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the inter frequency measurement event A3 with quantity RSRP is met. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS120 corresponds to 120 ms, MS240 to 240 ms and so on, while value MIN1 corresponds to 1 min, MIN6 to 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: A3 report interval RSRQ inter frequency
Description: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the inter frequency measurement event A3 with quantity RSRQ is met. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS120 corresponds to 120 ms, MS240 to 240 ms and so on, while value MIN1 corresponds to 1 min, MIN6 to 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger RSRP inter frequency
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the inter frequency measurement event A3 with quantity RSRP must be met in order to trigger a measurement report. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS0 corresponds to 0 ms, MS40 to 40 ms and so on.

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger RSRP inter frequency for Cat-M
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the inter frequency measurement event A3 with quantity RSRP must be met in order to trigger a measurement report for Cat-M.

Parameter name: A3 time to trigger RSRQ inter frequency
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the inter frequency measurement event A3 with quantity RSRQ must be met in order to trigger a measurement report. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS0 corresponds to 0 ms, MS40 to 40 ms and so on.

Parameter name: A5 report amount RSRP Inter-frequency
Description: Defines the number of A5 measurement reports that the UE can send once the RSRP based A5 threshold criteria is met for inter-frequency measurement

Parameter name: A5 report amount RSRQ Inter-frequency
Description: Defines the number of A5 measurement reports that the UE can send once the RSRQ based A5 threshold criteria is met for inter-frequency measurement

Parameter name: A5 report interval inter frequency
Description: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the inter frequency measurement event A5 is met. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS120 corresponds to 120 ms, MS240 to 240 ms and so on, while value MIN1 corresponds to 1 min, MIN6 to 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: A5 RSRQ inter-frequency mobility parameters - RSRQ A5 inter-frequency report interval
Description: The RSRQ based A5 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval  The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for A5 RSRP based event.

Parameter name: A5 time to trigger inter frequency
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the inter frequency measurement event A5 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS0 corresponds to 0 ms, MS40 to 40 ms and so on.

Parameter name: A5 RSRQ inter-frequency mobility parameters - RSRQ A5 inter-frequency time to trigger
Description: Duration for which the RSRQ based event A5 must be valid  Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRQ based measurement event A5 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Eutra carrier info
Description: Identifies E-UTRA carrier frequency for which this configuration is valid.  Mid-(-center)frequency of serving cell, used in EUTRA Measurement Configuration

Parameter name: Related hysteresis offset a3Offset RSRP inter frequency
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Better Cell Handover of Inter-Frequency  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis offset a3Offset RSRP inter frequency for Cat-M
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Better Cell Handover of Inter-Frequency for Cat-M  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis offset a3Offset RSRP inter frequency for QCI1 Cat-M
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Better Cell Handover of Inter-Frequency for Cat-M when a QCI1 bearer is present.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis offset a3Offset RSRQ inter frequency
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Quality Handover of Inter-Frequency  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of thresholds th3 and th3a for RSRP
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Coverage Handover of Inter-Frequency  Parameter is used within the entry and leaves condition of the A5 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: A5 RSRQ inter-frequency mobility parameters - RSRQ A5 inter-frequency hysteresis
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for Coverage Handover of Inter-Frequency when RSRQ thresholds are used for A5 event  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A5 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Inter-frequency group priority
Description: This parameter defines the related inter-frequency group priority(i.e group ID) within the whole group profiles  The smaller the value the higher the priority, i.e value "1" means highest priority and value "12" means "no group" (lowest priority, assigned with default profile).

Parameter name: Inter-frequency priority
Description: This parameter defines the related inter-frequency priority within the group  The smaller the value the higher the priority, i.e value "1" means highest priority and value "16" means lowest priority.

Parameter name: VoLTE quality target threshold profile identifier for inter-frequency handover
Description: Identifier of the Target Threshold Profile, which shall be used for VoLTE quality inter-frequency handover.  Note: The referred Target Threshold Profile Managed Object Instance must exist.

Parameter name: Presence antenna port1
Description: The IE PresenceAntennaPort1 is used to indicate whether all the neighboring cells use Antenna Port 1. When set to TRUE, the UE may assume that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighboring cells.

Parameter name: Measurement quantity inter frequency
Description: Defines which quantity to use for Event A3 measurements towards this frequency. This parameter refers to event A3. If set to 'both', two A3 events will be configured when measuring this carrier, one per specific measurement quantity.  Note: The value specified here is only applied for wideband UEs.

Parameter name: Measurement bandwidth
Description: Measurement bandwidth common for all neighboring cells on the frequency, used in Measurement Configuration.

Parameter name: Inter EUTRA offset frequency
Description: Offset value applicable to the EUTRA neighbor carrier frequencies.  The IE Q-OffsetRange is used to indicate a cell or frequency specific offset to be applied when evaluating candidates for cell re-selection or when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

Parameter name: RSRP filter offset for serv. RLQ with load bal.
Description: Offset for filtering target cells out of reported A4 event based on RSRP values due to serving radio link qualification with load balancing based trigger.

Parameter name: RSRQ filter offset or serv. RLQ with load bal.
Description: Offset for filtering target cells out of reported A4 event based on RSRQ values due to serving radio link qualification with load balancing based trigger.

Parameter name: priority steering of measurement events - priority of A3-RSRP event
Description: priority of A3-RSRP event for increased carrier monitoring

Parameter name: priority steering of measurement events - priority of A3-RSRQ event
Description: priority of A3-RSRQ event for increased carrier monitoring

Parameter name: priority steering of measurement events - priority of A5 event
Description: priority of A5 event for increased carrier monitoring (either RSRP or RSRQ based)

Parameter name: Timer T312
Description: Timer T312 supervises the recovery from physical layer problems when a measurement report has been triggered for a measurement identity for which T312 has been configured, while T310 is running. This parameter is used in inter-frequency measurement object.    It is recommended that the value of this parameter be smaller than SIB-t310.

Parameter name: Offsets for RSRP/RSRQ filter thresholds for SPID-based IF HO
Description: This structure holds a table of offsets for the RSRP/RSRQ filter thresholds for SPID-based IF HO (ind, rsrpOffset, rsrqOffset).  RSRP and/or RSRQ offsets are selected by setting MO/D/PR-erIndForSPIDHO == ind.

Parameter name: Index of RSRP/RSRQ offsets
Description: Index of the offsets for the RSRP/RSRQ filter thresholds (rsrpOffset, rsrqOffset) for SPID-based IF HO, contained in the same instance of 'thresOffsetsIFSPIDFilter'. An instance of thresOffsetsIFSPIDFilter can be used by configuring ind == MO/D/PR-erIndForSPIDHO.

Parameter name: RSRP offset
Description: Offset for the RSRP filter threshold (thresholdRsrpIFSPIDFilter) for SPID-based IF HO, referenced by parameter 'ind' in the same instance of 'thresOffsetsIFSPIDFilter'.

Parameter name: RSRQ offset
Description: Offset for the RSRQ filter threshold for SPID-based IF HO, referenced by parameter 'ind' in the same instance of 'thresOffsetsIFSPIDFilter'.

Parameter name: Threshold th3 for RSRP inter frequency
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving value ? threshold3InterFreq and RSRP of neighbor cell ? threshold3aInterFreq  then handover is triggered (A5 event)  Receive level threshold for serving cell in A5 event. Used in measurement event  type A5 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  threshold3InterFreq AND the neighbor cell becomes better than threshold3aInterFreq.  Set in ReportConfigEUTRA    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th3 for RSRP inter frequency for high power UE
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell when HPUE has no QCI1 bearer. If RSRP of serving cell ? threshold3InterFreqHpue and RSRP of neighbor cell ? threshold3aInterFreqHpue, then handover is triggered (A5 event)    Receive level threshold of serving cell in A5 event from high power UE. Used in measurement event type A5 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than threshold3InterFreqHpue AND the neighbor cell becomes better than threshold3aInterFreqHpue.  Set in ReportConfigEUTRA    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th3 For RSRP inter frequency during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell when UE has QCI1 bearer. If RSRP of serving value ? threshold3InterFreqQci1 and RSRP of neighbor cell ? threshold3aInterFreqQci1,  then handover is triggered (A5 event).    Receive level threshold for serving cell in A5 event when UE has QCI1 bearer. Used in measurement event type A5 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than threshold3InterFreqQci1 AND the neighbor cell becomes better than threshold3aInterFreqQci1.  Set in ReportConfigEUTRA.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: A5 RSRQ inter-frequency mobility parameters - RSRQ A5 inter-frequency threshold1
Description: Threshold for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ of serving value ? threshold3RsrqInterFreq and RSRQ of neighbor cell ? threshold3aRsrqInterFreq  then handover is triggered (A5 event)  Receive level threshold for serving cell in A5 event. Used in measurement event  type A5 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  threshold3RsrqInterFreq AND the neighbor cell becomes better than threshold3aRsrqInterFreq.  Set in ReportConfigEUTRA.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: Threshold th3a for RSRP inter frequency
Description: Threshold for RSRP of neighbor cell. If RSRP of serving value ? threshold3InterFreq and RSRP of neighbor cell ? threshold3aInterFreq  then handover is triggered (A5 event)  Receive level threshold for neighbor cell in A5 event. Used in measurement event  type A5 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  threshold3InterFreq AND the neighbor cell becomes better than threshold3aInterFreq.  Set in ReportConfigEUTRA    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th3a for RSRP inter frequency for high power UE
Description: Threshold for RSRP of neighbor cell when HPUE has no QCI1 bearer. If RSRP of serving value ? threshold3InterFreqHpue and RSRP of neighbor cell ? threshold3aInterFreqHpue  then handover is triggered (A5 event)    Receive level threshold of neighbor cell in A5 event from high power UE. Used in measurement event  type A5 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  threshold3InterFreqHpue AND the neighbor cell becomes better than threshold3aInterFreqHpue.  Set in ReportConfigEUTRA    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold th3a For RSRP inter frequency during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of neighbor cell when UE has QCI1 bearer. If RSRP of serving value ? threshold3InterFreqQci1 and RSRP of neighbor cell ? threshold3aInterFreqQci1  then handover is triggered (A5 event).    Receive level threshold for neighbor cell in A5 event when UE has QCI1 bearer. Used in measurement event type A5 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than threshold3InterFreqQci1 AND the neighbor cell becomes better than threshold3aInterFreqQci1.  Set in ReportConfigEUTRA.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: A5 RSRQ inter-frequency mobility parameters - RSRQ A5 inter-frequency threshold2
Description: Threshold for RSRQ of neighbor cell. If RSRQ of serving value ? threshold3RsrqInterFreq and RSRQ of neighbor cell ? threshold3aRsrqInterFreq  then handover is triggered (A5 event)  Receive level threshold for neighbor cell in A5 event. Used in measurement event  type A5 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  threshold3RsrqInterFreq AND the neighbor cell becomes better than threshold3aRsrqInterFreq.  Set in ReportConfigEUTRA.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: EN-DC capability based threshold for RSRP target filter
Description: Threshold for filtering target cells out of reported A5 event based on RSRP values due to EN-DC capability based HO  This parameter is aimed for postprocessing (RSRP) the related A5 report and is not to be configured in any report configuration in the UE.  Value Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4

Parameter name: Inter-freq load bal threshold for RSRP target filter
Description: Threshold for Filtering Target Cells out of reported A4 event based on RSRP values due to Inter Frequency Load Balancing  This parameter is aimed for postprocessing (RSRP) the related A4 report and is not to be configured in any report configuration in the UE.  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4

Parameter name: Inter-freq. service based threshold RSRP target filter
Description: Threshold for filtering target cells out of reported A4 event based on RSRP values due to inter-frequency service based trigger  This parameter is aimed for postprocessing (RSRP) the related A4 report and is not to be configured in any report configuration in the UE.  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4

Parameter name: RSRP filter threshold for SPID-based IF HO
Description: RSRP filter threshold for SPID-based IF HO.

Parameter name: RSRP filter for QCIx service-based handover
Description: RSRP filter for QCIx service-based handover.

Parameter name: RSRP filter threshold for serv. RLQ with load bal.
Description: Threshold for filtering target cells out of reported A4 event based on RSRP values due to serving radio link qualification with load balancing based trigger.

Parameter name: EN-DC capability based threshold for RSRQ target filter
Description: Threshold for filtering target cells out of reported A5 event based on RSRQ values due to EN-DC capability based HO  This parameter is aimed for postprocessing (RSRQ) the related A5 report and is not to be configured in any report configuration in the UE  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.7

Parameter name: Inter-freq load bal threshold for RSRQ target filter
Description: Threshold for Filtering Target Cells out of reported A4 event based on RSRQ values due to Inter Frequency Load Balancing  This parameter is aimed for postprocessing (RSRQ) the related A4 report and is not to be configured in any report configuration in the UE  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.7

Parameter name: Inter-freq. service based threshold RSRQ target filter
Description: Threshold for filtering target cells out of reported A4 event based on RSRQ values due to inter-frequency service based trigger    This parameter is aimed for postprocessing (RSRQ) the related A4 report and is not to be configured in any report configuration in the UE.  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4

Parameter name: RSRQ filter threshold for SPID-based IF HO
Description: RSRQ filter threshold for SPID-based IF HO.

Parameter name: RSRQ filter for QCIx service-based handover
Description: RSRQ filter for QCIx service-based handover.

Parameter name: RSRQ filter threshold for serv. RLQ with load bal.
Description: Threshold for filtering target cells out of reported A4 event based on RSRQ values due to serving radio link qualification with load balancing based trigger.

Parameter name: Neighbor NR gNB cell handover identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of the object LNHON. This parameter appears only in the distinguished name (DN) in the plan file and is used for O&M purposes.

Parameter name: Hysteresis of 5GCap mobility B1-NR RSRP threshold
Description: Hysteresis of B1-NR RSRP threshold for 5GSA Capability-based mobility (e.g. redirection)

Parameter name: Hysteresis of 5GCap mobility B1-NR RSRQ threshold
Description: Hysteresis of B1-NR RSRQ threshold for 5GSA Capability-based mobility (e.g. redirection)

Parameter name: 5GCap mobility B1-NR report amount
Description: 5GSA Capability-based mobility (e.g. Redirection) B1-NR report amount

Parameter name: 5GCap mobility B1-NR report interval
Description: 5GSA Capability-based mobility (e.g. redirection) B1-NR report interval

Parameter name: RSRP threshold for triggering 5GSA B1-NR
Description: RSRP threshold of neighbor NR cell for triggering of 5GSA B1-NR event.  Set in nr-RSRP-r15 of B1-NR event of ReportConfigInterRAT for NR frequency measurement.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 38.133:  * -156 dBm means a threshold lower than -156 dBm  * values between -155 dBm and -30 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -29 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -30 dBm

Parameter name: RSRQ threshold for triggering 5GSA B1-NR
Description: RSRQ threshold of neighbor NR cell for triggering of 5GSA B1-NR event.  Set in nr-RSRQ-r15 of B1 event of ReportConfigInterRAT for NR frequency measurement.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 38.133:  * -43.5 dB means a threshold lower than -43 dB  * values between -43 dB and 19.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  * 20 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 20 dB

Parameter name: RSRP 5GSA B1-NR Time to trigger
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the NR measurement RSRP triggered event 5GSA B1-NR must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: RSRQ 5GSA B1-NR Time to trigger
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the NR measurement RSRQ triggered event 5GSA B1-NR must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: 5GSA B1-NR Trigger Quantity
Description: Defines which quantity (RSRP or RSRQ) the UE has to use for triggering an event 5GSA B1-NR measurement report.

Parameter name: B2-NR beam level report quantity
Description: Specifies the B2-NR beam level report quantity according to 3GPP 38.215 5.1.5.  Depending on the selection, the corresponding thresholds b2NrBeamThreshRsrp and/or b2NrBeamThreshRsrq need to be configured.
Range and step: None (0), RSRP (1), RSRQ (2), RSRP and RSRQ (3)

Parameter name: RSRP Threshold for B2-NR beam level measurement report
Description: NR RSRP Threshold for B2-NR beam level measurement report

Parameter name: RSRQ Threshold for B2-NR beam level measurement report
Description: NR RSRQ Threshold for B2-NR beam level measurement report

Parameter name: NR Meaurement Cell Report Quantity of B2-NR
Description: Defines which measurement quantities (RSRP/RSRQ) of NR neighbor cell reported in an event B2-NR measurement report by UE.

Parameter name: Maximum number of NR beams in B2-NR measurement report
Description: Maximum number of NR beams included in B2-NR measurement report

Parameter name: Interval for periodical RSRP B2NR measurement reporting
Description: The RSRP based B2-NR event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval.    The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for RSRP based B2-NR event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: Time to trigger for RSRP B2-NR
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRP based B2-NR measurement must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Threshold1 of RSRP based B2-NR of serving cell
Description: Threshold1 for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP (own cell) based B2-NR measurement is activated, when RSRP of serving cell ? b2Threshold1RsrpNr and RSRP/RSRQ of NR neighbor cell ? b2Threshold2?RSRP, RSRQ?Nr (depending on b2NrMeasQuantity), RSRP based B2-NR event report is triggered and handover to NR may be triggered.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for NR    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold2 of B2-NR for RSRP of NR neighbour cell
Description: NR RSRP threshold for neighbor cell on NR frequency, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B2-NR event.  Applicable only if LNCEL-measQuantityNr="RSRP".  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for NR.  Parameter is optional depending on LNCEL-measQuantityNr.

Parameter name: Threshold2 of B2-NR for RSRQ of NR neighbour cell
Description: Threshold for neighbor cell on NR frequency, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B2-NR event.  Applicable only if LNCEL-measQuantityNr="RSRQ".  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for NR.  Parameter is optional depending on LNCEL-measQuantityNr.

Parameter name: NR carrier frequency
Description: Identifies the SSB frequency of NR carrier to be measured.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: NR Frequency Band Indicator List
Description: Indicates the list of NR frequency band in which the SSB and/or CSI-RS indicated in this NR frequency.  The NR frequency band is defined in TS 38.101.

Parameter name: Hysteresis for RSRP B2-NR
Description: Hysteresis for RSRP(Own cell) based B2-NR event for NR measurement.    The parameter is used in the entry and exit condition of event B2-NR triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: NR carrier priority for 5GCap mobility
Description: Priority of NR carrier for 5GSA mobility (e.g. redirection) measurement target selection.    A value of 1 means lowest, 64 is highest priority.

Parameter name: 5G HO neighbor relation NR-PCI counter decay factor
Description: Defines the NR carrier specific decay factor multiplier that is used to adjust the internal counter (nrPciHoCount) that tracks the number of times a particular NR PCI has been reported in measurement reports.  A value of 1.0000 would disable the hysteresis multiplier functionality for this NR carrier. See nrPciHoNbrRelAddThresh parameter for additional information on usage.

Parameter name: NR PCI neighbor relation addition threshold for 5G HO
Description: Defines the NR carrier specific threshold that when exceeded allows a particular PCI to be considered for automatic neighbor relation addition for 5G HO. The internal counter (nrPciHoCount maintained for each PCI-Carrier pair, initialized to zero) is incremented by 1 every time the specific PCI is encountered in a measurement report, for the specific carrier. The internal counter (nrPciHoCount) is multiplied by nrPciHoNbrCounterDecay every time the specific PCI is not encountered in a measurement report, for the specific carrier. When the internal counter (nrPciHoCount) value exceeds the nrPciHoNbrRelAddThresh for the specific carrier, the eNB will attempt to create a corresponding LNRELN neighbor relation, immediately or after NR-CGI procedure completion. A value of zero would disable the functionality for this NR carrier.

Parameter name: NR PCI neighbor relation removal threshold for 5G HO
