Description: Defines the NR carrier specific threshold that, when reached, allows LNRELN(s) corresponding to NR-PCI to be automatically removed. The internal counter (nrPciHoCount maintained for each NR-PCI/NR-Carrier pair) is multiplied by fractional value of nrPciHoNbrCounterDecay every time the specific NR-PCI is not encountered in a measurement report, for the specific NR-Carrier and incremented by 1 every time the specific NR-PCI is present in the measurement report. When the internal counter (nrPciHoCount) value drops below the nrPciHoNbrRelRemThresh for ANR-anrNrHoNbrRelRemGuardTime, the eNB will remove corresponding LNRELN(s). A value of zero disables the removal functionality for a particular NR-Carrier.

Parameter name: Quantity configuration set index for NR
Description: Specifies the index of nrQuantityConfig used for the NR carrier    The value of this parameter equals to quantityConfigId of one nrQuantityConfig instance in NRMEASDPR.

Parameter name: NR offset frequency
Description: Offset value applicable to the NR carrier frequency.  The IE Q-OffsetRangeInterRAT is used to indicate a frequency specific offset to be applied when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2-NR mobility parameters - Interval for periodical RSRQ B2NR measurement reporting
Description: The RSRQ based B2-NR event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval.    The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for RSRQ based B2-NR event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2-NR mobility parameters - Time to trigger for RSRQ B2-NR
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRQ based B2-NR measurement must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2-NR mobility parameters - Threshold1 of RSRQ based B2-NR of serving cell
Description: Threshold1 for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ based B2-NR measurement is activated, when RSRQ of serving cell ? b2Threshold1RsrqNr and RSRP/RSRQ of NR neighbor cell ? b2Threshold2?RSRP, RSRQ?Nr (depending on b2NrMeasQuantity), RSRQ based B2-NR event report is triggered and handover to NR may be triggered.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for NR    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: RSRQ B2-NR mobility parameters - Hysteresis for RSRQ B2-NR
Description: Hysteresis for RSRQ (Own cell) based B2-NR event for NR measurement.    The parameter is used in the entry and exit condition of event B2-NR triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Duration for SS/PBCH blocks
Description: Duration of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks. It is defined in number of subframes.

Parameter name: Offset for SS/PBCH blocks
Description: Offset in subframes, of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: Periodicity of SS/PBCH blocks
Description: Periodicity of the measurement window in which to receive SS/PBCH blocks.  Periodicity is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: SS/PBCH blocks Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier
Description: SS/PBCH blocks Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier

Parameter name: Neighbor TD-SCDMA BTS cell handover identifier
Description: Naming Attribute Of MOC LNHOT

Parameter name: Threshold CSFB to TD-SCDMA for PCCPCH-RSCP
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B1 event.  PCCPCH-RSCP is defined in TS 25.123 for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for TD-SCDMA.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.123:  * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm  * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

Parameter name: Time to trigger UTRA-CSFB measurement report
Description: Duration for which the RSRP based event B1 must be valid    Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRP based measurement event B1 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Threshold1 UTRA for RSRP of serving cell
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1Utra and RSCP of TD-SCDMA neighbor cell ? b2Threshold2UtraRscp,  then handover is triggered (B2 event)  Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event  type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  b2Threshold1Utra AND the TD-SCDMA neighbor cell becomes better than b2Threshold2UtraRscp.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for TD-SCDMA    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold2 RSCP for UTRA neighbor cell
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B2 event.  PCCPCH-RSCP corresponds to P-CCPCH_RSCP in TS 25.123 for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for TD-SCDMA.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.123:  * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm  * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

Parameter name: Time to trigger UTRA measurement report
Description: Duration for which the RSRP based event B2 must be valid  Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRP based measurement event B2 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold B1 for CSFB to TD-SCDMA
Description: Related Hysteresis of Margin for CSFB to TD-SCDMA    Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis thresholds B2Th1 ,B2Th2 HO TD-SCDMA
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for HO to TD-SCDMA  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Maximum number of CSFB target cells per frequency
Description: Defines the maximum number of target cells per frequency for CS fallback with PS-HO.  Setting this limit controls measurement object configuration and inhibits long measurement times.

Parameter name: Utran offset frequency
Description: Offset value applicable to the UTRA carrier frequency.  The IE Q-OffsetRangeInterRAT is used to indicate a frequency specific offset to be applied when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

Parameter name: Interval for periodical  UTRA measurement reporting
Description: The RSRP based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval  The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRP based event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: Utran carrier frequency
Description: Identifies UTRA carrier frequency for which this configuration is valid  The IE ARFCN-ValueUTRA is used to indicate the ARFCN applicable for a downlink (Nd, FDD) or bi-directional (Nt, TDD) UTRA carrier frequency

Parameter name: Neighbor WCDMA BTS cell handover identifier
Description: Naming Attribute Of MOC LNHOW  Instance Identifier of an WCDMA Handover Target

Parameter name: Threshold CSFB to UTRA-WCDMA for EcN0 neighbor cell
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency, considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B1 event.  Applicable only if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-EcN0.  cpich-EcN0 corresponds to CPICH_Ec/No in TS 25.133 for FDD only, and is not applicable for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityCSFBUtraFdd.    The dB value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -24 dB means a threshold lower than -24 dB  * values between -23.5 dB and 0 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 0.5 dB)  * 0.5 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 0 dB

Parameter name: Threshold CSFB to UTRA-WCDMA for RSCP neighbour cell
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency, considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B1 event.  Applicable only if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-RSCP.  cpich-RSCP corresponds to CPICH_RSCP in TS 25.133 for FDD, and P-CCPCH_RSCP in TS 25.123 for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityCSFBUtra.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm  * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold SRVCC to UTRA-WCDMA for EcN0 neighbor cell
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency for Voice Quality triggered SRVCC, considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B1 event.  Applicable only if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-EcN0.  cpich-EcN0 corresponds to CPICH_Ec/No in TS 25.133 for FDD only, and is not applicable for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityUtra.    The dB value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -24 dB means a threshold lower than -24 dB  * values between -23.5 dB and 0 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value 0.5 dB)  * 0.5 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 0 dB

Parameter name: Threshold SRVCC to UTRA-WCDMA for RSCP neighbor cell
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency for Voice Quality triggered SRVCC, considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B1 event.  Applicable only if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-RSCP.  cpich-RSCP corresponds to CPICH_RSCP in TS 25.133 for FDD, and P-CCPCH_RSCP in TS 25.123 for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityUtra.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm  * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

Parameter name: Time to trigger UTRA-CSFB measurement report
Description: Duration for which the RSRP based event B1 must be valid. For further important notice see the Additional Description.    Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRP based measurement event B1 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.    Important Note: Since the B1 event for the purpose of CSFB shall be reported by the UE as fast as possible not the full range of up to 5120 ms for TTT shall be applicable. Recommended value would be up to and not higher than 256 ms. Hence the range is restricted.

Parameter name: Time to trigger UTRA-SRVCC measurement report
Description: Duration for which the Voice quality (VQ) based event B1 must be valid.  Time for which the specific criteria for the VQ based measurement event B1 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 UTRA mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 UTRA threshold1
Description: Threshold1 for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ of serving cell is less than b2Threshold1RsrqUtra, then the first entering condition of the B2 event is fulfilled.  If also for the second entering condition the measurement results of RSCP or EcN0 of WCDMA neighbor cell are greater than b2Threshold2UtraRscp or b2Threshold2UtraEcn0 (depending on the configured quantity)  then handover is triggered.    The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 UTRA mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 UTRA threshold1 during QCI1
Description: Threshold1 for RSRQ of serving cell for B2-UTRA event when UE has QCI1 bearer. If RSRQ of serving cell is less than b2Threshold1RsrqUtraQci1, then the first entering condition of the B2 event is fulfilled.  If also for the second entering condition the measurement results of RSCP or EcN0 of WCDMA neighbor cell are greater than b2Threshold2UtraRscp or b2Threshold2UtraEcn0 (depending on the configured quantity) then handover is triggered.  The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: Threshold1 UTRA for RSRP of serving cell
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1Utra and RSCP or EcN of WCDMA neighbor cell ? b2Threshold2Utra?EcNo, Rscp?  then handover is triggered (B2 event)  Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event  type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  b2Threshold1Utra AND the WCDMA neighbor cell becomes better than b2Threshold2Utra?EcNo, Rscp? (dep. measQuantityUtra).  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold1 UTRA for RSRP of serving cell during QCI1
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell when UE has QCI1 bearer. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1UtraQci1 and RSCP or EcN0 of WCDMA neighbor cell ? b2Threshold2Utra?EcN0, Rscp?Qci1  then handover is triggered (B2 event).  Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event when UE has QCI1 bearer. Used in measurement event  type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  b2Threshold1UtraQci1 AND the WCDMA neighbor cell becomes better than b2Threshold2Utra?EcN0, Rscp?Qci1 (dep. measQuantityUtraFdd).  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold2 UTRA for ecNo neighbor cell
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B2 event.  Applicable only if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-EcN0.  cpich-EcN0 corresponds to CPICH_Ec/No in TS 25.133 for FDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityUtra.    The dB value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -24 dB means a threshold lower than -24 dB  * values between -23.5 dB and 0 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 0.5 dB)  * 0.5 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 0 dB

Parameter name: Threshold2 UTRA for ecNo neighbor cell during QCI1
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency when UE has a QCI1 bearer, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B2 event.    Applicable only when UE has QCI1 bearer and if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-EcN0.  cpich-EcN0 corresponds to CPICH_Ec/No in TS 25.133 for FDD only, and is not applicable for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityUtra.    The dB value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -24 dB means a threshold lower than -24 dB  * values between -23.5 dB and 0 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 0.5 dB)  * 0.5 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 0 dB

Parameter name: Threshold2 UTRA for RSCP neighbor cell
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B2 event.  Applicable only if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-RSCP.  cpich-RSCP corresponds to CPICH_RSCP in TS 25.133 for FDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityUtra.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm  * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

Parameter name: Threshold2 UTRA for RSCP neighbor cell during QCI1
Description: Threshold for UTRA neighbor cell on the current frequency when UE has QCI1 bearer, such that it is considered to be good and reported in the measurement result of B2 event.    Applicable only when UE has QCI1 bearer and if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-RSCP.  cpich-RSCP corresponds to CPICH_RSCP in TS 25.133 for FDD, and P-CCPCH_RSCP in TS 25.123 for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityUtraFdd.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm  * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 UTRA mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 UTRA time to trigger
Description: Duration for which the RSRQ based event B2 must be valid.  Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRQ based measurement event B2 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Time to trigger UTRA measurement report
Description: Duration for which the RSRP based event B2 must be valid    Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRP based measurement event B2 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold B1 for CSFB to WCDMA
Description: Related Hysteresis of Margin for CSFB to WCDMA    Parameter is used within the entry and leaves condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of threshold B1 for SRVCC to WCDMA
Description: Related Hysteresis of Margin for Voice Quality triggered SRVCC to WCDMA    Parameter is used within the entry and leaves condition of the B1 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 UTRA mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 UTRA hysteresis
Description: Related hysteresis of handover margin for HO to WCDMA applied to the first (threshold1) and second (threshold2) entering and leaving condition.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the RSRQ based B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis thresholds B2Th1, B2Th2 HO WCDMA
Description: Related Hysteresis of Handover Margin for HO to WCDMA  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Maximum number of CSFB target cells per frequency
Description: Defines the maximum number of target cells per frequency for CS fallback with PS-HO.  Setting this limit controls measurement object configuration and inhibits long measurement times.

Parameter name: Utran offset frequency
Description: Offset value applicable to the UTRA carrier frequency.  The IE Q-OffsetRangeInterRAT is used to indicate a frequency specific offset to be applied when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 UTRA mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 UTRA report interval
Description: The RSRQ based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval.    The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRQ based event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: Interval for periodical UTRA measurement reporting
Description: The RSRP based B2 or Voice Quality based B1 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval  The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRP or Voice Quality based B1 based event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: EcN0 threshold for load bal. handover to UTRAN
Description: Threshold for filtering target cells out of reported B1 events based on EcN0 values due to LTE-UTRAN load balancing  Applicable only if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-EcN0.  cpich-EcN0 corresponds to CPICH_Ec/No in TS 25.133 for FDD only, and is not applicable for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityUtraFdd.    The dB value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -24 dB means a threshold lower than -24 dB  * values between -23.5 dB and 0 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 0.5 dB)  * 0.5 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 0 dB

Parameter name: RSCP threshold for load bal. handover to UTRAN
Description: Threshold for filtering target cells out of reported B1 events based on RSCP values due to LTE-UTRAN load balancing  Applicable only if measQuantityUTRA-FDD=cpich-RSCP.  cpich-RSCP corresponds to CPICH_RSCP in TS 25.133 for FDD, and P-CCPCH_RSCP in TS 25.123 for TDD.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for WCDMA.  Parameter is optional depending on measQuantityUtraFdd.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 25.133:  * -120 dBm means a threshold lower than -120 dBm  * values between -119 dBm and -25 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -24 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -25 dBm

Parameter name: UTRAN carrier frequency
Description: Identifies UTRA carrier frequency for which this configuration is valid  The IE ARFCN-ValueUTRA is used to indicate the ARFCN applicable for a downlink (Nd, FDD) or bi-directional (Nt, TDD) UTRA carrier frequency

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor cell handover identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute Of MOC LNHOX.  It uniquely identifies a LNHOX instance.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 1XRTT mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 1XRTT threshold1
Description: Threshold1 for RSRQ of serving cell. If RSRQ of serving cell is less than b2Threshold1RsrqRtt, then the first entering condition of the B2 event is fulfilled.  If also for the second entering condition the measurement results of pilot strength of CDMA2000-1XRTT neighbor cell is greater than b2Threshold2PstrRtt, then handover is triggered.  The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: CDMA2000 SRVCC to 1xRTT measurement configuration - Threshold1 CDMA2000-1XRTT for RSRP of serving cell
Description: Threshold for RSRP of serving cell. If RSRP of serving value ? b2Threshold1Rtt and pilotStrength of 1XRTT neighbor cell ? b2Threshold2PstrRtt  then handover is triggered (B2 event)    Receive level threshold for serving cell in B2 event. Used in measurement event  type B2 where the event is triggered if the serving cell becomes worse than  b2Threshold1Rtt AND the 1XRTT neighbor cell becomes better than b2Threshold2PstrRtt.  Set in ReportConfigInterRAT for CDMA2000-1XRTT.  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: CDMA2000 SRVCC to 1xRTT measurement configuration - Threshold2 CDMA2000 for 1XRTT neighbour cell
Description: CDMA2000 pilot strength threshold for 1XRTT SRVCC measurements, the ratio of pilot power to total power in the signal bandwidth of a CDMA2000 forward channel.  See C.S0005-A (section 2.6.6.2.2) for CDMA2000 1xRTT.      The pilotStrength of 1XRTT SRVCC maps onto the 3GPP parameter b2-Threshold2CDMA2000 with 0 as the strongest and with 63 (-31.5 dB) as the weakest pilot strength.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 1XRTT mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 1XRTT time to trigger
Description: Duration for which the RSRQ based event B2 must be valid.  Time for which the specific criteria for the RSRQ based measurement event B2 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 SRVCC to 1xRTT measurement configuration - Time to trigger CDMA2000-1XRTT measurement report
Description: Time during which specific criteria for the RSRP&Pstr based measurement event B2 needs to be met in order to trigger a measurement report.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 1XRTT mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 1XRTT hysteresis
Description: Related hysteresis of handover margin for HO to CDMA2000-1XRTT applied to the first (threshold1) and second (threshold2) entering and leaving condition.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the RSRQ based B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 SRVCC to 1xRTT measurement configuration - Related hysteresis of CDMA2000-1XRTT B2Th1 and B2Th2
Description: Related hysteresis of handover margin for HO to CDMA2000-1XRTT    Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the B2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 SRVCC to 1xRTT measurement configuration - CDMA2000 1XRTT frequency specific offset
Description: Offset value applicable to the 1XRTT carrier frequency.    The IE Q-OffsetRangeInterRAT is used to indicate a frequency specific offset to be applied when evaluating triggering conditions for measurement reporting.

Parameter name: RSRQ B2 1XRTT mobility parameters - RSRQ B2 1XRTT report interval
Description: The RSRQ based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval.  The ReportInterval indicates the interval between periodical reports. The ReportInterval is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRQ based event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 SRVCC to 1xRTT measurement configuration - Interval for periodical CDMA2000-1XRTT meas reporting
Description: The RSRP&Pstr based B2 event triggers the UE to perform periodical reporting with the indicated interval    reportIntervalRtt indicates the interval between periodical reports. It is applicable if the UE performs periodical reporting for B2 RSRP&Pstr based event.  Value ms120 corresponds with 120 ms, ms240 corresponds with 240 ms and so on, while value min1 corresponds with 1 min, min6 corresponds with 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1XRTT carrier frequency - CDMA2000 1XRTT ARFCN
Description: Absolute Radio Frequency Number of CDMA2000 1XRTT carrier frequency  The CDMA2000 ARFCN used to indicate the CDMA2000 carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 band, see C.S0002-A.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1XRTT carrier frequency - CDMA2000 1XRTT band class
Description: Band Class of CDMA2000 1XRTT carrier frequency  The CDMA2000 band class is used to define the CDMA2000 band in which the CDMA2000 carrier frequency can be found, as defined in C.S0057-E [table 1.5-1].  Note: Bandclasses 18, 19, 20 and 21 are not supported by this release.

Parameter name: Maximum number of e1xCSFB target cells per frequency
Description: Defines the maximum number of target cells per frequency for enhanced CSFB to CDMA2000 1xRTT  Setting this limit controls measurement object configuration and inhibits long measurement times.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1XRTT search Window size
Description: Provides the search window size to be used by the UE for the neighboring pilot, see C.S0005-A.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT strength  threshold
Description: Defines the pilot strength threshold for enhanced CSFB to CDMA2000 1xRTT.  In 3GPP TS36.331, pilotStrength's range is [0 .. 63] which is different from current value range of parameter "rttStrengthThresh". The reason is that : in future phase 2 e1xCsfb feature, this parameter may be re-used as AggregatedThreshold which include strengths from multiple PNs and AggregatedThreshold 's value range is [-18 .. 63].    The formula used by the UE to report the pilot strength is [ -2 * 10 * log (measured pilot strength) ].  Therefore 63 maps to -31.5 dB. So [-18..63] maps to [9..-31.5] dB.

Parameter name: LTE MME M3 link identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC LNM3.  It uniquely identifies a LNM3 instance.

Parameter name: Administrative state
Description: Administrative state of the M3 link.  This parameter is used to lock and unlock the LNM3 M3 link. Locking LNM3 means closing the SCTP association between eNB and MME. All MBSFN will be deactivated if this is the last LNM3 being locked.  Unlocking LNM3 triggers SCTP association establishment and M3AP Setup procedure.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: M3 Link Status
Description: The parameter provides information whether the M3 link is successfully established.

Parameter name: M3 primary address
Description: This parameter holds the transport network IPv4/IPv6 address of the Mobility Management Entity (MME) primary M3 interface.    Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or an IPv6 address acc. to RFC4291.    Note: For FZM eNBs, only IPv4 addresses are supported on the M3 interface and are allowed to be configured. For AirScale and FSMr3 eNBs, both IPv4 and IPv6 are supported on the M3 interface and are allowed to be configured.

Parameter name: M3 Secondary address
Description: Secondary Application IP address of the Mobility Management Entity (MME) M3 interface if multihoming feature is enabled.    Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or an IPv6 address acc. to RFC4291.    This address field is a Read-Only field.

Parameter name: Multi-cell multicast coordination entity identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC LNMCE.  It uniquely identifies a LNMCE instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: M3 link bounce supervision  timer
Description: This parameter holds the timer value for M3 link supervision after link down condition is detected by lower layers. A value of zero indicates no timer is started.

Parameter name: M3 time reference
Description: Represents the time reference used for M3 interface.  This parameter reflects the time reference used by the BM-SC over the M3 interface.

Parameter name: MCE Identity
Description: This identifier along with primary PLMN is used to globally identify a unique MCE (Global MCE ID).    The MCE Id is derived from the lnBTSId.

Parameter name: MCE Name
Description: This is a human-readable name for the MCE. It corresponds to the MCE Name according to 3GPP 36.444.  The character set is restricted to Printable string according to 3GPP with following supported characters:  lower case letters 'a' through 'z', upper case letters 'A' through 'Z', the digits '0' through '9' and the characters ' = ( ) + , - . / : ? and space.

Parameter name: MBMS service area characteristics
Description: Represents the MBMS Service Area Characteristics.  This structure is not for the use of eNB.

Parameter name: MBMS service area FEC
Description: Indicates the FEC for the MBMS Service Area.  This parameter specifies the recommended Forward Error Correction (FEC) overhead that can be applied on this MBMS Service Area.

Parameter name: MBMS service area Id
Description: Indicates the Identity of the MBMS Service Area.  This parameter assigns the MBMS Service Area identity for which the regional business operational team will define some characteristics.

Parameter name: MBMS service area maximum bit rate
Description: Indicates the maximum bit rate for the MBMS Service Area.  This parameter specifies the maximum bit rate supported by the MBMS Service Area identity for the sum of the sessions which will be mapped on it.

Parameter name: MBMS service area maximum session bit rate
Description: Indicates the maximum session bit rate for the MBMS Service Area.  This parameter specifies the maximum bit rate that can be affected to a session for a given MBMS Service Area Identity.

Parameter name: LTE mobility management entity identifier
Description: Parameter lnMmeId is the naming attribute of the MOC LNMME.  It uniquely identifies a LNMME instance.

Parameter name: Accumulated list of MME served PLMNs
Description: The "Accumulated MME served PLMNs" list includes all PLMN IDs which are served by MME.

Parameter name: MCC of PLMN ID in served PLMNs per RAT of MME
Description: Mobile Country Code of PLMN ID included in served PLMNs per RAT of MME. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: MNC of PLMN ID in served PLMNs per RAT of MME
Description: Mobile Network Code of PLMN ID included in served PLMNs per RAT of MME. MCC and MNC build a unique PLMN ID.

Parameter name: Administrative state
Description: Administrative state of the LNMME S1 link.  This parameter is used to lock and unlock the LNMME S1 link. Locking LNMME means closing the SCTP association between eNB and MME. All impacted UEs in RRC connected mode will be released.  Unlocking LNMME triggers SCTP association establishment and S1AP Setup procedure.  If feature 'S1 Flex' is not activated, only the S1 link of LNMME instance 0 will be supported.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Exclude MME from EN-DC SON configuration transfer
Description: This parameter indicates if EN-DC SON configuration transfer procedure could be initiated for the MME or the MME is excluded from the procedure. When this parameter is set to true, the eNB will not send S1AP: ENB CONFIGURATION TRANSFER messages with the EN-DC SON Configuration Transfer IE towards this MME. Note that MMEs not supporting Wideband-LTE are assumed to not support the EN-DC SON Configuration Transfer procedure. When this parameter is not defined, only MMEs with mmeRatSupport set to NB-IoT are internally excluded from EN-DC SON configuration transfer procedure.    Hint: the modification on LNMME-excludeEndcSonConfTrans requests manually lock/unlock LNMME instance to take effect. Note 1: Setting LNMME administrativeState to 'locked' triggers S1 link deactivation. Setting LNMME administrativeState to 'unlocked' triggers S1 link activation. Note 2: eNB does not prevent the change of excludeEndcSonConfTrans on an unlocked MME.

Parameter name: Primary IPv4/v6 address
Description: This parameter holds the transport network IPv4/v6 address of the Mobility Management Entity (MME) primary interface.  Both IP address formats can be used.  Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter acc. to RFC 4291.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).    IPv6 address ranges:  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).

Parameter name: Secondary IPv4/v6 address
Description: Secondary application IPv4/v6 address of the Mobility Management Entity (MME) if multihoming feature is enabled.  This address field is a Read-Only field.    Format: exclusive IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or exclusive IPv6 address parameter acc. to RFC4291.

Parameter name: MME name
Description: This is a human readable name of the MME.

Parameter name: MME RAT support
Description: Indicates that Radio Access Technology can be supported by MME.  Hint: the modification on LNMME - mmeRatSupport requests manually lock/unlock LNMME instance to take effect. Note 1: Setting LNMME administrativeState to 'locked' triggers S1 link deactivation. Setting LNMME administrativeState to 'unlocked' triggers S1 link activation. Note 2: eNB does not prevent the change of mmeRatSupport on an unlocked MME.

Parameter name: Relative MME capacity
Description: This parameter indicates the relative MME capacity assigned to the MME.

Parameter name: Reachable PLMNs for RIM
Description: List of PLMNs which are reachable for RIM in addition to the served PLMNs for any RAT.    If the parameter is omitted, only served PLMNs are reachable via the MME.    The list currently only applies for RIM to WCDMA neighbor cells.

Parameter name: MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code which is part of the PLMN Id.

Parameter name: MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code which is part of the PLMN Id.

Parameter name: MNC length
Description: Length of Mobile Network Code (MNC) in digits.

Parameter name: S1 link status
Description: The parameter provides information whether the S1 link is successfully established.

Parameter name: Transport network identifier
Description: This parameter holds the identifier for the transport network to which the MME belongs.    The operator must take care that transportNwId of LNMME instance 0 (main MME) is identical to mainTransportNwId in LNBTS.

Parameter name: Neighborship identifierHRPD
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a LNNEIH instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: HRPD ARFCN
Description: Absolute Radio Frequency Number of CDMA2000 eHRPD carrier frequency  The CDMA2000 ARFCN used to indicate the CDMA2000 carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 band, see C.S0002-A.

Parameter name: HRPD Band Class
Description: Band Class of CDMA2000 eHRPD carrier frequency  The CDMA2000 band class is used to define the CDMA2000 band in which the CDMA2000 carrier frequency can be found, as defined in C.S0057-E [table 1.5-1].  Note: Bandclasses 18, 19, 20 and 21 are not supported by this release.

Parameter name: HRPD PN Offset
Description: Defines the Pseudo-Random Noise (PN) offset of this CDMA2000 HRPD neighbor cell.

Parameter name: HRPD SectorID
Description: This parameter contains the HRPD Sector ID used for HRPD handover preparation/execution and defined as specified in 3GPP2 C.S0024-A.    The parameter must be added as character string in hexadecimal notation with leading '0x'.  It is used to populate the CDMA2000 sector ID (128 bits) using hexadecimal characters.    In addition to the leading '0x' it shall only contain hexadecimal characters '0' to '9', 'A' to 'F', 'a' to 'f'.    The format of Sector ID equals the format of an IPv6 address but without colons.

Parameter name: PS Handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: LTE neighbor relation identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC LNREL.  It uniquely identifies a LNREL instance.  It is highly recommended to use for object creation the lowest free lnRelId value within all LNREL instances subordinate to an LNCEL object. This is to avoid rejection of plan file activation due to colliding lnRelId values if an LNREL instance is automatically created by eNB because of activated ANR features.

Parameter name: Active mode load equalization allowed
Description: This parameter indicates, if the neighbor cell referenced by this relation is an allowed partner cell for active mode load equalization.

Parameter name: Cell individual offsets of other neighbor cells
Description: Cell Individual Offset (CIO) of Neighbor cells for insertion into the CIO Cell List of EUTRA Serving or Neighbor Carrier Measurement Object.    All CIOs different from zero will be considered by eNB for Measurement Configuration (up to a limit of 32 CIOs per carrier frequency).

Parameter name: Cell individual offset delta for load balancing
Description: The parameter provides the delta value, which is temporarily added to the operator configured cell individual offset (LNREL parameter cellIndOffNeigh) for load balancing reasons.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Identity of eNB in ECGI of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter is the Macro eNB identifier which is part of the E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (ECGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Identity of cell in ECGI of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter is the cell identifier, which is part of the E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (ECGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls handover blacklisting. The instance of LNREL and the related cell relationship, defined by ECGI, identifies the specific cell to cell relation. The parameter allows HO for this neighbor relation, only S1 HO or no HO at all.  The blacklisting applies in addition to blacklisting via the LNCEL parameter blacklistHoL.    The meaning is as follows:  'allowed' means that any S1 or X2 outgoing handover is allowed.  'onlyS1' means that outgoing handover via S1 is allowed but not via X2.  'forbidden' means that no outgoing S1 or X2 handover is triggered.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN ID of eNB in ECGI of related neighbor cell - MCC in primary PLMN identity
Description: Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (ECGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN ID of eNB in ECGI of related neighbor cell - MNC in primary PLMN identity
Description: Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the E-UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (ECGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of managed object.

Parameter name: Neighbor relation control
Description: The parameter coordinates the access to parameter handoverAllowed, i.e. whether handover blacklisting setting at this instance of LNREL and the related cell relationship, is only allowed to be done manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct

Parameter name: Neighbor relation status
Description: Indicates the status of the neighbor relation.    unavailable:  Indicates that the neighbor relation is not considered for HO (e.g. because neighbor cell information is not available).    available:  Indicates that the neighbor relation is considered for HO if not blacklisted, i.e. if handoverAllowed is not set to 'forbidden'.    invalid:  Indicates that the neighbor relation is considered as not reliable because a CGI measurement reported a different CGI for the PCI of the neighbor cell the neighbor relation refers to or because eNB detected a conflict with another existing neighbor relation. [LTE2466 updated]  Invalid may also indicate that the neighbor relation is not considered as it is a CSG or Hybrid cell.  The nrStatus of a blacklisted neighbor relation may be nevertheless 'available'. This indicates that all information for HO is available and HO would be in principle possible if blacklisting would be released.    LNREL instances with nrStatus 'unavailable' or 'invalid'  - do not contribute to the limit which is configured with ANRPRL parameters nrLimitIntraFreq or nrLimitInterFreq  - are not counted for triggering X2-link establishment

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Remove allowed
Description: Inhibits autonomous removal of the neighbor relation by eNB.

Parameter name: Target cell DN
Description: Pointer to the adjacency target LTE cell or external LTE cell (EXEUCE). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object. Parameter used and visible only in NetAct Advanced Configurator.

Parameter name: GERAN neighbor relation identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a LNRELG instance.

Parameter name: ARFCN value geran
Description: ARFCN Value of the GERAN neighbour cell  (Part of CarrierFrequency)

Parameter name: Basestation colour code
Description: BaseStation Colour Code of GERAN neighbour cell    (Part of PhysicalCellId)

Parameter name: Cell identity
Description: Cell Identity of GERAN neighbor cell which is part of the GERAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DTM capability
Description: This parameter indicates whether the GERAN target cell is DTM capable. This information is evaluated during SRVCC to GERAN when deciding whether the UE will be available for PS service

Parameter name: ENACC allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether Network Assisted Cell Change to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: RAC GERAN
Description: Routing Areas Code (RAC) of GERAN neighbor cell.    Hint: The RAC value is needed for establishing a RIM association, that is no RIM association will be established if the value is omitted even if the feature  LTE498: RAN Information Management for GSM is activated.

Parameter name: Location Area Code
Description: LAC of GERAN neighbor cell which is part of the GERAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.  used as described in TS36.413 section 9.2.1.6    "0000 and FFFE not allowed."

Parameter name: PLMN Identity in CGI of GERAN neighbor cell - MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the PLMN ID, which is part of the GERAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: PLMN Identity in CGI of GERAN neighbor cell - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code (MNC) of the PLMN ID, which is part of the GERAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of target GSM cell (BTS/foreign BTS managed object) that is copied and updated automatically from target cell during Plan Prepare.

Parameter name: Network colour code
Description: Network Colour Code of GERAN neighbour cell    (Part of PhysicalCellId)

Parameter name: Neighbor relation control
Description: The parameter coordinates the access to mobility-feature whitelist parameters (type: *Allowed), that is whether handover blacklisting setting at this instance of LNRELG and the related cell relationship, is only allowed to be done manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct Optimizer Features. NetAct ANR features consider this setting accordingly. The Operator might consider the setting.  The parameter is for NetAct usage only. It is not evaluated by eNB.

Parameter name: Redirect with system information allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether the related neighbor cell is a candidate for providing system information in case of UE redirection to GERAN.  If system information is not configured in the related LNADJG object at least the frequency of the cell will be provided in the redirection information.

Parameter name: Single radio voice call continuity allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether SRVCC handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Target cell DN
Description: Pointer to the adjacency target BTS or external GERAN cell (EXGCE). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object.

Parameter name: New Radio neighbor relation cell identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC LNRELGNBCELL.  It uniquely identifies a LNRELGNBCELL instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Length of gnbId within nrCellId
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the gNB-Identifier included in the New Radio Cell Identifier of the neighbor cell served by en-gNB.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving NR cell activation blocked
Description: If this parameter is 'true' then EN-DC Cell Activation reattempts are blocked.

Parameter name: LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC) allowed
Description: The parameter controls, if LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC) for the NR neighbor cell referenced by the 'New Radio Neighbor Relation (NR-NRel)' is allowed. It is part of the New Radio Cell Global Identifier (NR-CGI).

Parameter name: Primary PLMN ID of en-gNB in NR-CGI of related neighbor NR-cell - MCC in primary PLMN identity
Description: Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the NR Cell Global Identifier (NR-CGI) of the related neighbor NR-cell. It is part of the New Radio Cell Global Identifier (NR-CGI).

Parameter name: Primary PLMN ID of en-gNB in NR-CGI of related neighbor NR-cell - MNC in primary PLMN identity
Description: Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the New Radio Cell Global Identifier (NR-CGI) of the related neighbor NR-cell.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN ID of en-gNB in NR-CGI of related neighbor NR-cell - MNC length in primary PLMN identity
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC. It is part of the New Radio Cell Global Identifier (NR-CGI).

Parameter name: New Radio global cell identifier
Description: This parameter is the New Radio Cell Identifier, which is part of the New Radio Global Cell Identifier (NR-CGI) of the neighbor cell served by en-gNB.

Parameter name: Neighbor relation status
Description: Indicates the status of the neighbour relation.    unavailable:  Indicates that the neighbour relation is not available for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC). E.g. because X2 links to gNB or neighbor cell information is not available.    available:  Indicates that the neighbour relation is available for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC), i.e. X2 link to gNB is available and neighbor cell information is available.

Parameter name: power saving deactivation indication
Description: The parameter set to 'true' indicates power saving deactivated NR cells.

Parameter name: Remove allowed
Description: Inhibits autonomous removal of the NR neighbor relation by eNB.

Parameter name: Source of data
Description: The parameter provides information whether the object creation or latest update was based on plan file (OM), or UE specific ANR measurements (UE).

Parameter name: Target cell DN
Description: Pointer to the adjacency target NRBTS cell or external NRBTS cell (EXNRCE). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object. Parameter used and visible only in NetAct Advanced Configurator.

Parameter name: NR neighbor relation identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of the object LNRELN. This parameter appears only in the distinguished name (DN) in the plan file and is used for O&M purposes.

Parameter name: New Radio global cell identifier
Description: This parameter is the New Radio Cell Identifier, which is part of the New Radio Global Cell Identifier (NR-CGI) of the logical neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: PLMN identity in CGI of NR neighbor cell - MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the PLMN-ID in NR CGI

Parameter name: PLMN identity in CGI of NR neighbor cell - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the PLMN-ID in NR CGI

Parameter name: PLMN identity in CGI of NR neighbor cell - MNC length
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC.

Parameter name: PS handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Remove allowed
Description: Inhibits autonomous removal of the NR neighbor relation by eNB.

Parameter name: TD-SCDMA neighbor relation identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a LNRELT instance.  It is highly recommended to use for object creation the lowest free lnRelTId value within all LNRELT instances subordinate to an LNCEL object. This is to avoid rejection of plan file activation due to colliding lnRelTId values if an LNRELT instance is automatically created by eNB because of activated ANR features.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Circuit switched fallback with PS handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether CSFB with PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity in CGI of UTRAN neighbor cell - MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.  Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the UTRAN (TD-SCDMA) Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity in CGI of UTRAN neighbor cell - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Neighbor Relation Control
Description: The parameter coordinates the access to mobility-feature whitelist parameters (type: *Allowed), i.e. whether handover blacklisting setting at this instance of LNRELT and the related cell relationship, is only allowed to be done manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct Optimizer Features. NetAct ANR features shall consider this setting accordingly. The Operator may consider the setting.  The parameter is for NetAct usage only. It is not evaluated by eNB.

Parameter name: PS Handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Last change origin - Reason for change
Description: Defines the reason for the modification.

Parameter name: Last change origin - Time stamp
Description: Defines the time when the modification has been done by eNB.

Parameter name: Target cell Id in UTRAN CGI of related neighbor cell
Description: This parameter is the UTRAN C-ID which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniquely identifies a neighboring cell within the RNC.

Parameter name: Target RNC Id
Description: This parameter is the UTRAN RNC identifier which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniquely identifies of a neighboring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN.

Parameter name: WCDMA neighbor relation identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a LNRELW instance.  It is highly recommended to use for object creation the lowest free lnRelWId value within all LNRELW instances subordinate to an LNCEL object. This is to avoid rejection of plan file activation due to colliding lnRelWId values if an LNRELW instance is automatically created by eNB because of activated ANR features.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Circuit-switched fallback with PS handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether CSFB with PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity in CGI of UTRAN neighbor cell - MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN identity in CGI of UTRAN neighbor cell - MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code of the primary PLMN ID, which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Name
Description: Name of target WCDMA cell (WCEL/EWCE managed object) that is copied and updated automatically from target cell during Plan Prepare.

Parameter name: Neighbor relation control
Description: The parameter coordinates the access to mobility-feature whitelist parameters (type: *Allowed), that is whether handover blacklisting setting at this instance of LNRELW and the related cell relationship, is only allowed to be done manually by the operator or also automatically by NetAct Optimizer Features. NetAct ANR features consider this setting accordingly. The Operator might consider the setting.  The parameter is for NetAct usage only. It is not evaluated by eNB.

Parameter name: Neighbor relation status
Description: Indicates the status of the neighbor relation.  unavailable: neighbor relation is not considered for HO  available: neighbor relation is considered for HO if not blacklisted.  invalid: the neighbor relation is considered as not reliable because a CGI measurement reported a different CGI for the primary scrambling code of the neighbor cell the neighbor relation refers to or because eNB detected a conflict with another existing neighbor relation.  The nrStatus of a blacklisted neighbor relation may be nevertheless 'available'. This indicates that all information for HO is available and HO would be in principle possible if blacklisting would be released.  LNRELW instances with nrStatus 'unavailable' or 'invalid' do not contribute to the limit which is configured with ANRPRW parameter lnRelWLimitForAnr

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: PS handover allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether PS handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Redirect with system information allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether the related neighbor cell shall be a candidate for providing system information in case of UE redirection to UTRAN.

Parameter name: Remove allowed
Description: Inhibits autonomous removal of the neighbor relation by eNB

Parameter name: Single radio voice call continuity allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether SRVCC handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Target cell DN
Description: Pointer to the adjacency target WCEL or external UTRAN cell (EWCE/EXUCE). Distinguished Name of the corresponding object.

Parameter name: Target cell Id in UTRAN CGI of related neighbor cell
Description: UTRAN Cell-ID which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniquely identifies a neighboring cell within the RNC.  The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either  - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or  - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).

Parameter name: Target frequency
Description: Target Frequency provides the DL Carrier Frequency of the neighbouring UTRAN cell.

Parameter name: Target location area code
Description: Provides the Location Area Code identifying the Location Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell.

Parameter name: Target routing area code
Description: Provides the Routing Area Code identifying the Routing Area of a neighbouring UTRAN cell.

Parameter name: Target RNC Id
Description: UTRAN RNC identifier which is part of the UTRAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell. It uniquely identifies of a neighboring UTRAN RNC within the primary PLMN.    Values in the range of 4096 .. 65535 are considered as Extended RNC-ID.  The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either  - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or  - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).

Parameter name: Primary scrambling code (FDD)
Description: Primary Scrambling Code (FDD) Of The Neighbouring UTRAN Cell  UtranTarget_SC_FDD: The primary scrambling code (FDD) of the neighbouring UTRAN cell. Received from RRM-CMC in the TCL, which together with the cell frequency identifies a neighbouring UTRAN cell

Parameter name: LTE-UTRAN load balancing allowed
Description: This parameter indicates, if the UTRAN neighbor cell referenced by this relation is an allowed partner cell for LTE-UTRAN load balancing.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor relation identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC LNRELX.  It uniquely identifies a LNRELX instance.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x carrier frequency
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) carrier frequency of this 1xRTT neighbor cell.  The CDMA2000 ARFCN used to indicate the CDMA2000 carrier frequency within a CDMA2000 band, see C.S0002-A.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x band class
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) band class of this 1xRTT neighbor cell.  The CDMA2000 band class is used to define the CDMA2000 band in which the CDMA2000 carrier frequency can be found, as defined in C.S0057-E [table 1.5-1].

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x cell ID
Description: Defines the cell number of this CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) neighbor cell

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: E1xCSFB allowed
Description: Define whether the CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor cell could be used for 1xRTT measure configuration for e1xCSFB.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x market ID
Description: Defines the market identifier of the CBSC for this CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x PN offset
Description: Defines the Pseudo-Random Noise (PN) offset of this CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Remove allowed
Description: Inhibits autonomous removal of the 1xRTT neighbor relation by eNB

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x sector ID
Description: Defines the sector number of this CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Single radio voice call continuity allowed
Description: The parameter controls whether SRVCC handover to the related neighbor cell is allowed.

Parameter name: Neighbor 1x switch number
Description: Defines the switching number of this CDMA2000 1xRTT neighbor cell.

Parameter name: Satellite eNB set identifier
Description: Uniquely identifies a LNSENB instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Peer eNB using secondary IPSec tunnel via sat link
Description: This parameter indicates whether an eNodeB shall assume that its peer eNodeB has switched to secondary IPSec backup tunnel via satellite backhaul when compensating satellite backhaul delay in handover supervision timers.

Parameter name: Satellite backhaul one way delay
Description: One way propagation delay for satellite backhaul link from eNB to the core network

Parameter name: Satellite backhaul eNB Id ranges
Description: eNB IDs which are reserved for eNBs having satellite backhaul  Please note that activation of the feature with the parameter actSatBackhaul does not necessarily mean that the eNB itself is connected via satellite backhaul. If so, the eNB ID (LNBTS-lnBtsId) must be also included in this list.

Parameter name: First eNB Id in the range
Description: First eNB ID in the range of eNB IDs with satellite backhaul

Parameter name: Last eNB Id in the range
Description: Last eNB ID in the range of eNB IDs with satellite backhaul  In case of a single eNB ID, the last eNB ID is the same as the first eNB ID

Parameter name: MCC in primary PLMN identity
Description: Mobile country code in the primary PLMN ID. MCC and MNC build the PLMN ID

Parameter name: MNC in primary PLMN identity
Description: Mobile network code in the primary PLMN ID. MCC and MNC build the PLMN ID

Parameter name: MNC length in primary PLMN identity
Description: The MNC length determines the length of MNC in the primary PLMN ID

Parameter name: The instance identifier of LNUPR
Description: This parameter identifies the LNUPR instance.

Parameter name: Unlicensed radio antenna gain
Description: This parameter defines the antenna gain of the unlicensed radio a cell is connected to when linked to this instance of LNUPR.

Parameter name: Offset for the average CCA failure rate
Description: This parameter defines the offset, by which the average CCA failure rate of an alternative LAA channel set must be minimum smaller than the one of the LAA channel set currently in use by the LP-RRH cells in order to replace it.

Parameter name: Offset for the average CCA failure rate for DFS
Description: This parameter defines the offset, by which the average CCA failure rate of an alternative LAA channel set must be minimum smaller than the one of the LAA channel set currently in use by the LP-RRH cells in order to replace it. It is considered for DCS between DFS-restricted and non-DFS restricted channels.

Parameter name: Average CCA failure rate threshold
Description: This parameter defines the threshold for the average CCA failure rate of the LAA channels currently in use by the LP-RRH cells, above which an alternative channel set would be searched.    Note: If this parameter is set to '0', DCS function will search for a better 'candidate LAA channel set' during the time when freqHoldoffTimer timer is not running, whatever the quality of the LAA channel set currently in use is.

Parameter name: Maximum CCA failure rate threshold
Description: This parameter defines the threshold for the maximum CCA failure rate of an LAA channel in use by any LP-RRH, above which an alternative LAA channel set would be searched.

Parameter name: CCA Threshold
Description: This parameter is used by the eNB to derive the maximum energy detection threshold "DataThresh_max" beyond which no PDCCH/PDSCH transmission is allowed from a cell in frequency band #46.    "DataThresh_max" is calculated taking the minimum between the configured ccaThreshold parameter value and the applied "Xthresh_max" (see lteUWiFiCoexistence parameter for details).

Parameter name: LAA kickdown channel availability threshold
Description: LAA cell kickdown will be triggered, if the cell utilization reaches a lower value than a defined threshold.  If the CCA success ratio is smaller than ccaThresholdDpc and the unlicensed channel utilization [%] is smaller than utilizationThresholdDpc and the these conditions will last for evaluationDurationDpc time, then LAA cell kickdown will be triggered.

Parameter name: CCA threshold for DRS transmission
Description: This parameter is used by the eNB to derive the maximum energy detection threshold "DrsThresh_max" beyond which no "DRS only" transmission is allowed from a cell in frequency band #46.    "DrsThresh_max" is calculated taking the minimum between the configured ccaThresholdDrs parameter value and the applied "Xthresh_max" (see lteUWiFiCoexistence parameter for details).

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: DCS averaging window size
Description: This parameter defines the effective window size (in time) the CCA sample data are filter-averaged for CCA failure rate evaluation.    The actual filter averaging ("smoothing") coefficient of the exponential moving average (EMA) filter is dynamically determined based on the received CCA sample pattern such that the overall effective averaging window size of dcsAvgWindowTime is maintained.    Note: Default value '0' changes the filtering from EMA to LMA (linear moving average).

Parameter name: DRS measurement time configuration period
Description: This parameter defines the period by which the DRS window is transmitted.

Parameter name: Enable discovery signal padding for LAA
Description: This parameter enables or disables the padding of blank symbols of the discovery signal transmitted on an unlicensed cell in 'LAA' mode with random data. Enabling of the padding prevents other devices operating on the frequency of an unlicensed cell in 'LAA' mode from acquiring the channel during the silent symbols of the discovery signal transmission (e.g., symbol 2, 3, 9, 10). It also increases the total transmitted power per symbol and therefore reduces the possibility of transmission collision between LTE and other technologies (e.g., Wi-Fi). It is recommended to enable the discovery signal padding if an unlicensed cell in 'LAA' mode is expected to co-exist with other radio technologies (e.g., Wi-Fi).  Note 1: This parameter takes effect only if the unlicensed cell is operated in 'LAA' mode, i.e., actUnlicensedAcc is set to 'LAA'.  Note 2: For definition of an 'unlicensed cell', please, see its definition at parameter actUnlicensedAcc.

Parameter name: LAA contiguous channel priority
Description: Controls the selection of contiguous vs. non-contiguous LAA channels.    Two values are supported:  - 'contiguousChannelOnly': non-contiguous channels will not be selected  - 'bestChannel': the best channel set is selected, regardless of whether or not they are contiguous

Parameter name: LAA transmit power mode
Description: Selects Transmit Power Control mode for LAA cells. Reduced mode trades off aggregate DL throughput while lowering aggregate multi-carrier transmit power.

Parameter name: LTE unlicensed Wi-Fi coexistence
Description: This parameter indicates whether or not the eNB has to share frequency band #46 with other systems (e.g., Wi-Fi). eNB will adapt accordingly the maximum continuous transmission period as per 3GPP TS 36.213 and derive which formula for the maximum energy detection threshold 'Xthresh_max' to apply as follows:    If lteUWiFiCoexistence is set to 'no WiFi':  'XThresh_max' corresponds to the maximum energy detection threshold defined in 3GPP TS 36.213 when absence of any other technology sharing the carrier can be guaranteed on a long-term basis. If this formula applies, the parameter ccaThresholdXr corresponds to the 'Xr' factor of the 3GPP specification.    If lteUWiFiCoexistence is set to 'WiFi':  'XThresh_max' corresponds to maximum energy detection threshold defined in 3GPP TS 36.213 when absence of any other technology sharing the carrier cannot be guaranteed on a long-term basis. If this formula applies, the parameter ccaThresholdXr does not play any role.    The so derived 'XThresh_max' is then used in combination with the parameters ccaThreshold and ccaThreholdDrs to calculate the maximum energy detection thresholds ('DataThresh_max' and 'DrsThresh_max') that the eNB will apply to decide about transmission.

Parameter name: Min. non-GBR data for using unlicensed carrier
Description: This parameter is used for calculating the minimum amount of data "MinBufferedData" which should be buffered in the unlicensed SCell for a given Channel Access Priority Class before considering its transmission.  "MinBufferedData" for data of a given Access Priority Class "P" is derived from nongbrThreshUnlicensed as follows:    For lteUItuRegion = 'USA'  MinBufferedData = nonGbrThreshUnlicened * (Tmcot,p -1)/10,  For lteUItuRegion = 'Japan'  MinBufferedData = nonGbrThreshUnlicened * (min(4, Tmcot,p -1))/10,  where: "Tmcot,p" corresponds to the maximum continuous transmission time allowed for the respective Access Priority Class "P", as defined in 3GPP TS 36.213.    If this parameter is set to '0', no threshold before data transmission is applied.    Note: For definition of an 'unlicensed cell', please, see its definition at parameter actUnlicensedAcc.

Parameter name: Number of times max. contention window is used
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of time for which the maximum Contention Window ('CWmax') is consecutively used for the generation of the 'Ninit' parameter, before it is reset to the minimum Contention Window ('CWmin') value.  (Note: The parameters 'CWmax', 'Ninit' and 'CWmin' are defined in 3GPP TS 36.213.)

Parameter name: Additional pMax limitation for subband B46a
Description: This parameter is used to define additional transmit power limit, when the LAA cell operates within subband B46a.  If the power level configured by pMaxB46a is higher than the value allowed by the country regulatory rules, pMaxB46a will be disregarded. If the power level configured by pMaxB46a is lower than the minimum pMax range value allowed by the radio module, then the radio module minimum pMax limit will be used instead of the configured pMaxB46a value.

Parameter name: Additional pMax limitation for subband B46b
Description: This parameter is used to define additional transmit power limit, when the LAA cell operates within subband B46b.  If the power level configured by pMaxB46b is higher than the value allowed by the country regulatory rules, pMaxB46b will be disregarded. If the power level configured by pMaxB46b is lower than the minimum pMax range value allowed by the radio module, then the radio module minimum pMax limit will be used instead of the configured pMaxB46b value.

Parameter name: Additional pMax limitation for subband B46c
Description: This parameter is used to define additional transmit power limit, when the LAA cell operates within subband B46c.  If the power level configured by pMaxB46c is higher than the value allowed by the country regulatory rules, pMaxB46c will be disregarded.
