If the power level configured by pMaxB46c is lower than the minimum pMax range value allowed by the radio module, then the radio module minimum pMax limit will be used instead of the configured pMaxB46c value.

Parameter name: Additional pMax limitation for subband B46d
Description: This parameter is used to define additional transmit power limit, when the LAA cell operates within subband B46d.  If the power level configured by pMaxB46d is higher than the value allowed by the country regulatory rules, pMaxB46d will be disregarded. If the power level configured by pMaxB46d is lower than the minimum pMax range value allowed by the radio module, then the radio module minimum pMax limit will be used instead of the configured pMaxB46d value.

Parameter name: Wi-Fi channels selection list
Description: The list of Wi-Fi channels to be selected (multiple choice selection).  A field encoded as a bitmap, where bit N is set to "0" if the corresponding channel is not in selection list, and set to "1" if the corresponding channel is within the selection list.    This selection list is later validated by the eNB, with the validated selection list reflected in the parameter uCellChannelSListReg.    Bitmask with bits defined as follows:  Bit 0 - channel 149  Bit 1 - channel 153  Bit 2 - channel 157  Bit 3 - channel 161  Bit 4 - channel 165  Bit 5 - channel 32  Bit 6 - channel 36  Bit 7 - channel 40  Bit 8 - channel 44  Bit 9 - channel 48  Bit 10 - channel 52  Bit 11 - channel 56  Bit 12 - channel 60  Bit 13 - channel 64  Bit 14 - channel 68  Bit 15 - channel 96  Bit 16 - channel 100  Bit 17 - channel 104  Bit 18 - channel 108  Bit 19 - channel 112  Bit 20 - channel 116  Bit 21 - channel 120  Bit 22 - channel 124  Bit 23 - channel 128  Bit 24 - channel 132  Bit 25 - channel 136  Bit 26 - channel 140  Bit 27 - channel 144
Range and step: bits mask: channel 149 (0), channel 153 (1), channel 157 (2), channel 161 (3), channel 165 (4), channel 32 (5), channel 36 (6), channel 40 (7), channel 44 (8), channel 48 (9), channel 52 (10), channel 56 (11), channel 60 (12), channel 64 (13), channel 68 (14), channel 96 (15), channel 100 (16), channel 104 (17), channel 108 (18), channel 112 (19), channel 116 (20), channel 120 (21), channel 124 (22), channel 128 (23), channel 132 (24), channel 136 (25), channel 140 (26), channel 144 (27)

Parameter name: Wi-Fi regulatory channels selection list
Description: The list of Wi-Fi channels selected after regulatory limitations are applied.  A field encoded as a bitmap, where bit N is set to "0" if the corresponding channel is not in selection list, and set to "1" if the corresponding channel is within the selection list.    Bitmask with bits defined as follows:  Bit 0 - channel 149  Bit 1 - channel 153  Bit 2 - channel 157  Bit 3 - channel 161  Bit 4 - channel 165  Bit 5 - channel 32  Bit 6 - channel 36  Bit 7 - channel 40  Bit 8 - channel 44  Bit 9 - channel 48  Bit 10 - channel 52  Bit 11 - channel 56  Bit 12 - channel 60  Bit 13 - channel 64  Bit 14 - channel 68  Bit 15 - channel 96  Bit 16 - channel 100  Bit 17 - channel 104  Bit 18 - channel 108  Bit 19 - channel 112  Bit 20 - channel 116  Bit 21 - channel 120  Bit 22 - channel 124  Bit 23 - channel 128  Bit 24 - channel 132  Bit 25 - channel 136  Bit 26 - channel 140  Bit 27 - channel 144
Range and step: bits mask: channel 149 (0), channel 153 (1), channel 157 (2), channel 161 (3), channel 165 (4), channel 32 (5), channel 36 (6), channel 40 (7), channel 44 (8), channel 48 (9), channel 52 (10), channel 56 (11), channel 60 (12), channel 64 (13), channel 68 (14), channel 96 (15), channel 100 (16), channel 104 (17), channel 108 (18), channel 112 (19), channel 116 (20), channel 120 (21), channel 124 (22), channel 128 (23), channel 132 (24), channel 136 (25), channel 140 (26), channel 144 (27)

Parameter name: LAA kickdown channel utilization threshold
Description: LAA cell kickdown will be triggered, if the cell utilization reaches a lower value than a defined threshold.  If the CCA success rate is smaller than ccaThresholdDpc and the unlicensed channel utilization [%] is smaller than utilizationThresholdDpc, and the these conditions will last for evaluationDurationDpc time, LAA cell kickdown will be triggered.

Parameter name: MDT logged cell trace session identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC LTRACE.  Only one LTRACE MOC can exist in a cell.

Parameter name: Logged MDT configuration - Anonymization of MDT data
Description: Area based MDT when Job Type is Logged MDT only. This configuration parameter provides anonymization of MDT data. The parameter is an enumerated type with the following possible values: No Identity, IMEI-TAC  IMEI-TAC = The eNB shall send the CELL TRAFFIC TRACE message to the MME.  No identity = The eNB shall not send the CELL TRAFFIC TRACE message to the MME.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: MDT logged trace rec. session start stop ind
Description: Indication for sending Trace Recording Session Start and Stop in LTE protocol tracing interface of eNB to TCE.  true - Trace Recording Session Start and Stop is send to TCE  false - Trace Recording Session Start and Stop is not send to TCE

Parameter name: Cell global ID EUTRA
Description: List of Cells, identified by CellGlobalIdEUTRA which is a structure consistent of PLMN-Identity (modelled as MCC, MNC and MNC Length) and global cell Id inside PLMN (modelled as BTS Id and LCR Id). Maximum multiplicity is 32.  The Area Scope, optional parameter defines the area in terms on Cells, where the MDT data collection shall take place. The area scope specified in a MDT session shall support the same PLMN. If the parameter is not present the MDT data collection shall be done in the whole PLMN.

Parameter name: BTS Id
Description: The btsId identifies the BTS part of the eutranCellList.  The Area Scope, optional parameter defines the area in terms on Cells, where the MDT data collection shall take place. The area scope specified in a MDT session shall support the same PLMN. If the parameter is not present the MDT data collection shall be done in the whole PLMN.

Parameter name: LCR Id
Description: The lcrId is the Local Cell Resource Id.  The Area Scope, optional parameter defines the area in terms on Cells, where the MDT data collection shall take place. The area scope specified in a MDT session shall support the same PLMN. If the parameter is not present the MDT data collection shall be done in the whole PLMN.

Parameter name: MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code as part of PLMN Identity  The Area Scope, optional parameter defines the area in terms on Cells, where the MDT data collection shall take place. The area scope specified in a MDT session shall support the same PLMN. If the parameter is not present the MDT data collection shall be done in the whole PLMN.

Parameter name: MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code as part of PLMN Identity  The Area Scope, optional parameter defines the area in terms on Cells, where the MDT data collection shall take place. The area scope specified in a MDT session shall support the same PLMN. If the parameter is not present the MDT data collection shall be done in the whole PLMN.

Parameter name: MNC length
Description: Length of Mobile Network Code (MNC) as part of PLMN Identity  The Area Scope, optional parameter defines the area in terms on Cells, where the MDT data collection shall take place. The area scope specified in a MDT session shall support the same PLMN. If the parameter is not present the MDT data collection shall be done in the whole PLMN.

Parameter name: Logged MDT configuration - Force UE consent
Description: The parameter allows to force information elements "Management Based MDT Allowed" (consists of user consent)  Parameter is not forwarded by HO.

Parameter name: MDT logged cell configuration - Local cell resource identifier
Description: This parameter contains the local cell resource identifier of the Cell corresponding to the traced cell. It is same as contained under LNCEL object.  For each cell there can be only one or no LTRACE configured.

Parameter name: Logged MDT configuration - Logged TCE ID in configuration
Description: TCE ID number corresponding to TCE IP address from mapping defined in CTRLTS MOC.

Parameter name: Logged MDT configuration - Logging duration
Description: The parameter defines the logging duration.  This configuration parameter defines a timer activated at the moment of configuration that continues independent of state changes, RAT or RPLMN change. When the timer expires the logging is stopped and the configuration is cleared (except for the parameters that are required for further reporting e.g. network absolute time stamp, trace reference, trace recording session reference and TCE Id).

Parameter name: Logged MDT configuration - Logging interval
Description: The parameter defines the periodicity for logging MDT measurement results for periodic downlink pilot strength measurement when UE is in Idle.

Parameter name: MDT logged cell configuration - MDT logged cell working mode
Description: This parameter describes behavior of the cell. When parameter is set to "configureOnlyUEs" only configuration of the UEs is possible, "retrieveOnlyDataFromUEs" only collecting logs from UEs is possible, "configureAndRetrieveDataFromUEs" configuration UEs and collecting logs from UEs is allowed.  Only one LTRACE MOC can exist in a cell.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: PLMN Identity per TAC list
Description: PLMNperTAlist (plmn-Identity-perTAC-List) is up to 8. Includes the PLMN identity for each of the TA codes included in trackingAreaCodeList. The PLMN identity listed first in plmn-Identity-perTAC-List corresponds with the TA code listed first in trackingAreaCodeList

Parameter name: MDT per TAC MNC Length PLMN Identity
Description: This parameter determines the length of MNC.

Parameter name: MDT per TAC mobile country code
Description: The Mobile Country Code parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.

Parameter name: MDT per TAC Mobile Network Code
Description: The parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code and is part of the PLMN identifier

Parameter name: Logged MDT configuration - MDT logged standalone GNSS UEs selection
Description: Parameter is allowing to choose those UEs which are GNSS functionality capable.  true - only the capable UEs of 'standaloneGNSS-Location' and 'loggedMeasurementsIdle' shall be configured for MDT logged.  false - only the capable UEs of 'loggedMeasurementsIdle' shall be configured for MDT logged.

Parameter name: Tracking area list
Description: List of Tracking Area, identified by TAC. Maximum of 8 TAC can be defined.    The Area Scope optional parameter defines the area in terms on Tracking Area/Routing Area/Location, where the MDT data collection shall take place. The area scope specified in a MDT session shall support the same PLMN. If the parameter is not present the MDT data collection shall be done in the whole PLMN.

Parameter name: MDT logged Trace Reference - Trace ID
Description: Trace ID identifies a cell trace session. In combination with PLMN ID, the identifier becomes unique.  Trace ID is part of Trace Reference contained in MDT logged Trace Reference  MDT logged Trace Reference is unique id identifying a trace session.  Trace Reference is globally unique and is 6 Octet length comprising of:  MCC+MNC+Trace ID.    MCC+MNC is of 3 Octet length  Trace ID is of 3 Octet length    E-UTRAN Trace ID is one of the trace parameters received for a trace session.

Parameter name: MDT logged Trace Reference - MDT logged Trace Reference MCC
Description: MCC of PLMN ID contained in Trace Reference.  This is the MCC of the PLMN ID contained in the MDT logged Trace Reference.

Parameter name: MDT logged Trace Reference - MDT logged Trace Reference MNC
Description: MNC of PLMN ID contained in Trace Reference  This is the MNC of the PLMN ID contained in the MDT logged Trace Reference

Parameter name: MDT logged Trace Reference - MDT logged Trace Reference MNC Length
Description: Length of MNC of PLMN ID contained in Trace Reference  This is the length of the MNC of the PLMN ID contained in the MDT logged Trace Reference

Parameter name: M1 sync identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC M1SYNC.  It uniquely identifies a M1SYNC instance.  It is recommended to modify the parameters of this MOC only if there are no active MBMS sessions.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Elapsed count includes M1 Sync header
Description: Indicates if the elapsed octet count includes the sync header.

Parameter name: MBMS SYNC reference - Fractional seconds
Description: Represents fraction of second. This along with the intergralSecs parameters form a 64bit NTP timestamp representation.  Actual value = Value /2^32 s    eg: Value = 2,147,483,648 Fractional Seconds:  Actual Value = (2,147,483,648 / 2^32) s = 0.5s

Parameter name: MBMS SYNC reference - Integral seconds
Description: Represents seconds since beginning of era epoch (Jan 1, 1900. 0H). This along with the fractionalSecs parameters form a 64bit NTP timestamp representation.

Parameter name: M1 time reference
Description: Represents the time reference used for M1 interface.  This parameter reflects the time reference used by the BM-SC to timestamp MBMS sync PDUs.

Parameter name: MBMS SYNC period
Description: Represents the duration of the sync period common for both Broadcast Multicast Service Center (BM-SC) and the eNBs. An increase in relative timestamped value within MBMS SYNC PDUs will be interpreted by eNB as a start of new SYNC sequence.  The actual SFN transmission time of data PDUs could be expressed as fn [(current time - mbmsSyncRef) mod mbmsSyncPeriod].    Recommend to set the mbmsSyncPeriod to at least twice the value of the longest amongst all instances of MBSFNSYNCAREA-MBSFN-mchinfo-mchSchedulingPeriod.

Parameter name: MBMS sync time offset
Description: Represents the adjustment made to the timestamp of each packet received.  This parameter specifies the time offset between the BM-SC and the eNB. The time stamp in the sync header minus mbmsSyncTimeOffset will be used by the eNB. All the eNBs shall have the same offset for a given bearer service. In case of modification, it should be made at BM-SC also. However, this parameter can be useful in case the eNBs are unsynchronized with one or several BM-SC. The value specified here will apply to all M1 bearers.

Parameter name: MBSFN Cell identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MBSFNCEL.  It uniquely identifies a MBSFNCEL instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: MBSFN area in use list
Description: An element of the mbsfnAreaInUseList identifies an MBSFN Area Id that is currently enabled for use. A minimum of one and up to eight MBSFN Area Ids may be configured per MBSFN Sync Area.

Parameter name: MBSFN hidden list
Description: An element of the mbsfnHiddenList identifies an MBSFN Area Id that is currently enabled for use, but shall not be included in SIB13. If this list is defined, a minimum of one and up to eight MBSFN Area Ids may be configured per MBSFN Sync Area.

Parameter name: MBSFN sync area in use
Description: Represents the MBMS Sync Area that is associated with this Cell.  The MBSFN Sync Area associated with this MBSFNCEL will have the EARFCN and Channel Bandwidth matching the EARFCN and Channel Bandwidth of the associated LNCEL.

Parameter name: MBSFN sync area identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MBSFNSYNCAREA_FDD.  It uniquely identifies a MBSFNSYNCAREA_FDD instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Maximum MBSFN sync area subframe pattern share
Description: Defines the maximum MBSFN Sync Area subframe pattern share based on the proportion of the system capacity that shall be reserved for MBMS Service. A Value of 25 indicates, 25% of subframes are reserved for MBMS Services and 75% is left for Unicast Service.    It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there is no active MBMS session. Otherwise MBMS service will be temporarily suspended and resumed.  This parameter determines the values of radioframeAllocationPeriod, radioframeAllocationOffset, subframeAllocation(fourFrames) defined in TS36.331.    A lower percental share may be allocated by eNB if the required percental share is not possible with the actual configuration. In this case the fault 'MBMS subframe pattern share exceeds avail. share' will be reported.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released, when this parameter is online modified together with Cat-M are activated.

Parameter name: MBSFN downlink channel bandwidth
Description: The downlink channel bandwidth used for MBSFN operation.  Only maximum downlink channel bandwidth '3 MHz', '5 MHz', '10 MHz', '15 MHz', and '20 MHz' can be used.  The downlink channel bandwidth mapping to the number of Physical Resource Blocks (PRBs) is:  1.4 MHz = 6 DL PRBs  3.0 MHz = 15 DL PRBs  5.0 MHz = 25 DL PRBs  10.0 MHz = 50 DL PRBs  15.0 MHz = 75 DL PRBs  20.0 MHz = 100 DL PRBs  It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there is no active MBMS session. Otherwise MBMS service will be temporarily suspended and resumed.

Parameter name: MBSFN EARFCN
Description: E-UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number used for MBSFN operation. Services which are assigned to the MBSFN will be broadcasted in all cells of the eNB with earfcnDL equal to mbsfnEarfcn and dlChBw equal to mbsfnChBw.    It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there is no active MBMS session. Otherwise MBMS service will be temporarily suspended and resumed.  If MFBI is also enabled, then UEs that support the mapped band as indicated in the MFBIPR instance corresponding to earfcnDL will also be able to use MBMS services.

Parameter name: MBSFN overlapping allowed
Description: Indicates if MBSFN Subframe overlapping configuration is allowed.  When this parameter is set to 'true', the MBSFNs belonging to this MBSFN Sync Area are allowed to have overlapping ranges of subframes.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released, when this parameter is online modified together with Cat-M are activated.

Parameter name: MBSFN sync area Id
Description: Defines the MBSFN Synchronization Area ID. Any specific Sync Area ID cannot be used across multiple carriers within an eNB.  This IE uniquely identifies an MBMS area supported for a specific frequency. There could be up to eight MBSFNs supported within a single MBSFN Sync Area.

Parameter name: MBSFN sync area PLMN identity list
Description: PLMN IDs associated with the MBSFN Sync Area.  These are PLMN IDs of the MBSFN Sync Area. The parameter indicates which operators' (PLMNID) networks are available for the specific MBSFN Sync Area. If not defined, all PLMNs are allowed for the MBSFN Sync Area.

Parameter name: Mobile country code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Country Code.  The Mobile Country Code parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.

Parameter name: Mobile Network Code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Network Code.  The Mobile Network Code parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.

Parameter name: Mobile network code length
Description: Indicates the length of the Mobile Network Code.  The Mobile Network Code length parameter indicates the length of the Mobile Network Code, either 2 or 3 digits.

Parameter name: Allowed MBSFN sync area subframe pattern share
Description: Indicates the maximum allowed MBSFN Sync Area subframe pattern share which is currently in use. A Value of 25 indicates that 25% of subframes are reserved for MBMS Services and 75% is left for Unicast Service.  This parameter determines the values of commonSF-Alloc, radioframeAllocationPeriod, radioframeAllocationOffset, FourFrame defined in TS36.331.    The eNB selects a MBSFN Subframe configuration pattern which fits to the maximum percental share while considering other features (example: ETWS, OTDOA) which also reserve subframes. The value may be less than or equal to maxSyncSubfrPShare.    If maxSyncSubfrPShare cannot be provided with the current eNB configuration, the value of syncSubfrPShareAllowed may be less than maxSyncSubfrPShare and the fault 'MBMS subframe pattern share exceeds avail. share' is reported.

Parameter name: MBSFN sync area identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MBSFNSYNCAREA_FDD.  It uniquely identifies a MBSFNSYNCAREA_FDD instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Maximum MBSFN sync area subframe pattern share
Description: Defines the maximum MBSFN Sync Area subframe pattern share based on the proportion of the system capacity that shall be reserved for MBMS Service. A value of 25 indicates that maximum 25% of subframes are reserved for MBMS Services and 75% are left for Unicast Service.    It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there is no active MBMS session. Otherwise MBMS service will be temporarily suspended and resumed.    This parameter determines the values of radioframeAllocationPeriod, radioframeAllocationOffset, subframeAllocation(fourFrames) defined in TS36.331.    A lower percental share may be allocated by eNB if the required percental share is not possible with the actual configuration. In this case the fault 'MBMS subframe pattern share exceeds avail. share' will be reported.    Note for TDD: Currently the use of MBMS is restricted to TDD subframe configuration#2.

Parameter name: MBSFN downlink channel bandwidth
Description: The downlink channel bandwidth used for MBSFN operation.  Only Maximum downlink channel bandwidth 10Mhz, 15Mhz, 20Mhz can be used.  The downlink channel bandwidth mapping to number of Physical Resource Blocks is:  1.4 MHz = 6 DL PRBS  3.0 MHz = 15 DL PRBS  5.0 MHz = 25 DL PRBS  10.0 MHz = 50 DL PRBS  15.0 MHz = 75 DL PRBS  20.0 MHz = 100 DL PRBS  It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there is no active MBMS session. Otherwise MBMS service will be temporarily suspended and resumed.

Parameter name: MBSFN EARFCN
Description: E-UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number used for MBSFN operation. Services which are assigned to the MBSFN will be broadcast in all cells of the eNB with earfcn equal to mbsfnEarfcn and chBw equal to mbsfnChBw.    It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there is no active MBMS session. Otherwise MBMS service will be temporarily suspended and resumed.  If MFBI is also enabled, then UEs that support the mapped band as indicated in the MFBIPR instance corresponding to earfcn will also be able to use MBMS services.

Parameter name: MBSFN overlapping allowed
Description: Indicates if MBSFN Subframe overlapping configuration is allowed.  When this parameter is set to 'true', the MBSFNs belonging to this MBSFN Sync Area are allowed to have overlapping ranges of subframes.

Parameter name: MBSFN sync area Id
Description: Defines the MBSFN Synchronization Area ID. Any specific Sync Area ID cannot be used across multiple carriers within an eNB.  This IE uniquely identifies an MBMS area supported for a specific frequency. There could be up to eight MBSFNs supported within a single MBSFN Sync Area.

Parameter name: MBSFN sync area PLMN identity list
Description: PLMN IDs associated with the MBSFN Sync Area.  These are PLMN IDs of the MBSFN Sync Area. The parameter indicates which operators' (PLMNID) networks are available for the specific MBSFN Sync Area. If not defined, all PLMNs are allowed for the MBSFN Sync Area.

Parameter name: Mobile country code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Country Code.  The Mobile Country Code parameter indicates the Mobile Country Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.

Parameter name: Mobile Network Code
Description: Indicates the Mobile Network Code.  The Mobile Network Code parameter indicates the Mobile Network Code and is part of the PLMN identifier.

Parameter name: Mobile network code length
Description: Indicates the length of the Mobile Network Code.  The Mobile Network Code length parameter indicates the length of the Mobile Network Code, either 2 or 3 digits.

Parameter name: Allowed MBSFN sync area subframe pattern share
Description: Indicates the maximum allowed MBSFN Sync Area subframe pattern share which is currently in use. A Value of 25 indicates that 25% of subframes are reserved for MBMS Services and 75% is left for Unicast Service.  This parameter determines the values of commonSF-Alloc, radioframeAllocationPeriod, radioframeAllocationOffset, FourFrame defined in TS36.331.    The eNB selects a MBSFN Subframe configuration pattern which fits to the maximum percental share while considering other features (example: ETWS, OTDOA) which also reserve subframes. The value may be less than or equal to maxSyncSubfrPShare.    If maxSyncSubfrPShare cannot be provided with the current eNB configuration, the value of syncSubfrPShareAllowed may be less than maxSyncSubfrPShare and the fault 'MBMS subframe pattern share exceeds avail. share' is reported.

Parameter name: MBMS single frequency network identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MBSFN_FDD.  It uniquely identifies a MBSFN FDD instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: B1 EN-DC meas. allowed for MBMS users
Description: This parameter indicates if NR-B1 measurement for EN-DC can be setup or is blocked when QCI 67 traffic is broadcasted over eMBMS and the UE expresses MBMS interest (via RRC:MBMSInterestIndication). The UEs with EN-DC already established are not impacted.  The parameter settings are irrelevant, if LNBTS-actMBMSServiceContinuity is set to false or LNBTS-actDynTrigLteNrDualConnectivity is set to false or ENDC is deactivated at cell level (LNCEL is not listed in dynTriggerLteNrDcConfList-lcrId in NRDCDPR or in any NRDCPR and NRDCDPR-dynTriggerLteNrDcConfList-lcrId is set not to '-1'). There could be multiple MBSFN_FDD instances representing different MBSFN synchronization areas (MBSFNSYNCAREA_FDD) associated with the cell serving the UE (see LNCEL/MBSFNCEL-mbsfnAreaInUseList) and it is enough to set endcAllowedForMbmsUsers to 'allowed' in at least one of them to enable NR-B1 measurement setup for EN-DC.    Note that MBMS interested UEs listening to QCI 67 might suffer from losses during inter-frequency/B1 measurements, if the measurement gaps and MBSFN subframes overlap.

Parameter name: Maximum MBSFN subframe pattern share
Description: Defines the maximum MBSFN subframe pattern share based on the proportion of the system capacity that shall be reserved for MBMS Service. For example, A Value of 25 indicates that 25% of subframes are reserved for MBMS Services and 75% is left for Unicast Service.    It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there is no active MBMS session.  This parameter determines the values of radioframeAllocationPeriod, radioframeAllocationOffset, subframeAllocation(fourFrames) defined in TS36.331.    If MBSFN subframes are statically defined (actDynMBMSRes is set to FALSE), eNB selects a MBSFN subframe configuration pattern which fits the maximum percental share.  Otherwise (actDynMBMSRes is set to TRUE), eNB selects a MBSFN subframe configuration pattern with an MBMS subframe percentage that is less than or equal to the maximum percental share.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released, when this parameter is online modified together with Cat-M are activated.

Parameter name: MBMS service area list
Description: Service Area Identities (SAI) of the MBMS service area.    This list contains the Service Area IDs belonging to this MBSFN instance for FDD.

Parameter name: MBSFN Area Identity
Description: Identifies the MBSFN area Id.  When MBMS is enabled, MBSFN Area Ids are broadcast over the air and is used to scramble the MBSFN reference signals.  mbsfn-AreaId should be unique (duplicate mbsfn-AreaId not allowed) under a given LNMCE

Parameter name: MBSFN sessions active
Description: Sessions Active for this MBSFN.  This parameter indicates whether there are active sessions for this MBSFN. The value of true will be displayed if at least one session of this MBSFN is active. This will be determined by the MCE and passed on to NetAct to be displayed.

Parameter name: MBSFN starting subframe
Description: Defines the MBSFN starting subframe for this MBSFN Area.  Only MBSFN subframes are considered.    Note 1: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released, when this parameter is online modified together with Cat-M are activated.  Note 2: mbsfnStartingSF for an MBSFN for 3MHz and 5MHz should not be set to 5, 11, 17, 23 in order to accommodate sessions that require 2 subframes for MCCH.

Parameter name: MCCH repetition period
Description: The parameter indicates the interval between transmissions of MCCH information. The MCCH is scheduled in the period where SFN mod mcch-RepetitionPeriod = mcch-Offset.  eNB will configure mchSchedulingPeriod of the first selected (P)MCH to be smaller than or equal to mcchRepetitionPeriod.

Parameter name: Multicast channel info
Description: Multicast channel configuration per GBR QCI

Parameter name: Data Modulation Code Scheme
Description: Indicates the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) applicable for the subframes of this (P)MCH.

Parameter name: Multicast channel Scheduling period
Description: Indicates the MCH scheduling period i.e. the periodicity used for providing MCH scheduling information at lower layers (MAC) applicable for an MCH. Value rf8 corresponds to 8 radio frames, rf16 corresponds to 16 radio frames and so on.  The mchSchedulingPeriod starts in the radio frames for which SFN mod mchSchedulingPeriod = 0.    If this (MSP) value is set excessively long when a high dataMCS is used, excessive packet discards might happen resulting in poor MBMS broadcast service.  The MSP length must be set to one or multiple times of the Synchronization sequence length on the BM-SC for MBMS Services in the MCH.

Parameter name: QCI
Description: QoS Class Identifier of the MBMS service. Only QCI values 1, 2, 3, 4, 65, 66 and 67 are valid values.  NOTE: Only unique GBR QCI value instances are allowed for MBMS.    It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there are no active MBMS sessions for the specific QCI.

Parameter name: Signaling Modulation and coding scheme
Description: Indicates the Modulation and Coding Scheme (MCS) applicable for the subframes indicated by 'sfAllocInfo' and for the first subframe of each MCH scheduling period (which may contain the MCH scheduling information provided by MAC). Value n2 corresponds to the value 2 for parameter in TS 36.213 [23, Table 7.1.7.1-1], and so on.

Parameter name: Allowed MBSFN subframe pattern share
Description: Indicates the maximum allowed MBSFN subframe pattern share which is currently in use. A value of 10 indicates that 10% of subframes are reserved for MBMS Services and 90% is left for Unicast Service.  This parameter determines the values of commonSF-Alloc, radioframeAllocationPeriod, radioframeAllocationOffset, FourFrame defined in TS36.331.

Parameter name: MBMS single frequency network identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MBSFN_TDD.  It uniquely identifies a MBSFN TDD instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Description: Defines the maximum MBSFN subframe pattern share based on the proportion of the system capacity that shall be reserved for MBMS Service. For example a value of 25 indicates that maximum 25% of subframes are reserved for MBMS Services and 75% are left for Unicast Service.    It is recommended to modify the parameter only if there is no active MBMS session.  This parameter determines the values of radioframeAllocationPeriod, radioframeAllocationOffset, subframeAllocation(fourFrames) defined in TS36.331.    If MBSFN subframes are statically defined (actDynMBMSRes is set to 'false'), eNB selects a MBSFN subframe configuration pattern which fits to the maximum percental share.  Otherwise (actDynMBMSRes is set to 'true'), eNB selects a MBSFN subframe configuration pattern with an MBMS subframe percentage that is less than or equal to the maximum percental share.    Note for TDD: Currently the use of MBMS is restricted to TDD subframe configuration#2.

Description: Defines the MBSFN starting subframe for this MBSFN Area.  Only MBSFN subframes are considered.

Parameter name: MFBI profile identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a MFBIPR instance.

Parameter name: Additional E-UTRA frequency band indicator
Description: Indicator of the mapped E-UTRA frequency band  A mapped E-UTRA frequency band must overlap with the native E-UTRA frequency band.  The native frequency band is either  - the operating band which is broadcast in SIB1 with IE freqBandIndicator or  - the frequency band which is related to the target EARFCN in case of interfrequency mobility    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Additional spectrum emission
Description: Additional spectrum emission requirement for the mapped frequency band.  The UE requirements related to IE AdditionalSpectrumEmission are defined in TS 36.101 [42, table 6.2.4.1].    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: E-UTRA carrier frequency
Description: EARFCN value of the native carrier frequency for which the MFBI profile applies.  A MFBI profile defines a mapped frequency band in order to serve UEs which support the physical cell frequency but indicate the mapped frequency band.  The profile applies to eNB cells and inter-frequency neighbor cells with a frequency value matching eutraCarrierFreq.

Parameter name: Frequency band indication priority
Description: This parameter allows to prioritizing mapped bands over native bands.  If the parameter is 'broadcast', the eNB indicates to the UE to prioritizing the corresponding frequency bands in the multiBandInfoList IE. Only if the UE does not support the frequency band in multiBandInfoList IE or does not support the frequency band adjustment, the UE shall then use the value in freqBandIndicator IE. Otherwise, the UE applies the frequency band according to the rules defined in multiBandInfoList.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Idle mode mobility default profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MODIMP.  It uniquely identifies a MODIMP instance.  MODIMP contains the Idle Mobility configuration to be assigned to UEs that do not have any profile corresponding to SPID or PLMN ID.

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of CDMA2000 HRPD parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band class for idle mode load balancing
Description: CDMA2000 HRPD band class value used for Idle Mode mobility.  The UE only performs Load Balancing cell reselection for bands that are already configured for Idle Mobility (in CDFIM) and transmitted in system information. There is no need to provide bands other than the once configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such bands.

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band class prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the CDMA2000 HRPD band class used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of CDMA HRPD Band used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.    When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of CDMA2000 1xRTT parameters needed for an Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band class for idle mode load balancing
Description: CDMA2000 1xRTT band class value used for Idle Mode mobility  The UE shall only perform Load Balancing cell reselection for bands that are already configured for Idle Mobility (in CDFIM) and transmitted in system information.There is no need to provide other bands the once configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such bands.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band class prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the CDMA2000 1xRTT band class used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of CDMA 1xRTT Band used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.    When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest. Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.
