Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: GERAN band parameters for idle mode load balancing - GERAN carrier freq band for idle mode load balancing
Description: This is an indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case ARFCN values are associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.    This parameter will be used together with "geranCarFrqIdleModeL" to build freqPriorityListGERAN IE in "IdleModeMobilityControlInfo" for Load Balancing.

Parameter name: GERAN carrier freq list for idle mode load balancing
Description: GERAN frequency as ARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility.  Each ARFCN value explicitly listed.    The UE only performs Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in GNFL) and transmitted in system information. There is no need to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.    This parameter will be used together with geranCarFrqBd to build freqPriorityListGERAN IE in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for Load Balancing.

Parameter name: GERAN band parameters for idle mode load balancing - GERAN carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the GERAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  This parameter will be used together with geranCarFrqIdleModeL to build freqPriorityListGERAN IE in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: GERAN band parameters for idle mode load balancing - GERAN carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of GERAN carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.    When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of NR carrier (SA) parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) frequency for idle mode load balancing
Description: This parameter defines the NR ARFCN carrier frequency of the NR carrier used for Idle Mode mobility. It corresponds to GSCN value as specified in TS 38.101.    The UE only performs Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in NRFIM). There is no need to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) frequency preference for idle mode load balancing
Description: NR carrier (SA) frequency preference for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing.  1: higher than LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR2 PScell  2: between LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR2 PScell and LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR1 PScell only  3: lower than LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR1 PScell only      NR carrier (SA) is always preferred for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing over LTE carrier w/o EN-DC support.
Range and step: higher than EnDc FR2 (1), between EnDc FR2 and EnDc FR1 (2), lower than EnDc FR1 (3)

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) freq prio for idle mode load balancing for NR SA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of NR carrier (SA) frequency layer used for secondary target selection of idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) weight factor for idle mode load balancing of NR SA capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of NR carrier (SA) frequency used by round robin algorithm for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs.

Parameter name: UTRA FDD carrier list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of UTRA-FDD parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message.

Parameter name: UTRA-FDD carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of UTRA FDD Carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.    When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: UTRA FDD carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the UTRAN FDD carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: UTRA FDD carrier freq for idle mode load balancing
Description: UTRA-FDD frequency as UARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility.  The UE performs only Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in UFFIM) and transmitted in system information. There is no need to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.

Parameter name: UTRA TDD carrier list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of UTRA-TDD parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message.

Parameter name: UTRA-TDD carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of UTRA TDD Carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.    When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: UTRA TDD carrier freq prio idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the UTRAN TDD carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 is the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: UTRA TDD carrier freq for idle mode load balancing
Description: UTRA-TDD frequency as UARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility  The UE shall only perform Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in UFFIM) and transmitted in system information. There is no need to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.

Parameter name: Mobility default profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MODPR.  It uniquely identifies a MODPR instance.

Parameter name: Allow EN-DC
Description: This parameter indicates whether measurement-based EN-DC and blind EN-DC setup are disabled or enabled and whether a dedicated NR frequency list or all neighbor NR frequency layers are considered.    Note: The parameter values have following meaning:  0:EN-DC disabled - both, measurement-based EN-DC and blind EN-DC setup are not allowed for UEs using this mobility profile.  1:dedicated_freq_layers - both, measurement-based EN-DC and blind EN-DC setup are allowed for UEs using this mobility profile and all neighbor NR frequency layers given in freqLayListEnDc are available (others are disabled).  2:all_freq_layers - both, measurement-based EN-DC and blind EN-DC setup are allowed for UEs using this mobility profile and no neighbor NR frequency layers are disabled (NOTE: this corresponds to legacy behavior).

Parameter name: Offload to UTRAN allowed
Description: This parameter indicates if the SPID Group is allowed to be offloaded to UTRAN for Connected Mode Load Balancing.

Parameter name: Auto adaptation to freq. layers of all neighbor cells
Description: This parameter offers the possibility to use existing LNCEL configuration as default mobility profile. This parameter defines auto adaptation rules for all mobility procedures except for Idle Mode Mobility Load Balancing procedures.    autoAdapt parameter is considered when MODPR applies. For details, see parameter description of LNBTS-actSelMobPrf.    If autoAdapt is 'true':  - the HO frequency lists defined in LNADJL, LNADJW and LNADJG objects are used instead of MODPR configuration. Frequency layers of newly created LNADJL, LNADJW and LNADJG objects are automatically included in the default profile. Exception for service based handover: eNB will treat the frequency list for service based handover as empty.  - VoLTE inter-frequency is not allowed.  - REDRT configuration of the corresponding cell is used instead of MODRED configuration. MODRED, if present, is not considered.    Note: Measurements are done only for adjacent objects (LNADJx) that are referred by a relationship object (LNRELx) with a frequency configured in the corresponding handover object (LNHOx).

Parameter name: Auto adaptation for IMLB
Description: This parameter offers the possibility to use existing LNCEL configuration as default mobility profile. This parameter defines auto adaptation rules for Idle Mode Mobility Load Balancing procedures only.    autoAdapt parameter is considered when MODPR applies. For details, see parameter description of LNBTS-actSelMobPrf.    If autoAdaptIMLB is 'true':  - IMLB weights can be differentiated on the serving cell level. In this case IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL configuration and serving carrier of the corresponding cell are used instead of MODIMP.  - MODIMP, if present, is not considered.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation blocking allowed
Description: This parameter indicates if a UE belonging to default mobility profile is subject to load-based carrier aggregation PCell and SCell blocking as defined by LTE4631.

Parameter name: Retry options for UE MR-DC Capability ENDC handover
Description: Defines the retry options for UE MR-DC capability based ENDC handover.  ENDC handover retries are NOT executed when 'noRetries' is selected, i.e. ENDC handover is attempted only when the UE, which is not a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC steering, enters the cell (e.g. via handover or initial context setup).  When configUeCapEndcHoRetry is set to 'priorityAboveLoadBasedHo' ENDC handover retries could be attempted periodically (see LNCEL.iFEndcHoRetryTimer) for the UE which is not a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover, and load balancing and load equalization handovers are not attempted.  When configUeCapEndcHoRetry is set to 'priorityBelowLoadBasedHo' ENDC handover retries could be attempted periodically for the UE which is not a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover, when eNB cell is not in load balancing or equalization active state.  Load balancing and load equalization handovers could be attempted for the UE which is not a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover, with 'priorityBelowLoadBasedHo' or 'noRetries' selection. For the UEs which qualify for ENDC-HO steering, load equalization could be done only towards target frequencies which are ENDC anchor layers.  For the UE candidate for NR coverage-based handover the load balancing and load equalization handovers could be attempted only if allowed by nrCovEndcHoRetryPrio.  Note that Volte service based handover and MBMS steering are always of higher priority and they will be always attempted periodically, if applicable.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: EN-DC blocking allowed
Description: This parameter indicates if a UE belonging to default mobility profile is subject to load-based EN-DC blocking as defined by CB008308.

Parameter name: Extended range indicator for SPID-based IF HO
Description: This indicator is an index to the table with filtering threshold offsets for SPID-based IF HO, which are defined per target carrier frequency.  An offset for a certain target carrier frequency is selected by setting MODPR-erIndForSPIDHO == threshOffsetsIFSPIDFilter-ind in the respective instance of LNHOIF.  Note: If this parameter is not configured or no matching index 'ind' is found, then no offsets will be applied.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for EN-DC capability-based HO
Description: This list specifies the frequency layers that are candidate for EN-DC capability-based handover.  The eNB will, based on the configured frequency layer list, try to steer EN-DC capable UEs to those candidate layers with EN-DC capability-based handover, i.e. EN-DC capable UEs will be guided to those frequency layers actively by the eNB.    The configured values are only applicable if the feature EN-DC capability-based HO is activated.    When in addition LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is configured to 'true', the specified frequency layers in MODPR freqLayEndcHoList apply only when no MOPR exists for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    If MODPR applies, no EN-DC capability-based HO will be provided if the parameter is omitted or autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Frequency layer for EN-DC capability-based HO
Description: Frequency layer for EN-DC capability-based handover.  The eNB will, based on the configured frequency layer list, try to steer EN-DC capable UEs to those candidate layers with EN-DC capability-based handover, i.e. EN-DC capable UEs will be guided to those frequency layers actively by the eNB.    The configured values are only applicable if the feature EN-DC capability-based HO is activated.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Preferred frequency layer
Description: Indicator for preferred frequency layer.  If this parameter is set to 'true', the frequency layer is candidate for EN-DC capability-based handover to preferred layer.    This parameter is applicable only in case EN-DC capability-based handover to preferred layer is activated in the LNCEL.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list high priority CSFB to TD-SCDMA
Description: List of TD-SCDMA target cell frequencies for high priority Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB). The list applies even if LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'false'.  If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'true' it additionally applies to UEs when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.  No CSFB to TD-SCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for high priority CSFB to WCDMA
Description: List of WCDMA target cell frequencies for high priority Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB). The list applies even if LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'false'.  If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'true' it additionally applies to UEs when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    No CSFB to WCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".  The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list normal priority CSFB to TD-SCDMA
Description: List of TD-SCDMA target cell frequencies for normal priority Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB). The list applies even if LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'false'.  If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'true' it additionally applies to UEs when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.  No CSFB to TD-SCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for normal priority CSFB to WCDMA
Description: List of WCDMA target cell frequencies for normal priority Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB). The list applies even if LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'false'.  If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'true' it additionally applies to UEs when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    No CSFB to WCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".  The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for ded. inter-frequency LB HO
Description: Specifies the dedicated target frequency layers for inter-frequency load balancing handovers. The configured values are only applicable if feature LTE2571 "Dedicated target frequency list for load balancing" is activated for inter-frequency LB frequencies, i.e. parameter actDedFreqListsLB is configured to 'inter-frequency' or 'all'(FDD only).  When the list does not contain any target frequency even if the feature is activated, the eNB will not allow inter-frequency load balancing handover to all targets.  If LTE1942 Dedicated VoLTE Inter-frequency Handover feature is activated, then the inter-frequency load balancing handover for VoLTE UEs will only be performed for frequency layers that are in both this list and in freqLayListDedVoLteHo of the MODPR instance.    In addition, when actSelMobPrf (Activate selective Mobility Profiles) is configured to 'true', the specified frequency layers in MODPR freqLayListDedLteLB apply only when no MOPR exists for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for ded. VoLTE inter-frequency HO
Description: Specifies the dedicated target frequency layers for inter-frequency mobility during VoLTE calls. The configured values are only applicable if feature LTE1942 "Dedicated VoLTE IF frequency layers" is activated, i.e. parameter actDedVoLteInterFreqHo is configured to 'true'.  When the list does not contain any target frequency even if the feature is activated, the eNB will not allow VoLTE inter-frequency handover to all targets.  For activated LTE1127 "Service Based Mobility Trigger" the list must include all frequency layers as defined in freqLayListServiceBasedHo of the MODPR instance.    When in addition actSelMobPrf (Activate selective Mobility Profiles) is configured to 'true', the specified frequency layers in MODPR freqLayListDedVoLteHo apply only when no MOPR exists for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for ded. load based handover to WCDMA
Description: Specifies the dedicated target frequency layers for WCDMA load balancing handovers. The configured values are only applicable if feature LTE2571 "Dedicated target frequency list for load balancing" is activated for WCDMA LB frequencies, i.e. parameter actDedFreqListsLB is configured to 'inter-system' or 'all'.  When the list does not contain any target frequency even if the feature is activated, the eNB will not allow WCDMA load balancing handover to all targets.    In addition, when actSelMobPrf (Activate selective Mobility Profiles) is configured to 'true', the specified frequency layers in MODPR freqLayListDedWcdmaLB apply only when no MOPR exists for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: List of NR frequencies allowed for EN-DC
Description: List of NR target frequencies allowed for EN-DC.    Note: This structure currently has only one member, but might be enhanced in the future.

Parameter name: NR neighbor frequency allowed for EN-DC
Description: This parameter indicates the frequency of a NR neighbor cell layer allowed for EN-DC (SSB frequency).

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for IMMCI support at TAU
Description: Default frequency (EARFCN) layer list, if IMMCI (Idle Mode Mobility Control Info) support during TAU is activated for selected EARFCN layers (MODPR-immciAtTau is equal to 'selected_layers').

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for LTE inter frequency mobility
Description: LTE inter-frequency mobility is restricted to the target frequency layers configured in freqLayListLte.    If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'true' the restriction applies when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'false' the restriction applies to all UEs.  No LTE Inter Frequency mobility will be provided if the parameter is omitted.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".  The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: SSB frequency layer list for packet switched handover to NR
Description: The list of target SSB frequencies for handover to NR-SA for UE without VoLTE bearer.  No mobility to NR will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted

Parameter name: Voice specific SSB frequency layer list for handover to NR
Description: The list of target SSB frequencies for handover to NR-SA for UE with VoLTE bearer.  No mobility to NR will be provided to UEs with VoLTE bearer which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for PS handover TD-SCDMA
Description: List of TD-SCDMA target cell frequencies for packet switched handover (PS HO) which applies to UEs when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.  No TD-SCDMA PS HO mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number 'ARFCN'.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for packet switched handover WCDMA
Description: WCDMA PS-HO mobility is restricted to the target frequency layers configured in freqLayListPsHoWcdma.    If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'true' the restriction applies when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'false' the restriction applies to all UEs.    No WCDMA PS HO mobility will be provided to UEs if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for SPID-based IF HO
Description: Specifies the frequency layers that are preferred for SPID-based IF handover. The eNB will be based on the configured frequency layer list try to steer UEs for the specified SPID values or combination of SPID, PLMN-ID, UE's EN-DC capabilities to those preferred layers via inter-frequency handover.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number 'ARFCN'.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for QCIx service-based HO
Description: Specifies the frequency layers that are preferred for QCIx service-based handovers. With QCIx service-based HO enabled, the eNB will try to steer to these preferred layers via inter-frequency handover UEs with QCIx bearer (see qciTab-servBasedHoAllowed and qciTabOperator-servBasedHoAllowed) and mapped to the MODPR profile.    Note: If the list is empty/not configured, then QCIx SHBO is not allowed for UEs mapped to the default mobility profile MODPR.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for VoLTE service based HO
Description: Specifies the frequency layers that are preferred for service based handover (LTE1127) or redirected VoLTE call setup (LTE2108). The eNB, based on the configured frequency layer list, tries to steer UEs with the established service to those preferred layers with service based handover, i.e. UEs with VoLTE calls will be guided to those frequency layers actively by the eNB.  The configured values are only applicable if either feature LTE1127 'Service Based Mobility Trigger' is activated (parameter actInterFreqServiceBasedHo is configured to 'true') or feature LTE2108 'Redirected VoLTE call setup' (parameter actRedirVoLte is configured to 'true') is activated.    When in addition LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is configured to 'true', the specified frequency layers in MODPR freqLayListServiceBasedHo apply only when no MOPR exists for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.  If MODPR applies no service based mobility will be provided if the parameter is omitted or autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for SRVCC to WCDMA
Description: List of WCDMA target cell frequencies for Single Radio Voice Call Continuity (SRVCC). The list applies even if LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'false'.  If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'true' it additionally applies to UEs when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    No SRVCC to WCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Inter Frequency Load Balancing candidate selection priority
Description: This parameter indicates UE candidate selection SPID priority for Connected Mode Load Balancing. With LTE3757 UE selection for offload is prioritized according to operator defined SPID groups.

Parameter name: Supported inter-RAT mode
Description: This parameter indicates which kind inter-RAT mobility feature is supported by default mobility profile.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing for CA capable UEs
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing for CA capable UEs.  MODPR-idleLBPercCaUe is taken into account for Idle Mode Load Balancing when actSelMobPrf is set to true and MODPR applies. (The value of autoAdapt does not matter).  When actSelMobPrf is set to false then LNCEL-idleLBPercCaUe is taken into account for Idle Mode Load Balancing for CA capable UEs.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  MODPR-idleLBPercUeTM9 is taken into account for Idle Mode Load Balancing when actSelMobPrf is set to true and MODPR applies. (The value of autoAdapt does not matter).  When actSelMobPrf is set to false then LNCEL-idleLBPercUeTM9 is taken into account for Idle Mode Load Balancing for TM9 capable UEs.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing.  MODPR-idleLBPercentageOfUes is taken into account for Idle Mode Load Balancing when actSelMobPrf is set to True and MODPR applies. (The value of autoAdapt is not relevant).  When actSelMobPrf is set to false then LNCEL-idleLBPercentageOfUes is taken into account for Idle Mode Load Balancing .

Parameter name: UE-level IMMCI support at TAU
Description: This parameter defines the UE-level type of support for IMMCI (Idle Mode Mobility Control Info) during Tracking Area Update (TAU) for the default mobility profile MODPR.    Following options are available:  0: disabled - - the support for IMMCI during TAU is disabled for MODPR  1: enabled_layers - - the support for IMMCI during TAU in MODPR is enabled in all activated cells - see actImmciAtTau  2: selected_layers - - support during TAU in MODPR is enabled in all activated cells of enabled EARFCN layers (MODPR-freqLayListImmciAtTau)

Parameter name: Measurement gap enable for NR measurements
Description: This parameter is used to enable/disable measurement gaps in measurements of NR frequencies for FR1 and/or FR2 bands if a UE is mapped to the MODPR.  If actMPMeasGapForNR is 'true' and if MODPR-measGapEnabledNRMeas is configured then the value of NRMEAS[D]PR-measGapEnabledNRMeas is ignored.    Note: The parameter values have the following meaning:  0: Disable - measurement gaps are not configured  1: FR1Only - measurement gaps are configured for FR1 frequencies and not for FR2 frequencies  2: FR2Only - measurement gaps are configured for FR2 frequencies and not for FR1 frequencies  3: FR1AndFR2 - measurement gaps are configured for FR1 and FR2 frequencies

Parameter name: NR coverage-based EN-DC HO retries priority
Description: This parameter determines whether load-based handover retries are allowed for UE candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover.  If configured to a value other than 'EndcHo only', the load-based handovers (load balancing or load equalization) are prioritized and NR coverage-based EN-DC anchor handovers are not initiated for the UE at the time it is a candidate for load-based handover retries (in active load balancing or load equalization load state).
Range and step: EndcHo only (0), allow LB retry (1), allow LB and LE (2)

Parameter name: Reference freq. list network assisted cell change GERAN
Description: ENACC mobility to GERAN is restricted to the target frequencies configured in refFreqListNaccGeran. The frequency values are used as references to GERAN measurement objects (LNHOG).    If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'true' the restriction applies when a MOPR does not exist for the specific SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to the UE.    If LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is set to 'false' the restriction applies to all UEs.    All LNHOG objects of a cell, which contain at least the reference ARFCN value in arfcnValueListGERAN are selected for UE measurement configuration. If the same ARFCN value would be configured in more than one LNHOG instance of a cell, only the first found LNHOG object is considered.    No NACC to GERAN mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Band indicator applied to reference ARFCN
Description: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either DCS1800 or PCS1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.

Parameter name: Reference ARFCN
Description: ARFCN value which is used as reference to a GERAN measurement object (LNHOG).

Parameter name: Reference frequency list for SRVCC to GSM
Description: List of ARFCN values which are used as references to GERAN measurement objects (LNHOG).  All LNHOG objects of a cell, which contain at least the reference ARFCN value in arfcnValueListGERAN are selected for UE measurement configuration. If the same ARFCN value is configured in more than one LNHOG instance of a cell, only the first found LNHOG object is considered.    No SRVCC to GSM mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter is meaningless if autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Band indicator applied to reference ARFCN
Description: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either DCS1800 or PCS1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.

Parameter name: Reference ARFCN
Description: ARFCN value which is used as reference to a GERAN measurement object (LNHOG).

Parameter name: Cell reselection method for idle mode load balancing
Description: Selection method for the target frequency/layer for idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Maximum time of periodic retries blocking in HO target cell
Description: This parameter determines the maximum time of EN-DC HO periodic retries blocking in target cell, after arrival from ENDC-HO target layer.    If the parameter is not configured then blocking of periodic retries enabled for MR-DC capability-based HO or EN-DC HO to preferred layer by blockEndcHoRetryAtHoFromTrg, or for NR coverage-based EN-DC HO by blockNrEndcHoAtHoFromTrg, continues in handover target cell without time limit.  If the parameter is set to special value 0 then enabled blocking is not applicable in target cell for UE mapped to MODPR.

Parameter name: Mobility default profile identifier for redirection
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MODRED.  It uniquely identifies a MODRED instance.

Parameter name: Add GSM system information to redirection message
Description: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which GSM system information is included in the RRC Connection Release message.  GSM system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further GSM cells will be omitted even if configured via LNLRELG settings.

Parameter name: Add UTRAN system information to redirection message
Description: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which UTRAN system information shall be included in the RRC Connection Release message.  UTRAN system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further UTRAN cells will be omitted even if configured via LNRELW settings.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Redirection priority for CS fallback with redirection
Description: This parameter defines the priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during CS Fallback with redirection procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 6 lowest.    The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter is meaningless if LTE3337 is enabled and the MODPR parameter iRatMode is set to 'CDMA2000_1xRTT' as R8 1xCSFB always uses LNCEL-REDRT parameters.

Parameter name: Redirection priority for emergency call
Description: This parameter defines the priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during Emergency Call handling procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 6 lowest.    The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter is meaningless if LTE3337 is enabled and the MODPR parameter iRatMode is set to 'CDMA2000_1xRTT' as R8 1xCSFB always uses LNCEL-REDRT parameters.

Parameter name: CDMA band
Description: This parameter specifies the cdma2000 band class. It must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000HRPD or redirRAT=cdma20001xRTT.    The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: CDMA frequency
Description: This parameter specifies the cdma2000 ARFCN.  It must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000HRPD or redirRAT=cdma20001xRTT.  The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: eUTRA frequency
Description: This parameter specifies the eUTRA frequency. It must be configured if redirRAT=eutra.  The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: UTRA frequency
Description: This parameter specifies the UTRA frequency. It must be configured if redirRAT=utraFDD.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".    The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: UTRA TDD frequency list
Description: This parameter specifies a list of UTRA TDD frequency. It must be configured if redirRAT=utraTDD.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".  The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN values list
Description: The parameter specifies a list of GERAN ARFCN values.  At least one element of the structure must be configured if redirRAT=geran.  The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN priority order
Description: The parameter specifies a priority order for GERAN ARFCN value according to which eNB shall built list of GERAN targets (CarrierFreqsGERAN IE of RedirectedCarrierInfo IE) in RRCConnectionRelease message with CSFB to GERAN via redirection.  GERAN ARFCN carriers will be placed in explicitListOfARFCNs IE as a choice of CarrierFreqsGERAN IE of RedirectedCarrierInfo IE in order of 'GERAN ARFCN priority order' value, starting from lowest value to highest configured by operator. GERAN ARFCN values without configured 'GERAN ARFCN priority order' will be placed at the end of list.    The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN value
Description: The parameter specifies a GERAN ARFCN value.  The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: GERAN band indicator
Description: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.  This parameter must always be configured if redirRAT=geran.  The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - NR neighbor cell SSB frequency
Description: The SSB frequency of the NR carrier used for redirection.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Duration of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the duration of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration) to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Offset of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the offset of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration). It is used together with periodicity to determine the first subframe of each SMTC window to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Periodicity of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the periodicity of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration). It is used together with offset to determine the first subframe of each SMTC window to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier
Description: Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier.  Configuration of ssbSubcarrierSpacing for a NR frequency in eNB must be the same as that in the neighboring gNB where UE is redirected to. Generally, for NR frequencies in FR1, ssbSubcarrierSpacing must be set to 15kHz or 30kHz. For NR frequencies in FR2, ssbSubcarrierSpacing must be set to 120 kHz or 240 kHz. Refer to TS 38.104 'Applicable SS raster entries per operating band' tables.

Parameter name: RAT for redirection
Description: This parameter selects the RAT to which the UE is redirected.  The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.
Range and step: eutra (0), geran (1), utraFDD (2), utraTDD (3), cdma2000HRPD (4), cdma20001xRTT (5), nr (6)

Parameter name: Redirection priority for UE context release
Description: This parameter defines the priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during UE Context Release with redirection procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 8 lowest.    The parameter is meaningless if the MODPR parameter autoAdapt is set to 'true'.

Parameter name: Idle mode mobility profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MOIMP.  It uniquely identifies a MOIMP instance.  MOIMP contains the Idle Mobility configuration to be assigned to UE with corresponding SPID or PLMN ID.  If MOIMP is not defined, then MODIMP configuration is used.

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of CDMA2000 HRPD parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message.

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band class for idle mode load balancing
Description: CDMA2000 HRPD band class value used for Idle Mode mobility.  The UE shall only perform Load Balancing cell reselection for bands already configured for Idle Mobility (in CDFIM) and transmitted in system information. There is no need to provide other bands than those configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such bands.

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band class prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the CDMA2000 HRPD band class used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: CDMA HRPD band weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of CDMA HRPD Band used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of CDMA2000 1xRTT parameters needed for an Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band class for idle mode load balancing
Description: CDMA2000 1xRTT band class value used for Idle Mode mobility  The UE shall only perform Load Balancing cell reselection for bands already configured for Idle Mobility (in CDFIM) and transmitted in system information.There is no need to provide bands other than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such bands.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band class prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the CDMA2000 1xRTT band class used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: CDMA 1xRTT band weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of CDMA 1xRTT Band used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of eUTRAN parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier frequency for idle mode load balancing
Description: eUTRA frequency as EARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility.  The UE only performs Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in IRFIM) and transmitted in system information. Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for 2CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 4CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for 4CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 5CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for 5CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 6CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for 6CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for 7CC CA UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the EUTRAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing for 7CC CA UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRAN carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the serving cell frequency layer used for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified the weight is considered as 0.

Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 4CC CA UEs. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor for idle mode load balancing for 7CC CA UEs
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for 7CC CA UEs.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing for CA capable UEs, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for EN-DC capable UEs.

Parameter name: EUTRA carrier weight factor for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of EUTRA carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: GERAN band parameters for idle mode load balancing - GERAN carrier freq band for idle mode load balancing
Description: This is an indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case ARFCN values are associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.    This parameter will be used together with geranCarFrqIdleModeL to build freqPriorityListGERAN IE in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for Load Balancing.

Parameter name: GERAN carrier freq list for idle mode load balancing
Description: GERAN frequency as ARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility.  Each ARFCN value explicitly listed.    The UE only performs only Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in GNFL) and transmitted in system information. It does not make sense to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.    This parameter will be used together with geranCarFrqBd to build freqPriorityListGERAN IE in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for Load Balancing.

Parameter name: GERAN band parameters for idle mode load balancing - GERAN carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the GERAN carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  This parameter will be used together with geranCarFrqIdleModeL to build freqPriorityListGERAN IE in IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: GERAN band parameters for idle mode load balancing - GERAN carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of GERAN carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of NR carrier (SA) parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) frequency for idle mode load balancing
Description: This parameter defines the NR ARFCN carrier frequency of the NR carrier used for Idle Mode mobility. It corresponds to GSCN value as specified in TS 38.101.    The UE only performs Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in NRFIM). There is no need to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) frequency preference for idle mode load balancing
Description: NR carrier (SA) frequency preference for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing.  1: higher than LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR2 PScell  2: between LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR2 PScell and LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR1 PScell only  3: lower than LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR1 PScell only      NR carrier (SA) is always preferred for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing over LTE carrier w/o EN-DC support.
Range and step: higher than EnDc FR2 (1), between EnDc FR2 and EnDc FR1 (2), lower than EnDc FR1 (3)

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) freq prio for idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs
Description: Absolute priority of NR carrier (SA) frequency layer used for secondary target selection of idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) weight factor for idle mode load balancing of NR SA capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of NR carrier (SA) frequency used by round robin algorithm for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs.

Parameter name: UTRA FDD carrier list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of UTRA-FDD parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message.

Parameter name: UTRA-FDD carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of UTRA FDD Carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: UTRA FDD carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the UTRAN FDD carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: UTRA FDD carrier freq for idle mode load balancing
Description: UTRA-FDD frequency as UARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility  The UE only performs Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in UFFIM) and transmitted in system information. There is no need to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.

Parameter name: UTRA TDD carrier list for idle mode load balancing
Description: List of UTRA-TDD parameters needed for Idle Mode mobility Load Balancing provided to UE in RRC Release message.

Parameter name: UTRA-TDD carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of UTRA TDD Carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  Weighted round robin algorithm shall always select one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always have the highest priority assigned in RRC Release message.  All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured for SIBs will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities.    The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.  When not specified, the weight is considered as 0.

Parameter name: UTRAN TDD carrier freq prio idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the UTRAN TDD carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest prio and 0 the lowest.  Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: UTRA TDD carrier freq for idle mode load balancing
Description: UTRA-TDD frequency as UARFCN value used for Idle Mode mobility  The UE shall only perform Load Balancing cell reselection for frequencies already configured for Idle Mobility (in UFFIM) and transmitted in system information. It does not make sense to provide other frequencies than configured already in SIBs. UE will ignore such frequencies.

Parameter name: Mobility profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MOPR.  It uniquely identifies a MOPR instance.

Parameter name: Allow EN-DC
Description: This parameter indicates whether measurement-based EN-DC and blind EN-DC setup are disabled or enabled and whether a dedicated NR frequency list or all neighbor NR frequency layers are considered.    Note: The parameter values have following meaning:  0:EN-DC disabled - both, measurement-based EN-DC and blind EN-DC setup are not allowed for UEs using this mobility profile.  1:dedicated_freq_layers - both, measurement-based EN-DC and blind EN-DC setup are allowed for UEs using this mobility profile and all neighbor NR frequency layers given in freqLayListEnDc are available (others are disabled).  2:all_freq_layers - both, measurement-based EN-DC and blind EN-DC setup are allowed for UEs using this mobility profile and no neighbor NR frequency layers are disabled (NOTE: this corresponds to legacy behavior).

Parameter name: Offload to UTRAN allowed
Description: This parameter indicates if the SPID Group is allowed to be offloaded to UTRAN for Connected Mode Load Balancing.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation blocking allowed
Description: This parameter indicates if a UE belonging to this mobility profile is subject to load-based carrier aggregation PCell and SCell blocking as defined by LTE4631.

Parameter name: Retry options for UE MR-DC Capability ENDC handover
Description: Defines the retry options for UE MR-DC capability based ENDC handover.  ENDC handover retries are NOT executed when 'noRetries' is selected, i.e. ENDC handover is attempted only when the UE, which is not a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC steering, enters the cell (e.g. via handover or initial context setup).  When configUeCapEndcHoRetry is set to 'priorityAboveLoadBasedHo' ENDC handover retries could be attempted periodically (see LNCEL.iFEndcHoRetryTimer) for the UE which is not a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover, and load balancing and load equalization handovers are not attempted.  When configUeCapEndcHoRetry is set to 'priorityBelowLoadBasedHo' ENDC handover retries could be attempted periodically for the UE which is not a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover, when eNB cell is not in load balancing or equalization active state.  Load balancing and load equalization handovers could be attempted for the UE which is not a candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover, with 'priorityBelowLoadBasedHo' or 'noRetries' selection. For the UEs which qualify for ENDC-HO steering, load equalization could be done only towards target frequencies which are ENDC anchor layers.  For the UE candidate for NR coverage-based handover the load balancing and load equalization handovers could be attempted only if allowed by nrCovEndcHoRetryPrio.  Note that Volte service based handover and MBMS steering are always of higher priority and they will be always attempted periodically, if applicable.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: EN-DC blocking allowed
Description: This parameter indicates if a UE belonging to this mobility profile is subject to load-based EN-DC blocking as defined by CB008308.

Parameter name: Extended range indicator for SPID-based IF HO
Description: This indicator is an index to the table with filtering threshold offsets for SPID-based IF HO, which are defined per target carrier frequency.  An offset for a certain target carrier frequency is selected by setting MOPR-erIndForSPIDHO == threshOffsetsIFSPIDFilter-ind in the respective instance of LNHOIF.  Note: If this parameter is not configured or no matching index 'ind' is found, then no offsets will be applied.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for EN-DC capability-based HO
Description: This list specifies the frequency layers that are candidate for EN-DC capability-based handover.  The eNB will, based on the configured frequency layer list, try to steer EN-DC capable UEs to those candidate layers with EN-DC capability-based handover, i.e. EN-DC capable UEs will be guided to those frequency layers actively by the eNB.    The configured values are only applicable if the feature EN-DC capability-based HO is activated.

Parameter name: Frequency layer for EN-DC capability-based HO
Description: Frequency layer for EN-DC capability-based handover.  The eNB will, based on the configured frequency layer list, try to steer EN-DC capable UEs to those candidate layers with EN-DC capability-based handover, i.e. EN-DC capable UEs will be guided to those frequency layers actively by the eNB.    The configured values are only applicable if the feature EN-DC capability-based HO is activated.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Preferred frequency layer
Description: Indicator for preferred frequency layer.  If this parameter is set to 'true', the frequency layer is candidate for EN-DC capability-based handover to preferred layer.    This parameter is applicable only in case EN-DC capability-based handover to preferred layer is activated in the LNCEL.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list high priority CSFB to TD-SCDMA
Description: List of TD-SCDMA target cell frequencies for high priority Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB).  No CSFB to TD-SCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for high priority CSFB to WCDMA
Description: List of WCDMA target cell frequencies for high priority Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB).    No CSFB to WCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list normal priority CSFB to TD-SCDMA
Description: List of TD-SCDMA target cell frequencies normal priority Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB).  No CSFB to TD-SCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for normal priority CSFB to WCDMA
Description: List of WCDMA target cell frequencies normal priority Circuit Switched Fallback (CSFB).    No CSFB to WCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the default profile if the parameter is omitted.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for ded. inter-frequency LB HO
Description: Specifies the dedicated target frequency layers for inter-frequency load balancing handovers. The configured values are only applicable if feature LTE2571 "Dedicated target frequency list for load balancing" is activated for inter-frequency LB frequencies, i.e. parameter actDedFreqListsLB is configured to 'inter-frequency' or 'all'(FDD only).  When the list does not contain any target frequency even if the feature is activated, the eNB will not allow inter-frequency load balancing handover to all targets.  If LTE1942 Dedicated VoLTE Inter-frequency Handover feature is activated, then the inter-frequency load balancing handover for VoLTE UEs will only be performed for frequency layers that are in both this list and in freqLayListDedVoLteHo of the MOPR instance.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for ded. VoLTE inter-frequency HO
Description: Specifies the dedicated target frequency layers for inter-frequency mobility during VoLTE calls. The configured values are only applicable if feature LTE1942 "Dedicated VoLTE IF frequency layers" is activated, i.e. the parameter actDedVoLteInterFreqHo is configured to 'true'.  When the list does not contain any target frequency even if the feature is activated, the eNB will not allow VoLTE inter-frequency handover to all targets.  For activated LTE1127 "Service Based Mobility Trigger" the list must include all frequency layers as defined in freqLayListServiceBasedHo of the same MOPR instance.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for ded. load based handover to WCDMA
Description: Specifies the dedicated target frequency layers for WCDMA load balancing handovers. The configured values are only applicable if feature LTE2571 "Dedicated target frequency list for load balancing" is activated for WCDMA LB frequencies, i.e. parameter actDedFreqListsLB is configured to 'inter-system' or 'all'.  When the list does not contain any target frequency even if the feature is activated, the eNB will not allow WCDMA load balancing handover to all targets.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: List of NR frequencies allowed for EN-DC
Description: List of NR target frequencies allowed for EN-DC.    Note: This structure currently has only one member, but might be enhanced in the future.

Parameter name: NR neighbor frequency allowed for EN-DC
Description: This parameter indicates the frequency of a NR neighbor cell layer allowed for EN-DC (SSB frequency).

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for IMMCI support at TAU
Description: Dedicated frequency (EARFCN) layer list, if IMMCI (Idle Mode Mobility Control Info) support during TAU is activated for selected EARFCN layers (MOPR-immciAtTau is equal to 'selected_layers').

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for LTE inter frequency mobility
Description: List of downlink carrier frequencies for LTE inter frequency mobility.  No LTE Inter Frequency mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: SSB frequency layer list for packet switched handover to NR
Description: The list of target SSB frequencies for handover to NR-SA for UE without VoLTE bearer.  No mobility to NR will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted

Parameter name: Voice specific SSB frequency layer list for handover to NR
Description: The list of target SSB frequencies for handover to NR-SA for UE with VoLTE bearer.  No mobility to NR will be provided to UEs with VoLTE bearer which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for PS handover TD-SCDMA
Description: List of TD-SCDMA target cell frequencies for packet switched handover.  No TD-SCDMA PS HO mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for packet switched handover WCDMA
Description: List of WCDMA target cell frequencies for packet switched handover.  No WCDMA PS HO mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for SPID-based IF HO
Description: Specifies the frequency layers that are preferred for SPID-based IF handover. The eNB will based on the configured frequency layer list try to steer UEs for the specified SPID values or combination of SPID, PLMN-ID, UE's EN-DC capabilities to those preferred layers via inter-frequency handover.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for QCIx service-based HO
Description: Specifies the frequency layers that are preferred for QCIx service-based handovers. With QCIx service-based HO enabled, the eNB will try to steer to these preferred layers via inter-frequency handover UEs with QCIx bearer (see qciTab-servBasedHoAllowed and qciTabOperator-servBasedHoAllowed) and mapped to the MOPR profile.    Note: If the list is empty/not configured, then QCIx SHBO is not allowed for UEs mapped to this dedicated mobility profile MOPR.

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for VoLTE service based HO
Description: Specifies the frequency layers that are preferred for service based handover. The eNB will, based on the configured frequency layer list, try to steer UEs with the established service to those preferred layers with service based handover, i.e. UEs with VoLTE calls will be guided to those frequency layers actively by the eNB. The configured values are only applicable if feature LTE1127 'Service Based Mobility Trigger' is activated, i.e. the parameter actInterFreqServiceBasedHo is configured to 'true'.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Frequency layer list for SRVCC to WCDMA
Description: List of WCDMA target cell frequencies for Single Radio Voice Call Continuity (SRVCC).    No SRVCC to WCDMA mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted.    The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: Inter Frequency Load Balancing candidate selection priority
Description: This parameter indicates UE candidate selection SPID priority for Connected Mode Load Balancing. With LTE3757 UE selection for offload is prioritized according to operator defined SPID groups.

Parameter name: Supported inter-RAT mode
Description: This parameter indicates the kind of inter-RAT mobility feature supported by the mobility profile.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing for CA capable UEs
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing.  This parameter is taken into account for load balancing when LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is true and the specific MOPR applies. (one MOPR is defined for the SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to UE).  When actSelMobPrf is false, "Percentage of UEs" to be taken into account for load balancing is defined in LNCEL.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing for TM9 capable UEs
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing for TM9 capable UEs.  This parameter is taken into account for load balancing when LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is true and the specific MOPR applies. (one MOPR is defined for the SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to UE).  When actSelMobPrf is false, "Percentage of UEs" to be taken into account for load balancing is defined in LNCEL.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing
Description: Percentage of UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing.  This parameter is taken into account for load balancing when LNBTS-actSelMobPrf is true and the specific MOPR applies. (one MOPR is defined for the SPID and/or PLMN ID assigned to UE).  When actSelMobPrf is false, "Percentage of UEs" to be taken into account for load balancing is defined in LNCEL.

Parameter name: UE-level IMMCI support at TAU
Description: This parameter defines the UE-level type of support for IMMCI (Idle Mode Mobility Control Info) during Tracking Area Update (TAU) for the dedicated mobility profiles MOPR.    Following options are available:  0: disabled - - the support for IMMCI during TAU is disabled for MOPR  1: enabled_layers - - the support for IMMCI during TAU in MOPR is enabled in all activated cells - see actImmciAtTau  2: selected_layers - - support during TAU in MOPR is enabled in all activated cells of enabled EARFCN layers (MOPR-freqLayListImmciAtTau)

Parameter name: Measurement gap enable for NR measurements
Description: This parameter is used to enable/disable measurement gaps in measurements of NR frequencies for FR1 and/or FR2 bands if a UE is mapped to the MOPR.  If actMPMeasGapForNR is 'true' and if MOPR-measGapEnabledNRMeas is configured then the value of NRMEAS[D]PR-measGapEnabledNRMeas is ignored.    Note: The parameter values have the following meaning:  0: Disable - measurement gaps are not configured  1: FR1Only - measurement gaps are configured for FR1 frequencies and not for FR2 frequencies  2: FR2Only - measurement gaps are configured for FR2 frequencies and not for FR1 frequencies  3: FR1AndFR2 - measurement gaps are configured for FR1 and FR2 frequencies

Parameter name: NR coverage-based EN-DC HO retries priority
Description: This parameter determines whether load-based handover retries are allowed for UE candidate for NR coverage-based EN-DC handover.
