If configured to a value other than 'EndcHo only', the load-based handovers (load balancing or load equalization) are prioritized and NR coverage-based EN-DC anchor handovers are not initiated for the UE at the time it is a candidate for load-based handover retries (i.e. in active load balancing or load equalization load state).
Range and step: EndcHo only (0), allow LB retry (1), allow LB and LE (2)

Parameter name: Reference freq. list network assisted cell change GERAN
Description: List of ARFCN values which are used as references to GERAN measurement objects (LNHOG).  All LNHOG objects of a cell, which contain at least the reference ARFCN value in arfcnValueListGERAN are selected for UE measurement configuration. If the same ARFCN value would be configured in more than one LNHOG instance of a cell, only the first found LNHOG object is considered.    No NACC to GERAN mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted.

Parameter name: Band indicator applied to reference ARFCN
Description: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either DCS1800 or PCS1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.

Parameter name: Reference ARFCN
Description: ARFCN value which is used as reference to a GERAN measurement object (LNHOG).

Parameter name: Reference frequency list for SRVCC to GSM
Description: List of ARFCN values which are used as references to GERAN measurement objects (LNHOG).  All LNHOG objects of a cell which contain at least the reference ARFCN value in arfcnValueListGERAN are selected for UE measurement configuration. If the same ARFCN value would be configured in more than one LNHOG instance of a cell, only the first found LNHOG object is considered.    No SRVCC to GSM mobility will be provided to UEs which are assigned to the profile if the parameter is omitted.

Parameter name: Band indicator applied to reference ARFCN
Description: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either DCS1800 or PCS1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.

Parameter name: Reference ARFCN
Description: ARFCN value which is used as reference to a GERAN measurement object (LNHOG).

Parameter name: Cell reselection method for idle mode load balancing
Description: Selection method for the target frequency/layer for idle mode load balancing.

Parameter name: Maximum time of periodic retries blocking in HO target cell
Description: This parameter determines the maximum time of EN-DC HO periodic retries blocking in target cell, after arrival from ENDC-HO target layer.    If parameter is not configured then blocking of periodic retries enabled for MR-DC capability-based HO or EN-DC HO to preferred layer by blockEndcHoRetryAtHoFromTrg, or for NR coverage-based EN-DC HO by blockNrEndcHoAtHoFromTrg, continues in handover target cell without time limit.  If parameter is set to special value 0 then enabled blocking is not applicable in target cell for UE mapped to this MOPR.

Parameter name: Mobility profile identifier for redirection
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MORED.  It uniquely identifies a MORED instance.

Parameter name: Add GSM system information to redirection message
Description: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which GSM system information is included in the RRC Connection Release message.  GSM system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further GSM cells will be omitted even if configured via LNLRELG settings.

Parameter name: Add UTRAN system information to redirection message
Description: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which UTRAN system information shall be included in the RRC Connection Release message.  UTRAN system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further UTRAN cells will be omitted even if configured via LNRELW settings.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Redirection priority for CS fallback with redirection
Description: This parameter defines the priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during CS Fallback with redirection procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 6 lowest.    The parameter is meaningless if LTE3337 is enabled and the MOPR parameter iRatMode is set to 'CDMA2000_1xRTT' as R8 1xCSFB always use LNCEL-REDRT parameters.

Parameter name: Redirection priority for emergency call
Description: This parameter defines the priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during Emergency Call handling procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 6 lowest.    The parameter is meaningless if LTE3337 is enabled and the MOPR parameter iRatMode is set to 'CDMA2000_1xRTT' as R8 1xCSFB always use LNCEL-REDRT parameters.

Parameter name: CDMA band
Description: This parameter specifies the cdma2000 band class. It must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000HRPD or redirRAT=cdma20001xRTT.

Parameter name: CDMA frequency
Description: This parameter specifies the cdma2000 ARFCN.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".    It must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000HRPD or redirRAT=cdma20001xRTT.

Parameter name: eUTRA frequency
Description: This parameter specifies the eUTRA frequency. It must be configured if redirRAT=eutra.

Parameter name: UTRA frequency
Description: This parameter specifies the UTRA frequency. It must be configured if redirRAT=utraFDD.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".

Parameter name: UTRA TDD frequency list
Description: This parameter specifies a list of UTRA TDD frequency. It must be configured if redirRAT=utraTDD.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".  This parameter must be configured if redirRat=utraTDD.  It specifies the TD-SCDMA frequencies list.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN values list
Description: The parameter specifies a list of GERAN ARFCN values.  At least one element of the structure must be configured if redirRAT=geran.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN priority order
Description: The parameter specifies a priority order for GERAN ARFCN value according to which eNB shall build list of GERAN targets (CarrierFreqsGERAN IE of RedirectedCarrierInfo IE) in RRCConnectionRelease message with CSFB to GERAN via redirection.  GERAN ARFCN carriers will be placed in explicitListOfARFCNs IE as a choice of CarrierFreqsGERAN IE of RedirectedCarrierInfo IE in order of 'GERAN ARFCN priority order' value starting from lowest value to highest configured by operator. GERAN ARFCN values without configured 'GERAN ARFCN priority order' will be placed at the end of list.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN value
Description: The parameter specifies a GERAN ARFCN value.

Parameter name: GERAN band indicator
Description: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.  This parameter must always be configured if redirRAT=geran.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - NR neighbor cell SSB frequency
Description: The SSB frequency of the NR carrier used for redirection.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Duration of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the duration of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration) to receive SS/PBCH blocks

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Offset of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the offset of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration). It is used together with periodicity to determine the first subframe of each SMTC window to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Periodicity of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the periodicity of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration). It is used together with offset to determine the first subframe of each SMTC window to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier
Description: Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier.  Configuration of ssbSubcarrierSpacing for a NR frequency in eNB must be the same as that in the neighboring gNB where UE is redirected to. Generally, for NR frequencies in FR1, ssbSubcarrierSpacing must be set to 15kHz or 30kHz. For NR frequencies in FR2, ssbSubcarrierSpacing must be set to 120 kHz or 240 kHz. Refer to TS 38.104 'Applicable SS raster entries per operating band' tables.

Parameter name: RAT for redirection
Description: This parameter selects the RAT to which the UE is redirected.
Range and step: eutra (0), geran (1), utraFDD (2), utraTDD (3), cdma2000HRPD (4), cdma20001xRTT (5), nr (6)

Parameter name: Redirection priority for UE context release
Description: This parameter defines the priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during UE Context Release with redirection procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 8 lowest.

Parameter name: Manual PUCCH configuration identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC MPUCCH_FDD.  It uniquely identifies a MPUCCH_FDD instance.

Parameter name: Add number active UEs radio reason handover
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.    This additional margin is used also for UEs accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Reduce load in serving cell" but only when Composite Available Capacity (CAC) in the cell is higher than 0. If CAC in the cell is zero, the HO for "Reduce load in serving cell" are always rejected.    The sum of maxNumActUE + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) must be less than the active UE capacity limits for the used bandwidth cell:  1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 840  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1000  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1250  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1500    This parameter is not used on any variant of AirScale ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOE/ASOF, ASOH/ASOG with at least one LTE cell configured as it is only used on non AirScale eNBs and (AirScale ABIA (any variant) without BBpooling activated) and dynamic PUCCH deactivated.    Dependencies:  (1) if riEnable is configured to 'true'  - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod  (2) if riEnable is configured to 'true' AND riPerM configured to '2'  - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp  (3) if riEnable is configured to 'true' AND riPerM configured to '1'  - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2    eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.    Any variant of AirScale ABIA only:  A special configuration has to be considered by operator:  - if AirScale deployment on 1 ABIA (any variant) has mixed BW cells i.e. at least 1 cell > 10MHz and cells <= 10 MHz then the 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells are restricted for parameter addAUeRrHo to 0...420.

Parameter name: Add number active UEs time critical handover
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.    The sum of maxNumActUE + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) must be less than the active UE capacity limits for the used bandwidth cell:  1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 840  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1000  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1250  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1500    This parameter is not used on any variant of AirScale ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ABIP/ABIQ, ASOE/ASOF, ASOG/ASOH with at least one LTE cell configured as it is only used on non AirScale eNBs and (AirScale ABIA/ABIAL without BBpooling activated) and dynamic PUCCH deactivated.    Dependencies:  (1) if riEnable is set configured to 'true'  - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod  (2) if riEnable is set configured to 'true' AND riPerM configured to '2'  - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp  (3) if riEnable is set configured to 'true' AND riPerM configured to '1'  - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2    eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.    Any variant of AirScale ABIA only:  A special configuration has to be considered by operator  - if AirScale deployment on 1 ABIA (any variant) has mixed BW cells i.e. at least 1 cell > 10MHz and cells <= 10 MHz then the 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells are restricted for parameter addAUeTcHo to 0...420.

Parameter name: Add Emergency Sessions
Description: Additional margin for Emergency Sessions.  This margin increases the thresholds for active UEs, active DRBs and active QCI1-DRBs in the cell if enhanced AC and GBR services (parameter actEnhAcAndGbrServices) are deactivated.    This margin increases the thresholds for only active UEs if enhanced AC and GBR services are activated.    The parameter is only relevant if actIMSEmerSessR9 is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise.    The parameter is only relevant on AirScale in case:  - BB pooling (actBbPooling) not activated  - enhanced AC and GBR services (parameter actEnhAcAndGbrServices) not activated  In this configuration this margin increases the thresholds of active DRBs and active QCI1 DRBs.    Emergency traffic shall have high preference against normal traffic in the cell.  The addEmergencySession value is used to increase several thresholds and it has to be considered, that the system limits are never exceeded for all resources.    The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 10  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 60  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 480  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 840  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 840    Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are:  1.4 MHz bandwidth 3  3 MHz bandwidth 4  5 MHz bandwidth 50  10 MHz bandwidth 70  15 MHz bandwidth 70  20 MHz bandwidth 90    Dependencies:  In order to give emergency sessions more chance to be established than normal handover traffic addEmergencySessions should be greater than max( addNumUeRadioReasHo, addNumUeTimeCriticalHo, addNumDrbRadioReasHo, addNumDrbTimeCriticalHo,  addNumQci1DrbRadioReasHo, addNumQci1DrbTimeCriticalHo).

Parameter name: Cell Sr Periodicity
Description: Define the admitted Scheduling Request periodicity in the cell, once the scheduling request reporting has been set to enable  This parameter is part of  sr-ConfigIndex  Parameter . See TS 36.213 [23,10.1].  Operator define periodicity and system define an allocation offset in time,; these two elements combined define the above mentioned sr-ConfigIndex    In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected:  IF riEnable is set to 'true' THEN  maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod  If the LNCEL is linked to AirScale ABIA/ABIAL and baseband pooling deactivated then  maxNumActUE + MinNumEmergencySessions + max(AddAUeRrHo,AddAUeTcHo) + MinNumRrcNoDrb <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod  eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is false.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CQI periodicity network period
Description: Sets the CQI Reporting Periodicity Np for CQI reporting.  Range is now extended up to include the 80ms periodicity option.  For each UE, the RRC algorithm calculate and add to this parameter a specific NOffset,CQI, depending on the UE offset allocation within the chosen periodicity determining the iCQI/PMI index value to be sent to UE.    EXAMPLE:  by default value of 20ms only iCQI/PMI index values among 17 and 36 will be allocated by CQI/PMI allocation algorithm.    In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected:  (1) if riEnable is set to 'true' and additionally riPerM is set to '2'  - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp  (2) if riEnable is set to 'true' and additionally riPerM is set to '1'  - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2    eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.

Parameter name: Delta cyclic shift for PUCCH
Description: Delta cyclic shift for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b.  This is a delta cyclic shift for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b. The shift is the cyclic shift difference between two adjacent ACK/NACK/Scheduling Request resources using the same orthogonal cover sequence and can be decided considering multipath delay spreads for the given cell deployment.

Parameter name: Max Number RRC
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection.  This threshold includes resource usage of UEs using this cell as SCell in case of Carrier Aggregation.  In case CAT-M UEs are served in the same cell (hosting cell) the admitted CAT-M UEs will reduce the RRC resources for legacy and CA SCell UEs accordingly up to maxNumRrcCatM because they share the same cell resources (admission is done according to first come first serve).  In case NB IoT UEs are served, there exists a separate RRC resource pool on FSMr3 but the configured sum of maxNumRrc and maxNumRrcNB cannot exceed the below given range limits.    This parameter is not used on AirScale, it used for internal calculation.    The maximum value depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:    1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 840  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1000  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1250  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1500    Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are:    1.4 MHz bandwidth 20  3 MHz bandwidth 80  5 MHz bandwidth 300  10 MHz bandwidth 300  15 MHz bandwidth 600  20 MHz bandwidth 600    Dependencies:  maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo) must be less than the margin values for the used bandwidth (see values above (40, 120, 840,1000,1250,1500))    For AirScale deployed eNBs the maximum values for the cells do not only depend on cell BW, but also on pool limits and configuration must be set as follows  - max cell BW limit >= maxNumActUE + MinNumRrcNoDrb.  A special configuration has to be considered by operator:  - if AirScale ABIA/ABIAL and actBbPooling is set to 'false' deployment on 1 ABIA/ABIAL has mixed BW cells i.e. at least 1 cell > 10MHz and cells <= 10 MHz then the 5 MHz and 10 MHz cells then the configuration is restricted to allow (maxNumActUE + MinNumRrcNoDrb) = 0...420.    In case of interworking with CAT-M the allowed CAT-M UEs (configurable threshold maxNumRrcCatM range up to 360) may reduce the available RRC connection resources for legacy and CA SCell UEs as they share the same resource pool and the sum may not exceed the given values for the used bandwidth (see above {40, 120, 840,1000,1250,1500})

Parameter name: Max Number RRC Emergency
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection, used to admit RRC connections for emergency calls.  In order to give emergency sessions more chance to be established than normal traffic maxNumRrcEmergency should be greater than maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo)  The parameter is only relevant if actEmerCallRedir is set to 'true' OR actIMSEmerSessR9 is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise.    The emergency call is only recognized when the UE was in idle state before initiating the connection.  The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  1.4 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 40  3 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 120  5 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 840  10 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1000  15 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1250  20 MHz bandwidth 0 .. 1500    Please note that the default value is not suitable for all bandwidths. The recommended values are:  1.4 MHz bandwidth 35  3 MHz bandwidth 100  5 MHz bandwidth 440  10 MHz bandwidth 560  15 MHz bandwidth 800  20 MHz bandwidth 800    Dependencies:  In order to give emergency sessions more chance to be established than normal traffic maxNumRrcEmergency should be greater than maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo, addAUeTcHo)  The parameter is only relevant if actEmerCallRedir is set to 'true' OR actIMSEmerSessR9 is set to 'true' and ignored otherwise.    In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected:    (1) if riEnable is set to 'true'  maxNumRrcEmergency <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod  (2) if riEnable is set to 'true' AND riPerM is set to '2'  maxNumRrcEmergency <= nCqiRb * 6 * cqiPerNp  (3) if riEnable is set to 'true' AND riPerM is set to '1'  maxNumRrcEmergency <= nCqiRb * 6 * cqiPerNp/2    eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is configured to 'false'.    For AirScale this parameter is not relevant!

Parameter name: Min number emergency sessions
Description: Minimum number reserved RRC connection resources for Emergency Sessions. This parameter is only used by AirScale in case dynamic PUCCH features are not activated.    Note: This parameter is even relevant, if emergency call handling is de-activated ( actEmerCallRedir or actIMSEmerSessR9 are set to false) in order to have reserve for high priority calls;    If dynamic PUCCH features are activated and AirScale is deployed, then the aPucchMinNumEmergencySessions parameter has to be configured.

Parameter name: Min number RRC
Description: This parameter is only for AirScale without baseband pooling and ignored otherwise.    Minimum allocated number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection.  This is needed for AirScale where resources may be shifted from one cell to the other where needed.  This parameter is only used in case dynamic PUCCH features are not activated.    If dynamic PUCCH features are activated and AirScale is deployed, then the aPucchMinNumRrc parameter has to be configured.  If dynamic PUCCH features are activated and AirScale is deployed, then the aPucchMinNumRrc parameter has to be configured.

Parameter name: Min number RRC No DRB
Description: Minimum number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection without a DRB establishment (e.g. doing tracking area updates); this parameter is relevant as additional margin for a minimum resource configuration. It is only used by AirScale in case dynamic PUCCH features are not activated.    If dynamic PUCCH features are activated and AirScale is deployed, then the aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb parameter has to be configured instead of this one.

Parameter name: ACK/NACK offset
Description: Offset used to calculate ACK/NACK resource from PDCCH CCE.  This is the AckNack index offset relative to the lowest CCE index of the associated DL scheduling PDCCH.    In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected:  if riEnable is set to 'true'  - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= n1PucchAn * cellSrPeriod    eNB will not check these rules when actCompChecks is false.

Parameter name: PUCCH bandwidth for CQI
Description: Number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b/3.  It is part of the set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called MaxPucchResourceSize. All other parameters are related to each other according to this formula:    Note: in the formula below the term dlChBw shall be considered in # of PRB and not in MHz!    MaxPucchResourceSize = nCqiRb + roundup{[((rounddown (((maxNrSymPdcch * 12 - X) * dlChBw - roundup (phichRes * (dlChBw / 8)) * 12 - 16) / 36)) + n1PucchAn - pucchNAnCs * 3 / deltaPucchShift ) * deltaPucchShift] / (3*12)} + roundup (pucchNAnCs / 8)-blankedPucch,  where  X=4; when maxNrSymPdcch = 1 or dlMimoMode set to 'SingleTX', 'TXDiv', 'Static Open Loop MIMO', 'Dynamic Open Loop MIMO' or 'Closed Loop Mimo'  X=8 when maxNrSymPdcch > 1 and dlMimoMode set to '4-way TXDiv' or 'Closed Loop MIMO (4x2)'    All parameters in this formula are configuration parameters, while MaxPucchResourceSize is a calculated value that has a maximum allowed value, which shall not be exceeded.  Therefore the MaxPucchResourceSize is utilized to determine the correct offset allocation of the PRACH resources and to verify that the maximal allowed amount of PUCCH resources per BW is not overcome.    In order to avoid PUCCH overbooking the following rules should be respected:  (1) If riEnable set to 'true' AND riPerM set to '2'  - maxNumRrc + max (addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp  (2) If riEnable set to 'true' AND riPerM set to '1'  - maxNumRrc + max(addAUeRrHo,addAUeTcHo) <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp/2    If the LNCEL is linked to AirScale ABIA / ABIAL and baseband pooling is deactivated then  (3) if riEnable is set to 'true' and additionally riPerM is set to '2'  - maxNumActUE + MinNumEmergencySessions + max(AddAUeRrHo,AddAUeTcHo) + MinNumRrcNoDrb <= (nCqiRb - blankedPucch) * 6 * cqiPerNp

Parameter name: Number of PUCCH PRBs for HARQ Format 3
Description: This parameter defines how many PRBs are allocated to Format 3 HARQ process when the cell is configured to support carrier aggregation with more than or equal to three component carriers.

Parameter name: PHICH duration
Description: Indicates the duration of PHICH.    phichDur also puts a lower limit on the size of the control region signalled by the PCFICH. Therefore, when phichDur is set to value (Extended), three OFDMA symbols need to be enabled to for PDCCH and maxNrSymPdcch needs to be set to value 3  When phichDur is set to value (Normal), PHICH is transmitted in the first OFDMA symbol, and when phichDur is set to value (Extended), PHICH is transmitted in first three OFDMA symbols.    phichDur is transmitted in system information as information is cell specific, and all UEs need to know whether to receive PHICH from 1 or 3 symbols.    phichDur also puts a lower limit on the size of the control region signalled by the PCFICH. Therefore, when phichDur is set to value (Extended), three OFDMA symbols need to be enabled for PDCCH and maxNrSymPdcch needs to be set to value 3. For further info see Table 6.9.3-1 in TS 36.211.    Hint for cells with bandwidth 1.4 MHz:  A slightly improved PDCCH and PHICH performance could be achieved if extended PHICH is configured.  Rationale: with phichDur set to 1 (meaning "extended PHICH Duration") the PHICH REs are distributed over 3 OFDMA symbols, so both time diversity for PHICH and better distribution of PHICH excess power used as a source for PDCCH power boost can be achieved.    Hint for downlink-only cell operating in unlicensed bands as defined in parameter actUnlicensedAcc: It is recommended to set this parameter to 'Normal'.

Parameter name: PHICH resource
Description: Indicates the PHICH resource size.  The Physical Hybrid ARQ Indicator Channel (PHICH) carries the hybrid-ARQ ACK/NAK. Multiple PHICHs mapped to the same set of resource elements constitute a PHICH group and the PHICH resource parameter defines the number of PHICH groups.    Hint for downlink-only cell operating in unlicensed bands as defined in parameter actUnlicensedAcc: It is recommended to set this parameter to 'N=1/6'.

Parameter name: Rank indication reporting enable
Description: Determines whether RI reporting is enabled (true) or not (false).

Parameter name: Multiplier M for periodic RI reporting period
Description: Multiplier M for defining periodic RI feedback reporting period.  It defines the multiplier for the cqiPerNp which results in the periodicity for RI periodic reports. RI periodicity = cqiPerNp * riPerM. When riPerM is equal to 1 (M=1) the parameter riPerOffset must be set to -1 (CQI and Ri are adjacent) while when riPerM is set to 2 (M=2) the parameter riPerOffset must set to 0 (in this case CQI and RI alternate).

Parameter name: Periodic RI reporting offset
Description: Time offset for periodic CQI/PMI reporting for defining the periodic RI reporting instance  The parameter defines the offset for periodic Rank Indicator reporting instance. The offset tells the time shift for the periodic CQI/PMI reporting instance. The range of the offset depends on the periodicity (cqiPerNp) of periodic CQI/PMI reporting.

Parameter name: Manual PUCCH configuration identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC MPUCCH_TDD.  It uniquely identifies a MPUCCH_TDD instance.

Parameter name: Add Number Active Ues Radio Reason Handover
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 10MHz bandwidth 0..550 (recommended: 20)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..800 (recommended: 30)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 20)    If the LNCEL is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 5MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 or conf.1 or conf.2, 0..192 (recommended: 10)  - for 10MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..400 (recommended: 20)  - for 15MHz and 20MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 30)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..400 (recommended: 20)    This parameter is not used on the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ASOE/ASOF as it is only used with dynamic PUCCH deactivated.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Add Number Active Ues Time Critical Handover
Description: Additional margin for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via hand over with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO". This margin is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 10MHz bandwidth 0..550 (recommended: 30)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..800 (recommended: 45)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 30)    If the LNCEL is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIA:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 5MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 or conf.1 or conf.2, 0..192 (recommended: 15)  - for 10MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..400 (recommended: 30)  - for 15MHz and 20MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 45)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..400 (recommended: 30)    This parameter is not used on the LNCEL which is linked to any variant of AirScale ABIC, ABIN, ABIO, ASOE/ASOF as it is only used with dynamic PUCCH deactivated.

Parameter name: Add Emergency Sessions
Description: Additional margin for Emergency Sessions;  this margin increases the thresholds for active UEs, active DRBs with a factor and active QCI1-DRBs in the cell  Emergency traffic shall have high preference against normal traffic in the cell.  The addEmergencySession value is used to increase several thresholds and it has to be considered, that the system limits are never exceeded for all resources.    The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 10 MHz bandwidth 0..550 (recommended: 20)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..800 (recommended: 30)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 20)    AirScale:  The maximum margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 or conf.1 or conf.2, 0..192 (recommended: 10)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..400 (recommended: 20)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 30)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..400 (recommended: 20)    the range of this parameter may be adapted considering baseband pooling configuration, including the value of actBbPooling    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Cell Sr periodicity
Description: Define the admitted Scheduling Request periodicity in the cell, once the scheduling request reporting has been set to enable  This parameter is part of  sr-ConfigIndex  Parameter . See TS 36.213 [23,10.1].  Operator define periodicity and system define an allocation offset in time; these two elements combined define the above mentioned sr-ConfigIndex

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CQI periodicity network period
Description: Periodic CQI / PMI feedback reporting period  The parameter defines the periodicity of periodic CQI / PMI feedback on PUCCH or PUSCH.

Parameter name: Delta cyclic shift for PUCCH
Description: Delta cyclic shift for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b.  This is a delta cyclic shift for PUCCH formats 1/1a/1b. The shift is the cyclic shift difference between two adjacent ACK/NACK/Scheduling Request resources using the same orthogonal cover sequence and can be decided considering multipath delay spreads for the given cell deployment.  Default Value: 1

Parameter name: Max Number RRC
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection  The maximum value depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 10 MHz bandwidth 0..550 (recommended: 200)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..800 (recommended: 300)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 200)    AirScale:  The maximum value depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 or conf.1 or conf.2, 0..192 (recommended: 100)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..400 (recommended: 200)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 300)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..400 (recommended: 200)    For AirScale deployed eNBs the maximum values for the cells do not only depend on cell BW but also on pool limits and maxNumRrc must be set as follows  - maxNumRrc = maxNumActUE + MinNumRrcNoDrb.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Max Number RRC Emergency
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection for an emergency call  The emergency call is only recognized when the UE was in idle state before initiating the connection.    The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 10 MHz bandwidth 0..550 (recommended: 300)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1, 0..800 (recommended: 400)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 300)    AirScale:    The maximum additional margin depends on the bandwidth of the cell. The following values are allowed:  - for 5 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0 or conf.1 or conf.2, 0..192 (recommended: 100)  - for 10 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..400 (recommended: 300)  - for 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.1 or conf.2, 0..600 (recommended: 400)  - for 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth with TDD conf.0, 0..400 (recommended: 300)    For AirScale deployed this parameter is not relevant;

Parameter name: Min number emergency sessions
Description: Minimum number reserved RRC connection resources for Emergency Sessions. This parameter is only used by AirScale in case dynamic PUCCH features are not activated.    Note: This parameter is even relevant, if emergency call handling is de-activated ( actEmerCallRedir or actIMSEmerSessR9 are set to false) in order to have reserve for high priority calls;    If dynamic PUCCH features are activated and AirScale is deployed, then the aPucchMinNumEmergencySessions parameter has to be configured.

Parameter name: Min number RRC
Description: Minimum allocated number of UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection.  This is needed for AirScale where resources may be shifted from one cell to the other where needed. This parameter is only used by AirScale in case dynamic PUCCH features are not activated.    If dynamic PUCCH features are activated and AirScale is deployed, then the aPucchMinNumRrc parameter has to be configured.

Parameter name: Min number RRC No DRB
Description: Minimum number of UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection without a DRB establishment (e.g. doing tracking area updates); this parameter is relevant as additional margin for a minimum resource configuration. It is only used by AirScale in case dynamic PUCCH features are not activated.    If dynamic PUCCH features are activated and AirScale is deployed, then the aPucchMinNumRrcNoDrb parameter has to be configured instead of this one.

Parameter name: ACK/NACK offset
Description: Offset used to calculate ACK/NACK resource from PDCCH CCE.  This is the AckNack index offset relative to the lowest CCE index of the associated DL scheduling PDCCH.  Parameter is one parameter in a set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called as MaxPucchResourceSize.

Parameter name: PUCCH bandwidth for CQI
Description: Number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b/3.  This parameter is the number of Physical Resource Blocks that are reserved for PUCCH formats 2/2a/2b/3.    This parameter is part of the set which defines the maximum PUCCH allocation called MaxPucchResourceSize. All other parameters are related to each other according to this formula:  Note: in the formula below the term dlChBw shall be considered in # of PRB and not in MHz!    MaxPucchResourceSize = nCqiRb + roundup{[ (max((M-i-1)* Np +i*Np1 + rounddown (((12 * (maxNrSymPdcch-Yi) - X) * chBw - mi*roundup(phichRes * (chBw / 8)) * 12 - 16 )/ 36)) + n1PucchAn - pucchNAnCs * c / deltaPucchShift) * deltaPucchShift] / (c*12)} + roundup (pucchNAnCs / 8),  All other parameters in this formula are O&M parameters, while MaxPucchResourceSize is a calculated value that has a maximum allowed value, which shall not be exceeded  Therefore the MaxPucchResourceSize is utilized to determine the correct offset allocation of the PRACH resources and to verify that the maximal allowed amount of PUCCH resouces per BW is not overcome.    Note: When CBRS related feature(s) are enabled, this parameter's value may be overridden by eNB based on CBRS/SAS allocation.

Parameter name: Number of PUCCH PRBs for HARQ format 3
Description: This parameter defines how many PRBs are allocated for PUCCH format 3.

Parameter name: PHICH duration
Description: Indicates the duration of PHICH.    phichDur also puts a lower limit on the size of the control region signaled by the PCFICH. Therefore, when phichDur is set to value (Extended), three OFDMA symbols need to be enabled to for PDCCH and maxNrSymPdcch needs to be set to value 3  When phichDur is set to value (Normal), PHICH is transmitted in the first OFDMA symbol, and when phichDur is set to value (Extended), PHICH is transmitted in first three OFDMA symbols.    phichDur is transmitted in system information as information is cell specific, and all UEs need to know whether to receive PHICH from 1 or 3 symbols.    phichDur also puts a lower limit on the size of the control region signaled by the PCFICH. Therefore, when phichDur is set to value (Extended), three OFDMA symbols need to be enabled for PDCCH and maxNrSymPdcch needs to be set to value 3. For further info see Table 6.9.3-1 in TS 36.211.

Parameter name: PHICH resource
Description: Indicates the PHICH resource size.  The Physical Hybrid ARQ Indicator Channel (PHICH) carries the hybrid-ARQ ACK/NAK. Multiple PHICHs mapped to the same set of resource elements constitute a PHICH group and the PHICH resource parameter defines the number of PHICH groups.

Parameter name: Rank indication reporting enable
Description: Determines whether RI reporting is enabled (true) or not (false).

Parameter name: Multiplier M for periodic RI reporting period
Description: Multiplier M for defining periodic RI feedback reporting period. It defines the multiplier for the cqiPerNp which results in the periodicity for RI periodic reports. RI periodicity = cqiPerNp * riPerM. When riPerM is equal to 0 (M=1) the parameter riPerOffset must be set to -1 (CQI and Ri are adjacent) while when riPerM is set to 1 (M=2) the parameter riPerOffset must set to 0 (in this case CQI and RI alternate).

Parameter name: Periodic RI reporting offset
Description: Time offset for periodic CQI/PMI reporting for defining the periodic RI reporting instance  The parameter defines the offset for periodic Rank Indicator reporting instance. The offset tells the time shift for the periodic CQI/PMI reporting instance. The range of the offset depends on the periodicity (cqiPerNp) of periodic CQI/PMI reporting.

Parameter name: Cell trace session identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC MTRACE.  Due to support of 192 cells per eNB the maximum number of cell trace sessions is extended, too.

Parameter name: Activate PCMD reporting
Description: This parameter activates the PCMD reporting for a trace session.  This parameter does not apply to NB-IoT technology.

Parameter name: Activate UE throughput measurement reports
Description: This parameter activates the UE throughput measurement reports for a trace session.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - Angle of arrival tracing
Description: This parameter describes whether tracing of AoA as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing is enabled or not.    This parameter is only applicable for TDD and 8 TX RRU.

Parameter name: Immediate MDT control - Cell maximum active MDT UEs traced
Description: Defines the maximum number of active MDT UEs configured for MDT UE measurement reporting within a cell. This value is set by the operator at MDT trace session start.    Only UEs that enter the cell (Initial Context Setup, Handover or RRC re-establishment) can be selected for MDT, i.e. will be configured for periodic measurement of reportStrongestCell (RSRP/RSRQ of serving cell and neighbor cells).    Only UEs that were configured for periodic UE measurement reporting and did not reach the reportAmount are counted as active MDT UEs.    UEs that were configured for periodic UE measurement reporting will continue to be traced after the last measurement report in an ImmediateMDTAndTrace session until the end of the call.    Also in case when the lcrId parameter is not set, i.e. the trace session is configured for all cells in the eNB, then this parameter cellMaxActiveMDTUEsTraced limits the number of active MDT UEs to be traced in each cell. This then limits the total number of MDT UEs traced per eNB as cellMaxActiveMDTUEsTraced multiplied by the number of cells in eNB. For the whole eNB operator shall not configure more than 900 UEs to be selected for LTE2202.

Parameter name: Cell maximum active UEs traced
Description: Defines the maximum number of active UE connections traced within a cell for a trace session. This value is set by operator at trace session start.    When maximum number of UEs that are traced for this trace session is reached in eNB, then eNB will continue to trace the currently traced UEs until the UEs leave the cell.  Also in case when the lcrId parameter is not set, i.e. the trace session is configured for all cells in the eNB, then this parameter cellMaxActiveUEsTraced limits the number of active UEs to be traced in each cell. This then limits the total number of UEs traced per eNB as cellMaxActiveUEsTraced multiplied by the number of cells in eNB. For the whole eNB operator shall not configure more than 900 UEs to be selected for LTE2202.    If jobType is "RLFReportsOnly" the parameter cellMaxActiveUEsTraced shall be ignored.

Parameter name: Cell vendor specific tracing - Cell TA tracing
Description: This parameter describes whether tracing of instantaneous TA value on cell level as part of vendor specific extension tracing is enabled or not.

Parameter name: Cell trace mode
Description: This indicates the status of the cell trace session i.e. whether the cell trace session is enabled or disabled.    Note: This parameter currently should only be set to enabled (i.e. TRUE).

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN trace identifier - MCC
Description: MCC of PLMN ID contained in Trace Reference  This is the MCC of the PLMN ID contained in the Trace Reference of E-UTRAN Trace ID.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN trace identifier - MNC
Description: MNC of PLMN ID contained in Trace Reference  This is the MNC of the PLMN ID contained in the Trace Reference of E-UTRAN Trace ID.

Parameter name: Force UE IDs repetition
Description: This optional parameter configures the eNB to send the three parameters MME UE S1AP ID, ENB UE S1AP ID and GUMMEI either in every trace record where they are available (true) of only once per call (false).    This field shall only be set to 'true' when required by used TCE.

Parameter name: MDT inter-frequency list
Description: The parameters of this structure describe Frequency and Measurement BW for MDT inter-frequency purpose

Parameter name: Frequency
Description: This parameter contains frequency used for inter-frequency MDT.

Parameter name: Measurement BW
Description: This parameter contains measurement bandwidth for frequency used in inter-frequency MDT.

Parameter name: Immediate MDT control - Percentage of MDT inter-frequency
Description: This parameter defines the percentage of MDT UEs configured for inter-frequency UE periodic measurement.

Parameter name: Immediate MDT control - Anonymization of immediate MDT data
Description: This parameter provides anonymization of MDT data to prevent subscriber identity from being sent to the Trace Collection Entity (TCE).    It is only used when Job Type is "Immediate MDT Only" or "Immediate MDT and Trace".  IMEI-TAC = The eNB shall send the CELL TRAFFIC TRACE message to the MME with the Privacy Indicator information element.    No identity = The eNB shall not send the CELL TRAFFIC TRACE message to the MME.

Parameter name: Immediate MDT control - Immediate MDT force UE consent
Description: This parameter controls whether the eNB will utilize or ignore the user consent for management based MDT when selecting UEs for Immediate MDT.      False - user consent not forced, i.e. the eNB considers "Management Based MDT Allowed" information element when selecting UE.    True - user consent forced, i.e. the eNB ignores "Management Based MDT Allowed" information element when selecting UE.

Parameter name: Immediate MDT control - Immediate MDT obtain location
Description: This parameter controls whether the eNB requests the UE to attempt to provide detailed location information.    It is only used when the Job Type is "Immediate MDT Only" or "Immediate MDT and Trace".  The UE is requested to attempt to have valid detailed location information available whenever sending a measurement report for which it is configured to include available detailed location information. The UE may not succeed e.g. because the user manually disabled the GPS hardware, due to no/poor satellite coverage. Further details, e.g. regarding when to activate GNSS, are up to UE implementation.    False - The eNB does not send the obtainLocationConfig-r11 field in RRC signaling to UE.    True - The eNB sends the obtainLocationConfig-r11 field in RRC signaling to UEs which are GNSS capable and are 3GPP Release 11 (or higher).

Parameter name: Immediate MDT control - Immediate MDT positioning method
Description: This parameter defines whether GNSS positioning method is applied to the Immediate MDT job or no positioning method is used.    For 'GNSS' method, the eNB will send the RRC includeLocationInfo field to the UE as part of measurement configuration. The UE will provide the GPS location information, if available, in the measurement report.    It is only used when the Job Type is set to "Immediate MDT" or "Immediate MDT and Trace".    Only GNSS is supported as a positioning method with Immediate MDT (E-Cell ID is not supported, but defined in TS 32.422 for positioning method)

Parameter name: Immediate MDT control - Immediate MDT select only GNSS UEs
Description: This parameter is used to limit the Immediate MDT to those UEs which are GNSS capable. It is used when the Job Type is "Immediate MDT Only" or "Immediate MDT and Trace".  False - any UE (independent of GNSS capability) can be considered for Immediate MDT.    True - only GNSS capable UEs will be configured for Immediate MDT.

Parameter name: Interface Selection
Description: This optional parameter allows the operator to choose the interface type for the trace session.    For NetAct TraceViewer only the old (NSNTI) interface is possible.  Other TCE tools don't support NSNTI interface.  When PCMD reporting is enabled or forceUeIdsRepetition is 'true' only the new (NSETAP) interface is possible.

Parameter name: Job type
Description: This parameter describes the type of trace session: ImmediateMDTOnly, ImmediateMDTAndTrace, TraceOnly or RLFReportsOnly. It shall be set by the operator.  For each cell there can be only one MTRACE object with jobType set to ImmediateMDTOnly or ImmediateMDTAndTrace.  NB-IoT technology is supported only when MTRACE-jobType is set to TraceOnly or to ImmediateMDTAndTrace.

Parameter name: Local cell resource identifier
Description: This parameter contains the Local Cell Resource Identifier (lcrId) of the Cell corresponding to the traced cell. It is the same as contained under LNCEL object.  MTRACE-lcrId shall be related to a real cell inside the eNB.  This contains the local cell resource identifier of the cell for which trace needs to be enabled.

Parameter name: Maximum buffering time
Description: This parameter configures the maximum buffering time for trace records until they are sent to the TCE.

Parameter name: Immediate MDT control - Maximum number of MDT Frequency Layers
Description: This parameter defines the maximum number of frequency layers used for MDT periodic measurements per UE.  1: each UE will be configured for either intra-frequency or inter-freq measurements (same as LTE2585)  2: intra-freq and one inter-freq measurement  3: intra-freq and two inter-freq measurements  4: intra-freq and three inter-freq measurements  5-17: intra-freq and 4 - 16 inter-freq measurements

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - PDSCH PRB Number Tracing
Description: Parameter pDSCHPRBNumberTracing configures whether tracing of PDSCH PRB Number Tracing, as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing, is enabled or not.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - Power HeadRoom tracing
Description: This parameter describes whether tracing of PHR as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing is enabled or not.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - PUSCH PRB Number Tracing
Description: Parameter pUSCHPRBNumberTracing configures whether tracing of PUSCH PRB Number Tracing, as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing, is enabled or not.

Parameter name: Periodic UE measurements - Report amount
Description: Number of periodic ReportStrongestCells measurement reports configured at the UE

Parameter name: Periodic UE measurements - Report interval
Description: Time interval between two consecutive periodic ReportStrongestCells measurement reports configured at the UE

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - RIP report interval
Description: Parameter ripReportInterval defines the reporting interval for RIP measurements and Remote Interference Report (RIR) measurements. This parameter is common for RIP and RIR measurements.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - RIP report type
Description: There are two types of RIP reporting: type1 for per RB&subframe&slot reporting (value RB_subframe_slot) and type2 for per subframe&slot based reporting (value subframe_slot).

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - RIP tracing
Description: Parameter ripTracing configures whether tracing of RIP as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing is enabled or not.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - Remote interference report tracing
Description: Parameter rirTracing configures whether tracing of RIR as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing is enabled or not.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - Timing advance tracing synchronized
Description: This parameter describes whether tracing of TA as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing is enabled or not.

Parameter name: 3rd party tool cell trace port number
Description: The Trace Port Number to be used for this Cell trace session while establishing trace connection(TCP) towards 3rd Party Tool. This will be used only if 3rd Party Tracing for Cell Trace is used.

Parameter name: Trace collection entity IP address
Description: IP address of the trace collection entity of 3rd Party Tool. This will be used only if 3rd Party Tracing for Cell Trace is enabled and the provided IP address is different from NetAct IP address.  This is the IP address of Trace Collection Entity, i.e., to which all trace records are sent for the user Trace Session.    If feature LTE955 is activated, the operator must provide an IPv6 address, otherwise the operator must provide an IPv4 address.    For IPv4, the parameter has to be entered in dotted decimal format.    For IPv6, the parameter has to be entered according to formats specified in RFC2460.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).  Note: IP 127.0.0.1 is allowed. Parameter should be filled with IP 127.0.0.1 when TCE is NetAct.    IPv6 address ranges:  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).  Note: ::1 value can be used when TCE is NetAct.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN trace identifier - Trace ID
Description: Trace ID identifies a cell trace session. In combination with PLMN ID, the identifier becomes unique.  Trace ID is part of Trace Reference contained in E-UTRAN Trace ID.  E-UTRAN Trace ID is unique id identifying a trace session.  E-UTRAN Trace ID is made up of Trace Reference and Trace Recording Session Reference.  Trace Reference is globally unique and is 6 Octect length comprising of:  MCC+MNC+Trace ID.    MCC+MNC is of 3 Octet length  Trace ID is of 3 Octet length    E-UTRAN Trace ID is one of the trace parameters received for a trace session.

Parameter name: Trace RRC msg category
Description: If traceRrcMsgCategory = UEspecific then the parameter traceRrcUeSpecMsgLst contains list of UE specific messages to be traced.  If traceRrcMsgCategory = nonUEspecific then the parameter traceRrcNonUeSpecMsgLst contains list of non-UE specific messages to be traced.  If traceRrcMsgCategory = all, then the both lists are present.

Parameter name: Trace RRC non UE spec msg list
Description: If traceRrcMsgCategory = all or traceRrcMsgCategory = nonUEspecific then traceRrcNonUeSpecMsgList contains list of enum for the non-UE specific messages to be traced.  Note: These non-UE specific (eNB related) messages (e.g. Paging) were not included in RL20 cell trace, but only in interface trace.

Parameter name: Trace RRC setting
Description: This parameter indicates if all RRC messages are traced (all), specific list(s) of RRC messages as defined in parameter traceRrcMsgCategory (specific), or RRC not traced at all (none).

Parameter name: Trace RRC UE spec msg list
Description: If traceRrcMsgCategory = all or traceRrcMsgCategory = UEspecific then traceRrcUeSpecMsgList contains list of enum for the UE specific messages to be traced.

Parameter name: Trace S1 msg category
Description: If traceS1MsgCategory = UEspecific then the parameter traceS1UeSpecMsgLst contains list of UE specific messages to be traced.  If traceS1MsgCategory = nonUEspecific then the parameter traceS1NonUeSpecMsgLst contains list of non-UE specific messages to be traced.  If traceS1MsgCategory = all, then the both lists are present.

Parameter name: Trace S1 non UE spec msg list
Description: If traceS1MsgCategory = all or traceS1MsgCategory = nonUEspecific then traceS1NonUeSpecMsgList contains list of enum for the non-UE specific messages to be traced.  Note: These non-UE specific (eNB related) messages (e.g. S1 setup or reset) were not included in RL20 cell trace, but only in interface trace.

Parameter name: Trace S1 setting
Description: This parameter indicates if all S1 messages are traced (all), specific list(s) of S1 messages as defined in parameter traceS1MsgCategory (specific), or S1 not traced at all (none).

Parameter name: Trace S1 UE spec msg list
Description: If traceS1MsgCategory = all or traceS1MsgCategory = UEspecific then traceS1UeSpecMsgList contains list of enum for the UE specific messages to be traced.

Parameter name: Trace X2 msg category
Description: If traceX2MsgCategory = UEspecific then the parameter traceX2UeSpecMsgLst contains list of UE specific messages to be traced.  If traceX2MsgCategory = nonUEspecific then the parameter traceX2NonUeSpecMsgLst contains list of non-UE specific messages to be traced.  If traceX2MsgCategory = all, then the both lists are present.

Parameter name: Trace X2 non UE spec msg list
Description: If traceX2MsgCategory = all or traceX2MsgCategory = nonUEspecific then traceX2NonUeSpecMsgList contains list of enum for the non-UE specific messages to be traced.  Note: These non-UE specific (eNB related) messages (e.g. X2 setup or reset) were not included in RL20 cell trace, but only in interface trace.

Parameter name: Trace X2 setting
Description: This parameter indicates if all X2 messages are traced (all), specific list(s) of X2 messages as defined in parameter traceX2MsgCategory (specific), or X2 not traced at all (none).

Parameter name: Trace X2 UE spec msg list
Description: If traceX2MsgCategory = all or traceX2MsgCategory = UEspecific then traceX2UeSpecMsgList contains list of enum for the UE specific messages to be traced.

Parameter name: E-UTRAN trace identifier - Trace recording session reference
Description: Trace Recording Session Reference is set to invalid value for Cell trace session by O&M as it does not need this. It is set by system for identification of every call in a cell and is written into Trace Report for the cell.  Trace Recording Session Reference is part of E-UTRAN Trace ID.  It is 2 Octet length.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - UE BSR Tracing
Description: Parameter uEBSRTracing configures whether tracing of UE Buffer Status Report Tracing, as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing, is enabled or not.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - UE RANK Tracing
Description: Parameter uERankTracing configures whether tracing of UE RANK, as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing, is enabled or not.

Parameter name: Enhanced cell vendor specific tracing - UpLink SINR tracing
Description: This parameter describes whether tracing of UL SINR as part of enhanced vendor specific extension tracing is enabled or not.

Parameter name: NBIOTPR identifier
Description: NBIOTPR identifier

Parameter name: Repetition Number of ACK/NACK for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0
Description: The repetition number for UEs sending ACK/NACK for downlink data transfer in the NB-IoT Coverage Level 0. See TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.

Parameter name: Repetition Number of ACK/NACK for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1
Description: The repetition number for UEs sending ACK/NACK for downlink data transfer in the NB-IoT Coverage Level 1. See TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.

Parameter name: Repetition Number of ACK/NACK for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2
Description: The repetition number for UEs sending ACK/NACK for downlink data transfer in the NB-IoT Coverage Level 2. See TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: C-Plane inactivity timer
Description: The parameter defines the time period for the indication of the UE- associated S1 logical connection inactivity in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Maximum number of repetitions for NPDCCH common search space for RA
Description: The maximum number of NPDCCH repetitions the UE needs to monitor for Common Search Space (CSS) (including RAR, Msg3 retransmission, and Msg4).    Note:  (1) If numCoverageLevels is equal to 3, all NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.  (2) The operator must set npdcchStartSfRa to v2 or v4 or v8 if numSib1RepNB, siWindowLenNB, sib2PeriodicityNB, sib2RepPatternNB are set to other values than the default values with more invalid subframes in downlink.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Starting subframes of the NPDCCH Common Search Space for RA
Description: The starting subframes configuration of the NPDCCH CSS for RAR/Msg3 re-transmission/Msg4,see TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.    Note:  (1) If numCoverageLevels is equal to 3, all NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.  (2) The operator must set npdcchStartSfRa to v2 or v4 or v8 if numSib1RepNB, siWindowLenNB, sib2PeriodicityNB, sib2RepPatternNB are set to other values than the default values with more invalid subframes in downlink.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Maximum number of repetitions for NPDCCH common search space for RA
Description: The maximum number of NPDCCH repetitions the UE needs to monitor for Common Search Space (CSS) (including RAR, Msg3 retransmission, and Msg4).    Note:  (1) All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.  (2) The operator must set npdcchStartSfRa to v2 or v4 or v8 if numSib1RepNB, siWindowLenNB, sib2PeriodicityNB, sib2RepPatternNB are set to other values than the default values with more invalid subframes in downlink.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Offset for NPDCCH Common Search Space
Description: Fractional period offset of starting subframe for NPDCCH CSS,see TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Starting subframes of the NPDCCH Common Search Space for RA
Description: The starting subframes configuration of the NPDCCH CSS for RAR/Msg3 re-transmission/Msg4,see TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.    Note:  (1) All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.  (2) The operator must set npdcchStartSfRa to v2 or v4 or v8 if numSib1RepNB, siWindowLenNB, sib2PeriodicityNB, sib2RepPatternNB are set to other values than the default values with more invalid subframes in downlink.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Maximum number of repetitions for NPDCCH common search space for RA
Description: The maximum number of NPDCCH repetitions the UE needs to monitor for Common Search Space (CSS) (including RAR, Msg3 retransmission, and Msg4).    Note:  (1) If numCoverageLevels is equal to or greater than 2, all NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.  (2) The operator must set npdcchStartSfRa to v2 or v4 or v8 if numSib1RepNB, siWindowLenNB, sib2PeriodicityNB, sib2RepPatternNB are set to other values than the default values with more invalid subframes in downlink.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Offset for NPDCCH Common Search Space
Description: Fractional period offset of starting subframe for NPDCCH CSS,see TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.    Note: If numCoverageLevels is equal to or greater than 2, all NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Starting subframes of the NPDCCH Common Search Space for RA
Description: The starting subframes configuration of the NPDCCH CSS for RAR/Msg3 re-transmission/Msg4,see TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.    Note:  (1) If numCoverageLevels is equal to or greater than 2, all NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.  (2) The operator must set npdcchStartSfRa to v2 or v4 or v8 if numSib1RepNB, siWindowLenNB, sib2PeriodicityNB, sib2RepPatternNB are set to other values than the default values with more invalid subframes in downlink.

Parameter name: Default paging cycle for NB-IoT cell
Description: Default paging cycle of NB-IoT, referred to as 'T' in TS 36.304.

Parameter name: Default number of repetition for paging
Description: Default number of NPDCCH repetitions for paging if not presented in the paging message from MME.  This information is optional IE and is provided transparently by the serving eNB to the MME at transition to ECM_IDLE together with the respective cell identifier and is provided to the E-UTRAN during paging.

Parameter name: Load weighting factor for NB-IoT UE in Anchor carrier of highest coverage level
Description: The load weighting factor for carrier selection when a new NB-IoT UE is connected to the highest coverage level.

Parameter name: MAC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Logical channel SR prohibit timer for NB-IoT
Description: Timer used to delay the transmission of an SR in NB-IoT, to wait for the potential UL grant for the UL transmission.

Parameter name: MAC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Retransmit BSR timer for NB-IoT
Description: Time when the regular BSRs are repeated in NB-IoT when the UE has data available for transmission and no corresponding UL grant is received so far.

Parameter name: MAC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Logical channel SR prohibit timer for NB-IoT
Description: Timer used to delay the transmission of an SR in NB-IoT, to wait for the potential UL grant for the UL transmission.

Parameter name: MAC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Retransmit BSR timer for NB-IoT
Description: Time when the regular BSRs are repeated in NB-IoT when the UE has data available for transmission and no corresponding UL grant is received so far.

Parameter name: MAC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Logical channel SR prohibit timer for NB-IoT
Description: Timer used to delay the transmission of an SR in NB-IoT, to wait for the potential UL grant for the UL transmission.

Parameter name: MAC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Retransmit BSR timer for NB-IoT
Description: Time when the regular BSRs are repeated in NB-IoT when the UE has data available for transmission and no corresponding UL grant is received so far.

Parameter name: Maximum number of repetitions for NPDCCH common search space for paging
Description: Maximum number of repetitions for N-PDCCH common search space (CSS) for paging.  Note: If there are multiple NB-IoT coverage levels configured, the parameter npdcchMaxNumRep should be set to the value which can satisfy the worst conditions for all coverage levels.

Parameter name: Common Search Space profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Offset for NPDCCH Common Search Space
Description: Fractional period offset of starting subframe for NPDCCH CSS,see TS 36.211 and TS 36.213.    Note: If numCoverageLevels is equal to 3, all NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: NPRACH Cyclic Prefix length
Description: Cyclic prefix length for NPRACH transmission.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Max number of preamble attempts of NPRACH
Description: Number of maximum preamble transmission attempts per NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Number of repetitions per preamble attempt of NPRACH
Description: Number of NPRACH repetitions per attempt for each NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Number of subcarriers of NPRACH
Description: Number of subcarriers in a NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - NPRACH periodicity
Description: Periodicity of a NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - NPRACH start time
Description: Start time of the NPRACH resource in one period.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - NPRACH subcarrier offset
Description: Frequency location of the NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Max number of preamble attempts of NPRACH
Description: Number of maximum preamble transmission attempts per NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Number of repetitions per preamble attempt of NPRACH
Description: Number of NPRACH repetitions per attempt for each NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Number of subcarriers of NPRACH
Description: Number of subcarriers in a NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - NPRACH periodicity
Description: Periodicity of a NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - NPRACH start time
Description: Start time of the NPRACH resource in one period.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - NPRACH subcarrier offset
Description: Frequency location of the NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Max number of preamble attempts of NPRACH
Description: Number of maximum preamble transmission attempts per NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Number of repetitions per preamble attempt of NPRACH
Description: Number of NPRACH repetitions per attempt for each NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Number of subcarriers of NPRACH
Description: Number of subcarriers in a NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - NPRACH periodicity
Description: Periodicity of a NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - NPRACH start time
Description: Start time of the NPRACH resource in one period.

Parameter name: NPRACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - NPRACH subcarrier offset
Description: Frequency location of the NPRACH resource.

Parameter name: Number of SIB1-NB repetitions
Description: Number of repetitions of SIB1-NB in periodicity 2560ms.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Maximum Coverage Level used for NB-IoT further paging attempts
Description: This parameter indicates a threshold in case of Paging Attempt Count greater than or equal to this, eNB shall apply the highest (maximum) configured coverage level parameters for NPDCCH and NPDSCH.

Parameter name: Paging nB for NB-IoT
Description: NB-IoT nB is used as one of parameters to derive the Paging Frame and Paging Occasion according to TS 36.304. Value in multiples of 'T' as defined in TS 36.304. A value of fourT corresponds to 4 * T, a value of twoT corresponds to 2 * T and so on.
Range and step: quarterT (4), one8thT (5), one16thT (6), one32ndT (7), one64thT (8), one128thT (9), one256thT (10), one512thT (11), one1024thT (12)

Parameter name: RACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Contention resolution timer for NB-IoT
Description: The maximum contention resolution timer parameter defines the maximum amount of time allowed for the contention resolution in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - RA response window size for NB-IoT
Description: Random Access Response Window Size parameter defines the window size for the random access response in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Contention resolution timer for NB-IoT
Description: The maximum contention resolution timer parameter defines the maximum amount of time allowed for the contention resolution in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - RA response window size for NB-IoT
Description: Random Access Response Window Size parameter defines the window size for the random access response in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Contention resolution timer for NB-IoT
Description: The maximum contention resolution timer parameter defines the maximum amount of time allowed for the contention resolution in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RACH profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - RA response window size for NB-IoT
Description: Random Access Response Window Size parameter defines the window size for the random access response in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Max retransmission threshold for NB-IoT
Description: The maximum number of poll retransmission for the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Poll retransmit for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-PollRetransmit-r13 of [36.331].  This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Timer for detection loss of NB-IoT RLC PDUs
Description: Timer is used to detect loss of RLC PDUs as specified in the 3GPP TS36.323 section 5.1.2.1.4.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Max retransmission threshold for NB-IoT
Description: The maximum number of poll retransmission for the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Poll retransmit for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit-r13 of [36.331].  This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Timer for detection loss of NB-IoT RLC PDUs
Description: Timer for detection loss of NB-IoT RLC PDUs.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Max retransmission threshold for NB-IoT
Description: The maximum number of poll retransmission for the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in NB-IoT.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Poll retransmit for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter specifies the parameter t-pollRetransmit-r13 of [36.331].  This timer is used by the transmitting side of an AM RLC entity in order to retransmit a poll.

Parameter name: RLC profile for NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Timer for detection loss of NB-IoT RLC PDUs
Description: Timer for detection loss of NB-IoT RLC PDUs.

Parameter name: RRC guard timer radio bearer management for NB-IoT
Description: This timer for NB-IoT is started when an RRC message for setup, modification or release of a radio bearer is sent to the UE. When the timer expires, the corresponding procedure is aborted.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Repetition Number of Msg4 ACK/NACK for NB-IoT
Description: The repetition number for UEs sending ACK/NACK for downlink message4.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Initial MCS in downlink
Description: Initial downlink modulation and coding scheme for NB-IoT UEs.    Note:  The highest MCS used in downlink NPDSCH transmission of Rel-13 NB-IoT UE is 12.  The highest MCS used in downlink NPDSCH transmission of Rel-14 NB-IoT UE is 13.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Initial MCS in uplink
Description: Initial uplink modulation and coding scheme for NB-IoT UEs.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Initial repetition number of NPDCCH for RA
Description: Initial NPDCCH repetition number for NPDCCH common search space (CSS) (including RAR, Msg3 retransmission, and Msg4), and User Specific Search Space (USS) for data transmission.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Initial repetition number of NPDSCH
Description: Initial unicast NPDSCH repetition number for NB-IoT UEs.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - Initial repetition number of NPUSCH
Description: Initial unicast NPUSCH repetition number for NB-IoT UE.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 2 - SRB inactivity timer
Description: The parameter defines the time period for the indication of the UE inactivity on signaling radio bearer in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Repetition Number of Msg4 ACK/NACK for NB-IoT
Description: The repetition number for UEs sending ACK/NACK for downlink message4.
