Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Initial MCS in downlink
Description: Initial downlink modulation and coding scheme for NB-IoT UEs.    Note:  The highest MCS used in downlink NPDSCH transmission of Rel-13 NB-IoT UE is 12.  The highest MCS used in downlink NPDSCH transmission of Rel-14 NB-IoT UE is 13.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Initial MCS in uplink
Description: Initial uplink modulation and coding scheme for NB-IoT UEs.  Note:  The highest MCS used in uplink single-tone NPUSCH transmission is 10.  The highest MCS used in uplink multi-tone NPUSCH transmission of Rel-13 UE is 12.  The highest MCS used in uplink multi-tone NPUSCH transmission of Rel-14 UE is 13.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Initial repetition number of NPDCCH for RA
Description: Initial NPDCCH repetition number for NPDCCH common search space (CSS) (including RAR, Msg3 retransmission, and Msg4), and User Specific Search Space (USS) for data transmission.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Initial repetition number of NPDSCH
Description: Initial unicast NPDSCH repetition number for NB-IoT Ues.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - Initial repetition number of NPUSCH
Description: Initial unicast NPUSCH repetition number for NB-IoT UE.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 - SRB inactivity timer
Description: The parameter defines the time period for the indication of the UE inactivity on signaling radio bearer in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Repetition Number of Msg4 ACK/NACK for NB-IoT
Description: The repetition number for UEs sending ACK/NACK for downlink message4.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Initial MCS in downlink
Description: Initial downlink modulation and coding scheme for NB-IoT UEs.    Note:  The highest MCS used in downlink NPDSCH transmission of Rel-13 NB-IoT UE is 12.  The highest MCS used in downlink NPDSCH transmission of Rel-14 NB-IoT UE is 13.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Initial MCS in uplink
Description: Initial uplink modulation and coding scheme for NB-IoT UEs.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Initial repetition number of NPDCCH for RA
Description: Initial NPDCCH repetition number for NPDCCH common search space (CSS) (including RAR, Msg3 retransmission, and Msg4), and User Specific Search Space (USS) for data transmission.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Initial repetition number of NPDSCH
Description: Initial unicast NPDSCH repetition number for NB-IoT UEs.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - Initial repetition number of NPUSCH
Description: Initial unicast NPUSCH repetition number for NB-IoT UE.

Parameter name: Scheduler profile in NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 - SRB inactivity timer
Description: The parameter defines the time period for the indication of the UE inactivity on signaling radio bearer in both DL and UL directions.

Parameter name: Offset of the start of SI-NB window
Description: Offset in number of radio frames to calculate the start of the SI window.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: SI-NB window length
Description: Common SI scheduling window for all SIs.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: The periodicity of SIB2-NB
Description: Periodicity of the SIB2-NB in radio frames.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: The repetition pattern of SIB2-NB
Description: Indicates the starting radio frames within the SI window used for SI message transmission. Value every2ndRF corresponds to every second radio frame, value every4thRF corresponds to every fourth radio frame and so on starting from the first radio frame of the SI window used for SI transmission.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: List of scheduled SI-Messages for NB-IoT
Description: List of scheduled NB-IoT SI-Messages containing optional SIBs.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: SI-Message Periodicity in NB-IoT
Description: Periodicity of this NB-IoT SI-Message.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: SI-Message Repetition Pattern in NB-IoT
Description: Number of NB-IoT SI-Message Repetitions.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: SI-Message of SIB Type for NB-IoT
Description: Indicates which SIB is contained in the NB-IoT SI-Message.    Note: All NB-IoT UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: Timer of T300 for NB-IoT
Description: Timer T300-NB supervises the RRC connection establishment procedure for NB-IoT.  Timer guards the period between RRCConnectionRequest-NB  and reception of RRCConnectionSetup-NB or RRCConnectionReject-NB message for NB-IoT.  Note: If there are multiple NB-IoT coverage levels configured, the parameter t300NB should be set to the value which can satisfy the worst condition for all coverage levels.

Parameter name: Timer of T301 for NB-IoT
Description: Timer T301-NB supervises the RRC reestablishment procedure for NB-IoT.  Timer guard the period between RRCConnectionReestabilshmentRequest  and reception of RRCConnectionReestablishment or RRCConnectionReestablishmentReject message for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Timer of T310 for NB-IoT
Description: Timer T310-NB supervises the recovery from physical layer problems for NB-IoT. Timer starts upon detecting physical layer problems i.e. upon receiving n310 consecutive out-of sync indications from lower layers and stops upon receiving n311 consecutive in-sync indications from lower layers, upon triggering the handover procedure and upon initiating the connection re-establishment procedure.    Note: If there are multiple NB-IoT coverage levels configured, the parameter should be set to the value which can satisfy the worst condition for all coverage levels.

Parameter name: Timer ExtendedWaitTime-r13
Description: tExtendedWaitNB suppresses the reselection of a NB-IoT cell for a while.  eNB sends this parameter to the NB-IoT UE in the message  -RRC CONNECTION REJECT-NB  -RRC CONNECTION RELEASE-NB.  The NB-IoT UE will consider access to the NB-IoT cell as barred for the time specified by tExtendedWaitNB.

Parameter name: Timer min lifetime of half-open RRC connection for NB-IoT
Description: The minimal time period for NB-IoT during which the internal state and the resources associated with half-open RRC connection (i.e. one for which no RRC connection setup complete message has yet been received) must not be deleted in the eNB.    Note: If there are multiple NB-IoT coverage levels configured, the parameter should be set to the value which can satisfy the worst condition for all coverage levels.

Parameter name: Timer missing L2 ack for NB-IoT RRC connection release
Description: The maximum time period indicates the time after which the RRC L3 releases the RRC connection for NB-IoT context, if no positive ack is received from RLC to the RRC CONNECTION RELEASE-NB message. This timer has to absorb the potential preceding NAS transmission, which can be approximated via rrcGuardTimerNB. This timer is reset to 10 second upon reception of L1 HARQ ACK of RRC Connection Release, as per 3GPP R2-169034.  Note:The recommended value can be tPollRetrNB of highest coverage level * (maxRetxThreNB + 1)

Parameter name: NB-IoT FDD specific cell identifier
Description: This is the instance identifier of object NBIOT_FDD. It uniquely defines the object containing FDD NB-IoT technology specific cell parameter. It is used only for operation and maintenance purposes.

Parameter name: RRC connections auto trigger access barring for NB-IoT cell - Cell RRC connection Access Barring start threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the upper threshold of RRC CONNECTED NB-IoT UEs which can trigger ACTIVE RRC_AB event on the NB-IoT cell level.  RRC_AB event becomes ACTIVE if number of RRC_Connected NB-IoT UEs in the cell >= ROUND(abNumRrcConnCellStartNB * maxNumRrcNB / 100) AND abRrcConnCellStartTimerNB expires.    ACTIVE RRC_AB event shall start upgrade of Access Barring settings and their broadcast in SIB14-NB message if dynamic AB ACTIVE state not started yet.    Note: maxNumRrcNB of NB-Iot Cell - indicates that this is Cell related maxNumRrcNB NB-IoT RAC limit.  Upgrade of Access Barring settings means overwriting Static or None AB IEs.

Parameter name: RRC connections auto trigger access barring for NB-IoT cell - Cell RRC connection Access Barring stop threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the lower threshold of RRC CONNECTED NB-IoT UEs which can trigger INACTIVE RRC_AB event on the NB-IoT cell level.  RRC_AB event becomes INACTIVE if number of RRC_Connected NB-IoT UEs in the cell < ROUND(abNumRrcConnCellStopNB * maxNumRrcNB / 100) AND abRrcConnCellStopTimerNB expires.    INACTIVE RRC_AB event shall start downgrade of Access Barring settings and their broadcast in SIB14-NB message if there's no other ACTIVE AB trigger.    Note: maxNumRrcNB of NB-Iot Cell - indicates that this is Cell related maxNumRrcNB NB-IoT RAC limit.  Downgrade of Access barring settings means: broadcast of Static settings or None AB IEs.

Parameter name: Access Barring profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the access barring profile which is linked to EABPR instance.

Parameter name: RRC connections auto trigger access barring for NB-IoT cell - Cell RRC triggered Access Barring start timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before triggering ACTIVE RRC_AB event on the NB-IoT cell level.  RRC_AB event becomes ACTIVE if number of RRC_Connected NB-IoT UEs in the cell >= ROUND(abNumRrcConnCellStartNB * maxNumRrcNB / 100) AND abRrcConnCellStartTimerNB expires.    ACTIVE RRC_AB event shall start upgrade of Access barring settings and their broadcast in SIB14-NB message if dynamic AB ACTIVE state not started yet.    Note: maxNumRrcNB of NB-Iot Cell - indicates that this is Cell related maxNumRrcNB NB-IoT RAC limit.  Upgrade of Access Barring settings means overwriting Static or None AB IEs.

Parameter name: RRC connections auto trigger access barring for NB-IoT cell - Cell RRC triggered Access Barring stop timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before triggering INACTIVE RRC_AB event on the cell level.  RRC_AB event becomes INACTIVE if number of RRC_Connected NB-IoT UEs in the cell < ROUND(abNumRrcConnCellStopNB * maxNumRrcNB / 100) AND abRrcConnCellStopTimerNB expires.    INACTIVE RRC_AB event shall start downgrade of Access Barring settings and their broadcast in SIB14-NB message if there's no other ACTIVE AB trigger.    Note: maxNumRrcNB of NB-Iot Cell - indicates that this is Cell related maxNumRrcNB NB-IoT RAC limit.  Downgrade of Access barring settings means: broadcast of Static settings or None AB IEs.

Parameter name: Activate NB-IoT Access Barring
Description: This parameter activates 'NB-IoT: Access Barring'.  The feature allows to configure either or both static and automatic access barring parameters broadcast in SIB14-NB.  Note: if automatic access barring is configured then either or both following configuration should be fulfilled:  (1) actAutoAcBarring is set to 'true'.  (2) abRrcConnAutoNB structure is configured.  otherwise automatic access barring does not work.

Parameter name: Activate DSS NR optimized PRB blanking for guardband
Description: This parameter activates support for DSS NR optimized DL/UL PRB blanking for coexistence with LTE NB-IoT guardband. NR PRB blanking is configured to constrain the negative impacts of overlapping cell bandwidths of NR cell and LTE cell, e.g. radio interference or transmit power erosion.    Following options are supported:  - 'disabled' (default) -- no optimization  - 'asymmetrical' -- DSS NR asymmetrical DL/UL PRB blanking for coexistence with LTE NB-IoT guardband.

Parameter name: Activates early contention resolution for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter activates the early contention resolution for NB-IoT. When this function is enabled, the eNB may schedule Contention Resolution Identity without RRC response message, before the contention resolution timer expired, for capable NB-IoT UE. Otherwise, the Contention Resolution Identity will be sent always together with RRC response message.

Parameter name: Activate extended NPRACH for 100km NB-IoT cell range
Description: This parameter activates the functionality to extend NB-IoT cell range to 100km.

Parameter name: Activates NB-IoT Category NB2 higher TBS
Description: This parameter activates NB-IoT Category NB2 higher TBS

Parameter name: Activation of Idle Mode Load Balancing
Description: The parameter activates the feature Idle Mode Load Balancing for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Activates multiple HARQ support for NB-IoT Category NB2 UE
Description: This parameter activates two HARQ support for NB-IoT.

Parameter name: Activates NB-IoT multi-tone in uplink
Description: This parameter activates NB-IoT multi-tone in uplink

Parameter name: Activating release assistance indication for NB-IoT cell
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates the function of RAI (Release Assistance Indication) for NB-IoT.  When this parameter is set to 'true' and NB-IoT UE is configured with RAI, eNB will release NB-IoT UE immediately if the Buffer Status Report from UE and the size downlink data in eNB are both zero.

Parameter name: Activate for independent MFBI setting and/or independent native band for inband and guardband NB-IoT cell
Description: This parameter activates independent MFBI setting for inband and guardband NB-IoT cell when actMFBI is enabled. If earfcnDL in NBIOT_FDD is not configured, the independent MFBI setting is from MFBIPR instance with eutraCarrierFreq equal to assignedEarfcnDL in ANBIOTCARR for downlink anchor carrier. If earfcnDL in NBIOT_FDD is configured, the independent MFBI setting is from MFBIPR instance with eutraCarrierFreq equal to earfcnDL in NBIOT_FDD.    This parameter activates inband and guardband NB-IoT cell use the native frequency band indicated by earfcnDL/earfcnUL in NBIOT_FDD if they are configured.    Note:  This parameter is applicable for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell only  Changing of this parameter may trigger NB-IoT non-essential SI modification

Parameter name: Activate serving cell measurement reports for NB-IoT
Description: This parameter activates/deactivates serving cell idle mode measurement reporting in RRCConnectionSetupComplete-NB message.

Parameter name: Activates Status PDU report after detection reception failure of RLC PDUs
Description: This parameter indicates the status reporting due to the loss of reception failure of an RLC data PDU, as specified in 3GPP TS36.322 section 5.2.3.

Parameter name: Base sequence of DMRS for NB-IoT uplink 12 tones
Description: Defines base sequence of DMRS for NB-IoT uplink 12 tones. If this parameter is not configured, it is given by NB-IoT phyCellId mod 30.

Parameter name: Base sequence of DMRS for NB-IoT uplink 3 tones
Description: Defines base sequence of DMRS for NB-IoT uplink 3 tones. If this parameter is not configured, it is given by NB-IoT phyCellId mod 12.

Parameter name: Base sequence of DMRS for NB-IoT uplink 6 tones
Description: Defines base sequence of DMRS for NB-IoT uplink 6 tones. If this parameter is not configured, it is given by NB-IoT phyCellId mod 14.

Parameter name: NB-IoT Carrier Selection Mode
Description: This parameter indicates the mode of NB-IoT carriers selection  - 'nonAnchorCarriers': After random access procedure, if an NB-IoT UE is multiple-carrier capable and power budget on a downlink non-anchor carrier is satisfied, the NB-IoT anchor carrier shall not be allocated, and a non-anchor carrier shall be selected based on load metrics of non-anchor carriers.  - 'AllCarriers': After random access procedure, if an NB-IoT UE is multiple-carrier capable and power budget on a downlink non-anchor carrier is satisfied, both anchor and non-anchor carrier(s) can be selected based on load metrics.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Cyclic Shift for NB-IoT uplink 3 tones
Description: Defines cyclic shift of uplink reference signals for NB-IoT 3 tones.

Parameter name: Cyclic Shift for NB-IoT uplink 6 tones
Description: Defines cyclic shift of uplink reference signals for NB-IoT 6 tones.

Parameter name: Downlink channel bandwidth
Description: Downlink channel bandwidth of NB-IoT cell, fixed to 200kHz

Parameter name: NB-IoT Downlink MIMO mode
Description: Downlink transmission MIMO mode for NB-IoT:  SingleTx: Single Stream Downlink: All downlink physical channels are transmitted using this mode;  TXDiv: Single Stream Downlink Transmit Diversity for two antennas using Transmission Mode 2.

Parameter name: Downlink non-anchor carrier power offset relative to the anchor carrier
Description: This parameter indicates the downlink power offset for non-anchor carriers.  This parameter provides the downlink narrowband reference-signal EPRE offset of the non-anchor carrier relative to the downlink narrowband reference-signal EPRE of the anchor carrier.    Note: the bigger absolute value of dlPowerOffsetNonAnchor, the more unlikely UE is allocated to non-anchor carriers.  if dlPowerOffsetNonAnchor is not set to 0dB then the bigger npdcchMaxNumRepRa, iniNpdschNumRep and iniNpdcchNumRep, the more unlikely UE is allocated to non-anchor carrier.

Parameter name: Downlink channel power boost for inband or guardband NB-IoT
Description: Downlink channel power boost for inband and guardband NB-IoT.  Note: When power boost is enabled for guardband NB-IoT together with DSS (actLteNrDss is set to 'true' and lteNrDssMode is set to 'DL_CRS_TDM_UL_FDM'), operator needs to configure the proper power density and number of blanking downlink PRBs in NR system, to ensure the sum power of NR carrier and power boosted NB-IoT carrier not exceeding the RF module capability.

Parameter name: EARFCN configured for downlink anchor carrier for inband or guardband NB-IoT cell
Description: When actSepMFBI is true, this parameter and earfcnUL in NBIOT_FDD are used together to indicate inband/guardband NB-IoT cell to a native band independent with host cell.  When actSepMFBI is false, this parameter is not used.  When actSepMFBI is true and this parameter is configured:  1. The eNB derives the native frequency band (broadcasted in SIB1-NB) for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell from this parameter.  2. If actMFBI is enabled, the eNB uses this parameter to look up eutraCarrierFreq in MFBIPR instances to determine the MFBI setting for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell.  3. If downlink non-anchor carrier is configured, the eNB derives the downlink non-anchor carrier EARFCN based on this parameter.  This parameter and earfcnUL in NBIOT_FDD must belong to the same frequency band.  This parameter and assignedEarfcnDL in ANBIOTCARR for downlink anchor carrier must indicate the same physical frequency.  The whole downlink anchor carrier must locate in the band indicated by this parameter.  The whole downlink non-anchor carrier, if configured, must locate in the band indicated by this parameter.    If this parameter is equal to assignedEarfcnDL in ANBIOTCARR for downlink anchor carrier, it is equivalent to not configured.    Note: Changing of this parameter may trigger NB-IoT non-essential SI modification.

Parameter name: EARFCN configured for uplink anchor carrier for inband or guardband NB-IoT cell
Description: When actSepMFBI is true, this parameter and earfcnDL in NBIOT_FDD are used together to indicate inband/guardband NB-IoT cell to a native band independent with host cell.  When actSepMFBI is false, this parameter is not used.  When actSepMFBI is true and this parameter is configured:  1. The eNB uses this parameter as uplink EARFCN (broadcasted in SIB2-NB) for inband/guardband NB-IoT cell.  2. If uplink non-anchor carrier is configured, the eNB derives the uplink non-anchor carrier EARFCN based on this parameter.  This parameter and earfcnDL in NBIOT_FDD must belong to the same frequency band.  This parameter and assignedEarfcnUL in ANBIOTCARR for uplink anchor carrier must indicate the same physical frequency.    The whole uplink anchor carrier must locate in the band indicated by this parameter.  The whole uplink non-anchor carrier, if configured, must locate in the band indicated by this parameter.    If this parameter is equal to assignedEarfcnUL in ANBIOTCARR for uplink anchor carrier, it is equivalent to not configured.    Note: Changing of this parameter may trigger NB-IoT non-essential SI modification.

Parameter name: NB-IoT guardband downlink Anchor PRB index
Description: eNB will dynamically decide if deployment change is needed and which cells are affected by the possible deployment change.  This parameter indicates the Frequency offset for guardband NB-IoT downlink anchor carrier.

Parameter name: NB-IoT guardband uplink Anchor PRB index
Description: This parameter indicates the Frequency offset in Anchor carrier for guardband NB-IoT uplink.  eNB will dynamically decide if deployment change is needed and which cells are affected by the possible deployment change

Parameter name: Cell reselection weight factor idle mode load balancing for NB-IoT
Description: Weight factor of the serving cell frequency layer used by the round-robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing for NB-IoT.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting the target for redirectedCarrierInfo for NB-IoT load balancing.  Weighted round-robin algorithm shall select the target frequency for NB-IoT idle mode load balancing, which is matching NB-IoT UE capabilities.  The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: Percentage of UE for idle mode load balancing for NB-IoT
Description: Percentage of NB-IoT UE to be selected for Idle Mode Load Balancing.

Parameter name: NB-IoT inband downlink Anchor PRB index
Description: This parameter indicates the PRB index of the host LTE cell used for NB-IoT inband downlink anchor carrier.  Only following anchor PRB indices are allowed to be used for inband NB-IoT based on the bandwidth of the host LTE cell:  3MHz: 2, 12  5MHz: 2, 7, 17, 22  10MHz: 4, 9, 14, 19, 30, 35, 40, 45  15MHz: 2, 7, 12, 17, 22, 27, 32, 42, 47, 52, 57, 62, 67, 72  20MHz: 4, 9, 14, 19, 24, 29, 34, 39, 44, 55, 60, 65, 70, 75, 80, 85, 90, 95

Parameter name: NB-IoT inband uplink Anchor PRB index
Description: This parameter indicates the Anchor PRB index of the host LTE cell used for NB-IoT inband uplink.  The PRB index used for NB-IoT must not be configured to the resources used by PUCCH and PRACH in the host LTE cell.  Note: If additional Cat-M CE ModeA narrowband (numNarBandModeACatM) is enabled for the host cell with PUCCH blanking de-activated and PUSCH masking de-activated, and number of NB-IoT cell downlink Non-Anchor carriers equals to 0 simultaneously, this configured parameter (inbandPRBIndexUL) will be ignored and re-assigned by eNB.

Parameter name: Load weight calculation mode
Description: This parameter defines the mode of NB-IoT load weight  - 'Manual': Load weighting factors of coverage levels 1 and 2 are configured with parameters loadWeightNBCL1 and loadWeightNBCL2 respectively.  - 'Automatic': Load weighting factors of coverage levels 1 and 2 are calculated based on the length of the NPDCCH search space per coverage levels 1 and 2.    Note:  The load weight of coverage level 0 is 1 always.

Parameter name: Load weighting factor for coverage level 1
Description: This parameter specifies weight of a coverage level 1 NB-IoT UE in load metric calculation for carrier selection.

Parameter name: Load weighting factor for coverage level 2
Description: This parameter specifies weight of a coverage level 2 NB-IoT UE in load metric calculation for carrier selection.

Parameter name: Maximum Coupling Loss (MCL) for NB-IoT cell
Description: Maximum Coupling Loss (MCL) for NB-IoT cell that NB-IoT UE can access.  144dB: Up to 144dB MCL limited by minimum receive level  154dB: Up to 154dB MCL limited by minimum receive level  164dB: Up to 164dB MCL limited by minimum receive level  Note: The maximum coupling loss which can be reached may also be limited by the maximum transmission power of the radio (e.g. small cells).

Parameter name: Max Number RRC NB-IoT
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of NB-IoT UEs in the cell which may establish an RRC connection.    For FSMF, two separate resources pools are realized for RRC connections of wideband UEs (incl. CAT-M UEs) and for NB-IoT. That means the threshold configuration of NB-IoT is independent from the threshold configured for wideband RRC connections. maxNumRrcNB may even be configured to a higher value than maxNumRrc respectively maxNumActUE.    For AirScale a common resource pool for wideband UEs and NB-IoT UEs was realized (in order to support pooling function), which leads to dependent resource threshold configurations (maxNumActUE threshold includes the number of allowed NB-IoT RRC connections (maxNumRrcNB is a subset)).  maxNumRrcNB should be set to a lower value than maxNumActUE;    The maximum number of RRC connected NB-IoT UEs can be set to a high value from radio admission control viewpoint, but performance of NB-IoT UEs are not guaranteed due to the air interface limitation.

Parameter name: Max Number RRC NB-IoT for Coverage Level 1
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of NB-IoT UEs in the coverage level 1 which may establish RRC connection in NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: Max Number RRC NB-IoT for Coverage Level 2
Description: Threshold for the maximum number of NB-IoT UEs in the coverage level 2 which may establish RRC connection in NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: Minimum number of NB IoT RRC connections
Description: This parameter defines minimum reserved number of NB-IoT UEs in the NB-IoT cell which may establish an RRC connection.This is needed only for AirScale deployments where resources may be shifted from one cell to the other where needed, but a minimum functionality shall be ensured per cell. This parameter is only used by AirScale eNB regardless dynamic PUCCH features activated or deactivated.  In case NB IoT is not activated in the cell then this minNumRrcNB parameter should be configured to 0 in order not to reserve unnecessary resources on AirScale BBpools.    Note: The value of minNumRrcNB should be less than the value of maxNumRrcNB. Otherwise, minNumRrcNB will override maxNumRrcNB as the limitation of the maximum number of RRC connected NB-IoT UEs.

Parameter name: Instance ID of the assigned NBIOTPR profile
Description: Instance ID of the assigned NBIOTPR profile.

Parameter name: NPRACH Config Index
Description: This parameter indicates NPRACH configuration pattern will be pre-defined or manually configured.  If 'Manual Configuration' is selected, the NPRACH configuration will be set based on the parameters in NBIOTPR profile.  If any pre-defined pattern is selected, the NPRACH configuration will be decided from pre-defined pattern.
Range and step: Manual Configuration (0), Pre-defined pattern 1-1 (11), Pre-defined pattern 1-2 (12), Pre-defined pattern 2-1 (21), Pre-defined pattern 2-2 (22), Pre-defined pattern 3-1 (31), Pre-defined pattern 3-2 (32)

Parameter name: NPRACH detection threshold scaling for Coverage Level 0
Description: The scaling factor of NPRACH detection threshold of NB-IoT for Coverage Level 0.  Note:  The higher threshold may reduce the false detection rate, but reduce the sensitivity at the same time.  The lower threshold may increase the sensitivity, but increase the false detection rate at the same time.

Parameter name: NPRACH detection threshold scaling for Coverage Level 1
Description: The scaling factor of NPRACH detection threshold of NB-IoT for Coverage Level 1.  Note:  The higher threshold may reduce the false detection rate, but reduce the sensitivity at the same time.  The lower threshold may increase the sensitivity, but increase the false detection rate at the same time.

Parameter name: NPRACH detection threshold scaling for Coverage Level 2
Description: The scaling factor of NPRACH detection threshold of NB-IoT for Coverage Level 2.  Note:  The higher threshold may reduce the false detection rate, but reduce the sensitivity at the same time.  The lower threshold may increase the sensitivity, but increase the false detection rate at the same time.

Parameter name: NPRACH RSRP Threshold-1
Description: The RSRP threshold to separate NB-IoT Coverage Level 0 (RSRP measurement >= this threshold) and Coverage Level 1 (RSRP measurement < this threshold).

Parameter name: NPRACH RSRP Threshold-2
Description: The RSRP threshold to separate NB-IoT Coverage Level 1 (RSRP measurement >= this threshold) and Coverage Level 2 (RSRP measurement < this threshold).

Parameter name: Timing Advance threshold for NPRACH detection
Description: The threshold of NPRACH Timing Advance (in unit of kilometer) for NB-IoT. It indicates the expected maximum Timing Advance value allowed for the eNB to consider NB-IoT preamble as valid. If the Timing Advance in received NB-IoT preamble is larger than the equivalent threshold, the NB-IoT preamble will be discarded.  The equivalent threshold will be calculated from this parameter (in meter) divided by 78m. The round-up threshold will be selected.    If extended NPRACH for 100km NB-IoT cell range (actExtendedNPRACH) is disabled, the maximum Timing Advance received from this cell can only reach 40km due to the limitation of NPRACH format 1 from 3GPP.  If extended NPRACH for 100km NB-IoT cell range (actExtendedNPRACH) is enabled, the maximum Timing Advance received from this cell is possible to reach 100km.    Note: The Timing Advance range is not exactly same as cell radius due to various factors like multiple-path propagation, RF cable length etc.

Parameter name: Number of Coverage Levels
Description: Number of coverage levels configured for NB-IoT cell. The coverage level is decided by the NPRACH resources used by NB-IoT UEs.

Parameter name: Number of NB-IoT cell downlink Non-Anchor carriers
Description: This parameter indicates the number of NB-IoT downlink Non-Anchor carriers.

Parameter name: Number of NB-IoT cell uplink non-anchor carriers
Description: This parameter indicates the number of NB-IoT uplink non-anchor carriers.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Nominal power for NB-IoT UE NPUSCH TX power calculation
Description: The parameter defines the NB-IoT cell-specific nominal power for the NPUSCH. Used for P0_NPUSCH calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P1) for controlling the mean received SNR for user data during (re)transmission corresponding to a received NPDCCH with DCI format N0 associated with a new packet transmission. This parameter is used to control mean received SNR for user data.

Parameter name: Redirected Carrier Information for NB-IoT Idle Mode Load Balancing - Frequency dedicated offset for NB-IoT
Description: An NB-IoT UE that supports multi-band cells considers the redirectedCarrierOffsetDedicated to be common for all overlapping bands (i.e. regardless of the EARFCN that is used).

Parameter name: Redirected Carrier Information for NB-IoT Idle Mode Load Balancing - Timer t322 for NB-IoT
Description: This timer supervised a period upon entering RRC_CONNECTED, when PLMN selection is performed on request by NAS, or upon cell (re)selection to another RAT, or upon reception of RRCEarlyDataComplete or RRCConnectionRelease for UP-EDT.

Parameter name: NB-IoT standalone EARFCN Downlink
NB-IoT standalone EARFCN Uplink
Starting Coverage Level supports Paging Optimization for NB-IoT
Description: Starting Coverage Level supports Paging Optimization configured for NB-IoT cell. Paging optimization will send the paging over specific cell for first paging message from MME, and paging over TAC region for re-paging messages from MME.  i.e.  Coverage Level 0 - Paging Optimization support start from coverage level 0 (all levels)  Coverage Level 1 - Paging Optimization support start from coverage level 1  Coverage Level 2 - Paging Optimization support in coverage level 2  if this parameter is not configured, then this function is considered to be disabled.
Range and step: Coverage Level 0 (0), Coverage Level 1 (10), Coverage Level 2 (20)

Parameter name: Synchronization signals transmission mode
Description: The parameter determines whether NB-IoT Primary and Secondary Synchronization Signals (NPSS, NSSS) are transmitted into a cell via one antenna port (SingleTx) or via all antenna ports using TX diversity with Precoding Vector Switching (PVS).

Parameter name: Guard time to force the release of UE context(s) when NB-IoT cell deletion
Description: The guard time period indicates the time after which the eNB forces the release of UE context(s) for NB-IoT cell deletion, even if not all RRC Connections were released yet.  Note: 'force release' means that UE Contexts are released by the eNB without waiting for their ordinary termination.

Parameter name: Timer Inter-frequency Cell Reselection for NB-IoT
Description: Defines the Inter-frequency cell reselection timer value for NB-IoT

Parameter name: Timer Cell Reselection for NB-IoT
Description: Defines the cell reselection timer value for NB-IoT

Parameter name: Uplink channel bandwidth
Description: Uplink channel bandwidth of NB-IoT cell, fixed to 200kHz

Parameter name: Preamble initial received target power in NB-IoT cell
Description: The parameter defines the initial power for Random Access preamble transmission in NB-IoT cell.

Parameter name: New Radio Dual Connectivity default profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC NRDCDPR.  It uniquely identifies an NRDCDPR instance.

Parameter name: Activate sorting the band combination list for MRDC
Description: If this parameter is set to 'true' then eNB will order the final band combination list in the allowedBC-ListMRDC in descending order of eNB's preference to provide it to gNB. By doing this, gNB can select the band combination, which is listed earlier in the list, if the band combinations have the equal preference from SgNB point of view. This selection will result in most preferred band combination from LTE point of view among the band combinations with equal SgNB preference. The sorting of final allowedBC-ListMRDC only applies to cells for which allowedBcSelectMethod is set different from no preference.

Parameter name: Selection method for the allowed band combination list for MRDC
Description: This parameter indicates which method the MeNB follows in the selection of the allowed band Combination List for MRDC and related feature sets to use in the SgNB Addition or MeNB initiated SgNB Modification for intra-eNB mobility procedure.    The following options are available:  - no preference  - max MIMO layers  - max MIMO layers with min CCs  - max MIMO layers with max CCs    If 'no preference' is chosen, MeNB provides to the target en-gNB the MRDC band combinations and related feature sets which include the UE's PCell band in both DL and UL directions.  Besides, when UE NR measurement results are included, there will be at least one MRDC band combination with the measured NR band in both DL and UL directions.    If 'Max MIMO layers' is chosen, MeNB further filters the outcome from choice 'no preference', keeping only those MRDC band combinations and/or feature sets with the maximum number of MIMO layers in the candidate or already configured LTE SCells.    If 'Max MIMO layers with min CCs' is chosen, MeNB further filters the outcome from choice 'Max MIMO layers', keeping only those MRDC band combinations and/or feature sets with minimum number of LTE component carriers.    If 'Max MIMO layers with max CCs' is chosen, MeNB further filters the outcome from choice 'Max MIMO layers', keeping only those MRDC band combinations and/or feature sets with maximum number of LTE component carriers.    3GGP 38.331 name: allowedBC-ListMRDC
Range and step: no preference (1), max MIMO layers (2), max MIMO layers with min CCs (3), max MIMO layers with max CCs (4)

Parameter name: Buffer trigger for EN-DC B1-NR measurements activation
Description: Postpones EN-DC B1-NR measurements activation until DL or UL buffer overflow occurs.  The behavior applies to NR carriers of all cells where NRDCDPR-dynTriggerLteNrDcConfList-method is set to 'coverageAndBufferBased' or 'coverageAndDlUlBufferBased'.

Parameter name: Carrier aggregation LTE-NR DC cell list
Description: This parameter defines the cells of the LTE BTS for which Carrier Aggregation in an LTE-NR Dual Connectivity scenario is enabled. The 'lcrId' of the own LNCEL instances shall be added.    If set to value '-1', carrier aggregation for all cells of the BTS is enabled. In this case no dedicated cells are allowed to be configured, i.e. the list is allowed to include only one item.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Disable data buffer-triggered EN-DC based on UE type
Description: This parameter indicates whether data buffer-triggered EN-DC is disabled for UEs having QCI-7 bearer configured.  If this parameter is not set to 'none', then NRDCDPR-dynTriggerLteNrDcConfList-method is overwritten to 'coverageBased' for such UEs.    If this parameter is not configured, the same behavior applies as if it is set to 'none'.

Parameter name: Downlink pathloss change
Description: This is a trigger condition for power headroom submission due to pathloss change for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).

Parameter name: Dynamic trigger LTE-NR DC configuration list
Description: This structure defines the cells of the LTE BTS for which dynamic measurements in an LTE-NR Dual Connectivity scenario are enabled. The 'lcrId' of the own LNCEL instances shall be added and the method defines which kind of measurement for this particular cell instance shall be used.    If the functionality shall be applied to all cells of the eNB, the lcrId shall be configured to value '-1'. Please note, in this case the method value will be identical for all cells.

Parameter name: Activate B1-NR beam level measurements
Description: Activates B1-NR beam level measurements in the LNCEL indicated by lcrId

Parameter name: Local cell resource ID
Description: This parameter defines the cell of the LTE BTS for which dynamic measurements in an LTE-NR Dual Connectivity scenario is enabled.    The 'lcrId' of the own LNCEL instances shall be added.    If set to value '-1', dynamic trigger based LTE-NR Dual Connectivity and B1-NR measurements for EN-DC IMLB purpose for all cells of the BTS are enabled. In this case no dedicated cells are allowed to be configured, i.e. the list is allowed to include only one item.

Parameter name: Dynamic trigger method
Description: This parameter defines the method for dynamic triggering of LTE-NR Dual Connectivity.  - coverageBased: EN-DC is setup upon reception of a valid (i.e. pointing to a candidate NR PSCell) B1 measurement report  - coverageAndBufferBased: EN-DC is setup when DL buffer is overflowed and a valid (i.e. pointing to a candidate NR PSCell) B1 Measurement Report (MR) has been received from the UE.  - coverageAndDlUlBufferBased: This option is for coverage and DL and UL Buffer based. DL buffer - EN-DC is setup when the layer2 buffer is overflowed and a valid (i.e. pointing to a candidate NR PSCell) B1 Measurement Report (MR) has been received from the UE. UL Buffer- UL data buffer overflow trigger for EN-DC is indicated by U-Plane and valid B1 Measurement Report (MR) is stored, the eNB shall start EN-DC setup procedure using PSCell candidates from stored MR.

Parameter name: p-MaxEUTRA power offset applied in EN-DC
Description: enDCpMaxEUTRApowerOffset defines the power reduction applied by the eNB to the UE maximum transmit power (maxUEtxPower) to derive the maximum power value (p-MaxEUTRA) that the UE can transmit to the EUTRA when in EN-DC as follows:  p-maxEUTRA [dBm] = maxUEtxPower[dBm] - enDCpMaxEUTRApowerOffset [dB].    Where:  - maxUEtxPower is the UE maximum UE transmit power per corresponding EN-DC power class (see TS 38.101-3).  - p-maxEUTRA is the value configured by the eNB to the UE (see TS 36.331).    Note: p-MaxEUTRA value provided to the UE may be further limited by the UL maximum power allowed in the UE LTE PCell (i.e. via the parameter lteULpMaxOwnCell)

Parameter name: p-MaxNR power offset applied in EN-DC
Description: enDCpMaxNRpowerOffset defines the power reduction applied by the eNB to the UE maximum transmit power (maxUEtxPower) to derive the maximum power value (p-MaxNR) that the UE can transmit to the NR when in EN-DC as follows:  p-maxNR [dBm] = maxUEtxPower[dBm] - enDCpMaxNRpowerOffset [dB].    Where:  - maxUEtxPower is the UE maximum UE transmit power per corresponding EN-DC power class (see TS 38.101-3).  - p-maxNR is the value configured by the en-gNB to the UE, based on indication received from the eNB (see TS 38.331).    Note: p-MaxNR value provided to the UE may be further limited by the UL maximum power allowed in the UE NR PSCell.

Parameter name: NR band for EN-DC carrier allocation
Description: NR band for EN-DC carrier allocation sanity check.  The NR carrier frequencies configuration refer to NIDD parameters of gNB.

Parameter name: NR carrier center frequency in downlink
Description: NR absolute radio frequency channel number in downlink. For TDD, it's NR absolute radio frequency channel number (NR-ARFCN)

Parameter name: NR carrier bandwidth (DL)
Description: NR carrier bandwidth in MHz (in case of FDD NR cell, DL bandwidth is required here)

Parameter name: NR carrier SSB central frequency
Description: NR carrier SSB central frequency as NR Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number of SSB PBCH (NR-ARFCN)

Parameter name: LAA prioritization over EN-DC cell list
Description: List of cells for which LAA prioritization over EN-DC is enabled. The 'lcrId' of the own LNCEL instances shall be added.  This list is a subset of the Carrier aggregation LTE-NR DC cell list (cAggrLteNrDcCellList) as LAA cannot work without CA.    If set to value '-1', LAA prioritization over EN-DC is enabled for all cells of the cAggrLteNrDcCellList. In this case no dedicated cells are allowed to be configured, i.e. the list is allowed to include only one item.

Parameter name: Periodic PHR timer
Description: UE configuration for sending periodic power headroom reports for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).

Parameter name: Prohibited PHR timer
Description: Minimum intermediate time between two consecutive Power Headroom Reports for LTE-NR Dual Connectivity (EN-DC).

Parameter name: New Radio Dual Connectivity profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC NRDCPR.  It uniquely identifies an NRDCPR instance.

Parameter name: Buffer trigger for EN-DC B1-NR measurements activation
Description: Postpones EN-DC B1-NR measurements activation until DL or UL buffer overflow occurs.  The behavior applies to NR carriers of all cells where NRDCPR-dynTriggerLteNrDcConfList-method is set to 'coverageAndBufferBased' or 'coverageAndDlUlBufferBased'.    If this parameter is not configured, then if configured, NRDCDPR-bufTrigForB1Nr will take effect also for NR carriers of all cells where NRDCPR-dynTriggerLteNrDcConfList-method is set to 'coverageAndBufferBased' or 'coverageAndDlUlBufferBased'.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Disable data buffer-triggered EN-DC based on UE type
Description: This parameter indicates whether data buffer-triggered EN-DC is disabled for UEs having QCI-7 bearer configured.  If this parameter is not set to 'none', then NRDCPR-dynTriggerLteNrDcConfList-method is overwritten to 'coverageBased' for such UEs.    If this parameter is not configured, the same behavior applies as if it is set to 'none'.

Parameter name: Dynamic trigger LTE-NR DC configuration list
Description: This structure defines the cells of the LTE BTS for which dynamic measurements in an LTE-NR Dual Connectivity scenario are enabled. The 'lcrId' of the own LNCEL instances shall be added and the method defines which kind of measurement for this particular cell instance shall be used.    If the functionality shall be applied to all cells of the eNB, the lcrId shall be configured to value '-1'. Please note, in this case the method value will be identical for all cells.

Parameter name: Activate B1-NR beam level measurements
Description: Activates B1-NR beam level measurements in the LNCEL indicated by lcrId

Parameter name: Local cell resource ID
Description: This parameter defines the cell of the LTE BTS for which dynamic measurements in an LTE-NR Dual Connectivity scenario is enabled.    The 'lcrId' of the own LNCEL instances shall be added.    NOTE: If same cell is defined in NRDCPR and NRDCDPR (via 'lcrId' setting, including all cells setting), then the parameters defined in NRDCPR for the instance that corresponds to the 'lcrId' shall take precedence over the same parameters defined in NRDCDPR. If parameters are not defined in NRDCPR then parameters from NRDCDPR will apply via inheritance.

Parameter name: Dynamic trigger method
Description: This parameter defines the method for dynamic triggering of LTE-NR Dual Connectivity.  - coverageBased: EN-DC is setup upon reception of a valid (i.e. pointing to a candidate NR PSCell) B1 measurement report  - coverageAndBufferBased: EN-DC is setup when DL buffer is overflowed and a valid (i.e. pointing to a candidate NR PSCell) B1 Measurement Report (MR) has been received from the UE.  - coverageAndDlUlBufferBased: This option is for coverage and DL and UL Buffer based. DL buffer - EN-DC is setup when the layer2 buffer is overflowed and a valid (i.e. pointing to a candidate NR PSCell) B1 Measurement Report (MR) has been received from the UE. UL Buffer- UL data buffer overflow trigger for EN-DC is indicated by U-Plane and valid B1 Measurement Report (MR) is stored, the eNB shall start EN-DC setup procedure using PSCell candidates from stored MR.

Parameter name: p-MaxEUTRA power offset applied in EN-DC
Description: enDCpMaxEUTRApowerOffset defines the power reduction applied by the eNB to the UE maximum transmit power (maxUEtxPower) to derive the maximum power value (p-MaxEUTRA) that the UE can transmit to the EUTRA when in EN-DC as follows:  p-maxEUTRA [dBm] = maxUEtxPower[dBm] - enDCpMaxEUTRApowerOffset [dB].      Where:  - maxUEtxPower is the UE maximum UE transmit power per corresponding EN-DC power class (see TS 38.101-3).  - p-maxEUTRA is the value configured by the eNB to the UE (see TS 36.331).    Note: p-MaxEUTRA value provided to the UE may be further limited by the parameter LTE_ULpMaxOwnCell  If not configured, the value from the default profile NRDCDPR is used.

Parameter name: p-MaxNR power offset applied in EN-DC
Description: enDCpMaxNRpowerOffset defines the power reduction applied by the eNB to the UE maximum transmit power (maxUEtxPower) to derive the maximum power value (p-MaxNR) that the UE can transmit to the NR when in EN-DC as follows:  p-maxNR [dBm] = maxUEtxPower[dBm] - enDCpMaxNRpowerOffset [dB].    Where:  - maxUEtxPower is the UE maximum UE transmit power per corresponding EN-DC power class (see TS 38.101-3).  - p-maxNR is the value configured by the en-gNB to the UE, based on indication received from the eNB (see TS 38.331).    Note: p-MaxNR value provided to the UE may be further limited by the UL maximum power allowed in the UE NR PSCell  If not configured, the value from the default profile NRDCDPR is used.

Parameter name: NR idle mode configuration identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an NRFIM (NR Frequency Idle Mode configuration) managed object.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: List of NR carrier frequencies
Description: This is a list of NR carrier frequencies

Parameter name: Derive NR SSB index from cell
Description: The parameter indicates whether the UE may use, to derive the SSB index of a cell on the indicated SSB frequency and subcarrier spacing, the timing of any detected cell with the same SSB frequency and subcarrier spacing. If this parameter is set to 'true', the UE assumes SFN and frame boundary alignment across cells on the same NR carrier frequency as specified in 36.133 [16].

Parameter name: NR downlink frequency value
Description: This parameter defines the frequency position of the NR SS Block. It is a NR-ARFCN that corresponds to GSCN (global synchronization channel number) as specified in 5.4.3.1 of TS 38.101-1 and 38.101-2.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) frequency preference for idle mode load balancing
Description: NR carrier (SA) frequency preference for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing.  1: higher than LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR2 PScell  2: between LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR2 PScell and LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR1 PScell only  3: lower than LTE carrier supporting EN-DC with FR1 PScell only      NR carrier (SA) is always preferred for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing over LTE carrier w/o EN-DC support.
Range and step: higher than EnDc FR2 (1), between EnDc FR2 and EnDc FR1 (2), lower than EnDc FR1 (3)

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) freq prio for idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs
Description: Absolute priority of the NR carrier (SA) frequency layer used for secondary target selection of idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs.  For this parameter, 6.8 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: NR carrier (SA) weight factor for idle mode load balancing of NR SA capable UEs
Description: Weight factor of NR carrier (SA) frequency used by round robin algorithm for primary target selection of idle mode load balancing for NR SA capable UEs.

Parameter name: NR carrier frequency absolute priority
Description: Absolute priority of the NR carrier frequency. Equal priorities between RATs are not supported according to [TS 36.304].

Parameter name: NR carrier frequency sub priority
Description: This parameter indicates a fractional value to be added to the value of nrCelResPrio to obtain the absolute priority of the concerned carrier frequency for NR

Parameter name: NR inter-RAT quality threshold high
Description: This specifies the quality threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority NR RAT

Parameter name: NR inter-RAT quality threshold low
Description: This specifies the quality threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a lower priority NR RAT

Parameter name: NR inter frequency threshold high
Description: This specifies the threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency than the current serving frequency

Parameter name: NR inter frequency threshold low
Description: This specifies the threshold used in reselection towards the frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency

Parameter name: First frequency band for the NR frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the first frequency band for the NR frequency.

Parameter name: Second frequency band for the NR frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the second frequency band for the NR frequency

Parameter name: Third frequency band for the NR frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the third frequency band for the NR frequency.

Parameter name: First SUL frequency band for the NR neighbors
Description: This parameter indicates the first SUL (supplemental uplink) frequency band supported for the NR neighbors

Parameter name: Second SUL frequency band for the NR neighbors
Description: This parameter indicates the second SUL (supplemental uplink) frequency band supported for the NR neighbors

Parameter name: Absolute threshold NR SSB RSRP consolidation
Description: This parameter defines the absolute RSRP threshold (in unit of dBm) for the consolidation of measurement results per NR SS/PBCH block(s) from L1 filter(s). More to refer TS 38.304 5.2.1 description of absThreshSS-BlocksConsolidation.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 38.133 Table 10.1.6.1-1:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm  * -42 dBm means a threshold 'Infinity'.

Parameter name: Absolute threshold NR SSB RSRQ consolidation
Description: This parameter defines the absolute RSRQ threshold (in unit of dB) for the consolidation of measurement results per NR SS/PBCH block(s) from L1 filter(s). More to refer TS 38.304 5.2.1 description of absThreshSS-BlocksConsolidation.    The dB value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 38.133 Table 10.1.11.1-1:  * -43 dB means a threshold lower than -43 dB  * values between -42.5 dB and 20 dB mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 0.5 dB)  * 20.5 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 20 dB

Parameter name: Absolute threshold NR SSB SINR consolidation
Description: This parameter defines the absolute SINR threshold (in unit of dB) for the consolidation of measurement results per NR SS/PBCH block(s) from L1 filter(s). More to refer TS 38.304 5.2.1 description of absThreshSS-BlocksConsolidation.    The dB value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 38.133 Table 10.1.16.1-1:  * -23 dB means a threshold lower than -23 dB  * values between -22.5 dB and 40 dB mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 0.5 dB)  * 40.5 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to 40 dB

Parameter name: End symbol for NR SS RSSI measurement
Description: This parameter indicates the measured end OFDM symbol in the specified slots (refer nrSsRssiMeasSlots0to31 description) for NR SS RSSI measurement. Start symbol is 0 for each specified slot. If this parameter is not configured, the end symbol is the last symbol of the slot.  If this parameter is not configured, the end symbol is the last symbol of the slot. If this parameter is not configured, ss-RSSI-Measurement-r15 IE is not present in SIB24. In this condition all symbols in SMTC window are measured base on need.    Note: NR SS RSSI measurement is part of action for NR RSRQ measurement by UE. Refer table TS 38.215 5.1.3.

Parameter name: Slot 0 to 31 for NR SS RSSI measurement
Description: Slot 0 to 31 for NR SS RSSI measurement.    This parameter, nrSsRssiMeasSlots32to63 and nrSsRssiMeasSlots64to79 together indicate the slots in which the UE can perform NR SS RSSI measurements in the SMTC window. If all bits of this parameter, nrSsRssiMeasSlots32to63 and nrSsRssiMeasSlots64to79 are set to 0 or not configured, ss-RSSI-Measurement-r15 IE is not present in SIB24. In this condition all slots in SMTC window are measured base on need. NR SS RSSI measurement is part of action for NR RSRQ measurement by UE (TS 38.215 5.1.3).  The UE measures in slots for which the corresponding bit is set to 1.  The number of valid slots determined by ssbMtcDurationNr (SMTC window duration in number of subframes) and ssbScsNr (SSB subcarrierSpacing).  If ssbScsNr is 15KHz, then each subframe contains 1 slot.  If ssbScsNr is 30KHz, then each subframe contains 2 slots.  If ssbScsNr is 120KHz, then each subframe contains 8 slots.  If ssbScsNr is 240KHz, then each subframe contains 16 slots.    For example: when ssbMtcDurationNr is '2sf' and ssbScsNr is 240KHz, there are total 32 slots in SMTC window and bitmap of slot 0 to 31 are used and sent to UE.
Range and step: bits mask: Slot 0 (0), Slot 1 (1), Slot 2 (2), Slot 3 (3), Slot 4 (4), Slot 5 (5), Slot 6 (6), Slot 7 (7), Slot 8 (8), Slot 9 (9), Slot 10 (10), Slot 11 (11), Slot 12 (12), Slot 13 (13), Slot 14 (14), Slot 15 (15), Slot 16 (16), Slot 17 (17), Slot 18 (18), Slot 19 (19), Slot 20 (20), Slot 21 (21), Slot 22 (22), Slot 23 (23), Slot 24 (24), Slot 25 (25), Slot 26 (26), Slot 27 (27), Slot 28 (28), Slot 29 (29), Slot 30 (30), Slot 31 (31)

Parameter name: Slot 32 to 63 for NR SS RSSI measurement
Description: Slot 32 to 63 for NR SS RSSI measurement. See description of nrSsRssiMeasSlots0to31.

Parameter name: Slot 64 to 79 for NR SS RSSI measurement
Description: Slot 64 to 79 for NR SS RSSI measurement. See description of nrSsRssiMeasSlots0to31
Range and step: bits mask: Slot 64 (0), Slot 65 (1), Slot 66 (2), Slot 67 (3), Slot 68 (4), Slot 69 (5), Slot 70 (6), Slot 71 (7), Slot 72 (8), Slot 73 (9), Slot 74 (10), Slot 75 (11), Slot 76 (12), Slot 77 (13), Slot 78 (14), Slot 79 (15)

Parameter name: Number of measurement NR SSB to average
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum number of measurement results per beam based on NR SS/PBCH blocks to be averaged. The same value applies for each detected cell in that carrier frequency. More to refer TS 38.304 5.2.1 description of nrofSS-BlocksToAverage.

Parameter name: Maximum UL transmit power on the NR carrier frequency
Description: This parameter indicates the maximum uplink transmission power for a UE on the NR carrier frequency.

Parameter name: NR minimum needed quality parameter
Description: This specifies the minimum required quality level in the NR cell in dB.

Parameter name: NR minimum required receive level
Description: This specifies the minimum required RX level in the NR cell in dBm.  (Qrxlevmin in 36.304)

Parameter name: NR minimum required receive level for SUL
Description: This specifies the minimum required receive level in the NR cell in dBm if the UE supports supplementary uplink frequency of the NR cell.  (Qrxlevmin in 36.304)

Parameter name: NR SSB measurement timing duration
Description: This parameter defines the duration of the measurement window in which to receive NR SS/PBCH blocks. It is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: NR SSB measurement timing offset
Description: This parameter defines the offset of the measurement window in which to receive NR SS/PBCH blocks. It is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: NR SSB measurement timing periodicity
Description: This parameter defines the periodicity of the measurement window in which to receive NR SS/PBCH blocks. It is given in number of subframes.

Parameter name: NR SS block subcarrier spacing
Description: This parameter indicates the subcarrier spacing value for NR SS block

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection NR - NR cell reselection timer factor high mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionNR-r15 is multiplied by this factor if the UE is in the high mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection NR - NR cell reselection timer factor medium mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionNR-r15 is multiplied by this factor if the UE is in the medium mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: NR cell reselection timer
Description: NR cell reselection timer

Parameter name: New Radio measurements default profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC NRMEASDPR.  It uniquely identifies an NRMEASDPR instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Measurement gap enable for NR measurements
Description: This parameter is used to enable/disable measurement gaps for NR measurements for FR1 and/or FR2.

Parameter name: Wait for high priority measurement report timer
Description: This parameter defines how long eNB will wait for a B1-NR measurement report from a UE for a high priority NR carrier after it has received a B1-NR measurement report from a UE for a low priority NR carrier. If parameter is not configured, EN-DC establishment or redirection is attempted without waiting for measurement report for higher priority NR carrier.

Parameter name: Quantity configuration for NR measurements
Description: Specifies the quantity configuration parameters for NR measurements.

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for RSRP index
Description: Filtering coefficient used for RSRP measurement results of an NR RS index for a particular RS Type (e.g. SS/PBCH block).

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for RSRQ index
Description: Filtering coefficient used for RSRQ measurement results of an NR RS index for a particular RS Type (e.g. SS/PBCH block).

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for RSRP
Description: Filtering coefficient used for RSRP measurement results of an NR cell for a particular RS Type (e.g. SS/PBCH block).

Parameter name: Filtering coefficient used for RSRQ
Description: Filtering coefficient used for RSRQ measurement results of an NR cell for a particular RS Type (e.g. SS/PBCH block)

Parameter name: Quantity configuration index
Description: Quantity configuration index

Parameter name: Retry timer for B1-NR measurements activation
Description: Timer between subsequent activations of B1-NR measurements used as dynamic trigger for EN-DC establishment or for redirection to 5G SA. Its expiration triggers B1-NR measurements reactivation. It is started at each activation of B1-NR measurements which means time in which measurements are not active at the UE is (retryTimerB1NR - supervisionTimerB1NR).    If retryTimerB1NR is not configured, then timer functionality is disabled in the cells assigned to NRMEASDPR (i.e. not explicitly assigned to any NRMEASPR via NRMEASPR-cellList). After supervision timer expiry there will be no attempt to reactivate B1-NR measurements unless reactivation is caused by other trigger.

Parameter name: Supervision timer for B1-NR measurements
Description: Timer defining how long B1-NR measurements can remain active at the UE. Its expiration triggers B1-NR measurements deactivation. If periodic B1-NR measurements functionality is enabled (i.e. actPeriodicB1NRMeas is set to different value than 'disabled'), timer is (re)started each time B1-NR measurements are activated at the UE.    If supervisionTimerB1NR is not configured, periodical B1-NR measurements are deactivated in the cells assigned to NRMEASDPR (i.e. not explicitly assigned to any NRMEASPR via NRMEASPR-cellList).

Parameter name: New Radio measurements profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC NRMEASPR.  It uniquely identifies an NRMEASPR instance.

Parameter name: Cell List
Description: This parameter defines cells that use NRMEASPR instance for configuring and control of NR measurements. The 'lcrId' of the own LNCEL instances shall be added.    If 'lcrId' of a cell is not defined in NRMEASPR-cellList of any NRMEASPR instance, then NRMEASDPR will be used for that cell.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Measurement gap enable for NR measurement
Description: This parameter is used to enable/disable measurement gaps for NR measurements for FR1 and/or FR2.

Parameter name: Wait for high priority measurement report timer
Description: This parameter defines how long eNB will wait for a B1-NR measurement report from a UE for a high priority NR carrier after it has received a B1-NR measurement report from a UE for a low priority NR carrier. If parameter is not configured, EN-DC establishment or redirection is attempted without waiting for measurement report for higher priority NR carrier.

Parameter name: Retry timer for B1-NR measurements activation
Description: Timer between subsequent activations of B1-NR measurements used as dynamic trigger for EN-DC establishment or for redirection to 5G SA. Its expiration triggers B1-NR measurements reactivation. It is started at each activation of B1-NR measurements which means time in which measurements are not active at the UE is (retryTimerB1NR - supervisionTimerB1NR).  If retryTimerB1NR is not configured, then timer functionality is disabled in the cells assigned to NRMEASPR instance. After supervision timer expiry there will be no attempt to reactivate B1-NR measurements unless reactivation is caused by other trigger.

Parameter name: Supervision timer for B1-NR measurements
Description: Timer defining how long B1-NR measurements can remain active at the UE. Its expiration triggers B1-NR measurements deactivation. If periodic B1-NR measurements functionality is enabled (i.e. actPeriodicB1NRMeas is set to different value than 'disabled'), timer is (re)started each time B1-NR measurements are activated at the UE.  If supervisionTimerB1NR is not configured, periodical B1-NR measurements are deactivated in the cells assigned to the NRMEASPR instance.

Parameter name: Network slice identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC NWSLICE.  It uniquely identifies a NWSLICE instance.

Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: IPv4 address 1 reference
Description: This parameter defines the reference to the IPADDRESSV4 object instance which holds the IPv4 address to be used for the slice U-Plane.  The related read only object will provide the actually assigned IP address. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNL or TNLSVC.    FDN example: MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-7/IPADDRESSV4-1  SDN example: TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-7/IPADDRESSV4-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line. The RAT restart will happen if the ipV4AddressDN1 is changed and it belongs to main transport network ( i.e NWLSICE-transportNwId= LNBTS-mainTransportNwId).

Parameter name: IPv6 Address 1 reference
Description: This parameter defines the reference to the IPADDRESSV6 object instance which holds the IPv6 address to be used for the slice U-Plane.  The related runtime object will provide the actually assigned IP address. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNL or TNLSVC.    FDN example: MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-2/IPADDRESSV6-1  SDN example: TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-2/IPADDRESSV6-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line. The RAT restart will happen if the ipV6AddressDN1 is changed and it belongs to main transport network ( i.e NWLSICE-transportNwId= LNBTS-mainTransportNwId).

Parameter name: Operator specific QCI list for slice
Description: This parameter provides the list of operator specific QCIs to be used for slicing.  NWSLICE-operatorSpecificQciList must contain only QCI values which are included in LNBTS-qciTabOperator-qci, except LNBTS-qciTabOperatorDefault.

Parameter name: Serving Gateway IPv4/v6 address
Description: By configuring this optional parameter GTP-U path supervision is activated for the slice defined in this instance.    NWSLICE-sgwIpAddress must contain only SGW IP address values which are included in GTPU-sgwIpAddressList-sgwIpAddress    Both IP address formats can be used.    Format: IPv4 address parameter in dotted decimals or IPv6 address parameter acc. to RFC 4291.    IPv4 address ranges:  It is not allowed to configure the address 0.0.0.0, the broadcast address 255.255.255.255 or an address within the range of multicast addresses  (224.0.0.0-239.255.255.255) or loop-back addresses (127.0.0.0-127.255.255.255).    IPv6 address ranges:  The address shall be within the range of Unique Local Unicast addresses (FC00::/7) or Global Unicast addresses (2000::/3).

Parameter name: CPlane Counters Activation

Exception to this is the case when at least for one PMQAP Profile the parameter actCplaneCounters is created, then for all the rest of the Profiles are assumed with default configuration 0 (deactivated).

Parameter name: L2 Counters Activation
Description: This parameter is for activation and deactivation of the L2 counters in each PMQAP Profile.    Note: By default the first 20 Profiles from PMQAP1 until PMQAP20 are active when this parameter is not created (left optional). Description: This parameter is for activation and deactivation of the Packet Scheduler counters in each PMQAP Profile.    Note: By default the first 20 Profiles from PMQAP1 until PMQAP20 are active when this parameter is not created (left optional). Exception to this is the case when at least for one PMQAP Profile the parameter actPacketSchedulerCounters is created, then for all the rest of the Profiles are assumed with default configuration 0 (deactivated).
