Parameter name: Search all candidates in case of emergency sessions
Description: Determines if special preemption rules shall be applied for emergency sessions.    Yes:  In case of an emergency session, candidates are searched in other PLMNs if no candidates are found in the list of preferred preemption candidates (preferredPreempCandList).  'Other PLMNs' means either PLMNs of the cell or of cells in the same baseband pool with the same preemption profile assigned which are not in the list of preferred preemption candidates.    applyRulesForRegularUsers :  The same preemption rules are applied as for regular users.

Parameter name: Search candidates from other PLMNs
Description: Determines if candidates should be searched in other PLMNs if no candidates are found in the list of preferred preemption candidates (preferredPreempCandList).    No  Preemption candidates are only searched in the list of preferred preemption candidates (preferredPreempCandList).    Yes  If no candidate is found in the list of preferred preemption candidates (preferredPreempCandList), candidates are searched in the other PLMNs.  'Other PLMNs' means either PLMNs of the cell or of cells in the same baseband pool with the same preemption profile assigned which are not in the list of preferred preemption candidates.    forRestPLMNGroupUsersOnly  If no candidate is found in the list of preferred preemption candidates (preferredPreempCandList), candidates are searched in the PLMN of the requestor (only applicable if the requestor PLMN does not belong to the list of preferred preemption candidates).

Parameter name: Power saving group identifier
Description: Instance identifier of the object PSGRP. This parameter is used only for O&M purposes.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving cSON control enabled
Description: Flag which indicates whether the cSON Solution is enabled to control the power group's cell membership and cell switch off priority order.  If lbpsCSONCtlEnabled is set to true, the cSON Solution application can create, delete and modify the power group cell list entries as well as set the power group cell switch off order and determine whether to enable the last cell to be switched off.  If lbpsCSONCtlEnabled is set to false, the cSON Solution cannot add cells to, or remove cells from, the power group and the cSON Solution cannot change the power group cell switch off order or change the last cell switch off enabled value..

Parameter name: Load-based power saving cell period list
Description: List of periods during which power saving may be initiated for the cell identified by lnCelId in the Power Saving Group.    Power saving time window lbpsCelPeriodList cannot be declared outside of time window set in lbpsPeriodList.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving for specific cell for specific day of week
Description: The load-based power saving day of week parameter identifies the day of the week for which the power saving period is defined for a specific cell. (No ID)
Range and step: Sun (0), Mon (1), Tue (2), Wed (3), Thu (4), Fri (5), Sat (6), everyDay (7)

Parameter name: Load-based power saving duration on cell level
Description: The load-based power saving duration parameter identifies the end time of the power saving period. The power saving period begins at the lbpsStartTime and continues for lbpsDuration number of minutes.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving switch off method on cell level
Description: Define a specific power saving method - Cell Switch Off, TX Paths Switch Off or Mixed Switch Off method for extended cell switch off configuration.
Range and step: Cell Switch Off (0), Tx Paths Switch Off (1), Mixed Switch Off (2)

Parameter name: Load-based power saving start time hour on cell level
Description: The load-based power saving start time hour parameter, along with the load-based power saving start time minute parameter, identifies the local time when the power saving period begins on cell level.  The eNB considers daylight saving time.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving start time minute on cell level
Description: The load-based power saving start time minute parameter, along with the load-based power saving start time hour parameter, identifies the local time when the power saving period begins on cell level.

Parameter name: LTE cell configuration identifier
Description: Instance identifier of MOC LNCEL included in the Power Saving Group. A cell may only be a member of one Power Saving Group.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving cell list
Description: List of cells that service the same coverage area or follow the same power saving schedule are included in the Power Saving Group.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving cell switch off order
Description: The load-based power saving cell switch off order parameter defines the relative number within a sequence in which a cell has resources switched off if the capacity of the enabled cells in the Power Saving Group can support the current load.  Cells have resources switched off according to Cell resource switch off order from 1 to N.    lbpsCellSOOrder value of 100 has a special meaning based on lbpsLastCellSOEnable value:  - If lbpsLastCellSOEnable is true, the cell has the lowest cell resource switch off order value.  - If lbpsLastCellSOEnable is false, the cell resources cannot be switched off.    Each cell within a Power Saving Group must be assigned to a unique cell switch off order value with the exception that multiple cells may be assigned to the special value of 100.    If PSGRP-lbpsCellList-lbpsUseExtConfig is set to 'true' for a cell configured with special meaning value lbpsCellSOOrder ==100 then all cells configured with special meaning value lbpsCellSOOrder ==100 must be configured for extended configuration AND must have same extended configuration OR not configured at all for extended case. It is not allowed to have different extended configurations for different cells with lbpsCellSOOrder = 100 as a consequence of common special handling of such cells as part of PSM mechanism

Parameter name: Load Based Power Saving Use Extended Configuration
Description: Allow to modify, at individual cell level, the switch off method to be applied and time windows under which switch off is allowed.    If lbpsUseExtConfig is set to true for a cell but no entry found for respective cell under the lbpsCelPeriodList then the cell is not allowed to switch off at all, neither Cell Switch Off Method nor Tx Paths Switch Off method, during the time period as defined by lbpsPeriodList. If lbpsUseExtConfig is set to true for a cell and at least an entry found for respective cell under the lbpsCelPeriodList then the cell is allowed to switch off, be it Cell Switch Off or Tx Paths Switch Off method as defined by lbpsCellSOMethod enum, only during the time period as defined by respective entry under lbpsCelPeriodList. If lbpsUseExtConfig is set to true for a cell and at least an entry found for respective cell under the lbpsCelPeriodList but the time is outside the time window as defined by PSGRP::lbpsPeriodList then the cell is not allowed to switch off at all, neither Cell Switch Off nor Tx Paths Switch Off method as defined by lbpsCellSOMethod enum, as time period as defined at Power saving group level by PSGRP::lbpsPeriodList is having a master role.    lbpsUseExtConfig allows to configure cell for extended configuration when set to true. When extended configuration is activated (lbpsUseExtConfig = true) for at least one cell with special value lbpsCellSOOrder = 100, then all the cells with lbpsCellSOOrder = 100 must be configured with extended configuration, or not configured at all for extended case. It is not allowed to have different extended configurations for different cells with lbpsCellSOOrder = 100 as a consequence of common special handling of such cells as part of PSM mechanism.

Parameter name: LTE cell configuration identifier
Description: Instance identifier of MOC LNCEL included in the Power Saving Group. A cell may only be a member of one Power Saving Group.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving NR activation cell list
Description: The coordinated NR cell configuration

Description: This parameter indicates the Primary Mobile Network Code of the gNB.

Parameter name: MNC length in PLMN
Description: This parameter indicates the length of the MNC (Mobile Network Code) in the PLMN (Public Land Mobile Network) ID, in digits.

Parameter name: New Radio Cell instance identifier
Description: This parameter is the New Radio Cell Identifier, which is part of the New Radio Global Cell Identifier (NR-CGI) of the neighbor cell served by en-gNB.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving guard timer for NR activation
Description: The parameter determines the minimum time, which must elapse before NR cell, switched off to energy saving state, can be reactivated to normal operation by eNB.    Note:  lbpsGuardTimerNrAct should set to a value which is higher than the value set for load-based power saving monitoring window NR cell activation.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving last cell minimum load
Description: Defines the low-watermark for the load of the last enabled cell of a power group.    If the power group load is below the last cell low-water mark (lbpsLastCellMinLoad), the eNB will switch off a cell if the last cell switch off enabled flag (lbpsLastCellSOEnabled) is 'true'. If there are no enabled power group cells, there is no power group load. All switched off power group cells will be switched on when not in a power saving period.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving last cell reduced TX min load
Description: Defines the low-watermark for the load of the last enabled cell of a power group for reduced TX power saving.  If the aggregate power group load of the enabled power group last cells* is below the last cell low-water mark for reduced TX power saving (lbpsLastCellRTXMinLoad) for a minimum duration, the eNB will switch off TX paths at the enabled power group last cells if the last cell switch off enabled flag (lbpsLastCellSOEnabled) is 'true'.    All switched off TX paths will be switched on at all power group cells when not in a power saving period.    * The power group last cells are either all power group cells with switch off order set to the last cell special value (lbpsCellSOOrder = 100) or if no power group cell is assigned the last cell special value, then the single enabled power group cell full TX paths with the greatest lbpsCellSOOrder value.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving last cell switch off enabled
Description: Flag which determines whether the last enabled power group cell may have resources switched off and whether power group cells with the special handling cell switch off order value may have resources switched off.  If lbpsLastCellSOEnabled is true, the last enabled cell and the cells with the special handling cell switch off order value may have resources switched off.  If lbpsLastCellSOEnabled is false, neither the last enabled cell nor the cells with the special handling cell switch off order value may have resources switched off.

Parameter name: Load based PS calculation method
Description: This parameter defines the load quantity calculation method where:    G: load from PRB usage for GBR  N: load from PRB usage for non-GBR  G_N_combined: Load from combined normalized PRB usage for GBR and non-GBR  W: load from weight-based metric for non-GBR  P: load from PDCCH CCE usage

Parameter name: Load-based power saving maximum load
Description: Defines the high-watermark for the aggregate load of a power group.  Two or more enabled power group cells:  - The eNb will not switch off a cell if the expected aggregate power group load of the remaining enabled power group cells will be above the high-water mark value of lbpsMaxLoad.  - If needed, the eNB will switch on power group cells in the reverse cell switch off order to increase the aggregate power group capacity until the expected power group load is below the high-water mark value of lbpsMaxLoad.    Last enabled power group cell:  - If the power group load is below the last cell low-water mark (lbpsLastCellMinLoad), the eNB will switch off a cell if the last cell switch off enabled flag (lbpsLastCellSOEnabled) is 'true'. The high-water mark is not considered as there is no expected aggregate power group load.  - If there are no enabled power group cells, there is no power group load. All switched off power group cells will be switched on when not in a power saving period.    It is recommended that lbpsMaxLoad be less than the following load-balancing threshold parameters to reduce the chance that load-balancing will be initiated for one of the remaining enabled power group cells:    LNCEL:: intraFreqLbLoadThresholds parameters:  highLoadGbrDl,  highLoadNonGbrDl, and  highLoadPdcchDl.    LNCEL::iFLBLoadThresholds parameters:  iFLBHighLoadGBRDL,  iFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL, and  iFLBHighLoadPdcch.    It is recommended to set lbpsMaxLoad > 2*lbpsMinLoad to avoid a situation where a cell is switched off due to the power group load being below lbpsMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above lbpsMaxLoad.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving maximum load level for NR cell activation
Description: The load level of the controlling LTE PSGRP, which must be exceeded to trigger NR cell activation.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving minimum load
Description: Defines the low-watermark for the aggregate load of a power group.  The eNB will switch off a power group cell in cell switch off order if the aggregate power group load is less than or equal to the low-watermark value of lbpsMinLoad and the expected aggregate power group load for the reduced aggregate power group capacity is less than the high-water mark value of lbpsMaxLoad.    lbpsMinLoad is used except when determining whether the last enabled cell in the Power Group may be switched off (see lbpsLastCellMinLoad).    It is recommended to set lbpsMinLoad < lbpsMaxLoad/2 to avoid a situation where a cell is switched off due to the power group load being below lbpsMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above lbpsMaxLoad.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving minimum number of EN-DC capable UEs
Description: Defines minimum number of RRC Connected EN-DC capable UEs within a controlling LTE PSGRP, which must be equal or exceeded to trigger NR cell activation.

Parameter name: Load based power saving monitoring window for cell switch off
Description: This parameter defines the cell switch off load window

Parameter name: Load based power saving monitoring window for cell switch on
Description: This parameter defines the cell switch on load window

Parameter name: Load based power saving monitoring window for RTX switch off
Description: This parameter defines the RTX switch off load window

Parameter name: Load based power saving monitoring window for RTX switch on
Description: This parameter defines the RTX switch on load window.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving monitoring window NR cell activation
Description: Monitoring window size for evaluation of controlling LTE PSGRP load for purpose of NR cell activation.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving PDCCH load offset
Description: Offset subtracted from the sum of normalized PDCCH load of each enabled power group cell.    The power group PDCCH load average may be greater than the power group GBR and non-GBR load averages. Load-based power saving PDCCH load offset (lbpsPdcchLoadOffset) is applied to align the power group PDCCH load average with the power group GBR and non-GBR load averages.    If the power group PDCCH load average is less than lbpsPdcchLoadOffset, then the power group PDCCH load average is set to 0%.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving period list
Description: List of periods during which power saving may be initiated for the cells in the Power Saving Group.  A period is defined as the time between a start time and an end time within a day of the week. There may be multiple periods defined during any single day of the week.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving day of week
Description: The load-based power saving day of week parameter identifies the day of the week for which the power saving period is defined.
Range and step: Sun (0), Mon (1), Tue (2), Wed (3), Thu (4), Fri (5), Sat (6)

Parameter name: Load-based power saving duration
Description: The load-based power saving duration parameter identifies the end time of the power saving period. The power saving period begins at the lbpsStartTime and continues for lbpsDuration number of minutes.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving start time hour
Description: The load-based power saving start time hour parameter, along with the load-based power saving start time minute parameter, identifies the local time when the power saving period begins.  The eNB considers daylight saving time.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving start time minute
Description: The load-based power saving start time minute parameter, along with the load-based power saving start time hour parameter, identifies the local time when the power saving period begins.

Parameter name: Load-Based Power Saving Suspended
Description: Indicates whether Energy Saving functionality is suspended for the Power Saving Group cells for the power saving period.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving reduced TX cell capacity offset
Description: Defines the percent cell throughput at a reduced TX path cell relative to the full TX path cell throughput expected due to the change in supported transmission mode due to reduction in cell TX paths.  The cell throughput is expected to be decreased due to the change in supported transmission mode by the cell with reduced TX paths.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving reduced TX maximum load
Description: Defines the high-watermark for the aggregate load of a power group for reduced TX power saving.  One or more enabled power group cells with all TX paths enabled:  - The eNb will not switch off TX paths at a cell if the expected aggregate power group load of the enabled power group cells will be above the high-water mark for reduced TX value of lbpsRTXMaxLoad.  - If the aggregate power group load is greater than the high-water mark for a minimum duration, the eNB will switch on TX paths of power group cells in the reverse cell switch off order to increase the aggregate power group capacity until the expected power group load is below the high-water mark for reduced TX value of lbpsRTXMaxLoad.    All switched off TX paths will be switched on at all power group cells when not in a power saving period.    It is recommended that lbpsRTXMaxLoad be less than the following load-balancing threshold parameters to reduce the chance that load-balancing will be initiated for one of the enabled power group cells with reduced TX paths:    LNCEL:: intraFreqLbLoadThresholds parameters:  highLoadGbrDl,  highLoadNonGbrDl, and  highLoadPdcchDl.    LNCEL::iFLBLoadThresholds parameters:  iFLBHighLoadGBRDL,  iFLBHighLoadNonGBRDL, and  iFLBHighLoadPdcch.    It is recommended to activate load-equalization (LNBTS:actAmle) to further reduce the chance that load-balancing will be initiated for one of the enabled power group cells with reduced TX paths.    Note: lbpsRTXMaxLoad is for the average load across the set of power group cells while the referenced load-balancing load parameters are for a single cell. Hence, these recommendation reduce the chance that load-balancing will be initiated at a power group cell and do not eliminate the chance.    It is recommended to set lbpsMaxLoad > 2*lbpsMinLoad to avoid a situation where a cell is switched off due to the power group load being below lbpsMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above lbpsMaxLoad.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving reduced TX minimum load
Description: Defines the low-watermark for the aggregate load of a power group for reduced TX power saving.  The eNB will switch off TX paths of a power group cell in cell switch off order if the aggregate power group load is less than or equal to the low-watermark for reduced TX power saving value of lbpsRTXMinLoad for a minimum duration and the expected aggregate power group load for the reduced aggregate power group capacity is less than the high-water mark for reduced TX power saving value of lbpsRTXMaxLoad.    lbpsRTXMinLoad is used except when determining whether the last enabled cell in the Power Group with all TX paths enabled may have its TX paths switched off (see lbpsLastCellRTXMinLoad).    All switched off TX paths will be switched on at all power group cells when not in a power saving period.    It is recommended to set lbpsRTXMinLoad < lbpsRTXMaxLoad/2 to avoid a situation where a cell has its TX paths switched off due to the power group load being below lbpsRTXMinLoad and within a few minutes is switched on due to the power group load increasing above lbpsRTXMaxLoad.

Parameter name: Load-based power saving retry timer for NR activation
Description: The parameter determines the retry timer for triggering again NR cell reactivation after timer expiry.

Parameter name: Load based power saving switch off method
Description: This parameter defines the applicable switch off method for all cells of respective power group:  0: Only Cell Switch Off  1: Only TX Switch Off  2: New Mixed MIMO Muting and Cell Switch Off behavior  3: Legacy 'Cell Switch Off'/'TX Switch Off' mixed behavior according to cell configured switch off order (default value)    Switch off method configured with this parameter is only applicable when MIMO Muting and Cell Switch OFF Cohabitation during same time window is activated (actMixedSOMethod='true').
Range and step: Cell Switch Off (0), TX Switch Off (1), Mixed Switch Off (2), Legacy Mixed Switch Off (3)

Parameter name: Load based PS switch off triggering rule
Description: This parameter defines the switch-off triggering rule.  - MaxValueMethod: (Max 10s load in switch_off_load_window <= min_thr) AND (LoadAftSwOff( latest 10s volume ) <= max_thr)  - SlidingAverageMethod: LoadAftSwOff(Average volume in switch_off_load_window ) <= min_thr

Parameter name: Load based PS switch on triggering rule
Description: This parameter defines the switch-on triggering rule.  - MinValueMethod: Min 10s load in switch_on_load_window > max_thr  - SlidingAverageMethod: Load( Average volume in switch_on_load_window ) > max_thr

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Redirection target configuration identifier
Description: This parameter defines the number of redirection targets specified for the respective cell and this parameter is naming attribute of MOC REDRT.

Parameter name: Add GSM system information to redirection message
Description: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which GSM system information is included in the RRC Connection Release message.  GSM system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further GSM cells will be omitted even if configured via LNLRELG settings.

Parameter name: Add UTRAN system information to redirection message
Description: The parameter selects the kinds of UE redirections (CS fallback, UE redirection with context release, both) for which UTRAN system information shall be included in the RRC Connection Release message.  UTRAN system information (SI) will be added for up to 16 cells. SI for further UTRAN cells will be omitted even if configured via LNRELW settings.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Redirection priority for CS fallback with redirection
Description: This parameter defines priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during CS Fallback with redirection procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 6 lowest.

Parameter name: Redirection priority for emergency call
Description: This parameter defines priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during Emergency Call handling procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 6 lowest.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: CDMA band
Description: This parameter must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000-HRPD or redirRAT=cdma2000-1xRTT.  Specifies the cdma2000 band class.

Parameter name: CDMA frequency
Description: Specifies the cdma2000 ARFCN.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".    This parameter must be configured if redirRAT=cdma2000-HRPD or redirRAT=cdma2000-1xRTT.

Parameter name: eUTRA frequency
Description: Specifies the eUTRA frequency (max value ref to 36.331)  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".    This parameter must be configured if redirRAT=eutra.

Parameter name: UTRA frequency
Description: This parameter specifies the UTRA frequency.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".    This parameter must be configured if redirRAT=utraFDD.

Parameter name: UTRA TDD frequency list
Description: This parameter specifies a list of UTRA TDD frequency.  The parameter value is based on the absolute radio-frequency channel number "ARFCN".    This parameter must be configured if redirRAT=utraTDD.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN values list
Description: The parameter specifies a list of GERAN ARFCN values.  At least one element of the structure must be configured if redirRAT=geran.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN priority order
Description: The parameter specifies a priority order for GERAN ARFCN value according to which eNB shall built list of GERAN targets (CarrierFreqsGERAN IE of RedirectedCarrierInfo IE) in RRCConnectionRelease message with CSFB to GERAN via redirection.  GERAN ARFCN carriers will be placed in explicitListOfARFCNs IE as a choice of CarrierFreqsGERAN IE of RedirectedCarrierInfo IE in order of 'GERAN ARFCN priority order' value starting from lowest value to highest configured by operator. GERAN ARFCN values without configured 'GERAN ARFCN priority order' will be placed at the end of list.

Parameter name: GERAN ARFCN value
Description: The parameter specifies a GERAN ARFCN value.

Parameter name: GERAN band indicator
Description: Indicator to distinguish the GERAN frequency band in case of ARFCN values associated with either GSM 1800 or GSM 1900 carriers.  For ARFCN values not associated with one of those bands, the indicator has no meaning.  This parameter must always be configured if redirRAT=geran.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - NR neighbor cell SSB frequency
Description: The SSB frequency of the NR carrier used for redirection.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Duration of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the duration of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration) to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Offset of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the offset of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration). It is used together with periodicity to determine the first subframe of each SMTC window to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Periodicity of SMTC
Description: This parameter defines the periodicity of SMTC (SS/PBCH block Measurement Time Configuration). It is used together with offset to determine the first subframe of each SMTC window to receive SS/PBCH blocks.

Parameter name: NR redirection carrier frequency - Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier
Description: Subcarrier spacing of NR carrier.  Configuration of ssbSubcarrierSpacing for a NR frequency in eNB must be the same as that in the neighboring gNB where UE is redirected to. Generally, for NR frequencies in FR1, ssbSubcarrierSpacing must be set to 15kHz or 30kHz. For NR frequencies in FR2, ssbSubcarrierSpacing must be set to 120 kHz or 240 kHz. Refer to TS 38.104 'Applicable SS raster entries per operating band' tables.

Parameter name: RAT for redirection
Description: This parameter selects the RAT to which the UE is redirected.
Range and step: eutra (0), geran (1), utraFDD (2), cdma2000HRPD (3), cdma20001xRTT (4), utraTDD (5), nr (6)

Parameter name: Redirection priority for UE context release
Description: This parameter defines priority for target RAT in selection of redirection target during UE Context Release with redirection procedure.  Value 1 means highest priority and value 8 lowest.

Parameter name: RIAPR identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC RIAPR, it uniquely identifies an instance of the RIAPR configuration.  RIAPR contains Remote Interference Avoidance functional parameters which is subordinate under LNBTS.

Parameter name: Allowance of TDD Remote Interference specific sequence sending for test purpose
Description: This parameter controls whether it is allowed to send Remote Interference specific sequence manually for test purpose.  If the parameter is set to "true", the cell will send own RI specific sequence expressing eNB RI specific identity at the last 2 symbols of legacy DwPTS in a period of 163840 GPS seconds .  The detail sequence index and sending time are determined by 'eNB RI specific identity'.

Parameter name: Allowance of rollback DwPTS of special subframe to SSP5 (3:9:2)
Description: This parameter controls whether this cell is allowed to rollback DwPTS of special subframe as SSP5 (3:9:2) if it is confirmed as the remote interference source.  If the parameter is set to "true", the cell may be ready to rollback DwPTS as ssp5 once the number of RI sequence detected exceed threshold. It should be known that this action might result in downlink throughput loss due to legacy DwPTS symbols are unavailable

Parameter name: Allowance of rollback DwPTS from SSP6/7 to SSP5(3:9:2) for downhill trend of remote interference in a defined duration
Description: This parameter controls whether this cell is allowed to rollback DwPTS of special subframe as SSP5 (3:9:2) regarding downhill trend of remote interference  If the parameter is set to "true", the cell may be ready to rollback DwPTS as ssp5 if downhill trend of remote interference is confirmed in a period. It should be known that this action might result in downlink throughput loss due to PUSCH is unavailable in DwPTS.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: The lower threshold per RB for Remote Interference detected on UpPTS and the first uplink subframe(dBm)
Description: This parameter indicates the lower threshold per RB for remote interference detected on UpPTS or the first uplink subframe(dBm).  If detected interference was lower than this parameter or downhill shape of interference disappears, remote interference is deemed as disappearance.

Parameter name: The lower threshold for Remote Interference detected
Description: The lower threshold for Remote Interference detected (dBm).

Parameter name: The threshold of signal power difference for jointing Remote Interference specific sequences detected in 1st half-frame and 2nd half-frame
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of signal power difference for jointing Remote interference specific sequences detected in 1st half-frame and 2nd half-frame.  Only if the signal power difference of two sequences is lower than this threshold, they will be available for joint.

Parameter name: The monitoring window length (the number of half-frame) of Remote Interference detection and disappearance in UpPTS or the first uplink subframe.
Description: This parameter indicates the monitoring window length (in unit of 1000 half-frames)of remote interference detection and disappearance in UpPTS or the first uplink subframe.

Parameter name: The monitoring window length (minutes) of Remote Interference specific sequence detection and disappearance in UpPTS and the first uplink subframe.
Description: The monitoring window length (minutes) for DwPTS rollback regarding remote interference trend or specific eNB identity detection and disappearance in UpPTS or the first uplink subframe.

Parameter name: The monitoring window length (the number of subframe) of Remote Interference detection and disappearance in UpPTS.
Description: This parameter indicates the monitoring window length (in unit of 1000 special subframes) of remote interference detection and disappearance in UpPTS.

Parameter name: The threshold of times(N3) for detecting Remote Interference specific sequence for recovering DwPTS rollback and stopping sending RI sequence purpose.
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of times(N3) for detecting Remote Interference specific sequence. If the times of external RI specific sequence was detected not exceed this threshold, the cell may trigger to recover DwPTS to legacy configuration and stop sending RI sequence.

Parameter name: The threshold of times(N2) for detecting Remote Interference specific sequence for DwPTS rollback purpose.
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of times(N2) for detecting Remote Interference specific sequence. If the times of external RI specific sequence was detected exceed this threshold, the cell may trigger DwPTS rollback as SSP5

Parameter name: The threshold of times(N1) for detecting Remote Interference specific sequence for purpose of own RI specific sequence sending.
Description: This parameter indicates the threshold of times(N1) for detecting Remote Interference specific sequence for purpose of own RI specific sequence sending. If the times of external RI specific sequence was detected exceed this threshold, the cell will trigger to broadcast its own RI specific sequence.

Parameter name: The upper threshold per RB for Remote Interference detected on UpPTS and the first uplink subframe(dBm)
Description: This parameter indicates the upper threshold per RB for remote interference detected on UpPTS or the first uplink subframe(dBm).  if detected interference exceed this parameter and downhill shape of interference take places, remote interference is deemed as appearance.

Parameter name: The upper threshold for Remote Interference detected
Description: The upper threshold for Remote Interference detected(dBm).

Parameter name: RAN Information Management (RIM) identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC RIM.  It uniquely identifies a RIM instance.

Parameter name: Blacklisted UTRAN cells for RIM
Description: List of filter criteria for UTRAN cells which are to be blacklisted in terms of RIM.  No RIM association will be established to UTRAN cells which match with at least one of the filter criteria.    If this parameter is omitted, no UTRAN neighbor cells are blacklisted.  In each list entry at least one of the blacklisting criteria rncId, carrierFreq or plmnId (mcc, mnc, mncLength) must be configured. Combined filters per list entry are supported in the following way:    only plmnId configured:  All cells with the primary or one of secondary PLMN Ids matching the blacklisted PLMN Id (mcc, mnc mncLength) are candidates for RIM blacklisting.    only carrierFreq configured:  All cells with frequency carrierFreq are blacklisted for RIM.    only rncId configured:  All cells of the RNC with id rncId are blacklisted for RIM.    only carrierFreq and plmnId configured:  All cells with frequency carrierFreq and with the primary or one of secondary PLMN Ids matching the blacklisted PLMN Id (mcc, mnc mncLength) are candidates for RIM blacklisting.    only rncId and plmnId configured:  All cells of the RNC with id rncId and with the primary or one of secondary PLMN Ids matching the blacklisted PLMN Id (mcc, mnc mncLength) are candidates for RIM blacklisting.    only rncId and carrierFreq configured:  All cells of the RNC with id rncId and with frequency carrierFreq are blacklisted for RIM.    rncId, carrierFreq and plmnId configured  All cells of the RNC with id rncId and with frequency carrierFreq and with the primary or one of secondary PLMN Ids matching the blacklisted PLMN Id (mcc, mnc mncLength) are candidates for RIM blacklisting.    Notes:  - The finer granular filter overrules the coarse granular filter.  - The sequence of the list entries has no meaning.  - In case of PLMN Id based blacklisting: all PLMN Ids of a WCDMA neighbor cell, i.e. primary and all secondary PLMN Ids, must be blacklisted in order to inhibit establishment of a RIM association.

Parameter name: MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code which is part of the UTRAN PLMN Id to be blacklisted for RIM.

Parameter name: MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code which is part of the UTRAN PLMN Id to be blacklisted for RIM.

Parameter name: MNC length
Description: Length of Mobile Network Code (MNC) in digits.

Parameter name: RNC Id
Description: UTRAN RNC identifier to be blacklisted for RIM  The UTRAN Cell Global Id is built as a 28 bit value. It consists either  - of a 12 bit RNC-ID (range 0..4095) and a 16 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..65535) or  - of a 16 bit Extended RNC-Id (range 4096..65535) and a 12 bit UTRAN Cell ID (range 0..4095).

Parameter name: UTRAN carrier frequency
Description: UTRAN carrier frequency to be blacklisted for RIM

Parameter name: Blacklisted GSM PLMNs for RIM
Description: List of GERAN PLMN IDs which are to be blacklisted in terms of RIM.  No RIM associations will be established for GERAN cells belonging to one of the blacklisted PLMN IDs.    If this parameter is omitted, all GERAN neighbor cells will be RIM-enabled provided that the routing area code is configured in each neighbor cell with the "gTargetRac" parameter.

Parameter name: MCC
Description: Mobile Country Code of the PLMN ID, which is part of the GERAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: MNC
Description: Mobile Network Code (MNC) of the PLMN ID, which is part of the GERAN Cell Global Identifier (CGI) of the related neighbor cell.

Parameter name: MNC length
Description: Length of MNC in digits.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Good radio condition threshold for CSFB redirect
Description: Threshold used to judge good or weak radio condition when RRC connection release with redirection is triggered due to CS Fallback procedure.

Parameter name: Max. UTRA SI size for good radio condition
Description: The maximum size of UTRA System Information included in RRCConnectionRelease message under good radio condition.

Parameter name: Max. UTRA SI size for weak radio condition
Description: The maximum size of UTRA System Information included in RRCConnectionRelease message under weak radio condition.

Parameter name: Maximum RIR attempts to GERAN
Description: The maximum number of attempted (re-)transmissions for a specific RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report PDU without success.

Parameter name: Max. RIR attempts to UTRAN
Description: The maximum number of attempted (re-)transmissions for a specific RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report PDU without success.

Parameter name: Timer to wait for next RI PDU from GERAN
Description: This timer is started when eNB receives a valid RAN-INFORMATION/Initial Multiple Report PDU.  This timer is restarted when eNB receives subsequent RAN-INFORMATION/Multiple Report PDU.  When the timer expires the eNB re-sends the RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report PDU.  Refer to [RIM.359].

Parameter name: Timer to wait for next RI PDU from UTRAN
Description: This timer is started when eNB receives a valid RAN-INFORMATION/Initial Multiple Report PDU from UTRAN.  This timer is restarted when eNB receives subsequent RAN-INFORMATION/Multiple Report PDU.  When the timer expires the eNB re-sends the RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report PDU.  Refer to [RIM.514].

Parameter name: Polling timer to ReStart RIR Procedure to GERAN
Description: This timer is started when RIM procedure for a GERAN neighbor cell fails or ends.  When the timer expires the eNB re-starts RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report procedure for the GERAN neighbor cell.    Note: If this timer's length is set to a short value (e.g. 5 minutes), the re-sending RIM PDUs may visibly increase the S1 link traffic.

Parameter name: Polling timer to ReStart RIR procedure to UTRAN
Description: This timer is started when RIM procedure for a UTRAN neighbor cell fails or ends.  When the timer expires the eNB re-starts RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report procedure for the UTRAN neighbor cell.    Note: If this timer's length is set to a short value (e.g. 5 minutes), the re-sending RIM PDUs may visibly increase the S1 link traffic.

Parameter name: Timer to wait for RIR Response from GERAN
Description: This timer is started when eNB sends out a RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report message.  When the timer expires the eNB re-sends the RIM message up to nRimRirG(see [CCPM.9031]) times.

Parameter name: Timer to wait for RIR response from UTRAN
Description: This timer is started when eNB sends out a RAN-INFORMATION-REQUEST/Multiple Report message to UTRAN.  When the timer expires the eNB re-sends the RIM message up to nRimRirU(see [CCPM.20156]) times.

Parameter name: SAS User Group Id
Description: This parameter is used to specify the SAS User Group instance ID.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Group Id String
Description: This parameter specifies the SAS user group identifier.

Parameter name: SCTP configuration identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC SCTP.

Parameter name: SCTP association failure retransmission counter
Description: This is the number of unanswered heartbeat messages or data acknowledgements (within a time defined by RTO/T3-rtx and calculated internally in SCTP), used for declaring the SCTP association failure.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Maximum time to wait for a new SCTP establishment
Description: When an X2 link establishment attempt is triggered for an eNB Controlled X2 link or for an X2 link to gNB, eNB attempts at most for the time 'maxTimeSctpSetup' to establish the respective SCTP association, before assuming that the SCTP association establishment failed.    Note: In case of long maxTimeSctpSetup interval it might happen that SCTP layer has already finished transmitting SCTP INIT sequence before maxTimeSctpSetup expires. In case of short maxTimeSctpSetup interval, the eNB signaling application will finish SCTP INIT retransmission before SCTP computed time interval expires.

Parameter name: SCTP path failure retransmission counter
Description: This is the number of unanswered heartbeat messages or data acknowledgements (within a time defined by RTO/T3-rtx and calculated internally in SCTP), used for declaring SCTP path failure.

Parameter name: Maximum retransmission timeout
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum value for retransmission timer T3-rtx when DATA or heartbeat was sent and no ACK has come back. Used for SCTP calculation range.

Parameter name: Minimum retransmission timeout
Description: This parameter specifies the minimum value for retransmission timer T3-rtx when DATA or heartbeat was sent and no ACK has come back. Used for the SCTP calculation range.

Parameter name: SCTP heartbeat message interval
Description: This parameter defines the interval between two SCTP heartbeat messages, counted in seconds.

Parameter name: SCTP maximum payload size
Description: This parameter configures the maximum size of an IP packet carrying an SCTP PDU as payload.  The number of octets available for an SCTP PDU is calculated as  sctpMaxPayloadSize - IP header (20 bytes for IPv4, more for IPv6 or IPSec)    If Ethernet MTU configured is greater than 512, Value must be less than or equal to the minimum of (Ethernet MTU, Upper limit of sctpMaxPayloadSize).  If Ethernet MTU configured is less than or equal to 512, Value must be set to 512 (Linux Kernel-SCTP_DEFAULT_MINSEGMENT).    Note:  Ethernet MTU shall be the configured ipMtu of the associated egress IP interface.

Parameter name: Selective acknowledge delay
Description: This parameter specifies the maximum time period the SCTP receiver waits before sending a Sack.  This parameter specifies the time period the SCTP receiver waits before sending a Sack. The SCTP receiver sends a SACK before the timer expires if the number of received frames achieves the value of the parameter selective acknowledge frequency (sctpSackFreq).

Parameter name: Selective acknowledge frequency
Description: This parameter specifies the number of SCTP frames that the SCTP receiver is allowed to receive before it sends a SACK.  This parameter specifies the number of SCTP frames that the SCTP receiver is allowed to receive before it sends a SACK. The SCTP receiver shall send a Sack if the waiting time (sctpSackDelay) for receiving this number of frames expires.

Parameter name: M3 wait Time before starting SCTP init
Description: This parameter defines the M3 wait time the eNB waits until it tries to re-initialize the SCTP association  Case A: after having tried unsuccessfully to establish an association to a peer with an SCTP sequence  Case B: After reception of SCTP SHUTDOWN/ABORT  The value defines a fixed time period. In addition, eNB adds an equally distributed random time period between 0 and 10s to the configured value.    This prevents the eNBs to which the network element that has sent the SCTP shutdown command (e.g. MME) will be overflooded by SCTP initialization from multiple eNBs.

Parameter name: S1 wait Time before starting SCTP init
Description: This parameter defines the S1 wait time the eNB waits until it tries to re-initialize the SCTP association  Case A: after having tried unsuccessfully to establish an association to a peer with an SCTP sequence  Case B: After reception of SCTP SHUTDOWN/ABORT  The value defines a fixed time period. In addition, eNB adds an equally distributed random time period between 0 and 10s to the configured value.    This prevents the eNBs to which the network element that has sent the SCTP shutdown command (e.g. MME) will be overflooded by SCTP initialization from multiple eNBs.

Parameter name: X2 wait Time before starting SCTP init
Description: This parameter defines the X2 wait time the eNB waits until it tries to re-initialize the SCTP association (X2 OAM controlled) to another eNB.  Case A: after having tried unsuccessfully to establish an association to a peer with an SCTP sequence  Case B: After reception of SCTP SHUTDOWN/ABORT  The value defines a fixed time period. In addition, eNB adds an equally distributed random time period between 0 and 60s to the configured value.    This prevents the eNBs to which the network element that has sent the SCTP shutdown command will be over-flooded by SCTP initialization from multiple eNBs.

Parameter name: DRX smart profile 6 - DRX inactivity timer
Description: Configures the Inactivity Timer for DRX.  The Inactivity Timer determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes for which the UE monitors the PDCCH after decoding an UL or DL resource assignment on PDCCH for an initial data transmission.    Note: It is not recommended to set this timer to shorter values than the default value to allow for sufficient scheduling flexibility.

Parameter name: DRX smart profile 6 - DRX long cycle
Description: Configures the long DRX cycle.  The long DRX cycle determines the periodic repetition of the DRX On Duration.

Parameter name: DRX smart profile 6 - DRX on duration timer
Description: Configures the On Duration Timer for DRX.  The On Duration determines the number of consecutive PDCCH-subframes at the beginning of a DRX cycle during which the UE monitors the PDCCH.    Note: It is not recommended to set this timer to shorter values than the default value to allow for sufficient scheduling flexibility.

Parameter name: DRX smart profile 6 - DRX profile index
Description: Smart DRX profile index.  Uniquely identifies a DRX profile.

Parameter name: DRX smart profile 6 - DRX profile priority
Description: Smart DRX profile priority.    Applied to identify the Smart DRX profile to be used if a UE has multiple bearers established.  Note: Modification of Smart DRX profile priority is not recommended; preparation for future use.

Parameter name: DRX smart profile 6 - DRX retransmission timer
Description: Configures the Retransmission Timer for DRX.  The Retransmission Timer determines the maximum number of PDCCH-subframes a UE monitors the PDCCH as soon as a retransmission in DL is expected by the UE.    Note: It is not recommended to set this timer to shorter values than the recommended default value to allow for sufficient scheduling flexibility.

Parameter name: DRX smart profile 6 - DRX short cycle
Description: Configures the short DRX cycle.  It is recommended to set this parameter equal to the drxLongCycle in order to optimize battery consumption during VoLTE calls.

Parameter name: DRX smart profile 6 - DRX short cycle timer
Description: Configures the short DRX cycle timer.  Integer value multiplied with drxShortCycle to determine the run time of short DRX cycle.
