Parameter name: System Information Broadcast (SIB) identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC SIB.  It uniquely identifies a SIB instance.

Parameter name: Access Class Barring BB pool profile used
Description: This parameter shows the identifier of the BB pool ACB (Baseband pool Access Class Barring) profile used for the cell.  If the feature 'RRC connection triggered access class barring - BB pool' is deactivated or no BB pool ACB profile is assigned, the parameter value is set to '-1'. If the feature is activated then the ACB profile identifier that has been assigned to the BB pool by the eNB is shown. Each cell in the BB pool gets the same ACB profile identifier assigned.

Parameter name: ACB for BB pool profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the referenced Access Class Barring for BB pool profile.  Please note that the final profile will be assigned by the eNB based on the profile priority and the cell to BB pool assignment.

Parameter name: AC Barring emergency calls timer
Description: When emergency call barring timer expires emergency calls will be barred automatically if configured so by the ACBPR-eCallAcBarredAuto parameter.  If the previous ACB level (Max threshold and ACB Skip IEs are deactivated) lasts for at least acbEcTimer, emergency calls may be barred if configured so by ACBPR-eCallAcBarredAuto.  The timer is configured in counter mode as multiplicity of acbUpdateTimer.    Note: If the timer is not configured that means that SIB2 or SIB2-BR ac-barringForEmergency will be set to FALSE or TRUE according to ACBPR-eCallAcBarredAuto settings.

Parameter name: RACH load immediate Max AC barring
Description: This parameter defines change in step-wise AC Barring algorithm behavior and allows to immediately go to the most stringent Max AC Barring threshold.

Parameter name: Cell RRC connection AC Barring start threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the upper threshold of RRC CONNECTED UEs which can trigger ACTIVE RRC_ACB event on the cell level.  RRC_ACB event becomes ACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the cell >= ROUND(acbNumRrcConnCellStart * maxNumRRC.Cell / 100) AND acbRrcConnCellStartTimer expires.    ACTIVE RRC_ACB event shall start step-wise upgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if dynamic ACB ACTIVE state not started yet.    Note: maxNumRRC.Cell - indicates that this is Cell related maxNumRRC RAC limit.

Parameter name: Cell RRC connection AC Barring stop threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the lower threshold of RRC CONNECTED UEs which can trigger INACTIVE RRC_ACB event on the cell level.  RRC_ACB event becomes INACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the cell < ROUND(acbNumRrcConnCellStop * maxNumRRC.Cell / 100) AND acbRrcConnCellStopTimer expires.    INACTIVE RRC_ACB event shall start step-wise downgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if there's no other ACTIVE ACB trigger.    Note: maxNumRRC.Cell - indicates that this is Cell related maxNumRRC RAC limit.

Parameter name: CFR based AC barring thresholds - RRC connection attempts AC barring start threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the upper threshold of RRC Connection Requests per 1 second which is the one of required two conditions to trigger ACTIVE CFR_ACB event on cell level. CFR_ACB is ACTIVE:  1. When the connection failure rate is above acbRacRejCFRStart  AND  2. the number of RRC attempts is above acbNumRrcReqCFRStart.    The connection failure rate is defined by the ratio between RRC connection setup rejections due to RAC at cell level and total RRC attempts. Both connection failure rate and number of RRC attempts are determined during a time window. Duration of the time window = ROUND(acbRrcReqFactor * acbUpdateTimer)  The real value of upper threshold of RRC Connection Requests per 1 second is the product of acbNumRrcReqStart and maxNumActUe and is calculated by the formula:  ROUNDUP(acbNumRrcReqCFRStart * maxNumActUE / 100) * duration_of_the_time_window.  ACTIVE CFR_ACB event shall start step-wise upgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if dynamic ACB ACTIVE state not started yet.  The upper and lower thresholds are introduced to prevent repeatedly starting and stopping LTE2823 step-wise ACB algorithm.

Parameter name: CFR based AC barring thresholds - RRC connection attempts AC barring stop threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the lower threshold of RRC Connection Requests per 1 second which is the one of two conditions that can trigger INACTIVE CFR_ACB - event on cell level. CFR_ACB is INACTIVE:  1. When the connection failure rate is below acbRacRejCFRStop  OR  2. the number of RRC attempts is below acbNumRrcReqCFRStop.    The connection failure rate is defined by the ratio between RRC connection setup rejections due to RAC at cell level and total RRC attempts. Both connection failure rate and number of RRC attempts are determined during a time window. Duration of the time window = ROUND(acbRrcReqFactor * acbUpdateTimer)  The real value of lower threshold of RRC Connection Requests per 1 second is the product of acbNumRrcReqStart and maxNumActUe and is calculated by the formula:  ROUNDUP(acbNumRrcReqCFRStop * maxNumActUE / 100) * duration_of_the_time_window.  INACTIVE CFR_ACB event shall start step-wise downgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if dynamic ACB ACTIVE state already started.  The upper and lower thresholds are introduced to prevent repeatedly starting and stopping LTE2823 step-wise ACB algorithm.

Parameter name: RACH load AC Barring start threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the upper threshold of RRC Connection Requests per 1 second which can trigger ACTIVE RACH_ACB event on the cell level.  The real value of upper threshold is the product of acbNumRrcReqStart and maxNumActUe.

Parameter name: RACH load AC Barring stop threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the lower threshold of RRC Connection Requests per 1 second which can trigger INACTIVE RACH_ACB event on the cell level.  The real value of lower threshold is the product of acbNumRrcReqStop and maxNumActUe.

Parameter name: AC Barring number of steps
Description: This parameter defines absolute number of ACB thresholds used by the algorithm, including: Min, Max and intermediate ACB thresholds.  Operator configures ACB Min and Max thresholds for ACB parameters as well as number of steps (inclination of access class barring changes) in which Max ACB threshold settings are reached.    If acbNumSteps=0 that is equal to disabling automatic AC barring in that specific cell.    If acbNumSteps=1 that means that ACB Max threshold is broadcasted.

Parameter name: Steps of adaptive access class barring per PLMN
Description: This parameter defines absolute number of access barring per PLMN thresholds, including: Min, Max and intermediate ACB thresholds.  Operator configures ACB Min and Max thresholds parameters as well as number of steps (inclination of access class barring changes) in which Max ACB threshold settings are reached.    If acbPlmnNumSteps=0 that is equal to disabling access class barring per PLMN in that specific cell.    If acbPlmnNumSteps=1 that means that Max threshold of ACB per PLMN is broadcasted.

Parameter name: ACB profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the assigned Access Class Barring profile.

Parameter name: CFR based AC barring thresholds - CFR AC barring start threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the upper threshold of the connection failure rate per sliding window duration time which is the one of required two conditions to trigger ACTIVE CFR_ACB event on the cell level. CFR_ACB is ACTIVE:  1. When the connection failure rate (CFR) is above acbRacRejCFRStart  AND  2. the number of RRC attempts is above acbNumRrcReqCFRStart.    The connection failure rate is defined by the ratio between RRC connection setup rejections due to RAC at cell level and total RRC attempts. Both connection failure rate and number of RRC attempts are determined during a time window. Duration of the time window = ROUND(acbRrcReqFactor * acbUpdateTimer)  Every second eNB performs calculation considering data aggregated per sliding window period:  A - aggregated Number of RRC Connection Requests per sliding window period  B - aggregated RRC Connection Rejects due to RAC per sliding window period    Every second eNB calculates new CFR:  CFR = roundup( B * 100 / A )  ACTIVE CFR_ACB event shall start step-wise upgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if dynamic ACB ACTIVE state not started yet.  The upper and lower thresholds are introduced to prevent repeatedly starting and stopping LTE2823 step-wise ACB algorithm.

Parameter name: CFR based AC barring thresholds - CFR AC barring stop threshold
Description: This parameter defines in percentage the lower threshold of the connection failure rate per sliding window duration time which is the one of two conditions that can trigger INACTIVE CFR_ACB event on cell level. CFR_ACB is INACTIVE:  1. When the connection failure rate (CFR) is below acbRacRejCFRStop  OR  2. the number of RRC attempts is below acbNumRrcReqCFRStop.    The connection failure rate is defined by the ratio between RRC connection setup rejections due to RAC at cell level and total RRC attempts. Both connection failure rate and number of RRC attempts are determined during a time window. Duration of the time window = ROUND(acbRrcReqFactor * acbUpdateTimer)  Every second eNB performs calculation considering data aggregated per sliding window period:  A - aggregated Number of RRC Connection Requests per sliding window period  B - aggregated RRC Connection Rejects due to RAC per sliding window period    Every second eNB calculates new CFR:  CFR = roundup( B * 100 / A )  INACTIVE CFR_ACB event shall start step-wise downgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if dynamic ACB ACTIVE state already started.  The upper and lower thresholds are introduced to prevent repeatedly starting and stopping LTE2823 step-wise ACB algorithm.

Parameter name: Cell RRC triggered AC Barring start timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before triggering ACTIVE RRC_ACB event on the cell level.  RRC_ACB event becomes ACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the cell >= ROUND(acbNumRrcConnCellStart * maxNumRRC.Cell / 100) AND acbRrcConnCellStartTimer expires.    ACTIVE RRC_ACB event shall start step-wise upgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if dynamic ACB ACTIVE state not started yet.    Note: maxNumRRC.Cell - indicates that this is Cell related maxNumRRC RAC limit.

Parameter name: Cell RRC triggered AC Barring stop timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before triggering INACTIVE RRC_ACB event on the cell level.  RRC_ACB event becomes INACTIVE if #RRC_Connected UEs in the cell < ROUND(acbNumRrcConnCellStop * maxNumRRC.Cell / 100) AND acbRrcConnCellStopTimer expires.    INACTIVE RRC_ACB event shall start step-wise downgrade of AC barring settings and their broadcast in SIB2 message if there's no other ACTIVE ACB trigger.    Note: maxNumRRC.Cell - indicates that this is Cell related maxNumRRC RAC limit.

Parameter name: RACH load sliding window factor
Description: This parameter defines the multiplication factor which together with acbUpdateTimer determines RACH load sliding window period over which number of received RRC Connection Requests are aggregated. And when LTE4175 is activated the the parameter determines the sliding window period over which number of RRC Connection Requests and number of RRC Connection Rejections are aggregated. This is multiplication factor and relates to acbUpdateTimer (LTE2823 parameter).

Parameter name: Special Class Barring step duration timer
Description: It defines duration of single Special Class (SC) step. Each SC step is of the same duration.  During SC ACB phase SC step duration timer determines sampling interval when ACTIVE/INACTIVE status of the ACB triggers is checked.  Its value has relationship to basic acbUpdateTimer and is running in the 'counter' mode (counts number of times acbUpdateTimer expired).

Parameter name: Special Class Barring timer
Description: When ACB Special Class timer expires and barAC1 is configured then in the first step Special Class barring bitmap barAC is replaced in broadcasted SIB2 by barAC1. With expiration of acbScStepDuration timer further Special Class steps are executed if configured.  The timer is configured in counter mode as multiplicity of acbUpdateTimer.    Note: If acbScTimer is not configured then step-wise Automatic Access Class Barring for Special Classes is disabled on LNCEL level.

Parameter name: AC Barring skip timer
Description: When ACB Skip timer expires and any ACB Skip IEs is configured to 'true' (LTE2505) and broadcasted in the SIB2 or SIB2-BR then ACB Skip IEs will be automatically deactivated it means NOT broadcasted till all ACB triggers are INACTIVE.  If any ACB Skip IEs is configured to 'true' then the acb Skip IEs may automatically be deactivated which means not broadcasted in SIB2 or SIB2-BR, only in case the maximum ACB level is already reached and remains active for acbSkipTimer time.  The timer is configured in counter mode as multiplicity of acbUpdateTimer.    Note: If the timer is not configured that means that Skip IEs shall not be removed from the SIB2 or SIB2-BR if they are configured to 'true'.

Parameter name: Access class barring TRS trigger
Description: Indicates whether the TRS_ACB indication which is consequence of switching over to Public Safety IPsec tunnel is valid trigger for PLMN specific Access Class Barring state machine. If trigger is not valid then it will be ignored by PLMN specific ACB functionality in the cell. Note that this functionality applies for Wide Band or Cat-M. TRS_ACB is always valid for NB-IoT cells. TRS_ACB is transparent (ignored) for Common ACB phase.

Parameter name: AC barring TRS triggered UE context release
Description: Indicates whether the TRS_ACB indication which is consequence of switching over to Public Safety IPsec tunnel is valid trigger for Partial Reset and UE Context Release of impacted UEs.  If parameter is set to:  - 'None' then no UE Contexts are released in the cell.  - 'All except EC & HPA' then all UE Contexts except Emergency and High Priority Access connections (EC & HPA) from impacted Network Id are released in the cell.  - 'All' then all UE Contexts from impacted Network Id are released together with Emergency and High Priority Access connections.  Note: this functionality applies for Wide Band and Cat-M UEs and is valid per Network ID and cell combination. If execution of PLMN specific Access Class Barring System Information Modification (SIM) procedure is required after TRS_ACB is received then Partial Reset is executed just after completion of SIM or immediately.
Range and step: None (0), All except EC and HPA (1), All (2)

Parameter name: AC Barring update timer
Description: This parameter defines when step-wise upgrade or downgrade of ACB settings and their modification in the SIB2 is allowed.  The RRC connection triggered ACB parameters changes are executed in the operator configurable update intervals controlled by ACB update timer.  The exception is ACB triggered by the C-Plane OVL2 which is executed immediately up to the ACB Max threshold.

Parameter name: Automatic AC Barring start timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before starting automatic AC barring broadcast of overload specific parameter value in SIB messages when BTS C-Plane get in overload.  As per TS36.331, systemInfoValueTag changes should be no more than 31 times within 3 hours. Otherwise, UE with a complete set of system information of the cell stored that has left the cell and has come back within three hours might not recognize that there was a system information change.  Note: This parameter is used in standalone NB-IoT cell also. For inband/guardband NB-IoT cell, the parameter in host cell will be used.    To avoid systemInfoValueTag overflow solely due to frequent automatic AC barring on/off, it is recommended that the sum of autoAcBarringStartTimer and autoAcbPlmnRmvlStopTimer is equal to or greater than 900 seconds (i.e. 15 minutes).

Parameter name: Automatic AC barring and PLMN removal stop timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before stopping both automatic AC barring broadcast of overload specific parameter value and further PLMN autonomous removal in SIB messages when BTS C-Plane gets out from overload.  As per TS36.331, systemInfoValueTag changes should be no more than 31 times within 3 hours. otherwise, UE with a complete set of system information of the cell stored that has left the cell and has come back within three hours might not recognize that there was a system information change.    To avoid systemInfoValueTag overflow solely due to frequent automatic AC barring on/off, it is recommended that the sum of autoAcBarringStartTimer and autoAcbPlmnRmvlStopTimer is equal to or greater than 900 seconds (i.e. 15 minutes).    Note: This parameter is used in standalone NB-IoT cell also. For inband/guardband NB-IoT cell, the parameter in host cell will be used.

Parameter name: Autonomous further PLMN removal start timer
Description: This parameter defines the guard timer before starting autonomous further PLMN removal from SIB1 message when BTS C-Plane gets in overload.  After starting automatic AC barring broadcast of overload specific parameter value in SIB messages when BTS C-Plane get in overload, if BTS C-plane overload level 2 keeps active for time defined by this parameter consecutively, the specified subset of further PLMNs is removed from SIB1 autonomously by eNB in the overload cell.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency reselection timer EUTRA - Cell reselection timer factor high mobility
Description: The cell reselection timer (t-ReselectionEUTRAN) is multiplied by this factor if the UE is in the medium high mobility state.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency reselection timer EUTRA - Cell reselection timer factor medium mobility
Description: The cell reselection timer (t-ReselectionEUTRAN) is multiplied by this factor if the UE is in the medium mobility state.

Parameter name: Cell barred flag
Description: The cell barred flag indicates if the cell status is barred or not. A barred cell is a cell that a UE is not allowed to camp on, not even for emergency calls. If a cell on which a UE is currently camped becomes barred, a cell reselection is triggered.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Cell reselection priority
Description: Defines the absolute priority of the serving layer.  The cell reselection priority parameter defines the absolute priority of the serving layer. 0 means the lowest priority.

Parameter name: Cell reselection sub priority
Description: This parameter indicates a fractional value to be added to the value of cellReSelPrio to obtain the absolute priority of the serving layer.

Parameter name: Minimum required quality in cell (Rel9) - Offset for minimum required RSRQ in cell (Rel9)
Description: Offset to the signaled qQualMinR9 taken into account in the Squal evaluation as a result of a periodic search for a higher priority PLMN while camped normally in a VPLMN.  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9.

Parameter name: Minimum required quality in cell (Rel9) - Minimum required RSRQ in cell (Rel9)
Description: Minimum required quality level in the LTE and NB-IoT cell.  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Closed Subscriber Group identifier
Description: This parameter defines the Closed Subscriber Identifier for the cell.  This parameter is only used if csgType is set to CSG.    The highest value allowed by 3GPP (134217727) is reserved.

Parameter name: Day light savings time indicator
Description: Defines the Daylight Savings Time (DST) offset that is used by the BTS to calculate its local time.    This parameter value, derived from TIME-timeZone, indicates if and how daylight saving time (DST) is applied to obtain the local time.  0 No adjustment for Daylight Saving Time  1 +1 hour adjustment for Daylight Saving Time  2 +2 hours adjustment for Daylight Saving Time    It is broadcast in SIB16 and is sent in the Mobility Parameters CDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in the RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the dayLtIncluded parameter is set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Uplink power control common rel10 add-ons - UL power offset for PUCCH format 1bCS
Description: The parameter defines the transport format dependent offset in power control for PUCCH format 1bCS.  This parameter is used only when the Cell is configured as PCell in Carrier Aggregation.

Parameter name: Uplink power control common rel10 add-ons - UL power offset for PUCCH format 3
Description: The parameter defines the transport format dependent offset in power control for PUCCH format 3.  This parameter is used only when the Cell is configured as PCell in Carrier Aggregation.
Range and step: deltaF-1 (-1), deltaF0 (0), deltaF1 (1), deltaF2 (2), deltaF3 (3), deltaF4 (4), deltaF5 (5), deltaF6 (6)

Parameter name: Home eNB name
Description: This parameter defines the Home eNB Name that may be broadcasted by a Closed Subscriber Group cell coded in UTF-8 with variable number of bytes per character, see TS 22.011 [10].  If this parameter is configured the cell shall broadcast a SIB9 message with hnb-Name IE set to this parameter.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency cell reselection allowed
Description: Used to control cell reselection on intra-frequency cells when the highest ranked cell is barred, or is considered as barred by the UE, as specified in TS 36.304.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE/NB-IoT UE.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Presence antenna port1
Description: Indicates whether all the neighboring cells use Antenna Port 1.  When set to TRUE, the UE may assume that at least two cell-specific antenna ports are used in all neighboring cells.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Local time offset
Description: Defines the offset between UTC and local time that is used by the BTS to calculate its local time. This parameter value is derived from TIME-timeZone.    Local time offset is broadcast in SIB16 and is also sent in the Mobility Parameters CDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode when the ltmOffIncluded parameter is set to TRUE. The LTM_OFF field value (6 bits), encoded in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE), if present, shall have a two's complement arithmetic representation with a granularity of 30 minutes (refer 3GPP2 C.S0005 Section 3.7.2.3.2.26).

Parameter name: MBMS neighbor cells configuration
Description: Provides information related to MBSFN configuration of neighbour cells of this frequency.  Provides information related to MBSFN configuration of neighbour cells of this frequency  00: Not all neighbour cells have the same MBSFN subframe allocation as serving cell  01: No MBSFN subframes are present in all neighbour cells  10: The MBSFN subframe allocations of all neighbour cells are identical to or subsets of that in the serving cell  11: Different UL/DL allocation in neighbouring cells for TDD compared to the serving cell    Notes:  Value of '11' is not applicable for FDD.  For TDD, 00, 10 and 01 are only used for same UL/DL allocation in neighbouring cells compared to the serving cell.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Modification period coefficient
Description: The parameter defines the length of the modification period.  Modification period = modificationPeriodCoeff * defaultPagingCycle / 10 ms.  Modification period is equal or lower than 1024.  (n2 corresponds to value 2, n4 corresponds to value 4 and n8 corresponds to value 8.)

Parameter name: Maximum number of out-of-sync indications
Description: This is the maximum number of consecutive "out of sync" indications received from lower layers.  n1 corresponds to 1 and so on.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Maximum number of in-sync indications
Description: Maximum number of consecutive "in-sync" indications received from lower layers.  n1 corresponds to 1 and so on.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent reselection structure - Number cell changes high mobility
Description: The parameter defines the number of cell changes to enter the high mobility state. For the idle mode, it corresponds to NCR_H in TS 36.304.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent reselection structure - Number cell changes medium mobility
Description: The parameter defines the number of cell changes to enter the medium mobility state. For idle mode, it corresponds to NCR_M in TS 36.304.

Parameter name: Pmax intra-frequency neighboring E-UTRA
Description: Pmax to be used for the intra-frequency neighboring EUTRA cells. If pmax is absent, the maximum power according to the UE capability is used.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE/NB-IoT UE.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Max. uplink transmission power own cell
Description: The IE P-Max is used to limit the UE's uplink transmission power on a carrier frequency; it is also used to calculate the parameter P-compensation defined in TS 36.304 .  Corresponds to parameter PEMAX in TS 36.101.  The UE transmit power should not exceed the minimum of this value (in dBm), if provided, and the maximum UE power for the UE power class, PUMAX, as specified in TS 36.101.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.    Note: One of the activation conditions for feature 'LTE2583: Support of high power UE' is this parameter being set to a value larger than '23' [dBm]. See customer documentation for more details.  Note: If this parameter is not created for a cell, p-Max information element will not be broadcasted in SIB1 in this cell.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Power ramping step
Description: The power ramping step size parameter defines the power increment step size for Random Access preamble transmission, including PRACH and NPRACH.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Preamble transmission maximum
Description: The preamble transmission maximum defines the maximum number of Random Access transmissions.  Note: The values n50, n100 and n200 should not be used.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Cell reserved for operator use
Description: Indicates if the cell/PLMN combination is reserved for operator use.  Cells reserved for operator use are treated as barred by 'normal' UEs without a USIM with AC 11 or 15 inserted. UEs with AC 11 or 15 USIM inserted are specific operator UEs and thus allowed to camp on and access such cells. The default value is not reserved.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.  The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Primary PLMN set to cell reserved for operator use
Description: Indicates if the cell/PLMN combination is reserved for operator use and incoming handovers for the combination are blocked when ACB max step is reached as a result of step-wise ACB. Note that this functionality only applies for the primary PLMN.

Parameter name: Cell PLMN indicator for supporting EN-DC.
Description: Indication of the cell/primary PLMN supports EN-DC in SIB2.

Parameter name: Cell reselection procedure hysteresis value
Description: The Qhyst parameter provides the hysteresis value in dB for ranking criteria in the cell reselection procedure. The parameter is used to minimize pingpong.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE/NB-IoT UE.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent reselection structure - Cell reselection hysteresis high mobility
Description: The parameter defines an additional hysteresis value to be applied in the high mobility state to the cell reselection procedure hysteresis value (q-Hyst).  Value db-6 corresponds to -6dB, db-4 corresponds to -4dB and so on.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent reselection structure - Cell reselection hysteresis medium mobility
Description: The parameter defines an additional hysteresis value to be applied in the medium mobility state to the cell reselection procedure hysteresis value (q-Hyst).  Value db-6 corresponds to -6dB, db-4 corresponds to -4dB and so on.

Parameter name: Min. required RSRQ in intra-freq neighbor cells (Rel9)
Description: Minimum required quality level in intra-frequency neighbor cells  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Q RX level min. offset
Description: Affects the minimum required RX level in the cell.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Minimum required RX level in cell
Description: Specifies the minimum required RX RSRP level in the cell.  (Qrxlevmin in 36.304)  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Min. required RX level for intra-freq neighboring cells
Description: Indicates the minimum required RX level in the cell (dBm) for intra-frequency.  Specifies the minimum required RX RSRP level for the intra-frequency neighbouring E-UTRA cells.  (Qrxlevmin in 36.304)  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency measurements thresholds (Rel9) - Intra-frequency measurements power threshold (Rel9)
Description: Power threshold  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency measurements thresholds (Rel9) - Intra-frequency measurements quality threshold (Rel9)
Description: Quality threshold  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE.

Parameter name: Intra-frequency measurements threshold
Description: The sIntrasearch parameter defines the threshold (in dB) for intra-frequency measurements.  The UE can omit measurements of intra-frequency neighbor cells if the serving cell is above a certain threshold.    The setting is commonly valid for all legacy category UE and Cat-M UE/NB-IoT UE.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: Inter-freq and inter-RAT meas thresholds (Rel9) - Inter-freq and inter-RAT power meas threshold (Rel9)
Description: Power threshold  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9

Parameter name: Inter-freq and inter-RAT meas thresholds (Rel9) - Inter-freq and inter-RAT quality meas threshold (Rel9)
Description: Quality threshold  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9

Parameter name: Inter-frequency and inter-RAT measurements threshold
Description: The sNonintrsearch parameter defines the threshold (in dB) for inter-RAT and inter-frequency measurements.  Note: This parameter is used in NB-IoT cell also.

Parameter name: SAI list of intra-frequency neighbor cells
Description: List of MBMS service area identities (SAI) for intra-frequency neighbor cells    Please note that the sum of SAIs configured in the lists saiListIntraFreqNeighbors and saiListIntraFreq of the optionally assigned SIB15 profile is maximum 63.  If saiListIntraFreqNeighbors is not configured the maximum number of SAIs in saiListIntraFreq is 64. eNB will omit SAIs if one of the above limits is exceeded!

Parameter name: SI window length
Description: Defines the common System Information scheduling window.  The parameter SI Window Length defines the common System Information scheduling window for all SIs.    Note: All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode may be released when this parameter is online modified.

Parameter name: SIB15 profile identifier
Description: Instance ID of the assigned SIB15 profile.    SIB15 contains MBMS Service Area Identities (SAI) of the current and/ or  neighboring carrier frequencies

Parameter name: System information 2 scheduling - Periodicity
Description: Indicates the periodicity of the SI-2 message.  The parameter System Information 2 Periodicity indicates the repetition period of the SI-2 message.

Parameter name: System information 2 scheduling - Repetition
Description: Indicates the repetition of the SI-2 message within the SI window.

Parameter name: System information 2 scheduling - Message mapping
Description: Indicates which System Information Block is contained in the SI-2 message.  The parameter System Information 2 Mapping Information indicates which System Information Blocks is contained in the SI-2 message.

Parameter name: Twofold transmission of SIBs per SI window
Description: As per basic system behavior, a SIB message (SIB2 and higher) is transmitted one time per each SI window, and further transmissions might be added if the message is too big (code rate is too high) for cell-edge UEs to decode it from fewer transmissions. If siWindowLen is greater than or equal to 20 ms, this parameter can be used to add another mandatory transmission per SI window for SIB2 and higher.  Up to four transmissions can be done in a SIB window. Any further transmission is done as 'best effort' and may or may not happen.    Setting sib2xTransmit=true in a system with 5 MHz or below is possible but not recommended for reasons of DL performance.    Even without sib2xTransmit set to 'true', SIB repetitions will be sent if this is required by message size and the code rate defined for SIB messages.  If siMessageRepetition is set to a value of 2 or higher, eNB tries (on best-effort basis only) to send SIB repetitions on top of the minimum number of transmissions defined by message size and code rate. In contrast to this, setting sib2xTransmit to 'true' adds a mandatory SIB repetition.

Parameter name: System information 3 scheduling - Periodicity
Description: Indicates the repetition period of the SI-3 message.  The parameter System Information 3 Periodicity indicates the repetition period of the SI-3 message.

Parameter name: System information 3 scheduling - Repetition
Description: Indicates the repetition of the SI-3 message within the SI window.  The parameter System Information 3 Repetition indicates the repetition of the SI-3 message within the SI window.

Parameter name: System information 3 scheduling - Message mapping
Description: Indicates which System Information Block is contained in the SI-3 message.  The parameter System Information 3 Mapping Information indicates which System Information Block is contained in the SI-3 message.

Parameter name: System information scheduling list
Description: List of scheduled SI-Messages containing optional SIBs  List of SI-Messages containing optional SIBs (SIB4 ... SIB13, SIB14, SIB15, SIB16, SIB18). This list is broadcasted in SIB1.    If SIB4 is configured, CatM SI broadcasts SIB4.  If SIB5 is configured and at least one CATMIRFIM instance is configured, CatM SI broadcasts SIB5.  If SIB14 is configured, CatM SI broadcasts SIB14. SIB14 is only broadcasted for CatM and in SIB1-BR list.  If SIB16 is configured, CatM SI broadcasts SIB16.    Notes:  SIB18 is not supported for TDD cells.  SIB14 is not supported in wideband FDD and TDD cells.

Parameter name: Periodicity
Description: Periodicity of this SI-Message. For SI-message containing SIB10/11/12 (warning notifications) a small value, for example 80ms should be used.  This SI-Message is broadcasted with the administered periodicity.

Parameter name: Repetition
Description: Number of SI-Message Repetitions  This SI-Message should be broadcasted "Repetition" times in each of its related SI-Message broadcast windows. The repetitions can be used by UE for enhanced decoding in case of bad radio conditions. If the SI-Message contains a warning message (SIB10/11/12), the number of repetitions could be raised autonomously by eNodeB if needed (absolute maximum code rate for SIB (maxCrSibDL) is exceeded, as the message size would be too big to transmit otherwise).

Parameter name: SIB type
Description: Indicates which SIB is contained in the SI-Message  This SIB Information Element is contained in the SI-Message scheduled in the System Information Scheduling List.    If SIB4 is configured, CatM SI broadcasts SIB4.  If SIB5 is configured and at least one CATMIRFIM instance is configured, CatM SI broadcasts SIB5.  If SIB14 is configured, CatM SI broadcasts SIB14. SIB14 is only broadcasted for CatM and in SIB1-BR list. SIB14 is not supported in wide band FDD and TDD cells.  If SIB16 is configured, CatM SI broadcasts SIB16.    Notes:  All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released, when this parameter is changed from or to SIB16 together with Cat-M and GPS/UTC broadcast are both activated.  All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released, when this parameter is changed from or to SIB5 together with Cat-M is activated and CATMIRFIM instance is configured.  All Cat-M UEs in RRC Connected mode will be released, when this parameter is changed from or to SIB14 together with Cat-M is activated and actEabCatM is not set to 'None'.

Parameter name: Timer T300
Description: Timer T300 supervises the RRC connection establishment procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionSetup or RRCConnectionReject message, cell re-selection and upon abortion of connection establishment by upper layers    At expiry: Perform the actions as specified in 36.331, 5.3.3.6    In case LNBTS-actContextPreemption is activated, the minimum recommended value is 600ms. If both LNBTS-actContextPreemption and LNBTS-actSatBackhaul are activated the minimum recommended value is further increased to 1500ms.

Parameter name: Timer T301
Description: Timer T301 supervises the RRC connection re-establishment procedure.  Start: Transmission of RRCConnectionReestabilshmentRequest  Stop: Reception of RRCConnectionReestablishment or RRCConnectionReestablishmentReject message as well as when the selected cell becomes unsuitable    At expiry: Go to RRC_IDLE

Parameter name: Timer T310
Description: Timer T310 supervises the recovery from physical layer problems.

Parameter name: Timer T311
Description: Timer T311 supervises the RRC connection re-establishment.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent reselection structure - Timer TCRmax
Description: Timer TCRmax defines the duration for evaluating the criteria to enter mobility states. For idle mode, it corresponds to TCRmax in TS 36.304.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent reselection structure - Timer TCRmaxHyst
Description: Timer TCRmaxHyst defines the additional duration for evaluating the criteria to enter normal mobility state. For idle mode, it corresponds to TCRmaxHyst in TS 36.304.

Parameter name: Cell reselection timer
Description: The Treselection parameter defines the cell reselection timer value. It allows averaging of the target cell quality before cell reselection is performed.

Parameter name: Q-threshold for reselection towards lower prio RAT/freq
Description: This specifies the Squal threshold used by the UE on the serving cell when reselecting towards a lower priority RAT/ frequency.  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9

Parameter name: Threshold serving low
Description: Specifies the threshold for the serving frequency used in reselection evaluation towards lower priority EUTRAN frequency or RAT.

Parameter name: Preamble initial received target power
Description: The parameter defines the initial power for Random Access preamble transmission.

Parameter name: SIB15 profile (SIB15PR) identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC SIB15PR.  It uniquely identifies a SIB15PR instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: MBMS service area identity list of the cell
Description: List of service area identities (SAI) that are supported by cells having the frequency of the cell, which references the SIB15 profile    Please note that the sum of SAIs configured in the lists saiListIntraFreq and saiListIntraFreqNeighbors of a referencing cell is maximum 63.  If saiListIntraFreqNeighbors is not configured in any referencing cell the maximum number of SAIs in saiListIntraFreq is 64.  eNB will omit SAIs if one of the above limits is exceeded.

Parameter name: Sidelink communication profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC SLCOMMPROF.  It uniquely identifies a SLCOMMPROF instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Sidelink EARFCN uplink
Description: E-UTRA Absolute Radio Frequency Channel Number in uplink  If the feature 'ProSe sidelink communication' is activated it applies implicitly to all cells with earfcnUL and ulChBw equal to slEarfcnUL and slUlChBw of the SLCOMMPROF instance.

Parameter name: Sidelink uplink channel bandwidth
Description: Uplink channel bandwidth defines the UL bandwidth for the eNode-B transmission in a cell.  This is not the bandwidth reserved for sidelink.    Uplink channel bandwidth defines the UL bandwidth for the eNB transmission in a cell, and also defines the number of available Physical Resource Blocks.    The uplink channel bandwidth mapping to number of Physical Resource Blocks is:  10.0 MHz = 50 UL PRBS    If the feature 'ProSe sidelink communication' is activated it applies implicitly to all cells with earfcnUL and ulChBw equal to slEarfcnUL and slUlChBw of the SLCOMMPROF instance.

Parameter name: Sidelink communication resources identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC SLCOMMRES.  It uniquely identifies a SLCOMMRES instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Subframe bitmap for sidelink data
Description: Indicates the subframe bitmap in time indicating resources used for sidelink Data    Changing this parameter to a non-default configuration has to be done carefully, as it may lead to suboptimal performance    The octets have to be defined as per TS36.331  The parameter must be added as character string in hexadecimal notation with leading '0x', where for each octet representing two character must be configured.  4 bits per character representing a total of 40 bits.

Parameter name: Offset indicator for sidelink data short
Description: Indicates the offset used by PSSCH resource configuration. it indicates the start of the data with respect to the start of associated slScPeriod

Parameter name: PRB end for sidelink data
Description: Specifies the PRB from which resources used for Sidelink Data ends    The PRB allocation for sidelink should not overlap with PRACH resources.

Parameter name: PRB num for sidelink data
Description: Specifies a set of PRB resources used for Sidelink Data

Parameter name: PRB start for sidelink data
Description: Specifies the PRB from which resources used for Sidelink Data begins    The PRB allocation for sidelink should not overlap with PUCCH resources.

Parameter name: Offset indicator for sidelink control short
Description: Indicates the offset of the first period of pool of resources within a SFN cycle

Parameter name: PRB end for sidelink control
Description: Specifies the PRB from which resources used for Sidelink Control ends    The PRB allocation for sidelink should not overlap with PRACH resources.

Parameter name: PRB num for sidelink control
Description: Specifies a set of PRB resources used for Sidelink Control

Parameter name: PRB start for sidelink control
Description: Specifies the PRB from which resources used for Sidelink Control begins    The PRB allocation for sidelink should not overlap with PUCCH resources.

Parameter name: Subframe bitmap for sidelink control
Description: Indicates the subframe bitmap in time indicating resources used for sidelink Control.    Changing this parameter to a non-default configuration has to be done carefully, as it may lead to suboptimal performance    The octets have to be defined as per TS36.331    The parameter must be added as a character string in hexadecimal notation with leading '0x', where for each octet representing two character must be configured.  4 bits per character representing a total of 40 bits.

Parameter name: Sidelink data CP length
Description: Sidelink Cyclic prefix length for Physical SL Data Channel (PSBCH)

Parameter name: Number of subbands for sidelink hopping configuration
Description: Indicates the number of subbands for hopping configuration used in sidelink

Parameter name: Sidelink hopping configuration parameter
Description: indicates the hopping configuration parameter used for sidelink  Setting this parameter to 0 disables hopping.

Parameter name: Hopping offset for sidelink
Description: Indicates the offset in resource blocks for hopping configuration used in sidelink

Parameter name: Sidelink control CP length
Description: Sidelink Cyclic prefix length for Physical SL Control Channel (PSCCH)

Parameter name: Sidelink control period
Description: Indicates the period over which all resources are allocated in a cell for both Sidelink Control and Data for which the transmission occur.

Parameter name: Sidelink communication synchronization identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC SLCOMMSYNC.  It uniquely identifies a SLCOMMSYNC instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Sidelink sync CP length
Description: Sidelink Cyclic prefix length for sidelink Sync

Parameter name: Sidelink sync offset indicator
Description: Sidelink Sync Offset Indicator. This value must match the pre-configured value in the SIM card of the UEs.

Parameter name: Sidelink sync transmit parameter alpha
Description: Alpha value for Sidelink Sync transmission

Parameter name: Sidelink sync transmit parameter P0
Description: P0 for Sidelink Sync Transmission

Parameter name: Sidelink sync transmit threshold IC
Description: Sidelink Sync transmission threshold

Parameter name: Sidelink communication TX pool identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC SLCOMMTX.  It uniquely identifies a SLCOMMTX instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates

Parameter name: Time to trigger for A2 measurement during sidelink
Description: Time to trigger for A2 measurement when UE has indicated interest in sidelink direct communication  Duration for which the event A2 must be valid at the UE such that the measurement report is sent by UE

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Related hysteresis of Th2 For RSRP during sidelink
Description: Related Hysteresis of RSRP Threshold Th2 for event A2 when UE is interested in sidelink direct communication    Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A2 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Threshold th2 for RSRP during sidelink
Description: RSRP threshold for A2 measurement of serving cell for start of inter frequency and inter-RAT measurements when UE has indicated interest in sidelink direct communication.  Defines the threshold for serving cell RSRP of A2 event, as a trigger to start Inter-Frequency and Inter-RAT handovers when UE is interested in sidelink communication. If RSRP value reported is below threshold2xxx of corresponding mobility type (inter-frequency, inter-RAT) then those mobility measurements are started.    The dBm value is mapped to the 3GPP IE value according to TS 36.133:  * -140 dBm means a threshold lower than -140 dBm  * values between -139 dBm and -44 dBm mean a threshold lower than the configured value but higher than or equal to the (value - 1 dB)  * -43 dBm means a threshold higher than or equal to -44 dBm

Parameter name: SRS 1.4 MHz PUCCH allocation default profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC SRS14PUCCHDPR.  It uniquely identifies an instance of the PUCCH for SRS-based positioning for 1.4 MHz Default Profile (SRS14PUCCHDPR).

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: SRS 1.4 MHz PUCCH allocation, add number UEs RR HO
Description: Additional margin in SRS14 automatic PUCCH allocation to be considered for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via handover with HO-cause: "HO desirable for radio reasons".  This margin (which is fix set to 0) is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.  This parameter was needed to be aligned with legacy automatic PUCCH configuration.

Parameter name: SRS 1.4 MHz PUCCH allocation, add number UEs TC HO
Description: Additional margin in SRS14 automatic PUCCH allocation to be considered for the maximum number of active UEs in the cell accessing the cell via handover with HO-cause: "Time Critical HO".  This margin (which is fix set to 0) is added to the threshold maxNumActUE.  This parameter was needed to be aligned with legacy automatic PUCCH configuration.

Parameter name: SRS 1.4 MHz PUCCH allocation, min num. emergency sessions
Description: Minimum number reserved for Emergency Sessions when SRS14 automatic PUCCH allocation is used.  This margin (which is fix set to 0) increases the thresholds for active UEs, active DRBs and active QCI1-DRBs in the cell.  This parameter was needed to be aligned with legacy automatic PUCCH configuration.

Parameter name: SRS 1.4 MHz PUCCH allocation, min number RRC
Description: This parameter defines the minimum number of RRC connections for SRS14 automatic PUCCH.  This parameter was needed to be aligned with legacy automatic PUCCH configuration.

Parameter name: SRS 1.4 MHz PUCCH allocation, min number RRC no DRB
Description: Minimum number of UEs in the cell which may establish a RRC connection without a DRB establishment (e.g. doing tracking area updates); this parameter is generally relevant as additional margin for configured maxNumActUe, but fix set to 0 for SRS14 usage.  This parameter was needed to be aligned with legacy automatic PUCCH configuration.

Parameter name: SRS 1.4 MHz PUCCH allocation, upper SR periodicity
Description: Defines the upper limit of the Scheduling Request periodicity to be used in the cell by the PUCCH algorithm.    The configured value expresses the upper SR periodicity allowed in the cell when SRS14 is active.

Parameter name: Target threshold profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC TGTTHRESHPR.  It uniquely identifies an instance of the Target Threshold Profile (TGTTHRESHPR).

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Offset of threshold3a for RSRP VoLTE quality inter frequency
Description: Offset of target cell A5 RSRP threshold3a for filtering target cells based on RSRP values. Used for filtering target cells reported by A5 measurement reports for inter-frequency handover to check if target cell is better than threshold3a plus offset.  This parameter is aimed for post-processing of measurement reports only. It is not used in any report configuration to UE.

Parameter name: Offset of threshold3a for RSRQ VoLTE quality inter frequency
Description: Offset of target cell A5 RSRQ threshold3a for filtering target cells based on RSRQ values. Used for filtering target cells reported by A5 measurement reports for inter-frequency handover to check if target cell is better than threshold3a plus offset.  This parameter is aimed for post-processing of measurement reports only. It is not used in any report configuration to UE.

Parameter name: Minimum target to source offset threshold RSRP
Description: Offset of target cell to source cell RSRP threshold for filtering target cells based on RSRP values. Used for filtering target cells reported by A3 measurement reports for intra-frequency handovers to check if target cell is better than source cell by at least this much. Negative value means target can be worse than source.  This parameter is aimed for post-processing of measurement reports only. It is not used in any report configuration to the UE.

Parameter name: Minimum target to source offset threshold RSRQ
Description: Offset of target cell to source cell RSRQ threshold for filtering target cells based on RSRQ values. Used for filtering target cells reported by A3 measurement reports for intra-frequency handovers to check if target cell is better than source cell by at least this much. Negative value means target can be worse than source.  This parameter is aimed for post-processing of measurement reports only. It is not used in any report configuration to the UE.

Parameter name: Minimum target threshold RSRP
Description: Absolute RSRP threshold for filtering target cells based on RSRP values. Used for filtering target cells reported by A3 measurement reports for intra-frequency handovers.  This parameter is aimed for post-processing of measurement reports only. It is not used in any report configuration to the UE.  Value-Range follows 3GPP TS 36.133 chapter 9.1.4

Parameter name: Minimum target threshold RSRQ
Description: Absolute RSRQ threshold for filtering target cells based on RSRQ values. Used for filtering target cells reported by A3 measurement reports for intra-frequency handovers.  This parameter is aimed for post-processing of measurement reports only. It is not used in any report configuration to the UE.  The dB values are mapped to 3GPP IE values according to TS 36.133:  - -20 dB means a threshold lower than -19.5 dB  - values between -19.5 dB and -3.5 dB mean a threshold higher than or equal to the configured value but lower than (value + 0.5 dB)  - -3 dB means a threshold higher than or equal to -3 dB

Parameter name: Transport network identifier
Description: This parameter is the instance identifier of the TRSNW object. It uniquely identifies the object.

Parameter name: Control plane configuration - IPv4 address 1 reference
Description: This parameter defines the reference to the IPADDRESSV4 object instance which holds the IPv4 address to be used for the first C-Plane.  The related read only object will provide the actually assigned IP address. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNL or TNLSVC.    FDN example: MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-17/IPADDRESSV4-1  SDN example: TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-17/IPADDRESSV4-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.

Parameter name: Control plane configuration - IPv4 address 2 reference
Description: This parameter defines the reference to the IPADDRESSV4 object instance which holds the IPv4 address to be used for the second C-Plane.  The related runtime object will provide the actually assigned IP address. The value can be either Fully Distinguished Name (FDN) or Shortened Distinguished Name (SDN) as long as it is unambiguous within the network element configuration and starts from TNL or TNLSVC.    FDN example: MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-17/IPADDRESSV4-2  SDN example: TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-17/IPADDRESSV4-2    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line.

FDN example: MRBTS-1/TNLSVC-1/TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-6/IPADDRESSV6-1  SDN example: TNL-1/IPNO-1/IPIF-6/IPADDRESSV6-1    Updating this parameter without changing the target object will be on-line. The parameter cPlane-ipV6AddressDN1 can be configured always. It will be taken into operational use only when actDualStackIpV4V6ForS1X2=TRUE.

Parameter name: Control plane configuration - IPv6 Address 2 reference
