Parameter name: Transport network identifier
Description: This parameter defines the identifier of the transport network.

Parameter name: Transport network in use
Description: This parameter defines whether the configuration related to the transport network shall be enabled.  The configuration of the main transport network must be always enabled.

Parameter name: Unmanned Aerial Vehicles profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC UAVPR.  It uniquely identifies an UAVPR instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: UAV UE identifiers list
Description: List of SPIDs (Subscribed Profile IDs) identifying UE as UAV. If UAV support is enabled in the cell, SPID for given UE is provided via S1/X2 signaling and it matches SPID/s within SPID range specified in the list, the UE is considered as UAV UE.

Parameter name: Subscriber profile ID
Description: Single SPID value or first SPID value of a range which identifies UE as Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (UAV).  With this parameter a single SPID or the first SPID in a SPID range is configured.

Parameter name: Last subscriber profile ID of a range
Description: Last SPID value if a range of SPID values shall identify UE as Unmanned Aerial Vehicle (UAV).  If this parameter is configured, it defines the last SPID in a SPID range.

Parameter name: Uplink power control configuration for UAV UEs - Uplink power control method for UAV UEs
Description: Specifies uplink power control method for Unmanned Aerial Vehicles (UAVs).    Available options:  - sameAsTerrestrial: UAV and terrestrial UEs share the same uplink power control method on PUSCH and PUCCH (as defined for the cell linking this UAV profile in LNCEL-actUlpcMethod)  - PuschOLPucchOL: UAV UEs use open loop uplink power control method on PUSCH and PUCCH (regardless of the configuration for terrestrial UEs in the cell linking this UAV profile in LNCEL-actUlpcMethod)

Parameter name: Uplink power control configuration for UAV UEs - Power offset for UAV UE PUCCH TX power calc
Description: This is a UE-specific power offset to be used for PUCCH power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P2). Applicable for UAV UEs only.

Parameter name: Uplink power control configuration for UAV UEs - Power offset for UAV UE PUSCH or NPUSCH TX power calc
Description: This is a UE-specific power offset to be used for PUSCH or NPUSCH power calculation in UE uplink power control equation (P1), which controls the mean received SNR for user data during a (re)transmission corresponding to a received PDCCH with the DCI format 0 associated with a new packet transmission. Applicable for UAV UEs only.

Parameter name: Utran FDD idle mode configuration identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies an UFFIM (UTRAN Frequency Idle Mode configuration) managed object.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: UTRA cell reselection timer
Description: UTRA cell reselection timer

Parameter name: List of UTRA FDD carrier frequencies
Description: This is a list of UTRA FDD Carrier Frequencies

Parameter name: UTRA downlink frequency value
Description: Contains the Downlink Frequency (Nd) as ARFCN value

Parameter name: UTRA-FDD carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the UTRAN FDD carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest priority and 0 the lowest.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: UTRA-FDD carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of UTRA-FDD carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: UTRA maximum allowed transmit power
Description: UTRA Maximum Allowed Transmit Power

Parameter name: UTRA minimum needed quality parameter
Description: This specifies the minimum required quality level in the cell in dB. It is not applicable to TDD cells or GSM cells or E-UTRA cells.

Parameter name: UTRA minimum required receive level
Description: This specifies the minimum required RX level in the cell in dBm

Parameter name: UTRA carrier frequency absolute priority
Description: Absolute priority of the UTRA carrier frequency    Equal priorities between RATs are not supported according to [3GPP 36.304].

Parameter name: UTRA inter-RAT quality threshold high (Rel9)
Description: This specifies the quality threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority UTRA RAT  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9

Parameter name: UTRA inter-RAT quality threshold low (Rel9)
Description: This specifies the quality threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a lower priority UTRA RAT  Not recognized by UEs < Rel9

Parameter name: UTRA inter frequency threshold high
Description: This specifies the threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency X than the current serving frequency

Parameter name: UTRA inter frequency threshold low
Description: This specifies the threshold used in reselection towards the frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection UTRAN - UTRA cell reselection timer factor high mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionUTRA is multiplied by this factor if the UE is in the high mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: Speed-dependent scaling factors t-reselection UTRAN - UTRA cell reselection timer factor medium mobility
Description: The field t-ReselectionUTRA is multiplied by this factor if the UE is in the medium mobility state as defined in 36.304.

Parameter name: List of UTRA TDD carrier frequencies
Description: This is a list of UTRA TDD Carrier Frequencies

Parameter name: UTRA downlink frequency as ARFCN value
Description: Contains the Downlink Frequency (Nd) as ARFCN value

Parameter name: UTRA-TDD carrier freq prio for idle mode load balancing
Description: Absolute priority of the UTRAN TDD carrier frequency used for idle mode load balancing.  For this parameter, 6 is the highest prio and 0 the lowest.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in IdleModeMobilityControlInfofor load balancing.    Note:  According to 3GPP 36.304, carriers in different RATs must have different Cell Reselection Priorities.

Parameter name: UTRA-TDD carrier weight factor idle mode load balancing
Description: Weight factor of UTRA-TDD carrier frequency used by round robin algorithm for idle mode load balancing.  When the parameter is not defined, the corresponding carrier is not used in selecting main target for IdleModeMobilityControlInfo for load balancing. Weighted round robin algorithm shall select always one target frequency for idle mode load balancing, which is matching UE capabilities, to be used as main target for idle mode load balancing and this target will have always highest priority assigned in RRC Release message. All other target frequency for idle mode load balancing matching UE capabilities and configured in LNCEL, IRFIM, UFFIM, CDFIM and GNFL will be added as well, but with lowered priorities as configured for SIB with kept hierarchy of priorities. The algorithm shall calculate proportional weights corresponding to configured values. There is no check about the sum of weights configured by the user.

Parameter name: UTRA Maximum Allowed Transmit Power
Description: UTRA Maximum Allowed Transmit Power

Parameter name: UTRA Minimum Required Receive Level
Description: This specifies the minimum required RX level in the cell in dBm

Parameter name: UTRA Carrier Frequency Absolute Priority
Description: Absolute priority of the UTRA carrier frequency    Equal priorities between RATs are not supported according to [3GPP 36.304].

Parameter name: UTRA Inter Frequency Threshold High
Description: This specifies the threshold used by the UE when reselecting towards a higher priority frequency X than the current serving frequency

Parameter name: UTRA Inter Frequency Threshold Low
Description: This specifies the threshold used in reselection towards the frequency X priority from a higher priority frequency

Parameter name: Uplink coordinated multipoint identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a ULCOMP instance.  The BTS will dynamically decide depending on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: A3 measurement parameters for UL CoMP - A3 offset for UL CoMP
Description: Margin for intra-frequency better cell UL CoMP.  Used in UL CoMP measurement event type A3 where the event is triggered when the neighbor cell becomes better than the serving cell by the value of the A3 offset. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: A3 measurement parameters for UL CoMP - A3 report interval for UL CoMP
Description: Defines the interval with which measurement reports are sent as long as the specific criteria for the UL CoMP measurement event A3 are met (Intra-Frequency).  This parameter defines the interval with which measurement reports are repeatedly sent as long as the specific criteria for the UL CoMP measurement event A3 are met. Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS120 corresponds to 120 ms, MS240 to 240 ms and so on, while value MIN1 corresponds to 1 min, MIN6 to 6 min and so on.

Parameter name: A3 measurement parameters for UL CoMP - A3 time to trigger for UL CoMP
Description: Time for which the specific criteria for the UL CoMP measurement event A3 must be met in order to trigger a measurement report (Intra-Frequency).    Value definitions as stated in 3GPP TS36.331: value MS0 corresponds to 0 ms, MS40 to 40 ms and so on.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: A3 measurement parameters for UL CoMP - Hysteresis A3 offset RSRP intra-frequency for UL CoMP
Description: Related hysteresis margin for UL CoMP better cell of intra-frequency RSRP.  Parameter is used within the entry and leave condition of the A3 triggered reporting condition. The IE value is multiplied by 2.

Parameter name: Old Distinguished Name
Description: The parameter specifies the old distinguished name of the managed object before a configuration change like rehosting. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Uplink CoMP Cell List
Description: List of cells belonging to the same uplink comp set (UL CoMP).    Configuration rule for a TDD UL CoMP set:  For 4 Rx UL-CoMP (LTE1691), only cells with 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth are supported.  For 2 Rx, 4 Rx and 8 Rx UL-CoMP (LTE1402, LTE2104, LTE2128 and CB006754) cells with 10 MHz, 15 MHz and 20 MHz bandwidth are supported.    Note:  - All cells in this list should be hosted by the same AirScale ABIA. Otherwise, e.g. fault 1868 might be raised.  - When/where supported, IQ forwarding may enable hosting a cell on one BB pool while it is physically cabled to another BB pool and/or BB card.

Parameter name: UL CoMP mode
Description: This parameter defines the mode of UL coordinated multipoint (CoMP) reception. It is applicable only for a UL CoMP group of TDD cell instances.    IQ_Combining: uses IQ combining algorithm  SoftBit_Combining: shall be used for 2RX / 4RX / 8RX UL CoMP reception with softbit combining.    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Uplink CoMP SINR Threshold
Description: Signal-Interference-Noise Ratio to be use for uplink CoMP operation.  The received uplink signal from a neighbor cell is combined to the serving cell signal if its SINR is less than ulCoMPSinrThreshold below the SINR of the serving cell signal.  The recommended default value is for:  - 2RX CoMP: 10 dB  - 4RX CoMP: 15 dB    Note:  For 2-RX / 4-RX / 8-RX CoMP with Softbit combination, the parameter is not used. A3 measurement configuration is done in a3UlCoMpConfig.

Parameter name: Ul CoMp Basic Configuration identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of MOC ULCOMPBASICCONF.  This parameter uniquely identifies a ULCOMPBASICCONF instance.    The BTS will dynamically decide dependent on the current and newly required resource allocation if BTS restart or resetting of cells is needed. This may also impact other LTE cells or, in case of SRAN deployment, cells of other RATs.

Parameter name: Uplink CoMP Basic Cell List
Description: List of cells belonging to the same uplink comp set (Basic UL CoMP).    Note:  - All cells in this list should be hosted by the same AirScale ABIN/ABINL or ABIP/ABIQ, or on the same BB pool on an AirScale ABIO/ABIOL or AirScale ABIP or AirScale ASOE/ASOF or AirScale ASOG/ASOH. Otherwise, e.g. fault 1868 might be raised.  - When/where supported, IQ forwarding may enable hosting a cell on one BB pool while it is physically cabled to another BB pool and/or BB card.

Parameter name: Uplink CoMP Cell
Description: Cell Id of the Basic UL CoMP cell

Parameter name: Avg Ingr Coef per basic UL CoMP cell
Description: Average Ingress Coefficient per basic UL CoMP cell  Average (or target) value of a coefficient which scales the rate at which basic UL CoMP ingress traffic is allowed per cell.  The actual amount of ingress allowed per cell is also adjusted based upon a variety of other factors.  Configuring/setting or not configuring this parameter should be done in accordance with customer documentation/release notes.  Each basic UL CoMP cell transmits requests for helper data from one or more different helper cells. This parameter may impact the actual amount of helper data ingress requested per cell during each TTI. Decreasing this parameter may reduce the amount of UL CoMP traffic used by this cell.

Parameter name: Avg SnrRt Coef per basic UL CoMP cell
Description: Average SnrRt Coefficient per basic UL CoMP cell  Average (or target) value of a coefficient which scales the rate at which the reception set for each UE is re-evaluated (SnrRt).  The final re-evaluation rate which is used also depends upon a variety of other factors.  Configuring/setting or not configuring this parameter should be done in accordance with customer documentation/release notes.  Each basic UL CoMP cell may request helper data from a group of reception set cells. This parameter may impact the rate at which the reception set for each UE is re-evaluated. Decreasing this parameter may reduce the amount of reception set re-evaluation processing done per cell.

Parameter name: Max Ingress Coef per basic UL CoMP cell
Description: Maximum Ingress Coefficient per basic UL CoMP cell  Maximum value of a coefficient which scales the amount of ingress traffic allowed per cell.  The actual amount of ingress allowed per basic UL CoMP cell is also adjusted based upon a variety of other factors.  Configuring/setting or not configuring this parameter should be done in accordance with customer documentation/release notes.  Each basic UL CoMP cell transmits requests for helper data from one or more different helper cells. This parameter may impact the actual amount of helper data ingress requested per cell during each TTI. Decreasing this parameter may reduce the amount of UL CoMP traffic used by this cell.

Parameter name: Max SnrRt Coef per basic UL CoMP cell
Description: Maximum SnrRt Coefficient per basic UL CoMP cell  Maximum value of a coefficient which scales the rate at which the reception set for each UE is re-evaluated (SnrRt).  The final re-evaluation rate which is used also depends upon a variety of other factors.  Configuring/setting or not configuring this parameter should be done in accordance with customer documentation/release notes.  Each basic UL CoMP cell may request helper data from a group of reception set cells. This parameter may impact the rate at which the reception set for each UE is re-evaluated. Decreasing this parameter may reduce the amount of reception set re-evaluation processing done per cell.

Parameter name: UL CoMP Need Alpha
Description: This parameter determines a filtering coefficient of for basic UL CoMP Need estimation averaging. As alpha increases, the existing average is given greater importance, and the most recent instantaneous observation is given less importance, i.e. the filtering time constant increases (more filtering).  The long term average UL CoMP Need per basic UL CoMP cell may impact the amount of UL CoMP performed per cell.  Configuring/setting or not configuring this parameter should be done in accordance with customer documentation/release notes."

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: UL CoMP SINR Alpha
Description: The parameter determines the filtering coefficient of the basic UL CoMP SINR measurements for averaging both serving cell and helper cell. As alpha increases, the existing average given greater importance, and the most recent instantaneous observation is given less importance, i.e. filtering time constant increases (more filtering).    The long term average SINR is calculated for a specific UE. At a high level, this is done based upon the instantaneous SINR observations, where the avgSINR is the current average SINR estimate for that UE, i.e. along the lines of avgSINR = alpha*avgSINR + (1-alpha)* SINR.

Parameter name: UL CoMP SINR threshold
Description: The received uplink PUSCH signal from a neighbor cell may be combined to the serving cell signal if its SINR is less than sinrThreshold below the SINR of the serving cell signal.    The recommended default value is for:  - 2RX CoMP: 10 dB  - 4RX CoMP: 15 dB

Parameter name: Unicast over MBSFN subframe identifier
Description: This parameter uniquely identifies a UMBSFN instance.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: LTE cell configuration identifier
Description: Instance identifier of MOC LNCEL in own eNB.

Parameter name: Unicast over MBSFN PDCCH overload handling enabled
Description: Allows use of the Unicast over MBSFN PDCCH Overload Handling; where If Unicast over MBSFN PDCCH Overload Is detected then additional TM9 is scheduled on the Normal Subframes

Parameter name: Max DL unicast MBSFN subframe pattern share
Description: Defines the maximum Unicast MBSFN subframe pattern share based on the proportion of the system capacity that shall be reserved for Unicast PDSCH over MBSFN.  The uMbsfnShareMax should be at least 30%, i.e. this is a "strong" recommendation.  E.g. a value of 50 represents the operator desire that at most 50% of subframes are reserved for Unicast PDSCH over MBSFN and 50% is left for normal subframe (nsf) PDSCH.  This parameter impacts the calculation of the value of subframeAllocation(fourFrames) defined in TS36.331 and sent in SIB2, i.e. corresponding to uMbsfnShareUsed.  The eNB automatically selects a MBSFN subframe configuration pattern which is both:  - consistent with other enabled features (ETWS/CMAS, OTDOA), and other factors e.g. related to CSI-RS, and  - will be less than or equal to uMbsfnShareMax

Parameter name: TM MBSFN sf pattern share used
Description: This is a read only parameter that models (i.e. reflects) exactly what share of DL subframes are used by Unicast MBSFN within a 40ms time window.  Indicates the Unicast MBSFN subframe share which was selected by the eNB and is currently in use.  A value of 50 indicates 50% of subframes are reserved for Unicast MBSFN and 50% is left for non-MBSFN (i.e. nsf or normal subframes).  This parameter determines the following SIB2 values that configures MBSFN (commonSF-Alloc, FourFrame) as defined in TS36.331.

Parameter name: VoLTE quality profile identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute of the MOC VOLTEQUALPR.  It uniquely identifies an instance of the VoLTE quality profile (VOLTEQUALPR).

Parameter name: Bad quality DL voice gap threshold
Description: Time duration with consecutive QCI1 DL PDCP packet losses or discards in order to consider voice quality as bad.    If the parameter is not configured then DL voice gap is not considered as voice quality criterion.

Parameter name: Bad quality residual BLER threshold
Description: Final residual BLER threshold for bad voice quality. The parameter applies for TTI- and non-TTI mode.    If the parameter is not configured then final residual BLER is not considered as voice quality criterion.    If harqMaxTrUl = 1, the final residual BLER equals the BLER (target value 10%) and badQualityRBlerThres should be set to > 10% .

Parameter name: Bad quality UL voice gap threshold
Description: Time duration with consecutive QCI1 UL PDCP packet losses or discards in order to consider voice quality as bad.    If the parameter is not configured then UL voice gap is not considered as voice quality criterion.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Good quality UL DL voice gap threshold
Description: DL/UL time duration with consecutive successful transmissions/receptions to consider voice quality as good

Parameter name: Good quality residual BLER threshold
Description: Final residual BLER threshold for good voice quality. The parameter applies for TTI- and non-TTI mode.    If harqMaxTrUl = 1, the final residual BLER equals the BLER (target value 10%) and goodQualityRBlerThres should be set to > 10% .

Parameter name: Residual BLER condition time to trigger
Description: Time for which the final residual BLER condition must be met in order to consider voice quality as bad or good.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT mobility parameters identifier
Description: This parameter is the naming attribute Of MOC XPARAM.  It uniquely identifies a XPARAM instance.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT auth mode indicator
Description: Defines the authentication mode. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in the RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the authIncluded parameter is set to TRUE.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT auth mode indicator included
Description: Defines the authentication mode included indicator. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT band class
Description: Defines the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (CDMA2000 1xRTT) band class number associated with this cell.

Parameter name: Configuration templates
Description: The parameter defines the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Template name
Description: The parameter defines the name of the configuration template assigned for the managed object. Non-network parameter data.

Parameter name: Include day light savings time indicator
Description: Defines whether the Daylight Savings Time (DST) indicator is included. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in the RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: FPC FCH INIT SETPT for RC11
Description: Defines the Initial Fundamental Channel outer loop Eb/Nt setpoint for RC11. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: FPC FCH INIT SETPT for RC12
Description: Defines the Initial Fundamental Channel outer loop Eb/Nt setpoint for RC12. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: FPC FCH INIT SETPT for RC3
Description: Defines the Initial Fundamental Channel outer loop Eb/Nt setpoint for RC3. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: FPC FCH INIT SETPT for RC4
Description: Defines the Initial Fundamental Channel outer loop Eb/Nt setpoint for RC4. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: FPC FCH INITSETPT for RC5
Description: Defines the Initial Fundamental Channel outer loop Eb/Nt setpoint for RC5. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: GCSNAL2Ack timer indicator
Description: Defines the length of time the Inter Working Solution (IWS) waits for an acknowledgment after it sends the GCSNA1xCircuitService message indicating an acknowledgment is required. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: GCSNA sequence context timer indicator
Description: Defines the length of time the UE retains the last received Generic Circuit Services Notification Application (GCSNA) sequence number and IWS_ID. This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT home registration included
Description: Defines whether the homeReg parameter is included in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: IMSI 11th and 12th digit
Description: Defines the 11th and 12th digits of an International Mobile Subscriber Identity (IMSI).  - When an IMSI has 12 or more digits, IMSI_11_12 is equal to the 11th and 12th digits of the IMSI.  - When an IMSI has fewer than 12 digits, digits with a value equal to zero are added to the most significant side to obtain a total of 12 digits and the IMSI_11_12 is equal to the 11th and 12th digits of the resulting number.  This field is sent as a 7-bit binary representation in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.  Set this parameter to the integer obtained by encoding the 12th and 11th digits of the IMSI using the formula 10 x D12 + D11 - 11.  Where:  D11 is the 11th digit  D12 is the 12th digit  If the digit is equal to zero, then 10 is used  For example, for an IMSI_11_12 of '04', the derived value 93 (= 10 x 10 + 4 - 11) should be set for this parameter.  The decimal value 127 corresponds to the escape code of all 1's: '1111111'.

Parameter name: IMSI T supported
Description: Defines whether 15-digit IMSI_T addressing is supported.  This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: Leap seconds included
Description: Defines whether the lpSec parameter is included in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: Local time offset included
Description: Defines whether the ltmOff parameter is included in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT max number of alt SO
Description: Defines the maximum number of alternative service options that the UE is allowed to include in the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) Origination message or in the CDMA2000 1xRTT Page Response message.  This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: Mobile country code
Description: Defines the 3-digit MCC (Mobile Country Code) of the PLMN for the CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) neighbor.  A special value 1023 is also defined to correspond to the 3GPP2 escape code.    At eNB, the 3-digit MCC will be converted to 10-bit binary code according to MCC encoding rule (Refer to 3GPP2 C.S005-E, Section 2.3.1.3), and the special value is converted to the 3GPP2 escape code of all 1's: '1111111111'. The final 10-bit binary code will be used to populate MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE).

Parameter name: CDMA2000 1xRTT minimum protocol revision
Description: Defines the minimum protocol revision level. This field is set to prevent UEs which cannot be supported by the Inter-Working Solution (IWS) from accessing the system. The eNodeB shall set this field to the minimum protocol revision level that the IWS supports.  This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: 1x protocol revision
Description: Defines the Protocol Revision level of the CDMA2000 1xRTT network.  This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: Pilot increment
Description: Defines the pilot Pseudo-Random Noise (PN) sequence offset index increment. A UE searches for Remaining Set pilots at pilot PN sequence index values that are multiples of this value.  Set this field to the pilot PN sequence increment, in units of 64 PN chips, which UEs use for searching the remaining set. Set this field to the largest increment such that the pilot PN sequence offsets of all neighboring CDMA2000 1x Radio Transmission Technology (1xRTT) base stations are integer multiples of that increment.  This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode only when the pilotIncIncuded parameter is set to TRUE.

Parameter name: Pilot increment included
Description: Defines whether the pilotInc parameter is included in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.

Parameter name: Preferred mobile station identifier type
Description: Defines the Preferred Access Channel Mobile Station Identifier Type.  This parameter is sent in the MobilityParametersCDMA2000 Information Element (IE) in RRC_CONNECTED mode.
